('bronzombie', 'BRONZOMBIE', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: Jaws hungry for BRAAAAAAAAAINS\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+APP**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +4\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +1\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nHALF-DEAD [Shadowdropper]\r\nMASTICATE [Shadowdropper]\r\nTIS BUT A SCRATCH [Shadowdropper]\r\nTHE HORDE [Shadowdropper]\r\n'),
('bustinBaddie', 'BUSTIN\' BADDIE', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT, +HUB**\r\nSTATS: +3 GRT, +2 IMG, +2 HUB\r\nThe Bustin’ Division has immense power behind it, since every clown is practically an army in their own right. Baddies are the ‘lowliest’ tier, but ranks in the Bustin’ are closer to vibes than a real indication of danger. Honkshoo..\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nUNRELENTING RAGE\r\nTERRORIZE\r\nCHUCKLETERRORS\r\nBUSTIN- TRAINING'),
('bustinBozo', 'BUSTIN\' BOZO', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: Standard Church Issue POLTERBUSTER\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +4\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nMAKES ME FEEL GOOD [Bustin’]\r\nLIL’ EXORCIST [Bustin’]\r\nPOLARITY-CROSSING KAMIKAZE [Bustin’]\r\nMIRACLE MAKER [Purple]\r\nCASTIGATE [Purple]\r\n'),
('bustinLaughsassin', 'BUSTIN\' LAUGHSASSIN', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**10 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+PSP, +GRA**\r\nSTATS: +3 GRA, +2 PSP, +2 GRA, +2 HUB, \r\nLaughsassasins are the sneaky elite of the Clown Church, clad in purple and blue camouflage to blend in with the foliage of Alternia. They’re rarely seen, and often it’s the last thing their victims do see. That and a cyanide pie to the face.\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nSHADOWY STALKER\r\nTERRIFY\r\nROOM FOR ONE OF US\r\nBUSTIN\' TRAINING'),
('bustinSeagoatRider', 'BUSTIN\' SEAGOAT RIDER', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 3 LUSUS/NPC\r\n**16 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++GRT**\r\nSTATS: +4 GRT, +3 HUB, +2 ALL\r\nYou know how knights slay dragons? Yeah. Okay, now imagine that– but it’s a clown on a gigantic fucking aquatic goat charging a literal horrorterror tendril protected by an army of shadowdroppers and Cthonomancers. Now you’re getting at what the Bustin’ Seagoat Rider’s job is. Not much else needs to be said. They’re the toughest of the tough for a reason.\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nMAGICAL SCYTHEAXE\r\nSTUNNING SPEED\r\nAQUATIC\r\nUNSTOPPABLE\r\nBLOOD IN THE WATER\r\nRAMPAGE AND RUIN\r\nBUSTIN\' TRAINING'),
('buzzedOutBee', 'BUZZED OUT BEE', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A sturdy cane, short shotgun, or a buncha bullshit to throw everywhere\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +1\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +4\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nDYING BATTERY [Voidrot]\r\nANIME POWERSPIKE [Voidrot]\r\nBATTERY DRAIN [Voidrot]\r\nPSIONIC MAGNET [Voidrot]\r\n'),
('carnivorousMoocreature', 'CARNIVOROUS MOOCREATURE', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 1 LUSUS\r\n**8 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT, +APP**\r\nSTATS: **+2 GRT, +3 APP**\r\nThe carnivorous moocreature is a staple of any good bronze farm on Alternia, providing dairy, meat, and plenty of security against trespassers.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> SECOND STOMACH\r\n> MAD COW DISEASE\r\n> DREADFUL DAIRY\r\n> STRIFE COOK MEAL'),
('cavernousOviguzzler', 'CAVERNOUS OVIGUZZLER', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 3 LUSUS\r\n**22 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++APP, +HUB, -PSP**\r\nSTATS: **+4 APP, +2 HUB, +2 RAS**\r\nThe jade caverns are, for the most part, a safe place to raise eggs and grubs due to the tunnelwarden\'s vigilance. However, occasionally something like the Cavernous Oviguzzler will make its way past the warden\'s defenses. This giant subterranean serpent exclusively feeds on troll eggs. Every few months, one will make its way into the brood caverns and absolutely gorge itself on hundreds of troll eggs, filling itself with eggs until it\'s a perfect sphere and it literally rolls away through the caverns. Dastardly beastie. \r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\n- OMNOMLETTE\r\n- EGGSTRAORDINARY EGGBREATH\r\n- SCRAMBLED PANCELLS\r\n- TERRI-FRIED'),
('celestialGrub', 'CELESTIAL GRUB', 'ENTITY', 'LVL 4 ENTITY\r\n**30 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG**\r\nSTATS: **+5 PLC, +3 GRT, +3 IMG, -2 PSP**\r\nDeep within the soil where all life returns, the lost life yet to be rebirthed awaits to be summoned, as a troll or lusus, plant or creature. Or, in this case, a Celestial Guardian, imbued with the very spirit of the Mother Below All sent to preserve Her chosen. Bearing resemblance to the Mother Grub and bursting with the hemospectrum\'s hue to give shape to their wings, these legendary creatures often considered myths even among the faithful of the Cloistered Church, the Mother Grub\'s eternal memory of Her most favored saints are said give life and personality to these beings of light. As Celestial Grubs are created through the Cloister’s magic, you cannot summon or encounter one outside of the usage of HERALD CALLER.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> LIGHTBRINGER\r\n> HOPEBRINGER\r\n> DOOMBRINGER\r\n> RESURRECTION'),
('ceruleanBigShot', 'CERULEAN BIG SHOT', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**16 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A gem studded cane, gold plated submachine gun, or platinum knife\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+APP**\r\nRAS: +2\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +4\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +3\r\nPSP: +1\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nLUCK BE A SPIDER [Cerulean]\r\nCHEATING BASTARD [Cerulean]\r\nSWINDLERY [Cerulean]\r\nEIGHT-SIDED ENTROPY [Cerulean]\r\nUNCRACKABLE CONFIDENCE [Cerulean]\r\nSCOURGE [Cerulean]\r\n'),
('ceruleanBlackWidow', 'CERULEAN BLACK WIDOW', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**16 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A terrified rust lackey who throws rocks from a safe distance, an indifferent gold lackey who blasts lazers from a safe distance, or a pistol\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +3\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +1\r\nIMG: +4\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nFREAKY EYE [Cerulean]\r\nCOMPULSATE [Cerulean]\r\nHYPNOEMPATHICS [Cerulean]\r\nSUPERIOR PSIONICS [Cerulean]\r\nPSYCHIC DOUBLE REACHAROUND [Cerulean]\r\nSCOURGE [Cerulean]\r\n'),
('ceruleanDuke', 'CERULEAN DUKE', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**18 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: An ancestral rapier of impeccable quality, a war banner with their sign, or a fucking cannon they roll around\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+HUB**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +3\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +4\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nARISTOTAGONIST [Cerulean]\r\nEN GARDE! [Cerulean]\r\nDAREDEVILRY [Cerulean]\r\nMANIACAL LAUGH [Cerulean]\r\nDEGREES OF VRISKOCITY (Not Vriska) [Cerulean]\r\nSCOURGE [Cerulean]\r\n'),
('ceruleanPunk', 'CERULEAN PUNK', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**20 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A spiked bat, shiny knife, or heavy knuckle dusters\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +2\r\nGRT: +4\r\nHUB: +3\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nLOOKING FOR TROUBLE [Cerulean]\r\nBACK-ALLEY BRAWLER [Cerulean]\r\nUNHINGED ATTITUDE [Cerulean]\r\nAGGRESSIVE ATTITUDE [Cerulean]\r\nINSANELY COOL [Cerulean]\r\nSCOURGE [Cerulean]\r\n'),
('ceruleanShadow', 'CERULEAN SHADOW', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**16 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A hidden knife, silenced gun, or garrote wire\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+RAS**\r\nRAS: +4\r\nPLC: +2\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +1\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +3\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nSUSPICIOUS STRANGER [Cerulean]\r\nUNDERCOVER ACTIVITY [Cerulean]\r\nYOU FOOL! [Cerulean]\r\nMYSTERIOUS FIGURE [Cerulean]\r\nBELOW THE BELT [Cerulean]\r\nSCOURGE [Cerulean]\r\n'),
('ceruleanSlashionista', 'CERULEAN SLASHIONISTA', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A pair of razor sharp knitting needles or extra sharp scissors\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PSP**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +2\r\nAPP: +1\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +1\r\nPSP: +2\r\nIMG: +4\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nART OF THE DRESS [Haute Clawture]\r\nFASHION FAUX-PAS [Haute Clawture]\r\nTHE DEVIL WEARS TROLL PRADA [Haute Clawture]\r\nTRENDSETTER [Haute Clawture]\r\n'),
('chuckletrice', 'CHUCKLETRICE', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 2 LUSUS\r\n**15 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++RAS, +HUB, +GRT**\r\nSTATS: **+3 RAS, +2 HUB, +2 GRT**\r\nA lusus species bred for the explicit purpose of aiding laughsassains and subjugglators on their most righteous and holy missions of shoving heretics off the mortal shelf. Its gaze causes instant and uncontrollable laughter. It’s actually quite small, not much larger than your average Cluckbeast!\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> MASTER & HOUND\r\n> PARALAUGHIC GAZE\r\n> FLAPFLAPFLAPKICKFLAPPECK\r\n> ARGUABLY A BIRD!'),
('clownBarker', 'CLOWN BARKER', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**17 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: THE SICKEST BEAT(DOWN)S KNOWN TO TROLL DELIVERED VIA HELLA MAGICS AND SPIKED MIC’D FLAILS\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG**\r\nRAS: +3\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +1\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +4\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nMIRACLE MAKER [Purple]\r\nCASTIGATE [Purple]\r\nTHE DARK CARNIVAL BECKONS [Purple]\r\nDIVINE WARDS [Purple]\r\nFRAYVOCALIZE [Purple]\r\n'),
('clownCarny', 'CLOWN CARNY', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**16 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: Some fireworks!!! Oooooor…A stuffed ‘toy’ ;o) (It’s a bomb)\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+APP**\r\nRAS: +2\r\nPLC: +3\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +4\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +1\r\nIMG: +1\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nROLL UP, ROLL UP (Carny) [Purple]\r\nALL THE WORLD’S A CIRCUS [Purple]\r\nRAZZLEDAZZLE [Purple]\r\nIN THE SPOTLIGHT [Purple]\r\nTHE BIG NUMBER [Purple]\r\n'),
('clownFortuneTeller', 'CLOWN FORTUNE-TELLER', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**16 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A glass ball mace or some razor sharp Terror cards, all portraying one omen…DEATH. DEATH TO YE FAITHLESS!\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PSP**\r\nRAS: +2\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +4\r\nIMG: +3\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nSCHOLAR OF SECRETS (Luck Relic) [Purple]\r\nENSORCELL [Purple]\r\nOBTAIN BOGLE [Purple]\r\nPACTBROKER [Purple]\r\nSLAPSTICKY MISCHIEF [Purple]\r\n'),
('clownHellraiser', 'CLOWN HELLRAISER', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**20 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: THE MOST WICKED HATCHETS THESE WICKED BITCHES EVER DID SEE\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT**\r\nRAS: +3\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +4\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +1\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nVIDEONASTYQUIN [Purple]\r\nAFFRIGHT [Purple]\r\nSHADOWY STALKER [Purple]\r\nGONNA GETCHA [Purple]\r\nKEEP COMING BACK [Purple]\r\n'),
('clownMobster', 'CLOWN MOBSTER', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**19 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: Eyyy, just some squirt guns ovah here…squirt guns filled wit’ a little bit of acid, hehehehe. >:o)\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+APP**\r\nRAS: +2\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +4\r\nGRT: +3\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +1\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nTHE FAMILY (CLEANER) [Purple]\r\nTYRANNIZE [Purple]\r\nVERSUS THE MOB [Purple]\r\nCRIME PAYS [Purple]\r\nLOVE A CHALLENGE [Purple]\r\n'),
('corpsefowl', 'CORPSEFOWL', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 2 LUSUS\r\n**14 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++APP, +RAS** \r\nSTATS: **+3 APP, +3 RAS**\r\nCorpsefowl are massive and intimidating scavenger birds, covered in razor-sharp feathers from the neck down with bald heads plated with armored chitin. While they prefer eating the already deceased, they won\'t hesitate to attack if they\'re interrupted while feasting in the cullpits.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> BONECRUNCHER\r\n> MY LEG\r\n> FOUL FOWL\r\n> BRAVE BIRD\r\n> WASTE NOT WANT NOT'),
('crocageckor', 'CROCAGECKOR', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 2 LUSUS\r\n**12 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++GRT, +GRA**\r\nSTATS: **+2 GRT, +2 GRA, +2 IMG, -1 HUB**\r\nOne third crocodilian, one third gecko, another third a slightly different kind of crocodilian, crocageckors have the one tool most crocodiles could only dream of: the ability to walk on walls.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> CRUNCH\r\n> WALLCLIMB\r\n> LASER BREATH\r\n> GUNKED UP'),
('cullscoutAlthistorian', 'CULLSCOUT ALTHISTORIAN', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+HUB, -PLC**\r\nSTATS: +5 HUB, +3 GRT, +2 ALL, -2 PLC\r\nThe ‘Alt’ is short for ‘Alternian’. Obviously. History is written by the victors, and Cullscout Althistorians are the ones who write it. When they win, which they surely will, since they’re indigos. Keep up. Clearly you don’t even read the news.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\nCHECKMATE, HEMOANONS\r\nALTERNIATIVE FACTS\r\nHISTORICAL REVISIONS\r\nDEATH OF THE AUTHOR\r\n'),
('cullscoutCadet', 'CULLSCOUT CADET', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT**\r\nSTATS: +4 GRT, +3 HUB\r\nThe Cullscout Cadet is at the frontline of the Empire’s more elite extermination forces, ready to intervene wherever the battle is fiercest and in the most need of support. Through hard work and victory, they will climb their surprisingly meritocratic ranks.\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nHONORABLE FIGHTER\r\nGLORY CHARGE\r\nALL FOR ONE\r\nONE FOR ALL'),
('cullscoutStar', 'CULLSCOUT STAR', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A survival knife, hatchet, or hunting rifle\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +1\r\nGRT: +4\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nMEDAL COLLECTOR [Cullscout]\r\nINDIGO EXCEPTIONALISM [Cullscout]\r\nMORE MEDALS THAN YOU [Cullscout]\r\nTHE BEST AROUND [Cullscout]\r\n'),
('cullscoutWorldshaker', 'CULLSCOUT WORLDSHAKER', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**18 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++GRT**\r\nSTATS: +4 GRT, +3 PSP, -4 GRA, +2 ALL\r\nCullscout Worldshakers are the very pinnacle of showmanship. They are the greatest athletes, the STRONGEST archers, the mightiest of mighty men and wondrous of women, and something starting with N for everything else. The height of Indigo might can be found in the Worldshakers; brawlers kitted with the Empire’s finest anti-grav armor so that they can truly make the world quake beneath their fists.\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nSTRIKE THE ALTERNIA!\r\nNATURAL DISASTER\r\nSTRONG STRIKE\r\nLAST ONE STANDING'),
('cyberhusk', 'CYBERHUSK', 'ROBOT_MONSTER', 'LVL 3 ROBOT\r\n**10 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++GRT, +HUB, -APP, -PSP**\r\nSTATS: **+4 GRT, +3 HUB, +3 GRA**\r\nThe more cybernetics a troll has installed, the less likely it is that their death’ll shut them all down. And when it doesn’t, a Cyberhusk is born - a mindless robot with all its former owner’s favored weapons and favorite mods at its disposal, designed to listen to a thinkpan that’s long since rotted away.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> CYBEREXOSKELETON\r\n> PRELOADED PATTERNS\r\n> OVERLOADED UPGRADES\r\n> RETRIEVE ARMS'),
('direpigeonUltimate', 'DIREPIGEON ULTIMATE', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 1 ANIMAL FROM REAL LIFE\r\n**10 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+RAS, +GRT**\r\nSTATS: **+3 RAS, +2 GRT**\r\nA mix of natural selection, interbreeding with local Alternian fauna and dark magic has resulted in a terrifying winged beast of- okay yeah, this is just a bigger version of a regular pigeon. In a video game it\'d use the same model as the LVL 1 pigeon but recolored and resized slightly so high-level players look less like losers for killing it.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> ULTIMATE COO\r\n> FLAP FLAP- OH WAIT\r\n> NASTIEST SURPRISE\r\n> TUBERCULOSIS OR SOMETHING, PROBABLY'),
('dreamingDead', 'DREAMING DEAD', 'ENTITY', 'LVL 3 ENTITY\r\n**22 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++IMG, +ALL**\r\nSTATS: **+3 IMG, +2 ALL**\r\n\r\nWalking in endless slumber, a mind kept in stasis and a body that moves by a different will. Cloaked in thick inky shadow, silent stepping through empty halls. Muttering phrases that would drive any troll mad- these are the Dreaming Dead. Fools who fell before they could enact the Horrorterror’s will, and are by that same will kept moving and shambling in unnatural contortions and wriggles. \r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\n> SHADOW PUPPET\r\n> GRIMDARK THROES\r\n> BABBLING MAD\r\n> ABYSSAL INFLUENCE\r\n> MOTHER\'S LIGHT'),
('driftingDreamvoid', 'DRIFTING DREAMVOID', 'ENTITY', 'LVL 4 ENTITY\r\n**33 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+++IMG, +ALL**\r\nSTATS: **+4 IMG, +2 ALL**\r\nAlternia is full of ghosts. The unthinking remnants of the powerless dead, snared by dark magicks, warped by that which lies beyond the veil. Some still think; most just linger. But all remember. And when a Cthonomancer gets much more than they bargained for, or an especially hollowed-out Grimdark presents themself, a simple haunting quickly turns into something yet darker. The vessel becomes a singularity full of a thousand shades, memories overflowing out into physical reality within its event horizon. A bubble full to bursting with dreams... and hunting, now, for more dreamers.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> A FLEETING DREAM\r\n> WELCOME TO BLACK SPACE\r\n> ETERNAL REST\r\n> SOUL TYRANT'),
('emptyPuppet', 'EMPTY PUPPET', 'ENTITY', 'LVL 2 ENTITY\n**16 HP**\nTALENTS: **+IMG**, **+PSP**\nSTATS: **+3 IMG, +3 PSP, +2 GRT, -4 PLC**\nNot every Limeblood makes it in a world that is hostile to their very existence. Not every Limeblood survives without strings. Not every Limeblood survives leaving its Mother’s dreams. Those that fall to the cruel, harsh world so soon after tasting freedom are often easily hollowed out by darker powers eager to lap at the strange magics the caste seems to be intertwined with. \n\nMOVES:\n> LOST CHILD\n> FORGOTTEN PARABLE\n> LUCKY YOU\n> FILLED VESSEL\n> RADIANT REBIRTH'),
('exorphibian', 'EXORPHIBIAN', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 2 LUSUS\r\n**12 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT, +APP**\r\nSTATS: **+2 GRT, +2 APP, +2 GRA**\r\nA large, unsettling frog that feeds on ectoplasm. Bane to ghosts everywhere, its ethereal croaks are said to strike fear into the hearts of the undead.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> CROAK\r\n> GHOST GULPER\r\n> MLEM\r\n> IT\'S NOT SLIME\r\n> SPIT UP\r\n> GRAVESTONE SPECIES'),
('fairyBull', 'FAIRY BULL', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 0 LUSUS \r\n**3 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG, +RAS**\r\nSTATS: **-1 APP, -1 GRT**\r\nThis tiny little fairy bull flits around, sprinkling glitter in its trail. It’s… it’s kind of pathetic.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> ACHOO!\r\n> FLIT FLIT\r\n> PATHETIC SQUEAL\r\n> GLARING WEAKNESS\r\n'),
('falseMessiahs', 'FALSE MESSIAHS', 'ENTITY', 'LVL 3 ENTITIES\r\n**?? HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++???, +RAS, +GRA**\r\nSTATS: **+3 ???, +3 RAS, +3 GRA**\r\nLike every good joke, clowns must die eventually. Unfortunately, like jokes, some clowns never quite do. Even the Messiahs’ blessings have limits. Even a highblood’s toughness can’t keep its form together forever. And when two especially faithful, or just particularly determined, clowns who’ve already died one too many times fall side-by-side... a uniquely terrible kind of miracle can be born. No longer quite trolls, but still very much a clown.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> HERE WE ARE\r\n> MAKEUP MAYHEM\r\n> COME JOIN THE FUN\r\n> THE DARKER CARNIVAL'),
('feralFiduspawn', 'FERAL FIDUSPAWN', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 1 LUSUS\r\n**10 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT, +VARIABLE**\r\nSTATS: **+2 GRT, +VARIABLE**\r\nFiduspawn are genetically engineered to be battle companions for trolls, and generally can’t reproduce on their own or even survive in the wild. Despite this, some messed-up Fiduspawners release their monsters into the wild anyways! Chances are the Fiduspawner was breeding for shinies, or perfect stats, or maybe their cute new pet developed an unexpected taste for troll flesh. Regardless of reason, these very angry and bitter Fiduspawn occasionally show up in the tall grass around Alternia.\r\n\r\nMOVES?: \r\n> BUILD-A-BEAST\r\n> WONDER LINK\r\n> FINALISH GAMBIT\r\n> FIDUSPAWN LOGIC'),
('fidumaster', 'FIDUMASTER!', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: They got their hands? What do you mean you aren’t gonna Fidubattle-\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +2\r\nIMG: +4\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nMY LITTLE MONSTER [Fiduspawner]\r\nGOTTA CATCH ‘EM ALL [Fiduspawner]\r\nDOUBLE BATTLE [Fiduspawner]\r\nFINAL GAMBIT [Fiduspawner]\r\n'),
('firedUpFirefueler', 'FIRED-UP FIREFUELER', 'NPC_MONSTERS', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT, +HUB**\r\nSTATS: +4 GRT, +3 HUB, +2 ALL\r\nFirefuelers are hard at work all across Alternia loyally burning any opposition to the Empire to the ground, and this one’s no different. Burning rebels, burning eeries, burning themselves (makes it all the easier to burn the other two) - no cost is too great where the Empire is concerned.\r\n\r\nMONSTER:\r\nTHIS FFFIRE\r\nTHE REGULAR KIND OF ARSON\r\nLIVE (AND DIE) TO SERVE'),
('flappybara', 'FLAPPYBARA', 'ENTITY', 'LVL 0 ENTITY\r\n**3 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+PLC**\r\nSTATS: **+2 PLC, -2 PSP, -2 GRA**\r\nThese placid, limeblooded capybara-shaped entities tend to inexplicably spawn in areas where character deaths, dropped plotlines and major retcons once happened. While harmless and little more than narrative glitches on their own, their presence tends to serve as a harbinger for ill omens to come.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> TO KILL A HYDRA\r\n> DECEPTIVELY HARMLESS\r\n> NARRATIVE CAPYCASCADE\r\n> UNUSUALLY NARRATIVELY IMPORTANT RODENT CREATURES'),
('foolsJar', 'FOOL\'S JAR', 'ROBOT_MONSTER', 'LVL 1 ROBOT\r\n**10 HP**\r\nTalents: **+RAS, +PLC**\r\nStats: **+2 RAS, +2 PLC**\r\nA strange machine resembling a clay jar on six long, mechanical, spider-like legs. The jar is covered in intricate depictions of events from days long past, and a speaker is fitted onto the bottom- from which the Fool’s Jar speaks with an annoying text-to-speech voice. These constructs have the odd habit of collecting seemingly random items, and if the object of their adoration isn’t given over willingly they’ll fight to the death for it. Gimme, Gimme!\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> ANCIENT TECHNOLOGY\r\n> PRETTY PLEASE? PRETTY PRETTY PLEASE?>\r\n> AS A ROBOT, I\'M SHOCKED\r\n> STRATEGIC RETREAT'),
('ghastlyGoldGhost', 'GHASTLY GOLD GHOST', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: GHOST LAZERS\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG**\r\nRAS: +2\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +1\r\nIMG: +4\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nTHE FRIENDLY GHOST [Ghost]\r\nPOLTERIFICATE [Rust]\r\nBOO! [Ghost]\r\nPOSSESSION [Ghost]\r\n'),
('ginormouthBass', 'GINORMOUTH BASS', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 2 LUSUS\r\n**12 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+APP, +GRT**\r\nSTATS: **+1 APP, -2 PSP**\r\nHOLY FUCK THAT\'S A BIG FISH. Found in freshwater rivers and lakes the world over, Ginormouth Bass are scuttletruck-sized fish that swallow their prey whole before razing them with their horrifying THROAT TEETH. Yep. It’s got teeth. In its throat. That’s canon now. Enjoy thinking about that.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> IT\'S A FISH, IDIOT\r\n> AOUM\r\n> PTUI\r\n> GLUBGLUBGLUB\r\n> COUGHCOUGHCOUGHCOUGH'),
('gobblefiend', 'GOBBLEFIEND', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 1 LUSUS\r\n**8 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++IMG**\r\nSTATS: **+2 IMG, +2 HUB, +2 APP**\r\nThis awful, awful creature resembles a turkey, but it is not one. A fiend filled with graceless rage, it has NOTHING to be thankful for… not even its own country.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> WHOMST SHALL I KILL\r\n> GLAGUGLAGUGLA\r\n> HARD TO KILL\r\n> RADIANT RETRIBUTION'),
('goldBuzzer', 'GOLD BUZZER', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 1 NPC\r\n**9 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A stinging swarm, big metal honeycomb, or jar of stale honey\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+RAS**\r\nRAS: +3\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +1\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +2\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nELECTRIC ENTOMOLOGY [Gold]\r\nSTICKY INVENTORY [Gold]\r\nU MAD? [Gold]\r\n'),
('goldGamer', 'GOLD GAMER', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 1 NPC\r\n**8 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: More lazers\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PLC**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +3\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +2\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +1\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +2\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nHOPES AND STREAMS [Gold]\r\nSUPERCHARGED [Gold]\r\nDUALITY [Gold]\r\n'),
('goldNeonblood', 'GOLD NEONBLOOD', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 1 NPC\r\n**10 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A shitty neon katana, laser pistol, or neon knuckle dusters\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+APP**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +3\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nNEONLIBERAL (Gutcortex) [Gold]\r\nINTERNET TROLL [Gold]\r\nEMOTIONAL INSTABILITY [Gold]\r\n'),
('goldNetworker', 'GOLD NETWORKER', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 1 NPC\r\n**8 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A reinforced laptop, overclocked taser, or pistol\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PSP**\r\nRAS: +2\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +2\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +1\r\nPSP: +3\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nTHE CLOUDMIND [Gold]\r\nDISSEMINATE EMOTIONS [Gold]\r\nDIGITAL NATIVE [Gold]\r\n'),
('goldPsyker', 'GOLD PSYKER', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 1 NPC\r\n**8 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: Lazers from their lazer eyes\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +1\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +2\r\nIMG: +3\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nSUPERCHARGED [Gold]\r\nSYSTEM DISCHARGE [Gold]\r\nINSUFFERABLE ATTITUDE [Gold]\r\n'),
('goneGoneGoneGrimdark', 'GONE, GONE, GONE GRIMDARK', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: who needs one? just let the darkness consume you\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +1\r\nPSP: +2\r\nIMG: +4\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nGONE GRIMDARK [Grimdark]\r\nTENDRILS [Grimdark]\r\nVOID INCARNATE [Grimdark]\r\nEVENT HORIZON [Grimdark]\r\n'),
('grublordSupreme', 'GRUBLORD SUPREME', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 4 LUSUS\r\n**30 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++APP, +ALL**\r\nSTATS: **+3 GRT, +3 APP, +3 RAS, -2 PSP**\r\nThis immense, grublike creature is the size of a tank, with scurrying legs and claws, bulbous, jello eyes, and a lamprey-like mouth filled with swirling layers of teeth. It is full of prizes and value and quite a lot of hatred, and would like nothing more than to devour you whole and transfer the contents of your wallet into its various offbiome accounts.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> OH SWEET JEGUS\r\n> GOTTA MUNCH\r\n> FILTHY ACTS AT AN UNREASONABLE PRICE\r\n> ROBBER BARON\r\n> ABOMINABLE ACTIONS\r\n> BLOATED FORM\r\n> MISTRUST FUND'),
('hackerForHire', 'HACKER-FOR-HIRE', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: Overclocked stun gun or back-up pistol\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PSP**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +2\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +4\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nSCRIPT GRUBBIE [Hackerman]\r\nHYPERVIGILANCE [Hackerman]\r\nTROLL IN THE CHAIR [Hackerman]\r\nCRACKS IN YOUR CODE [Hackerman]\r\n'),
('hatefulHellion', 'HATEFUL HELLION', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A runed dagger or hateful energy\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +2\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +4\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nDARK MAGICKS [Cthonomancer]\r\nDEMON DEAREST [Cthonomancer]\r\nTHEY SEE YOU [Cthonomancer]\r\nWARPSTORM [Cthonomancer]\r\n'),
('hemohound', 'H3M0H0UND', 'ROBOT_MONSTER', 'LVL 1 ROBOT\r\n**10HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRA**\r\nSTATS: **+2 GRA, +2 GRT**\r\nThis vaguely barkbeast-shaped quadrupedal robot is favored by Cullscouts, HET agents and other ORGs as a means of detecting and rooting out mutants, aliens and for dunking on Hemoanons. Despite being dog-shaped, this is not a Friend creature- this is a War Bot, biting with titanium jaws and communicating through a monotone metallic voice from its collar. It doesn’t even like belly scratches. \r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> 1NFR4RUST V1S1ON\r\n> BL00DS33K3R\r\n> F0XHUNT\r\n> NOT_4_CR34T1VE_C0L0R.EXE'),
('herocruncher', 'HEROCRUNCHER', 'PLANT_MONSTERS', 'LVL 1 PLANT\r\n**8 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG**\r\nSTATS: **+3 IMG**\r\nThe Herocruncher is a kind of shrub with many large, violet leaves which grows in nutrient-deficient environments such as acidic bogs. It’s quite bulky, and it’s covered in poisonous thorns, meaning any unlucky troll creature that wanders into it will quickly find themself stuck amongst the thorns and leaves until they succumb. Just like my mother in law, am I right?\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> HELP ME\r\n> PLANT PUN HERE\r\n> TOXIC\r\n> PLANTUPINE\r\n> FLASH FREEZE'),
('honkdemon', 'HONKDEMON', 'LUSUS\r\n', 'LVL 1 LUSUS\r\n**5 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++RAS, ++HUB**\r\nSTATS: **+3 RAS, +4 HUB**\r\nIt’s a lovely night on Alternia, and you are a horrible honkdemon.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> HONK\r\n> THE OTHER KIND OF HONK\r\n> TO-DO LIST\r\n> MEGA-YOINK\r\n> HONK 2\r\n'),
('horridAbomination', 'HORRID ABOMINATION', 'ENTITY', 'LVL 2 ENTITY\r\n**13 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG, -GRA**\r\nSTATS: **+2 RAS, +2 IMG**\r\n\r\nUnder the freezing moon, from the impossible angles, born from the anathematic realm of the Horrorterrors and emerging from the tangent lines where Is and Isn’t meet comes a Horrid Abomination. Horrible to look at and worse still to be around, a Horrid Abomination looks like nothing of this reality as its form seems to unmerge and reshape itself every second as impossible sounds hurgle in an aura around it. Send this thing back to whatever impossible hole it crawled out of, NOW.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> UNREAL\r\n> HEAR IT HURGLING\r\n> CANNOT, WILL NOT, SHOULD NOT\r\n> ONLY RESPITE'),
('imperialDrone', 'IMPERIAL DRONE', 'ROBOT_MONSTER', 'LVL 3 ROBOT\r\n**20 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT, +HUB**\r\nSTATS: **+3 GRT, +3 APP, +3 HUB**\r\nThe footsoldiers of the Alternian Army, Imperial Drones are ruthless, dangerous robotic opponents who have no idea what the meaning of mercy is. Don’t get on their bad side; they always shoot first, and never ask questions.\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\n> MACHINE\r\n> PULVERIZE\r\n> ON CALL\r\n> HEAVY ARMOUR\r\n> ADDITIONAL AMMO\r\n> SHOOT FIRST\r\n'),
('imperialShockdrone', 'IMPERIAL SHOCKDRONE', 'ROBOT_MONSTER', 'LVL 4 ROBOT\r\n**40 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++GRT, ++HUB, +ALL**\r\nSTATS: **+4 GRT, +4 APP, +4 HUB, +2 ALL**\r\nIf you see one of these, chances are you’re already dead. Imperial Shockdrones are practically invincible; towering as tall as a building and armed to the teeth with gatling guns for hands, Shockdrones are made to kill and nothing else. Shockdrones cannot usually be summoned by players, only by the Clouder.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> MACHINE\r\n> ALWAYS JUST\r\n> BRAKABRABRAKA\r\n> HEAVY ARMOUR\r\n> UNLIMITED AMMO\r\n> SHOOT FIRST\r\n> BOMBING RUN\r\n> LEGENDARY REWARDS'),
('indigoBeacon', 'INDIGO BEACON', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**19 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A sword and shield heralded with their sign, glowing with hope, untarnished against the wicked masses they face\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+GRA**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +2\r\nGRA: +4\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +3\r\nHUB: +0\r\nPSP: +1\r\nIMG: +1\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nARMORCLAD CRUSADER [Indigo]\r\nOATHKEEPER (Oath of Stewardship) [Indigo]\r\nSMITE [Indigo]\r\nSTARCHOSEN DESTINY (Bladeshielder) [Indigo]\r\nWALKING WALL [Indigo]\r\n'),
('indigoCEOmega', 'INDIGO C-E-OMEGA', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**18 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A big shiny revolver, oversized maul, or their damn bare hands\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+HUB**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +1\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +4\r\nPSP: +3\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nAUTHORITY FIGURE [Indigo]\r\nMEGAPUNCH [Indigo]\r\nTACTICAL MANEUVERING [Indigo]\r\nOVERWHELMING PRESENCE [Indigo]\r\nFIGHT FOR YOUR HONOR [Indigo]\r\n'),
('indigoGenius', 'INDIGO GENIUS', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**16 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A DIY plasma rifle or powergloves (when built with SCIENTIFIC PROWESS)\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PSP**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +2\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +3\r\nPSP: +4\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nSUPERGENIUS [Indigo]\r\nSCIENTIFIC PROWESS [Indigo]\r\nQUICK ADJUSTMENTS [Indigo]\r\nUPGRADES, PEOPLE! [Indigo]\r\nWEIRD BUILDS [Indigo]\r\n'),
('indigoPrefect', 'INDIGO PREFECT', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**18 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: IT’S JUST MORE BOOKS\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+RAS**\r\nRAS: +4\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +3\r\nPSP: +1\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nPRIVATE SCHOOL PRODIGY (+RAS) [Indigo]\r\nPRACTICAL STUDY [Indigo]\r\nREPEAT EXAM [Indigo]\r\nCRAM SESSION [Indigo]\r\nEXTRACURRICULAR EXEMPLARY (Bullying) [Indigo]\r\n'),
('indigoTeamCaptain', 'INDIGO TEAM CAPTAIN', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n20 HP\r\nSPECIBUS: EVERY DAMN SPORTSBALL IN EXISTENCE\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +2\r\nGRT: +4\r\nHUB: +3\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nQUARTERBACK QUONQUERER [Indigo]\r\nMASCOT MANIA (Piggustus Lard) [Indigo]\r\nTEAMWORK MAKES THE DREAM WORK [Indigo]\r\nHALF-TIME COMEBACK [Indigo]\r\nMIXED MUSCULAR ARTS [Indigo]\r\n'),
('jadeInUniform', 'JADE IN UNIFORM', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**13 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A standard issue pistol, telescopic baton, or flip knife\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PLC**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +4\r\nGRA: +2\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +1\r\nHUB: +1\r\nPSP: +2\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nCOMMISSARY OF INTERPLANETARY SECURITY [CIS]\r\nSECRET FILES [CIS]\r\nTAKE MATTERS INTO YOUR OWN HANDS [CIS] - LIGHTS, CAMERA, DRONESTRIKE! [HET]\r\nWRIGGLERSITTER [Jade]\r\n'),
('jadeLunchLady', 'JADE LUNCH LADY', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A heavy ladle, big cleaver, or frying pan\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+APP**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +4\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +0\r\nPSP: +2\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nCOOKING BY THE BOOK (Frying) [Goremand]\r\nHERO SUB SANDWICH [Goremand]\r\nCROWD PLEASER [Goremand]\r\nIDIOT SANDWICH [Goremand]\r\n'),
('jadeMonster', 'JADE MONSTER', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**16 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A reinforced guitar, microphone flail, or ILLEGAL PIT MOVES\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT**\r\nRAS: +2\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +1\r\nGRT: +5\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: -1\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nCOUNTERCULTURIST (Metalhead) [Jade]\r\nFIT CHECK [Jade]\r\nREBEL WITH A CAUSE [Jade]\r\nSUN TOUCHED [Jade]\r\n'),
('jadeSentinel', 'JADE SENTINEL', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**16 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A balanced claymore, towering shield, or hefty halberd\r\n\r\nTALENTS: +GRT\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +2\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +4\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +1\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nHUMBLE HERO [Jade]\r\nDRESS WOUNDS [Jade]\r\nFORFEND [Jade]\r\nKEEP GOING! [Jade]\r\n'),
('jadeTutor', 'JADE TUTOR', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A metal ruler, heavy rulebook, or “correctionial” morningstar\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PLC**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +4\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +1\r\nPSP: +2\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nTEACHER, TEACHER! [Jade]\r\nCLASSROOM CHAOS [Jade]\r\nINDIGNANT HOWL OF THE SCORNED EDUCATOR [Jade]\r\nTUTELATION [Jade]\r\n'),
('jadeWarrior', 'JADE WARRIOR', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A holy sword, blessed hammer, or revolver loaded with sanctified silver bullets\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+GRA**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +4\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +1\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nCAVERNVANIA (Wights) [Jade]\r\nEXORCISE [Jade]\r\nSLAYER’S TRICKS [Jade]\r\nINQUSITOR’S JUDGEMENT [Jade]\r\n'),
('jadeWormCaller', 'JADE WORM-CALLER', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A heavy prayerbook, weaponized rosary, or specialized dagger\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +2\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +1\r\nPSP: +2\r\nIMG: +4\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nWORM CHURCH [Jade]\r\nORISONICS [Jade]\r\nPRAYER POWER [Jade]\r\nTHE VOICE [Jade]\r\n'),
('jrCisBreacher', 'JR. CIS BREACHER', 'NPC_MONSTERS', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+HUB, +PLC**\r\nSTATS: +4 HUB, +3 PLC, +2 ALL\r\nJR. CIS Breachers, despite the name, do not kick doors. They use massive battering rams to take down entire walls instead while Operators on the other side reveal themselves and shoot everyone in the confusion. At least, that’s the dream. More often they just smash down heavily armored targets for their allies to finish off.\r\n\r\nMOVE:\r\nHEAVY ARMOR\r\nMOM IS COMING IN OPEN THE DOOR OR NOT\r\nPREEMPTIVE INTERVENTION\r\nBREACH AND CLEAR\r\nJR. CIS TRAINING'),
('jrCisDronePilot', 'JR. CIS DRONE PILOT', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**16 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT, +PSP**\r\nSTATS: +4 GRT, +4 PSP, +3 ALL\r\nThe JR. CIS Drone Pilot is an elite member of those renowned jades who not only directly sends drones into battle, but can even directly control them. Drones in their own right are a menace, but a drone that has a thinking mind behind the armor and gatling guns is something else entirely. Thankfully, safety precautions against hijackings mean only certain models can be piloted. And they tend to be… not as tough.\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nMACHINE\r\nPULVERIZE\r\nNETWORKED ARMOUR\r\nKEYBOARD WARRIOR\r\nJR. CIS ELITE TRAINING'),
('jrCisOperator', 'JR. CIS OPERATOR', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRA, +PLC**\r\nSTATS: +4 GRA, +3 PLC, +3 PSP, +2 ALL\r\nJR. CIS Operators do not get deployed to field work often, but when they do each agent shares the unspoken goal of proving the myth of the friendly, motherly, harmless Jadeblood wrong. Efficient and ruthless, but still known to taunt their targets about their search history.\r\n\r\nMOVE:\r\nPRECISE STRIKE\r\nFEMME FATALE\r\nCISHETKIND USER\r\nINFOWARS\r\nJR. CIS TRAINING\r\n'),
('jrHetAllSeer', 'JR. HET ALL-SEER', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+HUB, +GRA**\r\nSTATS: +4 HUB, +3 GRA, +2 ALL\r\nThespians make up the bulk of the JR. HET’s field agents, foot soldiers with a flair for the dramatic and a distaste for rebels. Their arrival heralds spectacular destruction; and escape is particularly more difficult from the HET’s all-seeing eyes than from the indiscriminate slaughter of drones.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\nALL-SEEING EYE\r\nSHORT STRAW\r\nMINDBLAST\r\nJR. HET TRAINING\r\n'),
('jrHetExecuterror', 'JR. HET EXECUTERROR', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**16 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+HUB, +GRT**\r\nSTATS: +5 HUB, +4 GRT, +2 ALL, +0 GRA\r\nRaw efficiency sacrifices the despair and fear that a crushing victory brings to the enemy; or so is the motto of the Executerrors that the JR. HET deploys to make examples of particularly annoying rebels, Heavily armored, faces hidden behind masks and bearing a number of flashy weapons to inspire their compatriots, these agents often mark a drastic turn for the worse in a street fight (and finally answers the question of where all the buff ceruleans are).\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nLIGHTS, CAMERA\r\nGLADIATOR IN THE RING\r\nELEMENTAL STRIKE\r\nATTENTION SLORE\r\nBUT WAIT, THERE\'S MORE!\r\nJR. HET ELITE TRAINING'),
('jrHetThespian', 'JR. HET THESPIAN', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+HUB, +GRA**\r\nSTATS: +4 HUB, +3 GRA, +2 ALL\r\nThespians make up the bulk of the JR. HET’s field agents, foot soldiers with a flair for the dramatic and a distaste for rebels. Their arrival heralds spectacular destruction; and escape is particularly more difficult from the HET’s all-seeing eyes than from the indiscriminate slaughter of drones.\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nOVERWATCH\r\nTHRUST, THRUST, PARRY\r\nFLANK AND DESTROY\r\nI\'M A MAIN CHARACTER NOW\r\nJR. HET TRAINING'),
('jrTitAdept', 'JR. TIT ADEPT', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+PSP, +IMG**\r\nSTATS: +5 PSP, +3 IMG, +2 ALL, -1 GRT\r\nJR. TIT agents understand one thing above all else. Magic is fake as absolute FUCK. But a step further than that are the Adepts who understand the next part of the phrase. “But things that are fake as fuck can still fuck someone up.” That is to say, magic might be fake but fake magic can still kill. And boy, Adepts have trained in this fake school of soon-to-be-science intensely, and come out the other side wielding powers unexplainable by science (for now). They also tend to float a little.\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nRAPID ANALYSIS\r\nSCIENCE MISSILE\r\nFLOATING WIZARD FUCK\r\nUNREALITY RECREATION\r\nJR. TIT TRAINING'),
('jrTitAmestilogician', 'JR. TIT AMESTIOLOGICIAN\r\n', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**16 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+PSP, +GRT**\r\nSTATS: +4 PSP, +3 GRT, +2 ALL\r\nJR. TIT Amnestilogicians are the amnestics bearing, flamethrower wielding terminators of wrongthink and corruptive knowledge. Their launcher spews both memory erasing gas and body scorching flames; largely thanks to amnestic gas also being flammable. \r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nSPEW AND FORGET\r\nTHICK OF THE FLAMES\r\nBURN AWAY THE UNCLEAN\r\nSMOKESCREEN\r\nJR. TIT ELITE TRAINING'),
('jrTitMobileResponder', 'JR. TIT MOBILE RESPONDER', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG, +PSP**\r\nSTATS: +4 IMG, +3 PSP, +2 ALL\r\nJR. TIT Mobile Response agents are the bread and butter of entity elimination and capture, the signature gas mask mook. Few have seen them.. At least, few that remember. They have a tendency to walk through busy streets without anyone realizing they’re there thanks to amnestics. That you see them at all bodes poorly.\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nSQUAD OP\r\nKETER DUTY\r\nPARANORMAL ERADICATION\r\nSPECIAL WEAPONS AND TACTICS\r\nJR. TIT TRAINING'),
('kidOnABike', 'KID ON A BIKE', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n***12 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A heavy flashlight, baseball bat, or rake\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+RAS**\r\nRAS: +4\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +0\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +2\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nNEIGHBORHOOD WATCHKID [Kids on Bikes]\r\nWALK THAT WALK [Kids on Bikes]\r\nGOVERNMENT AGENT ENEMIES [Kids on Bikes]\r\nEMINENT DOMAIN [Kids on Bikes]\r\n'),
('limeAuthor', 'LIME AUTHOR', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 1 NPC\r\n**8 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A pen-sword, narrative happenstance, or two narrative devices called “fists.”\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PSP**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +2\r\nGRA: +2\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +0\r\nPSP: +3\r\nIMG: +1\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nTHE LIMEBLOOD PARABLE [Lime]\r\nTHREE ACT STRUCTURE [Lime]\r\nWITS ABOUT YOU [Lime]\r\n'),
('limeHero', 'LIME HERO', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 1 NPC\r\n**10 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A trusty sickle, dull blade, or dented shield\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+GRA**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +2\r\nGRA: +3\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +1\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nTHE CHOSEN ONE [Lime]\r\nALTERCATE [Lime]\r\nPLOT ARMOR [Lime]\r\nWON’T GIVE IN [Lime]\r\n'),
('limeKnave', 'LIME KNAVE', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 1 NPC\r\n**10 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A shortsword, dueling dagger, or light hammer\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+HUB**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +2\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +3\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +1\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nALTERNATE UNIVERSE (Fantasy) [Lime]\r\nFROM ANOTHER WORLD [Lime]\r\nIN PLAIN SIGHT [Lime]\r\n'),
('limeOc', 'LIME OC', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 1 NPC\r\n**8 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: ANCIENT SWORD OF CURSED KAIJU BONE! (Actually a regular sword), PURE ENERGY BLASTS FROM THEIR HALF DEMON HALF ANGEL SOUL MANIFESTATION! (It’s a lazer pistol), or EYE FLAMES!!! (A lighter and an aerosol can)\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+RAS**\r\nRAS: +3\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +2\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nORIGINAL CHARACTER [Lime]\r\nANY CASTE [ULTRA] MOVE\r\nCONTRIVED COINCIDENCE [Lime]\r\n'),
('limePowergamer', 'LIME POWERGAMER', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 1 NPC\r\n**8 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A physical hardcover copy of the Subgrubs & Snazzards TTRPG rulebook, a perfectly balanced sword, or a back-up back-up knife\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG**\r\nRAS: +2\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +2\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +1\r\nPSP: +1\r\nIMG: +3\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nPAST THE FOURTH WALL [Lime]\r\nSUSPICIOUS STATS [Lime]\r\nLIKE ME [Lime]\r\n'),
('lonelyOrphaner', 'LONELY ORPHANER', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A specialized harpoon gun, sniper rifle, or big fucking axe\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+GRA**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +4\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +1\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +2\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nEMISSARY’S ORPHANERS [Orphaner]\r\nHORRORTERROR’S LITTLE TERROR [Orphaner]\r\nMOBY DICK REFERENCE NAME [Orphaner]\r\nPRIZED HUNTER [Orphaner]\r\nSURMOUNT [Violet]\r\n');
INSERT INTO `monster` (`key`, `title`, `doc`, `text`) VALUES
('lostRustButler', 'LOST RUST BUTLER', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A mop, reinforced broom, or sterling silver knife\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+RAS**\r\nRAS: +4\r\nPLC: +2\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +0\r\nPSP: +1\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nRIGHT HAND TROLL [SERVICESQUIRE]\r\nNO NEED FOR ALARM [SERVICESQUIRE]\r\nHIT-BUTLER [SERVICESQUIRE]\r\nPROPER POSTURE [SERVICESQUIRE]\r\n'),
('lowbloodRedshirt', 'LOWBLOOD REDSHIRT', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 1 NPC\r\n**6 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT**\r\nSTATS: +2 ALL\r\nThe auxiliaries of the Empire’s fighting troops consist largely of lowblood conscripts guilty of rebellion, volunteers seeking higher placement in society or simply the oddly fanactical violet influencer simp. While ill equipped and poorly respected, Redshirtmunitions move in swarms and still carry the lowblooded camaraderie that kept them alive up to this point.\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nEUSOCIAL COMBAT TRAINING\r\nTHERE IS POWER IN A\r\nBAYONET CHARGE'),
('megatoad', 'MEGATOAD', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 4 LUSUS\r\n**35 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++GRA, +APP, +GRT**\r\nSTATS: **+4 GRT, +3 GRA, +2 ALL**\r\nAn immense, fanged toad clambers around, roaring loudly. Hey, you know this guy! He’s from the cover of Subgrubs & Snazzards! Oh god, he’s about to eat you, fuck!\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> MEGAMOUTH\r\n> MEGATONGUE\r\n> MEGALEAP\r\n> MEGANOPE\r\n> MEGACROAK\r\n> MEGASENSETHETERRORINYOURBONESANDHONEINFORTHEKILL'),
('monstersMortalEnemy', 'MONSTER\'S MORTAL ENEMY', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**16 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A gun to take down a Megatoad, a spear to fight off a Grublord, or an axe to take on a Kaiju\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +4\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +2\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nTHE EVERYTHING HUNTER [Beast Brawler]\r\nMAVEN MONSTROCITY (Barkfiend) [Beast Brawler]\r\nAROOOOOO [Barkfiend]\r\nSERIOUSLY, SCREW CELADINE [Beast Brawler]\r\n'),
('moonhauntMemory', 'MOONHAUNT MEMORY', 'ENTITY', 'LVL 3 ENTITY\r\n**-18 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++GRT, +GRA**\r\nSTATS: **+2 GRT, +2 GRA, -2 PLC**\r\nDid you know death is technically a cure for moonbarkness? If a Psionic moonbark dies and produces a ghost, the ghost will not retain the moonbark curse due to a lack of a physical body to contain it. Instead, the moonbark part of their soul will split off and travel on its own, roaming Alternia as a feral beast made of smoke and plague looking for a new host to curse.\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\n> ROAMING PESTILENCE\r\n> WEAKENING THE BEAST\r\n> INFECTED FANGS\r\n> SHADOW SHARDS\r\n> BEASTLY SUBTYPES\r\n> CARRYING THE CURSE'),
('nadsDemolitionist', 'NADS DEMOLITIONIST', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**10 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+HUB, +RAS**\r\nSTATS: +4 HUB, +3 RAS, +2 ALL\r\nOnce again, NADS is here to save the night! This heroic masked member’s taken to the domes of Ripslag, blasting enemy fortifications to bits as they push ever closer towards blowing the palace sky-high and rescuing the innocent heiress. Ripslag must be liberated! Rebellion Now!\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nACTUAL MILITARY EXPLOSIVES\r\nSMITHEREENATE\r\nEXPLOSIVE FINISH\r\nINSURGENT DEVOTION'),
('nadsJunkMech', 'NADS JUNK-MECH', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 3 ROBOT/NPC\r\n**20 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++GRT, +APP**\r\nSTATS: +4 GRT, +3 APP, +3 HUB, +2 ALL\r\nWho the hell do you think we are?? Each and every one of these mechas is the product of perigees of passionate effort from NADS’s junkers and engineers - through tireless toil and just a bit of interstellar supplying, they’ve created a small fleet of robots that can face off against the finest Imperial drones and come out on top.\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nMAVERICK MENACE\r\nARTILLERIZE\r\nSO LONG, SPACE MECHA\r\nINSURGENT DEVOTION'),
('nadsRevolutionary', 'NADS REVOLUTIONARY', 'NPC_MONSTER', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**10 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT, +HUB**\r\nSTATS: +4 GRT, +3 HUB, +2 ALL\r\nOnce again, NADS is here to save the night! And this heroic rebel’s here to do just that - decked out in military gear from a mysterious benefactor, and ready and eager to storm the palace with it. The Heiress will be secured! Ripslag will be liberated! Rebellion Now!\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\nACTUAL ARMOR\r\nACTUAL GUN\r\nHERO MOMENT\r\nINSURGENT DEVOTION'),
('notFourFairybullsInATrenchCoat', 'NOT FOUR FAIRYBULLS IN A TRENCH COAT', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 1 LUSUS\r\n**12HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+HUB, -GRA**\r\nSTATS: **+2 HUB, -4 GRA**\r\nThis is a regular troll walking around the surface of Alternia. Yes, this is a respectable and definitely very troll-like troll with regular troll arms and hands and a head and all those other troll things. Invite them in for a cup of tea!\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> VAGUELY CONVINCING DISGUISE\r\n> QWOP\r\n> HOW DARE YOU HURT THIS NORMAL AND REGULAR PERSON\r\n> AUGH SCATTER'),
('oliveFan', 'OLIVE FAN', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A keyboard flail, ridiculously sturdy palmhusk, or stupidly sharp notebook\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+RAS**\r\nRAS: +4\r\nPLC: +2\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +1\r\nIMG: +1\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nFANDOM CAT [Olive]\r\nSIDES OF GRUMBLR (Memes) [Olive]\r\nDASHBOARD CLOGGER [Olive]\r\nLOLCAT [Olive]\r\n'),
