('rustStreetUrchin', 'RUST STREET URCHIN', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 1 NPC\r\n**10 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A pocket knife, broken pipe, or their own gritty fists\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+APP**\r\nRAS: +2\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +3\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +1\r\nIMG: +1\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nSLUMBLOOD [Rust]\r\nPLAY POSSUM [Rust]\r\nLATENT PSIONICS [Rust]\r\n'),
('rustyDecompositionist', 'RUSTY DECOMPOSITIONIST', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A shovel or pickaxe\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PLC**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +4\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +0\r\nPSP: +1\r\nIMG: +2\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nLAST RITES [Orthodox Decompositionists]\r\nAESOP SAYS [Orthodox Decompositionists]\r\nSPEAK TO ME [Orthodox Decompositionists]\r\nTHE GOLDEN RULE [Orthodox Decompositionists]\r\n'),
('selfTaughtOliveDocterror', 'SELF-TAUGHT OLIVE DOCTERROR', 'TEMPLATE-NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A razor-sharp scalpel, bonesaw, or needle full of ‘the cure’\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PSP**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +2\r\nGRA: +2\r\nAPP: +1\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +1\r\nPSP: +4\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nTHE DOCTERROR IS IN [Docterror]\r\nEMT TRAINING [Docterror]\r\nMEDICAL MALPRACTICE [Docterror]\r\nMCAT-LIKE RELFEXES [Docterror]\r\n'),
('shimmerfowl', 'SHIMMERFOWL', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 2 LUSUS\r\n**12 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++GRA, +HUB**\r\nSTATS: **+3 GRA, +2 HUB**\r\nAs beautiful, powerful birds with glimmering reflective tail feathers twice as long as their body, shimmerfowl make popular ornamental pets for highbloods— provided you get past their moody temperament, at least.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> LIFT-OFF\r\n> RUFFLED FEATHERS\r\n> PINION PANDEMONIUM\r\n> FEATHER DANCE\r\n> ADOPTIVE SIBLING'),
('skyhorse', 'SKYHORSE', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 2 LUSUS\r\n**14 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRA, +GRT**\r\nSTATS: **+3 GRA, +2 GRT**\r\nSkyhorse! Like a seahorse, but in the sky. Cursed no longer to drift aimlessly through the ocean on that singular fin, free to roam the skies and seas as it pleases... unfortunately, as a violet lusus, its freedom is everyone else’s suffering.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> TRIPHIBIAN\r\n> PREHENSILE TAIL\r\n> BE THE RIDER\r\n> IN MY SIGHTS'),
('skySlug', 'SKY SLUG', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 1 LUSUS\r\n**6 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRA**\r\nSTATS: **+2 GRA, -1 GRT**\r\nIt\'s a cute little flying sea-slug! With stingray wings! These guys are all over Ripslag- and are even considered pests- but above the water are considered exotic pets. Like all lusii, their body itself is white- however, the slime covering their body is the same hue as their blood color! Violet Sky Slugs are extremely rare and are often kept as pets by Snootier-Than-Average highbloods. \r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> SLIPPERY SON OF A SLUG\r\n> SLIME TIME\r\n> SLIME- stop?'),
('snazzard', 'SNAZZARD', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 4 LUSUS\r\n**40 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++GRT, ++IMG, ++HUB, +ALL**\r\nSTATS: **+4 GRT, +4 IMG, +3 HUB, +2 ALL**\r\nOne of the rarest and most powerful lusii, these white dragons have crimson red eyes, powerful wings, and sharp, sharp fangs. Its psionic voice booms inside your mind, speaking in the language of the trolls. To come across one of these majestic creatures is a stroke of unbelievable luck; to survive an encounter with one, even more unbelievable.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> POWERFUL WINGS\r\n> DRAGON\'S BREATH\r\n> LEGENDARY RESISTANCE\r\n> GLARESPLOSION\r\n> DRACONIC JAPES\r\n> ANCIENT ARBITATOR\r\n> SOULSEARCHER\r\n> SCION OF JUSTICE\r\n> SWEET LOOT'),
('snazzling', 'SNAZZLING', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 1 LUSUS\r\n**8 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+RAS**\r\nSTATS: **+3 RAS, +2 PSP**\r\nIt’s like a snazzard, but tinier! Snazzlings are, in a word: Gross. They live mostly in subgrubian areas, where they scavenge out of trash cans and make annoyingly loud noises at incredibly late hours of day. Against all logic, it would seem these are the Snazzard’s closest living relatives.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> SNAZZ-SCRATCH\r\n> SLUDGEBALL\r\n> KNOWING STARE\r\n> EVOLUTIONARY HERITAGE'),
('sobbingSpriggan', 'SOBBING SPRIGGAN', 'PLANT', 'LVL 2 PLANT\r\n14 HP\r\nTALENTS: ++GRT\r\nSTATS: +3 GRT, +2 APP\r\nHorticullturists and rich indigoes generally grow ornamental plants and topiaries specifically to make things beautiful and spread joy. This once-ornamental, now-invasive plant was engineered by a particularly depressing horticullturist to do the exact opposite of that! The Sobbing Spriggan is a tree that resembles a hunched over, miserable troll with its hands over its eyes and fronds of willowy \'hair\' draping its entire body. It unilaterally spoils the vibes of everyone around it, to the point that small woodland creatures that approach it often die of sadness on the spot. Just like my mother-in-law!\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> CRUNGLED BEYOND BELIEF\r\n> LEAVE ME ALONE TO WALLOW\r\n> NO FUN ALLOWED EVER THANK YOU\r\n> SIREN OF THE WAAMBULANCE'),
('souljar', 'SOULJAR', 'PLANT', 'LVL 2 PLANT\r\n**12 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+APP**\r\nSTATS: **+3 IMG, +2 APP**\r\nThe Souljar is a wildflower that resembles golden Queen Anne’s Lace; it has long stalks that end in big clusters of many tiny yellow flowers. It tends to form long root networks that pop up in many places, so several stalks of the flower are often all one organism. While relatively harmless to the living, it does have a very dangerous effect on the dead. Just like any number of my bizarrely floral and toxic family.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> POLLEN ALLERGY\r\n> UNDEAD MINIONS\r\n> YOU TOO\r\n> PLANT WEAKNESS #3'),
('soullessbot', 'SOULLESSBOT', 'ROBOT_MONSTER', 'LVL 2 ROBOT\r\n**12 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+APP, +GRT, -GRA, -PSP**\r\nSTATS: **+2 APP, +2 GRT**\r\nOh dear, something real bad happened to this Soulbot. Its chassis is all warped and damaged, maybe burnt out and missing a few pieces. Whatever happened to this thing, it has no recollection of who or what it was, all it knows now is that it hates everything living and seeks only to KILL. KILL. KILL.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> BUSTED MACHINE\r\n> EXTERMINATE! EXTERMINATE!\r\n> I WANT MY SOUL BACK!\r\n> FUCKED UP FRAME\r\n> TEMPORARY BLISS STATE'),
('spearslaughterPlant', 'SPEARSLAUGHTER PLANT', 'PLANT', 'LVL 1 PLANT\r\n**6 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRA, +GRT**\r\nSTATS: **+3 GRA, +2 GRT**\r\nThe Spearslaughter is a long and supple purple vine with thorns and few leaves. These particular plants are one of the most common in Alternian forests and jungles, and while they’re more of an annoyance than a danger, they can still cause plenty of trouble for anyone venturing into the wilds. Just like my ex-wife!\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> HARD TO SEE\r\n> HARD TO BURN\r\n> HARD TO FIGHT\r\n> PLANT WEAKNESS #2'),
('spidermom', 'SPIDERMOM', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 4 LUSUS\r\n**30 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++IMG, +GRT, +APP**\r\nSTATS: **+3 GRT, +3 IMG, +2 ALL**\r\nThis ferocious, house-sized spider has a head, thorax, and abdomen, unlike a regular spider; also unlike a regular spider, its voice echoes through your head, demanding that you feed it corpses.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> PSIONIC VOICE\r\n> LONG LASTING RELATIONSHIP\r\n> SNACKS\r\n> WELCOME TO MY PARLOR\r\n> YOUR WILL IS MINE'),
('spurnedHerballist', 'SPURNED HERBALLIST', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: BIG DAMN PLANT SHEARS TO GET RID OF ALL THESE STUPID PLANTS AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA-\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PSP**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +1\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +4\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nMEAN GREEN GARDENER FROM OUTER SPACE (Herballist) [Horticullturist]\r\nFAUNAFLORA [Horticullturist]\r\nGREEN THUMB [Horticullturist]\r\nMIRACLE GRO [Horticullturist]\r\n'),
('spydrone', 'SPYDRONE', 'ROBOT_MONSTER', 'LVL 1 ROBOT\r\n**8 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+PSP**\r\nSTATS: **+3 PSP**\r\nDrones are rightly championed and feared as the foremost manifestation of Imperial power. For a simple definition of ‘power’, Spydrones are the exception to that rule; in a broader one, they are its foundation, the Empire’s thousands of unblinking eyes across Alternia. Take heart, citizen. You are seen, whether you like it or not.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> ALWAYS WATCHING\r\n> WAR IS PEACE\r\n> DOUBLETHINK'),
('stellarStargazer', 'STELLAR STARGAZER', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A mystical wand, arcanic staff, or focus crystal\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG**\r\nRAS: +2\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +4\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nASTROSORCERY [Astrosorcerer]\r\nHUZZAH! A WIZARD [Astrosorcerer]\r\nCONJURIFICATE [Astrosorcerer]\r\nNEBULITCHCRAFT [Astrosorcerer]\r\n'),
('stingCenturion', 'STING-CENTURION', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 3 LUSUS\r\n**20 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++GRT, +GRA, +PSP**\r\nSTATS: **+2 GRT, +2 GRA, +2 PSP**\r\nA Sting-Centurion is a scuttlebuggy-sized bundle of hate, fury, and chitin. If a normal Sting-Scout’s wings can cause a pinprick, these beests can cause full-on gashes. Their role in the hierarchy is the defense and protection of the colony, as well as bringing dispatched prey back to the hive. \r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\n> CENTURION\'S TACTICS\r\n> B#\r\n> HT VISION\r\n> NOT THE BEES (ABRIDGED)\r\n> ATTACK PHEROMONES\r\n> SONIC BOOM\r\n'),
('stingWingPsiSwarm', 'STING-WING PSI-SWARM', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 2 LUSUS\r\n**14 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG, +GRA**\r\nSTATS: **+3 IMG, +2 GRA, +2 PSP**\r\nThat whole thing about Sting-Wings not having psionics? Complete bullshit. Yeah, I lied to you. Cry about it. This is a highly specialized member of the colony, and its role is to defend the hive from more… esoteric threats. And the only way to fight fire is with more terrifying bee-themed fire! I mean that literally, that\'s not a metaphor.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> BEES TOGETHER STRONG\r\n> SWARM SWARM SWARM SWARM\r\n> TERRIFYING BEE-THEMED FIRE\r\n> B.B.B.B\r\n> SCATTERBRAINED'),
('stingWingScout', 'STING-WING SCOUT', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 0 LUSUS\r\n**1 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRA**\r\nSTATS: **-2 GRT**\r\nIt’s a Bee. A single Bee. It’s a “B,” if you will. The Sting-Wing Species is known for having incredibly sharp wings, more than enough to draw blood. In addition, the Sting-Wing species is noted for lacking psionics of any kind! These teeny tiny members of the colony are responsible for learning where potential food sources are and reporting their findings back to the colony.  \r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> BUZZ-BUZZ\r\n> APPROPRIATE NAME\r\n> DISTRESS PHEROMONES\r\n> PATHETIC.'),
('sugarSoldier', 'SUGAR SOLDIER', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**13 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: BIG LOLLYPOPS TO LOLLYBOP THE SAD LITTLE SUGARDROPS!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+RAS**\r\nRAS: +4\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +2\r\nGRT: +1\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +1\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nA SPOONFUL OF SUGAR [Trickster]\r\nLIFEBLOOD [Trickster]\r\nSUCKERPUNCH [Trickster]\r\nSO SO SO SO SO SO SO GREAT SO COOL SO GREAT [Trickster]\r\n'),
('tealEnforcer', 'TEAL ENFORCER', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**16 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: An oversized gavel, standard issue revolver, or execution axe\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +2\r\nAPP: +1\r\nGRT: +4\r\nHUB: +1\r\nPSP: +2\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nDEAD OR ALIVE [Teal]\r\nLITIGATE [Teal]\r\nINTERROGATION TACTICS [Teal]\r\nKINDA BADASS [Teal]\r\n'),
('tealLabcoat', 'TEAL LABCOAT', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A bandolier of caustic mixtures, DYI laser rifle, or WHY THE FUCK DO YOU HAVE THAT RIDICULOUSLY OVERHEATED FLAMETHROWER THERE’S NO WAY THAT’S SAFE EVEN FOR YOU TO EVEN BE NEAR\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PSP**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +2\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +4\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nOMNIDISCIPLINARY SCIENTIST [Teal]\r\nCONCOCTIOMANCY [Teal]\r\nCRAZED CACKLE [Teal]\r\nNOT SCIENTIFICALLY POSSIBLE [Teal]\r\n'),
('tealScalescribe', 'TEAL SCALESCRIBE', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**13 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: Vicious claws, powerful jaws, or A GUN POWERED BY THE LAW(S)\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+HUB**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +2\r\nAPP: +1\r\nGRT: +1\r\nHUB: +4\r\nPSP: +2\r\nIMG: +1\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nSNAZZARD RIDER [Teal]\r\nGIDDY UP! [Teal]\r\nPROTECTIVE INSTINCTS [Teal]\r\nDRAGON WHISPERER [Teal]\r\n'),
('tealSplattorneyAtLaw', 'TEAL SPLATTORNEY-AT-LAW', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A heavy briefcase, prized report of a sweeps long case laminated in metal, or WHY IS THIS FUCKING LAWBOOK SO IDIOTICALLY FUCKING BIG I HATE BOOKS JUST USE NORMAL WEAPONS YOU FUCKING FREAKS\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PLC**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +4\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +2\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +1\r\nPSP: +2\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nSHOWTRIAL DRAMA [Teal]\r\nLEGAL TRAINING [Teal]\r\nOBJECTION FUNK [Teal]\r\nWHODUNNITRY [Teal]\r\n'),
('tealToiler', 'TEAL TOILER', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A weaponized husktop, office chair, or Imperially Legal Overclocked Taser\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+GRA**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +4\r\nAPP: +1\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +2\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nWORKPLACE WHIZ (Assistant) [Teal]\r\nGET TECHNICAL [Teal]\r\nAGGRAVATED BUREAUCRACY [Teal]\r\nSNITCHBLOOD [Teal]\r\n'),
('theCantyman', 'THE CAN\'TYMAN', 'ENTITY', 'LVL 2 ENTITY\r\n**13 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT, +HUB**\r\nSTATS: **+3 GRT, +3 HUB, -3 APP**\r\n\r\nWHO CAN BEAT YOU SENSELESS?! WHOSE AIM IS SCARILY TRUE?! TAKE A ROCK CANDY HAMMER AND HAVE IT CRUSH YOU?!\r\nTHE CAN\'TYMAN CAN!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\r\nA Can\'tyman is born from one of two circumstances: when a Trickster and a Grimdark have a violent battle and both die, or when a Trickster suffers a Sugar Crash so bad and life-changing the sugar magic literally rips its way out of the person and spontaneously morphs and forms into the Can\'tyman. Gone is all the happiness and hyperactive silly antics, Can\'tymen wish to see the universe crushed and cracked like cheap jawbreakers, melted like ultradark chocolate, and smushed under their feet like candy corn. FUCK CANDY CORN. AND FUCK YOU. They are tall, lanky, and look edgy enough to cut you. Because they can! And will! They wanna cut you and crush you with rock candy hammers and hurt you so so so so so so so bad.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> THE CAN\'TYMAN CAN (KILL YOU AND HURT YOU AND CRUSH YOU SO BAD)\r\n> SUGARBORN\r\n> SHUTUPSHUTUPSHUTUPSHUTUPSHUTUP!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! \r\n'),
('theSnail', 'THE SNAIL', 'ENTITY', 'LVL 3 ENTITY\r\n**24 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **+IMG, +APP**\r\nSTATS: **+3 IMG, +2 GRT, -3 GRA**\r\nResiding in both the deepcaverns and dark jungles the world-round, THE SNAIL is a special kind of Alternian nightmare- a troll-sized mollusk that induces an emotional crisis in its prey via psionics. It uses this opportunity of confusion in its prey to slowly consume them with its acidic slime. \r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> SNAIL\'S PACE\r\n> SHIMMERSTALKS\r\n> HELL\'S SHELL\r\n> SLIME ATTACK MOVE #??\r\n> IRONIC DOWNFALL'),
('trollInTeal', 'TROLL IN TEAL', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**12 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A standard issue pistol, telescopic baton, or tranq gun with too much tranquilizer\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PSP**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +1\r\nAPP: +2\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +4\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nTROLLS IN TEAL [TIT]\r\nCALL FOR BACKUP [TIT]\r\nNEUROMEDDLING [TIT]\r\nTINFOIL IMPLANTS [TIT]\r\n\r\n'),
('tsuchineko', 'TSUCHINEKO', 'LUSUS', 'LVL 1 LUSUS\r\n**8 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++PLC**\r\nSTATS: **+4 PLC**\r\nFrom your understanding, Tsuchineko Real. It is a small serpent creature with a particularly fat body which it uses for locomotion; however, on its head, it has two little cat ears, and some cute whiskers around its nose.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> IRRESISTIBLE\r\n> BOING\r\n> STUPID\r\n> POWER OF BABEL'),
('vampedUpVampyr', 'VAMPED-UP VAMPYR', 'TEMPLATE_NPC', 'LVL 2 NPC\r\n**14 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: Fangz for dayz\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+GRA**\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +2\r\nGRA: +4\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +2\r\nHUB: +1\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +1\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nVESTAL VAMPYR [Rainbow Drinker]\r\nHIIIIIISSSSSSSSSSS [Rainbow Drinker]\r\nHYPNOTIC GAZE [Rainbow Drinker]\r\nSTEALTHLING [Rainbow Drinker]\r\n'),
('venusTrolltrap', 'VENUS TROLLTRAP', 'PLANT', 'LVL 3 PLANT\r\n**22 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++GRT, +PLC, +GRA**\r\nSTATS: **+3 GRT, +2 PLC**\r\nSome botanists believe that the Venus Trolltrap isn’t actually native to Alternia. Regardless, with its long, snaking vines that are much more agile than they seem and a huge bulb at its center that opens into a maw full of razor teeth, the Trolltrap fits right into its surroundings. This one is just like… me. I\'m a Venus Trolltrap. I have been all along, haven\'t I..? \r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> LUNCH TIME\r\n> FEED ME, SEYMOUR\r\n> VENUS PLANTLETS\r\n> WEIRD-PLANT-HEADACHE'),
('violetGeneralToBe', 'VIOLET GENERAL-TO-BE', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**19 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A portable cannon, harpoon launcher, or impossibly high-quality cutlass\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+GRA**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +4\r\nAPP: +1\r\nGRT: +3\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nNAUTICAL NIGHTMARE [Violet]\r\nNAVAL FLEET [Violet]\r\nSURMOUNT [Violet]\r\nFLAWLESS TRAINING [Violet]\r\nGET THROUGH ME FIRST [Violet]\r\n'),
('violetGoblin', 'VIOLET GOBLIN', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**20 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: Millions of needle teeth, dripping with hate and venom\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+GRT**\r\nRAS: +3\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +0\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +4\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +1\r\nIMG: +1\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nSUBPHOTIC VARIANT (Needle Teeth) [Violet]\r\nHEMOLUMINESCENCE [Violet]\r\nNOT FROM AROUND HERE (STAND OUT) (Sharkskin) [Violet]\r\nMUTAGENIC ADAPTION (Venomous) [Violet]\r\nGLUBGLUBBERY [Violet]\r\n'),
('violetLancer', 'VIOLET LANCER', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**19 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: A mounted laser platform, large cannon, or fuck-off big sword\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+HUB**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +0\r\nGRA: +2\r\nAPP: +0\r\nGRT: +3\r\nHUB: +4\r\nPSP: +1\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nGET IN THE ROBOT [Violet]\r\nMECHA-ANTICS [Violet]\r\nPIERCE THE TRENCHES [Violet]\r\nFIRM IDEALS [Violet]\r\nSHARED PRIDE [Violet]\r\n'),
('violetSuperstarfish', 'VIOLET SUPERSTARFISH', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n16 HP\r\nSPECIBUS: A savage stan swarm, mic flail, or glittery gun\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+PLC**\r\nRAS: +1\r\nPLC: +4\r\nGRA: +2\r\nAPP: +3\r\nGRT: +0\r\nHUB: +1\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nULTRAMEGASUPERSTAR [Violet]\r\nADORING FANS [Violet]\r\nCLAIM TO FAME (Superstar) [Violet]\r\nPUBLICITY STUNT [Violet]\r\nVETERAN VIP [Violet]\r\n'),
('violetViceroy', 'VIOLET VICEROY', 'CASTE_NPC', 'LVL 3 NPC\r\n**17 HP**\r\nSPECIBUS: An extremely fancy rapier, golden trident, or personal guard of far off archers\r\n\r\nTALENTS: **+APP**, **+Paladin** (SMITE)\r\nRAS: +0\r\nPLC: +1\r\nGRA: +3\r\nAPP: +4\r\nGRT: +1\r\nHUB: +2\r\nPSP: +0\r\nIMG: +0\r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\nDIVINE RIGHT OF FISH (Stratocracy - 20 LUX) [Violet]\r\nARMORCLAD CRUSADER [Indigo]\r\nSMITE [Indigo]\r\nPRINCE PARRY [Violet]\r\nSUBTLE FLEX [Violet]\r\nINVINCIBLE! [Violet]\r\n'),
('wastelandHorror', 'WASTELAND HORROR', 'ENTITY', 'LVL 4 ENTITY\r\n**30 HP**\r\nTALENTS: **++GRT, ++APP, +ALL**\r\nSTATS: **+4 GRT, +4 APP, +3 ALL**\r\nThe terrors of the Alternian wasteland are well-known to trollkind: packs of lusii, throngs of undead, and all other manner of frightening beast and fiend. Some things that roam the wastes cannot be known, only seen. Often is a monster called a horror... but these alone take their name from the horror they inspire.\r\n\r\nMOVES: \r\n> UNDENIABLE HORROR\r\n> UNSTOPPABLE FORCE\r\n> UNNATURAL ENDURANCE\r\n> UNMATCHED PREDATOR\r\n> UNFATHOMABLE MIND\r\n> ENVELOP\r\n> UNTHINKABLE DEVASTATION');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('abdicate', 'ABDICATE', 'OTHER', 'TEAM_STRIFE', '[Team Strife][Physical][Free]', 'Alright! That\'s enough STRUGGLING for you! You wanna drop onto the back bench and let someone else take the stage. You can make a LET\'S STRIFE roll to ABSCOND, switching positions with someone on STANDBY. Surely nobody will attempt to ANNEX you!'),
('absentAgency', 'ABSENT AGENCY', 'SPACE', 'SPACE', '[Aspect][Basic][Free][Locked: Space]', 'Space is vast. That’s a tautology, or something— you’re just repeating the same thing twice. But it’s not just that space is vast, it’s that you are very, very small. To call you lonely might be an understatement... your whole life you’ve had a lack of agency as fate seems to ignore you and deprive you of important experiences. The world seems to move on without you, sometimes. As a **[Free]** action, you can choose to become **[Slowed]**; after three full rounds of being **[Slowed]**, you can remove it for **[Free]**. When you become **[Slowed]** by this move or start your turn **[Slowed]**, choose an opponent; on their next turn, their non-**[Strife]** rolls are **[Inept]** as their own actions undo them, not yours.'),
('academixravaganza', 'ACADEMIXRAVAGANZA', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Student]', 'Top of your class, coolest kid in school, outstanding in your field, etcetera etcetera. You\'re not just a star pupil, you\'re a whole supernova. You\'ve got your face on promotional material for your school, and hey, when the workdrone is out of order, maybe you even teach classes to your underclasstrolls. The bottom line? You\'re kind of a big deal here. You gain access to HERO MODE through the stat you became **[Talented]** in through PRIVATE SCHOOL PRODIGY. Additionally, you gain the following abilities based on your school of choice.\r\n\r\n> **+RAS:** Nobody will ever stop you from breaking every rule there is to break! Neener neener! Whenever an opponent gains **[Drag]**, you gain an equal amount of **[Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **+PLC:** Everything you create is nothing short of a masterpiece. When an ally gains an **[Emotion]**, you may spur this feeling to be **[Heightened]** as a **[Reaction]** by throwing some art their way. \r\n\r\n> **+GRA:** You don\'t ever stop performing. EVER. All **[Physical]** rolls against you have a **-2 [Nerf]**.\r\n\r\n> **+APP:** THE ECONOMY BOWS BEFORE YOU! All items always cost **1 VP** or **LUX** less than normal, and you have 12 **VP**, not 8.\r\n\r\n> **+GRT:** CHAAAAAARGE! You have learned the secrets of ancient warfare, and are near impossible to take out! You have an additional **2 HP** while wielding a weapon you gained from your school, and when you would be knocked to 0 HP, you may use a **[Last Stand]** to not go down, staying at **1 HP**.\r\n\r\n> **+HUB:** AT MY MARK! You may use an action to order an ally to use actions you call out— for example, GRIEF and then SWASHBUCKLE to PCHOOOOO. If the ally does so, their rolls are **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n\r\n> **+PSP:** You are a literal genius, having written more groundbreaking thesises than anyone would think possible. If someone rolls a **[Mental]** roll on their turn, you cannot roll lower than them and match their result if it would be lower (unless you get a **MIN**, whoopsy).\r\n\r\n> **+IMG:** You\'re a wizard, Indigoblood. You may take the ASTROSORCERER or SHADOWDROPPER templates without it using a **[Template]** slot or your **[Ultra]** slot. You gain the **[Entry]** now, or another move from the template. You do not gain the **[Cullbait]** tag if you do so.'),
('acceptAid', 'ACCEPT AID', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Open][Free][Recharge: 1]', 'It\'s nice to… let others help you. You\'ve spent so much time only focusing on others and helping THEM, that you never realised how much you needed someone to have your back. You\'re done turning down people\'s help; you could really use a hand. When an ally gives you a positive effect or buff of some description, such as an **[Emotion]** or **[Heal]**, you can take a **[Free]** action to give yourselves both **1 [Boost]**. You can\'t increase this **[Boost]**.'),
('accordingToDesign', 'ACCORDING TO DESIGN', 'OTHER', 'BLIGHTSMITH', '[Template][Basic][Reaction][Recharge: 4][Locked: Blightsmith]', 'Arghh!! You HATE being able to see how to do things right when others can\'t! When an ally rolls a **MIN** or **BAD**, you may **[React]** to instead **[Tier Up]** their roll to a **BAD** or **OKAY** respectively, or have them REROLL as a **[One-Off]**. Your POSTURE was OFF!!! Adjust your GRIP!!\r\n'),
('aceCustom', 'ACE CUSTOM', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Pilot]', 'Mechas may be vehicles, son, but they\'re so much more than that. They\'re SICK AS FUCK vehicles. As such, they get upgrades that the average dirtblood in their pathetic scuttlebuggies could only dream of. You\'ve customized your Mecha to look exactly like you want it to, and your personality blazes through it. You gain access to the following upgrades; these upgrades cost LICENSING POINTS, or LP. You gain 1 LP for killing a Level 2 Monster in your mecha, 3 LP for killing a Level 3 one, 8 LP for killing a Level 4 one, and 5 LP for defeating another mecha pilot. You gain one upgrade worth 3 LP now.\n\n**POWER SCANNER; 3 LP**: You can scan enemy combatants, figuring out their abilities easily. Your **[Analyze]** rolls while inside the Mecha are **[Tiered Up]**, even to a **MAX**.\n\n**ADDITIONAL COCKPITS; 3 LP**: You can fit multiple people into your mech, and they have access to the controls with you. You can carry one additional person, and they can roll VEHICULATE to control the Mecha on your turn.\n\n**80-SHIELD; 5 LP**: Something something thigh high inspired force field. Don\'t care. Point is, your Mecha has a shield system that staves off weirder attacks. Your vehicle gives you **1 [Resistance]** to **[Psychic]** damage.\n\n**B.C.T.A TANK; 5 LP**: Your cockpit is submerged in a healing violet liquid. You can use GUTSUCKERY on a **[Recharge: 3]** while inside your Mecha. This doesn\'t repair the Mecha, just you.\n\n**REPAIR DRONES; 5 LP**: Your robot comes equipped with smaller robots that have a medical degree. As a **[One-Off]**, you can roll GUTSUCKERY on your Mecha. This doesn\'t trigger the **[One-Off]** your own GUTSUCKERY triggers but doesn\'t stack with the B.C.T.A Tank Upgrade.\n\n**LASERSWORD; 5 LP**: Your attacks cut through ANYTHING! All your damage is **[Unblockable]**.\n\n**MICROMECH; 8 LP**: You customize your mecha to be less of a supergiant robot, and more of a powered exoskeleton. It\'s you sized! The Micromech can be upgraded as a regular Mecha could be, but doesn\'t have its own HP, doesn\'t require an action to summon (instead of deploying for **[Free]** from your watch, your choker, etc), and can\'t make VEHICULATE rolls. You can, however, make any **[Physical]** rolls you like inside the Micromech, and can even ride inside other Vehicles.\n\n**MK. Z UNIT; 8 LP**: Aw, shit, it\'s a different Mecha! You can have as many Mechas as you like, giving them each individual upgrades. Have different builds for different situations! A tank Mecha, a monster killing Mecha, a jet one… world is your oyster, baby!'),
('aComplicatedProfessional', 'A COMPLICATED PROFESSIONAL', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Legislacerator]', 'Legislaceration isn\'t easy. You do the job you\'re given, and don\'t ask questions, or else you aren\'t getting paid. But considering how many questions arise, many lesser Legislacerators get caught up in what\'s good, what\'s right… and sure, maybe you used to worry. But you know now. And you do your job with the efficiency of a machine. You gain access to HERO MODE through your MYTHIC MANGRIT. Your keen eyes and swift blade make you a real threat; you gain **1 [Resistance]** against your HUNTED target\'s attacks. Additionally, you can spend **[Drag]** that the HUNTED target has accumulated to shut off their most basic instincts as you wail on ‘em. You remove one of their moves with the cost of 3 **[Drag]** for a **[Basic]**, 5 **[Drag]** for an **[Advanced]**, 10 **[Drag]** for an **[Entry]** or **[Ultra]**. This effect lasts **2 turns** before you need to reactivate it. You cannot remove moves that are fundamental to their being, like an **[Eerie]** troll\'s **[Entry]** or a Mutation.'),
('actAllCute', 'ACT ALL CUTE', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Recharge: 2][Manipulate][Mental]', 'The way other castes treat Olives is a little weird. You\'re not a lowblood or anything, but everyone constantly makes you out to be a cutesy and harmless fluffball. It gets a little draining to be constantly belittled like that; insulting, even! But hey, you can use it to your advantage when you wanna. When you act adorable, roll **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: YOU ACTUALLY LOOK SO TERRIFYING. Your target shrieks and considers attacking you. They gain **2 [WHAM]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You act cutesy, but it doesn’t do shit. You feel stupid.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You catch your opponent off-guard, and they pause for a moment. They take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Awwww. Surely this little guy wouldn’t harm a fly, right? Your opponent is **[Charmed]** for 1 turn, and you gain **1 [WHAM]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: OHHHHHH, LOOK? YOU’VE GOT SUCH A CUTE FACE. PSPSPSPSPSPSPSPSPS. Your opponent is **[Fascinated]** for **1 turn**, **[Charmed]** for 1, and you gain **1 [WHAM]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: They would die for you. Your cutesiness has completely convinced them to do what you say forever. FOREVER! You **[Fascinate]** the opponent for the encounter, gain **2 [WHAM]**, and expose the opponent to the SIMPTOMS **[Affliction]**.'),
('actCompetent', 'ACT COMPETENT', 'HEART', 'HEART', '[Aspect][Advanced][Free][One-Off][Locked: Heart]', 'You know to put your interests and your identity aside when you need to so you can focus your whole self on completing the task at hand. At the start of an encounter, you can shuffle your **[Talents]** to different stats.'),
('actionsHaveConsequences', 'ACTIONS HAVE CONSEQUENCES', 'HOPE', 'HOPE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Hope]', 'You’re done pretending that those you believe in are infallible. Your friends, while still your friends, are capable of making mistakes— and pretending they can’t just makes things worse! When you want to take an action and tell someone that what they’re doing is wrong, roll **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: N-now, wait just a moment, buster! You- you, ah… well… keep up the good work! Oh, no, what did you just say!? You encouraged them! The target gains **3 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You stumble over your words awkwardly, and get nowhere. Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Hold up, buster! What are you thinking, you scallywag? You spout some stuff at them, and it makes them hesitate— but more out of confusion than guilt. The target takes **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You tell your target that what they’re doing isn’t right. Their **[Boost]** is reset to 0; if they had no **[Boost]**, they instead gain **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You rail a litany of truths against your target, breaking down why what they just did was totally wrong— and your target can’t help but listen, transfixed to the spot as if through some supernatural force. Any **[Boost]** the target has is turned to **[Drag]** immediately, and they gain the **[Dread]** condition as guilt weighs them down. If they had no **[Boost]**, they instead gain **3 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You unravel the fundamentals of truth and goodness to your target, and they experience the true consequences of their actions as they peer into the infinite deluge of hope that is your heart. Your target gains the effects of a **GREAT**, but takes the **[Despair]** condition and **2 [Non-Lethal]** damage.'),
('actUnprofessional', 'ACT UNPROFESSIONAL', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'You’ve been forced to be this perfect, reserved and intelligent person since you were a wriggler. But you’ve made friends, you’ve talked, and you’ve learned… you’re tired of fitting in! You wanna go WILD sometimes! And sometimes, you do! You gain the following **GOOD** SWASHBUCKLE effects.\r\n\r\n> **DO SOMETHING IRRESPONSIBLE**: This is definitely a terrible idea. Your next move is **[Tiered Up]**, even to a **MAX**, but you take **2 [Somatic]** damage. This stacks with other **[Tier Up]** effects, but increases the damage by 2.\r\n\r\n> **KNOCK SHIT OVER**: WHAM! Whether it’s an act of defiance or vandalistic celebration of a success, it’s REALLY satisfying to kick shit to the floor and make a mess! Opponents **[Flourish]** rolls next turn are **[Inept]**, on account of you making a mess everywhere.\r\n\r\n> **TAKE SHIRT OR COAT OFF AND WHIP IT AROUND OVER YOUR HEAD GOING “WHOOOO!” BEFORE CAREFULLY PUTTING IT BACK ON**: Yeah! Your **[Boost]** isn’t reduced by **[Drag]** for **2 turns**, instead being stored separately. If you don’t use the **[Boost]** before the end of the 2 turns, they combine. \r\n\r\n> **DON’T INTERVENE**: Smugly, silently, you make a note of how you AREN’T going full teal on stupid illegal shit around you. You let someone else pick a SWASHBUCKLE effect equivalent to what you have rolled, as you don’t intervene with their dumbassery.'),
('aCurseUponYourHive', 'A CURSE UPON YOUR HIVE', 'DOOM', 'DOOM', '[Aspect][Basic][Reaction][Locked: Doom]', 'Your resentful words stick with people after they best you. Surely you didn’t mean what you said at the end of the fight, right? Surely you didn’t mean it when you said bad things were coming? Surely. When you’re knocked out, you get a **[Free]** **[Reaction]** to babble out some bitter promises about how bad things are coming to your opponent before going down. Whether it’s your opponent low-key panicking and obsessing about what you said, or it’s an actual fucking hex you cast upon them, they have trouble with their **[Downtime]** activities. Their next general **[Downtime]** roll is **[Godawful]**, or their next purchase costs **1 extra LUX**.'),
('adaptableAssessment', 'ADAPTABLE ASSESSMENT', 'BREATH', 'BREATH', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Breath]', 'You have to accept it: life isn’t always perfect! And you can’t always just expect to be able to outrun your problems. Sometimes, you need to stand your ground and face them, instead of just turning a blind eye to everything going on around you. When that moment comes, you need to be prepared for anything! At the start of an encounter, you can spend an action to switch which stats are rolled for any non-GRIEF and non-SHENANIGANS Universal Moves.'),
('adaptableGrowth', 'ADAPTABLE GROWTH', 'OTHER', 'HEIR', '[Class][Advanced][One-Off][Locked: Heir]', 'It’s so easy to get comfortable. Your aspect and routines are so familiar and so second-hand that branching out never made sense. But if you never expand your horizons, how will you ever grow? When you enter an encounter, you can choose to rearrange your stats, **[Talents]**, and **[Ineptitudes]** however you like. You cannot switch what HERO MODES you have access to.'),
('administrate', 'ADMINISTRATE', 'OTHER', 'TEAM_STRIFE', '[Team Strife][Analyze]', 'Hey, STRUGGLER! Watch out! You make a PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll, but rather than keep the roll results to yourself, you give them to your allied STRUGGLER. Of course. '),
('adoringFans', 'ADORING FANS', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Recharge: 2][Flourish][Locked: Celebrity]', 'They like you! They really like you! In the eyes of your loyal fan base, you can do no wrong. And everything you do is to impress them, isn\'t it? You gain a POSSE, a gang of superfans who are always ready to kiss the ground you walk on, and will cheer for you in encounters! If your POSSE is not with you when you enter an encounter, never fear- sending out a quick Chittr post with your location as a **[Free]** **[Tech]** activity summons them immediately! When you want to put your fanbase to action, roll **+PLC**. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: CANCELLED. What?! I can’t believe my favourite celeb would DO this! Your fans scatter, rendering you unable to use this move again for the rest of the encounter, and you become **[Agitated]** as you have to start thinking about your apology video.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: The Posse doesn’t respond. You didn’t throw in enough hashtags or catchphrases to alert them you needed them, or something?\r\n\r\n**OK**: These useless numbnuts don’t do anything, but they cheer for you, and it makes you feel nice. You receive **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD: A few brave Posse members do exactly as you wanted! Choose one of the following effects**:\r\n\r\n> **CHEER**: You gain **2 [Boost]** as they shout your name. You get +1 POP any time you gain POPS for the next **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **JEER**: Your fans start shouting insults at your opponent, which makes YOU feel good. You lose -2 POPS (min. 0) any time you lose POPS for **1 turn**.\r\n\r\n> **DONATE**: Your fans throw you helpful items for you to use! You buy an item on the fly.\r\n\r\n> **BRING SNACKS**: Much munch munch… Thank you, my minions! You **[Heal] 1 HP**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Damn! Doting doesn\'t even begin to cover how much they love you! You get a **GOOD**, and **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You are a god to these people, and they worship you as one. Heaven is fame, and you are FAMOUS. You get a **GOOD**, and **3 [Boost]**.'),
('advancedHemoandrogyny', 'ADVANCED HEMOANDROGYNY', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Full-Time]', 'That’s right, baby! It’s even harder to tell what caste you are now! This move functions almost identically to HEMOANDROGYNY, except instead of taking **[Open]** moves, you may now take non-**[Psionic]**, non-**[Locked] [Advanced]** moves! How about that? You can take this move 4 times in total, the same as **HEMOANDROGYNY**.\r\n'),
('aesopSays', 'AESOP SAYS', 'OTHER', 'DECOMPOSITIONIST', '[Template][Basic][Recharge: 3][Heal][Locked: Decompositonist]', 'There\'s no such thing as a unified Decompositonist doctrine. No holy book to turn to, no vast library of the history of your faith. It has long been destroyed, or simply never made. The Empire has assured that with all their might. But through determination and refusal to let the world grind you down, your fellows have spread the legends and tales that inspire the flock through word of mouth, teacher to student. You can continue that cycle now, and share a tale of a troll long dead; caste indeterminate yet relatable to all warm hues. Roll **+PLC** to share a story.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: This.. oh, that\'s not the right story. That\'s the one that the rat Troll Juudas inserted into the storyfold on behalf of the Empire! Woe, you\'re a fool! You and your target both experience **[Dread]** as a faux-story of the Empire\'s inevitable victory shakes the both of you.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: They\'re not listening. You\'re being too cryptic. Talk like a normal person, you\'re like eighteen. Not a sixty year old preacher. You take **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: So.. is that like, about a helmstroll? Or a rust? It kind of sounds like it could be either-- that\'s not the point! That\'s not the point! Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Ah, so it\'s not about a specific caste but about the overall message that we are all diverse and different in how the world brings us harm, but that harm is what unites us as those who are stepped upon! A helmstroll and a red shirtmunition aren\'t that different after all! Your target **[Heals] 1 HP**!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: They\'re truly inspired by your story, and it\'s able to do a great deal to pick their spirits up. They heal **2 HP**, or **1 HP** and dispel a HAUNTING **[Affliction]** as you speak to the specters, urging them to do better and pass on. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: It\'s a true awakening! You knew that studying these stories would pay off! Your target heals **2 HP**, or **1 HP** and dispels a HAUNTING **[Affliction]** in addition to becoming **[Hopeful]** if they are a Lowblood or Mutant, or **[Insightful]** if they are a Midblood or higher.\r\n\r\n'),
('affright', 'AFFRIGHT', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Recharge: 2][Chicanery][Locked: Subjugglator]', 'You LOOOOOVE fear. It’s the best. It means people respect you, and don’t wanna mess with you. As such, you choose to scare the bulge off people before beating them to a pulp, just as a fun little ego trip. When you want to pull out some slasher tropes, roll **+GRT**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: YOU SLIP ON A BANANA PEEL! How’d this get here!? You’re **[Floorbound]** :o( If the target was **[Scared]** or **[Terrified]**, they are no longer. If you were **[Hidden]**, you are no longer.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Aw, nuts, you didn’t react fast enough! You don’t manage to pull anything off. \r\n\r\n**OK**: At the very least, you scare them! The target takes **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You fucking Get them. You GET them! Choose one of the effects from the list below.\r\n\r\n> **POUNCE**: You jump out of nowhere, shake \'em around and chomp your teeth, scaring them half to death! The target takes **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> **PHONECALL**: Hello, Enpece. Ya like scary movies? The target’s phone rings, removing the **[Hidden]** condition from them.\r\n\r\n> **MENACING LAUGH**: Aw, jeez, that’s the worst sound you could make! The target becomes **[Distracted]**!\r\n\r\n> **GRABBED**: GOTCHA! AHAHAHAH! Your target is **[Trapped]**!\r\n\r\n> **PULLED AWAY**: YANK! You grab a target, pulling them out of sight. You and the target both become **[Hidden]** to other trolls, but not to each other.\r\n\r\n> **HERO DEATH SCENE**: You should know better than to act tough to a slasher villain, that’s always when they get you! You immediately remove **[Brave]** or **[Heroic]** from a target, and they gain **1 or 2 [Drag]** accordingly.\r\n\r\n> **INSTA-KILL**: You automatically kill an NPC troll. This troll must be made of flesh and blood, not some kinda robot or whatever, and can’t hold special importance to the Clouder’s plot. Don’t one-shot the heiress, douchebag, kill a random side character or something!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Absolutely fucking horrifying. You get a **GOOD**, and give all enemy witnesses **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: **GREAT** GOOGLY MOOGLY, THIS IS A NIGHTMARE! You get a **GOOD**, and all enemy witnesses gain **3 [Drag]**.'),
('aFineEar', 'A FINE EAR', 'OTHER', 'MUSICREANT', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Musicreant]', 'You\'re fine tuned to hear a needle drop, and the perfect musical note! Also, you play so loud you\'ve done permanent damage to your ears anyway. Oops! You can become **[Permadeaf]** forever, though you still hear; you\'re just able to avoid sounds you don\'t wanna deal with pretty easily. You can’t hear them! You’ve been wearing airpods too often!'),
('aGameOfChance', 'A GAME OF CHANCE', 'OTHER', 'BARD', '[Class][Basic][Free][Magic][Locked: Bard]', 'Ah, why not even the playing fields a little, friend? You clearly are so much more skilled than I, and yet… perhaps luck shall be the victor of our fun? ;) At the top of each round, you can choose to suppress the innate skills of all those around you, forgoing rolling all moves with any **[Talents]** or stats, rolling flat 2d8 dice for any rolled move. If you choose to do so, your opponents are also forced to forfeit their bonuses and roll flat with you. You can’t pull this shit and not do any rolled moves yourself though, because then you’d be a dirty cheating fun wrecker and everyone in the encounter aside from you would become **[Enraged]** for one round and forced to target you with their next **[Strife]**. SHUT THE FUCK UP ABOUT WHIMSICAL GAMES OF CHANCE AND LET ME KILL YOU.\r\n\r\n'),
('aggravatedBureaucracy', 'AGGRAVATED BUREAUCRACY', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Passive][Recharge: 3][Locked: Penpusher]', 'Oh, so they want to get an EFFECT on you? Weeeeeell… I mean, okay, first you need to notify your intent to the admin, obviously, they\'re on the second floor, they\'ll get you a right of effect thing. Oh, but you\'ll need to get an appointment, that\'s secretary block b on floor seven, but if she\'s out she might be on floor six. To get to floor six, you need to solve The Ogres Riddle on floor four, which you need to discuss with admin first— why are you crying? Every time an opponent makes a roll against you, roll 1d8. On a 1, their move becomes **[Lengthy]** as their mind becomes obscured by stupid amounts of beautacratic procedurals that the mechanics of the game itself start yammering at them. Imagine the Strife HUD got all clogged up by it. They can force the move to not be **[Lengthy]**, but this makes them **[Stressed]**, which may stack into **[Agitated]**.'),
('aggressiveAttitude', 'AGGRESSIVE ATTITUDE', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Delinquent]', 'You\'re quick to anger, but you aren\'t a rampaging monster or anything! You just like causing trouble, breaking shit, whatever. As such, when you would go **[Out-Of-Control]**, you can instead choose to become **[Aggravated]**.\r\n\r\n**AGGRAVATED**\r\n[Heightened][Opposite: Hyperfocused]\r\n\r\nHey, hey, hey, HEY! What\'s the big idea? An emotion where you just feel insenced to teach a lil twerp a lesson!! An emotion where your **[Strife]** rolls have a **+1 [Buff]**, and you can make **[Talented]** JAB rolls even after a fight has broken out. You do +1 damage to items, vehicles, machines and trolls with positive **[Emotions]** while Aggravated. You cannot become **[Out-Of-Control]** or **[Tired]** while Aggravated. If a trigger would render you **[Enraged]** while you are Aggravated, you gain **1 [WHAM]**.'),
('aha', 'AHA', 'BREATH', 'BREATH', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Breath]', 'Your forward thinking can really surprise people sometimes! Who knew you had such amazing insight into the problems around you, huh? When you assess a situation with PROBLEM SLEUTHING, you can gain insight into something that nobody has noticed yet; decide what nobody has realized yet, and say that it’s there. Hey, maybe there’s a piece of rope nearby that would help you swing from point A to point B! Maybe there’s a weak point in what you’re looking at! You can forgo rolling your next roll after PROBLEM SLEUTHING, instead getting the same roll result on a different move as you incorporate what you’ve noticed into your actions (like punching the weak point with a GRIEF, or tying someone with the rope with SHENANIGANS).'),
('aHamperingHand', 'A HAMPERING HAND', 'OTHER', 'MAID', '[Class][Advanced][Buildup: 3][One-Off][Locked: Maid]', 'Sometimes, the best way to help someone else is to get in the way of the people trying to do them harm! Perhaps you\'re even just doing this to help yourself if you\'re feeling particularly bold! As an action, you can decide to hamper your enemies by choosing to completely reset up to 3 of their **[Buildup]** or **[Recharge]** moves or effects, forcing them to wait longer to use them! They\'re going to need a minute to recover from that one.'),
('aHexOnYou', 'A HEX ON YOU!', 'OTHER', 'WITCH', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Witch]', 'Alright! Let’s get up to some mischief! Ehehehe~ More than anyone, you know how to cause a scene and disrupt anyone trying to hold you back. Because you’re the best, you become **[Talented]** at the **UNIVERSAL MOVE SHENANIGANS** if you weren’t already. Additionally, you gain the following **SHENANIGANS** effects:\r\n\r\n> **OOGAH BOOGAH**: You screech right in the opponent’s face! They become **[Scared]**!\r\n\r\n> **KA-POW**: ABRACADABRA THIS, BITCH! You deal 1 **[Somatic]** damage as you manage to get the enemy off guard with a sucker punch!\r\n\r\n> **HOCUS POCUS**: You distract your opponent with a movement that leads to nowhere in particular, taking away their ability to use any **[Reaction]** for 1 round!\r\n\r\n> **RIDDLE ME THIS**: You speak in riddles, say something cryptic or just down right fucking stupid. The opponent becomes **[Confused]**.\r\n'),
('aieeeee', 'AIEEEEE!!', 'OTHER', 'TEAM_STRIFE', '[Team Strife][Physical]', 'NOOOOOO! YOU DON’T WANNA BE A STRUGGLER! PLEEEEASE! If you are hit by an APPREHEND roll, you can roll LET’S STRIFE to ABSCOND and get the fuck outta there! PLEAAAASE LET YOU GO!\r\n'),
('aJobToDo', 'A JOB TO DO', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Being from a caste notorious for being all work, no play, your caste gets saddled with jobs pretty early on in life. Pick an option from the list below representing what it is you work at most often…\r\n\r\n> **Engineering**: You\'re the type of troll that works with anything with an engine, wires, or similar. You can buy items for **1 VP** less (min. 1).\r\n\r\n> **Construction**: You work on building buildings, baby! HIVECRAFTING UPGRADES cost **1 LUX** less than normal.\r\n\r\n> **Farming**: You work with animals all the time; you\'re a natural. Lusii cannot make you use **[Drag]** in a fight.\r\n\r\n> **Smithing**: The heat of the forge and the clang of hammers keep you schmovin\'! When you buy an item, you can choose to give it **2 HP** more than normal in exchange for raising its price by **1 VP**.\r\n\r\n> **Resource Gatherer**: Whether you\'re a miner, a lumberjack, or a fisherman, you pick up items from nature and bring them home to make shit with. You gain access to a biome through the Olive Nyanarchist HERMIT WISDOM move. You may only select WOODLANDS, MOUNTAINS, SWAMP, or DEEPSEA (though that\'s more river or lake-themed!).\r\n\r\n> **Banditry**: YOU FIEND! YOU\'RE A CRIMINAL! THAT\'S NOT A JOB AT ALL! You steal stuff, smuggle lusii, and make everyone around you feel a little less safe. Such is the way of the bandit! If you defeat someone in combat, you can take an item from their Sylladex; it costs half as much **VP** as normal for you. You can also choose to take up to **Treasure II** or **3 LUX**.\r\n\r\n> **Entertainment**: Huh..? You don\'t do much manual work. You tell stories, make art, and do beautiful things. Not typical, but… it is nice. You can make ART with **2 VP** mid-encounter; this **[Consumable]** item/effect gives you or an ally the **[Hopeful]** condition. This can be anything from poetry to food to a sweet dance!\r\n\r\n> **Some Other Bullshit**: What do you MEAN you\'ve got a job not listed? Other Bronzes are gonna look at you funny now! You take an effect from this list, but your job is different from what\'s listed.'),
('alchemicalDabbling', 'ALCHEMICAL DABBLING', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Esotericist]', 'Now THESE are potions! You’ve taken to brewing up concoctions with strange herbs, powdered phantoms and other bizarre ingredients. You gain access to the following unique items, each of which cost **2 VP** (it costs money to collect the stuff needed for it, okay?)\r\n\r\n> **HEALING ELIXIR**: That’s better! You regain **1 HP** and gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n> **MINDSPAN BREW**: Expand your mental powers significantly! For **2 turns**, all **[Mental]** rolls you make are **[Tiered Up]**, but all **[Physical]** are **[Tiered Down]**.\r\n> **PHILTER OF VISION**: Your eyes suddenly glow like a lamp! All **[Hidden]** trolls in the encounter are revealed as you see through walls.\r\n> **HEARTSPIN TONIC**: Turn that frown upside down! Take **1 [Drag]** and swap your emotion for its opposite.\r\n> **QUICKSTEP ICHOR**: You become **[Quickened]** for **2 turns**, and **[Slowed]** for **1 turn** afterwards.\r\n> **JUICE THAT MAKES YOU EXPLODE**: If you willingly and consciously drink this, you take **5 [Somatic]** damage.'),
('alienExpert', 'ALIEN EXPERT', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Passive]', 'Aha! Alien culture, figured out! You’ve watched a tonne of movies, you’ve read their manga, you’ve maybe even made out with a few? The point is, you definitely get this whole alien thing now! Select an aspect of Alternia\'s culture from the list below. When you witness it in an encounter for the first time, you immediately become **[Enthusiastic]**.\r\n\r\n> Psionics\r\n> Quadrants\r\n> Lusii\r\n> Magic\r\n> Cullbait\r\n> A particular Caste Culture\r\n\r\n'),
('allAccordingToKeikaku', 'ALL ACCORDING TO KEIKAKU', 'OTHER', 'MAGE', '[Class][Advanced][Recharge: 5][Magic][Mental][Locked: Mage]', 'You’ve opened up your mind to differing world views after so long of being stubborn… And you’ve begun to notice some things. Namely that a lot of people are pretty set in their ways too!\r\nYou watch the same patterns repeat again and again - everything spirals into predictability as the natural order carries on. People are more guaranteed to do things than one might think, and you can definitely use that to your advantage! When you want to peer into the future, roll **+PLC, +HUB**, or **+PSP**. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: They did it. They broke the cycle? How? Not only can your opponent do as they please, but they gain one **[Free]** reroll on a roll they aren\'t happy with next turn as they change their fate. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: They don\'t do what they\'re supposed to. What? You get 1 **[Drag]** for each different move your opponent uses over the next two rounds. \r\n\r\n**OK**: The world carries on, occasionally surprising you. Your opponent acts as normal. \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Fate is set; your opponent must declare what move they will use first next turn, and cannot deviate from this stated intent no matter what. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Your opponent declares all moves next round now, and cannot change them no matter what you do. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: Your opponent declares every move they will use for the next two rounds right now, chaining themselves to the wheel of fate alongside you. They must roll each move in order, no matter the outcome.\r\n'),
('allFiguredOut', 'ALL FIGURED OUT', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'You\'ve got a good thing going for you! You do good at what you do, you have friends and money… those repressed feelings you were hiding, doubts and bitterness and whatever, they aren\'t stopping you. You\'re doing pretty good, despite everything! Whenever you use **[Boost]**, you get a free **+1 [Buff]** to your roll too.'),
('allOutAttack', 'ALL OUT ATTACK', 'OTHER', 'ROGUE', '[Class][Advanced][One-off][Locked: Rogue]', 'What would a master rogue be without their criminal compatriots!? You’ve done so much for your friends, as they mean the world to you. It is because of your dedication and kindness that people are ready to have your back at a moment\'s notice. You’ve given so much boss, let us take it from here! When an enemy is below half **HP** and has accumulated 8 **[Drag]**, you may spend an action on your turn to call for an ALL-OUT ATTACK. Allies can then spend a **[Reaction]** to attack the enemy on your turn instead of their own, as you all dogpile the poor bastard. FINISH ‘EM!'),
('allTheDice', 'ALL THE DICE', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Magic][Passive][Locked: Metagamer]', 'All of them. Most trolls have about the same chances of success as you, to your knowledge. That\'s because all rolls use 2d8, or if you\'re pretty good at what you do, 3d8. But what if there was another way? You will the hands that guide you beyond the Fourth Wall into rolling a different way. You can choose the following replacements for dice rolls. Each replacement has an individual **[Recharge: 2]** for its use - try out new ways of bending the rules, or just go back to the tried-and-true 2d8 for a bit!\r\n\r\n\r\n**4d4**: If you want to play it safe, roll 4d4. You\'re likely to get an average result, but not a great one either. Wonderful for when you don\'t want to take risks! If you\'re using a **[Talented]** roll, roll 6d4 and discard the lowest 2 dice. You get a **MIN** on a 4 or lower.\r\n\r\n**1d16**: Bet you don\'t own any of these IRL! Roll a sweet, juicy hexadecagon dice when you wanna play it risky. You\'re more likely to roll a **MAX**, but also more likely to roll a **MIN**! If you\'re rolling **[Talented]**, just roll twice and take the higher number.\r\n\r\n**1d6+1d10**: Not… entirely sure how this affects your probability I\'ll be frank. I imagine it\'s basically the same? Why don\'t you test it out and see, sport? If you\'re rolling **[Talented]**, just, uh… gosh. Roll the d10 twice, take the higher number? I suppose?\r\n\r\n**8d2**: Stop it!!! This isn\'t practical! You\'re just getting an extremely middle of the road result! You\'re flipping coins!!! This roll is always a flat 8d2, ignoring any **[Talents]** and stats that would otherwise apply to it. More dice doesn\'t make you stronger! You get a MIN on a 9 or lower, a BAD on a 10, and an OK on an 11.'),
('allTheIronsInTheFire', 'ALL THE IRONS IN THE FIRE', 'LIGHT', 'LIGHT', '[Aspect][Advanced][One-Off][Locked: Light]', 'You’ve come to realize that being vindictive isn’t going to make you any more important and relevant; it’s just going to make you look like a bluh bluh huge bitch. Your success does not need to stem from the failures of others. Instead, it can stem from your own successes. You can use the reroll bonus from ALL THE LUCK to reroll one of your own rolls, taking the better ones, instead of putting down an opponent’s roll. You must have ALL THE LUCK before taking this move.'),
('allTheLuck', 'ALL THE LUCK', 'LIGHT', 'LIGHT', '[Aspect][Basic][One-Off][Locked: Light]', 'Let’s face it: life wants you to win, and it tends to prefer other people not get in your way. So suck it, bulgebreath, roll that again! Once per encounter, you can force someone to reroll a roll they just made, and go with the lower result. Seems you just weren’t meant to be the victor!\n\n'),
('allTheWorldsACircus', 'ALL THE WORLD\'S A CIRCUS', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Passive][Locked: Circusfolk]', 'And all the trolls it\'s silly clowns :o) Though the Infinite Performances of the Carnival District don\'t ever rest, smaller circuses break up their shows into four acts; and you prepare all your skirmishes just the same! You get the following effects depending on your HP.\r\n\r\n> **FULL HP**: The Opening Act! Gotta make the start count! You have a **+1 [Buff]** to all rolls!\r\n\r\n> **ABOVE HALF HP**: The Build-Up! The hype is building… gotta keep it this way! You gain **1 [Boost]** every turn!\r\n\r\n> **HALF HP OR LOWER**: The Star Performance! Everyone\'s looking for a REAL treat now! You can use **3 [Boost]** to **[Tier Up]** a roll!\r\n\r\n> **3 HP OR LOWER**: The Grand Finale! It all ends here! You can use 3 **[Boost]** to **[Tier Up]**, even to a **MAX**! This is a **[One-Off]** effect.'),
('aloofOutlook', 'ALOOF OUTLOOK', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Passive][Locked: Cool Kid]', 'Huh? Oh, yeah. That didn’t bother you. You’re good. You’re unbothered, really. Nothing slows you down. Hurt feelings? Pssht. That sounds like something for UNCOOL kids. And I believe I’ve made it very clear that that’s something you’re NOT. Uncool, that is. Whenever you would take an Emotional effect, you can instead choose to take **2 [Drag]** in its place.'),
('aLookBeneathTheMask', 'A LOOK BENEATH THE MASK', 'HEART', 'HEART', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Heart]', 'You don’t need to always put on your act around everyone. People won’t think of you as lesser, or strange, or annoying- you’re still you, mask on or mask off. You can choose another **[Talent]** based on aspects of yourself you don’t show to the world; if you were some kinda Troll Carl Jung fangirl, you’d say that you’re peeling away the Persona (the part of your of your personality you show the world) and glimpsing at the Shadow (the parts of yourself you deny to the world). You can’t use this to boost stats you’re already **[Talented]** in. Upon taking this move, you lose 1 more stat point permanently.'),
('altercate', 'ALTERCATE', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Physical][Strife][Locked: Protagonist]', 'When you fight, it\'s like you\'re meant to win. Or maybe you\'re meant to lose? It doesn\'t really matter— the outcome of your actions are meant to be, and you just bring them forth. Which is a long way of saying \"let\'s fight.\" When you want to bring justice, roll **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: NghHHRGH- a twist in your tale! The Narrative surprises you with a low point. Is your tale one of those where the supposed hero dies? You lose the ability to use ALTERCATE for the rest of the encounter, and take **2 [Psychic]** damage that ignores **[Resistance]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Another challenge for the road, it seems. You take **1 [Psychic]** damage that ignores **[Resistance]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: A near miss… but this is where the tale starts to turn your way, you know it! You gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: A solid hit! You do **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: A DIRECT one! Take that! You do **2 [Somatic]** damage, or do **1 [Somatic]** damage and gain **2 [Boost]**\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Your sword cleaves through tales, bringing you to stand among heroes of old! You do **3 damage** of any type you choose, and gain **3 [Boost]**.'),
('alternatePath', 'ALTERNATE PATH', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive]', 'Sometimes, you dream differently than the rest of your caste. Maybe you just want to be different from the others. Maybe you\'re an Olive who really likes gaming. Maybe you\'re a Cerulean who wants nothing more than a little business downtown. With enough effort, some trolls break the mold and try things that are not typical to their regular caste. You can only take this move at level 1. When you take this move, you don\'t gain the **[Unlock]** to a tree from your caste. Instead, you gain the **[Unlock]** to a tree from the list below, which you take now for free. You gain all effects from the move, and have access to the tree as normal. However, you cannot gain more than 5 **[Advanced]** moves from your Caste. You can select from the following options.\n\n> **RUST**: Dungeoneer, Gutterblood (Only for Lime and below), Worker\n> **BRONZE**: Folklorist (Only for Lime and below), Junker, Labourer, Vagabond\n> **GOLD**: Beekeeper, Cyberpunk, Streamer\n> **OLIVE**: Fanyatic, Meowchant, Nyanjutsu, Nyastrologist\n> **JADE**: Slayer, Subcultist\n> **TEAL**: Legislacerator (Only for Cerulean and up), Scienceling\n> **CERULEAN**: Delinquent, Espiacrooner\n> **INDIGO**: Inventor, Jock\n> **PURPLE**: Esoterist\n> **VIOLET**: Celebrity (Only for Teal and up)\n\nIn certain cases, you may be able to altpath into trees not on this list, provided the flavor makes reasonable sense for your character and does not conflict with established lore. For example, while teaching is a caste-restricted career on Alternia, a human character could reasonably be a teacher and take the Auxiliatrice tree. Always provide justification for your choice and gain permission from your Clouder (or from moderators on Serverstuck during character approval) if you plan to altpath into a tree not on the above list. Some trees are never altpathable, such as **[Psionic]** trees, Lime trees, Kid trees and trees that rely on caste-specific customs and spiritualities.'),
('alternateUniverse', 'ALTERNATE UNIVERSE', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Passive][Cullbait][Unlock: AU]', 'The concept of the multiverse is a constant in storytelling. Narrative paths that could have been, how things would unfold under different historical contexts, what if everyone was a pony… well, the thing is, you are a Lime who walks between this universe and the next, subtly altering our world to rhyme with that one! Or something close to it at least. While you are not truly from another world and cannot escape from the one you\'re in now, you still can draw upon the idea of such settings to make this one a little more fun. Select one of the following choices; you get the associated **[Talent]**, and always have the listed **[Emotion]**. This **[Emotion]** is on top of the normal limit of **3 [Emotions]**, and you\'re immune to the **[Emotion]**’s opposite.\r\n\r\n> **Crack (+RAS)**: You\'re from an AU that\'s maybe a little silly. Ponystuck, Buffstuck, Everyone\'s-Gamzeestuck, you know the type of AU. You are always **[Enthusiastic]**.\r\n\r\n> **Slice of Life (+PLC)**: You exude an aura of comfort and calm; a world without strife. Maybe you have a coffee shop, or maybe you\'re just on your way to your highschool class, but you are always **[Happy]**.\r\n\r\n> **Musical (+GRA)**: You know when people just burst into musical numbers in movies and everyone\'s kinda just okay with that? Yeah, you\'re… you\'re that. Music spontaneously plays, people spontaneously join in, all that good stuff. You are always **[Smug]**.\r\n\r\n> **Gritty (+APP)**: The real world is a piece of cake compared to the nightmare world you come from. Zombie apocalypses, cannibal bakeries, all that trauma… that EVIL… hnnmrhhh… yes, you\'d like a bagel… you are always **[Serious]**.\r\n\r\n> **Feral (+GRT)**: You\'ve got a particularly visible AU affecting you— you\'re  ALL some kind of weird, animalistic troll! Tails, fur, fangs, whatever. You are always **[Enraged]**.\r\n\r\n> **Fantasy (+HUB)**: Hark! An interloper! You come from a Snazzard slaying world of magic and swords. Whether you\'re a mighty knight, a cunning thief or a powerful wizard, you are always **[Brave]**.\r\n\r\n> **Historical (+PSP)**: The world alters to look like a different era around you. Maybe you\'re greyscale with a laughtrack like a 1950s sitcom, or maybe you see things from the point of view of a steampunk engineer. You are always **[Insightful]**.\r\n\r\n> **Fandom (+IMG)**: No way! You look like the troll version of a popular fandom! Culllock Holmes, Doctor Goo, Supernormal… you don\'t represent a character so much as you represent the fandom as a whole. You are always **[Hopeful]**.'),
('alternianCockroach', 'ALTERNIAN COCKROACH', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Gutterblood]', 'Okay, yeah, you\'re basically invincible. How. HOW ARE YOU STILL ALIVE? You\'re meant to be the easiest to kill! The bottom of the bottom! STOP EATING MY SHOE!! Your will to survive combined with your unfathomable resistances has made you practically untouchable. You gain access to HERO MODE through your AWESOME APPETITE. Nothing ever negatively affects your **[Healing]**, whether through **[Ineptitude]**, **[Tier Downs]**, **[Nerfs]** or effects that reduce how much healing you do, though **[Bloodied]** still healblocks you. You\'ve figured out the best spots to find rich trash, and can now access **Rich** items with SLUMBLOOD. Somehow. Finally, you\'re kind of… radioactive? Probably all that nuclear waste you\'ve eaten in the past. Any time someone hits you with a **[Physical]** **[Strife]** roll, the target is exposed to the RADIATION POISONING **[Affliction]**. The target only hits the effects of Stage 3 if they knock themselves to **0 HP** through their own attacks. That was dumb.'),
('alternianGothic', 'ALTERNIAN GOTHIC', 'OTHER', 'ABOMINARTIST', '[Template][Basic][Free][One-Off][Locked: Abominartist]', 'Oh… woe is me… I am but a miserable little artist in the world that is Alternia… sniffle, sniffle. The first time you roll a **BAD** on any move, you can also take the **GOOD** result… along with **1 [Drag]**. Even if it hurts, you’ve learned to make the best of your failure… or something… \\*wipes away a tear\\* \\*emo\\*'),
('alterniasMostWanted', 'ALTERNIA’S MOST WANTED', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Vagabond]', 'You\'ve robbed allowance dispensaries. You\'ve wrangled snazzards. You\'ve had capers that have brought you within an inch of your demise, only for you to give a charming wink and make the comeback of the century. Technically, you should be cullbait by now… but the empire is too goddamn scared of you to have you executed. These are the kind of things people say about you, and who can blame them? You\'re basically a legend at this point. You gain access to HERO MODE through your RESPLENDENT RASCALITY. And you know what? You carry SO MANY GODDAMN GUNS. At the start of your turn, you can swap the firearm modification you have from DREAM-CHASING DRIFTER as a **[Free]** action as you pull more and more guns from your belt. All damage you do with your firearms is **[Unblockable]** as you shoot RIGHT in the weak points. Whenever you gain **[WHAM]**, you only lose 1 when you are damaged, rather than all of it. Pew pew!'),
('altricialize', 'ALTRICIALIZE', 'OTHER', 'CUSTODIANS', '[Recharge: 3]', 'You call out for your custodian, begging them to come to your aid! If your **CUSTODIAN** was not present, they appear, and do as you command. Maybe. Each individual Feature is a **[One-Off]**. When you want to get your **CUSTODIAN** to help, roll **+PLC**.\n> **MIN**: Your **CUSTODIAN**… makes life worse for you! What an unexpected twist! Your guardian being subpar?! My god! Your **CUSTODIAN** uses their Feature on you, or on an enemy if it was a beneficial one. Thanks a lot, MOM.\n> **BAD**: GET OFF YOUR ASS AND HELP ME! The **CUSTODIAN** just fucking sits there, or does something irrelevant.\n> **OK**: While they don\'t help very well, their reassuring growls and snarls are slightly comforting. You get **1 [Boost]**.\n> **GOOD**: GET THEM, DAD! Your **CUSTODIAN** uses one of their Features to aid you! The feature will usually have a set of results separated by slashes; you use the first result.\n> **GREAT**: God, your giant lobster is so cool. Your **CUSTODIAN** uses one of their Features, with the second result listed.\n> **MAX**: CUSTODIAN… YOU REALLY CARE THAT MUCH? Your **CUSTODIAN** uses one of their Features, with the final result listed.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('andWereLive', 'AND WE\'RE LIVE', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Mental][Tech][Locked: Streamer] \r\n', 'You\'re building up quite the audience here! Even your most hardened of enemies can\'t help but feel a little excited to know that there are thousands of eyes watching you all. Subconsciously, everyone around you wants to put on one hell of a show! Of course, less scrupulous streamers may simply just want to use other people\'s presence to scum views off them for their own benefit, myeh heh heh. As a **[Free]** action you can declare that WE\'RE LIVE!, and all of social media can see what\'s going on. Consider dropping a ping on Chittr and let people know where they can watch this encounter! While live, all **[Boost]** and **[Drag]** from all participants in an encounter are pooled together— even your enemies! You can use the **[Boost]** your enemies or allies generate yourself, or allow your allies to buff themselves— but watch out, fame can get to the heads of your enemies, too! If an enemy uses **[Boost]**, you gain a number of **[WHAM]** equal to a third of the **[Boost]** used, rounded up, minimum 1. Obviously, as a **[Mental]** effect, this doesn\'t apply to most lusii.'),
('andWhatDoYouDoYouStartMonologuing', 'AND WHAT DO YOU DO? YOU START MONOLOGUING!', 'OTHER', 'PRINCE', '[Class][Advanced][Buildup: 4][One-off][Locked: Prince]', 'Oh, for fuck’s sake. All your teammates have gotten tuckered out already? Enpece doesn’t want to move because he’ll have that status effect for HOW many turns!? UGGHH! Fine, you’ll save this like you always do. AHEM… SHUT UP, stop everything, I am TALKING and you will LISTEN, you curr. How DARE you. You think your little plans will stop me? ME? I am like a god compared to you, your piddly little attacks mean nothing and your cause is weak- \r\n\r\nOnce per fight, at an appropriately dramatic or inopportune moment, you may force the fight to halt as you begin monologuing. No one including yourself may make any moves, actions, or reactions for an entire round as you buy some time by cranking the cartoon villain act up to eleven. Damage over time effects like [Ablaze] apply damage as normal. Moves that activate every X amount of turns are still activated. **[Stunned]** and **[Quickened]** still wear off. The fight is still happening, you\'re just... talking. Please shut up.'),
('aNewOutlook', 'A NEW OUTLOOK', 'SPACE', 'SPACE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Space]', 'Forget this! Taking your time doesn’t mean being aimless— it just means you have more time to appreciate the small things in life that nobody else has time to properly enjoy. Why rush through everything? Take time to focus on the little things, and better yourself because of it. A single stat you had a 0 in becomes a +2 instead, as you take up a form of creative output involving your weaknesses, like a rust taking up swordplay, or a jade trying out Excessive Bodily Force Poetry. If you had no 0’s, you instead gain a **[Talent]** in your weakest stat.'),
('angerManagement', 'ANGER MANAGEMENT', 'RAGE', 'RAGE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Rage]', 'You’ve started to realize that your anger can hurt people— I mean, duh, but people you care about. You hope to try to control yourself and avoid going ham as often as you used to in order to protect people a little better. That’s not to say that you can’t choose to go ham; it’s when others make you do it that it’s a problem. When someone else would use an effect that would turn you **[Enraged]**, you instead gain **2 [Boost]** as you stomach it and grit your teeth.'),
('aniimeIisReal', 'ANIIME IIS REAL', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Battery]', 'You are the hope of the omniverse. You are the lightbulb in the dark. You are the bacon in the meal vault for all those that cry out in hunger. You are the alpha and the omega. You are the terror that flaps in the night! You are a BATTERY TROLL! And you are a Super Saiyan! You gain access to HERO MODE through your INCREDIBLE IMAGINATION. So incredible are your uberpsionics, in fact, that you have an Absolute Territory field that suppresses the power of other \"psychics\". Tch! All enemy psionics without the ANIIME IIS REAL move are weakened by your very presence; they get a **-2 [Nerf]** to all **[Psionics]**. If they have ANIIME IIS REAL, however, the fight is on! You both become **[Quickened]** as long as you are strifing each other. Side by side, you simply complement each other; you get a +2 on **[Psionic]** rolls while teamed up with your laser-eyed allies. Using OVERCLOCKING or SYSTEM DISCHARGE ends this effect for 2 turns as you take time to summon back your mighty power. You also gain the following new effects for SUPERCHARGED:\r\n\r\n> **COLLATERAL DAMAGE**: Dear general coordinates, fuck you. Instead of focusing on a single target, you spread your carnage far and wide. You can pick up to 2 additional targets to deal damage to, but deal 1 less damage (min. 1) for each extra opponent targeted.\r\n\r\n> **JUMP START**: You give an ally your energy, an ally of your choice gets **2 [Boost]**. :)\r\n\r\n> **FU...SION...HA!**: You choose to share your charge with another willing Battery Gold, like some atoms share electrons. It’s all very gay. Any CHARGE gained by either party is shared, and your CHARGE cap goes up to 20. This option costs no CHARGE, has no **[Recharge]**, and you can add more Battery Golds to the fusion like a Battery daisy chain, increasing the CHARGE cap by 10 for each Battery added. Sharing is caring.'),
('animePowerspike', 'ANIME POWERSPIKE', 'OTHER', 'VOIDROT', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Voidrot]', 'Plus Ultra! You know, plus? Like the voltage? You may not be a battery anymore, but voidrots still have anime gold rights - you’ve learned to channel that bioenergy you’re always draining into immediate bursts of strength, rather than only using it to heal all the time. For **[Free]**, you can spend **1 [Reserve]** to make your next **[Physical]** roll **[Talented]**; if you spend **2 [Reserve]**, your next **[Physical]** roll is instead **[Talented]** and **[Tiered Up]**, as you go even further beyond!\r\n\r\n'),
('animorphosis', 'ANIMORPHOSIS', 'OTHER', 'WYLDERDRUID', '[Template][Advanced][Free][One-Off][Magic][Locked: Wylderdruid]\r\n', 'Sometimes being a troll isn’t the best way to get around a problem. Say it with me, folks… ASSUME PIGEONFORM! As a **[Free]** action, you can shapeshift into any monsters you have previously made **WYLDERPACTS** with, disappearing entirely as you turn into a spectral version of the monster of your choice. This effect lasts for up to 2 rounds, although you can end it earlier. During your transformation, you can only roll moves the monster has access to and **SOLSTICIALIZE**, although you retain all of your passives. You acquire the stats and moves of the monster, although you either keep your **+PSP** stat or the **+PSP** stat of the monster, whichever is higher. Your **HP** also stays the same. \r\n'),
('annex', 'ANNEX', 'OTHER', 'TEAM_STRIFE', '[Team Strife] [Physical][Free][Reaction]', 'Hey! Is that chump trying to run away? In the middle of a fight? Fuck you! Whenever someone in STANDBY tries to ABDICATE their obligation to get their shit kicked in by you, you can roll LET\'S STRIFE to ANNEX, a specialised version of CAN\'T ABSCOND BRO. If you get a higher result, their ABDICATE roll fails, and they’re forced into a STRUGGLE with you.'),
('antiAntiVaxxer', 'ANTI ANTI VAXXER', 'OTHER', 'DOCTERROR', '[Template][Advanced][Downtime][Heal][Locked: Docterror]', 'There’s more to being a trained Docterror than being a combat medic or selling people’s organs on the white market. Any troll with a medicalizer or access to a scalpel and a picnic cooler can do that! But you can tackle the complex stuff that needs, y’know, actual schoolfeeding to do? You now have the ability to write people little scripts in god awful handwriting that they can trade in for all their money and assets in exchange for the lifesaving medication they need! Yay! The system works! As a **[Downtime]** action, you may roll **+PSP** to **[Heal]** a troll of an **[Affliction]** they have. On a **GOOD** or above, they are cleansed of any **[Afflictions]**, or any lingering status effects they might have- for example, if a move says they would have **-2 HP** for a week as a penalty of a **BAD** roll, you can remove that. ON a **MAX**, you may remove their MOONBARK status. This drops the target a Wealth level, and you gain **Treasure I**.'),
('antiimperialContraband', 'ANTI-IMPERIAL CONTRABAND', 'OTHER', 'NADS', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: NADS]\r\n', 'What\'s in it for me, you ask? You get exposure. And some sick, illegal items. You’ve managed to pick up some item-crafting techniques that make the battlefield a little more advantageous for you and your fellows, whether you did so by learning from someone else, watching highly illegal spewtube tutorials before they were taken down, or maybe just finding leftover stuff from riots gone by. You gain access to the following VP items:\r\n\r\n> **SILVERDUST BOTTLE (2 VP, CONSUMABLE)**: It’s a POCKET CLOUD! Smashing this on the ground will envelop everything in the encounter in a cloud of hazy grey dust, rendering caste impossible to tell. Trolls that start **[Crying]** or become **[Bloodied]** do not reveal their blood color; additionally, the drone’s caste sensors are clogged so empire-loyal highbloods are not immune to the drone’s bullet-laden fury.\r\n\r\n> **ANTIPROPAGANDASCREEN (2 VP)**: It’s… spraypaint, more or less. Mostly, this is used to draw phallic symbols on fancy ORG vehicles and cover up cameras and whatnot. Spray this on any foe’s ocular globes and they’ll be **[Blinded]** until they take an action to wipe it off- a **[Lengthy]** action if the foe is mechanical. That’s not all this does, though! The compounds present in this paint’s vapors universally disable **[Control]** moves for all participants in the encounter for **three turns** after this is deployed, even if it’s wiped off.\r\n\r\n> **CULLBAIT-B-HERE (2 VP, CONSUMABLE)**: This weird, slightly glowing sludge, pulled from the minifridge of a long-abandoned diner in the Slimescale underbelly, has highly variable effects. As a **[One-off]**, you can lob it at an enemy, and… Woah, is their skin glowing? Are they PINK? Are those stubby little wings growing out of their back all of a sudden? Point is, this gives your enemy the **[Cullbait]** tag until they wash off the slutch with a day of **[Downtime]** or a **[Lengthy]** action. These effects are entirely temporary, after all.  Your sludged enemy can’t attempt to wash it off until **two rounds** have passed. Strangers and drones will be completely fooled; people who know the attacked person, however, can tell something is wrong with a good **+PSP** roll.\r\n\r\n> **RENEGADE’S WHISTLER (2 VP, CONSUMABLE)**: This handmade firework was made for distraction, and boy does it work! Shoot this out on the battlefield and it will explode in a shower of hemospectrum-colored sparks; for **two turns** after the fact, your enemies are unable to use moves or effects that assist their allies as they’re scattered and bedazzled by your disruptive pyrotechnics!\r\n'),
('anythingGoesOnTheOpenSea', 'ANYTHING GOES ON THE OPEN SEA', 'OTHER', 'RAPSCALLINEER', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][locked: Rapscallineer]', 'Hemoism? Caste stereotypes? On the insular scuttleboats and airships manned by pirates? Heck, caste may be the butt of a joke sometimes, but caste loyalty generally goes right out the window in favor of loyalty to your crew. You all kind of learn from each other. And after a time, a Rust will be socially indistinguishable from a Violet in favor of a much more prominent identity: BEING AN INFAMOUS PIRATE. You may take up to three **[Open]** moves from the caste of any of your crewmates; take one when you take this move. Additionally, you gain access to items accessible by the wealth levels of any of your crewmates; for example, a bronze with a cerulean crewmate would have access to items with the **Well-Off** tag.'),
('apiarchitect', 'APIARCHITECT', 'GOLD', 'ADULT', '[Gold][Recharge: 4][Locked: Adult]', 'BEES! For troll tech, these little bastards are in everything, and spaceships are no different! Whether it be some rebel vessel with tube tvs for screens or a violet’s warship decked out in holograms, they all run on powerful little anthophila! You control the computer interfaces and machines of a ship by sending in your little bee friends to input commands for you! Apiarchitects can be found all over a ship, from on deck helping assist in massive space dogfights to recalibrating the shield system down below. Why lock onto the enemy ship using FINGERS and BUTTONS, when you can COMMAND other beings to DO IT FOR YOU!? KEHEHEHEHHEHEHEH! With your advanced beekeeping skills, you may spend a **[Lengthy]** action to **[Tier Up]** one **[Tech]** roll made by yourself or any roll made by a ROBOT. You may also spend this action to **[Tier Down]** one **[Tech]** roll made by an enemy or any roll made by a ROBOT. This effect can only happen once per round, but lasts two rounds. Hard to fight back full of honey and with a hundred bees in you huh, bitch?!'),
('apprehend', 'APPREHEND', 'OTHER', 'TEAM_STRIFE', '[Team Strife] [Physical][Physical][Strife]', 'GET OVER HERE! You wrestle with someone on STANDBY and force them to come play with you over in STRUGGLE territory. You make a GRIEF roll, but you do 1 damage less than normal and cannot apply any other effects. They can attempt to immediately scream AIEEEEE!! at this roll, but if they don’t roll numerically higher than this APPREHEND roll, they take **+1 damage** on a **GOOD+**. You can only roll this move on enemy trolls on STANDBY, even though you can’t normally target them.'),
('apprenticesLessons', 'APPRENTICE\'S LESSONS', 'OTHER', 'PAGE', '[Class][Advanced][Locked: Page]', 'You can be particularly good with your aspect one second and then particularly bad the next. Still, you try really hard! One trick you’ve learned is to watch the enemy and how they succeed. You keep an eye out for foes who perform your aspect exceptionally well and keep their techniques in mind for later! Depending on your aspect when your enemies come under certain conditions you gain extra **PP**:\r\n\r\n> **TIME**: Gain 1 **PP** extra each round an enemy is **[Quickened]** at a cap of 1 **PP** per round.\r\n\r\n> **SPACE**: Gain 1 **PP** extra when the enemy gets a **GREAT+** result with a UNIVERSAL MOVE.\r\n\r\n> **LIFE**: Gain 1 **PP** extra when an enemy succeeds a **[Heal]** roll.\r\n\r\n> **DOOM**: Gain 1 **PP** any time an enemy gives 3 or more **[Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> **HOPE**: Gain 1 **PP** whenever an enemy gains a **[Positive] [Emotion]** at a cap of 1 **PP** per round.\r\n\r\n> **RAGE**: Gain 1 **PP** extra when an enemy uses **[WHAM]** against you.\r\n\r\n> **BLOOD**: Gain 1 extra **PP** when an enemy gives **[Boost], [Tier Ups]** or **[Buffs]** to their allies.\r\n\r\n> **BREATH**: Gain 1 **PP** for each round an enemy is **[Flying]** at a cap of 1 **PP** per round.\r\n\r\n> **LIGHT**: Gain 1 **PP** any time an enemy **[Tiers Up]** a move.\r\n\r\n> **VOID**: Gain 1 **PP** when an enemy **[Nerfs]** one of your rolls.\r\n\r\n> **HEART**: Gain 1 **PP** when an enemy makes a **GREAT+** roll against you with a stat they have **[Talent]** in.\r\n\r\n> **MIND**: Gain 1 **PP** extra when an enemy gets a **GREAT+ [Analyze]** roll.\r\n'),
('approachingOmniscience', 'APPROACHING OMNISCIENCE', 'OTHER', 'SEER', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Seer]', 'You\'ve spent so long in an overstimulated information haze that you\'ve been forced to learn to cope. Healthy coping, even! It\'s so dreadful. But what’s done is done, and now you can parse the information you receive into manageable chunks. You\'re on fire? Don\'t freak out - analyze what it\'s doing to your body. Focus on how to put it out. You\'re bleeding out? Focus on how to staunch the wound. You\'re crying your eyes out?. Remember what your terrorpist told you about emotional regulation. All **[Negative]** status effects gain a time limit of 2 rounds before they wear off on their own. **[Negative]** effects with existing time limits have them lowered by 1 round to a minimum of 1. Any time you would become **[Peaceful]** you instead gain **[Serenity]** for **[Free]**. If you already have **KNOW IT ALL BITCH**, you instead begin with **[Serenity]**. Your modifier cap when rolling to **[Analyze]** raises to 6, your +PSP stat cap raises to 6 as well, and you gain 1 point in +PSP immediately upon taking this move.'),
('archastrologist', 'ARCHASTROLOGIST', 'OTHER', 'ASTROSORCERER', '[Template][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Astrosorcerer]', 'You have unlocked the greatest secrets of the stars. Never again will people tell you Magic is fake as shit; it\'s real, just like Anime and Troll Bigfoot. Your magic is powerful beyond comprehension; you gain access to HERO MODE thanks to your INCREDIBLE IMAGINATION if you took the **+IMG** **[Talent]** upon entry, or you become **[Talented]** in it now. Your magic is overwhelmingly strong, dominating the field around you; all opponents **[Magic]** rolls are **[Inept]** if they target you or an ally. BEGONE, ENEMY WIZARD! Finally, any time an enemy says the words \"WIZARD\", \"MAGIC\", \"SORCERER\" or \"CAST\", you trigger HUZZAH! A WIZARD, because you\'re seriously so pumped about this shit.'),
('archetypist', 'ARCHETYPIST', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][Magic][Locked: Protagonist]', 'Your subtle metapresence alters the way you interact with your companions and opponents alike. It might even actually alter them in your presence, period, making them act more or less like a particular cliche from a particular genre, either subtly, visibly, or only in your mind\'s eye. You may assign trolls archetypes with a Request WORDPLAY roll while in an encounter with them. If they accept, you both get specific effects. Giving a second troll an archetype you already gave out removes it from the first, and you cannot give a troll multiple archetypes. You may attempt to Request an Archetype onto a troll even if it doesn\'t fit them; this fundamentally alters how they treat you if they accept. Turn that former enemy into a begrudging ally, or tell an old friend you\'ll never trust them again! \r\n\r\n> **THE ALLY**: The Troll Han Solo to your Troll Luke Skywalker; your foil! Their flaws bring out the others’ best characteristics. How can you show how idealistic you are without a cynic present? If one of you gets a **BAD** or lower on a roll, the other cannot get lower than an **OK** on that same roll next turn.\r\n\r\n> **THE MENTOR**: The Troll Gandalf. They can tell you secrets and give you wisdom that will help you on your journey! When either of you succeeds on an **[Analyse]** roll, the other person gets **1 [Boost]** as they share knowledge.\r\n\r\n> **THE TRICKSTER**: Oh, Troll Olaf. Their antics amuse you. Their comic relief keeps you fighting during the darkest days! Whenever you would take a negative **[Emotion]**, you can choose to start **[Giggling]** for **2 rounds** instead while in an encounter with the Trickster.\r\n\r\n> **THE SHAPESHIFTER**: Can you really trust this character..? Troll Catwoman here could either be your friend or your foe, and you can never tell which. If a strife breaks out between you both, you both instantly get **2 [WHAM]**. Let the first hit land hardest!\r\n\r\n> **THE GUARDIAN**: This troll is an obstacle, stopping you from getting what you want, just like the Snazzard from Troll Shrek stopping you from crossing a bridge! While in an encounter with this character, your GUTSUCKERY becomes **[Recharge: 3]** rather than **[One-Off]**. They cannot be your ally.\r\n\r\n> **THE HERALD**: This troll has changed your life with unusual news, for better or for worse. Troll Fairy Godmother, you can really take me to the Ball? While in an encounter with this character, you both become **[Talented]** on LET\'S STRIFE rolls the first time you use it in an encounter other than to ORDER UP as you alert each other of trouble.\r\n\r\n> **THE SHADOW**: VILLAIN! You\'re the one that\'s hurt me the most, Troll DIO! You and your greatest foe are always ready to hurt one another; you always do **+1 damage** against each other, and ignore each other\'s **[Resistance]**.'),
('archgamblignant', 'ARCHGAMBLIGNANT', 'CERULEAN', 'ADULT', '[Cerulean][Free][Recharge: 3][Locked: Adult]', 'Whether you practiced on Alternia as a Gambligant or have lucked into this role, it remains the same: you gamble. Gamble with what? Who knows! Perhaps you are an aid that advises your superiors which planets would have more worthwhile resources. Maybe you are in charge of the Alternian stock market, ensuring that you live a volatile life full of self-imposed highs and lows. Hell, perhaps you diversify your reach. After all, all the irons in the fire? Those are yours. ALL of them. Whenever you want to shake things up in a fight, you can spin a wheel. Or more accurately, roll 1d8. This roll cannot be modified in any way, you get what you get.\n\n> 1. Your rolls next turn are all **[Tiered Down]**.\n> 2. Your opponent can apply a -2 [Nerf] to one of  your rolls on your upcoming turn.\n> 3. You gain 3 [Drag].\n> 4. You gain 1 [Drag].\n> 5.  You gain 1 [Boost].\n> 6. You gain 3 [Boost].\n> 7. You can apply a -2 [Nerf] to one of your opponent’s rolls on their upcoming turn.\n> 8. Your rolls next turn are all [Tiered Up].'),
('areYouSure', 'ARE YOU SURE?', 'OTHER', 'SYLPH', '[Class][Basic][Reaction][One-Off][Locked: Sylph]', 'Listen. You’re not trying to imply anything, but they could’ve done that a bit differently. Obviously you don’t mean to be bossy about it, but next time, try and think for a second about it, okay? When an ally rolls a move that is affected by an enemy’s debilitating effects (**[Inept]**, **[Nerf]**, etc.) and they roll an **OK** or lower, you may spend a **[Reaction]** to gently chide them and make sure their next roll will be unaffected by an enemy’s debilitating effects.\r\n'),
('aristotagonist', 'ARISTOTAGONIST', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Free][Recharge: 3][Unlock: Marquis]', 'Yaaaaahkyahahaha! Nobility, baby! You got that! Stacks of cash? Got it. Loyal servants? Got it? Rapiers and puffy shirts? Got it, got it, got it. The world is yours!!!!!!!! Whether you\'re a pirate, a princess or a celebrity, you\'re definitely sure of one thing- you\'re the best thing out there, baby!! You have the **Rich** Wealth level rather than **Well-Off**. You are **[Talented]** at **+HUB**. Any time someone else in an encounter uses a **+HUB** move, you get a burning need to outperform them; you get a +1 to your next **+HUB** roll as you remind them of your aristocratic excellence. This effect can be stacked up to a max of +3 on a single **+HUB** roll if an opponent uses multiple **+HUB** rolls since your last turn.'),
('armorcladCrusader', 'ARMORCLAD CRUSADER', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Passive][Unlock: Paladin]', 'Culture. It is the soul of the people; history, laws, literature and art. Some believe that Indigos are the greatest at culture, and any other take is irrelevant, but you know different. ALL trolls, regardless of place on the Hemoladder, contribute to society. You are a member of the INDIGO ORDER OF CRUSACULTURISTS, an exclusive club of noble warrior poets who read ancient texts, create beautiful art and fight to protect the weak and the strong alike and keep Alternia singing. You are **[Talented]** at **+GRA**. You have a set of specially treated armour that you literally are not allowed to take off ever. But why would you? Your armour channels hits that you take into powerful effects that keep you going. You gain the following effects when you take damage. You only gain 1 per turn. If an attack does **[Somatic]** and **[Energy]** damage, it only does the **[Energy]** effect.\r\n\r\n> **SOMATIC**: Your armour toughens. **[Strife]** rolls against you next turn have a **-2 [Nerf]**.\r\n> **HOLY**: Your armour traps some healing energy. You gain another usage of GUTSUCKERY.\r\n> **FROST**: Your armour becomes packed with ice. You take 1 less damage (min. 1) from **[Physical]** attacks on your next turn.\r\n> **FREAKY**: Your armour glows. The attacker is **[Blinded]** for **2 turns**.\r\n> **LASER**: Your armour deflects the attack! Roll 1d8; on a 1-6, it hits you as normal. On a 7+, the attack hits a different troll, maybe even the attacker!\r\n> **ELECTRIC**: The electricity courses over your plating. If someone attacks you with a **[Physical]** attack next turn, they take 2 **[Drag]**.\r\n> **BLAZE**: Your armour glows red. Anyone who makes a **[Physical]** roll against you next turn must roll 1d8; on a 1 or a 2, they take **1 [Blaze]** damage.\r\n> **SONIC**: Your armour makes the sound reverberate. Everyone on the field takes this damage.\r\n> **GLITCHY**: Uhhhh… all of the above? A random armour effect triggers.\r\n> **ACID**: Your armour comes out shinier than ever. You gain **1 [Boost]**.'),
('articulate', 'ARTICULATE', 'OTHER', 'TEAM_STRIFE', '[Team Strife][Manipulate]', 'BOO, YOU SUCK! YOU’RE FUCKING AWFUL! BOOOOOO! You eloquently voice an opinion of the other fighter. You make a WORDPLAY roll against the enemy STRUGGLER; on a **GOOD**, you give them **1 BOO** point. On a **GREAT**, 2, and on a **MAX**, 3. Once an enemy has accumulated **3 BOO** points, they are **[Sad]** for **2 rounds** and flee, swapping out with someone on STANDBY.'),
('artOfLiving', 'ART OF LIVING', 'OTHER', 'ABOMINARTIST', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Abominartist]', 'Your lusus told you you could be anything, so you became an artist. Pretty sick. The fascist dystopia that you live in says that all of your art must be made to further their perfect society, and depending on who you are, you may or may not like that. Even the most diehard of bootlickers still try and support the Empire in their own ways, and the rebels\' creed is to be as firebrand as possible, though, so you make as you please and please as you make. Even if it takes hours upon hours of sleepless days fighting with your tablet to just fuCKING DRAW THE DAMN HAND CORRECTLY AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA-\r\n\r\n**Choose one of the options to decide what kind of artist you\'ve decided to become**: \r\n\r\n**PAINTING**: You put the pain in pain-ting! Yeah, I don’t know what you expected. This is still Alternia, after all. Your opponent’s first **[Strife]** roll takes a **-1 [Nerf]** against you, because nobody expects the painter to sharpen their paintbrush handle into a makeshift dagger! Even though they really should, because again, this is still Alternia.\r\n\r\n**POETRY**: With your quill and bottle of ink always with you, you speak from a delicate, poetic place of mind, making up a bunch of random words that don’t make sense but somehow do at the same time. You’re rather well spoken. Your WORDPLAY rolls can never be **[Tiered Down]** or made **[Inept]** by an opponent, instead taking a **-2 [Nerf]**.\r\n\r\n**SCULPTURE**: You fucking love breaking things into more intricate things. You deal **+1 damage** against items, weapons, and drones. They’re just weird rocks, and when you think about it… aren’t we all…?\r\n\r\n**GRAFFITI**: You’re a rebel! Or… maybe you’re not. Maybe you’re one of those freaks that spray paints “I LOVE HIGHBLOODS” on people’s windows. The first time you succeed on a **+RAS** roll, you gain **2 [Boost]**. This **[Boost]** cannot be increased through any means. Stop trying to be troll Banksy.\r\n\r\n**ANIMATION**: Short on time, that’s a gift! You can choose to start an encounter **[Slowed]** for **[Free]**, which allows your first non- LET’S STRIFE! roll to **[Tier Up]**, even to a **MAX**! This **[Slowed]** wears off by your second turn.\r\n\r\n**JEWELRY**: Isn’t this pretty? Yes it is. That was a rhetorical question. Shut up. As a **[One-Off]** action, you can **[Blind]** an opponent for one round as you wave armfuls of pretty jewelry at them.\r\n\r\n**CERAMICS**: You’re great with being able to keep your hands steady and your brain patient. When you succeed on **[Flourish]** rolls, you gain the **[Proud]** emotion.\r\n\r\n**SOMETHING ELSE**: Even among the many unique styles many have, yours is too unique to even put on this list. What is it? Taxidermeritation? Sand painting? ...Butter sculptures? End of the world is the limit, as they say. Choose one of the above effects and narratively flavor it to your liking.'),
('artOfTheDress', 'ART OF THE DRESS', 'OTHER', 'HAUTE_CLAWTURE', '[Template][Downtime][Unlock: Haute Clawture]', 'Stitch here, sew there, cut a little off the top, and- voíla! You’ve created something new and exciting to wear! Sometimes what’s on the rack simply isn’t very inspiring to wear. This is where good old troll imagination comes into play! Whether it’s from scratch or just some slick thrifting, these fabrics are ready for your personal touch. You gain access to the CUSTOM TAILORING **[Downtime]** roll. When you’re ready to create, roll **+IMG**!\r\n\r\n**MIN**: … Oh my gog. What have you done? You\'ve massacred this poor fabric! Into, what is this supposed to be, a fursuit? … This was supposed to be a bucket hat? Let’s all agree to never be creative again! In a fit of despair, you throw out half your **[Fashion]** items. Why did you do that?!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: What were you thinking, trying to pair chartreuse with puce?! If anybody from the fashion world sees this, you’re a dead troll. You lose a **[Fashion]** item.\r\n\r\n**OK**: The stitching is a little messy, and you’re not sure about the color choices in a certain light. At least this has been a learning experience! You start your next encounter with **+1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Hey, check this out! You’ve made something pretty cool! It’s a little small, but it’ll work. You can make an item that belongs to the **[Head]**, **[Gloves]**, or **[Accessories]** with your choice of +1/-1 stats. You can use this item to substitute into any existing **[Fashion]** collection for an item with the same +1 or same -1. The Collection changes 1 stat of its total, your choice.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Ooooh! How chic! Très magnifique! This piece is positively stylish to the core! You can either make an item that belongs to one of the categories listed in **GOOD**, or **[Top]**, **[Bottoms]**, or **[Feet]** with your choice of +1/-1 stats.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Divine inspiration has struck you with the most magnificent of fashion pieces! You can hear choirs of angels singing about your creation! You can make any fashion item in the below categories, and create a whole new Collection with it and your choice of +2, +1, -1, -2 stats. This Collection steals an existing effect from another pre-existing Collection.'),
('asEquals', 'AS EQUALS', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Passive][Open]', 'You\'ve been better than everyone your entire life! Why not try something new? Why not stop competing for greatness, and instead stand on the same ground as the others you face? When you are in a TEAM STRIFE, you can ignore the rules for both CHAMP and CHALLENGER; instead, both teams gain both a CHAMP and CHALLENGER effect as you face off against one another!'),
('askForHelp', 'ASK FOR HELP', 'MIND', 'MIND', '[Aspect][Advanced][Free][Locked: Mind]', 'You’ve realized that just because you might be smarter than others, it doesn’t make you better than them. People are all intelligent in their own ways, and emotional maturity is just as valuable as your booksmarts. When you ask someone for advice on an emotional matter, you can allow them to get a **GREAT** WORDPLAY roll for a Request or Question on you for **[Free]**. If you accept this advice, you get **2 [Hold]**; these **[Holds]** can be used to make any two rolls **GREAT** this encounter.'),
('aspectDance', 'ASPECT DANCE', 'OTHER', 'HEIR', '[Class][Advanced][Magic][Passive][Locked: Heir]', 'As you become one with your aspect, it grows easier and easier to sink into it, to let it flow through you… kind of like this total JAM you\'re boogying out to, dudes! You become **[Talented]** at **FRAYMOTIF** rolls if you weren’t already. When you **FRAYMOTIF**, you meld with your aspect so thoroughly that you gain benefits others of your aspect might not have. These are in addition to the regular benefits you would gain from **FRAYMOTIF**. No one can receive these extra benefits but you, even with a **COMBO**. You gain the following aspect based bonus:  \r\n\r\n> **TIME**: You become **[Quickened]** and **[Slow]** your opponents.\r\n> **SPACE**:  While **[Flying]**, you become **[Peaceful]**. Whee!\r\n> **LIFE**: Your **[Heal]** moves heal an additional +1 **HP**. \r\n> **DOOM**: Your **[Resistance]** to **[Drag]** increases to 2.\r\n> **HOPE**: When you use **[Boost]**, you get 1 **[Boost]** back.\r\n> **RAGE**: You gain **1 [Boost]** anytime you gain **[WHAM]**.\r\n> **BREATH**: **[Recharge]** for moves decreases by 1 to a minimum of 1.\r\n> **BLOOD**: Rolls you make against your allies and rolls your allies make against you get a +2 **[Buff]**.\r\n> **LIGHT**: You can use **[Boost]** to increase a **MIN** roll, or use **[Boost]** to go from a **GREAT** to a **MAX**.\r\n> **VOID**: You can become **[Hidden]** every other turn for **[Free]**. On turns you are not **[Hidden]**, you gain +1 **[Boost]** instead.\r\n> **HEART**: Rolls for every move you don’t have a **[Talent]** for have a +1 **[Buff]**.\r\n> **MIND**: Every time you roll an **[Analyze]** roll, you gain 1 **[Boost]**. The first time you use **RUN THE CALCULATIONS** in an encounter with this **FRAYMOTIF** activated, you are **[Quickened]** next round.\r\n\r\n'),
('aspectdemia', 'ASPECTDEMIA', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Passive][Locked: Nyastrologist]', 'You understand that Aspects are not singular; many of them are two sides of the same coin! Take Rage and Hope; both are about belief and conviction, just in their own way. You gain access to your own Aspect\'s inverse\'s **[Entry]**; Space/Time, Light/Void, etc. You cannot take any other moves from the Aspect. If two trolls\' aspects would count as INCOMPATIBLE, but they have inverse aspects, you may decide to make their aspects count as COMPATIBLE if you choose.'),
('aspectialCrisis', 'ASPECTIAL CRISIS', 'OTHER', 'BARD', '[Class][Advanced][Recharge: 4][Locked: Bard]', 'BREAKDOWN, BREAKDOWN. BREAKDOWN, BREAKDOWN. Reality is meaningless! The universe is a LIE! NOTHING MATTERS! NGHHHRGHH! You have come to the point in your metanarrative journey that the aspect you\'ve been ghosting means nothing to you. It is, and always has been, a lie. Your core beliefs are challenged, your future is in jeopardy... And you wasted so much time, feeding yourself the lie, and what are you meant to do now, huh? What are you, without what you thought mattered? Whenever you would gain a **[Negative] [Emotion]** trait, you can instead choose to start **[Dissociating]**. While **[Dissociating]**, the flames of the metanarrative engine that power the zodiac freeze over. Nobody can benefit from **[Aspect]** moves or **[Class]** moves related to **[Aspect]** as your despair corrupts all those around you. \r\n\r\n'),
('aSpoonfulOfSugar', 'A SPOONFUL OF SUGAR', 'OTHER', 'TRICKSTER', '[Template][Passive][Eerie][Unlock: Trickster]', 'HEEHEE! You’re feeling just jolly! Sure, you may have looked too deep into that door you saw in the corner of your eye, but you got some candy out of it! Now, you’re as happy as can be!! You’re FEELING a lot, actually! All Emotions you feel from now on are always **[Heightened]**. At the expense of an action, you may enter a MOED MOSTE TRICKSEY, where you shed your hard candy shell and show the world the true warhead within! The colors you turn are bright enough to make even the most emo of trolls tear up and you gain a sweet confectionary in your hair! All **[Negative]** Emotions are cleared from anyone who witnesses your transformation, and all **[Positive]** Emotions they may be feeling are instantly **[Heightened]**- except for TIT and SCP members, who are total buzzkills. All that nasty **[Drag]** everyone has is also instantly converted to **[Boost]**, even your enemies! WEEEEE!!! When you enter your MOED MOSTE TRICKSEY, a timer begins! A timer to a very fun party!! **3 turns** after your transformation, everyone in the encounter gains **4 [Boost]** and begins **[Giggling]**. The timer resets whenever someone hits you with a **GREAT** **[Strife]** roll, and after it activates, it starts over. YAAAAY! You become talented at **+RAS** while losing your previous talent, as it was causing you so much unhappiness!'),
('asskickingOutfit', 'ASS-KICKING OUTFIT', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Downtime][Locked: Subcultist]', 'You are a master of hive-brewing new looks that completely redefine your subculture. Even if it looks fucking bizarre. You can create a new Fashion Collection as a Downtime action using other pieces of Fashion Items. These Collections MUST include the item you gained in COUNTERCULTURIST, and at least three other Fashion Items. If these Fashion Items add up to a new highest stat (for example, a combining a SCENE HAIR **[+1 RAS/-1 PSP]**, FANCY TIE **[+1 PLC/-1 RAS]** FLORAL SHIRT **[+1 PLC/-1 HUB]** and a DRESS PANTS **[+1 PLC/-1 APP]** for a total of **[+3 PLC, -2 HUB, -1 PSP]**), the collection swaps your **[Talent]** to be in that stat. You must redistribute the **+[Buffs]** and **-[Nerfs]** from this combination to other stats to ensure nothing goes over ±2 (in the example above, you could make the collection **[+2 PLC, -1 HUB, -1 PSP]**). Ensure everything is balanced out to 0! Yeah, dude, making the ultimate fit takes work. Changing your **[Talent]** here alters the stat used in FIT CHECK.'),
('assurance', 'ASSURANCE', 'OTHER', 'KNIGHT', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Knight]', 'Sicknasty moves that make you look like the good guy? Yeah. Yeah you’ve got that. Sure, you may not necessarily want to do them, or dislike the idea entirely. But somebody has to take charge in this group, and it may as well be you. Upon taking this move, choose a condition from the list below as your preferred condition; each time you inflict it on an opponent or ally (not yourself), you gain **2 [Boost]** as the small amount of self esteem your debilitating self doubt and crushing inferiority complex hasn\'t smothered yet rises to the surface. \r\n\r\n> **[Bloodied]**\r\n> **[Slowed]**\r\n> **[Quickened]**\r\n> **[Ablaze]**\r\n> **[Hopeful]**\r\n> **[Heal]** \r\n\r\n'),
('aStoryOfFourFriends', 'A STORY OF FOUR FRIENDS', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Passive][Reaction]', 'The power of friendship CANNOT be overstated. Do you know how many wars were won by friends standing up against bad guys? ALL OF THEM. You are a hero, and so are your friends, whether they’re a troll or a human. You can add up to 3 other characters to your Story. Characters in your Story are your closest allies, ones you can take on the world with, no matter how bad the odds are. When in an encounter with a character from your Story, you can use a **[Reaction]** to let them reroll a roll they just made as you throw them encouraging words or a warning. When you take this move, the three people who agree to be part of this story gain this move too, even if they wouldn\'t normally have access. Depending on the number of people from your Story present, you start an encounter with the following boons…\r\n\r\n> 1. You’re here with a close friend! You have **1 [Boost]**.\r\n> 2. The Terrific Trio is here to rock and roll! You are **[Hopeful]** and have **2 [Boost]**.\r\n> 3. Let’s make history: the whole gang is here. You are **[Inspired]** and have **3 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n'),
('astrosorcery', 'ASTROSORCERY', 'OTHER', 'ASTROSORCERER', '[Template][Recharge: 3][Flourish][Magic][Unlock: Astrosorcerer]\r\n', 'Charts of the stars… magic staves… a pointed hat… Yeah, baby, you\'re an Astrosorcerer alright. You cast spells empowered by the celestial bodies above and how they interact with you. You may choose to lose your **[Talent]** from your caste, and instead become **[Talented]** at **+IMG**. In addition, you gain a unique spell based on your Sign, based on your Caste, your Sway and your Aspect. This spell is named after your sign- for example, a Teal, Derse and Hope Astrosorcerer would gain a spell named INCANTATION OF THE SEAMSTRESS, or a Rust, Prospit and Blood Astrologer would gain a spell named INCANTATION OF THE OFFICER. That\'s 288 unique moves, legit go fuck yourself. Additionally, when you take this move, you cannot take the DARK MAGICKS move from the Cthonomancer Template. The starless darkness shall not tempt you tonight! When you want to cast a spell, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: It backfires HORRIBLY! Your opponent gains the effects of the spell, and it always affects them, regardless of your Sway. You count as any opponent targeted.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: It backfires… tamely. Thank goodness for that. You take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Your spell peters out… which is annoying, but at least you didn\'t get hurt.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You cast a spell, but… it\'s not quite there yet, is it? You do the spell, but only the ASPECT and SWAY sections. No CASTE, sorry!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: That\'s more like it! You cast a spell, and it works perfectly! Your spell does the ASPECT, SWAY and CASTE options.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Holy shit… you are not only bound to your own thread of astrological fate, but can call upon the stars to harness the fates of those around you. You either cast a spell using someone else in the encounter\'s ASPECT, SWAY, and CASTE, or cast your own spell and additionally grant **2 [Boost]** to your target of choice.\r\n\r\n\r\nSPELL MODULES\r\n\r\n**ASPECT**:\r\n\r\n> **TIME**: You give **1 [WHAM]** to… \r\n> **SPACE**: You make it impossible to remove the effects of a **[Positive]** Emotion from...\r\n> **LIFE**: You give **1 [Resistance]** to all damage for **two turns** to… \r\n> **DOOM**: You remove half the **[Drag]** of…\r\n> **HOPE**: You remove the effects of a **[Negative]** Emotion from… \r\n> **RAGE**: You **[Heighten]** the Emotions of… \r\n> **BREATH**: You remove a **[Physical]** condition from… \r\n> **BLOOD**: You **[Heal] 1 HP** of… \r\n> **LIGHT**: You give **3 [Boost]** to… \r\n> **VOID**: You remove a **[Positive]** Emotion from the last troll to strike… \r\n> **HEART**: For **2 turns**, you give an opponent\'s **[Talents]** to… \r\n> **MIND**: You **[Tier Up]** the next **[Analyze]** roll of… \r\n\r\n**SWAY**:\r\n\r\n> **PROSPIT**: An ally (or yourself, only if you have no allies)…\r\n> **DERSE**: Yourself… \r\n\r\nCASTE\r\n\r\n> **RUST**: …and then become **[Hidden]**.\r\n> **BRONZE**: …and give a **-2 [Nerf]** to the next **[Strife]** roll to target you. \r\n> **GOLD**: …and do **1 [Somatic]** electrical damage to the next person to deal damage to you.\r\n> **LIME**: …and then gain the effects of **[Permablind]** for **3 turns**.\r\n> **OLIVE**: …and become **[Quickened]** on your next turn. \r\n> **JADE**: …and **[Heal]** the target by **1 HP**.\r\n> **TEAL**: …and erase all **[Drag]** the target has.\r\n> **CERULEAN**: …and do **1 [Psychic]** damage to one opponent.\r\n> **INDIGO**: …and make the target **[Legendary]** at **+GRT** for a turn.\r\n> **PURPLE**: …and cause an opponent to start **[Laughing]** for **two turns**.\r\n> **VIOLET**: …and cause the target\'s **[Tier Ups]** to go to **MAX** for **two turns**. \r\n> **FUSCHIA**: …and select any of the other Caste options as you please.'),
('aTiredSmile', 'A TIRED SMILE', 'DOOM', 'DOOM', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Doom]', 'Come on now, just because the world is an endless closed loop of suffering and absence of agency and nothing you do really matters in the grand scheme of things doesn\'t mean every little thing has to be bad! It just means you have to celebrate the victories you do get and remember why life is worth living. When you use **[Boost]** in an encounter, you can spend an additional **2 [Boost]** to give yourself your choice of the **[Happy]**, **[Brave]** or **[Proud]** conditions.'),
('atlasPersonality', 'ATLAS PERSONALITY', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Open][Free][Mental]', 'Show weakness? No, no, no, you could never! You need to serve as a role model for everyone! Ahahaha! You’re perfectly okay, please, PLEASE don’t look into it— so long as everyone else is fine, you are fine. You can choose to ignore any **[Physical]** condition that happens to you, like becoming **[Floorbound]** or **[Bloodied]**, gaining **2 [Drag]** instead. As a **[Reaction]**, you can gain **1 [Resistance]** to an incoming attack, gaining **3 [Drag]** instead.'),
('atYourService', 'AT YOUR SERVICE', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Passive][Unlock: Worker]', 'It\'s a tough job, but somebody\'s gotta do it. That somebody is you, whether you like it or not! Rusts are always given the most grueling of tasks, both off-world and on it. That includes everything from janitorial duties to retail to butlerhood. The worst part is that, like all jobs on Alternia, you don\'t even get paid— it\'s just valuable experience for your eventual Ascension. Stings a little to know that technically, all of these jobs could be automated by drones, but whatever. Select one of the following roles.\r\n\r\n> **Janitorturist (+RAS)**: What a mess. You are immune to **[Disgusted]**, and can cure allied status conditions with a quick mop. Mop their **[Ablaze]** away, a good spritz of OxiScream for their **[Dread]**... This is a **[Lengthy]**, **[Physical]** action.\r\n\r\n> **Underhost (+PLC)**: You may dress fancy, and do fancy things, but… you\'re still a lowblood wage slave. Hope those highbloods you\'re serving horderves like your bowtie! You have **12 VP**, not 8, since you\'re used to carrying plates of party favors so often.\r\n\r\n> **Splathlete (+GRA)**: You\'d think that a job in sports would be lucrative, but half of Stickball\'s appeal is the fact that the players can be killed mid-game. When someone makes an **OK** or lower **[Strife]** roll at you, you do **1 [Somatic]** damage back for **[Free]** as you bat their attack right back! \r\n\r\n> **Henchtroll (+APP)**: What? Okay, sure, you sold out and became like, a supervillain goon or assistant to a rich bastard. And what of it? You can roll **[Downtime]** rolls on behalf of others.\r\n\r\n> **Stuntster (+HUB)**: For all those amateur filmmakers out there, throwing a rust at a wall and seeing how many bones they break is invaluable! You gain access to a free SMALL Vehicle with no features. You are always **[Proud]** while riding it.\r\n\r\n> **Rustshirt (+GRT)**: You are a future disposable frontliner, be it on the battlefield, in shady labs or on research expeditions on hostile alien worlds. When you hit **0 HP**, all allies gain **4 [Boost]** and **1 [WHAM]** as they cry your name in disbelief. \r\n\r\n> **Retailanguisher (+PSP)**: Will that be all, sir..? Any **LUX** items you purchase are 1 cheaper than normal. You know where to get the good stuff.\r\n\r\n> **Minionwick (+IMG)**: You are in eternal servitude to a mighty wizard. Your status as apprentice means while you aren\'t allowed to use magic yourself, you can help others do so; if an ally fails a **+IMG** roll, you may reroll it on your turn and retroactively give the new result to them, even if it\'s worse.'),
('auditerrorizer', 'AUDITERRORIZER', 'TEAL', 'ADULT', '[Teal][Locked: Adult]', 'Auditerrorizers come in such a wide and colorful variety. Colorful as in personality of course, since folks in this career path are Teal and more shades of Teal. Auditerrorizers are the vast masses of office society, taking orders from Manajeers and holding glamorous positions in numerous specialized guilds that exist, like \\\'The Data Entry Enforcers of Alternia\\\'s Empire\\\'. Hopefully you\\\'ve worked hard to increase your standing with your peers; you don\\\'t want to work in the Troll Resources department.\nIf you can find some teals you get along with, you can form a guild together. One person must be appointed the Guild Head, and they must have this move. You can add as many people to the GUILD, so long as everyone agrees. They do not need to have this move, but they must be teal.\n\n> **Guild Head**: You’ve got several Manajeers poking you for results and a GUILD that has no idea what’s going on. The first time you receive a **[Base] [Negative]** emotion in an encounter, you instead gain the opposite **[Base] [Positive]** emotion. We gotta get through this one way or another.\n\n> **Troll Resources**: Someone has to pretend that the Empire cares if you keel over, if only so everyone continues working. You can use **GUTSUCKERY** on a **[Recharge: 2]**, and you can also target others with it. \n\n> **Assistant**: Coming through, I’ve got the paperwork right here. If someone else in the encounter is part of your GUILD, your sylladexes combine into one communal sylladex. Someone needs that a little more than you do right now, okay? \n\n> **Penpusher**: Still as average and common as ever, but that’s not to say you’re not useful! You get a +1 **[Buff]** to **[Strife]** moves as you’re used to being as efficient as possible.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('authorityFigure', 'AUTHORITY FIGURE', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Passive][Unlock: Boss]', 'The people of Alternia need strong, powerful figures to look up to. And you are happy to provide. With your stoic attitude, impressive leadership skills and commanding presence, things always go the way you want them. Whether you are a military leader in the making, a future CEO, or perhaps even a would-be dungeon boss, one thing is for sure— you are the Boss. It’s you. You are **[Talented]** in **+HUB**. You are always **[Serious]**, and should you fall below half HP, you become **[Dead Serious]** as you hone in on being a boss bitch. If someone gets a **GREAT** or higher on a **+RAS** roll against you, they become **[Scared]** cuz HOOOOO MAMA. This can stack into **[Terrified]**.'),
('avoidant', 'AVOIDANT', 'BREATH', 'BREATH', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Breath]', 'You don’t mind conflict! You just don’t really want to have anything to do with it— ever! Ahaha! Why not just… ignore the problem, and hope it goes away? Talk things over nicely? Things don’t need a resolution, they just need to be avoided. Your ABSCOND rolls always **[Tier Up]**, counting the minimum result (8 for **OK**, 11 for **GOOD**, etc.) of the next tier as your roll in order to compare it to an opponent’s CAN’T ABSCOND BRO roll. If you make a WORDPLAY roll to try to ask someone nicely to stop fighting, your roll is **[Tiered Up]**. People’s PROBLEM SLEUTHING rolls to find you while you are **[Hidden]** are **[Tiered Down]**.\n\n'),
('awesomeAppetite', 'AWESOME APPETITE', 'OTHER', 'HEROMODE', '', 'You\'ve got an iron gut, nerves of steel, a heart of gold and various other innards that seem to be made of different metals and alloys. Metallurgy is where the money is after all! When it comes to sticking around long enough to make something out of nothing, nobody can hold a candle to you! When you enter **HERO MODE**, you may select one of the following benefits.\r\n\r\n> **COST BENEFIT ANALYSIS**: Whether it’s business, working a stall on a roadside or just trying to figure out if lending caegars to a friend is worth the hassle, you have to make one. You can spend one **LUX** to bet that you will either deal 3 damage, **[Heal]** 3 **HP**, knock an opponent out or gain 5 **[Boost]** in the next 2 turns. You gain 1 **LUX** back for each you succeed in accomplishing, plus the original refunded.\r\n \r\n> **STILL STANDING**: The smoke clears, and everyone was SURE you were down… but oops! You\'re still going! As a **[Reaction]**, you gain a **[Last Stand]** against an incoming attack, staying at 1 **HP** when you should be down.\r\n \r\n> **BATTLE CRY**: MORE! COME ON, GIVE ME MORE! THIS IS NOTHING! Your hunger for battle is, I\'ll be frank, fucking terrifying. You can howl out at your opponent to hit you harder. You reset the opponent\'s **[Boost]** to 0 (if they had any), and they become **[Terrified]**.\r\n\r\n> **COMPLETELY INSATIABLE**: I\'m gonna munch! I\'m gonna crunch! Your appetite is absolutely improbable. You can use **GUTSUCKERY** on a **[Recharge 2]**. If you already had a move that stops **GUTSUCKERY** from being a **[One-Off]** move, then every time you **[Heal]**, you regain an extra **HP**.\r\n\r\n> **UNSHAKEABLE**: There\'s no holding you back! You shake off anything! You convert all your **[Drag]** into **[Boost]** and/or flip a negative **[Emotion]** into its opposite. '),
('backalleyBrawler', 'BACK-ALLEY BRAWLER', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Passive][Locked: Delinquent]', 'Oh? So you’re approaching me? You’re going to walk up to a stone-cold skirmisher like me and try to start something? Try it. You could use a workout. You can add the following effects to your **GREAT** or **MAX** GRIEF rolls in exchange for doing **1 damage less**.\r\n\r\n> **MESS-EM-UP**: The target is **[Stressed]** for **2 turns** by how much pain you\'re putting them through!\r\n\r\n> **KNOCK DOWN**: BOOM! You knock \'em on their ass! Fuckerrrr. The target is **[Floorbound]**.\r\n\r\n> **CONCUSSION**: DONK! The target is **[Inept]** at **[Mental]** rolls next turn.\r\n\r\n> **BULLIED**: YEAH, FEEL BAD! You **[Heighten]** a **[Negative]** emotion of the target.'),
('backbreakingWork', 'BACKBREAKING WORK', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Passive][Unlock: Labourer]', 'You? You work. HARD. While Rusts tend to take the service roles side of shitty jobs, Bronze business is in manual labour. Whether it\'s hauling hunks of metal in a sweltering hot factory, grueling over the harvest in massive farmlands, or working on the construction of new buildings, one thing\'s for sure— this is hard work! Your stamina is frighteningly high; you are **[Talented]** at **+APP**. As an action, you can choose to GET TO WORK. When you GET TO WORK, you can\'t roll **[Mental]** rolls at all, but all of your **[Physical]** rolls use **+APP**. That being said, all this hard work comes at a price; after **2 turns** of GETTING TO WORK, you become **[Tired]**; after 4, you become **[Exhausted]**, and after 6, you become **[Unconscious]**. These effects can\'t be removed in an encounter. You can\'t stop GETTING TO WORK if you\'re in a combat encounter, so be sure you know when you want to start!'),
('badAttitude', 'BAD ATTITUDE', 'DOOM', 'DOOM', '[Aspect][Basic][Free][Reaction][Recharge: 2][Locked: Doom]\r\n', 'Seeing other people succeed can be... hard. Why are other people able to do well when you just can’t seem to get a break? How do other people find happiness so easily? When a target rolls 3 successful rolls in a row without rolling an **OK** or lower between them, or if they gain the **[Hopeful]** or **[Happy]** conditions, you can choose to become either **[Enraged]** OR **[Numb]**.'),
('badEnd', 'BAD END', 'OTHER', 'GRIMDARK', '[Template][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Grimdark]', 'Not everyone gets the chance to heal. You didn\'t. Although… is it fair to call you \"you\", anymore? They have experienced the death of the self. The person they were when they first took on the template is gone, and their bitter, resentful, terrified, furious, mourning shell is all that is left. They cannot take the REBIRTH move. When a troll gains this **[Ultra]**, they remain permanently in A MODE MOSTE GRIM, and may never leave it. Rather than move, they blip in and out of existence, hiding them from all detection between encounters. As such, ABSCOND rolls always succeed. They are permanently **[Dissociating]**, and trolls normally immune to such effects are affected by the radius of **[Despair]** and **[Scared]** the user of this move emits. BLACK HOLE no longer affects them as it would with EVENT HORIZON. They no longer summon any PARANORMAL ACTIVITY after 5 turns. Finally, no other trolls may benefit from emotions other than the ones given to them by A MODE MOSTE GRIM. It\'s nothing but pure horror from here on out. This move can’t be removed or retconned away unless something borderline impossible happens involving magic or shit. In short… you’re stuck like this.\n\nDon\'t let this happen to you. Reach out.\n\n'),
('badLuck', 'BAD LUCK', 'DOOM', 'DOOM', '[Aspect][Basic][Reaction][One-Off][Locked: Doom]', 'Luck doesn’t exist. Happy endings come at the cost of struggle and effort, and fate doesn’t pave a way to victory for you— if these things seem to happen, it’s just coincidence. Why can’t anyone but you seem to realize that they need to EARN their luck? Once per encounter, on a non-**MAX** roll, you can force your opponent to reroll what they just got; they take the lower roll result. Alternatively, if someone has an ability which would allow them to reroll something, you can choose to cancel it out.'),
('badTemper', 'BAD TEMPER', 'RAGE', 'RAGE', '[Aspect][Free][One-Off][Unlock: Rage]', 'You’ve struggled your entire life with your short fuse. Whether over something serious like your long term plans being shattered, or something minor like being jostled in line, you’re often quick to give into anger to solve your problems. If you ever accumulate 4 or more **[Drag]**, you can choose to become **[Enraged]** and eliminate said **[Drag]**.'),
('bagOfHolding', 'BAG OF HOLDING', 'OTHER', 'ROGUE', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Magic][Recharge:3][Locked: Rogue]', 'You always make sure you have enough carrying capacity for useful things! When you need an item, you have an item. Where did you get that cat? Where did you get that scuttlebuggy?!?? Uh, you packed them in your giant ass purse, duh. Now who wants fuit gummies? Your **VP** increases by 6 to hold all your goodies! Additionally, as an action, you can purchase **LUX** items mid-thread. When you want to go \"hey, check out what I had\", roll **+RAS, +APP** or **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You… wait, it isn\'t here. Oh, gosh, you realize you got scammed. Curses! You drop a Wealth level.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You did not, in fact, have anything to show them.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Look what I… WILL have, when it gets here! You buy the item, but it won\'t be here til the end of the encounter.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Tada! You get the item for its regular price. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: TARATADA! You get the item at half price. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: TAAAAAARATATADA! You just get the item. No seriously, where the hell did you get that scuttlebuggy? \r\n'),
('barkingMad', 'BARKING MAD', 'OTHER', 'MOONBARK', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Eerie][Locked: Moonbark]', 'Your animal instincts leave you a little unable to reason. Add the following trait to MOONBARK mode:\r\n\r\n> **[Manipulate]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n**Add the following trait to your MOONFRENZY mode**:\r\n\r\n> You are totally immune to **[Manipulate]** rolls, but **[Control]** rolls against you are **[Tiered Up]**.'),
('batteryBuddy', 'BATTERY BUDDY', 'OTHER', 'VOIDROT', '[Template][Basic][Friendship is Power][Locked: Voidrot]', 'A fact of life living with voidrot is that your energy has to come from somewhere. Leeching off the power grid, spending your entire allowance on batteries at Trollmart, it\'s usually not pretty. If you\'re lucky, though, you can find a friend willing to keep you alive with a little more dignity. In an encounter with an allied **[Psionic]** troll, like a telekinetic burgundy or freaky eye blue, you may ask very nicely if they could please help you not die for a little longer. They may transfer up to 3 points of **[Boost]** to you as they like for **[Free]**, converting it to **[Reserve]** at a 1:1 ratio. It\'s like the chronic illness equivalent of your friend spotting you a clucknug meal at McMiracles when you don\'t get paid for another two days. On the other hand, you’re great to have around if someone’s got too much energy to spare- any **+APP** rolls made for PSIBURN by your allies are **[Legendary]**, and on a successful roll, you gain 2 **[Reserve]** as you feast upon the leftovers.'),
('batteryDrain', 'BATTERY DRAIN', 'OTHER', 'VOIDROT', '[Template][Advanced][Recharge: 2][Physical][Locked: Voidrot]', 'You\'ve lost the ability to retain energy, but that also makes you an excellent sapper! While not every troll is a psion, all living beings carry some amount of psionic energy that you can leech when things get going! Roll **+APP** to feast on the life energies of a target!\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Talk about indigestion! You take **1 [Psychic]** damage from the overwhelming lifeforce you just tried to munch.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: The energy is too much for your burnt out little battery brain to contain; you waste this action.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You graze them, and it snatches some energy as you pass. You gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: A firm grip lets you leech a significant amount of energy, and it sucks for the poor sap! Heh, sap. Choose one of the following effects.\r\n\r\n> **PSIONIC SAP**: Psionic energy is extremely energizing, and you know just how to take it! Your target’s next **[Psionic]** roll is at a -2 **[Nerf]**, and whenever they use it you gain **1 [Reserve]**!\r\n> **LETHARGIC LUMBER**: Slow down so you can speed up. Borrow their energy! Your target gains 1 **[Drag]** and you gain 1 **[Reserve]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Sluuuuuuuuuuurp. That’s not pretty, but it wakes you up! Choose one of the following effects.\r\n\r\n> **SPOT ME**: Your lifeforce, can you like… have some of it? Spot me another wipe of being alive bro. You take a positive Emotion or up to **2 [Boost]** from the target.\r\n> **UNDERPERFORMER**: You don’t have the energy for it tonight. Choose a **GOOD** effect and gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You latch on and don’t let go until you’ve had your fill. Choose one of the following effects.\r\n\r\n> **PSIONIC BLACKHOLE**: Psionic or not, this blackhole is leeching every bit of energy they have! You reset the target’s status effects, **[Boost]** and **[Drag]** as if they just began the encounter, and you gain **1 [Boost]** and **1 [Reserve]** for everything you consume. All **[Drag]** and all **[Boost]** are converted to **1 [Reserve]** rather than **1 [Reserve]** per **[Drag]** or **[Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **OVERPERFORMER**: You have just enough of your fill tonight. Choose a **GREAT** effect and gain **2 [Boost]**, or two **GOOD** effects.\r\n\r\n'),
('beaglepussAegis', 'BEAGLEPUSS AEGIS', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Goofball]', 'They can\'t prank you… you\'ve already PRANKED YOURSELF! Your masterpranksmanship has left you with a knack to outdo incoming pranks at the last moment, making them lose their impact in favour of something innocuous like slapping a beaglepuss on your face. All **[Chicanery]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**.'),
('bearerOfBadNews', 'BEARER OF BAD NEWS', 'OTHER', 'MAGE', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Recharge: 2][Locked: Mage]', 'Sometimes, you bring forth the perfect solution to the problem at hand. Every single time, however, people do not appreciate your efforts. It\'s tiring and annoying, but you keep trying anyway. You may pass a **PROBLEM SLEUTHING** result off to an ally at the cost of gaining 2 **[Drag]**. They get the benefit of knowing the broad strokes, but they don’t know what hoops you had to jump through to get to your conclusion.\r\n'),
('beastlyBurden', 'BEASTLY BURDEN', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Passive][Recharge: 2]', 'Your caste is often the one tasked with doing the heavy lifting, hard work or otherwise shedding blood sweat, and other bodily fluids in the name of labour. Even those who aren\'t actively labourers themselves will often find themselves being asked to throw in some elbow grease at the expense of others… so yeah, you do that. Whenever you would gain a **[Physical]** condition, you can choose to immediately take **2 [Drag]** instead to power through it. Y\'know, in the name of labour.'),
('beastMode', 'BEAST MODE', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Reaction][Recharge: 1][Locked: Nyanarchist]', 'Ring ring! Ring ring! Who’s that on your phone? It’s your inner beast, and it’s telling you that this is complete bullshit! Any time you are hit by a **GREAT** **[Strife]** roll, you can choose to become **[Enraged]** and activate BEAST MODE. You can use this to become **[Out Of Control]** if you are hit by a second **GREAT** roll later, but further **GREAT**s don’t do anything. Engaging BEAST MODE **[Heal]**s you for **1 HP**, and you regain an additional **1 HP** each time you land a **MAX**.'),
('beatdown', 'BEATDOWN', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Physical][Strife][Locked: Cool Kid]', 'This whole cool thing isn’t just for show. You’re actually extremely good at this whole combat thing. Whether it’s through training or martial instinct, you’re a savage with a sword, a king with a katana, a trailblazer with a trebuchet. And you NEVER miss. When you want to get your beatdown on, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: URGH- oh god, that wasn’t cool at all. Shit, fuck, you look like such a poser. You are **[Humiliated]** for **3 rounds** as you try to get your act together. Also, you take **2 [Somatic]** damage, fuck you.  \r\n\r\n**BAD**: Miscalculation, but not a terrible one. You land a blow and deal **1 [Somatic]** damage, but take **1 [Somatic]** damage in return as you put yourself in harm’s way. \r\n\r\n**OK**: Accuracy is your greatest boon, and you strike true- even if you stumble in the process. You deal **1 [Somatic]** damage, and take **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Direct hit. That’s **1 [Somatic]** damage, no drawbacks. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Not only a direct hit, but one that’s gonna leave them flat footed. You deal **1 [Somatic]** damage, and the opponent takes **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: DECAPITATION. Or, it would be, if this was an unfair and unbalanced game. Instead, this is a wounding hit, both to your opponent’s body and pride. You deal **2 [Somatic]** damage, **2 [Drag]**, and they’re too mad to roll anything except **[Physical]** moves for **2 turns** as they realize how much cooler you look in a fight than they do, and try to at least look the part.'),
('begoneAncientGuardians', 'BEGONE ANCIENT GUARDIANS', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Dungeoneer]', 'On your journeys through countless crypts, you’ve tangoed with the angry dead more than once before. Honestly,they’re not all that scary. An angry amalgamation of troll faces melting and reforming in the wall? Okay? Ratio + you’re dead + nobody asked. You are immune to **[Scared]**, and **[Strife]** and **[Chicanery]** moves by undead creatures or dungeon-y robots are **[Inept]** against you. So like, yes to weird clay pot robots, no to drones or soulbots.'),
('behold', 'BEHOLD!', 'OTHER', 'SUPERSCOUNDREL', '[Template][Advanced][Buildup: 2][Locked: Superscoundrel]', 'While others claim to be the pioneers of invention, you\'re the REAL DEAL! Your inventions can literally knock the socks off anyone you meet, which is a great way to gain generous patrons to fund your acts of superiority (stupidity). Once you start showing off and making sure everyone knows you\'re so cool, roll **+PSP** to reveal to them your brand new INVENTION...INATOR!\r\n\r\n**MIN**: AH SHIT!! That’s not the activation button! Your new invention comically blows itself apart, or uses the intended feature against itself, dealing **2 [Somatic]** damage to yourself, on top of giving the move a **[Cooldown: 2]**!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: That’s also not the button! You stick your hand in the electrical panel, and ELECTROCUTE YOURSELF!! This all plays out like a hilarious cartoon act, while in the meantime you take **1 [Somatic]** damage, and need to take **[Cooldown: 1]** as to rewire everything to avoid your sad little mistake.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You press the button! And... A little fake gun pops out of a compartment from the side, and a flag rolls out as it pulls the trigger. You must have wired it into the tampering failsafe.\r\n\r\n**GOOD: Aha! BEHOLD! The Write-a-name-here-inator! You may choose one quality of your new invention from the following features**:\r\n\r\n> **LASER BEAM**: You’ve brought upon the power of the sun! In the PALM OF YOUR HAND! You may attach this to your strife specibus and fire it at one opponent to set them **[Ablaze]**.\r\n> **IT\'S JUST A GUN**: It’s times like these where you’re really glad BRATATATA HAHA FUCK YOU!! Firing this has all opponents take **1 [Somatic]** damage!\r\n> **A BANDAID**: You’re pretty certain this was already invented, but you can put it over a wound to heal **1 HP**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You may choose two **GOOD** qualities for your new invention, or one **GREAT** quality.\r\n\r\n> **GO GO SOMETHING, TASER BEAM**: You’ve taken your sweet Laser pointer and have added a small prism to the front of it, you may choose to deal **1 [Somatic]** damage, or take on the effects of a BLAZEKIND weapon as a **[One-off]**.\r\n\r\n> **THE PIANO DROPPER-INATOR**: With a lot of persistence and about 15 minutes of time, you’ve unleashed a STUPENDOUS DRONE THAT CARRIES AROUND A GRAND PIANO AT ALL TIMES, should you wish to drop it on the enemy, it would deal **1 [Somatic]** damage and render them **[Floorbound]** since it’s a piano, dude.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You may choose two **GREAT** qualities for your new invention, or a **GREAT** and a **MAX**.\r\n\r\n> **THE RUNNING OUT OF NAMES-INATOR**: There’s no quantifiable name to explain this one! It’s seriously nothing elaborate, it’s just a giant arm that picks up the nearest bystander and hits the opponent with them to deal **2 [Somatic]** damage and leave them **[Trapped]** since you just dumped the guy on them.'),
('beKnown', 'BE KNOWN', 'VOID', 'VOID', '[Aspect][Advanced][Free][Reaction][Locked: Void]', 'You’ve spent a lot of your life putting up barriers and hiding yourself from everyone around you, lamenting your lack of relevance in the world— but by isolating yourself, you’re all but ensuring that you’ll never be able to do all the things you want to! You’re finally ready to talk to other people, and experience the mortifying ordeal of being known. Any time someone rolls to **[Analyze]** you, you can choose to just automatically make their roll a **GOOD** result without making them roll, letting them succeed but only on your terms. Doing so gives you **2 [Boost]**. This cannot be used when a troll is rolling to spot you while **[Hidden]** themselves.'),
('belowTheBelt', 'BELOW THE BELT', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Open][Chicanery]', 'Blue bitches don\'t FUCKING play around, so you better be ready for these dirty tactics because I\'m going to FUCK YOU UP!!! Nothing is unfair in a fight, bitch! You gain the following **GOOD** SHENANIGANS effects:\r\n\r\n> **DIRTY FIGHTING**: Blues don\'t fight fair :) You hit them hard and fast and vicious, giving them a **-2 [Nerf]** to **[Strife]** moves for **1 round**.\r\n\r\n> **OHOHO**: You laugh a knowing blue laugh, hand delicately over your mouth. Your opponent cannot be **[Smug]** or **[Confident]** for **3 rounds**, and if they are already, the effect is dispelled. \r\n\r\n> **BLIND EYES**: You go for the eyes, with a poke, a stab, or a well placed dose of pocket sand. They are **[Blinded]** for **one round**, OR if they have moves based on their eyes, relevant moves are disabled for **2 rounds**. \r\n\r\n> **KNEECAP**:  Yeah. You just fucking kneecap them. What? You just said nothing is unfair. They become **[Floorbound]** and cannot rise for at least **1 round**.'),
('bePatient', 'BE PATIENT!', 'SPACE', 'SPACE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Free][Locked: Space]', 'All good things come with time, and bad stuff isn’t forever. You know that better than anyone else! There’s no point in forcing change; after all, it IS inevitable! All negative conditions affecting you can be shrugged off for **[Free]** after **3 turns**, if you so choose them to be.'),
('beStrongHitStuff', 'BE STRONG HIT STUFF', 'OTHER', 'KNIGHT', '[Class][Advanced][Free][Locked: Knight]', 'Comfort in your own skin is a luxury some folks never achieve. Thankfully in working through your insecurity and brushing off your protective layers, you are now able to take genuine pride in who you are. What you do you do well, and faking it until you make it is no longer necessary: you’re already there. Pick either **IN SHINING ARMOR** or **JOUSTING**. Your **MAX** threshold for this decreases to 19. You cannot change which move you picked later. The first time in an encounter you get a **MAX** on one of these moves, you can choose to feel either **[Hopeful]** or **[Smug]**. Now how’s THAT for assurance?'),
('beyondTheBeenary', 'BEYOND THE BEENARY', 'OTHER', 'HACKERMAN', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Hackerman]', 'Life isn’t like a goddamn action movie! You’re not just wiggling your fingers on the clickity-clack machine and making anything happen! You’ve got specialties! Expertise! A specific pixelated subject that you have hyperfixated on, and have made your specialty. Everyone needs to understand while you can do anything (you’re a scripting god), blowing up palmhusks may not be your thing. You can take any **[Tech]** move from any Caste, though these moves cost 2 levels, not 1. Choose a branch below to specialize in from SCRIPT GRUBBIE. You now gain this extra effect for any rolls involving this field.\r\n\r\n> **INFOSNATCHING**: With this… you can know EVERYTHING. You gain the CIS **[Template]** move, SECRET FILES.\r\n\r\n> **DISMANTLERUPTING**: You\'ll make the internet totally unusable before you get caught! When you make a SCRIPT GRUBBIE roll, you can disable all other **[Tech]** moves for **2 rounds**.\r\n\r\n> **VIRUSCORCHERS**: Get owned, dipshit! Your virology surpasses the kind that just affects phones. You can make devices seep contagions! As a **[One-Off]**, you can expose the victim of a SCRIPT GRUBBIE roll to a randomly selected disease based **[Affliction]**. \r\n\r\n> **TOOLBAG**: Ayup! Just doing your place to make the internet nicer! On a **GREAT** SCRIPT GRUBBIE roll, roll 1d8. On an even, all trolls are **[Charmed]** by you as well as the normal effects. Yay!\r\n\r\n> **APIANARCHIST**: ARGH! IS— DID YOU MAKE THE PHONE TURN INTO A BEAST? You may use the Bronze XENODRUID move, except you use PSP, and the creature takes **+2 damage** from **[Electric]** sources. This has **[Buildup: 4]**.\r\n\r\n> **SCAMLORD**: Chaw haw haw! MONEY. Your Wealth Level increases by 1, permanently! If you were already **Ultrarich**, you gain **+1 LUX** from MONEYMAKERY instead.'),
('bigSexyBrain', 'BIG SEXY BRAIN', 'MIND', 'MIND', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Mind]', 'Yes, you do the studying. Yes, you do the thinking. The threshold for SIMPLE DEDUCTION is reduced from a **GREAT** to a **GOOD** requirement on a **[Analyze]** roll to gain the bonus. Additionally, you gain a **+2 [Buff]** to rolling **[Analyze]** moves on account of your big sexy brain muscles.'),
('bigShot', 'BIG SHOT', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Penpusher]\r\n', 'Nobody works harder than you do. Literally, nobody. Whether you\'re an exceptionally dedicated intern or a Super^8-Exec, you are renowned around the office for your dedication to the craft. And for good reason! Seriously, holy shit! You gain access to HERO MODE through the stat you gained a [Talent] in with WORKPLACE WHIZ. You also gain the following benefit depending on your department.\r\n\r\n> **ACCOUNTING (+RAS)**: HAHAHAHA. TAXATION IS THEFT? SURE, AND YOU\'RE A MASTER CRIMINAL. At the end of every combat encounter you win with another troll, you gain **Treasure I**. That\'s the BULGEGAGGER TAX. Loser. Enemy trolls with a lower Wealth than you feel **[Dread]** in your presence.\r\n\r\n> **TROLL RESOURCES (+PLC)**: Mmmm, no. This isn\'t professional at all. Troll opponents take **1 [Drag]** every time they try to **[Strife]** you until you use a **[Physical]** roll that affects them. You can always JAB, even after a fight breaks out.\r\n\r\n> **ASSISTANT (+GRA)**: YES BOSS! You can roll any moves your allies have on their sheets, aside from **[Ultra], [Psionic]** or **[Magic]** ones.\r\n\r\n> **ACQUISITIONS (+APP)**: Buy em cheap, buy ‘em in bulk, and buy em NOW. You have **16 VP**, not 10, and can purchase items on the fly. LUX items cost 1 less than normal (min. 1).\r\n\r\n> **INSURANCE AGENT (+GRT)**: You are so insanely corrupt it\'s kind of funny. You are considered an honorary sib by Juggalo Mafiosos; you may take the Purple Mafioso tree as a **[Template]**, and gain the **[Entry]** now. All rolls in that tree use **+GRT**, but you can never be higher than a Concierge, and you can\'t get the **[Ultra]**. You can start your own Insurance Agency with other Teals only; in which case yeah you can be the Don. Still can\'t have the **[Ultra]**.\r\n\r\n> **SALES (+HUB)**: KA-CHING! You are SO magnetic, babe. You gain access to PERFECT PULCHRITUDE as well as HARDCORE HUBRIS, and you can use HERO MODE one additional time per encounter (but never in the same stat). Your WORDPLAY rolls can never be **[Inept], [Tiered Down] or [Nerfed]**.\r\n\r\n> **ADMINISTRATION (+PSP)**: You are so, so, SO absorbed into your administration work that it\'s kind of crazy. Are you even a person? Or are you a conduit of data? You may become **[Hyperfocused]** as an action; when like this, you are also **[Quickened]**, but can only use this extra action to use **[Mental]** rolls.\r\n\r\n> **OFFICE WARLOCK (+IMG)**: AEIHYOOOUGH! FOR THE OFFICE! You are well learned in the arts of Beurarcana, and evildoers had best beware of you. You gain access to the ASTROSORCERER or CTHONOMANCER Template, gaining the [Entry] now; it does not count towards your template limit, nor your **[Ultra]** limit. If you already had the **[Entry]**, take another move from the tree. If you already had all the moves, you may take the other Template\'s **[Entry], [Basic], [Advanced]** or **[Ultra]** now.\r\n'),
('blackHole', 'BLACK HOLE', 'OTHER', 'GRIMDARK', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Eerie][Locked: Grimdark]', 'The darkness inside you pushes, always, bleeding out the edges of you and sinking itself into those around you like hooks, tearing away pieces of their souls and devouring them. When you are **[Bloodied]** or **[Gushing]**, the effect fills the air with a dark miasma of void that settles on all combatants. At the top of the round, each non-Grimdark combatant loses 1 stat point at random, rolling 1d8 to decide what. If the selected stat is already 0, roll again. \n\nIf you have taken all moves in this template, this effect doubles to 2 stat points per round. Additionally, as the last of your self preservation slips away, you gain a new ability. As an action you may target yourself, tearing open a hole in your being and becoming **[Bloodied]**.'),
('blasphemingBitch', 'BLASPHEMING BITCH', 'OTHER', 'CTHONOMANCER', '[Template][Advanced][Locked: Cthonomancer]', 'Turns out evil, dark magick makes literally every religious movement on this planet hate you. Seems kind of unfair to you. All you did was spit on every tenet all three major religious movements on Alternia have. On the bright side, their entirely undeserved scorn for you means you can totally bitch right back at them! Choose a specific faith that has earned your ire to justifiably rip them off. \r\n\r\n> **ORTHODOX DECOMPOSTIONISTS**: They have such crocogator tears for the undead! It’s so cringy! Thankfully, you’ve totally looted their lame ass candle stands they leave unguarded like idiots. Lol. You always have an Everlit Candle that costs no **VP**. In lieu of the usual effects, other **[Eerie]** trolls instead take **3 [Drag]** when it is lit as your dark magicks warp the candle.\r\n\r\n> **CLOISTERED JADES**: So soft and squishy, you’re pretty sure you could sacrifice them and “level” “up” the amount of attention you’re getting from The Unperceivable Blotches Watching immediately. You always have a vial of Rainbow Syrup. Rainbow Syrup is a **0 VP** **[Consumable]** item that when drunk **[Heals] 2 HP** to Cloistered Jades and Rainbowdrinkers, or deals **2 [Holy]** Damage to any other **[Eerie]** targets. You can throw it for the same effect as a **GOOD** **[Strife]** roll.\r\n\r\n> **MIRTHFUL MANIACS**: Kind of scary not gonna lie, but that just means they have it coming all the more! Their facepaint is surprisingly useful after all. You always have a Makeup Kit which costs **0 VP**. When equipped as a **[Passive]** **[Equipment]** item by painting your body with it, Clown **[Magic]** is **[Inept]** against you, and you do not receive Emotions from their **[Magic]** attacks. \r\n\r\n> **ASTROSORCERERS**: Not exactly a religious faith, but their nookbitch wriggler magic is irritating enough to deserve appropriation anyways. Get magic from an actual god, not from the stars! Loser! Your presence blots out the light of the stars in the ethereal world around you, causing the success thresholds of Astrosorcerer **[Magic]** to be increased by 1, meaning a **GREAT** is on a 15, a **GOOD** on a 12, and so on. Upon gaining FAVORED FIEND, they are increased by 2 instead.'),
('blatantLies', 'BLATANT LIES', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Passive]', 'Highbloods have crazy weird stereotypes about lowbloods. They crawl into little holes! They eat phones! They have bat wings and shoot lasers from their eyes! Of course, you\'re willing to play with these assumptions… especially when they\'re made by dipshit rich people! If a troll of the **Well-Off** Wealth or higher gets an **OK** or lower roll to **[Analyze]** you, it **[Tiers Down]** to a **MIN**. These trolls also don\'t know when you lie to them if they use a QUESTION WORDPLAY roll. Whenever they get a **MIN** on an **[Analyze]** roll against you, you get a **[Free]** **GOOD [Analyze]** roll. Easy to learn about someone based on the assumptions they make.'),
('blindFury', 'BLIND FURY', 'RAGE', 'RAGE', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Rage]', 'You have a problem with tunnel vision when you’re angry; all you care about is destruction. If you like, your eyes permanently slide to an orange hue, and when you are angry, they glow a furious red. While **[Out Of Control]**, you gain the **[Permablind]** condition; not out of actual blindness, but more out of seriously entering a fury state. If you’re already **[Permablind]**, you gain **2 [Boost]** when you first become **[Out Of Control]**.'),
('bluhBluhHugeLich', 'BLUH BLUH HUGE LICH', 'OTHER', 'SHADOWDROPPER', '[Ultra][Passive][Eerie][Locked: Shadowdropper]', 'Okay, so, you accidentally became an all powerful necromantic Spellcaster with an army of undead minions. It happens, no big deal. You gain access to HERO MODE through your INCREDIBLE IMAGINATION. Your necromantic power means your own **[Drag]** is no longer affected by NECROMANTIC DEBUTANT. You are immune to the effects of Emotions; you\'re pretty sure you\'re beyond that by now, albeit you may still possess them. As an action you may allow an Emotion you\'re feeling to take effect once more as you draw upon a former trollmanity, but doing so allows a **[Negative]** Emotion to take effect as well should you gain or possess one. Emotions you permanently possess do not need to be activated. Every **3 turns**, rather than use a move normally, you can turn it into a **[Lengthy]** action and cast it with your **[Magic]**, rolling with **+IMG** instead. Rather than GRIEF, use SPECTRAL FIST! Rather than WORDPLAY, use GHOUL\'S CRY. You get the flavor. When you do this, the move **[Tiers Up]**, even to a **MAX** if applicable. If it’s already a **MAX**, you gain **2 [Boost]** instead. Most importantly, you literally have control over life and death. If the remains of a troll are brought to you, you can bring them back to life, no matter how long dead they are. However, their return is not necessarily an easy one; they\'re exposed to the DROPSHADOW SYNDROME **[Affliction]**, and should they fail to survive, they may soon find themselves in your position. They\'ll always bear some evidence of their return; miscoloured eyes or hair, odd skin… you name it. Every time you bring them back, they\'re an additional stage deeper into the **[Affliction]**, meaning they\'re more and more likely to suffer from it. The necromantic ritual takes a day of **[Downtime]** to finish, and is completed under the midday sun; the revived troll is **[Blinded]** at the start of their next encounter.'),
('bodymodpack', 'BODYMODPACK', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Passive][Locked: Cyberpunk]', 'Wow! Cool robot hand! You really dig this whole cyborg aesthetic, and are fully willing to commit to it. Left arm, you served well. CHOP. You gain the **[Entry]** and both **[Basic]** moves from the ROBOT Template now with the CYBORG flavor, even though you aren’t a robot. You are not, however, weak to **[Electricity]** and the ROBOT template does not count towards your two Template limit. Folks who are Soulbots and Robots cannot take Cyborg options in addition to their own.\r\n'),
('boo', 'BOO!', 'OTHER', 'GHOST', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Eerie][Locked: Ghost]', 'AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA!!! You’re EXTREMELY scary! You can take an action to go WOOGA WOOGA WOOGA at someone, scaring the absolute shit out of them. They gain the **[Scared]** condition. Any time someone is **[Terrified]** around you, you gain some serious delight; what’s better than a nice, steaming meatbag of fear? You gain **2 [Boost]**, and an additional **2 [Boost]** every time an additional **[Scared]** tag is stacked onto them.'),
('boonbuckaneer', 'BOONBUCKANEER', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Downtime]', 'You’ve installed a new client onto your flip-phone or computer, and when you break stuff, it… explodes into dust, sometimes! And with that weird tech around, you can refine that dust into… stuuuuff? You can roll a **[Downtime]** move called CLIENTBUFF which allows you to smash stuff up and gain BUILDGRIST. You also gain BUILDGRIST equal to an eighth of the level of a foe rounded up when you defeat them in combat (or an eighth of the level of a team in a TEAM STRIFE, or the effective team level of a monster when you beat it in combat too). When you want to look for BUILDGRIST, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Argh! You broke something you weren’t supposed to break! You lose an item worth **2 LUX** or higher. Great work, genius!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Uh… yeah, kind of a waste of time. Maybe you just suck at this? Your next CLIENTBUFF roll is **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Nnnnnothing. Whoo! \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Nice work! You get **1 BUILDGRIST**. You can spend BUILDGRIST in the following ways…\r\n\r\n> **LUXURY ITEMS**: You can replicate any item worth **LUX** for an effective cost of **1 BUILDGRIST** less than the **LUX** you’d spend (for example, a **2 LUX** item costs 1 BUILDGRIST).\r\n\r\n> **TOWERING FLOORS (2 BUILDGRIST)**: You build up an extra level onto your house, or onto an existing hive! This deploys instantly. The first three HIVECRAFTING upgrades you put on this floor cost **1 LUX** less than normal (and therefore, 2 BUILDGRIST less than normal). \r\n\r\n> **INCREDIBLE ITEMS (3 BUILDGRIST)**: Taking inspiration from what you’ve seen on Alternia, you create a replica of an item from any Wealth Level without needing to make a BIG BUY. The item costs **1 VP** less than normal, though it looks nothing like the original item, since it’s got that trademark SBURB style.\r\n\r\n> **ECTOCOMPANION (3 BUILDGRIST)**: Look at this sweet DOG you just created! How cool is it that you made a DOG? You love DOGs. You gain access to the CUSTODIAN COMPANION move for an ectocreature rather than just your actual parent. This particular ectocreature only has 2 features, but they can be anything, not just mundane effects your boring ass dad has.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: AWESOME WORK! You get **2 BUILDGRIST**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: GUYS, YOU’RE NEVER GONNA BELIEVE THIS. YOU GET **3 BUILDGRIST**. THIS IS THE MOST UNPREDICTABLE MOVE RESULT IN SUBGRUBS AND SNAZZARDS 6TH EDITION CREATED BY THE SUBGRUBS AND SNAZZARDS SNITCHZONE TEAM.'),
('boop', 'BOOP!', 'OTHER', 'WITCH', '[Class][Basic][Free][Locked: Witch]\r\n', 'Sometimes when you come up against a problem, all you need to do is think creatively… or refuse to play by the rules! What do you mean that guy\'s wearing an armored vest? Just hit him in the head! You can spend **[Boost]** to circumvent **[Resistance]** of any kind, at a rate of 2 **[Boost]** per 1 point of **[Resistance]** circumvented. Common sense is the greatest magic of all.\r\n'),
('bossyboots', 'BOSSYBOOTS', 'LIFE', 'LIFE', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Life]', 'Whether it’s through anxiously given and insistent advice or a self-assured knowledge that you know better than anyone else, you can be a little pushy with your opinions! You can roll multiple WORDPLAY rolls in a round. When you fail a WORDPLAY roll, you can try a second WORDPLAY roll with your next action; this WORDPLAY roll is **[Tiered Up]**. If you fail this second WORDPLAY roll, your next WORDPLAY roll is **[Tiered Up]** twice, bringing **OK** Rolls to **GREAT** rolls. This chain of consistent WORDPLAY can continue stacking until you either roll something else or succeed.'),
('bounceRightBack', 'BOUNCE RIGHT BACK', 'OTHER', 'HEIR', '[Class][Basic][One-Off][Passive][Locked: Heir]', 'URK! OH GOG HERE IT IS! THE ALL IS LOST MOMENT, IT’S… Honestly not that bad? Like, yeah, it’s not great, but it’s not terrible either. Now that you think about it, you can probably come back from this. Yeah everything will be a-okay! Either through your immense optimism or the fact you’re a magnet for bullshit, negative conditions don’t get you as down as they would other people. When you first gain one of these effects in an encounter, you gain **[Boost]** to cushion the blow.\r\n\r\n- **[Base] [Negative]** Emotions give 2 **[Boost]**.\r\n- **[Negative]** status effects give 3 **[Boost]**.\r\n- **[Heightened] [Negative]** Emotions give 4 **[Boost]**. '),
('brainboxSpectacles', 'BRAINBOX SPECTACLES', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Passive][Locked: Bookworm]', 'Hey. Player. I\'m talking to you right now. Did you give this character glasses? I bet you did. Glasses are a shorthand way to say \"this character is smart\". But hey, maybe you didn\'t! Maybe they\'re a stealthy nerd who forgoes the visual language of glasses! It\'s a binary though, so pick one of the following options:\r\n\r\n**BESPECTACLED**: Look at this NERD with their GLASSES! You gotta be careful not to hit them too hard- you wouldn\'t want to break them, you know! Opponents have a **-2 [Nerf]** to **[Strife]** rolls against you.\r\n\r\n**UNADORNED**: Oh my god— they don\'t have glasses! This completely throws you off! You don\'t know what to expect now! Opponents have a **-2 [Nerf]** to **[Flourish]** rolls around you.'),
('brainGhost', 'BRAIN GHOST', 'HOPE', 'HOPE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Hope]', 'You can never forget the people you’re fighting for; your friends. No, really— you can’t. You develop a Brain Ghost of one of your friends: an imaginary(?) friend who reflects the best in your companions, but helps you stay grounded. Whether this manifests as you imagining their voices nagging you, or a full-bodied apparition who appears when you need it most depends on you; either way, when you’re in a tough spot, your friend’s voice guides you. Whenever you get an **OK** or lower **[Mental]** roll, you can reroll it with another action as your Brain Ghost tells you how it’s done. You use the stat and any **[Talent]** of your friend in this second roll rather than your own. You can’t change this BRAIN GHOST unless something significant happens.'),
('broadResearch', 'BROAD RESEARCH', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Bookworm]', 'You\'re quite the canny little thing, you know! And these trolls… strange as they are, you have an idea by now of how they do things. In fact, you\'re gonna incorporate their ways of thinking into your own! You can take any tree of a troll caste that uses **+PSP** as a Template, except you can only take the **[Entry]**, one **[Basic]** and one **[Advanced]**. You gain the **[Entry]** now. You can\'t take trees that you\'re physically incapable of, such as Network Golds, but you can take trees that offer a choice of **[Talents]** so long as you only take the **+PSP** option.'),
('brokenBattery', 'BROKEN BATTERY', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive][Psionic]', 'Not all psions are trained equal. It’s not terribly rare for a particularly unlucky troll to be born with psionics that don’t function just right; or to have trained into them terribly enough that it would take a miracle to fix their form. Whatever the reason is, you’re one of them, and your **[Psionic]** powers suck! Whenever you roll a **[Psionic]** move, roll a 1d2 for **[Free]**. On a 1, you gain a **+2 [Buff]** to your roll, over roll limit if possible. On a 2, you gain a **-3 [Nerf]** to your roll. You can spend **[Boost]** to stabilize yourself, **2 [Boost]** for a turn without needing to roll a 1d2.'),
('bronzebo', 'BRONZEBO', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Open][Manipulate]', 'Aw, shucks, don\'t mind me, partner, I\'m just a silly ol\' Bronze! You\'re well aware that your folksy charm is alluring, and you can weaponize the stereotypes your caste has received to get what you want. When you start the long con and act like a big sexy hunk of meat to get what you want, roll **+PLC**.\n\n**MIN**: No. Nononono, you can\'t do this. It\'s DEMEANING! Fuck, man, you\'re desperate, but not THAT desperate, you know?! Fuck! Oh, you\'re so embarrassed. You become **[Humiliated]**. \n\n**BAD**: Hhhhgh- no, nonono, time out. You can do this, just- just give you a moment. You\'re **[Embarrassed]**. Eurgh.\n\n**OK**: Ahyu- aw, fuck, voice crack. You can do this, you swear, just give a moment- nothing happens this turn.\n\n**GOOD**: Ahyuk! Yessiree, you sure are a sexy moron, 100%! Your attitude disarms and charms the opponent, and gets you ready for what you need to do next. Your next WORDPLAY roll against the opponent is **[Tiered Up]**. \n\n**GREAT**: Niiiice! Not only do you convince the opponent you\'re a sweet, thoughtless idiot, but you totally make them think you\'re kinda hot too! You get a **GOOD** roll, and the opponent is **[Charmed]** by you.\n\n**MAX**: Oh, wow, it REALLY works on them, huh? Like, wow. Either you\'re really good at this or they’ve got a type. You get a **GOOD** roll, but the opponent is **[Fascinated]** by you.'),
('brothersInArms', 'BROTHERS IN ARMS', 'BLOOD', 'BLOOD', '[Aspect][Advanced][Free][Locked: Blood]', 'You’ve come to remember that the best way to lead isn’t just to throw orders down and expect people to follow them; you need to inspire people to be the best versions of themselves. Whenever you’re in an encounter with an ally, choose one (willing) person to be said ally as a **[Free]** action and any **[Boost]** gained by either party is given to both of you.'),
('bugfix2077', 'BUGFIX 2.077', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Locked: Cyberpunk]', 'You\'ve started messing with your brain! Why? (Long, drawn-out pause)... it\'s cool, and seemed like the cyberpunk thing to do. Of course, this has left you a buggy mess… but it bugs out other people too, thanks to your subtle altering of electrodes in the air. **[Mental]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**. Any time you or someone in an encounter around you receives an **[Emotion]** (yourself included), you may choose to bug out, rewiring the emotion. Roll 2d8, and select from the below list:\r\n\r\n> 2. Roll again, twice.\r\n> 3. **[Out of Control]**\r\n> 4. **[Giggling]**\r\n> 5. **[Dread]**\r\n> 6. **[Confused]**\r\n> 7. **[Charmed]**\r\n> 8. **[Scared]**\r\n> 9. **[Enraged]**\r\n> 10. **[Overwhelmed]**\r\n> 11. **[Proud]**\r\n> 12. **[Joy]**\r\n> 13. **[Smug]**\r\n> 14. **[Brave]**\r\n> 15. **[Serious]**\r\n> 16. Choose an Emotion yourself, and **[Heighten]** it.'),
('buggedBugs', 'BUGGED BUGS', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'CIS', '[Template][Basic][Locked: CIS]', 'Iiiiinteresting. Very interesting. You know that people don\'t just cause a ruckus online; they do it offline too. You gain access to the following items, which you can purchase with LUX:\r\n\r\n> **SPYBUG (1 LUX)**: SPYBUGS allow you to listen in on trolls on your WATCHLIST, and hear what they say around their hive. You don\'t need to inform the player or Clouder of your decision to bug a character, but you must note it down in private somewhere with a timestamp to prove that you had done so. This bug lasts for a single encounter that you aren\'t in, and records what is said in said encounter. If they say something worthy of raising their WATCHLIST POINTS over, you may do so, but choose your time right before revealing you bugged them; don\'t want them to clamming up by giving them a notification on their phone that\'s like HEY GET WATCHLISTED. \r\n\r\n> **SPYDRONE (3 LUX)**: SPYDRONES are the eyes and ears of the CIS, more permanent than Spybugs and suitable for observing trolls over longer periods of time. On a successful RUMORHUNGER [Downtime] roll, you may dispatch a SPYDRONE to follow a target in addition to the usual results; the SPYDRONE will tail them for their next three encounters, or until the target successfully ABSCONDS from or destroys it. While it tails them, you may control the SPYDRONE remotely if needed or wanted. Alternatively, you may deploy a SPYDRONE or other robot from this move in combat as a **[One-Off]** action; if deployed like this, it takes its turn after yours in the turn order.\r\n\r\n> **ROBO-PIGEON (3 LUX)**: ROBO-PIGEONS are another model of Imperial surveillance bot, depending on your personal preferences for government robospyware. You can deploy them for surveillance or combat as with SPYDRONES; unlike SPYDRONES, you must use an action on your turn to command them and choose actions for their next turn, or else they just run their default bird-imitation subroutine until further notice.\r\n\r\n> **ROBOFROG (2 LUX)**: This one isn’t just a surveillance bot - it’s also a friend! :) You can still deploy it for surveillance or combat as with SPYDRONES, of course. It’ll hop around and cheer you on!\r\n\r\n'),
('bugWings', 'BUG WINGS', 'OTHER', 'MUTANT', '[Mutant][Cullbait][Passive]', 'From your back unfold a large pair of insectoid wings; sometimes they are different, but are most commonly insect-like. This lets you begin **[Flying]** as a **[Free]** action, and you are **[Talented]** at **+GRA** rolls when your wings are out. Additionally, you can Abscond for **[Free]**, and your opponent cannot roll a **[Reaction]** to stop your Abscond unless they are **[Flying]** as well. While your wings are hidden, you instead take a **-1 [Nerf]** to every **[Physical]** roll. You must take great care to hide them. This mutation loses its **[Cullbait]** tag if you are a Cloistered Jade, since it is considered a blessing from the Grandmother Grub.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('bulletTime', 'BULLET TIME', 'TIME', 'TIME', '[Aspect][Advanced][One-Off][Reaction][Analyze][Locked: Time]', 'You’ve spent your whole life rushing, trying to accomplish things, trying to get stuff done- but you’ve recently learned to take a step back and reflect. Pausing in your constant march forward has helped you realize that hey, maybe there’s smarter ways of accomplishing what you need to do? When you’re about to be subject to an incoming **[Strife]** roll, you can feel time slow down a little as you figure out the best way to overcome the situation. When you take a moment in slow-mo to think things through, roll **+PSP**.\n\n**MIN**: Oh, fuck this. You slink back into your old habits and just try to go in for the kill- and instead, you take the full force of the incoming attack. The opponent’s attack is **[Tiered Up]**.\n\n**BAD**: Instead of reflecting, you just hesitate— and that’s all that needs to happen for the incoming attack to land.\n\n**OK**: You don’t dodge the attack, but you have a moment of realization; you get a **[Free]** **GOOD** PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll against the target.\n\n**GOOD**: You manage to parry the incoming attack, if even only a little as you suss ‘em out a little. Their attack is **[Tiered Down]**, and you get a **[Free]** **GOOD** PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll against the target.\n\n**GREAT**: You read their attack coming from a mile away, and you dodge it entirely— and you get a **[Free]** **GOOD** PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll against them! Surprise!\n\n**MAX**: Whoa. Time almost slows down to a complete halt, and you take a moment to totally psychoanalyze them before kicking their ass. You get a **[Free]** **GOOD** **[Strife]** roll against the target, dodge their attack completely, and get a **[Free]** **GREAT** PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll against them.'),
('burningBliss', 'BURNING BLISS', 'OTHER', 'FIREFUELER', '[Template][Basic][Mental][Locked: Firefueler]', 'A scary but oddly effective technique of Firefuelers to help keep dark influence or dissident thoughts at bay is to set themselves on fire, letting the flames burn away the impurities of the mind. 451 degrees seems to do the trick. As an action, you can set yourself **[Ablaze]**. While **[Ablaze]** from any source, you only take damage every other turn starting from your next turn and take a -3 **[Nerf]** to all **[Mental]** and **[Analyze]** rolls. Additionally, you are **[Inept]** at all **PROBLEM SLEUTHING** rolls. Your mindless inferno is not without benefit, though. You gain 1 **[Verbal]** and **[Psychic] [Resistance]** while **[Ablaze]**, and every time a creature is set **[Ablaze]**, including yourself, you get 1 **[Hold]** to get an automatic **GOOD PROBLEM SLEUTHING** roll to either **PREPARE**, **SPOT**, or **REASSESS** as the fire guides you, like a sixth sense. You can only get **[Hold]** once from each creature.\r\n'),
('burningDownTheHive', 'BURNING DOWN THE HIVE', 'OTHER', 'FIREFUELER', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Firefueler]\r\nPrerequisite: Must be a Rust, Bronze, or Goldblood\r\n', 'You are a member of the Firefuelers, an all lowblood group of fire-based troopers that work alongside other ORGS when more firepower (heh) is needed. It’s an alienating job, but if it keeps the highbloods off your back and secures a slightly better future in space, then why not take the chance? You wake up, don your suit, heat up your flamer, and get to work burning dissidents, Eeries, and anything else your superiors point you at. You may be low, but Imperial insignia is not something most trolls would rage against without serious consideration. You have conditional authority over all non-Org trolls of Teal and below, and Drones will not target you while in your ORG Uniform, which you gain now for free (even though it\'s not an official ORG but you really try so hard to pretend it is), as well as a flair on all social media marking you as a member of the Firefuelers. In addition, you also gain a special-issue **FLAMEFLINGER**, a firearm tailored to your liking which comes with a free **BURNKIND** Strife Abstrata. This specibus cannot be given another Strife Abstrata. Moreover, as an incentive to stay loyal and do your job, you go up one Wealth level. Finally, whenever you or another target in an encounter is set **[Ablaze]**, you gain 1 **[Boost]** immediately and 1 **[Boost]** for every other round that they stay burning as the sight of fire ignites pride within your loyal soul.\r\n'),
('busyBusyBusy', 'BUSY BUSY BUSY!', 'OTHER', 'MAID', '[Class][Basic][Free][One-Off][Locked: Maid]', 'Okay, your chores are set. Time to work overtime! Do this, and do this, but not that! Keep going! Clocks ticking! No distractions, NO DISTRACTIONS!!! When you set your mind to something or are given a job to do, you work tirelessly at it, which makes setbacks and distractions all the more irritating. You may make yourself **[Quickened]**. When you become **[Quickened]**, choose a tag, like **[Chicanery]** or **[Manipulate]**. You can use the extra action to use a move with that tag. If you already used a move with your chosen tag in that turn, you may still use the extra action for a move with the tag, except it will be **[Inept]**. However, you may also use the extra action for a move that doesn\'t have the tag... buuuut doing so will make you **[Stressed]**. Doing so AGAIN will make you **[Agitated]** and remove **[Quickened]**. Fuck, fuck, FUCK- your flow! Augh, it\'s all RUINED now. This extra action cannot be predetermined or affected by **WORKING RELATIONSHIP**, nor can the [Inept] be mitigated by **STUMBLE FORWARD**. You have enough on your plate already, stop thinking and just get your moves done!'),
('butterflyEffect', 'BUTTERFLY EFFECT', 'OTHER', 'HEIR', '[Class][Basic][Magic][One-Off][Locked: Heir]\r\n', 'You’ve got so much of your aspect that it tends to rub off on the people you’re around - encouraging them to be a little more caring, maybe, or bringing out the fire they didn’t know they had within them. As an action, you can share one of your **[Basic] [Aspect]** moves, or the **[Unlock]**, with a teammate. They gain any of its start-of-encounter effects now, and you both have the move for the rest of the encounter.\r\n'),
('butYouFailedToAccountForThis', 'BUT YOU FAILED TO ACCOUNT FOR… THIS!', 'OTHER', 'BARD', '[Class][Basic][Reaction][Recharge: 4][Locked: Bard]', 'Hm? Oh? What was that? They thought they were in THEIR world playing by THEIR rules? Heeheehee! HA HA HA! NOPE! INCORRECT, BITCH! This is YOUR hall of mirrors, this is YOUR house of cards, and it’s YOUR. CHAOS. TO SOW! You point out something the opponent didn\'t realize until too late (your knife bent on my hidden armor, DUMBASS!) that totally changes their plan. You can either re-roll one dice roll you made or force your opponent to re-roll theirs and take that instead!\r\n\r\n\r\n'),
('bweewaaaahBweewaaaaaah', 'BWEEWAAAAH BWEEWAAAAAAH', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'BUSTIN', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Bustin’]', 'That iconic siren lets all ghosts around know that they should have stayed dead! You smash into the scene with your sweet ride, and hunt down specters with ease. You gain access to the following **[Vehicle]** modification.\r\n\r\n> **BUSTMOBILE (3 LUX)**: EVILDOERS BEWARE! This special vehicle is a phantom’s worst nightmare! When you’re riding this vehicle, you can make **[Strife]** rolls against **[Eerie]** trolls as though you weren’t in the vehicle. Mostly cuz you’re leaning out the window and waving your BUSTIN’ weapon around. Additionally, the sirens blaring make all **[Eerie]** trolls in the vicinity **[Scared]**, even if they normally could not be.\r\n\r\n'),
('caegartrap', 'CAEGARTRAP', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Gamblignant]', 'You\'re taking your first steps into sending people into spiralling debt, my friend! All while lining your own pockets, naturally. You gain the CAEGARTRAP Hive Upgrade, which you can add for free to your hive or a new building you can upgrade separately. This may be a poker hall, a musclebeast-wrestling-betting ring, an arcade, slot machines, a casino, a game show… anything that people might go to in hopes of spending Caegars to make Caegars! Alas… you don\'t play fair, and your SWINDELRY may lead to players being totally out of cash by the end of their visit! When they want to gamble, they must roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: What a shaaaaaame! Who could have foreseen this? They lost everything! The roller gains the **Destitute** Wealth level. You gain **2 LUX** for every wealth level they drop.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Aw, friend, bad luck! You\'ll do better next time, though! The roller drops a Wealth level. You gain **2 LUX**!\r\n\r\n**OK**: No wins yet, champ? That\'s okay! You\'ve got this! You gain **1 LUX**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Wow, you won something! That\'s great, you must be lucky today! The roller goes up a Wealth Level for a week.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: What a win! You must be on a winning streak, keep it up! The roller goes up two Wealth Levels for a week!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: HOLY F— YOU GOT THE JACKPOT? UHHHH. The roller becomes **Ultrarich** for a week, and you go down a Wealth Level!'),
('calledAttacks', 'CALLED ATTACKS', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Open][Recharge: 2]', 'Watch out! You\'re charging up an ULTRA MEGA GRIEF ATTACK! Your caste maybe has a little bit of a flair for the dramatic, which puts off other castes sometimes. But to be honest, being loud and proud is just… part of you. You can spend an action to CALL OUT YOUR ATTACK. You must state the move you intend on rolling next in character, and say it LOUD. On your next turn, if you make that roll, it\'s **[Tiered Up]**. If you roll anything else, it\'s **[Tiered Down]**. Don\'t lie about your attacks, man! Not cool!'),
('callForBackup', 'CALL FOR BACKUP', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'TIT', '[Template][Basic][Locked: TIT]', 'You aren\'t going to be kicking anyone\'s ass anytime soon. You\'re just here to keep an eye on the weird shit. Whenever you see a **[Cullbait]** troll, you may choose to immediately alert a CIS, HET, Cullscout, Bustin\' or Orphaner troll, whichever is most applicable to the situation. They can get here in **2 rounds**.'),
('callOfTheWild', 'CALL OF THE WILD', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][One-Off][Manipulate][Locked: Nyanarchist]', 'Aren’t you tired of being civilized? Don’t you just want to go wild out? You LOVE being a weird little nature scamp and can’t understand why anyone else would want to dress in normal people clothes and eat cooked food. This leaves you to often taunt your friends and enemies alike, tempting them into giving up their place in society and just act like an animal or something! When you want to urge someone to forget about this whole capitalism thing and come climb a tree, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Midway through your taunts, you start questioning the safety of your lifestyle. Living like an animal doesn’t sound appealing at all! You are **[Confused]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: They hang up on your call of the wild. Rude!\r\n\r\n**OK**: You are a little annoying at best. The opponent gets **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Yeah, that’ll show them! Society sucks! Come eat this shit you dug from the ground! Nyahhhh! Your opponent is **[Confused]** for **2 rounds**. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You bring up some great points. Why SHOULD trolls put themselves through capitalism if there’s food right here in the jungle? They become **[Confused]** as they keep questioning their life.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: HEY, ACTUALLY, MAYBE THIS WHOLE SOCIETY THING IS KINDA STUPID. Maybe they SHOULD give up life and go live as a forest goblin. The target becomes **[Dumbfounded]** for **3 rounds**, and then **[Confused]** as they reel under this immense philosophical guilt.'),
('callToArms', 'CALL TO ARMS', 'OTHER', 'KNIGHT', '[Class][Basic][One-Off][Manipulate][Locked: Knight]', 'Listen, morale is low right now. Everyone’s exhausted (you think), nobody knows what to do (you think). You need to push things forward and inspire folks. Otherwise, how will they ever do it without you? Brothers, sisters, allies, lend me your strength and CHARGE! You can use this move on yourself. When you want to inspire you and your allies to ever higher levels of badassery, roll **+PLC** OR **+GRT** OR **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You fall on your face with a comical quack sound effect. Everyone cringes at you and takes **1 [Drag]**. You\'re **[Floorbound]** too, which sucks.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Yeah, dude, they know. They were already killing the thing. Nothing really happens. \r\n\r\n**OK**: Yeah! Everyone gets **+1 [Boost]**!\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: YEAH! Everyone gets **+3 [Boost]**!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: The masses hear you and they are out for blood. Your entire party becomes **[Hopeful]** and either gains **+1 [WHAM]** OR **+3 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: In the words of the ancient swordsaints who once cleansed the land of Snazzards and other titanic monstrosities: LET\'S FUCKING GOOOOOOOOO! Everyone gets **1 [WHAM]**, **3 [Boost]** and becomes **[Inspired]**.\r\n\r\n'),
('candyblood', 'CANDYBLOOD', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][One-Off][Reaction]', 'Oh, crud! Everyone on this planet seems weirdly obsessed with blood colour, and if they catch you, they might try to get the killer robot guards they have patrolling the streets to shoot you. And that’s no good! To perfect your Trollish disguise (made of a sweet pair of fake horns), you must hide your blood when possible. When someone would make you **[Bloodied]**, you can use a **[Reaction]** to hide it by clutching the wound and slapping a bandage or two over it asap, gaining **2 [Drag]** instead.'),
('cantKillWhatYouCantSeeAndIsAlsoAlreadyDead', 'CAN’T KILL WHAT YOU CAN’T SEE AND IS ALSO ALREADY DEAD', 'OTHER', 'GHOST', '[Template][Basic][Recharge: 3][Eerie][Locked: Ghost]', 'You gain the ability to go invisible at will! As an action, you become **[Hidden]**. You cannot be detected ordinarily, but **[Psionic]** trolls and trolls with non-Aspect **[Magic]** may roll PROBLEM SLEUTHING or a similar **[Analyze]** move with the **[Psionic]** or **[Magic]** tags added respectively to find you. Anyone can also find you by dealing a total of **3 [Somatic]** damage to the environment you\'re hiding in - if you\'re found like this, you become **[Stressed]** as they punch through the wall or something to get to you. You are unable to use any rolls except **[Chicanery]** as you stack a tonne of chairs to frighten someone, or some shit. If you are damaged by a **[Psionic]** or **[Magic]** attack, your invisibility immediately ends, and the **[Recharge: 3]** tag kicks in. Good luck hiding now!'),
('capitalistAdventure', 'CAPITALIST ADVENTURE', 'FUCHSIA', 'FUCHSIA', '[Fuchsia][Basic][Passive]', 'Who the fuck is going to make you pay money for something? You have **25 VP**. Capitalism is your bitch!'),
('carefulAnalysis', 'CAREFUL ANALYSIS', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Passive]', 'You know, despite your reputation as an annoying little grublouse, you\'re a lot smarter than others might give you credit for. Your **OK** and **BAD** PROBLEM SLEUTHING rolls always **[Tier Up]**.'),
('carefulPlanner', 'CAREFUL PLANNER', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Mental][Locked: Auxiliatrice]', 'Taking care of students has made you an excellent planner. You keep an itinerary, you make lesson plans, and you have a routine you stick the fuck to. Nothing can ever go wrong if you have a plan! Nothing! In an encounter, you can take an action to plan your next 3 moves. You lock yourself into rolling these moves in the order you chose; succeeding on these rolls gives you **1 [Boost]** for each **GOOD** or higher roll, and if you succeed at all three, you get an extra **[Boost]** at the end. However, if you fail a move, you gain **1 [Drag]** instead, and the chain ends. Intentionally breaking away from the plan also removes all **[Boost]** gained, gives you the **[Dread]** condition, and ends the chain. You can\'t use this move for the rest of the encounter.'),
('cargooligan', 'CARGOOLIGAN', 'OLIVE', 'ADULT', '[Olive][Locked: Adult]', 'Are you an Olive? Like, nothing special or anything, just a run of the mill ordinary dude with no life skills that could make you interesting in the grand scheme of the Empire\\\'s will? Cargo. Cargo. Cargo! A fairly self-explanatory job, Cargooligans are trolls who aren\\\'t cut out to be anything particularly exciting, not even cannon fodder. Who wants a soldier who won\\\'t get back up after, or who isn\\\'t particularly hardy? But you\\\'re just hardy enough to help move supplies and clean floors and perform basically any manual labor task being asked of you in an industrial warehouse. When you take the middle road in life, the role you get is middling. As a **[Free] [Reaction]** you may remove **[Tired]**, or when made **[Exhausted]** choose to be just **[Tired]** instead. Sure! You could probably lift a few more boxes! This move is **[One-Off]**.'),
('carnevaledictorian', 'CARNEVALEDICTORIAN', 'PURPLE', 'ADULT', '[Purple][Locked: Adult]', 'Few purples are afforded the privilege you have received. You were personally selected by the Princess to be part of her inner circle, celebrating the mirth and violence heralded by the Messiahs from within her personal circus. You\\\'re well accustomed to being around the puppeted limebloods used by the Princess in her productions - freed limebloods start encounters feeling **[Dread]** around you, and all rolled lime moves are **[Inept]** while you are in an encounter. In addition, your endless celebrating has taught you how to start a party almost instantly. **FRAYMOTIF** becomes a **[Buildup: 2]** for you, and if another Purpleblood would normally be able to **COMBO** with you, then they can even if they haven’t met the **[Buildup]** requirement. If there is another **CARNEVALEDICTORIAN** allied with you, **FRAYMOTIF** loses the **[One-Off]** tag completely. Come on brother, you know me, let’s dance! '),
('carnivalsCrown', 'CARNIVAL\'S CROWN', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Circusfolk]', 'You are the reason trolls come to see the circus. Your charisma, your skill, your luck… even other circus folk see you as near royalty. And it\'s no surprise that that\'s the case; larger than life doesn\'t even begin to cover it. You\'re a SUPERSTAR. You gain access to HERO MODE through the **[Talent]** you gained through ROLL UP, ROLL UP! Your increased fame and skill have given you incredible mastery of your area of expertise; you gain the following effects based on your trick.\r\n\r\n> **COMEDIAN (+RAS)**: Your slapstick borders on the cartoony! Whenever you deal at least **2 [Somatic]** damage to a target, you and all allies get an equal amount of **[Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **ANIMAL TAMER (+PLC)**: You\'ve learned how to ride your tamed partner into battle. And YES, it\'s awesome. Your target counts as a VEHICLE with 2 HORSEPOWER, except your VEHICULATE rolls use **+PLC**, and don\'t need to STEER on it. You may roll any move you like while riding your partner, and may choose to let it go **[Out-Of-Control]**. If someone attempts to HIJACK your partner, it deals **1 damage** to the new rider every turn. It has 4 stat points it can spend as you choose.\r\n\r\n> **ACROBAT (+GRA)**: THAT SPEED— IMPOSSIBLE?! While in NIMBLEMODE, you are **[Quickened]**, and SWASHBUCKLE uses **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n> **CARNY (+APP)**: Roller Coasters, helter-skelters, all of that— you\'re building a castle of carnivalism! All items that cost **LUX** cost 1 less (min. 1), and HIVECRAFTING items cost 2 less.\r\n\r\n> **STRONGMAN (+GRT)**: I\'m not gonna beat around the bush. I\'m pretty sure you\'re invincible. You add your **+GRT** to your HP, use **+GRT** to roll against **[Afflictions]** that require **+APP** rolls, and can never have your **[Strife]** rolls **[Tiered Down]**.\r\n\r\n> **DAREDEVIL (+HUB)**: What… the fuck. How are you alive? That\'s unbelievable. Once you drop to half HP, you may choose to engage DIEHARD FUCKWAD MODE. While in this mode, you are at **1 HP** and cannot **[Heal]**, but you are **[Quickened]**, all your rolls are **[Talented]**, and all **[Strife]** rolls against you are **[Godawful]**.\r\n\r\n> **RINGMASTER (+PSP)**: You can control those around you with genuine ease! Your WORDPLAY rolls use **+PSP**, and you can make enemies roll moves as well as allies, though this costs **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **MAGICIAN (+IMG)**: MAGIC IS REAL AS FUCK BOOOOY! You can purchase new items on the fly in an encounter as you pull them out of hats (though you can\'t buy the same item more than once). You also teleport through puffs of smoke from place to place, but that\'s not really a mechanical thing. You can just do that. Also you can **[Fly]**. Seeya!'),
('carrionlinaReaper', 'CARRIONLINA REAPER', 'OTHER', 'FIREFUELER', '[Template][Advanced][Flourish][Recharge: 3][Locked: Firefueler]', 'Your flame is red, hot, and SPICY, much like an Eerie Pepper or a fabled, deadly, legitimately-dangerous-to eat Carrionlina Reaper. Your skullville units are through the roof and Empress grant even an inkling of mercy to those who stand in your way, no matter their blood. When you are set [Ablaze], you can spend an action to benefit from one of the following effects.\r\n\r\n> **FURIOUS FLAMEFLINGER**: You’ve been cleared for experimental ammunition loaded with fuel they use for Megalodon class ships! Your **FLAMEFLINGER** gains the **RANGEDKIND** and **MASSIVEKIND** Strife Abstrata for 3 turns. Whenever you land a **MAX [Strife]** roll with your FLAMEFLINGER, you can reduce the damage by 2 and give the enemy 1 **[Weakness]** to **[Blaze]** damage for 1 turn.\r\n\r\n> **FIREY FIGHTING SUIT**: Don’t these dissidents know not to fight fire with fire? For 3 turns, while you have your ORG Uniform, you gain **[Immunity]** to **[Blaze]** damage from all sources except for setting yourself **[Ablaze]**, which instead only deals 1 **[Blaze]** **[Somatic]** damage. The **[Boost]** gained from **BURNING DOWN THE HIVE** is increased to 2 **[Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **WARMING WILDFIRE**: You activate a specialized heatsink on your **FLAMEFLINGER** and absorb nearby sources of flame, healing yourself in the process. You can end the **[Ablaze]** condition on up to 4 targets, including yourself, and **[Heal]** for the number of targets you selected. Alternatively, you can end a FIRE! **[Hazard]** as a **[Lengthy]** action and **[Heal]** for 2 **HP** as long as the **[Hazard]** has not reached STAGE 3.'),
('caseWorker', 'CASE WORKER', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'CIS', '[Template][Advanced][Locked: CIS]', 'You\'re on this dipshit\'s case! You\'re not letting them get away from you that easily. Select a target on the CIS WATCHLIST. Your RUMORHUNGER rolls against them **[Tier Up]**, and you can make a **[Free]** RUMORHUNGER roll every day against them… so long as they\'re on the WATCHLIST. If the timer runs dry and they aren\'t on the WATCHLIST anymore, you can\'t spend all your free time watching them.\n\n'),
('casinoRoyal', 'CASINO ROYAL', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Gamblignant]', 'You\'re the best, bitch! You\'ve got oodles of coin, tons of debtors on their knees, and… some of the luck? Maybe forty percent of the luck? Nah nah nah. You\'ve got AAAAALL THE LUCK. ALL OF IT. You are infamous for your skulduggery and shady practices, and even more famous for your sweet gambling venues. You gain access to HERO MODE through your AWESOME APPETITE and are now **Rich**. You\'re innately good at screwing with people who are down on their luck; any time you are targeting someone with lower Wealth than you, you ignore any **[Passive]** effects they have that would **[Tier Down]** or make your rolls **[Inept]**. In fact, the opposite is true! These effects are **[Tiered Up]** or **[Talented]**! This doesn\'t work on people who aren\'t vulnerable to your fortunes; the **Rich** and **Ultrarich** are immune to this effect. You just get a **+1 on [Strife]** rolls against these douchebags, cuz they suck.'),
('castifumigation', 'CASTIFUMIGATION', 'OTHER', 'FIREFUELER', '[Template][Advanced][Lengthy][One-Off][Tech][Locked: Firefueler]', 'The sight of a lowblood confidently summoning a Drone would be a terrifying sight on its own, but when that Drone drops a huge canister leaking out fumes and gasses just begging to be ignited? You better RUN, grub. As a **[Lengthy]** action, you can call a Drone to drop a **CASTIFUMIGATION CANISTER** into an encounter. The **CASTIFUMIGATION CANISTER** is only potent for 2 turns, including the one it was called in on, but while it’s active, all non-ORG trolls suffer 2 **[Drag]** per round as the fumes and gasses choke them out. If any **[Blaze]** damage occurs within these 2 rounds, the CANISTER explodes, dealing 2 **[Blaze] [Somatic]** damage to you and all non-ORG trolls. Anyone who takes this damage is also set **[Ablaze]**, which requires a **[Lengthy]** action to put out.\r\n'),
('castigate', 'CASTIGATE', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Magic][Strife][Locked: Honkpostle]', 'Sometimes, the unfaithful won’t listen to your prayers. And that, frankly, is no good! You clasp your hands together in prayer, not to aid your allies, but to harm your foes, reprimanding them for their sweet motherfuckin’ heresy. When you want to lay down some punishment, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: As you rail against the opponents, your own sins come back to haunt you. What have you done!? You take **2 [Holy]** **[Psychic]** damage, and you feel **[Agitated]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: They aren’t listening to your words. Why aren’t they listening!? You become **[Stressed]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You intimidate them… slightly. You give the target **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Your litany is empowered by magic, and try as they might, they can’t do anything but listen! The target takes **1 [Holy]** **[Psychic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: HEED MY WORDS, NONBELIEVER! Your target either takes **2 [Holy]** **[Psychic]** damage, or takes **1 [Holy]** **[Psychic]** damage and cause the target to become **[Bloodied]** as wounds spontaneously open all over them!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: GODDAMN- DID YOUR WORDS LIKE, CAUSE THEM TO EXPLODE A LIL? Your target either takes **3 [Holy]** **[Psychic]** damage, or takes **2 [Holy]** **[Psychic]** damage and becomes **[Bloodied]**.'),
('causeAScene', 'CAUSE A SCENE!', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Passive][One-Off][Buildup: 3]', 'Sometimes just hiding doesn’t cut it. Sometimes you’re torn from your comfortable hidey hole and out into the light in front of the eyes of Gog. Oh so you wanna look at me? You wanna look at my blood, huh? WELL TURN YOUR GAZE ON THIS WRETCHED THING, BULGE NIPS! PIPE BOMB, GO! When you’re not **[Hidden]** cornered out in the open you may use your chaotic wits to create a distraction. Choose one of **[Hazards]** from the list below to cause.\r\n\r\n> **FIRE**: Do you know just how many objects around you are flammable? That trashcan is flammable. Your palmhusk? Flammable. You? Extra flammable.\r\n\r\n> **ANGRY MOB**: Ah, the double edged sword. On one hand, inciting a riot by pointing at your opponent and making an outlandish claim could work. On the other, they may think you are the one causing trouble. Either way, here comes the mob.\r\n\r\n> **SCREEGUL SWARM**: Screeguls: The hazard anyone can afford, so long as you have some food to throw and a lack of self preservation.'),
('cavernGossip', 'CAVERN GOSSIP', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Analyze][Manipulate][Mental]', 'Jade culture is pretty close-knit compared to other castes. As such, word gets around VERY fast among you all. When you want to remember a rumour, roll **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You remember a rumour… but it\'s FALSE! When you say this out loud, the opponent calls you a dipshit, and you become too **[Humiliated]** to **[Analyze]** til the end of the encounter. You take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Ugh! Think, brain, think! Is there seriously nothing you can remember? You take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You don\'t remember anything worthwhile, but you do remember a funny joke you heard once, so it wasn\'t for nothing.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Oh, yes, that\'s where I know you! You recall an embarrassing rumour about the target, and it flusters them! The opponent becomes **[Disgusted]** at themselves. Make it stop!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You know some pretty good tea on the opponent indeed, frankly! You casually toss it out, and the opponent feels sick to their stomach. They become **[Revolted]**. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: Grandmother Grub\'s Mercy, that\'s some DEEP lore! You remember an EXCEPTIONALLY embarrassing rumour that not only **[Revolts]** the opponent… but it **[Slows]** them for **2 turns** as their mind reels!'),
('cavernousMinutetroll', 'CAVERNOUS MINUTETROLL', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Passive][Ultra][Locked: Tunnelwarden]', 'When people are in need, it is you they turn to. When the meek are imperiled, they call your name. When a hero is needed… the Cavernous Minutetroll is the name on everyone\'s lips. Cavernous Minutetrolls are the strongest rank of Tunnelwardens, famous for their ability to show up at a minute\'s notice. While there aren\'t exactly official ranks… by now, you\'ve gotten to the point where everyone\'s assigned you this mantle, and you hold it with pride. You have access to HERO MODE through your MYTHIC MANGRIT. You will fight with all your might when you\'re protecting your friends. In a TEAM STRIFE, your allies all add **1 extra HP** to the Team\'s HP, and your CHALLENGER effects apply at **¾ HP**, not **½ HP**. All of your allies are **[Quickened]** on the first turn of a TEAM STRIFE, and you get the following effects that are always active on top of your CHAMPION or CHALLENGER effects…\r\n\r\n> **(CHAMPION) HEROES OF ALTERNIA**: Everything you do, you do to FIGHT for justice! Enemy **[Team Strife]** rolls such as ANNEX or APPREHEND are **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n> **(CHALLENGER) HEART BLAZE FOR JUSTICE**: COME ON! WE CAN DO THIS! All of your team\'s **[Team Strife]** rolls are **[Talented]** from the start of the encounter.'),
('cavernvania', 'CAVERNVANIA', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Passive][Unlock: Slayer]', 'DIE, MONSTER! YOU DON\'T BELONG IN THIS WORLD! Though the Jade caste is widely considered to be the caste most interested in the corporeal undead, they are also the caste tasked with vanquishing them. You are among the number of trained hunters who seek out the wicked who refuse to turn to rot like the rest of us. Like come on dude, grow up. Just die, man. You have trained in the art of combating the mortally inept. You aren\'t a Ghostbuster, the hamfisted highblood attempt to maintain the status quo; you are a Slayer, and you slay monsters for their wickedness, not their refusal to bow to the Empire. You are **[Talented]** at **+GRA**. Choose one type of opponent you hunt.\r\n\r\n> **VAMPYRS**: The oldest plague on the Caverns, you seek to vanquish the bloodthirsty Rainbow Drinkers. If in the presence of a troll entering BLOODHYSTERIA MODE, you also become **[Quickened]** and **[Out-Of-Control]** so long as the Drinker still stands. You have a **+1 [Buff]** to **[Strife]** rolls against Jade trolls.\r\n\r\n> **LYCANTHROPES**: The bestial demons of the woods, you smite Moonbarks in all their forms. Your **[Strife]** rolls against trolls in MOONBARK MODE are **[Tiered Up]**, and you are immune to the MOONBARK MUMPS Affliction. You have a **+1 [Buff]** to **[Strife]** rolls against LUSII and MONSTERS.\r\n\r\n> **PHANTASMS**: This machine kills chronic depression. Grimdarks are no match for your sharp wit and sharper blades. You are not **[Scared]** or in **[Despair]** around trolls in A MODE MOSTE GRIM, and you have **1 [Resistance]** to all damage from the incoming PARANORMAL ACTIVITY hazard it summons. You have a **+1 [Buff]** to **[Strife]** rolls against trolls with **[Negative]** emotions.\r\n\r\n> **WIGHTS**: Return to death, foul creature! The Shadowdroppers of old are your favored enemy. You gain **1 [WHAM]** at the start of your turn whenever someone **[Heals]** around you. You have a **+1 [Buff]** to **[Strife]** rolls against trolls with more than 10 HP.\r\n\r\n> **VVITCHES**: Burn the Vvitch! You have to pronounce it like that, or it doesn\'t work. Like, vi-vitch. Look, point is, those who use evil magic must be punished. Looking at you, Cthonomancers. **[Magic]** rolls are **[Inept]** against you. You have a **+1 [Buff]** to **[Strife]** rolls against trolls with **[Magic]** aside from FRAYMOTIF.\r\n\r\n> **CAVITIES**: Strange and saccharine entities created by breaches in reality, you shan\'t allow goodness to be decayed by Tricksters! **[Chicanery]** rolls are **[Inept]** against you. You have a **+1 [Buff]** to rolls against trolls who have at least +3 RAS.'),
('caveServitude', 'CAVE SERVITUDE', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Passive]', 'Your caste is… suffocating. The history of Jadekind revolves around the winding caverns that riddle the crust of Alternia. In antiquity, all Jades were locked away from the surface in the deep Undercaverns, tending to the Grandmother Grub, birther of Trollkind. In recent millennia, only a minority of the \"purest\" have stayed there, with many now working in the streetblock-like Uppercaverns where they raise wrigglers and tend to Lusii, and some even forgo the caves entirely, living on the surface and saying \"fuck you, caves\". But one thing is for sure— there\'s no such thing as a Jadeblood not affected by the caste\'s dedication to the caves. Select an option from below. \r\n\r\n> **LOVE**: The caves matter a WHOLE BUNCH to you. So much so, in fact, that you might count yourself among the worshippers of the Grandmother Grub, even if you\'re not a cloister. **[Control]** moves are **[Inept]** against you; a higher power protects you.\r\n\r\n> **AMBIVALENT**: You work in the caves, yeah. You don\'t like, think it DEFINES you or anything. But it\'s a part of you, sure, same as the nation someone\'s born in. The majority of Jades who aren\'t fervent believers (including more lax Cloisters) fall under this. Your HIVECRAFTING upgrades cost **1 LUX** less; you don\'t mind digging holes into walls for your stuff, something that some more dedicated trolls might find appalling.\r\n\r\n> **DISLIKE**: Fuck the caves! Maybe you don\'t feel THAT strongly about it and choose to live on the surface, or don\'t go to Cloister Classes, but you certainly don\'t love the self-oppressing culture Jadekind cultivates. **[Manipulate]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**; you don\'t like taking orders from anyone.'),
('certifiedHiveGrownOrganic', 'CERTIFIED HIVE GROWN ORGANIC', 'OTHER', 'HORTICULLTURIST', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Horticullturist]', 'You are the plant master, master of the plants. Plantseidon quivers before you. You’ve seen just about everything there is to see about Alternian’s flora, and what you haven’t seen you can make an educated guess at. You’re basically a botanist, is the point. This move cannot be taken until all other moves in this template have been taken. You can take a second option from MEAN GREEN GARDENER FROM OUTER SPACE. Additionally, you’ve found some really cool and creative uses for them! You gain access to new additions to your strife specibi and items, which you gain for free. When you want a new one, the old one withers away and croaks. Your options are as follows… \r\n\r\n> **POLLENKIND**: An ABSTRATA UPGRADE you can apply to your weapons. Your weapon is threaded with pollen, spores, and other nasty allergens. On a **GREAT** or **MAX** **[Strife]** roll, you may choose to do one less damage in exchange for making the target **[Tired]** for a turn. \r\n\r\n> **HIVE GROWN**: An item property that means you grew this item at hive! How did you make your plants grow you a palmhusk? That doesn’t make sense. How did you do that? This item costs **1 VP** no matter what.\r\n\r\n> **GROWN HIVE**: AYO! YOU MADE A WHOLE ROOM OUT OF A GIANT PEACH? HOW! You gain a HIVECRAFTING UPGRADE for free.\r\n\r\n> **CELLULOSE REINFORCED**: A property applied to **[Fashion]** items this property grants you **2 extra HP** worth of reinforcing with plant tendrils, roots, etc.'),
('champicipant', 'CHAMPICIPANT', 'INDIGO', 'ADULT', '[Indigo][Locked: Adult]', 'The Empire doesn\\\'t just have the best generals and minds of any sapient species. They also have the best athletes! There\\\'s a reason the Empire takes home every gold medal in the Space Olympics: trolls are absolutely SHREDDED, and you\\\'re here to uphold that reputation! From the velvet of Arena Stickball to the rink of Figure Slaying (With Guns), you\\\'re not letting anyone get in the way of your path to glory. Can you hear it, young Champicipant? The fans are screaming your name and the winner\\\'s podium beckons. All that stands in your way is the other team - show \\\'em why you\\\'re the best there is. Any **[Physical]** move you roll can never be worse than a **BAD** because you are the CHAMP! The best of the best! You\\\'re the one who WINS! You also get additional **GOOD SHENANIGANS** effects as you play your enemies like an Explosive Prongball.\n\n> **CAN WE GET A REF?**: That was absolute BULLSHIT and YOU KNOW IT! Take one **GREAT** or **MAX** roll that the target rolled on their last turn. It becomes an **OK** or **GOOD** respectively.\n\n> **SPORTSBALL BLAST!**: BALLS IN YOUR FACE! You pull out a sportsball launcher, stuff it full, and pelt your enemy with a barrage of sportsballs! The target is **[Distracted]** as they try to survive the BALLSLAUGHT.\n\n> **THE WINNER IS...!**: YOU! It\\\'s always YOU! YOU ARE THE CHAMPION OF THE WORLD! Your target feels **[Dread]**, because you\\\'re going to win anyways...'),
('championOfTheRealm', 'CHAMPION OF THE REALM', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Paladin]', 'Everyone looks up to you. Maybe they don\'t like you, but certainly, they respect you. There are likely countless rumours of the foes you\'ve fought, the speeches you\'ve given and overall how fucking awesome you are. And I mean that in the way an 80s rock album might call a fireball \"awesome\". Like, you really do inspire awe in others. You gain access to HERO MODE through your GLORIOUS GRACE. Your armour is given some major upgrades in the name of fighting off evil. You can start **[Flying]** as an action thanks to jets installed into your boots, acting as a 2 HORSEPOWER Tiny Vehicle with **+GRA** to VEHICULATE. Your Strife Abstrata always does **[Holy]** damage, even if you already have an ABSTRATA UPGRADE. Choose a type of **[Energy]**; **[Strife]** rolls from sources with this tag are **[Inept]** against you, and you gain the following effect based on the bracket your energy resistance falls into.\r\n\r\n> **SOMATIC**: Your armour is a hulking mass of metal! You don\'t gain the **[Inept]** effect this move otherwise describes, but you are immune to **[WHAM]** and have **+2 HP**.\r\n\r\n> **HOLY/FREAKY**: Your armour shines a dark light or a bright darkness. People who use **[Magic]** or **[Psionic]** rolls around you automatically take **1 [Drag]** as your armour interferes.\r\n\r\n> **FROST/BLAZE**: Your armour is fashioned to look like crackling magma or a titanic iceberg. Targets who touch you with **[Physical]** rolls always take **1 [Drag]** from the elemental might coming off your armour.  \r\n\r\n> **LASER/SONIC**: With bright lights or humming sounds, your armour looks very technological. Any time you are hit by a **[Strife]** roll, your armour hums to protect you, and you gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **ACID/ELECTRICITY**: Your armour drips with caustic chemicals or lets crackles of lightning course through the limbs. Whenever you take 3 or more damage from an attack, the attacker takes 2 back.\r\n\r\n> **GLITCHY**: What… are you WEARING… your armour **[Quickens]** you when you get a **MIN**, and **[Stuns]** opponents who get a **MAX**. Somehow.'),
('characterGrowth', 'CHARACTER GROWTH', 'LIFE', 'LIFE', '[Aspect][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Life]', 'You’ve come a long way, all in all. By now, you’ve changed so much— and honestly, for the better. You understand that it’s good to help people, yes, but not to your own detriment! You need to put yourself first; after all, how can you expect to help anyone even a little if you’re miserable? You cannot pour from an empty cup. Embrace who you are and continue blossoming into the best version of yourself that you can be. Your life-force is genuinely growing nonstop; you can remove negative conditions with MOLLYCODDLE, spending **3 [Boost]** per condition removed, and can heal others with MOLLYCODDLE as you share your limitless vitality! And even when you\'re hurt, you know how to bloom back stronger - whenever you take damage or negative conditions, you gain **1 [Boost]** for each point of damage and negative condition taken. Finally, you\'re way past sticking to what you\'re used to - you always benefit from both effects of COMFORT ZONE, finding comfort in the unknown and room for new growth even in familiarity.\r\n'),
('cheatingBastard', 'CHEATING BASTARD', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Buildup: 2][Recharge: 3][Locked: Gamblignant]', 'You play fair all the time! Honest! People always assume the worst of you. It\'s unwarranted! Well, okay, maybe sometimes it\'s warranted. You may attempt to sneakily **[Tier Up]** a roll result without signalling it to your opponent. If your opponent doesn\'t out-of-character notice what you did, they don\'t in-character notice you using cheap tricks, underhand techniques and unfair tactics. If they do notice, and call you out for it, your move is **[Tiered Down]** twice, even retroactively. Gulp! You can\'t use this move against monsters.'),
('chinUp', 'CHIN UP!', 'PROSPIT', 'PROSPIT', '[Sway][Passive][Locked: Prospit]', 'You don’t let stuff drag you down for too long. After all, things WILL get better, one way or another— you just need to have faith in yourself! If you have **[Drag]**, you lose **1 point of [Drag]** every **3 turns** as your past mistakes slowly fade away. This move stops when you hit **0 [Drag]**; the counter only resets once you have again accumulated **[Drag]**.'),
('chronicWorrywart', 'CHRONIC WORRY-WART', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'The, uh. Yeah. Uh, so, Bronzebloods have a strangely high proportion of trolls with pretty bad anxiety. Maybe it\'s a coincidence, maybe it\'s because you\'re juuuuust on the cusp of being totally numbed like rusts are, but are also given enough reprieve from the horrors of reality that when it hits you it hits you HARD… uh. Yeah! You get the following PROBLEM SLEUTHING results.\r\n\r\n> **NERVOUS SIDE-EYE**: You glance at an ally, praying they aren\'t going to do something stupid. They privately tell you what they\'re going to do next. If you approve, gain **2 [Boost]** (phew!). If you disprove, shake your head rapidly at them and give them **2 [Boost]** if they reconsider.\r\n\r\n> **GULP**: Is this going to fuck you over? It totally is. You glance around, looking for a way out; your next ABSCOND roll is **[Talented]** and has a **+2 [Buff]**.\r\n\r\n> **DOUBLE-CHECK**: There\'s no way this is gonna backfire, right? You have an ally explain their plan to you; once they do so, their next roll for it is **[Talented]**.\r\n\r\n> **WHAT\'S THE WORST THAT COULD HAPPEN**: You imagine the worst possible thing that could happen. Every turn for the next 3 turns, roll 1d8 at the start of a round. On a 1, ALL ROLLS ARE **[Godawful]** AND **[Tiered Down]** FOR EVERYONE. Why did you imagine it?!'),
('chucklerequiem', 'CHUCKLEREQUIEM', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Ultra][Passive][Magic][Locked: Mafioso]', 'This is it: the reason many trolls stay part of the mob or die trying to get here. You\'ve stayed a member of the Clutch long enough now that you\'re being taught the most secret of secrets; the long sought after CHUCKLEREQUIEM. Long ago, this Chuckleterror was banned by the Grand Highblood themselves for its dangerous uses, but criminal juggalos have yet to forget its secrets. Because, see, brother, what this jutsu does— it doesn\'t affect others. It affects you. CHUCKLEREQUIEM looks like a purple haze of mist gently flowing from your mouth and tear ducts (usually only manifesting in moments of stress), accompanied by a desire to wear fresh as fuck outfits. You gain access to HERO MODE with your AWESOME APPETITE as the magic infuses you with hunger for power. More importantly, however… you are also completely immune to other trolls **[Magic]** moves as your own magic actively cancels out witchenergy that would harm you. You should probably only take this move if you are a CAPO or higher in your MAFIALADDER; figuring out the secrets of the CHUCKLEREQUIEM before you\'re allowed could totally destabilize the power structure your Clutch, and could count as immediate grounds for expulsion if a lowly Associate takes it. You can take this move anyway if you choose, but think of the in-character consequences if someone finds out!'),
('chuckleterror2TerrorsUnleashed', 'CHUCKLETERROR 2: TERRORS UNLEASHED', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Passive]', 'Your mastery over your Chuckleterrors has increased significantly, making you even more chuckleterrifying! You get the following effects you can substitute in on a **GOOD**, **GREAT** and **MAX** CHUCKLETERROR roll. If you don\'t have the move yet, you can\'t take this move.\r\n\r\n> **CHUCKLEVISION**: CHU-CHU-CHUCKLEVISION! You impose your will on the target with hypnotic force, as the theme song from the British Sitcom CHUCKLEVISION blasts through their mind. The move fails if you don\'t play the song. On a **GOOD**, you make the target roll a move on a target of your choice for **[Free]**. On a **GREAT**, the move is **[Tiered Up]** and on a **MAX**, their roll is automatically a **MAX**. \r\n\r\n> **CHUCKLEMINDWIPE**: What do you think you saw? You didn\'t. You make the target forget something they saw within the last hour. This otherwise functions as CHUCKLETERROR, but it makes the target **[Confused]** or **[Dumbfounded]**.\r\n\r\n> **CHUCKLETICKLE**: GOOCHIE GOOCHIE GOO! You psychically tickle the shit out of someone. They can\'t communicate with anyone except to yelp and squirm around for the duration. This otherwise functions as CHUCKLETERROR, but it makes the target **[Giggle]** or **[Laugh]**.\r\n\r\n> **CHUCKLEAAAAAAUGHHHHHHH**: AAAAAARGH! THE AGONY! FUUUUCK! The target is exposed to the CHOKING or PSIBURN **[Affliction]**.  On a **GREAT**, their rolls against it are at a **-1 [Nerf]**, and on a **MAX**, they\'re **[Tiered Down]**. This has the **[One-Off]** tag. \r\n\r\n> **CHUCKLESECRETS**: You wanna tell me, don\'tcha? Your target can\'t help but tell the truth when you make REQUEST rolls for **2 turns**, ignoring effects that depower **[Manipulate]** rolls. On a **GREAT**, further REQUEST rolls are **[Tiered Up]**, and on a **MAX**, so are the REQUEST rolls.'),
('chuckleterrors', 'CHUCKLETERRORS', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Control][Magic][Recharge: 3]', 'Nightmare, nightmare, nightmare! One of the earliest lessons taught to students of the church is how to let nonbelievers see the Dark Carnival. This, in practice, is a deterrent from rebellion imposed by the Church made to scare other castes into submission. Of course, most of the time, you just probably use it to help win a fight. When you want to send visions of horror into the target\'s mind, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: UH-OH! Looks like you made em STRONGER! The target\'s resolve heightens all of their positive **[Emotions]**, and adds **[Inspired]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Howowowowonk… the target gains **2 [Boost]** as they power through your nightmare visions!\r\n\r\n**OK**: You didn’t do it right! Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Honk Honk Honk! Your target sees the other side, and becomes woozy… they are **[Stressed]** for **2 turns**, replacing an existing positive or neutral **[Emotion]** if applicable.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Dark shadows flit around your target’s peripheral visions, and they hear some weird honking. Who\'s there?! You get a **GOOD**, but the target is **[Agitated]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Your target is sent, even for just a moment, to Clown Hell, and experiences horrific visions like some kind of bad LSD trip, full of clowns and terrible, terrible religious imagery. You get a **GREAT**, but the **[Agitation]** lasts for the encounter, and the target is also **[Confused]**.'),
('circleOfTheTwinMoons', 'CIRCLE OF THE TWIN MOONS', 'OTHER', 'WYLDERDRUID', '[Template][Ultra][Magic][Locked: Wylderdruid]', 'There’s no such thing as being ‘the best Wylderdruid’, just like there’s no such thing as ‘the coolest animal’. You, however, come pretty damn close. You’ve spent nights out in the butt-ass cold, witnessed the cycles of life of both the smallest insects and the most imposing kaiju, and through experience and hard work have slowly gotten stronger. You can now forge **WYLDERPACTS** with level 2 **LUSUS** and **PLANT MONSTERS**, and subsequently shapeshift into them with **ANIMORPHOSIS**. Additionally, your **WYLDERPACTS** are now stronger, lasting for 3 uses upon acquiring them rather than 2. Finally, you’ve managed to hone your use of **SOLSTICIALIZE** so your elemental attacks now do 1 additional damage if you conduct them while the appropriate **[Hazard]** is active; DAYTIME for summer, RAINSTORM for fall, SNOWSTORM for winter and BEE SWARM for spring.\r\n');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('circusCant', 'CIRCUS CANT', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Passive]', 'Did you know Juggalos have their own language? It\'s true! Known as Ciazanguish (KEY-uh-zanguish) the Purple Caste has a secret dialect that they often use to communicate with one another, usually by inserting the infix \"zonk\" into the middle of words (for example, \"check out that lowblood\" becomes \"chezonk ouzonkt thazonkt lowbzonklood\"). It\'s like double-dutch, but for clowns! This is a closed cultural practice; teaching other trolls the cant is worse than walking around with no makeup. You gain access to the following WORDPLAY effects, which you are **[Talented]** at.\r\n\r\n> **SWEAR BARRAGE**: MOTHERZONKFUCKING BULLZONKSHIT! You spew out your frustrations at the target. Your target can\'t gain **[Boost]** for **1 turn**.\r\n\r\n> **PARLEY**: You speak with another clown in Ciazanguish, aiming to obscure your message. On a **GREAT**, other trolls are **[Confused]** for **1 turn**, and on a **MAX**, they\'re **[Dumbfounded]**.\r\n\r\n> **PUNCHLINE**: HAHAHA! HONK! You crack a joke in Ciazanguish. All Juggalos present start **[Laughing]** for **1 turn**, and all non-Juggalos present become **[Embarrassed]** for this time. Were you joking about them..?\r\n\r\n> **RAP BATTLE**: AW SHIT! WHAAAT? You just threw some raps at the target! The target must make a **[Manipulate]** roll for **1 turn**. You can roll JAB even if a punch has already been thrown once a RAP BATTLE is initiated, and trolls have a **+1 [Buff]** to them. If all trolls agree, you can allow JAB rolls to be thrown for the rest of the encounter. JAB loses the **[Strife]** tag in this case, but all trolls must make **1 [Manipulate]** roll per turn in the form of rapping or take **3 [Drag]**.'),
('claimToFame', 'CLAIM TO FAME', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Passive][Locked: Celebrity]', 'There are many ways to get famous! Of course, the root is to have a stupid amount of wealth to get you to that level in the first place, but… hey, it\'s what you DO with the money that counts! Pick a claim to fame from the list below!\r\n\r\n> **INFLUENCER**: Selfies, vlogs, and streams, oh my! You may take the Gold Streamer Tree as a Template. If you do so, you can only take the **[Entry]**, one **[Basic]**, and one **[Advanced]**. You gain the **[Entry]** now.\r\n\r\n> **SUPERSTAR**: Movies, television, radio… people recognize you as an incredible actor, because you are EVERYWHERE! **[Analyze]** and **[Manipulate]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**, because people can\'t really tell your personas and you apart!\r\n\r\n> **SINGER**: Whether you are an idol, a rock star, or something else, people LOVE your voice! You gain the Purple Honkpostle FRAYVOCALIZE move as you sing your way to success! You use your **+PLC** for this move.\r\n\r\n> **DANCER**: Ballerina? Breakdancer? Who knows, who cares! You use your **+PLC** to roll FRAYMOTIF, and the **[Buildup]** is reduced to 3.\r\n\r\n> **FASHIONISTA**: Your style is untouchable, and so are you, baby. You gain access to every fashion item in the game, including ones locked by castes such as the FANTASTIC FLAIR item from the Cerulean Marquis DEBONAIR DRESS move, or the METALHEAD TEE item from the Altkid Jade COUNTERCULTURIST move. You can use the Collections associated with these trees too. However, items from these moves cost **3 LUX**, not 1.\r\n\r\n> **OTHER**: Maybe you\'re a celebrity chef, a rock star, or something similar! You gain the **[Entry]** to a Template surrounding a job or hobby now, as well as two **[Basic]** moves for free.'),
('classroomChaos', 'CLASSROOM CHAOS', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Auxiliatrice]', 'It\'s you versus so many wrigglers when you\'re working. Seriously, young trolls seem to have one single task when you take your eyes off them for even a moment: SELF TERMINATION. As such, your crowd control skills are top-notch. Whenever you start an encounter where you and your allies are outnumbered, you become **[Quickened]** as you dash around, making sure nothing goes wrong.'),
('claustrophobicCulture', 'CLAUSTROPHOBIC CULTURE', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Free]', 'You\'re part of a culture that\'s… kind of a lot, sometimes. Everyone strives to be perfect, to protect their friends, to never not look graceful… it can get to you sometimes! Thankfully, you\'ve learned how to internalise your bad feelings into a nice little box, and not worry about it! Whenever you gain a negative **[Emotion]**, you can instead choose to become **[Stressed]**. Yippee! Now you just can\'t fuck up, and it\'ll all be okay.'),
('clericarny', 'CLERICARNY', 'PURPLE', 'ADULT', '[Purple][Locked: Adult]', 'None are more powerful than the Messiahs, but you would be foolish to ignore the other magic out there in the universe. Especially now that you’ve breached the vast outer space, you’re on the hunt for magic that can be used to further your strength and show that no one fucks with clowns. Besides, this is your mission! By bringing these strange and possibly heretical powers to your Messiahs, they can change and bless them into a true holy force. Your Warpstorms and Conjurifications are summoned through the Messiahs! If bringing the japes and miracles of the Dark Carnival requires you to be more… flexible, then call yourself a contortionist. Any **[Magic]** rolls you make are **[Talented]** if they were not already. You also gain the **[Entry]** to either the **ASTROSORCERER** or **CTHONOMANCER [Template]** if you did not have one already; and if taken the **CTHONOMANCER [Template]** loses the **[Eerie]** tag. This does not count towards your **[Template]** limit. Dealing in magic is practically as easy as breathing, after all. You also gain the ability to purchase **[Rare]** items.'),
('cloakedVulnerability', 'CLOAKED VULNERABILITY', 'DERSE', 'DERSE', '[Sway][Passive][Locked: Derse]', 'You don’t like highlighting your weakness very much. In fact, you don’t like looking weak, full-stop. Whenever you would take a condition, you can choose to tough it out, acting like it isn’t affecting you half as much as it is. Oh, you’re on fire? No big deal. You’ve dealt with worse. Being on fire still hurts like hell, but your ability to pretend stuff doesn’t phase you has led to stuff… not always phasing you, on the small scale. Any time you gain **[Drag]**, you only gain half the incoming **[Drag]** (min 1). You cannot halve self-inflicted **[Drag]** this way. Moves that trigger from taking X number of **[Drag]** trigger as though it were not halved.'),
('closeAnalysis', 'CLOSE ANALYSIS', 'DERSE', 'DERSE', '[Sway][Passive][Locked: Derse]', 'You’ve a pretty critical eye, and you’re a dedicated problem solver. It’s easy to figure out the solution when you’re as cerebral as you! Whenever you succeed at PROBLEM SLEUTHING, you gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n'),
('closingArgument', 'CLOSING ARGUMENT', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Splattorney]', 'https://youtu.be/UFcJmOs8DRQ \r\n\r\nThe final stages of the argument are the most dire! Steel your will, start the pursuit and CORNER them! When you have a single opponent left, or you are the last ally you have standing, and either your opponent or you have **4 HP** or less left, you become **[Quickened]**. You can only use the extra action from **[Quickened]** to make **[Manipulate]** moves in this state.'),
('coagulatedConviction', 'COAGULATED CONVICTION', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Advanced][Passive]', 'It doesn’t matter what or who they throw at you, desperate to reveal that which you keep locked away within your veins. You bleed for none of them, and your blood has solidified into a vault door that refuses to tarnish. This is your door of conviction, and they’ll have to kill you to get it open. When you take this move, you may use **STANCH SECRET** one extra time. Also, you do not gain **[Drag]** the first time you use **STANCH SECRET**. When you would be **[Bloodied]** a second time in an encounter, you may make the move a **[One-Off]** and become **[Enraged]** as a **[Reaction]**. \r\n'),
('combobreaker', 'COMBOBREAKER', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Reaction][Physical][Locked: Cool Kid]', 'Oh, so you’re going to keep on hitting me, over and over again? Nah, get dunked on. When an opponent gets the same Roll Result to deal damage to you or an ally with **[Strife]** roll **3 times** in **3 turns** (For example, 3 **GREAT**S in a row), you know how to deal a savage block that completely undermines the third result. Roll **+HUB** to go NOT SO FAST.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: I\'m not going to lie to you. You ran directly into that attack. You take **2 damage** of the same type.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Ouch, oof, okay, fuck. That was dumb. You take **1 damage** of the same type.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You flail around making noises like a dying chicken. Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Curbstomp! You retroactively **[Tier Down]** the opponent\'s **[Strife]** roll to an **OK**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: ASSKICK REVERSAL! You retroactively **[Tier Down]** to a **BAD**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Holy SHIT, you completely dunk on them! My fucking word! The pain and agony they must feel right now! You retroactively **[Tier Down]** their roll to a **MIN**!'),
('comfortablyNumb', 'COMFORTABLY NUMB', 'OTHER', 'MAGE', '[Class][Basic][Free][Locked: Mage]\r\n', 'Sometimes knowledge isn\'t a boon. Sometimes you don\'t want to think about it, or even think about anything at all. That doesn\'t mean you\'re a flat emotionless brick! Just that you are Not Thinking About It. You can choose to ignore any **[Negative] [Emotion]** that happens to you, gaining 2 **[Drag]** instead for a **[Base] [Emotion]** and 4 **[Drag]** for a **[Heightened] [Emotion]**.\r\n\r\n\r\n'),
('comfortZone', 'COMFORT ZONE', 'LIFE', 'LIFE', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Life]', 'You don’t like being out of your comfort zone; why should you? It’s your comfort zone because you like it there. Choose an environment you can call your comfort zone— most often, choices would be “indoors”, “underwater”, “in the jungle”, or similar, though other options exist!— and declare it when taking this move. While in your comfort zone, any time you gain **[Boost]**, you gain an extra 1 **[Boost]**. When you’re out of your comfort zone, you tend to be a bit more on edge; you are **[Quickened]** on the first turn in a **[Strife]**.'),
('commanderander', 'COMMANDERANDER', 'CERULEAN', 'ADULT', '[Cerulean][Locked: Adult]', 'Blues are fucking scary, which makes them excellent for the positions of Commanderanders. They are the ones who bark out the orders and get people moving, pointing trolls to where they need to go and shouting what they need to do with terrifying composure and force. Commanderanders are also found talking with the last lines of resistance and the leaders of weak upstarts that show disobedience and cowardice. Listen to them or die. Choose **GRT, HUB**, or **PLC**. You become **[Talented]** in your chosen stat. You cannot choose a stat you already have a **[Talent]** in. If you’re somehow talented in all these stats already, choose one to have a **+1 [Buff]** with instead. On a **[Recharge: 5]**, whenever you roll a move with the stat you chose and achieve a **GREAT** or **MAX**, you can add one of the following effects.\n\n> **WITHERING GLARE**: Don\\\'t. Fucking. Try it. The next **[Strife], [Chicanery], [Manipulate]**, or **[Flourish]** move your target rolls is **[Inept]** and will **[Tier Down]**. This supersedes defenses against rolls being made **[Inept]** or **[Tiered Down]**.\n\n> **FINAL OFFER**: Punishment or death. The target must perform one action or course of action you demand of them or else suffer a **[Free] [Strife]** roll that cannot be lower than a **GOOD**. If this effect was chosen from a **GREAT** or **MAX [Strife]** roll, then it can be lower than a **GOOD** and is also **[Inept]**.\n\n> **GASLIGHT**: Defection? Stop being a stupid slore. All **[Analyze]** checks the target performs are **[Godawful]** for the next three rounds, superseding all defenses against such an effect, and experiences your choice of either **[Despair]** or **[Dumbfounded]**.'),
('commandFamiliar', 'COMMAND FAMILIAR', 'OTHER', 'WITCH', '[Class][Basic][Free][Reaction][Recharge: 4][Locked: Witch]', 'With how great and talented you are, of course you’re surrounded by so many people! What is a witch without their obedient familiars? All these peons are clearly here to help you reach your goals, ready to be commanded! As a **[Reaction]**, before an ally rolls, you can **[Tier Up]** their action as you butt in and meddle. No, don’t do it like that! It’s like this, see! When you do this you both take 2 **[Drag]** as you inadvertently create animosity for treating them more like a pet than a person.'),
('commandingPersonality', 'COMMANDING PERSONALITY', 'BLOOD', 'BLOOD', '[Aspect][Passive][Unlock: Blood]', 'Whichever way you look at it, everyone around you is stupid and makes poor decisions. There’s only one troll around who can make the right choices going forward to unite you all and keep everyone safe: YOU! So everyone better listen up and do what you say, already! Any time you roll to **[Manipulate]** someone, your roll is **[Tiered Up]**; if you have a similar effect from a different source, you gain **[Boost]** on any successful **[Manipulation]** roll (1 for a **GOOD**, 2 for a **GREAT**, 3 for a **MAX**).'),
('commediaDellmorte', 'COMMEDIA DELL’MORTE', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Passive]', 'Rich in their wonderfully murderous history across several cities and the whole of Alternia itself, there’s no one right way to be clown. Clowns come in all different shapes, sizes, and flavors; choose the flavor of clown you’d like to be from these options below:\r\n\r\n> **JESTER**: Hoho! You jingle across the floor with your jingle jangly hat. People are so focused on your cute little tricks that they don’t stop to consider the particularly harsh words or your particularly devious actions. You can roll to JAB after a fight has broken out; you can also choose to become **[Talented]** at WORDPLAY and lose the Universal Move **[Talent]** typically associated with your tree, though you\'d still be **[Talented]** at all other rolls with that stat.\r\n\r\n> **MIME**: Shhh… Let’s all be silent for a while. You are the MIME. Certainly the most quiet of clowns, but also the most imaginative. Nobody can ever tell what items you use when you use them, and the benefits they give you are a secret. Your items are invisible, after all! SPOT rolls against you are **[Tiered Down]**.\r\n\r\n> **HARLEQUIN**: Trapeze! Tightrope walking! Complimentary aerial hoops! That’s all YOU, baby! Known for your trickster personality and your impressive acrobatics, you are the true star of the show. The audience loves you, your effortless charm and the extravagant shows you can put on. Whenever you get a **GREAT** on a **+GRA** roll, all opponents are **[Charmed]** for **1 turn**.\r\n\r\n> **PIERROT**: Please forgive the unworthy poet, who has taken liberty to perform for thee. You are the most miserable of clowns; your poems speak of hardships. Life as a Pierrot is hard — or so it seems. Your latent sad energy is good fuel to make your audience feel sympathy for you. You can choose to become **[Numb]** as an action, causing all others to become **[Numb]** too. So sad… \r\n\r\n> **RODEO**: YEEEEHAW! HONK HONK! MESSIAHS BLESS ALTERNIA! The monsters of Alternian wildlife don\'t scare you one bit. It’s all part of the show to take these beasts down and show them what for! You get the CUSTODIAN COMPANION Perfectly Generic move if you didn\'t already have it, and you can ride your Custodian like a **[Vehicle]** of the appropriate size. You use **+HUB** for both VEHICULATE and ATRIACLIZE rolls. Yeehaw! \r\n\r\n> **AUGUSTE**: In the extravagant yet flashy, murderous world of clowns, sometimes all you want to be is a simple default clown. And that’s fine! You subscribe to typical slapstick humor, making people take pies to the face, pulling rainbow handkerchiefs from their sleeves, or just all around being a pretty silly guy. Your **[Chicanery]** rolls can never be **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]** or **[Nerfed]**.\r\n\r\n> **JUGGALO**: Yeeeeeah. The OG. The most common. The motherfuckin\' Juggalo. You smash shit, you scare people, you\'re the reason the clown church is the powerhouse it motherfuckin\' is, got it? Yeah. You can become **[Enraged]** as an action and enter MURDER MODE. While in MURDER MODE, you become **[Talented]** in **+GRT** if you weren\'t already, and you can\'t lose more than 1 **[WHAM]** at a time. Watch out!\r\n\r\n> **SOME OTHER CLOWNSHIT**: I dunno, what are you, a gamer clown or something? Select a **[Basic]** **[Open]** move, and theme your clown around that.'),
('commissaryOfInterplanetarySecurity', 'COMMISSARY OF INTERPLANETARY SECURITY', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'CIS', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: CIS]', 'Prerequisite: Must be Jade\r\n\r\nYou are a member of the Junior branch of the Commissary of Interplanetary Security, the ever watching eye of the Colorguard Organization and more importantly the empire . It is your solemn duty to aid in the defense of the planet from rebels and aliens alike through the meticulous surveillance of everything anyone has ever done ever and snitching back the the long arm of the law to properly punish good-doers. You have conditional authority over all non-org trolls, as long as you can justify your orders as ORG related. Drones will not target you while in your ORG uniform, which you now gain for free as well as a flair on all social media. You gain access to all online chat clients and website results (excluding ones obscured by metapowers, such as Limeblood Chat Clients), as it is your duty to monitor them for suspicious content. When you spot a troll who seems to be up to no good, you may tag a CIS WATCHLIST level onto them. The more WATCHLIST points a troll has, the more trouble they\'re in! You can only give trolls a WATCHLIST level if they do something illegal, like talking back to you. If they do something SUPER illegal, like conspiring to blow up the Clown Church, you can move right up to 5 points!\r\n\r\n> **1 POINT**: Stop that. The troll is **[Stressed]** if they start an encounter today, and puts +ON WATCHLIST+ on all their text messages for a day. \r\n\r\n> **2 POINTS**: Seriously, I\'m warning you. As 1 POINT, but it lasts a week instead.\r\n\r\n> **3 POINTS**: Alright, buster, you asked for it! The troll can\'t use Social Media for the rest of the day and can only send phrases like a club penguin safechat, like \"I THINK THE EMPIRE IS GREAT!\". Meanwhile, you\'re authorized to contact the HET and ask them to investigate this troll. Or even do it yourself! This lasts a day, then downgrades to 2 POINTS tomorrow.\r\n\r\n> **4 POINTS**: Yeah, okay, fuck you. You send a DRONE to fight them. This otherwise works as a 3 POINT tag.\r\n\r\n> **5 POINTS**: WE NEED A DOZEN DRONES ON THIS DICKBAG, STAT! You call up a DRONE STRIKE **[Hazard]** to attack the troll. This otherwise works as a 3 POINT tag.'),
('competitiveStreak', 'COMPETITIVE STREAK', 'OTHER', 'BLIGHTSMITH', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Blightsmith]', 'There’s a lot of weapons going around. That means you have to constantly prove that yours are the best. Otherwise, how else are you going to make sales or prove you actually do something worthwhile with your time? If anyone in an encounter besides yourself is using one of your weapons, they become **[Talented]** at **[Strife]** moves as they do their best to show off your craftsmanship. You also become **[Smug]** on top of this. That’s right, your enemies are getting beaten up by your weapon.\r\n'),
('compulsate', 'COMPULSATE', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Strife][Psionic][Locked: Mastermind]', 'Secrets schmecrets! You can pull the information people don’t want you to know directly from your target. It is NOT a pleasant experience, but hey, who gives a shit, right? When you want to invade someone’s privacy completely, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Your psionics short-circuit, and you accidentally use your powers on yourself! You spill secrets and give the opponent a free PROBLEM SLEUTHING answer of their choosing. You take **2 [Psychic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Your opponent realizes what you’re pulling, and they shrug you off! You take a **-1 [Nerf]** to **+IMG** rolls for the thread.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You don’t do what you set out to do, and know no secrets— but you’re pretty annoyed by that, frankly! You gain **1 [WHAM]** as you start getting kinda mad.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Whoop! Your opponent “gladly” “offers” you their secrets. The opponent is forced to speak out loud, and tell you one secret about them they wouldn\'t ordinarily tell you, and they take **1 [Psychic]** damage. They know what just happened.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: WHOOOP! Your opponent “accidentally” “overshares” to you, and has a pretty bad “headache”. You are told a secret that the target wouldn\'t tell anyone except their closest friends, and they either take **2 [Psychic]** damage, or take **1 [Psychic]** damage and give your next **[Manipulate]** or **[Control]** roll to have a +2 **[Buff]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Your target tells you their whole life-story. You know ALL their darkest secrets, even the ones they would never tell anyone… maybe stuff they haven\'t even admitted to themselves. They take **3 [Psychic]** damage, and they leave themselves open to further manipulation; your next **[Manipulate]** or **[Control]** roll against them is **[Tiered Up]**.'),
('concoctiomancy', 'CONCOCTIOMANCY', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Recharge: 2][Locked: Scienceling]', 'Potions? No, no, NO, these are CONCOCTIONS, ADMIXTURES, etcetera! Every Scienceling\'s first foray is to mix random chemicals together without thinking twice. It\'s fun, and educational! As an action, you can throw together and drink a test tube of weirdly coloured liquids. If all goes well, you\'ll do… decently..? Roll 1d8.\r\n\r\n> 1. You immediately get sick. Genius. You take **1 [Somatic]** damage and become **[Revolted]** and **[Bloodied]**.\r\n> 2. Uh-oh. You are exposed to the Fury Fever Affliction.\r\n> 3. You explode. You and everyone present take **3 [Somatic]** damage. You are then **[Slowed]**.\r\n> 4. Your mind feels clear. You gain **1 EUREKA**.\r\n> 5. Tastes like orange juice..? Strange, but you feel pretty okay. You become **[Focused]**.\r\n> 6. Hoogh… that boosted your bodily functions, indeed! You can use **+PSP** to roll all moves for **1 turn**.\r\n> 7. Yes! Perfect! You can use **+PSP** to roll all moves for **2 turns**.\r\n> 8. AEIIIOUUGH! You feel INCREDIBLE! You **[Heal] 2 HP**, and can use **+PSP** to roll all moves for **3 turns**.'),
('confectionaryTerror', 'CONFECTIONARY TERROR', 'OTHER', 'TRICKSTER', '[Template][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Trickster]', 'YOU CAN SEE IT. THE HOLE IN THE WORLD, THE HOLE IN EVERYONE AROUND YOU. It all needs to be filled, filled with the glorious reality shown to you by that sweet sawdust behind the angles of space and time. And you’re the anomaly for the job! You are always **[Joyful]**, and this emotion cannot be cleared. You can no longer experience **[Serious]**, **[Dead Serious]** or the **[Heightened]** versions of any Negative emotions except **[Laughing]**. Trolls around you can\'t be **[Serious]**. In addition, you have a natural resistance to getting dragged down by others- your will to fulfill your most delicious mission is absolute. You cannot have more than **2 [Drag]**, any other **[Drag]** that would be inflicted on you is instantly reflected and put onto its source instead. Your transformation has gotten stronger too, and now affects SCP and TIT trolls!! No one is exempt from your rainbow glory. Your reality-bending effects every 5 turns have grown in power and now all sorts of fun stuff can happen!! In addition to the standard effects, a fun extra effect occurs based on the roll of 1d8! \r\n\r\n> **1**: You and an opponent of your choice swap an item. You each get to decide which of your own items you’ll be giving to each other, and the items are returned at the end of the encounter. \r\n\r\n> **2**: Everyone in the encounter gains an additional **2 [Boost]**, but takes **1 [Psychic]** damage. \r\n\r\n> **3**: One random participant in the encounter is turned into a robot for **2 rounds**! They take **1 extra damage** from VOLTKIND-abstrata attacks, and cannot gain **[Drag]** or **[Boost]** during the duration. \r\n\r\n> **4**: A little rain cloud appears above each participant’s heads, making everyone all **[Soggy]**. SOPPING WET BEASTS, ALL OF YOU.\r\n\r\n> **5**: Everyone is **[Quickened]** this turn, and **[Slowed]** next turn. \r\n\r\n> **6**: Everyone gains **1 [WHAM]**!! \r\n\r\n> **7**: A random combatant is turned into a Lvl 2 MONSTER next round, they get to use the monster\'s moves, but they keep their own stats and HP. This effect ends after their turn is over. \r\n\r\n> **8**: Everyone spends one action to goof off this turn, they are **[Stunned]**. \r\n\r\n'),
('confidenceIsKey', 'CONFIDENCE IS KEY', 'HEART', 'HEART', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Heart]', 'You never give up! You don’t let your mistakes drag you down, no matter what. So long as you believe in yourself, the whole world will believe too! Any time you’re made to use **[Drag]**, you bounce right back, and gain an amount of **[Boost]** equal to half the **[Drag]** you had, rounded up.'),
('conjecturify', 'CONJECTURIFY', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Recharge: 2][Manipulate][Locked: Nyastrologist]', 'What a Libza thing to say, right? You can tell at a glance the kind of person someone is, depending on the sign they wear on their shirt. This gives you an immense power; the power to affirm their greatest traits, or to act like a bluh bluh huge bitch. The choice is yours! You can\'t target a troll more than once with this move per encounter. When you want to judge someone\'s sign, roll **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Shucks!!! Did you say something wrong? Your target starts **[Crying]** if they\'re an ally, or becomes **[Out-Of-Control]** if they\'re an enemy.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Well that\'s. Less than great. Your target takes it the wrong way; you give **2 [Boost]** or **2 [Drag]**, whichever is less beneficial.\r\n\r\n**OK**: They tell you they don\'t believe in the zodiac. You say OK.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You make a statement; it either pisses them off or makes them understand you better. You either give them **2 [Boost]** or **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Choice words! You do the following effect, based on your words. You choose whether each module affects you or them individually.\r\n\r\n**Sway**: \r\n\r\n> **Prospit**: They seem nice, but… **[+1 Boost]**\r\n> **Derse**: They seem like a dick, but… **[+1 Drag]**\r\n\r\n**Sign**:\r\n\r\n> **Earth**: They look like they struggle with their emotional responses… **[Gain 1 Resistance to all damage for 2 turns]**\r\n> **Water**: They seem so lonely… **[Heal 1 HP]**\r\n> **Fire**: They\'re so obviously distressed under the surface… **[Gain 2 Boost]**\r\n> **Air**: They\'re giving crazy unpredictable vibes… **[Reduce Recharge of all moves by 1]**\r\n\r\n**Aspect**:\r\n\r\n> **Body**: So they should probably chill. **[Lose an Emotion or become Numb/Peaceful if they had none]**\r\n> **Soul**: So they should probably do something about that. **[Gain an Emotion, you choose if negative or positive, they choose specifics]**\r\n\r\n**MAX**: THE STARS OPEN THEMSELVES TO YOU! Increase all numerical values listed by 2!'),
('conjurificate', 'CONJURIFICATE', 'OTHER', 'ASTROSORCERER', '[Template][Basic][Magic][Strife][Magic Missile][Locked: Astrosorcerer]', 'One of the most important reasons to use magic is, of course, the sick spells you can use to hurt and kill people. DEVASTATION RAINS FROM YOU! The damage from this spell is both **[Somatic]** and **[Psychic]**. When you want to shoot blasts of magic, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: AAAAEEEIIOOUUUUGHHHHH… your magic explodes in your face. You take **2 [Somatic/Psychic]** damage. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: Your spellcasting implement kinda farts out a spell that burbles onto the floor. F.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You start charging up a WICKED spell. Your next CONJURIFICATE spell is **[Tiered Up]**\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: WHA-POW! A solid blow! You deal **1 [Somatic/Psychic]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: PSSSEW! A stream of magic energy hits the opponent hard! You do **1 [Somatic/Psychic]** damage, or the effects of any one of the following wicked spells. Each individual effect is **[Recharge: 3]**.\r\n\r\n> **MAGIC MISSILE**: It\'s the one! The one everyone uses all the time! You target everyone in the Encounter, dealing **1 [Somatic/Psychic]** Damage to your target and **1 extra [Somatic/Psychic]** Damage to you and your allies.\r\n\r\n> **SHIELDBLAST**: You love being behind a big hunk of magic metal! You summon a shield and throw it at a target. You deal 0 Damage, but your target gains **2 [Resistance]** until your next turn. This loses the **[Strife]** tag and gains the **[Flourish]** tag.\r\n\r\n> **FIREBALL**: You do not need an explanation. You deal **2 [Blaze]** **[Somatic/Psychic]** Damage to a target, but unless one of you are **[Flying]** or are at a far distance apart, you take it as well. Too close!\r\n\r\n> **STARFREEZE**: You flash freeze your opponent! You deal **2 [Frost]** **[Somatic/Psychic]** Damage to a target, but you become **[Slowed]** for a turn as you need to warm up after.\r\n\r\n> **NEBULA CLOUD**: This stuff tears spaceships up because of microfragments, you know! You deal **2 [Laser]** **[Somatic/Psychic]** Damage to a target, but become **[Blinded]** as the battlefield gets foggy.\r\n\r\n> **SPACE NOISE**: The myth that space is quiet is very untrue. Here, listen! You make the exact sound that stars make, and inflict **1 [Sonic]** **[Somatic/Psychic]** Damage on all present in addition to **[Deafened]** for **2 Turns**. Trolls already **[Deafened]** are immune.\r\n\r\n> **I CAST FIST**: You start saying mumbojumbo that sounds magical... THEN PUNCH THEM INSTEAD THAT FOOL!!! MAGIC IS FAKE AS FUCK. This loses the **[Magic]** tag and instead gains **[Physical]**, dealing purely **[Somatic]** Damage. Your target takes **1 damage** for every successful PROBLEM SLEUTHING you have targeted them with prior to this roll, to a maximum of **3 [Somatic]** damage, as you trick them so goodly; the count of PROBLEM SLEUTHINGS resets after each use of this effect.\r\n\r\n> **UPSPELL**: Sometimes you don\'t want to do a fancy spell. Sometimes you just want to do damage. You deal **2 [Somatic/Psychic]** Damage instead of 1, or 3 instead of 2 on a **MAX**. This effect has no recharge.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Your spell is overwhelmingly devastating! The opponent is blown the fuck up by a fireball or whatever! You do a **GREAT**, but you do 2 Damage instead.'),
('contrivedCoincidence', 'CONTRIVED COINCIDENCE', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Passive]', 'Limes are a caste which shouldn\'t exist; and yet sometimes, they do exist, and the universe goes to odd lengths to keep them kicking. You gain access to the following SHENANIGANS effects:\r\n\r\n**GOOD**:\r\n\r\n> **MY STUFF!**: Your opponent\'s Sylladex just happens to malfunction, and their items unload onto the floor! They can either take an action to pick them up, or fight on without their items. \r\n\r\n> **MARTHAAAAA**: Something happens mid combat that shows your opponent that you and they are not so different. Fiduspawn cards fall out of your pocket, and your opponent loves Fiduspawn. Your playlist starts jamming, and the music is sentimental to them. They either allow you to **[Heal] 2 HP**, stop fighting, or take **3 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> **SCATTER**: A camera picks up that there\'s a hemoanomalous troll in the area… but doesn\'t figure who it is. Eh, just kill everyone. Sirens go off, and A DRONE STRIKE **[Hazard]** is on its way in **3 turns**, and all present trolls temporarily gain the **[Cullbait]** tag, even if they were highbloods. Everyone, let\'s stop fighting, and RUUUUN!\r\n\r\n> **FREAK ACCIDENT**: WHOAH! That\'s EXTREMELY strange! Your opponent is struck by lightning, knocked over by an explosion or falls down a pit. How… narratively unsatisfying. The target takes **2 damage**. This effect can be used on the same turn as a **[Strife]** effect, but has the **[One-Off]** tag.'),
('controlFreak', 'CONTROL FREAK', 'OTHER', 'WITCH', '[Class][Basic][Recharge: 3][Locked: Witch]', 'You like to be the one... in control of things. You\'re aware of your surroundings and how to manipulate them to your liking. An eye of newt here, a prod at someone’s life choices there… This comes in handy quite often! When you roll a **GOOD** or higher **SHENANIGANS** result, you may choose to inflict one more free **GOOD** result on top of what you rolled. This does not apply to **MAX** rolls. Please, you can only call down so much pox on one house. Calm down.\r\n\r\n'),
('controlledBurn', 'CONTROLLED BURN', 'OTHER', 'FIREFUELER', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Firefueler]', 'When a HET officer or a Bustin’ Clown points you at a target and commands you to burn it, you don’t waste time asking “how hot” or “how long”, you just burn it until you run out of fuel or receive the order to stop. The combined efforts of the ORGS, both low and high, give more kindling to the burning beacon of Imperial order. When in an encounter with a member of a different ORG, you gain a specific bonus. You can benefit from multiple bonuses if more than one ORG is present.\r\n\r\n> **CIS**: As a **[One-Off]** action, you can ask a **CIS** agent to designate a target. They may take a **[Free]** action to mark one target as a Threat. For the next 3 rounds, your rolls against that target have a +1 **[Buff]**.\r\n\r\n> **TIT**: You may spend up to 3 **[Boost]** to inflict an equal about of **[Drag]** on your target as an action when you successfully **[Strife]** a target.\r\n\r\n> **HET**: As an action, you can recite Imperial doctrine to make both you and a **HET** officer **[Brave]** for 3 rounds. This has a **[Recharge: 5]**.\r\n\r\n> **Cullscout**: You gain the effect of the badge tier under the Cullscouts current tier to a max of 8 MEDALS tier.\r\n\r\n> **Bustin’**: Your FLAMEFLINGER now deals **[Holy]** damage alongside **[Blaze]** damage.\r\n\r\n> **Orphaner**: You gain 1 **[Hold]** to reduce the damage of a Lusii monsters attack by 1, after **[WHAM]** and **[Weaknesses]**. You gain another **[Hold]** if an Orphaner scores a **MAX [Strife]** roll against a Lusii monster.\r\n'),
('cookingByTheBook', 'COOKING BY THE BOOK', 'OTHER', 'GOREMAND', '[Template][Downtime][Unlock: Goremand]', 'You’re not like other trolls. You know spices. You know flavor. You know fire bad, but you also know fire good… for cooking! Best of all, you know cooking has a wide range to master! You gain the CULLINARY PURSUIT move, which allows you to make any **[Consumable]** items as a piece of food, which costs **1 VP** less than normal. When you want to make your own extraordinary dish, roll **+APP**:\r\n\r\n**MIN**: OH GOG, OH JEGUS, EVERYTHING’S ON FIRE! HOW DID YOU FUCK UP POURING A BOWL OF CEREAL THIS **BAD**LY?! SHAME ON YOU AND YOUR LUSUS! You start all encounters for the next week with **+2 [Drag]** and feeling **[Agitated]** by your wrongdoing.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Something went terribly, horribly wrong. Whether you mixed up the baking powder for baking soda or shoved an entire gobblebeast where you weren’t supposed to, your creation is an inedible wreck. Seriously, put censor bars on that thing. You start your next encounter with **1 [Drag]** and feeling **[Stressed]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: I’mma keep it real with you chief, this isn’t your best work. But hey, it’s also not your worst! Nothing particular happens with you or your dish.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Oh! Ohoho! Through the miracle of reading and following a recipe, you’ve made something edible! You create a dish using a **[Consumable]** item you have access to. It costs **1 VP** less than normal. Nice work! Choose one of the following effects; this will be your specialty. All dishes you create will have this effect by default. However, you can also add an additional effect by spending **1 LUX** on your great meal to create another portion. You can make up to three portions of your meal. You can’t stack effects, so no baking three portions that restores HP, jerk!\r\n\r\n> **Baking**: From humble homemade bread to the most lavish quad bonding cakes, the pastry is a mistress to be feared and respected in her versatility. All dishes you create give a **+1 HP** as sugar rushes through your veins and restores your vitality. \r\n\r\n> **Frying**: Dunk some shit in oil, let it sit for a little while, and BAM! Deliciousness. All dishes you create give **+1 WHAM** as the power of frying everything fills you with determination to fry more things.\r\n\r\n> **Grilling**: The only thing keeping your ingredients from the burning flame is metal bars and your skillset. The perfect method for meats and veggies of all kinds. All dishes you create give a temporary +1 stat point to any single encounter.\r\n\r\n> **Boiling**: Not all foods have to be solid! Soups, stews, and broths warm the body and the soul. Unless you eat it cold. You monster. All dishes you create can **[Tier Down]** a Negative emotion as the comfort of warm cluckbeast noodle soup soothes your soul.\r\n\r\n> **Mixing**: For the foods that are basically a bunch of ingredients chopped up and thrown into a bowl together, like salads and smoothies. Grubslurry Agitator go BRRRRRRR. All dishes you create can impart a **[Base]** Positive emotion as you eat healthy and do your body some good for once.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: What a fabulous meal, cooked to perfection with love (and maybe a little spite)! A little bit of your own flair went a long way! You get a **GOOD**, but you can add an additional effect for free!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Smell that? That’s browned butter, kid. Everybody else is out of their fuckin’ league. You are a god in the kitchen, and this dish is proof! You get a **GREAT**, but you feel so awesome about your future that you become **[Inspired]** in your next encounter.\r\n\r\n'),
('coolCat', 'COOL CAT', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Passive]', 'You know what? No! You\'re tired of being \"average\"! You\'re tired of people treating you like you\'re just a cute kitty! You\'re not some harmless pet— you\'re awesome, remarkable, COOL! This kitty\'s got CLAWS! You gain the following **GOOD** SWASHBUCKLE effects…\r\n\r\n**PURRFECTION**: Whoa! That last attack was way stronger than anyone expected! You take a bow as the true effects come in with a delay, **[Tiering Up]** a previous roll you made this turn. \r\n\r\n**POUNCE**: You LEAP really hard directly into someone. KHWAAAAH! This acts as a PCHOOOOOOOO, except you take someone with you!\r\n\r\n**SKITTERSLIDE**: You wall jump, dash, and scamper around the place like a crazy fast cat, almost becoming a blur!  The next time you make your opponent use **[Drag]** on a **[Physical]** move, you can double the **[Drag]** used as a **[Reaction]** as you finally jump at them. \r\n\r\n**PRESSURE ON**: Skid to the side, the other side, run circles around them… the pressure is on! The target\'s LET\'S STRIFE rolls are **[Godawful]** for **2 turns**.'),
('coordinationIsKey', 'COORDINATION IS KEY', 'OTHER', 'SEER', '[Class][Basic][Recharge: 3][Locked: Seer]', 'As one of, if not the only, tactician of your squad of friends (or foes?), you\'re not always the one actually doing things, but you do know how to boss people around to do the things! As an action, you may call out your plan of attack, telling your allies what to do next and granting them a **+2 [Buff]** to their next action. Alternatively, you may call out a plan of attack for your enemies... which still grants them a **+2 [Buff]** to their next action, but leaves them **[Dumbfounded]** for **2 rounds** as they\'re left wondering why the hell you did that.\r\n\r\n'),
('copingBySeething', 'COPING BY SEETHING', 'OTHER', 'BARD', '[Class][Advanced][Free][Heal][One-Off][Locked: Bard]', 'Okay, sure. You’ve let go of your unhealthier coping mechanisms (most of them, anyways), but in the absence of those mechanisms, you choose to vent your frustrations in a much more… DIRECT way. After all! The releasing of anger can better any medicine under the sun! After witnessing an enemy get 4 **GREAT** or 2 **MAX** results within 2 rounds, or witnessing an ally get 4 **BAD** or 2 **MIN** results within 3 rounds, you can ignore the effects of any **[Negative] [Emotions]** you currently have and instead be afflicted with **[Stressed]** and **[Disgusted]**, going over the 3 **[Emotion]** limit if needed but still affecting you with **[Drag]**. In exchange, you **[Heal]** 2 **HP** (ignoring **[Disgusted]**) when you gain the **[Emotions]** and deal +1 damage for as long as you have the **[Stressed]** and **[Disgusted] [Emotions]**. If you lose one, you lose both. You can’t cope but not seethe and you can’t seethe if you aren’t coping.\r\n'),
('copingMechanism', 'COPING MECHANISM', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Look… let’s be honest. Living life here is… it’s enough to really make you anxious. Doesn\'t matter if you live in a swamp or online, the world of Alternia isn\'t a great place. So everyone needs something to keep themselves grounded. And that means you! Select one of the following coping mechanisms.\r\n\r\n> **MUSIC**: Just keep your headphones in, don\'t make eye contact, it\'s all okay, it\'s all fine… you are immune to the **[Stressed]** condition from others. If you give it to yourself, you gain **2 [Drag]** instead. \r\n\r\n> **CRAFTS**: Making stuff always means having specific materials, whether that\'s brushes for painting or tongs for metalworking. You can create items on the fly in the middle of an encounter, but these items cost **1 VP** extra.\r\n\r\n> **ATHLETICS**: You are so good at muscles. So so so good. The first time you would become **[Tired]** in an encounter, you don\'t, and you instead gain **1 [Boost]**. RAAAAAWR!\r\n\r\n> **CINEMA**: RomComs, Spewtube, RomComs, Television, RomComs, anime, RomComs… look, you LIKE watching stuff. Especially RomComs. A weird amount of RomComs. That said, you know your tropes. Rolls for Tree Moves or Effects from Dungeoneer Rusts, Vagabond Bronzes, Cyberpunk Golds, Nyanjutsu Olives, Slayer Jades, Scienceling Teals, Marquis Ceruleans, Jock Indigos, Mafioso Purples or Pilot Violets are SOOOO cliché; they\'re **[Inept]** against you. \r\n\r\n> **PLANTS**: Ssssh ssh ssh… a little water, a little plant food, some blood… theeeere. Plant monster moves are **[Inept]** against you.\r\n\r\n> **PETS**: Surround yourself with MANY cats. You can have multiple **[Custodians]** through the CUSTODIAN COMPANION move; you gain one now, or gain the move if you didn\'t already have it. You can have as many as you like, but you take the move over and over again, and can only have one **[Custodian]** in an encounter. Just get a SWARM **[Custodian]** if you want many.\r\n\r\n> **SOMETHING ELSE**: Books? Cooking? MURDER? You get a **[Template]** **[Entry]**; the **[Template]** uses a stat you are already **[Talented]** in.'),
('corpsposal', 'CORPSPOSAL', 'RUST', 'ADULT', '[Rust][Locked: Adult]\r\n', 'Rust… rust… rust… damn, that gold got WRECKED… bronze… lime? Huh. All in all, just another stack of corpses to be mulched and turned into… biofuel? Maybe. You don\'t care about what happens to the corpses - you just make sure they get out. Eventually, counting the many ways that bodies get mutilated begins to feel like just another Splatterday. You are always **[Serious]** because holy shit life is brief. The first time someone tries to give you either **[Scared]**, **[Dread]**, or **[Disgusted]**, you instead become **[Dead Serious]**. Any subsequent rounds in which you would get any of the listed emotions, you receive them as normal. On a **[Recharge: 2]** when an enemy is below half **HP**, or is a Rainbow Drinker or Shadowdropper, you can render them **[Trapped]** when you deal damage as you bash those pesky moving parts. If they were already **[Trapped]**, they are knocked **[Floorbound]**. \r\n'),
('couldBeWorse', 'COULD BE WORSE!', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'The life of a rust is full of misery but you’ve learned to begrudgingly accept the aspects of life that aren’t the most blessing. For an enemy to heighten a negative **[Emotion]** on you the base must be inflicted twice extra rather than once extra, since you’re a bit hard to put down after you’ve gotten so tough. If an enemy inflicts a heightened negative **[Emotion]** you do not have yet, it is instead inflicted as its base form.\n\n'),
('coulrophobiaWarning', 'COULROPHOBIA WARNING', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Free]', 'People are scared of you! Is that really a surprise? Just look at you— you\'re a walking representation of the scariest things in the world! Slashers, clowns and religious people! When someone around you would become **[Scared]** or **[Terrified]**, you can choose to instead make them **[Frightened]** or **[Horrified]**, emotions unique to you. Trolls immune to **[Scared]** are not immune to these new emotions.\r\n\r\n**FRIGHTENED**: An emotion where every instinct in your body is telling you to run… but you can\'t make yourself do it! Your LET\'S STRIFE rolls are **[Inept]**, **[Magic]** rolls against you gain a **+1 [Buff]**, and you can\'t make opponents use **[Drag]** without becoming **[Stunned]** next turn.\r\n\r\n**HORRIFIED**: An emotion where a wave of revulsion totally overwhelms you as you stare in absolute fear at the sight before you. Your LET\'S STRIFE rolls are **[Godawful]**, **[Magic]** rolls against you are **[Tiered Up]**, and you can\'t make opponents use **[Drag]** or use **[Boost]** yourself. If you would become **[Scared]** while **[Horrified]**, you gain **2 [Drag]**.'),
('counterculturist', 'COUNTERCULTURIST', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Passive][Unlock: Subcultist]', 'You don\'t really care for all that cave stuff. I mean, it\'s cool, whatever. No big deal, you guess. It just isn\'t for you. Your thing is self-expression, and boy howdy, do you express the self. Fashion is your passion, and you stay very true to your passion. As for what KIND of passion… well, pick a subculture from the list below, and gain a **[Talent]** and Fashion Item (See Chapter 29: FASHION) from it!\r\n\r\n> **Scene**: (**+RAS**) Rawr! x3 You dress like an eye-strain warning, you\'ve got thick eye shadow and that signature scene haircut. You gain the SCENE HAIR Fashion Head Item, which gives you **+1 RAS** and **-1 PSP**.\r\n\r\n> **Decora**: (**+PLC**) Wanna see how many brightly coloured accessories you can wear? You reject maturity and go full kidcore with many colours and many, many accessories. You gain the ACCESSORY OVERLOAD Fashion Accessory Item, which gives you **+1 PLC** and **-1 GRT**.\r\n\r\n> **Lolita**: (**+GRA**) You are the most dignified-looking bitch on Alternia. You dress in old, Troll Victorian wear and take pride in your appearance. You have the STATELY WEAR Fashion Top or Bottom Item, which gives you **+1 GRA** and **-1 APP**.\r\n\r\n> **Cybergoth**: (**+APP**) Oh bitch that is one FUNKY get up. You wear facemasks, goggles, heavy makeup and of course, this WILD hair-do that may or may not have LED lights. You gain the CYBERGOTH HEADGEAR Fashion Head Item, which gives you **+1 APP** and **-1 GRA**.\r\n\r\n> **Metalhead**: (**+GRT**) RAAAAAAAAAGE! You headbang, you mosh, you listen to the sickest music, and of course… you wear your signature band merch. You gain the METALHEAD TEE Fashion Top Item, which gives you **+1 GRT** and **-1 PSP**.\r\n\r\n> **Punk**: (**+HUB**) You don\'t do things in half measures; you have a sickass deathhawk, a tonne of piercings, and a rage in your heart against the machine (drones). You gain the PUNKASS DEATHHAWK Fashion Head Item (though it doesn\'t need to be a deathhawk so much as it is any wild punk Hairdo), which gives you **+1 HUB**, **-1 PLC**.\r\n\r\n> **Goth**: (**+PSP**) Yours is the most contemplative rebellion against the Mother Grub. Wearing white makeup to mirror rainbow drinkers and inverting holy symbols of the Cloister, you are a bad bitch. A bad, spooky bitch. You gain the BLASPHEMOUS PENDANT Fashion Accessory Item, which gives you **+1 PSP** and **-1 RAS**.\r\n\r\n> **Alt**: (**+IMG**) Something else? Did we miss your Witch House Jades? Your Faerie Goth? Your Skatepunk? Your imagination is the limit, so long as you wield your fashion with it. You gain the ALTFASHION PIECE, a Fashion Item for any one slot with **+1 IMG** and -1 to any one other stat.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('countryVsCity', 'COUNTRY VS CITY', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Bronze trolls have a reputation for being country hicks. On the one hand, yeah, there are a lot of Bronzes that populate rural places and work farming lives. On the other hand, there\'s about as many Bronzes as other castes in the city, too, so what the fuck. The stereotype sticks though, so many trolls will often ask… which do you call home, the city or the countryside? Pick an option from below.\r\n\r\n**CITY SLICKER**: You\'re an urbanite for sure. The mean streets are all you\'ve ever known, and you\'ve gotten pretty used to them by now. You can make BIG BUYS for items up to the **Well-Off** Wealth with no repercussions.\r\n\r\n**COUNTRY FOLK**: You don\'t really care about the big city— a nice place to visit, but it\'s full of drones and shit! No, you prefer to live out in the sticks, that\'s for sure. Lusii and animalistic monsters have a **-2 [Nerf]** to **[Strife]** rolls against you.\r\n\r\n**NEW TO THE CITY**: Yeah, you\'re from the country, sure. But you\'re here in the city now, and things are… different! **[Analyze]** rolls at you are **[Inept]**; people can\'t figure you out as you step between both worlds.\r\n\r\n**MOVED TO THE COUNTRY**: That\'s better. No more smog, no more concrete jungle… life out here is harder but better. You are immune to the **[Stressed]** emotion; whenever you would get it, you instead feel **[Peaceful]**.\r\n\r\n**ITINERANT**: You\'re a traveler! You wander between worlds, never stopping in either forever. You\'ve seen basically everything by now; as such, your **[Analyze]** rolls can never be **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]**, or **[Nerfed]**.'),
('cracksInYourCode', 'CRACKS IN YOUR CODE', 'OTHER', 'HACKERMAN', '[Template][Advanced][One-off][Locked: Hackerman]', 'The funny thing about an empire that’s lasted millenia and sprawls across the galaxy is that they tend to not update tech that much. Another funny thing is that on Alternia, where the kids are, tech updates far too fast. Therefore, there’s exploits that can be done due to this disconnect. The battle GUI included! Once per encounter, you can give yourself as much **[Boost]** as you like. This does, however, put you on the CIS WATCHLIST with 5 WATCHLIST POINTS immediately. Maybe it\'s worth it?'),
('cramSession', 'CRAM SESSION', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Student]', 'Come on, come on, come on! You\'re cutting it way too close right now! You\'ve learned to put in a fuckload of work when the going gets tough, even to your own detriment. When you are below half HP, you may choose to become **[Quickened]**. However, you become **[Stressed]** when you do so. Who knew cramming was bad for your mental health?'),
('crazedCackle', 'CRAZED CACKLE', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][One-Off][Manipulate][Mental][Locked: Scienceling]', 'Oh, they think you\'re crazy? Would a crazy person be so darn excited about science? Observe! KYAAAHAHAHA!! I AM AMONG GODS, FOR THE CREATION OF LIFE IS WITHIN MY HANDS! WAAAAAAAAHAHA! See? That\'s a neurotypical thing to do. Each effect here is **[One-Off]** for each troll you use it on, but you may use it on other trolls later. When you want to cackle, roll **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Oh god, you\'re choking! Blegh— hagh— pthewy— you gain the CHOKING Affliction, oh no! You\'re **[Embarrassed]** by your gaff.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: It wasn\'t that funny, man. You are **[Embarrassed]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Yeah, you\'re laughing. Makes you feel good. You get **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You laugh pretty hard, yeah! You either gain **2 [Boost]**, give **2 [Boost]** to an ally, or give an enemy **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: MWAHAHAHA! There you go, THAT\'S a cackle. Choose one of the following.\r\n\r\n> **SELF**: You feel great! You become **[Proud]**. \r\n> **ENEMY**: Okay, kinda freaked out by this. Your target becomes **[Stressed]**.\r\n> **ALLY**: Heheh. You\'re right, Scienceling! There\'s always time to laugh out there! Your ally becomes **[Hopeful]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Jegus, you really have some lungs backing up that laugh, aye? You get a **GREAT**, but the emotions are **[Heightened]**.\r\n\r\n'),
('crimePays', 'CRIME PAYS', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Downtime][Locked: Mafioso]', 'Money makes the world go round, and you like it when the world does that. Whether it\'s through extorting lowbloods, threatening highbloods, or just making money at the pizzeria the boss owns, being part of the Clutch pays you well! When you want to make some money, roll **+APP**. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: Someone snitched!! Your criminal operations are uncovered by some bozos who think they\'re hot shit, and you need to lay low for a while. All your **[Downtime]** rolls are **[Godawful]** for a month! Hate it when you go shopping and a legislacerator sees you.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: As a **MIN**, but just **[Inept]**. The legislacerator isn\'t chasing you, but he\'s walking pretty quickly. \r\n\r\n**OK**: The legislacerator just shakes his head at you when he sees you out shopping. As a **BAD**, but it\'s just a **-2 [Nerf]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Ka-ching! Your nasty crimes pay off! You get **Treasure I**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: That\'s the ticket! You make **Treasure II**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Now. Now we\'re talking. That\'s a whole fucktonne of cash. That\'s **Treasure III**.'),
('crowdPleaser', 'CROWD PLEASER', 'OTHER', 'GOREMAND', '[Template][Advanced][Lengthy][Locked: Goremand]', 'There are few things that trolls agree on. One is the almighty rule of the Empire. Two is that violence always solves everything. Three is that when violence doesn’t do the trick, a good meal will! As a **[Lengthy]** action, you can make a dish to be shared with the members of the encounter, whether they be friend or foe. Those who choose to eat this dish gain the effect of the dish type you specialize in and enjoy being **[Peaceful]** for **three rounds**. Wait, why were we fighting again…?'),
('crusaculturist', 'CRUSACULTURIST', 'INDIGO', 'ADULT', '[Indigo][Locked: Adult]', 'Alternian culture is one of violence and death. From daily routine, the fauna that inhabit the lands, to the violent portmanteaus that compromise Alternian names and terms. All trolls grow up learning and knowing that violence and living go claw in unlovable claw. As a Crusaculturist, you bring this culture wherever you go, both as frontline infantry against the enemies of the Empire and as a reminder to make every troll stay vigilant against the reaper\\\'s scythe that hangs around every single corner. Remember, it\\\'s not paranoia if they\\\'re actually out to get you. Whenever you roll a move and get a **GOOD** or better, allies that roll a move with the same tag gain a +1 **[Buff]** to that same roll and gain 1 **[Boost]** if they match or exceed your result. If an ally rolls a **MIN** on a move with a tag corresponding to a move you rolled on your turn, you may take a **[Free] [Reaction]** to scream at them and immediately make the result an **OK** instead. This also renders your ally **[Overwhelmed]** for two rounds, starting on the round you used the reaction on. This is a **[One-Off]** for each ally.'),
('culturalStudy', 'CULTURAL STUDY', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Passive]', 'By now, you’ve gotten very good at researching the history of Alternia. You’re keenly aware that that is the true role of an Indigo; to find out more about the past, and pass it on to tomorrow. As such, you’ve learned some important stuff, and you’re sure to preserve what you know for oncoming generations too. Select one of the following options.\r\n\r\n> **LITERATURE**: Ah… nothing beats a well told tale, don’t you agree? Lime **[Magic]** rolls against you are all **[Inept]** or **[Tiered Up]**, your choice, and you become **[Enthusiastic]** if one uses it on you. You recognize these story beats! Why, they must be one of the 32 Dramatic Situations, according to Troll Georges Pulti, that–\r\n\r\n> **THEATRE**: Whether it’s performance arts or the type of “theatre” popular among many Indigos (Muscular Theatre, it’s basically wrestling, although there’s also Indoor Sportsball too), you’re a real fan of sitting back and watching others do the work for you. In a TEAM STRIFE, you can choose to take no action on your turn if you are on STANDBY, instead cheering for your allies as they go ham. All allies gain **2 [Boost]** if you do this. \r\n\r\n> **FASHION**: YOUTHS IN SUITS wasn’t enough for you. You’re a genius when it comes to dressing up right, you know? When you purchase a **[Fashion]** item, you get a second one for free. HAUTE CLAWTURE moves are always **[Talented]** for you.\r\n\r\n> **MUSIC**: Hum, hum, ha hum hum, hum ha hum hum huuuum… sorry, you were humming! You love a good piece of music. Whenever someone enters a FRAYMOTIF, you can choose to become **[Peaceful]**, or **[Serene]** if it is an enemy.\r\n\r\n> **ART**: Now this… THIS is beautiful. Whenever you would become **[Charmed]**, you may immediately make a PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll to PSYCHOANALYZE the target, comparing them to beautiful art. On a **GOOD**, you aren’t **[Charmed]**. On a **GREAT**, the charmer is **[Charmed]** instead! On a **MAX**, they’re **[Fascinated]** by you. Wow! This is a **[Reaction]**. You get all regular effects from PSYCHOANALYZE.\r\n\r\n> **SOMETHING ELSE**: There’s a thousand other options you can take here, I don’t know! Take an **[Open]** move from another caste, if you can justify tying it into a culture thing. Don’t minmax!'),
('cultureShock', 'CULTURE SHOCK', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][One-Off][Manipulate]', 'Whoaaaa! Wow, how weird! How different? What’s this? What’s that? Here, let me explain to you how it happens on Earth, in great detail, skimming over any context that may help. Trolls and Humans are, you may have noticed, quite different; notably, human curiosity far outweighs most troll’s patience. When you want to pepper a Troll with questions or over explain your own culture, roll **+RAS**. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: SHUT THE FUCK UUUUUP! SHUT UP!!!!! The opponent is **[Out-Of-Control]**. Oops? \r\n\r\n**BAD**: Oh, they’re cranky now. Maybe it was something you said? The opponent is **[Enraged]**. \r\n\r\n**OK: You just waste your breath and everyone’s time. **:(\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Blah blah blah blah blah blah blah! The opponent is **[Confused]** for **2 rounds** by how fucking much you’re talking.  \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Wh- huh- words- what??? Huh??? The opponent is completely overwhelmed by your alien talk, and is **[Dumbfounded]** for **2 rounds**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Jesus Fucking Christ. The opponent is EXTREMELY bewildereed, and begins to doubt their own existence. No, they DON’T know how come some ceruleans have spider eyes and some don’t. Genetics??? Maybe??? They’re **[Humiliated]** for **2 rounds**, and **[Dumbfounded]** for the encounter.'),
('cuspblood', 'CUSPBLOOD', 'OTHER', 'MUTANT', '[Mutant][Passive]', 'Your blood is visibly a little off-hue, and while not off-hue enough to qualify you as cullbait, you definitely lean towards one of your neighboring castes more than the other. You probably share some traits with the caste you cusp, too- for example, a purple cuspblood might have vestigial gills if their blood color is more violet, or freakishly strong Subjugglator STRENGTH if they lean indigo! Violets can only cusp purple, and rusts can only cusp bronze-  no fuchsia cuspbloods for you! I see you! Additionally, Limes cannot be cusped into from either gold or olive, they’re a little too weird even for the Empire. Gold and olive cuspbloods cannot skip over lime, they must cusp to bronze or to jade respectively.\r\n\r\nPick an adjacent caste to yours- you can take up to three **[Basic]** non-**[Psionic]** moves from that caste. However, while it might not be illegal to be a cuspblood, it’s certainly something other trolls will bully you for. After all, you’re different! You become **[Embarrassed]** if you begin **[Crying]** or become **[Bloodied]**, and ORG members have you on record and immediately know of your cuspblood status so they can like, bully you for it. If you are a Limeblood, your status is not recorded by ORGs as you still do not technically exist!'),
('custodianCompanion', 'CUSTODIAN COMPANION', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive]', 'You\'ve spent a lot of time with your custodian lately… and you know what? You feel like you can get along with them pretty well. Why not invite them out to go do stuff sometimes? You gain access to the ATRICIALIZE move from Chapter 18: CUSTODIANS, and 4 Features for your Custodian. Pretty sweet!'),
('cyanSelfworth', 'CYAN SELF-WORTH', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'Huh. You know, after some important lessons learned very painfully… Maybe your image of yourself is wrong. Maybe you AREN’T some big hotshot, smarter and better than everyone else. Or maybe you’re not as worthless as you thought you were! You gain the following effect, depending on your choice of SHADE OF TEAL. You don’t need to have taken that move to take this move, but you must choose the same option for both if you do later take it.\r\n\r\n> **SMUG SAXE**: You’ve eaten your humble pie, and have learned a thing or two about respect by now. Whenever someone other than you makes a **GOOD** or higher **[Manipulate]** roll to someone else, you get **1 [Boost]**; either you can acknowledge when someone makes a good point, or you won’t let people talk down to others like that!\r\n\r\n> **AVERAGE AQUAMARINE**: Huh! Looks like you had a pretty good read on yourself all along. UNLESS YOU DIDN’T? DID YOU GET WORSE? Maybe. Either select the effect of SMUG SAXE or TREMBLING TURQUOISE from SHADES OF TEAL, or remain content in yourself and gain **1 HP** extra. How nice!\r\n\r\n> **TREMBLING TURQUOISE**: Hey! You… you aren’t going to take that sitting down, you know! You’ve got values, you have strengths, and you’re tired of being treated as lesser. So you’re NOT GONNA LOSE! Whenever you’re knocked to **6 HP** or lower, you automatically become **[Proud]**, and feel **[Icarian]** when you’re at **3 HP** or lower.'),
('cyberspaceCowboy', 'CYBERSPACE COWBOY', 'OTHER', 'ADULT', '[Locked: Adult]', 'What\'s yours is mine is mine is yours in the vast, vast realms of cyberspace and actual space. Nowadays some of the most precious cargo a ship could hold isn\'t even tangible. Empire fleet plans, rebel whereabouts, and of course sweet, sweet caegars in off-planet bank accounts are all a mere keystroke away.  When you take this move, you gain the **SCRIPT GRUBBIE** move for free. If you already had this move, you become **[Talented]** at **SCRIPT GRUBBIE**. Either way, you also gain access to several new GOOD results for the move.\r\n\r\n> **REBUGGER**: You hijack into a **[Robot]** monster or troll with the Robot **[Template]** and change around the code that works with their logic. **[Robot]** monsters and those with the Robot **[Template]** other than the Cyborg option ally with you for their next turn. Cyborgs instead cannot attack you on the next turn - there’s still a real troll in there saying something’s not quite right. Once this effect wears off, the troll becomes **[Stressed]** for 1 round as they pull themselves together.\r\n\r\n> **FIREWALLED**: Don’t bother looking over here! There’s nothing suspicious at all. You lower an ally on the CIS WATCHLIST by 1 **POINT**. If you’re caught doing this, the ally in question gets raised to 5 **POINTS**.'),
('cyborginator', 'CYBORGINATOR', 'OTHER', 'ADULT', '[Locked: Adult]', 'Adult trolls are already terrifying, with their towering figure, scythe-like claws and bulletproof carapace. You\\\'ve taken it even further, turning YOURSELF into a twenty-foot-tall biomechanical weapon worthy of sipping motor-oil tea with the finest Imperial shockdrone. Fucking plebs hopping from planet to planet using commercial spacecraft? Couldn\\\'t be you. You have rocket boots and don\\\'t need oxygen to breathe anymore. As a **[Free] [One-Off]** action, you overclock your shiny new tech body with energy to outspeed those loser fleshlings. You become **[Quickened]** for 2 rounds, however when the effect ends, you become **[Overwhelmed]** as your circuits fry. This is **[Unblockable]**, and cannot be circumvented by things like the **SOULBOT** option from **MECHANICAL MAN**. You\\\'re not eerie or detached enough to ignore that electrical fire inside you!'),
('dairyOfTheGods', 'DAIRY OF THE GODS', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Passive]', 'Dairy is highly sought after in Indigo culture! It’s the PINNACLE! NOTHING is greater than this. And the dairy you have finally gained access to through your deeds and works are some of the RAREST around. This may seem like an exaggeration, but… going back millenia, only Indigos were trusted with cultivating dairy products, since the bovine creatures that produced it were considered too rare or strong for lower castes to handle. Now, in modern times, it’s a cultural artifact of your caste. Lessons like these have helped you learn that even small things make a difference in the steps of history, and it’s important to treasure even things that seem unimportant. As such, you carry a fuckload of milk and cheese everywhere. You gain access to the following **[Consumable]** items.\r\n\r\n> **LOTS OF BUTTER (1 VP)** This stuff is 200% fat, baby! Look at how GOLDEN it is. My god. Throwing this on the floor when someone is **[Floorbound]** forces the target to roll SWASHBUCKLE to PCHOOOOOOOO to get up, because suddenly the floor is super slippery.\r\n\r\n> **MILK BOTTLE (2 VP)** Yup! It’s a bottle of milk! Drinking it soothes you after stressful situations, **[Healing]** you **1 HP** and giving you **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **STINKY CHEESE (3 VP)** Yeaaaah, this shit is RANCID, but that’s a sign of how good it is. When you eat it, it **[Heals]** you **1 HP**, and makes all other trolls **[Disgusted]** for **2 rounds**.\r\n\r\n> **GODLIKE YOGURT (4 VP)** This is it. This is the PEAK. No dairy product beats this nectar of the gods. When you eat this item, you **[Heal] 2 HP** and become **[Inspired]**. HYAAAAAH!'),
('danceTillYoureDead', 'DANCE TILL YOU’RE DEAD', 'OTHER', 'TRICKSTER', '[Template][Advanced][Eerie][Locked: Trickster]', 'POSITIVITY IS INFECTIOUS!!! I mean, look at that Trickster go! They’re groovin! Don’t you WANT to be happy too??? You take this action to dance, and your opponent can’t help but dance along. They are exposed to the DANCING FEVER **[Affliction]**, and on failing the initial **GREAT** **+IMG** check skip straight to stage 2 of DANCING FEVER. Every round a target is in stage 3 of DANCING FEVER because of this move, they take **1 [Psychic]** damage from the mental toll you’re inflicting upon their mind. VIVA LA DISCO!!!! \r\n\r\n'),
('dangerDancer', 'DANGER DANCER', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Open][Mental][Physical]', 'OH GOD, THE WORLD\'S ON FIRE, ROCKS ARE FALLING, THERE\'S A SNAZZARD NEARBY, AAAAND you\'re actually pretty good at avoiding disasters, all things considered. You\'ve seen so many drone strikes on your subgrub that you can keep your composure, skit through disasters and dance through the danger. Whenever you wanna avoid getting got by a hazard, roll **+GRA**. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: You walk right into the eye of the storm and eat shit. All stages of the Hazard affect you at once.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: AUGH OOOOO!! You try to run away but you sprain your ankle! You take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You don’t really get out of the way, but you assess the situation enough to take a **+2 [Buff]** the next time you make a roll associated with the Hazard.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Not today, Hazard! You avoid being screwed over by the Hazard this round, and don\'t need to roll the associated roll.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Pssh you’ve seen this all before! Maybe in a past life? You get a **GOOD**, but you don\'t need to roll next turn either.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: For you, this is a cataclysm. For me, it is Toilsday. You don\'t need to roll for the Hazard for the rest of its duration, safely sidestepping any issues. Your allies follow your lead, and their rolls against the Hazard are **[Tiered Up]**.'),
('dangerSense', 'DANGER SENSE', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Free]', 'You have an innate sense of danger. Like… like some kind of spider… Whenever you would normally be caught unaware by something, you instead can react to it as if you knew of it ahead of time! **[Hidden]** opponents’ rolls targeting you are **[Inept]**, and your LET\'S STRIFE rolls to ORDER UP are **[Legendary]**. AIN\'T NOBODY GOT QUICKER REFLEXES THAN YOU BITCH!!!!!!!!\r\n'),
('daredevilry', 'DAREDEVILRY', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Flourish][Locked: Marquis]', 'It takes practice to be this impossibly cool. You ride the masts of ships with an open puffy shirt. You swordfight flying monkeys from atop towers, princesses in your arms. If you open up a dictionary and look for Swashbuckler, there\'s a picture of you there. You know, you paid the dictionary company to do that. Yeah… at this point, you\'re kind of a seasoned badass. You get the following new SWASHBUCKLE effects:\r\n\r\n> **TAUNT**: Come on, HIT ME, coward! Or are you that worthless of a fighter?! You gain **2 [Boost]**, and **1 [Weakness]** for a turn. If you are hit during that turn, you gain **2 [Boost]** again.\r\n\r\n> **BRAG**: Ohohoho! Watch THIS! You score a **MAX** roll on a 17+ on your next roll. If you don\'t get a 17+, you get **1 [WHAM]** in frustration. \r\n\r\n> **PRESS**: You quicken your pace of combat, readying a fiersome flurry of attacks! On your next turn, you may use **[Strife]** rolls twice, but the second is **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n> **MONOLOGUE**: You go on a powerful rant about your convictions, sealing in exactly how you feel about a topic. You **[Heighten]** any one Emotion you have, or remove it. This has the **[Mental]** tag, not the **[Physical]** one.'),
('darkMagicks', 'DARK MAGICKS', 'OTHER', 'CTHONOMANCER', '[Template][Passive][Eerie][Magic][Unlock: Cthonomancer]', 'The power you wield is unnatural, dark and powerful in equally unearthly amounts. You may not possess the limitless power of What Mustn\'t Be Seen that the chosen Grimdarks wield, but you are not unarmed. Your talents are seen as disgusting and cowardly by the devout, dangerous and destabilizing by the powers that be and a damn good deal by your fellow magickians. You’re more than just edge! Watch! When you gain **[Boost]** you gain 1 less to a minimum of 1, instead reducing your next **[Magic]** move’s **MAX** threshold for each **[Boost]** you lose, resetting upon attaining a **MAX** as Those Above tilt destiny in your favor. For example, if you lose **2 [Boost]** in this way, you will achieve a **MAX** on an 7,7 rather than 8,8. Additionally, if you have or later gain the CUSTODIAN COMPANION move, your lusus gains the Eldritch trait for free, and should it already have had it then give it another trait now. It will serve excellently as a focus for your magicks! Finally, you cannot have both this move and the ASTROSORCERY move from the ASTROSORCERER Template. Those idiotic stargazers can wallow in their weakness!'),
('dashboardClogger', 'DASHBOARD CLOGGER', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Lengthy][One-Off][Manipulate][Locked: Fanyatic]', 'Do you love the colour of the sky? Let\'s get real: you talk a LOT. Like, a LOOOOOT. And sometimes, you go on very, very, VERY long rants. So long and passionate are these rants that it kind of forces everyone to just stare at you in bewilderment as you talk people\'s ears off. When you wanna clog the airwaves with a very long ramble, roll **+RAS**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Everyone ignores you, and you just stand there, **[Slowed]** for **3 rounds** as you just kinda… talk… \r\n\r\n**BAD**: You move on pretty quick, but you still spend your entire turn doing this. Sucks.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You talk for an action, realize it\'s going nowhere, and don\'t spend a second action doing it.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You take up everyone\'s time! **2 rounds** pass.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You\'ve REALLY got their dashboards clogged now! **4 rounds** pass.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Did… did everyone stand here and let you start the rant over again? Several times? **8 rounds** pass, and everyone\'s **[One-Off]** moves reset.'),
('ddosificate', 'DDOSIFICATE', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Psionic][Strife][Locked: Network]', 'You\'ve gotten to the point where you can link other trolls into the network. This is abjectly horrifying and painful. How would YOU like to be forced to read the entire Wickedpedia for cheese-smelting in 1.37 seconds?! When you want to overwhelm a target\'s brain, roll **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: AAAEEIOOUUGGH— NO, NO GOD, YOU DIDN\'T WANT TO SEE THAT! OHHHHH GOD, NO NO NO, NOOOO— NO, THAT\'S HORRIBLE! AAAAAARGH! FUCK! NOOOOOO! FLUTTERSHY?! NO, NO NO, GOD— JESUS, FUCK! OH, NO! YOU DIDN\'T WANT THIS! FUCK! WHO— WHY! NOOOO! FUCK! You see something horrible before you can shove it onto them, and experience **[Sensory Overload]**.  \r\n\r\n**BAD**: Hmmmm. No, you didn\'t like how suggestively posed that squeakbeast mascot was. That made your brain go fizzy. You find nothing, and become slightly **[Overwhelmed]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: A frown crosses the target\'s face. They felt that. The target takes **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Oneofthebasicpiecesoffurniture,achairisatypeofseat. Whoa! Talk about an intrusive thought! The target takes **1 [Psychic]** **[Electric]** damage.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: TheGreaterMuckweevilhasablackbodywithpaleyellow/whitescaleswhichareattheirmostdenseonthepronotum,headandontheelytralintervals.Thesewhitescalesformstripesontheabdomen.Itsbodyrangesinlengthfrom20.5–28mm.ThisspeciesissympatricwithLyperobiusfallax,butcanbedistinguishedbyitslargersize.LikeotherGulchscourgeNativeWeevils,thisweevilisflightless.Itslarvaehaveacreamy-whitebodywithadarkred-blackhead. The target takes **2 [Psychic]** **[Electric]** damage, or takes **1 [Psychic]** **[Electric]** damage and becomes **[Overwhelmed]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: THEY ABSORB EVERYTHING. The target is briefly shunted directly into the Cloudmind, and feels every individual thought and feeling of the entire group all at once. Also, they download all of Wickedpedia into their brain. The target either takes **3 [Psychic]** **[Electric]** damage, or takes 2 and experiences **[Sensory Overload]** for **2 turns**, and then becomes **[Overwhelmed]**.'),
('deadOrAlive', 'DEAD OR ALIVE', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Passive][Unlock: Legislacerator]', 'Sometimes, someone really wants another person dead. Maybe they broke the law. Maybe they just don\'t like them. Doesn\'t matter to you; if you get paid to do it, you\'re sure you\'ll find something they\'re guilty of. Everyone\'s guilty of something. As a Legislacerator, you walk the line between detective and bounty hunter. You are **[Talented]** at **+GRT**. You may spend an action to HUNT DOWN an opponent. The HUNTED target can\'t roll to ABSCOND, and you get **MAX** **[Strife]** rolls on a 19+. If someone paid you to take out the twerp, you instead get **MAX** **[Strife]** rolls on an 18+. Your damage against your HUNTED Target is **[Unblockable]**, and your **[Analyze]** rolls against them are always **[Tiered Up]**. In return for all the above, you cannot roll to **[Strife]** any targets but your HUNTED target.'),
('dealsWarlock', 'DEALS WARLOCK', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Meowchant]', 'Come in, come in! Would you like to make a deal? You have only the finest, RAREST wares to purchase, you know! Look over here; it\'s a glass bauble that holds your fondest memory. And here! A mirror that shows you a likeness of your dead moirail\'s screaming face, how unusual! Yes, suffice to say… there\'s no other shop quite like yours! You gain access to HERO MODE through your AWESOME APPETITE. You are known throughout the lands for your INCREDIBLE variety of rare wares, and it\'s really starting to pay off! You have the **Rich** Wealth, and have **16 VP** instead of 8. Your famous luck is the stuff of legends, and sometimes the way you move seems to defy logic; all **[Strife]** rolls against you have a **-2 [Nerf]**. You hop into a giant vase, it\'s smashed, you\'re not there, you emerge from the cabinet. How did you do that?!'),
('deathOfTheAuthor', 'DEATH OF THE AUTHOR', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Ultra][Downtime][Magic][Psionic][Locked: Narrator]', '...is the birth of the reader. There comes a point where every story gets away from those who originally wrote it. At what point does the original intent of the author matter? Does it matter at all? Can different interpretations of stories spawn new realities? Would you like meat... or candy? You understand that nobody\'s take on a narrative is more correct than anyone else\'s. Furthermore, narrative isn\'t a straight line— it\'s more like infinite roots on a plant, sprawling in countless directions of interpretation. The way you understand the narrative is massively different to the way others do, and there\'s no such thing as truth when it comes to a story. You gain access to HERO MODE through your RESPLENDENT RASCALITY. Furthermore, as a **[Downtime]** Activity, you may create self contained branches of narrative free from consequence. These NON-CANON encounters diverge from our timeline and reality much as derivative fiction does from the source it\'s based on. At the end of the encounter, all events that took place in the NON-CANON encounter are undone, save for certain participants\' memory of the event (of your choosing) who have a dreamlike recollection of the event. A great way to figure out how a particular course of action would play out! You can also RETCON events that have affected people, such as a character death or a terrible mistake with the request of at least five other people directly affected by the event. Obviously, this can\'t affect the entire narrative, so no wishing the Hemospectrum didn\'t exist!'),
('debonairDress', 'DEBONAIR DRESS', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Passive][Locked: Marquis]', 'What\'s the point of having all this money if you don\'t spend it on looking INCREDIBLE? You gain access to the FANTASTIC FLAIR Fashion Item, which can be either a Head Item or an Accessory Item. Whether it\'s a thief\'s mask, a feather in your cap or a gorgeous set of rings, it really completes the look for you, and gives you +1 HUB, -1 APP. You can combine it with other items to make the following Collections… \r\n\r\n> **GALA-GOER**: (FANTASTIC FLAIR, FANCYASS FIT, SILKEN GLOVES, HEAVY MAKEUP) **[+2 HUB, +2 PLC, -2 RAS, -2 APP]** Oh, yes yes yes, you\'re so dainty and law abiding, you\'re the beauty of the ball! Your FLIRT Wordplay Rolls are **[Tiered Up]**, and if you have access to HERO MODE, you use PERFECT PULCHRITUDE, not HARDCORE HUBRIS.\r\n\r\n> **AVAST!**: (FANTASTIC FLAIR, BOOTIFUL BOOTS, WASTEFUL COAT, STUPID HAT) **[+2 HUB, +2 RAS, -2 PLC, -1 APP, -1 PSP]** Yo-ho-ho, bitches! Not even seadwellers are safe from you! While aboard a VEHICLE with the WATER tag, you get a +2 to all **[Strife]** and **[Chicanery]** rolls. \r\n\r\n> **LUPINIC LOOK**: (FANTASTIC FLAIR, SILKEN GLOVES, TRAILING COAT, SNEAKY SNEAKERS) **[+2 HUB, +2 GRA, -2 APP, -2 GRT]** Get in, get out, and SNAG! When you are **[Hidden]**, your rolls to YOINK are **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n\r\n> **ROMANTIC HERO**: (FANTASTIC FLAIR, BASIC BUTTON-UP, BOOTIFUL BOOTS, RAPIERKIND Strife Specibus) **[+2 HUB, +2 GRT, -2 APP, -2 PSP]** Clink, clink clink, SWISH! With your shirt unbuttoned a little too low and an iconic swashbuckling weapon in hand, you are ready to swordfight anyone to the death! Opponents have a **-2 [Nerf]** on **[Physical]** **[Strife]** rolls against you as you clink and clank swords with them.'),
('decentWages', 'DECENT WAGES', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Passive][Locked: Worker]', 'Because you aren\'t entirely reliant on allowances, you don\'t struggle… QUITE as much as other Rusts. You live moderately comfortably, even! Your Wealth Level increases to **Decent**. Additionally, your position as a professional (even in the least impressive way) gives you access to the occasional sweet discount. You are always **[Talented]** at MONEYMAKERY and when you roll a **GOOD** or up on it, you earn **1 extra LUX**.'),
('deeperStudies', 'DEEPER STUDIES', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Folklorist]', 'With time and effort, you can uncover even greater lore than you thought possible! Select an upgraded effect to the choice you made with YARNCHASER.\r\n\r\n> **Faeries & Magic**: Circles of power, leylines, all that stuff. Just stand in juuuuust the right spot, and you\'ve got a wellspring of power at your feet! As a **[Lengthy]** action, you can consecrate a spot that **[Tiers Up]** ALL magic in the area, even to a **MAX**. This includes enemies and monsters, so watch out! \r\n\r\n> **Beasts & Creatures**: Hmmmm… you know all about these things! When you roll PROBLEM SLEUTHING against a monster, lusus, or similar, your roll uses **+PLC**, and is **[Tiered Up]**, even to a **MAX**.\r\n\r\n> **Beliefs & Religions**: You immerse yourself in the practices of others, figuring out where their magic comes from. You may take a single **[Magic]** move from a tree or template linked to religion; practitioners can tell that your magic is a replicate and generally aren\'t too bothered, since it\'s clearly inferior. You use **+PLC** to roll.\r\n\r\n> **The True Meaning of the Holidays in General**: You gotta stock up on decorations! During in-world holidays and festivals, all items cost **1 VP** and **1 LUX** less than normal, but they become holiday-themed. You can also purchase exclusive holiday items after the holiday ends, if your Clouder adds any to the event.\r\n\r\n> **Foodways & Cuisine**: ADVAAAAAANCED COOKERY! You gain the following recipes you can make with your TAPAS.\r\n\r\n> Remove **[Poisoned]** or **[Clumsy]**.\r\n> Half your current **[Drag]**.\r\n> Remove an **[Emotion]**.\r\n> Ignore an **[Inept]** or **[Tier Down]** effect for a turn.\r\n\r\n> **Proverbs & Language**: Ah, hear your words indeed! Your **[Manipulate]** rolls are never **[Inept]**, **[Nerfed]** or **[Tiered Down]**.\r\n\r\n> **Music & Dance**: You know how to give allies some inspiration, bardic style! You can spend an action to give all allies in an encounter **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **Art & Literature**: You\'ve got a real eye for aesthetics, written or visual, and have learned to appreciate every small thing. Whenever you gain **[Boost]**, you gain +1 extra.'),
('defendescort', 'DEFENDESCORT', 'OLIVE', 'ADULT', '[Olive][Locked: Adult]', 'While any chump can take a bullet for someone, it takes a troll of high caliber to make it a career. Defendescorts are employed by important highbloods to protect them from other important highbloods with their own Defendescorts. It\\\'s really a problem that creates itself. Being a good defendescort is tough; you have to keep your cool, be hardy enough to take a good wallop, and most of all? Be high enough on the hemospectrum where someone hiring you wouldn\\\'t have to worry about you killing them in their sleep. To take the heat off someone else, as a **[Reaction]** to someone taking damage, you may give the target +1 **[Somatic] [Resistance]** for 3 turns. You can use this on yourself if you’re the one who took damage. When it ends, you take 3 **[Drag]** as it’s emotionally taxing to be everyone’s bullet sponge! This effect is **[Recharge: 4]**.'),
('degreesOfVriskocity', 'DEGREES OF VRISKOCITY', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Passive]', 'After everything you’ve been through, maybe you’ve learned to cope. Maybe you… kind of have learned to cope. Maybe you super fucking have not, but you’re still learning. If only there was some metric to figure out how far along your coping journey you’ve come? Turns out, you can! This handy scale presents how deeply you’ve internalized the lessons you’ve learned, or how much progress you still have to go. You can change your option as your character develops, but you usually can’t change it again for at least a month. \r\n\r\n**NOT VRISKA**: Yeah… you’re done using violence to hide your sadness, if you ever did in the first place. You’ve got things to keep you grounded. You’re… **GOOD**, even, you know? At least, you’re trying. Whenever you gain a Negative **[Emotion]**, it wears off after three turns.\r\n\r\n**PROBABLY VRISKA**: Okay, you’ve learned, but your attitude definitely still leans to the spiderbitchy. But ultimately, your flaws outweigh your ego, which you are able to keep in check. Do you have bad habits that horrifically affect those around you? Maybe. Who doesn\'t! But you’re making an effort. Whenever someone experiences a Negative **[Emotion]** around you (other than ones you caused), you gain **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**VRISKA**: Whoof. Um. Alright, so… you’re definitely still kind of fucked up. You might be making an effort to be better, you might actively not be, but your past actions still tie you down, and you haven’t earned back the trust of those around you enough to… yeah. You’ve got a long way to go. Maybe stop pushing people off cliffs and blaming your bad upbringing. Or just continue being an ass, I\'m not your custodian. Your warped emotional range means whenever you would take a Negative **[Emotion]**, you may select a different Negative or Neutral **[Emotion]** of an equal **[Heightened]** level.'),
('demonDearest', 'DEMON DEAREST', 'OTHER', 'CTHONOMANCER', '[Template][Basic][Recharge: 3][Flourish][Magic][Locked: Cthonomancer]', 'It is not enough to merely profess an intent to become powerful, you must study! Learn! Sacrifice! Both your own time and the souls of other people! But for now you ought to focus on the studying part. How do Dark Magickians study if it’s nearly impossible to make or find study materials? The souls of the damned, of course! When you need to channel the spirits to do your homework for you, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: YOUR FUCKING LEG!! The power of the dark side in the form of angry ghosts rips one of your limbs away as punishment for messing with the natural order of things. You take **2 damage** and become **[Bloodied]**, potentially losing an actual limb honest to the Messiahs.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: ARGH! You are overwhelmed by evil magic still known as angry ghosts beating your ass. You become **[Bloodied]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You draw a big fucking magic circle on the ground, and then realize you didn’t need to fucking do that.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: IA! IA! FLUTHULU FT’GHAN! You whisk out and pull spirits into you, gaining one of the following effects…\r\n\r\n> **RESTLESS RUSTS**: There is no stopping now. Remove a Status Condition from yourself.\r\n> **GAMING GOLDS**: So that’s how you do that speedrunning strat! You are **[Quickened]** next turn.\r\n> **OBLIVIOUS OLIVES**: You have never been so good at being irrelevant. You gain **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You reach further into the aether, plucking out rarer spirits for your needs. You gain one of the following **GREAT** effects.\r\n\r\n> **TERRIFYING TEALS**: Appropriate their property is.. Civil forfeiture, that’s the word! You gain a **[Hold]** you can use for **[Free]** as a **[Reaction]** to steal the next positive effect a target would gain, such as **[Boost]** or **[Heal]**ing. You may only possess one of these at a time.\r\n> **PAINED PURPLES**: There’s something ironic about using dead clowns like this, isn’t there? You become immune to Emotions for **two turns**, unable to be affected by any inflicted.\r\n> **LESSER LESSONS**: You get a **GOOD** result, and your opponent becomes **[Scared]**!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: They say that some castes don’t produce ghosts, not even the ambient spectres that linger before passing. They just don’t know where to look. You gain one of the following **MAX** effects.\r\n\r\n> **VALOROUS VIOLETS**: It’s not like these pompous royals did much in life anyways, you might as well put them to work now! Your next **[Strife]** roll is **[Talented]** and **[Free]**.\r\n> **GREATER LESSONS**: You get a **GREAT** result or two **GOOD** results, and your opponent becomes **[Terrified]**!'),
('derisiveWords', 'DERISIVE WORDS', 'MIND', 'MIND', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Mind]', 'Whether you mean it or not, you can be a little sharp-tongued at times. Your focus on logic over emotions means that the things you say can be pretty hurtful— maybe even borderline cruel— because you don’t put thought into how your words could hurt someone on a personal level. It’s just the truth, in your eyes. Whenever you do **[Verbal]** damage, you gain **1 [Boost]**. You ignore any **[Resistances]** trolls might have that would lower this.'),
('destinedForGreatness', 'DESTINED FOR GREATNESS', 'LIGHT', 'LIGHT', '[Aspect][Ultra][Locked: Light]', 'You’ve done the studying, and you’ve used your luck— now fate has rewarded you for it. You didn’t get this far just by being brash or rude, though; you’ve learned that with great power comes— get this, guys— great responsibility. Your role isn’t to outshine everyone in the world. Your role is to help everyone else reach their destiny too, whether it’s good or bad. Any time you make a **[Talented]** roll, you can keep one extra die result, losing the benefit of the **[Talent]** for that roll, and save it to replace a number on any roll anyone in the encounter makes as a **[Free]** **[Reaction]**. You may save 3 dice results at a time, but may only use one per turn. A natural **MIN** or **MAX** cannot be avoided with this, as lady luck has shown her hand already.'),
('didNothingWrong', 'DID NOTHING WRONG', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Open][One-Off][Manipulation]', 'Jade culture teaches you to stick up for your friends, no matter what. Hey, no, you\'ve got it all wrong! It\'s not like you think- they just grew up in a harsh world with a toxic lusus, it\'s not her fault she broke that guy\'s legs, also it wasn\'t her, it was that rust who did it, call the drones on them instead. You can use this move on yourself. When you want to deflect blame, roll **+RAS**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: BITCH YES THEY DID DO SOMETHING WRONG, AND SO DID YOU! You and the ally you were trying to protect gain **1 [Weakness]** to all damage for three turns.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Your interfering just annoys the target. The next time they attack that ally, they do **+1 [Unblockable]** damage.\r\n\r\n**OK**: The target squints at who you\'re defending, and then continues wailing on them. They still take **1 [Drag]** though.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Your words redirect the anger of an enemy… somewhere else! Your targets **[Strife]** and **[Chicanery]** rolls against your ally are **[Inept]** until they do something that would upset the target, such as a **[Strife]** or **[Chicanery]** roll. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Not only do you defend your ally with the effects of a **GOOD**… you redirect the fury onto someone else! If they accept this new target, they become **[Hopeful]**, and may even join your side in a TEAM STRIFE. They must have genuinely intended harm to your ally to gain this effect. If your ally violates the terms of a **GOOD** against them, they lose this condition and become **[Enraged]** at both of you. Dude! \r\n\r\n**MAX**: FUUUUUCK. They really bought it, huh? Your target cannot attack you or your ally for the duration of the encounter, unless you violate the terms of a **GOOD** to them. They become **[Inspired]** if they attack the target you pointed out on a **GREAT**, and so does your ally!'),
('digitalNative', 'DIGITAL NATIVE', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Golds are just better at tech! That\'s just how it is! Mostly because from birth they\'re given tasks and jobs related to computers, so, y\'know, it be like that. Your **[Tech]** rolls are all **[Talented]**, and can\'t be made **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]** or **[Nerfed]**. If you are a Network Gold, this extends to your **[Psionics]** in general.'),
('dimensionhopper', 'DIMENSIONHOPPER', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Ultra][One-Off][Magic][Psionic][Locked: AU]', 'Your powers have grown to such levels that you can not only create a miniature setting that brings the one you\'ve imagined to real life, but also bring others into your own pocket AU too! You gain access to HERO MODE through the stat you became **[Talented]** in through ALTERNATE UNIVERSE. Additionally, you can expand the rift into your world from inside you to all around you as an action, plunging all other trolls into your world. Buildings might change appearance, people might turn into ponies… the multiverse is in your hand! While in your world, your permanent **[Emotion]** is heightened. Additionally, you gain the following benefits. \r\n\r\n> **CRACK (+RAS)**: Your world barely makes any sense! All **[Mental]** rolls have a **[Recharge: 3]** attached as it becomes hard to think; any emotions targets have or receive immediately become **[Confused]** instead.\r\n\r\n> **SLICE OF LIFE (+PLC)**: In your world, everyone gets along! Nobody can roll **[Strife]** moves aside from **[Verbal]** ones as the encounter devolves into situation comedy. \r\n\r\n> **MUSICAL (+GRA)**: Aw, shit, MUSIC NUMBER! For the rest of the encounter, all trolls must make one **+PLC** roll a turn and rhyme what they\'re saying, or make a **+GRA** roll as they dance around. Any turn they don\'t, they take **1 [Drag]**. FRAYMOTIF uses **+GRA** here.\r\n\r\n> **GRITTY (+APP)**: It\'s not safe here! You bring everyone to the apocalypse; choose either an ANGRY MOB Hazard, a STAMPEDE Hazard or the RADIATION POISONING Affliction. It happens! GRIEF rolls use **+APP** here.\r\n\r\n> **FERAL (+GRT)**: GURAAAAWR! Everyone\'s an animal or monster in your world! All trolls **[Physical]** rolls are **[Tiered Up]**, but **[Mental]** rolls are **[Tiered Down]**.\r\n\r\n> **FANTASY (+HUB)**: ADVENTURE AWAITS, TRAVELLERS! All trolls receive **1 [Resistance]** to **[Somatic]** damage and are **[Talented]** at **[Strife]** OR have access to the Astrosorcerer **[Entry]** move using **+HUB** to roll as everyone becomes swashbucklers and wizards.\r\n\r\n> **HISTORICAL (+PSP)**: Interesting technology! All items take an extra action to activate as they\'re retrofitted to fit the time period you\'re from. You can ignore this effect by rushing the item, but it takes **1 damage** in the process. You can choose to halt this effect when needed.\r\n\r\n> **FANDOM (+IMG)**: FANDOM IS FOREEEVEEEEER! You bring everyone into the world of your own fandom. While here, they immediately join in and take on roles of characters from your fandom, assigning themselves roles from the ARCHETYPIST Protagonist Lime move.'),
('diplomaster', 'DIPLOMASTER', 'JADE', 'ADULT', '[Jade][Passive][Locked: Adult]', 'Not all life has recognized the all-encompassing glory of Trollic society. That\\\'s where you come in! Whether as a missionary of the Grandmother Grub or a wandering herald of the Empire, it is YOUR job to bring the good news (we\\\'re going to kill you if you don\\\'t bow to us) to other planets. Your **[Manipulate]** rolls against sapient aliens are **[Tiered Up]**, as are your **PROBLEM SLEUTHING** rolls against sapient aliens. You can convince these aliens to join crews for half the price of a regular crewmate; when one of these aliens dies, you are **[Quickened]** for a round as you feel a rush of emotions.'),
('directAction', 'DIRECT ACTION', 'FUCHSIA', 'FUCHSIA', '[Fuchsia][Advanced][Passive]', 'You don’t have time for this run-around bullshit! Well, you do, but you still don’t want to have to put up with it- and that’s valid! You can only be affected by a direct, **[Physical]** or **[Psionic]** **[Strife]**; non-**[Strife]** moves such as WORDPLAY cannot damage you, and you are immune to **[Verbal]** damage as a whole.'),
('discerningEye', 'DISCERNING EYE', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Teals are told from the moment that they hatch to keep their eyes peeled. Information is your greatest tool, and if you can\'t use it, you\'re nothing! So keep your eyes peeled, you do. You gain access to the following **GOOD** PROBLEM SLEUTHING options.\r\n\r\n> **POLYGRAPH GAZE**: You stare at someone, figuring out if they\'re up to something. Ask them OOC if they feel guilty or not. If they do, you gain **1 [WHAM]**. If they don\'t, your next PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll is **[Tiered Up]**. WORDPLAY rolls to LIE to you are **[Tiered Down]** for a turn.\r\n\r\n> **SAFETY PRECAUTIONS**: Hah! You know exactly what to do in a situation like this. Your rolls against a **[Hazard]** are **[Tiered Up]** for **2 turns**. \r\n\r\n> **IDENTIFY CHUMP**: Sometimes, you need to analyze everyone around you to figure out who\'s the easiest stooge to mess with. In a TEAM STRIFE, randomly select an opponent. You figure out their weak points, and how to one up them. You can roll against them even if they aren\'t in a position which would normally allow you to, and your roll is **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n\r\n> **IS THIS DUDE FOR REAL**: You\'ve gotten used to putting up with a lot of dipshittery by now, but… this really takes the cake. OR DOES IT? You figure out if a target is really that stupid, or just fucking around. If they\'re fucking around, you gain **1 [WHAM]**. If they\'re really that stupid, you gain **2 [Boost]**.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('disseminateEmotions', 'DISSEMINATE EMOTIONS', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Passive][Psionic][Locked: Network]', 'Your inherent connection to all information known to all other Network Golds is an exhausting strain. It\'s also mad useful. With a quick tilt of the head, you can say PROBLEMS BEGONE in an instant! You are immune to effects that automatically give you a negative **[Emotion]**. This is because you can simply offload your mental baggage into the Cloudmind, disseminating overwhelming dread into just mild spikes of stress among hundreds of other trolls. Rolls that give you emotions are **[Inept]**, even if they have a move that would otherwise prevent it from being **[Inept]**. **[Strife]** rolls that would give you an emotion on a **GREAT** can only do the extra damage option.'),
('distant', 'DISTANT', 'SPACE', 'SPACE', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Space]', 'It can be hard to reach you sometimes. Alternia to Spacebound? Hello? You gain **1 [Resistance]** against all **[Verbal]** damage as people’s words don’t really hit you. You might even agree with them, to an extent...'),
('divineRightOfFish', 'DIVINE RIGHT OF FISH', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Passive][Unlock: Royal]', 'All Violetbloods are nobility. Of course, that\'s true. But YOU do not squander the land granted to you by the empire, instead crafting your own perfect kingdom. One day, you\'ll rule planets, so this is a good start! You are **[Talented]** at **+APP**. You own a FIEFDOM, a swathe of land that is yours for the developing. Name your FIEFDOM, probably some bullshit like THE CHURNING DEPTHS or THE GRAVEL WASTES, and a title for yourself like ECTODUKE or MISERYPRINCE. You start play with **5 LUX**, which you can only use on Hivecrafting upgrades. These upgrades can either be in the form of upgrades to your hive, or entirely new buildings for your FIEFDOM (That is no mere FOODBLOCK! That\'s a 5 Shell RESTAURANT!). Track how much **LUX** you spend on your FIEFDOM; you gain the following abilities as your FIEFDOM expands.\r\n\r\n> **0 LUX**: Spend your fucking **LUX**.\r\n\r\n> **5 LUX**: Alright, you\'ve got the start of a kingdom going on here. But now, you need to figure out what kind! Select an option; you gain the **[Entry]** move for that tree; you are **[Talented]** only at moves from this tree, rather than the entire stat it would give **[Talent]** in.\r\n\r\n> **ARISTOCRACY**: (Marquis Cerulean) Keeping it traditional, babes!\r\n> **PLUTOCRACY**: (Gambligant Cerulean) Money makes THIS nation go round!\r\n> **STRATOCRACY**: (Paladin Indigo) Raise a sword, and CONQUER!\r\n> **TECHNOCRACY**: (Inventor Indigo) The future is TODAY in this fiefdom!\r\n> **MAGOCRACY**: (Esotericist Purple; only 1 option) Yeah, this is basically an evil wizard kingdom.\r\n> **WHIMSICRACY**: (Circusfolk Purple, Magician only) A magical, whimsical land that\'s yours to rule!\r\n\r\n> **20 LUX**: Looking good! You gain access to a **[Basic]** move from your -CRACY tree!\r\n\r\n> **50 LUX**: Now THIS is a kingdom! You gain access to an **[Advanced]** move from your -CRACY tree!\r\n\r\n> **100 LUX**: You\'ve created an absolutely MONSTROUS FIEFDOM, worthy of the Heiress herself! You gain one final move, **[Basic]**, **[Advanced]**, or **[Ultra]**, from your -CRACY tree. If you take the **[Ultra]**, you don\'t gain any HERO MODE benefits, but it does not take up an **[Ultra]** slot. Sexy!'),
('divineWards', 'DIVINE WARDS', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Passive][Magic][Locked: Honkpostle]', 'In your studies of your own magic, you have come across many other types of magic. Other faiths with their false idols, profane spellcasters and monstrous entities. You will not allow yourself to fall to them. **[Magic]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**.'),
('diyDynamo', 'DIY DYNAMO', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'Nobody else is gonna fix your leaky roof, right? You\'ve gotten used to fixing up your hive and the ramshackle state it often finds itself in; as such, HIVECRAFTING UPGRADES cost **1 LUX** less than normal (min. 1).'),
('doNotSteal', 'DO NOT STEAL', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][One-Off][Magic][Locked: Mary Sue]', 'Memetics. When Monkey sees, Monkey does. Your ideas aren\'t exceptionally original, but that\'s because you\'re copying from the awesome things you see and mirror them in yourself. You gain any one rollable move so long as it\'s **[Advanced]** or **[Basic]**.'),
('doomGloom', 'DOOM & GLOOM', 'DOOM', 'DOOM', '[Aspect][Passive][Unlock: Doom]', 'Alternia isn\'t a kind place. Or even a good place. Just walking out your front door means opening yourself up to death, and hurt, and all the cruelty of life under a totalitarian regime. No one knows this better than the Doombound. You become immune to the **[Dread]**, **[Despair]** and **[Crying]** conditions because... You know! You are aware of the sadness of the world! That’s just Tuesday for you, stop beating a dead hoofbeast! Any time someone would give you these effects, they gain the **[Dread]** condition as they realize how deep you already are in the doomzone. You also become immune to **[Inspired]**, however.'),
('doomsday', 'DOOMSDAY', 'OTHER', 'PRINCE', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][One-off][Magic][Locked: Prince]', 'You cut things down, you destroy, and you kill. That\'s your job, because sometimes it just needs to be done. Sometimes people will hate you for it, but the more you destroy, the more you realize that sometimes you\'re the only one who can do it without destroying your own psyche over it. Who\'s gonna kill the real bad guy in the end, the one that\'s too dangerous to live? Your friends? No. You’re not putting them through that. At the start of an encounter, if you’ve determined your enemies are too dangerous to be kept standing, you may become an **AWOKEN PRINCE** as a **[Free]** action. Once you have become **AWOKEN**, you enshrine the encounter in a concentrated veil of destruction, ensuring someone WILL fall here. Roll a 1d4+2 to determine what round this move will take effect. At the end of that round, whoever is lower HP at that time will immediately fall **[Unconscious]** if they have not already. At the start of that same round, you all gain 3 **[Boost]** and 1 **[WHAM]** because you can feel the end approaching you both. This move can affect several enemies, but doesn’t affect your allies, as you’ve found a way to make your destructive powers more targeted.'),
('doubleBattle', 'DOUBLE BATTLE', 'OTHER', 'FIDUSSPAWNER', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Fiduspawner]', 'Training with your new Fiduspawn companion has taught you that nothing is more important than teamwork… And spamming the attack button! If your fiduspawn has an ability that would only affect you, such as **[Flying]** or **[Resistance]**, you can instead use an action to give that ability to an ally! Any time you do this, or you use any of the other abilities on an opponent during a team strife, you gain **1 [Boost]**! Additionally, you can send out up to two Fiduspawn allies to battle for you in a GROUP STRIFE, though their rolls are **[Inept]** if you aren’t on STANDBY. If you do this, they get full turns, as if they were individual NPCs! Teamwork makes the dreamwork, babeyyy, now time to spam Earthquake.'),
('downWithTheClownChurch', 'DOWN WITH THE CLOWN CHURCH', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Passive]', 'Your caste is one governed entirely not by the Empire, not by seadwellers… but the CLOWN CHURCH. Run by the mysterious GRAND HIGHBLOOD who rules from the depths of space, ALL Purplebloods are required to wear makeup or face becoming targets for enraged Juggalo. Of course… this all-seeing, all-controlling church isn’t really a universally loved one. Select an option from the list below to choose your relationship with the Mirthful Messiahs and the Juggaloic faith. \r\n\r\n> **ORTHODOX FAITHFUL**: DUDE YOU FUCKING. YOU FUCKING LOVE THE CHURCH. YOU LOVE KILLING PEOPLE AND SMEARING RAINBOWS ON THE CHURCH WALLS. SOPOR IS YOUR FAVOURITE. HONK HONK HONK. You see no problem in how the Church operates whatsoever, and hold yourself closely to your ideals. Whenever you witness someone become **[Bloodied]**, you get **1 [Boost]**. BLOOD FOR THE BLOOD GODS!\r\n\r\n> **CHURCH ENJOYER**: Yeah… you like the Clown Church well enough! It doesn’t, like, define you by any means, but you still follow its beliefs, and you still don’t want people breaking tradition, you know? You’re just not the type to go on a divinely inspired killing spree, you simply enjoy the murderhymns and make time to go to slaughtermass when you have some free time. Your LET’S STRIFE rolls to ORDER UP are **[Talented]** (**[Legendary]** if they already would be) as you feel a flip switch inside you as soon as combat breaks out, willing you from clowny citizen to faithful juggalo, whoop whoop!\r\n\r\n> **SCHISMATIC SADCLOWN**: You… you really don’t enjoy the Church. Like, at all. Maybe you think its obsession with ultraviolence is flawed and broken, and that there’s no way such an institution should be allowed to terrorize the meek. Maybe you’re viscerally queasy around gore, and have to go to mandatory church meetups with a blindfold and nose plugs! Either way, you don’t vibe with the church, even though you’re still forced to go. Whenever you witness a **[Cullbait]** troll reveal themselves, you gain the **[Hopeful]** condition; they trust you enough for you to see this, or you know you can help them hide from the other clowns you know.'),
('draconicSpiritsync', 'DRACONIC SPIRITSYNC', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Ultra][Passive][Buildup: 3][Magic][Locked: Draquestrian]', 'The power of friendship overwhelms you! You and your Snazzard share the same soul now. You gain access to HERO MODE through your HARDCORE HUBRIS. Additionally, when you and your Snazzard\'s hearts beat as one, something incredible happens; the dragon is absorbed into you. After accomplishing **[Buildup: 3]**, your Snazzard demanifests and enters your soul, and you gain a few draconic features, like wings, claws, a tail and scales. You gain access to all of the abilities of an actual SNAZZARD from Chapter 17b, such as POWERFUL WINGS, DRAGON\'S BREATH, as well as your own Snazzard\'s moves. Your HP remains the same, but you otherwise use the highest stat between you and your Snazzard for any one stat in this form. You have all your Snazzard\'s **[Talents]**, including HERO MODE through INCREDIBLE IMAGINATION, and all of your Snazzard\'s moves. You still have two instances of **[Recharge]**, **[One-Offs]** and **[Buildup]**, and can mitigate incoming physical or emotional effects through BODYBLOCK in exchange for **2 [Drag]**.'),
('dragonWhisperer', 'DRAGON WHISPERER', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Draquestrian]', 'Ssssh. No, no. It\'s okay. I can fyifking speak to dragons. Your time working alongside your Snazzard means that you have an empathic bond with the reptilian. Lusii that are reptiles not immune to **[Manipulate]** moves from you, and you can understand their basic wants and desires. They will not attack you or your allies if you raise a hand, go ssssh sh sh and gently put a hand on their snout. This doesn\'t cost an action, you just kinda do it automatically. You could feasibly use WORDPLAY to turn a reptile on your enemies, making it an ally if needed… and wouldn\'t you know it, your Snazzard can roll WORDPLAY on reptiles with **+HUB**!'),
('dreamchasingDrifter', 'DREAM-CHASING DRIFTER', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Passive][Unlock: Vagabond]', 'A mysterious stranger (you) pushes through the doors into the smokey room. Everyone goes quiet as you silently make your way to your seat. Hey, some guy says, hey, you got a lot of nerve showing up here. Yeah, you say, you\'ve got a lot of nerve in general, you figure. Combat ensues, maybe! This is just a brief insight into your life. Whether that smokey room be a saloon in a rural town or a night club in a city is irrelevant. Maybe you\'re an outlaw. Maybe you\'re a rebel. Maybe you\'re a rebel outlaw. The point is that you\'re a charming rogue that gets up to all sorts of dubious activities. You are **[Talented]** at **+RAS**. You always carry a trusty firearm with you wherever you go. You immediately gain a RANGEDKIND ABSTRATA UPGRADE that can have one other UPGRADE attached. Additionally, you can add the following modifications to your trusty firearm. You can swap your modification as a **[Downtime]** action.\r\n\r\n> **GIMMICKKIND**: Wow, this weapon does all sorts of funky shit. Most of its functions seem better fit for a party than a fight, but if you’re clever, you could definitely trip somebody up with it. On a **GREAT** **[Strife]** roll, you can deal 1 less damage and apply a **GOOD** SHENANIGANS effect. On a **MAX**, you can get the effects of a **GREAT** and apply a **GREAT** SHENANIGANS effect. Your damage against opponents with a negative status effect is **[Unblockable]**.\r\n\r\n> **DOUBLEKIND**: Rule #2, double-tap. You add a secondary barrel to your weapon, or maybe you just have two of the same weapon now. You can use **[Strife]** moves twice in a turn, but you cannot roll a **[Strife]** move during the next round. Twice the firing means twice the reload time.\r\n\r\n> **QUICKDRAWKIND**: Your weapon is super easy to get out and use. Strike first, and strike hard. You can roll for LET’S STRIFE using **+RAS**, and if you land the first attack, you deal **+1 [Unblockable]** damage. If you miss or get hit first, your next **[Strife]** roll is **[Free]**. You were just a bit too slow to the draw is all…\r\n\r\n> **GAUDYKIND**: Those engravings provide no tactical advantage. This weapon was just built to look cool and intimidate your foes. Any opponent who sees this weapon is **[Scared]**, and you gain **1 [Boost]** whenever you succeed on a **[Flourish]** or **[Strife]** roll, because merely wielding this thing makes you look sick as fuck. If you lose the gun, the target is no longer **[Scared]**.\r\n\r\n> **SEMIAUTOKIND**: BLAM! BLAM! BLAM! This weapon was made to rattle off multiple shots in succession. Each turn you don’t make a **[Strife]** roll, an extra shot can be loaded into your weapon, up to a maximum of 3 stored shots. As an action, you can unload all your shots at once as a series of **[Strife]** rolls, which can all be of the same move. \r\n\r\n> **CREWKIND**: MAN THE CANNONS! This weapon requires an entire team to wield. You and your allies can all roll **[Strife]** moves at once, combining the total damage and effects into one big attack. Teamwork makes the dream work. You must have at least one ally to use this weapon. This is a **[Lengthy]** move, with **[Recharge: 3]**. You can\'t make other **[Strife]** rolls during this time.'),
('dreamsAndHopes', 'DREAMS AND HOPES', 'HOPE', 'HOPE', '[Aspect][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Hope]', 'In the end, blind faith and pretending that the problems of the world don\'t exist isn\'t a viable way to live. Bad things happen even if you don\'t want them to and denying that won\'t fix anything. That doesn\'t mean that you have to let it get you down though or that the world is inherently **BAD**, or that a better world isn\'t possible. Your faith, whatever it is for, inspires you to be permanently **[Hopeful]**, as even a flawed world has hope in it. You may have this emotion alongside others without losing it. STAND TALL expands to include all **[Negative]** Emotions, and becomes a **[Recharge: 1]** as you start to look on the bright side; not from ignorance but genuine belief that it can and will get better.'),
('dreamWarrior', 'DREAM WARRIOR', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Ultra][Passive][Magic][Locked: Subjugglator]', 'With a body count in the hundreds, an iconic M.O. and urban legends surrounding you that would freak out even the most stoic of trolls, you are a living nightmare. You gain access to HERO MODE through your MYTHIC MANGRIT. You are one of the few allowed to undertake the UNHOLY SACRAMENT OF THE EVERLASTING CHUCKLE, a blasphemous Clown Church ritual that allows you to willingly take on an unholy curse that turns you into a SHADOWDROPPER or MUTANT. You do not gain the **[Cullbait]** tag with these, but you cannot alter your blood with the mutation option, you cannot already have been a mutant or shadowdropper, and you may only take one, if any. So great is your presence that you can chase people… into their NIGHTMARES. You can enter into trolls\' dreams while they sleep, or bring the dream world to them and all nearby trolls by forcing the target to spend **10 [Drag]** on your turn. While in the DREAMSCAPE, everything looks ethereal and their darkest secrets are revealed; **[Analyze]** rolls against the target troll are **[Tiered Up]**. The target is **[Exhausted]** and **[Scared]**, and they cannot roll ABSCOND. You can take advantage of their fears with ease here; for **10 [Drag]** you can cause a Hazard or **[Rapid]** Affliction to beset them as an action. Your body is totally mutable in the DREAMSCAPE; your **[Chicanery]** rolls are **[Talented]**, and you are always the CHAMP in TEAM STRIFES here. The only way to escape the DREAMSCAPE is to die, to use **10 [Boost]** to wake up, or to be given **10 [Boost]** as a **[Lengthy]** action by all their allies. The power of friendship! If your target leaves the DREAMSCAPE, you vanish from the encounter… defeated for now.'),
('dressWounds', 'DRESS WOUNDS', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Recharge: 2][Heal][Physical][Locked: Tunnelwarden]', 'Aw, jeez! You’ve learned to quickly try and stop any bloodshed you come across— your own, your friends, your enemies, doesn’t matter! Just slap some bandages onto the wound, and hope for the best. When you want to use your combat knowledge to heal people, roll **+GRT**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Ah, jeez, you’re out of band-aids! You can’t roll this for the rest of the encounter.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Your band-aid just kinda slides off. Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**OK**: It doesn’t help, but it’s the thought that counts. You or the target gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: That helps, at the very least. Your target heals **1 HP**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You bandage your target up, healing **2 HP* or healing **1 HP**, and give them either the **[Charmed]** or **[Hopeful]** condition. If they already had either, you give them **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You break out the big guns: the Salutations Meowbeast novelty band-aid. You heal the target for **3 HP**, end any status effect the target was suffering from (Like **[Ablaze]** or **[Floorbound]**), and give them either the **[Fascinated]** or **[Inspired]** condition. Gaining the **[Inspired]** condition from this move does not include the healing from the condition.'),
('drivenToSuccess', 'DRIVEN TO SUCCESS', 'LIGHT', 'LIGHT', '[Aspect][Advanced][Last Stand][One-Off][Locked: Light]', 'Your role as destiny’s favourite does not make you a hero; it’s what you do with your role that does that. You need to push on and keep going no matter what in search of your goals. In an encounter, you only go down if you don’t have any **[Boost]** left; the moment you hit **0 [Boost]** and **0 HP**, you’re out. This stacks with other moves that would keep you going. You lose **2 [Boost]** per turn this move is active, and every time you take damage you lose **[Boost]** equivalent to twice the amount of damage you took. In addition, when this move activates, you cannot gain any more **[Boost]**; you\'re stuck with the amount maximum you had once hitting **0 HP**.'),
('droidgeneer', 'DROIDGENEER', 'GOLD', 'ADULT', '[Gold][Buildup: 3][Locked: Adult]', 'They told you that machines can’t solve every problem, that you needed to be friends with “real people” and stop making out with that robot you fashioned after your favorite LoL waifu. LOOK WHO’S LAUGHING NOW! You eat, sleep and BREATHE machines as a Droidgeneer. In factories and on ships, you make repairs to these infamous murder machines, so they can take a lickin and keep on kickin! And not just that… you MAKE new ones! You may take an action to call down a BASELINE PATROL DRONE to assist you in combat, unless you are more rebel aligned, in which case you probably hijacked this thing. Either way, your technological prowess has allowed you to make special modifications to this drone. Specifically, a neuralink that lets you and the drone move in tandem! This functions like the effects of the INDIGO INVENTOR tree move, **SUPERGENIUS**. How healthy is it to link minds with an unfeeling, uncaring murder entity? Uhm… well… y’see… eAT LEAD, SUCKA! BRATATATTATATATTATATTATA!'),
('duality', 'DUALITY', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Passive]', 'Golds have a LOT going on for them vis a vis the number two. Two sets of horns, two colourful eyes, two sets of hobbies… huh! Golds often flip between binary options and habits, kinda like going from AC to DC. Point is though, you can select a second Gold Tree as a **[Template]**. You may take one other Gold Tree as a **[Template]**, gaining the **[Entry]** now. You do not gain the **[Talent]** listed in the **[Entry]**. You can\'t take both Battery and Network; those are incompatible! You also can\'t become a Battery or Network troll, since you need to be born like that, though you can still take it so long as becoming that isn\'t a new development in character (this can be flavored as latent psionics manifesting, or training hard into psionics that were negligible beforehand- you just can\'t in-character consciously decide to become one of these out of the blue!).'),
('duckAndCover', 'DUCK AND COVER', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Basic][Physical]\r\n', 'Yeah, y’know, drones are kind of a problem. Like, a big one. Unfortunately, all drones are able to easily tell your caste thanks to thermal detectors, and they don’t take kindly to hemoanonymity. Like, it’s not ILLEGAL, but neither is half the shit that gets other people killed by drones, so… the point is, the amount of times you’ve tangled with drones has made you pretty good at hiding. When you want to duck out of sight, even while already being observed, roll **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: URF! Oh, fuck, that’s not good. You duck for cover and smash your face on the floor, immediately becoming **[Bloodied]**. Nightmare scenario.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Fear or choice paralysis overwhelms you, and you can’t hide in time.\r\n\r\n**OK**: I mean, it’s not BAD, but still… you gain 1 [Boost] as you get ready to try again.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You dash behind a garbage can, catching your breath and hiding from view. You are **[Hidden]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You hide so great, not even drones can find you now! Or, at least, they’re probably not patient enough to find you. You gain the benefits of a **GOOD**, and any **[Analyze]** roll to find you must be **[Lengthy]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Gogdamn, you… you really are pretty good at this, huh? Fuckin’... hide and seek champion lookin’ ass… where the fuck did you GO? You get the effects of a **GREAT**, but your opponent is also **[Inept]** at the roll.\r\n'),
('duplicitousDoppelganger', 'DUPLICITOUS DOPPELGANGER', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Espiacrooner]\n', 'This Espiacrooner could be any one of us. They could be you. They could be me. They could even be— OOPS IT WAS INDEED YOU #BACKSTABBED. You\'re the ultimate infiltrator, a top-tier spy, and a cool guy supreme. Everybody knows your name and face and reputation— BUT WHY WOULD THAT MATTER WHEN YOU CAN JUST WEAR SOMEONE ELSE\'S FAAAAAACE! You gain access to HERO MODE through your RESPLENDENT RASCALITY. With time, your spying abilities have only improved- you gain the ability to take non-**[Open]** moves for your disguises, though they still cannot be **[Psionic]** or **[Magic]**, and you cannot take additional **[Unlocks]** and their associated **[Locked]** moves. You can also make **HEMOANON** disguises, though you are limited to selecting the **FULL-TIME** option, and your reason cannot be **SOCIETAL ROLES** or **OTHER** reflavored to give you the benefits of **SOCIETAL ROLES**. Using **LET ME TELL YOU A SECRET** reveals not only your caste, but your spy identity. Be careful! This is top secret information! Additionally, you have an unmatched ability to impersonate other trolls— to the point where you may as well be a shapeshifter! As well as **HERO MODE**, you gain an additional **EIGHT ESPIACROONER LEVELS**, along with the ability to impersonate specific trolls, be they PCs or NPCs. You can even imitate LIMES or PURPLES, as long as you are one. This gives you access to the **[Caste]** and **[Template]** moves on their sheet, though you can\'t use their **[Psionic]**, **[Magic]**, **[Ultra]**, **[Eerie]**, **[ORG]**, or **[Mutant]** moves. If any moves with the latter three tags come up, you are immediately outed as **[Cullbait]** and must reveal yourself as a spy, because... hey, wait, you\'re not supposed to have those! If you abandon your disguise entirely, **[Mutant]** and **[Eerie]** moves you were faking will not be considered **[Cullbait]**, but impersonating an **[ORG]** member is still treason! You can even dupe people out of character by requesting another player play their own PC to get information out of an unwitting other player before revealing TA-DA, IT\'S ME! \r\n'),
('dyingBattery', 'DYING BATTERY', 'OTHER', 'VOIDROT', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Voidrot]', 'You have previously overexerted yourself in a psychic manner, which caused your eyes and energy to burn up. Now you have to constantly leech off energy in this half-dead state to keep yourself from becoming full-dead. Nuts! You gain access to a pool of latent power called **[Reserve]**. It doesn’t do much… for now. Any time you make a **GREAT** or higher **[Physical]** roll or deal **[Somatic]** damage, you gain **1 [Reserve]** as you drain your opponent’s bioelectricity. In exchange, you passively lose either **1 [Reserve]** or **1 HP** every round (your choice) as your own lifeforce slowly drains away bit by bit. You cannot use any **[Psionic]** trees or moves, and must retrain any **[Psionic]** trees or moves you had. You are also **[Permablind]**; did you think you’d have eyes, like some kinda normie?\r\n\r\n'),
('easilyDistracted', 'EASILY DISTRACTED', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Hm? Huh, wuh? Sorry, you saw a bird flying by. Olivebloods are raised to be a little fickle, and some have exceptionally good senses that make it… hard to stay 100% dialed in. Point is, something’s always demanding to be the next thing you take a look at. Whenever you gain a negative **[Emotion]** from an enemy, roll 1d8 at the end of each of your turns. On a 7 or an 8… hey, man, that scuttlebuggy over there sure is sparkly! What were we talking about again? The **[Emotion]** is removed.'),
('easilyUnderestimated', 'EASILY UNDERESTIMATED', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Passive]', 'You\'re used to being considered small fry! But hey, doesn\'t bother you; you\'ll happily choose to kick some butt! If the opposing team in a TEAM STRIFE has more highbloods than yours, you can choose to count your team as CHALLENGERS even if you\'d be CHAMPS through levels. Additionally, you gain the following CHALLENGER effects. \r\n\r\n> **UNDERDOG**: Yeah, you might look like you\'re tough, but everyone likes us more! Your team all becomes **[Hopeful]** and the opponent team\'s **OK** rolls **[Tier Down]** to a **BAD**.\r\n\r\n> **UNDERVALUED**: Your opponents think they\'ve already won… but they haven\'t! The opponent team becomes **[Icarian]**.'),
('easyBreezy', 'EASY BREEZY', 'BREATH', 'BREATH', '[Aspect][Passive][Unlock: Breath]', 'Like a rustle in the wind, you’re a pretty calm and relaxed person. Whether it’s because you’re actually laidback and chill, or desperately trying to look like it through these trying times, others probably know you well for your carefree attitude. Things that would slow you down just kinda slide off you! You gain **1 [Resistance]** against all **[Drag]**; if you would gain **3 [Drag]** from a move, you instead only gain 2. Unlike most **[Resistance]**, this can reduce **1 [Drag]** to **0 [Drag]**. Whenever you’re made to use **[Drag]**, you bounce right back, gaining an equal amount of **[Boost]**. This does not reduce **[Drag]** you take from your own actions, such as failing moves or trading effects for **[Drag]**; only **[Drag]** inflicted by other players is reduced.'),
('eatAnything', 'EAT ANYTHING', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Passive][Heal][Locked: Gutterblood]', 'There\'s no easy way to say this. Sometimes, you eat phones. Or shoes. Hell, you\'ll even eat a TV if it\'s small enough. Your diet consists of so much low-grade random crap that you can kind of just… derive nutrition from basically anything. Look at you, you feral little survivalist! You are immune to the **[Disgusted]** condition. Any time you have an item in your Sylladex that has any organic components (be they biotech, clothing, etc) you can consume that item in exchange for **1 HP**. Obviously, you can\'t eat totally inedible items like a fucking rock or high grade steel. You have super digestion, not super teeth! The item must be from your Sylladex, not just a random thing around you. The item is destroyed in the process. You fucking ate it. You do not gain **[Boost]** from this.'),
('eatTheMighty', 'EAT THE MIGHTY', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Passive]', 'People with more money than you think they\'re soooo much better than you guys down on the bottom. But uh, guess what? You can screw up too! Whenever a troll of **Well-Off** Wealth or higher gets an **OK** or lower on a roll, you gain **2 [Boost]** as you feel kinda vindicated. In a TEAM STRIFE with at least three trolls in this category present on either side, this decreases to 1… mostly because you\'re paying attention to the huge amount of dipshits around you!'),
('ectoplasmicForm', 'ECTOPLASMIC FORM', 'OTHER', 'GHOST', '[Template][Advanced][Eerie][Physical][Locked: Ghost]', 'Your body is a weapon— literally! You’re getting better at making yourself corporeal, and have regained the ability to roll **[Physical]** **[Strife]** moves, but your very being hisses at the touch of life. Anyone who succeeds on a **[Physical]** roll against you takes **1 [Somatic]** damage as their hand passes through your slimy body or something. You can roll GRIEF to rush into the target to roll a **[Physical]** **[Strife]** move and do **+1 extra [Psychic]** damage, but you take the damage you dealt right back as your body is disrupted. You cannot use Abstrata in this attack.'),
('egotisticResilience', 'EGOTISTIC RESILIENCE', 'OTHER', 'THIEF', '[Class][Basic][Free][Recharge: 3][Locked: Thief]', 'You’re the most important figure in any story, and you coming to harm would do you no good at all. Anytime you attempt to use a **[Heal]** move on yourself or are the subject of one, you gain **+1 extra HP** and gain **1 [Boost]** as it gets you feeling better. This does not stack with a Sylph’s HEALING AURA.\r\n\r\n'),
('eightsidedEntropy', 'EIGHT-SIDED ENTROPY', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][One-Off][Magic][Locked: Gamblignant]', 'Your luck has landed you an artifact of the original Gambligants: A set of Fluorite Octets, an enchanted set of 8d8. Whether you purchased them or found them, it seems that fate decided you should have them. These dice have mighty powers that can drastically change the course of an encounter— for better or for worse! When you want to test your luck, roll 8d8.\r\n\r\n> **8: CALAMITY**: All of the COLOSSI appear, ready to attack everyone present. They remain in the area, attacking anyone present for a month or until they are dispelled. Do you realize how phenomenally unlucky that is? You just rolled the equivalent of 4 **MIN** rolls in a row. That\'s a 0.0000000596046% chance. Jesus. Fucking hell.\r\n> **9-13: NUCLEAR HEADSPLOSION**: You take 20 **[Unblockable]** damage; if this brings you to 0 HP, you become a SHADOWDROPPER.\r\n> **14-18: END OF THE WORLD**: A DIMMING STARS Hazard occurs.\r\n> **19-22: TIME FOR CRAB**: Everyone on the field is exposed to the CARCINIZATION Affliction.\r\n> **23-26: NAPTIME**: Everything on the field becomes **[Exhausted]**\r\n> **27-31: WEASEL OF UNUSUAL SIZE**: You summon a large weasel. It doesn\'t do anything.\r\n> **32: NOT THE BEES**: A BEE SWARM Hazard occurs.\r\n> **33: UNSEASONABLE BLIZZARD**: A SNOWSTORM Hazard occurs.\r\n> **34: ONLY LEFT FEET**: Everyone becomes **[Inept]** at **[Physical]** rolls for the encounter.\r\n> **35: PARALLEL REALITY**: Everything on the field is affected by a random universe from the Lime AU **[Ultra]**, DIMENSIONHOPPER.\r\n> **36: GUILLOTINE DE LA MARQUISE**: A colossal guillotine manifests, dealing **2 damage**. If the opponent is a Lusus, they take **15 damage**.\r\n> **37: LEVITATION**: You begin **[Flying]**.\r\n> **38: RIDICULOUS HAT**: You give a random opponent a silly hat, deeply **[Embarrassing]** them.\r\n> **39: PONY STAMPEDE**: A STAMPEDE Hazard occurs; you and your allies are immune.\r\n> **40: BLASTOFF**: A random opponent is removed from the fight, expelling them violently through the air and into the horizon.\r\n> **41-44: MAGIC ANON**: You are affected by a random effect from the Lime AU Move, MAGIC ANON.\r\n> **45-47: MUSCLEBEAST**: A Musclebeast spawns, and aligns itself with you.\r\n> **48-51: LOTTERY WIN**: **Treasure IV** spawns before you. It\'s a **[Lengthy]** action to stuff **Treasure I** into your pockets.\r\n> **52-55: ALL THE LUCK**: Gain **10 [Boost]**, which can be spent in increments even without GLASS HALF FULL. \r\n> **56-58: REROLL X2**: Reroll twice, and take both results.\r\n> **59-63: EXTRA LIFE**: You receive a HEARTGEM NECKLACE; wearing it and kissing a recently dead troll will bring them back to life. The necklace turns to dust afterwards.\r\n> **64: ANCESTRAL AWAKENING**: Oh… my god? You rolled all 8s. That\'s… that\'s insane. Again**: the equivalent of 4 **MAX** rolls in a row, 0.0000000596046 chance. Well… you immediately gain all **[Caste]**, **[Aspect]**, **[Class]** and **[Template]** moves you have access to. Already had all of one of these? No worries, just select another. You are **[Healed]** to full HP. Holy shit. This is permanent.'),
('einsteinicYouth', 'EINSTEINIC YOUTH', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Bookworm]', 'Let\'s be clear! You\'re a genius! You\'re one hell of a smart cookie! You\'re always right, never wrong, and everyone knows that about you. You don\'t necessarily have grace or brawn, but with your super smarts, nobody\'s ever gonna stop you! You gain access to HERO MODE through your PRECISE PERSPICACITY. Your max **+PSP** increases to +5, and you may immediately reduce another stat to increase it now if you choose. So impacted by your intellect are you, that even your destiny alters itself to better suit your mind. Choose one of the following options.\r\n\r\n> Your Aspect parts ways; you gain access to the Mind Aspect if you did not already. \r\n\r\n> Your Class gestalts with another to show you the way forward; you gain access to either Seer or Mage, your choice.\r\n\r\n'),
('electricEntomology', 'ELECTRIC ENTOMOLOGY', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Passive][Psionic][Unlock: Beekeeper]', 'Buzz buzz! Is that the sound of a vibrating gadget or bees? With you around, it could be either! You are a Beekeeper, a friend of all things that buzz. On Alternia, most technology is biotech, with honeycomb making up organic motherboards and larvae living batteries. You juggle the role of an entomologist and an electronic engineer, always working to find the next breakthrough in tech. You are **[Talented]** in **+RAS**; you don\'t need to be SMART, you need to be creative (and friendly to bees or they\'ll sting you). Right now, you only have access to the rawest of materials from your work with bees, but soon, you\'ll be able to make some pretty interesting tech with it! If you take this move as a Goldblood, you can choose if this move is **[Psionic]** or not. Not everyone has natural bee psionics, but the life can call to them anyway. Otherwise, this move ceases to be **[Psionic]** as you resign yourself to getting your hands sticky. You gain access to the following items.\r\n\r\n**WAXBOARD (1 VP)**: Sticky, but useful! You can use this motherboard to stick two other items together, adding up all three items\' VP and dividing it by 2, rounding up. The item can then be used as a **[Tech]** item to connect to the internet. Somehow. You can\'t use WAXBOARD-combined items with other WAXBOARDS - they don\'t support dual-core processing.\r\n\r\n**AMP-HONEY (1 VP)**: This specially treated honey gets power from point A to point B more efficiently than any wiring… but it also tastes nice. Eating it **[Heals] 1 HP**. This item is **[Consumable]**.\r\n\r\n**SIGNAL PHEROMONES (2 VP)**: Pheromones! The answer to bug-based wireless tech! Send messages from one item to another, and let those Network Golds store the heavy info. Either way, this item comes in sets of up to 3; when you clip the emitter to your ear, you and your allies can share **[Emotions]** with each other. Neat!\r\n\r\n**POWERLARVAE (2 VP)**: Squeezing one of these wriggly yellow bugs gives you an electric shock, which is enough to snap you out of a slump! Don\'t worry, they\'re resilient, and like being squeezed :) Squeezing one halves your current **[Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**JAR OF BEES (3 VP)**: Just fucking spike it on the ground and summon a BEE SWARM Hazard, who gives a shit. This is a **[Consumable]**, obviously. And a **[One-Off]**, too.\r\n\r\n**CONDUCTOR JELLY (3 VP)**: Dip something in this bad boy, and it turns into a VOLTKIND weapon for the encounter, even if it already has a STRIFEKIND upgrade. **[Strife]** rolls that deal **[Electric]** damage to someone with a weapon coated in CONDUCTOR JELLY are **[Inept]**. This is a **[Consumable]**.'),
('electricShepherd', 'ELECTRIC SHEPHERD', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Inventor]', 'You don’t just build machines. You build works of art. More advanced than real, living creatures, more profound than the most beautiful sunset… and controlling them all is you, their mighty master. You? You fucking rule. You gain access to HERO MODE through your PERFECT PERSPICACITY. Your machines are all heavily upgraded; they have a +2 to all stats, and if given the PERSONALITY CORE Upgrade from UPGRADES, PEOPLE!, they gain full sapience and get an extra action to do as they please at the end of your turn rather than the extra +1 stat boost. Your robots are so advanced, even, that even the ones that aren’t given their own minds sometimes act as if they do. Your robot also gains access to HERO MODE, through whatever stat they are **[Talented]** in. You do not share your activation of HERO MODE with your robot.'),
('eminentDomain', 'EMINENT DOMAIN', 'KID', 'KOB', '[Template][Basic][Recharge: 3][Chicanery][Locked: Kids on Bikes]', 'Part of being a kid who owns a bike is fighting tyrannical villainous genocidal alien empires that launch nuclear missiles at your home every few days, only stopped by a weird clown that flies around flashing green and white. It\'s a normal everyday job, honestly. Someone has to help your fellow kids who don\'t have bikes. And with that experience, you\'ve started to figure out what some of these alien doohickeys look like! When you\'re on Alternia you may attempt to commandeer Imperial Color Guard machinery to turn it against your opponents. It\'s risky, but hey-- this robopigeon has a death ray in it! Perfect for the Imperial Drone chasing your teacher over there! When you want to engage in guerilla warfare, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: That set off an alarm. This is very not good. Either an Imperial Drone is dispatched and arrives in **two turns**, targeting you and any other Kids present, or Org trolls are dispatched to arrive **next turn** in the encounter if available. Better run.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: A localized alert sounds, not enough to summon the big guns, but the security cameras are definitely on you now. Color Guard trolls gain a **+1 [Buff]** against you if any are present, and you take **3 [Drag]** as the robopigeon pecks at you.\r\n\r\n**OK**: That was a real bird, what the hell! You take **2 [Drag]** as it pecks at you.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You manage to pull it loose and turn it against your target. Excellent. Choose one of the following effects.\r\n\r\n> **ROBOPIGEON**: Say cheese! The target is flagged as SUSPICIOUS as you aim the camera bird at them, causing any drones present to use at least one action against them next turn.\r\n> **BLOODPRICKER**: These creepy crawly mechanical things get dumped in trashcans to latch onto unsuspecting mutants and hemoanons to check their blood while they dumpster dive. And you\'re throwing it at the target to inflict **[Bloodied]** on them for **two turns**!\r\n> **LANDMINE**: This is just a landmine someone left out. When it explodes, it plays a propaganda soundbite. Weird. It also inflicts **1 [Somatic]** Damage to everyone present when used.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: \r\n\r\n> **ROBOPIGEOHFUCK**: You were just trying to take a picture! Why do the robopigeons have deathrays!? Your target receives **3 [Drag]** as you nearly deathray them.\r\n> **I LOVE CONDEEZ**: Nuts, that\'s a propaganda bush, isn\'t it? Well, no matter. A splash of a bucket of water over it, and.. Sparking! All your allies\' Strife Weapons gain the VOLTKIND Abstrata next turn if possible!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: \r\n\r\n> **OH FUCK**: You didn\'t move the robopigeon out of the way in time. Your target receives **2 [Somatic]** Damage and **2 [Drag]** as you blast them directly in the face. Is that what you wanted? To finally use the robopigeon\'s deathray? You did it.\r\n> **HAUNTED HOUSE**: There\'s a psionic suppressor over there keeping the latent ghost population down. If you kick it just right, then... Bingo! That\'s a PARANORMAL ACTIVITY **[Hazard]** unleashed on all of your opponents, as the spectral undead reward you for freeing them! You cannot use this effect if you have already activated a **[Hazard]** in this encounter.'),
('emissarysOrphaners', 'EMISSARY\'S ORPHANERS', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'ORPHANER', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Orphaner]', 'Prerequisite: Must be a Violet.\r\n\r\nYou are a member of the Orphaners, a select group of seadwelling trolls with the greatest duty of all trollkind; ensuring that the Emissary of the Horrorterrors, dual-lusus of the Empress and Heiress and the living dark maginuclear bomb known as Gl\'bgolyb is kept fed, for only the semi-ritualistic act of the Emissary\'s chosen caste hunting the great beasts of Alternia can sate its hunger, both physical and magical. Orphaners are an odd split between hunter and servant both for the Horrorterror in the Vast Depths, and for good reason; it is difficult to feed a god and come back from it without being a little changed! You have a conditional authority over all non-Org trolls, and Drones will not target you while in your ORG Uniform, which you gain now for free, as well as a flair on all social media marking you as a member of the Orphaners. Your basic training covers everything and anything regarding the hunt, and you gain a **+2 [Buff]** to all rolls against Monsters and Lusii.\r\n\r\n'),
('emotionalInstability', 'EMOTIONAL INSTABILITY', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Passive][Psionic]', 'You are not a particularly stable person. I mean, makes sense, right? You\'re a living psychic nuke that struggles to keep their powers in check all the time, and also a teenager. You\'re bound to break down sometimes. Sometimes, this is great! Other times, nnnnnot so much. You can choose to FREAK OUT when you drop below half HP. While FREAKING OUT, all **[Emotions]** you have are heightened, good and bad. When someone tries to give you an **[Emotion]** while you\'re FREAKING OUT, they must roll 1d8. On a 1 or an 8, the **[Emotion]** becomes its opposite, and heightened too! Watch out!'),
('emotionalLabor', 'EMOTIONAL LABOR', 'OTHER', 'SYLPH', '[Class][Advanced][Mental][Physical][One-off][Locked: Sylph]', 'Shit’s going wrong again. Okay, you’re capable and you can fix this. You’ll take the lead and show the path everyone can take that will end with the least amount of things that have gone wrong. Now, what’s within your power to fix right now without launching into a full-scale intervention or pseudo pale pile? \n\n> **TIME:** You give yourself and each ally 1 **[WHAM]** this round and every three rounds after as you plan and calculate for them. \n\n> **SPACE:** You reset all Universal Move effect cooldowns for yourself and allies as you intervene and give them a second to breathe.\n\n> **LIFE:** You heal each ally and yourself by **2 HP** as you flit around the field doing welfare checks. This **[Heal]** effect isn’t boosted by other sources.\n\n> **DOOM:** You remove any **[Nerf]**s from your allies. If they have no **[Nerf]**, you heal all **[Drag]**.\n\n> **HOPE:** You give each ally +1 **[Buff]** on all rolls for 3 rounds.\n\n> **RAGE:** You turn your attention to harrying the enemy, giving them each 1 **[Weakness]** to an **[Energy]** type of your choice for 2 rounds.\n\n> **BREATH:** You remove one **[Emotion]** of your choice from each ally, and another every 3 rounds after for **[Free]**.\n\n> **BLOOD:** You focus on keeping everyone together; when one ally gains **[Boost]**, all of you gain half that **[Boost]** rounded up, to a minimum of one. This effect lasts the rest of the encounter.\n\n> **LIGHT:** You lend your allies your good fortune. When your allies gain **[Boost]**, they get one more point of **[Boost]** to top it off.\n \n> **VOID:** Each ally gains 1 **[Hold]**. This hold can be used to become **[Hidden]** as you cover and distract for them, even if they otherwise wouldn’t be able to.\n\n> **HEART:** All allies on the field gain access to your **[Talents]**. If you have no allies, you can copy the **[Talent]** of your enemy and add it to your **[Talents]**.\n\n> **MIND:** All opponents’ **SHENANIGANS, SWASHBUCKLE**, and **ACT FAST** rolls **[Tier Down]** for 3 rounds as you stay one step ahead of their plans.'),
('emotionally', 'EMOTIONALLY', 'OLIVE', 'ADULT', '[Olive][Locked: Adult]', 'Few folks could count themselves as lucky as those who become Emotionallies. Troll society is fraught with danger and sorrow, yet somehow the fearless leaders of the Alternian Empire need the strength to push past it. You are a troll specially trained to help pacify and soothe the folks they serve as a therapy troll, or an emotional sponge. In return you get free room and board, all for the price of completely dedicating your devotion and life to whoever you serve. Isn\\\'t that great? For the low, low price of traumadumping to you instead of seeing a Terrorpist, your partner can redirect any negative **[Emotions]** and **[Drag]** to you. You gain one less **[Drag]** than the amount being removed, and any **[Heightened] [Emotions]** are brought back to **[Base]** level. Equal partnership!'),
('employeeExtravagant', 'EMPLOYEE EXTRAVAGANT', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Worker]', 'You\'ve learned the ins and outs of your job to an extent that\'s practically supernatural. NOBODY can do your job better than you, and your boss has secretly told you that YOU are their favorite employee. Can you believe that?! You gain access to HERO MODE, with the stat you became **[Talented]** in with AT YOUR SERVICE. Additionally, you get one of the following options.\r\n\r\n> **Janitorturist**: You\'re full on wearing a Hazmat Suit, that\'s how prepared for toxic working conditions you get to be now. All **[Physical]** conditions you would gain have a chance of just not affecting you; roll 1d2. On a 1, it doesn\'t.\r\n\r\n> **Underhost**: You\'ve graduated from Underhost to Overhost, the Frontman of every party now. It\'s JUST like in Jellykraken Game. You can summon Rust Worker NPCs to any scene if you need them, making them wade into dangerous situations instead of you. You can use **1 action** to make them roll one move. You can have up to 3 NPCs with you in a scene.\r\n\r\n> **Splathlete**: Your continued success has made you quite famous! You gain access to HARDCORE HUBRIS as well as GLORIOUS GRACE for HERO MODE, and as a **[One-Off]** can roll **+GRA** to use SWASHBUCKLE.\r\n\r\n> **Henchtroll**: EY, BOSS! YOU AIN\'T EVER GIVIN\' UP! You can roll GUTSUCKERY at a **[Recharge: 2]** rather than **[One-Off]**.\r\n\r\n> **Rustshirt**: Actually? You AREN\'T disposable. Someone else can go be disposable for you! Any time an ally takes damage in an encounter, you gain **1 [Boost]**. Additionally, you have **1 [Resistance]** to **[Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n> **Stuntster**: ALRIIIIGHT! You LOVE crashing vehicles and being hurt! WHOOOOO! You can raise the HORSEPOWER of any vehicle up to double its current capability while driving it; rather than in increments of -2, your penalty to VEHICULATE like this goes down in penalties of -1, and your VEHICULATE rolls **[Tier Up]** while moving faster than normal.\r\n\r\n> **Retailanguisher**: You ALWAYS have EVERYTHING in stock. ALWAYS. You can purchase items on the fly in the middle of encounters. You can only buy a particular item once. This is a **[Free]** action.\r\n\r\n> **Minionwick**: You grow in power every day, threatening to overpower your master! It\'s just like Disney\'s The Sorcerer\'s Apprentice (1940). You get a **MAX** on **[Magic]** rolls on a 17+, not a 20+.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('emtTraining', 'EMT TRAINING', 'OTHER', 'DOCTERROR', '[Template][Basic][Recharge: 2][Heal][Locked: Docterror]', 'You’re well on your way. You even cracked open your textbook once, you think you can give this healing thing a shot! Slap a band-aid here, use a medicalizer and call it medicine there, bam! Roll **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Waaaaait a moment. This is a troll you’re healing, not a hoofbeast. You used your veterinary nursing tutorials by accident! The target takes **2 [Somatic]** damage and becomes **[Poisoned]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You fucked up. Oh god, you fucked up so bad. You’re pretty sure this is the same as the arterial spray picture that was on your online seminar? Your target takes **1 [Somatic]** damage and becomes **[Poisoned]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Okay, sure. You didn\'t cut the wrong tube and the stitches are... Well, they aren’t harmful. But they’re not beneficial either. They gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Huh. You actually paid attention in your online CPR seminar. They heal **1 HP** OR have a status effect removed.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: They heal **2 HP**, OR have a status effect removed.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You are the greatest amateur docterror to ever live. They are healed by 30% of their max health (rounded down), OR have 2 status effects removed.'),
('enchantedWeaponry', 'ENCHANTED WEAPONRY', 'OTHER', 'KNIGHT', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Magic][Locked: Knight]', 'Over the course of your adventure you’ve found enemies that are just as beefy and armored as you are. With foes like that, recklessly flinging yourself at them doesn’t do any good. Sometimes, you’ve got to fight smarter! Take a deep breath and feel the power of the universe around you. Your weapon shall be the one that helps turn the tide. You may exploit your aspect to supercharge your weapons with **[Energy]**. Upon taking this move, pick an **[Energy]** type that would make sense aspect wise for you to wield (i.e a Knight of Hope with **[Holy] [Energy]**). You may not change your **[Energy]** type later, so choose wisely. At the cost of 2 **[Boost]**, you may apply that energy to your weapon for **[Free]** as you charge up and blast the enemy with cosmic power. '),
('enGarde', 'EN GARDE!', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][One-Off][Locked: Marquis]', 'Swish swish swish! You dart into combat with your weapon swinging gracefully. You can select a single target to DUEL. While DUELING, both you and your target are **[Talented]** at **[Strife]** rolls, and do **1 extra damage** to each other any time you deal damage, and neither party can heal nor attack anyone else. Either party can call off the duel, but they become **[Inept]** at all rolls for **3 rounds** from the shame of surrender. While DUELING, you feel **[Smug]**, and for good reason! Look at how the wind is blowing at your hair as you dash forward like that! Your opponent does not get this benefit. Using **[Manipulate]** rolls to make the opponent surrender counts as you surrendering. TAKE NO PRISONERS!'),
('ensorcell', 'ENSORCELL', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Magic][Strife][Locked: Esotericist]', 'As the living dead shamble towards you, you flick through your keychain with many historical versions of religious clown symbols, until- AHA! THAT is the one they recognize, and the holy power turns the motherfucker to dust! A word of power here and the right holy relic from your collection there is always more than enough to harm an opponent. When you want to channel magic into a bitch, roll **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: MAGIC SHORT CIRCUIT KZZZRT! You crossed streams, dumbshit! You take **2 [Freaky]** **[Psychic]** damage and experience **[Sensory Overload]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Argh, that wasn’t the right word of power! You take **1 [Freaky]** **[Psychic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**OK**: They’re withstanding the curses, but your power is growing! You take **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: HEX! HEX! HEX! Your tools fuck em up! The target takes **1 [Freaky]** **[Psychic]** damage!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Overwhelming power! You deal **2 [Freaky]** **[Psychic]** damage, or deal **1 [Freaky]** **[Psychic]** damage and increase the **[Recharge]** of an enemy move currently on **[Recharge]** by 1.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: LIGHTNING ARCS FROM YOUR RELIC, AND THE SKIES CLEAVE OPEN! THE END IS UPON US! You deal **3 [Freaky]** **[Psychic]** damage, or deal **2 [Freaky]** **[Psychic]** damage and trigger the **[Recharge]** of a move not currently on **[Recharge]**.'),
('esotericClasspectery', 'ESOTERIC CLASSPECTERY', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Nyastrologist]', 'Whoa whoa… you\'ve learned about some really deep star-lore now. Sure, your Aspect is a weapon, but the weapon needs a hand to wield it. Classes are a bottom of the iceberg level secret in astrology; the way that the individual blessed with a Zodiac Sign wields their aspect. You gain access to **[Basic]** class moves now, and **[Advanced]** ones at level 12. Additionally, you have a new level of chartology to study! When figuring out if people are compatible, you can now use the following additional chart, with the following additional effects stacked up on the ones from ZODIAC CAT. This doesn\'t count towards the Rule of 3 in ZODIAC CAT\'s compatibility test; it\'s its own little thing.\r\n\r\n**COMPATIBLE**: One of you is active, the other passive, which means you ying-yang each other to perfection. When one of you gains a Positive **[Emotion]**, you both do, unless you (the Nyastrologist) decide against it.\r\n\r\n**INCOMPATIBLE**: You\'re both sharing the same role! Now you\'re just going to compete with one another!! When one of you gains a Negative **[Emotion]**, you both become **[Enraged]** or **[Out-Of-Control]** instead. \r\n\r\n**CLASSES**:\r\n\r\n> **Active**: [Prince, Thief, Maid, Mage, Knight, Witch]\r\n> **Passive**: [Bard, Rogue, Heir, Seer, Page, Sylph]'),
('espiacrooner', 'ESPIACROONER', 'CERULEAN', 'ADULT', '[Cerulean][Free][One-Off][Locked: Adult]', 'While killing people outright is an effective method of dealing with someone, things occasionally require a more delicate touch. Those who acted like spies on Alternia or show a talent for sneaking around can become Espiacrooners. Your life is now dedicated to infiltrating alien governments and stabbing people in the back! After all, if not you then who will slowly integrate themselves into new civilizations and tear it apart from the inside? Apologies for the future trust issues you will develop. When in a **[Strife]** with someone, you can pretend to lay your weapons down. Look, you don’t really want to fight. You were just backed into a corner, blackmailed, or some other thing! This really isn’t under your control. You can put your hands up and offer mercy to end a strife. If they accept, you gain 2 **[WHAM]**. Fool, you thought I meant it? If they don’t believe you, then you become **[Quickened]** for a turn as you stay light on your feet.'),
('eternalEnigma', 'ETERNAL ENIGMA', 'VOID', 'VOID', '[Aspect][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Void]', 'You’ve hidden yourself from the world for so long, but now you’re finally learning to open up and talk to other people. That doesn’t mean you can’t still have an air of mystery to you! To pretend that you’re an open book is incorrect… while you’re happy to finally accept that maybe you don’t need to be isolated, you also don’t need to let everyone know everything about you, nor everything you know! You begin every encounter **[Hidden]**, even if people think they can see you— attacking you might prove you weren’t actually where they thought you were, and you can duck for cover elsewhere. Your ability to hide is so great, that even **[Permablind]** trolls have difficulty spotting you, and don’t gain their usual benefits against **[Hidden]** trolls, although they get a **+2 [Buff]** to PROBLEM SLEUTHING to do it. Your FAR APART bonus instead makes other\'s rolls **[Inept]** instead of **[Nerfed]**; if they would already be, they also take a **-1 [Nerf]**. Coming out of hiding exhilarates you; when you are not **[Hidden]**, you gain **1 [Boost]** at the start of every turn.'),
('eventHorizon', 'EVENT HORIZON', 'OTHER', 'GRIMDARK', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Eerie][Maximum Edge][Locked: Grimdark]', 'You are lost. You are lost. You are lost. What fragile tethers to your trollmanity that remain begin to fray, and then to snap, one by one by one. You look the same outside as you ever did, unless you are in A MODE MOSTE GRIMM, but your heart is as black and cold as the space outside the stars. You completely lose the ability to benefit from **[Boost]** and **[Positive]** Emotions. The last vestiges of color and personality drain from you, and you can no longer roll anything involving **+PLC**, **+PSP**, or **+RAS**. When you are **[Bloodied]**, it is not blood. Your paper-thin skin spills thick, black ichor that reflects no light, instantly identifying you as Wrong to any onlookers. Entity-type monsters are non hostile to you, recognizing their own. \n\nOnce you take this move, which must be taken last, you gain access to the secondary benefits of all other prior moves. BLACK HOLE now affects you as well, your stats slipping away into the void with the rest of you.'),
('everTheMartyr', 'EVER THE MARTYR', 'LIFE', 'LIFE', '[Aspect][Basic][Heal][Locked: Life]', 'You put others before yourself, even when you shouldn’t necessarily. Other people’s healing comes before your own, after all! You can sacrifice your own energy to give others the boosts they need; you can give away up to **3 HP**, **3 [Boost]**, or one of your **[Positive] [Emotions]** to an ally as an action as you give them a pep talk that reminds them of the strengths and talents they have— ones you don’t have, which pains you to think about. You do take **2 [Drag]** each time you use this move as you\'re weighed down, but it\'s okay. So long as it\'s helping others, right?\r\n'),
('everyLastDetail', 'EVERY LAST DETAIL', 'LIGHT', 'LIGHT', '[Aspect][Basic][Locked: Light]', 'Rule systems and minor details delight you, even if they frustrate others. Perhaps especially if they frustrate others? Your pedantic approach to the pursuit of knowledge can put you at odds with people, but it helps you immensely. When you roll an **[Analyze]** move, you can turn the action into a **[Lengthy]** one as you make sure to take in even the smallest details, putting others at unease. Your **[Analyze]** roll is **[Tiered Up]**, and if you succeed the target gains **[Drag]** respective to your tier of success— (1 for a **GOOD**, 2 for a **GREAT**, 3 for a **MAX**).'),
('everythingAnythingAllAtOnce', 'EVERYTHING ANYTHING ALL AT ONCE', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Full-Time]', 'At one point you would have said the future is monochrome, but through your journey, you have learned: it is a spectrum. However, who said that said spectrum had to fit into neat little lines? This is your journey, how you decide to represent yourself, how others decide to represent themselves… The future isn’t monochrome. It\'s a choice. And no matter where this journey goes, no matter how your story ends? This is just the beginning. And you’re going to make every single moment worth it.You gain the **HERO MODE** of the stat you chose in your **[Entry]**. Every 3 **[Boost]** you gain over the course of the encounter, you can give 1 **[Drag]** to an enemy of your choice. After all, you’re living your best life as a Hemoanon. Haters can die mad. Finally, choose one Universal Move. That Universal Move’s **MAX** threshold is now 18+. You’ve spent so long honing your sense of self, that you’re able to refine and become something you enjoy.\r\n'),
('eviscerate', 'EVISCERATE', 'OTHER', 'MOONBARK', '[Template][Basic][Recharge: 3][Eerie][Physical][Strife][Then Perish][Locked: Moonbark]', 'Your bestial fury is so powerful and horrific that it gives your fights an R-rating when you transform! With claws, jaws and rage, you stop caring about sound… and instead, go as loud as possible! After first using this move, an ANGRY MOB HAZARD appears in four rounds to cull you as they hear your roars; you must fight them rather than flee if you are in MOONFRENZY mode. You can only use this move if you are at least in MOONBARK MODE. Roll **+GRT**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Arooooo- urgh? Oh, SHIT! THE ANGRY MOB GOT HERE EARLY! They\'re only targeting you, and they\'re mad! They skip Round 1 and immediately start attacking when the HAZARD starts after the four round wait.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Your noisy killing spree grabs the attention of the incoming Mob! They skip Round 1 when the hazard starts!\r\n\r\n**OK**: Nothing but air! The target takes **1 [Drag]** regardless.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: SLASH GNASH! You attack with full force, roaring and snarling as you go. You do **2 [Somatic]** damage to the opponent!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: SLASH GNASH CRASH THRASH! Hellish attacks sunder opponents entirely! You do **3 [Somatic]** damage to the opponent. The ANGRY MOB takes an extra round to get here.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: AROOOOOOOO! Your roars echo, hiding your whereabouts. You do **4 [Somatic]** damage to the opponent, and the ANGRY MOB takes two extra rounds to get here.'),
('evolvedSenseOfSelf', 'EVOLVED SENSE OF SELF', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Full-Time]', 'Nobody’s stories stay a perfectly straight line. After all, if they did, then you wouldn’t be on this path, would you? That’s alright though. We all grow as people whether that be into someone more actualized or just a bigger sack of shit. Whatever you want, no rules, just right. Choose an option below based on the path you chose in **SYSTEMIC SPITE**:\r\n\r\n> **Hiding from the Past**: While you have had to hide from the past, and still choose to, the future you’ve made for your reborn self is bright. As a **[One-Off]**, gain the effects of a **GREAT PSYCHOANALYZE PROBLEM SLEUTHING** for **[Free]**. \r\n\r\n> **Persecution**: Over time you have learned that folks can persecute you all they want; it is their insecurity in your existence that’s the issue, not you. Once per encounter, you may repeat a move of the same type as your previous action (such as two **[Strife]** or two **[Chicanery]** rolls). This does not let you repeat an effect that is on **[Recharge]**.\r\n\r\n> **Idealism**: To hell if they don’t agree, you know that the path you’ve taken is true… and you’ll make sure they know it. Once a physical strife breaks out, you may make a badass speech to get one last **[Verbal] [Strife]** move in. This still keeps the +2 **[Buff]** from the entry. \r\n\r\n> **Societal Roles**: While you still do not want the roles society has placed on you, you’ve also come to understand how the circumstances you were born into shaped who you are today. You can acknowledge these things, and work forward from there. You may take 1 more Basic and Advanced move from your caste tree. \r\n\r\n> **Other**: This is your life to lead, and your reasons for being. Like before, choose an effect from the reasons listed above and make them your own.'),
('excellentCaegerscore', 'EXCELLENT CAEGERSCORE', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Passive]', 'You don\'t sweat the details! By now, you\'ve cultivated an excellent financial presence, and you\'ve got the banking systems that regulate Alternia\'s economy to give you some leeway and loans sometimes. When you make a **[Big Buy]**, you can access **Ultrarich** items. If you were already **Ultrarich**, you make **+1 LUX** when you roll MONEYMAKERY.'),
('excellentDisguise', 'EXCELLENT DISGUISE', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Passive]', 'In order to blend in with trolls… you need to act like one! You aren’t content with just wearing some horns on your head; you’re going the full mile, with face paint, a wig, contact lenses, etcetera. Even if your blood is revealed, people might just think you’re a mutant if you’re lucky. Select a caste (for your sake, it’s probably smarter to choose something from Olive or below; you CAN disguise yourself as higher castes, but all **[Analyze]** rolls against you in your disguise **[Tier Up]** twice, even to a **MAX**). You disguise yourself as this caste, and you can take a **[Basic]** **[Open]** move from them, or any **[Basic]** Hemoanon move. You’re exceptionally convincing!'),
('exceptionallyLarge', 'EXCEPTIONALLY LARGE', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive]', 'UHHHHH. YOU ARE. YOU ARE BIG. WHAT… HOW. You\'re weirdly big and buff. Maybe you\'re just crazy strong? Maybe you\'re just a large person. Who fucking knows. You have **+2 HP**, but take **2 [Drag]** whenever you\'re **[Floorbound]**. You fall pretty hard is the thing. You cannot have this move and SHORT LITTLE FUCKER.'),
('exclusiveBargains', 'EXCLUSIVE BARGAINS', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Meowchant]', 'What makes people return to you, again and again? Deals they can\'t get anywhere else!! You gain access to the following exclusive items; they each cost you **2 VP**, but you can choose how much you sell them for. After all, you\'re the only one who can sell these items!\r\n\r\n**RINGS OF POWER: These magic rings can swap your **[Talent]** to a different one! Taking the ring off takes an action, but returns your **[Talent]** to normal. There\'s multiple kinds, each with their own **[Talent]:\r\n\r\n> **RUBY**: +RAS\r\n> **AMETHYST**: +PLC\r\n> **EMERALD**: +GRA\r\n> **TOPAZ**: +APP\r\n> **MOONSTONE**: +GRT\r\n> **AMBER**: +HUB\r\n> **SAPPHIRE**: +PSP\r\n> **QUARTZ**: +IMG\r\n\r\n> **MIGHTY RELIC**: The Talisman of Azaied?! Or something? This ancient (definitely real, probably) artifact is loaded with power... and for a low price, it can be anyone\'s! If you have HERO MODE, this alters the stat it uses. This item is **[Consumable]**.\r\n\r\n> **CURSED BONES**: An ossuary smorgasbord that freaks even ghosts out! Maybe it\'s a little necklace, maybe it\'s just some loose bones in your pocket. Spooky trolls and monsters have a **-2 [Nerf]** on **[Strife]** rolls against you once you pull this item out.\r\n\r\n> **GOOD LUCK CHARMS**: Camaaaawn, it\'s a lil good luck charm! With your face on it! Who wouldn\'t be interested? Remember, you\'re a lucky merchant! It\'s real, you know? Rumour says, if you use this **[Consumable]** item as an action, three rounds after engaging HERO MODE you can do it again. \r\n\r\n> **PIGMENT-B-GONE**: Great for cosplays and refusing to show your peers your caste, this dye turns any caste-coloured biological stuff grey for a week. This can be made permanent if you use it for four weeks in a row, but it\'ll cost ya!  \r\n\r\n> **MYSTERIOUS BREW**: This is a terrible idea. When you drink this brew, you regain 4 HP… but you\'re immediately subject to a randomly selected Affliction. With any luck, it won\'t immediately affect you, but… '),
('excuseMeKnave', 'EXCUSE ME, KNAVE?', 'OTHER', 'PRINCE', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Recharge: 4][Tantrum][Locked: Prince]\r\n\r\n', 'Did they just... heal? Did they just stop in the middle of a fight to take out a bandaid for their widdle booboos like this isn\'t a fight? You\'re not a JRPG villain, you little shit, you’re not just going to sit there and stare while they take a breather, how DARE they, how DARE they do this, fight FAIR! You gain **+1 [Buff]** to a stat of your choice for 2 turns when an enemy **[Heals]** in front of you.\r\n'),
('exile', 'EXILE', 'OTHER', 'ADULT', '[Free][Reaction][Recharge: 3][Locked: Adult]', 'Not everyone on the Empire\\\'s shitlist is a guns blazing hero or a cape twirling villain. Oftentimes there are simply civilians caught in the crossfire that, for whatever reason, cannot live as they were intended to by the Condesce\\\'s regime. Perhaps you are an Eerie or Mutant troll who managed to escape, a troll targeted for helming who found a way to bounce, or any number of infinite possibilities. While everyone’s reason for exile is different… The one commonality is that you don’t want ANYONE to find out that reason. It is because of this that you’ve developed a pretty mean “THE FUCK YOU LOOKING AT BUDDY!?” look. As a **[Free] [Reaction]** you may give someone the REBELLIOUS DEATH GLARE before they make an **[Analyze]** roll against you. This inflicts the target with 3 **[Drag]** as they feel uneasy for even trying to perceive you.'),
('existentialDread', 'EXISTENTIAL DREAD', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Advanced][Passive]\r\n', 'Listen, man, you’re well aware by now that you’re considered a mar on the otherwise perfectly spectrumed landscape of Alternian Society. Folks may be less inclined to want to interact with you, but that’s their issue. You’ve learned how to use their own insecurity over your existence to your advantage. Your identity, your way. At the beginning of the battle, your opponents gain the emotion **[Dread]**.\r\n'),
('exMachina', 'EX MACHINA', 'OTHER', 'ROBOT', '[Template][Ultra][Locked: Robot]', 'End of the line, pal. The assembly line, that is. You made it. This is a good thing. You’re now fully equipped with an RGX 5060 gigadrive and RGB fans or whatever. Your advanced computer mind allows you to process things quicker than any normal troll could dream of. You gain the BEYOND THE BEENARY HACKERMAN move. Additionally, you get a new upgrade to your body, based on the option you choose with the **[Entry]**.\r\n\r\n> **Robot**: You were made for a certain purpose. At least initially. But now? Now you’re your own troll with your own wants and abilities. Or maybe you still work for the indigo who made you. Either way, you gain a +2 in any stat that would correspond with your mechanical duties.\r\n\r\n> **Soulbot**: You died, and yet, kept pushing past it. And now, you know you can keep pushing forward, past your limitations. Your psionics begin to manifest in new and powerful ways, granting you access to one **[Basic]** or **[Entry]** **[Psionic]** move from any caste. This move gains the **[One-off]** tag as it is taxing on your already frail soul.\r\n\r\n> **Cyborg**: This is what happens when you sell your limbs on Scamazon. You get a sick robot body. Hell yeah! You even have your own Wifi signal, which might just be an actual EMP. You make all **[Tech]** moves that would target you **[Inept]**. Anything with the **[Mechanical]** tag that targets you with a **[Physical]** move takes a **-1 [Nerf]** as you cause them to bug out a bit.\r\n\r\n'),
('exorcise', 'EXORCISE', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Physical][Strife][Locked: Slayer]', 'The power of the Mother Grub compels thee, as does this chainsword I\'m using to tear you open! You have little hope in overpowering the undead with nothing but brawn; it comes down to technique and guile, both of which you have an excess of. When you want to hunt the wicked, roll **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: THE SLAYER HAS BECOME THE SLAIN! You take **2 [Psychic]** damage, and are exposed to the HAUNTING Affliction as your past victories come back to haunt you.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Curses— Ngh! You take **1 [Psychic]** damage as you berate yourself for such an amateur failure.\r\n\r\n**OK**: It\'s not too late to recover from this botched attempt! You gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: To the heart! You do **1 [Somatic]** **[Holy]** damage.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Mere armour won\'t stop your hallowed verses! You strike, and pray out loud; you do **2 [Somatic]** **[Holy]** damage, or 1 and give the target **2 [Drag]**. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: BACK TO HELL, FIEND! You do **3 [Somatic]** **[Holy]** damage, or 2 and give the target **3 [Drag]**.'),
('expandedHorizons', 'EXPANDED HORIZONS', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Passive]', 'By now, you\'ve probably spent your fair share of time mingling with other castes and learning there\'s more to life than just caves, love \'em or hate \'em. You can take any one **[Basic]** **[Open]** move from another caste or one from Hemoanon, so long as you\'ve got a very close friend of that group.'),
('expandedPerspective', 'EXPANDED PERSPECTIVE', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Passive]', 'You… want to learn more about others. You\'ve made friends, you\'ve gone on adventures, but you want to see what life is like for trolls that aren\'t you, you know? You can take any one **[Open]** move.'),
('expansassin', 'EXPANSASSIN', 'JADE', 'ADULT', '[Jade][Passive][Locked: Adult]', 'It takes a certain finesse to make wholesale slaughter look graceful. That\\\'s, evidently, something you\\\'ve turned out to be pretty good at! Your style of assassination is less \"stalk prey through the night\", and more \"talk to prey, flirt a little, stab them in the neck after you get what you want.\" Your first **[Strife]** roll is **[Legendary]** as you turn the tables on them and kill them! They thought you were a Diplomaster, waaaah! Optionally, you can forgo the **[Legendary]** and instead become **[Hidden]** on your first turn for **[Free]**. When you attack and remove **[Hidden]**, you deal +1 damage. Strike from the shadows!'),
('expeditedEngineering', 'EXPEDITED ENGINEERING', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Beekeeper]', 'BZZZZ CLICK CLICK CLICK! You\'re VERY good at building stuff on the move. Who needs time to make a working laptop when you\'ve got MAD SKILLS? You can make working items in no time on the fly. You can invest a number of **VP** up to your max into RAW MATERIALS. RAW MATERIALS can be converted to items from ELECTRIC ENTOMOLOGY or HONEYTECH on the fly, except these items cost **1 VP** less than normal (min. 1). Flexibility and reduced prices, all in one place!'),
('expensiveTastes', 'EXPENSIVE TASTES', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Passive][Locked: Posh]', 'Back on Earth, you had a very lavish lifestyle that you are particularly used to. And you don\'t see why that has to change because you\'re on some alien world now! If anything, you ought to lean into it further now. And you WILL! You have **12 VP** rather than 8; additionally, when you purchase a Fashion Item, you get a second one free. Hooray for old money!'),
('exploitAbility', 'EXPLOIT ABILITY', 'OTHER', 'KNIGHT', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Magic][Locked: Knight]', 'At some point in your life, it was easy to exploit you. Now you’re the one that’s vibing, in your element, and close to your aspect. Once you’ve achieved this state of self recognition and worth? You’re able to use what you’ve got to help others in a meaningful way. Depending on your aspect when you come under certain conditions,you gain the following bonuses for when you roll IN SHINING ARMOR & JOUSTING:\r\n\r\n> **TIME**: You roll these moves **[Talent]** while **[Quickened]** for up to 2 rounds for each instance of **[Quickened]**.\r\n\r\n> **SPACE**: When you roll a **GREAT+** result on a UNIVERSAL MOVE, you may gain a **[Hold]** to roll these moves with **[Talent]**. These **[Holds]** do not stack.\r\n\r\n> **LIFE**: For 1 round after using a **[Heal]** move on someone else, you roll these moves with **[Talent]**.\r\n\r\n> **DOOM**: While experiencing a **[Negative] [Emotion]**, you roll these moves with **[Talent]**. \r\n\r\n> **HOPE**: You roll these moves with **[Talent]** for up to 2 rounds after reducing you or an ally’s **[Drag]** by 2.\r\n\r\n> **RAGE**: You roll these moves with **[Talent]** while **[Out of Control]**.\r\n\r\n> **BREATH**: You roll these moves with **[Talent]** while you have less than 4 **[Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> **BLOOD**: You roll these moves with **[Talent]** for up to 2 rounds after giving an ally 2 **[Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **LIGHT**: While you have at least 4 **[Boost]**, you roll these moves with **[Talent]**.\r\n\r\n> **VOID**: While **[Hidden]**, you roll each move with **[Talent]**.\r\n\r\n> **HEART**: When you get a **GREAT+** result rolling with your highest stat you gain a **[Hold]** to roll these moves with **[Talent]**. These **[Holds]** do not stack.\r\n\r\n> **MIND**: When you get a **GREAT+** result rolling an **[Analyze]** move you gain a **[Hold]** to roll these moves with **[Talent]**. These **[Holds]** do not stack.\r\n'),
('expungeBaggage', 'EXPUNGE BAGGAGE', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Lengthy][One-Off][Heal][Psionic]', '4GH FUCK 3V3RY7H1NG HUR75 G00D L0RD FUCK 5H17 17 HUR75 FUUUUUCK— oogh! Okay… okay! You\'re good! You just had a lil too much going on. You\'ve learned to control your erratic vibes by psionically expelling negative energy out of you, allowing you to calm the fuck down sometimes. Using this move while you are FREAKING OUT ends the FREAKING OUT effect and **[Tiers Up]** even into a **MAX**, but you must have been FREAKING OUT for 3 turns to use this move in that case. When you want to get a grip, roll **+APP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Uh oh. Well. That\'s not good. You gain 4 random heightened negative **[Emotions]** and are exposed to PSIBURN. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: NGHHRFH— you gain 1 random heightened negative **[Emotion]**. Sorry.\r\n\r\n**OK**: HENHGH… try again? Reroll this move!\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: HMGHA! HAH… hah… that\'s a relief..! You can remove up to **2 [Drag]**, lower a **[Heightened]** emotion and/or **[Heal] 1 HP**. You then become **[Peaceful]**. Hahhh… much better.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: HNNAAAAAAH… BETTER. MUCH BETTER. WOW. You get a **GOOD**, but all numbers are increased by 1, you either lower 2 **[Heightened]** emotions or totally remove 1, and become **[Serene]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: HRRRURRRRHHHHHHNHGGGAAAA! Oh, wow, you\'re like, glowing now? Huh? You get a **GREAT** but increase all numbers by 1 again, and gain 2 random positive **[Heightened]** emotions!'),
('extensiveConnections', 'EXTENSIVE CONNECTIONS', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'You\'ve made a LOT of connections with people online. And not all of them are bad. Some **GOOD**, even! As such, you always know someone to reach out to do a thing for you. You can spend **1 LUX** to roll any **[Downtime]** roll (except MONEYMAKERY) as a **[Tech]** move. You can even do this for other people… if they pay you the **LUX** for it!'),
('extractLore', 'EXTRACT LORE', 'OTHER', 'SEER', '[Class][Advanced][One-Off][Magic][Manipulate][Mental][Locked: Seer]\r\n', 'You have a near supernatural ability to get people to spill their guts to you. Maybe it’s a well-worded, extremely specific question that somehow needles through their guard and prompts them to spill their life story to you. Maybe it’s the cosmic engine that metapowers your soul and allows people to do this kind of strange, mystic thing that can’t exactly be explained by logic. Maybe it’s magic. Maybe you’re just a master of weaponized obnoxiousness! But one way or another, you are able to ask people their life story. When you want to know someone’s life, roll **+GRA, +PSP** or **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Haha, peon. Now, tell me your life. Were you, too, abandoned as a grub by your caretakers, and- shit! You accidentally overshare and speak out YOUR life story! That wasn’t part of the plan! You take **3 [Drag]** as your opponent gains the effects of a **GOOD** EXTRACT LORE roll.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Your opponent gives you the middle finger. That wasn’t much to go off. You become **[Confused]** for **a turn**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Your words send a chill down your opponent’s spine as they begin to speak, and then catch themselves. What the hell..?\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Briefly, your opponent speaks, letting out a secret they wouldn’t tell someone under the current circumstances. You learn a fact that the target would not normally share; anything from “My lusus was highly neglectful and I learned to cook by starting fires in the woods to cope with that” to “I wet the recuperacoon \'till I was 6 sweeps old”. The target is **[Stunned]** as they speak.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: The gate opens, and you bleed your opponent dry for information. A continuous flow of lore flows from their mouth, and they are powerless to stop it. You get a more in-depth fact; a short story giving context to it, rather than a single sentence. The target is **[Slowed]** for **3 turns** as each turn they are forced to continue giving details and context, which is in itself a valuable tool.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: They tell you everything. The target is powerless to stop speaking, telling you more, and more, and more- until the opponent becomes **[Unconscious]**, ABSCONDS or removes the condition, they are **[Slowed]** as they keep giving you more and more details, piecing together their entire backstory and trauma for you over the course of the rest of the encounter. Troll Archivist lookin’ ass.\r\n\r\n'),
('extracurricularExemplary', 'EXTRACURRICULAR EXEMPLARY', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Student]', 'You have hobbies outside of your classes, honest! Here, just look! Select an extracurricular option from the list below.\r\n\r\n> **LUSUSRIDING**: You gain a new lusus, which you use exclusively for riding. This counts as a Small VEHICLE with 3 HORSEPOWER. You are **[Talented]** at VEHICULATE rolls with this lusus. If you already had the move MIGHTY MOUNT move, you gain a second lusus with a second list of abilities.\r\n\r\n> **LESSER SPORTS**: You don\'t go all out like those sweaty jocks, but you can definitely appreciate the thrill of the game. Especially the Studyheart Sportsball leagues! When in an encounter with more than 3 participants, you can\'t help but feel pumped up, and get a little **[Enraged]**!\r\n\r\n> **PARTYING**: YEAAAH, WOOHOO! The price to purchase HIGH QUALITY FUNJUNK is reduced to **1 VP**.\r\n\r\n> **JUMPING**: Found a list that said this is an extracurricular activity, so fuck it. Whenever you start **[Flying]** through STRONGJUMP or PCHOOOOOOO, you gain **1 [WHAM]**, I suppose.\r\n\r\n> **BULLYING**: Yeah, you love making people\'s lives hell. It\'s **GREAT**. You gain **1 [WHAM]** whenever you make someone feel a negative **[Emotion]**.\r\n\r\n> **YOGA**: You\'ve been really into finding your happy place lately. You can become **[Peaceful]** as an action.'),
('extrasensoryDialup', 'EXTRASENSORY DIAL-UP', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Passive][Psionic][Locked: Network]', 'Beeeeep-boop-boop-boop— hi there! Welcome to the Cloudmind!  Your deep connection to the internet allows you to telepathically link in others to the Cloudmind temporarily, giving them access to any Network tree moves even if they don\'t normally count as Psionic. Of course, this doesn\'t make them half as good as you; they only see a FRACTION of what you can. If you want it to hurt, you can, y\'know. DDOSIFICATE them.'),
('extrasensoryTricks', 'EXTRASENSORY TRICKS', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Chicanery][Psionic][Locked: Psychic]', 'Life at the bottom of the spectrum’s rough, even for the most powerful of psions. Sometimes, you’ve just gotta get creative... and you’ve found a ton of creative uses for your powers! Each individual EXTRASENSORY TRICKS option has **[Recharge: 2]** - have to keep your trickery fresh if you want to get away with it. When you want to trip your opponent up with your psionics, whether causing some ‘bad luck’ or just messing with their thinkpan, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Nnnnrgh… ah, fuck, you gave yourself a nosebleed! You become **[Bloodied]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Nothing happens. Dipshit. \r\n\r\n**OK**: Okay, they’re like, kinda brainfoggy, but it really didn’t help you out. They get 1 **[Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD: You pull a clever psionic trick of some kind - that’ll throw them off! Choose one of the following effects**:\r\n\r\n> **TELEWAVE**: You focus your psionics on the opponent’s thinkpan, giving them one killer headache and making them **[Confused]** for **2 turns**!\r\n\r\n> **ESPSIONAGE**: With a delicate touch of psionics, you unlock a door or move aside some obstacles, clearing a path! You or another target is no longer **[Trapped]** or **[Floorbound]**; you can use this option to narratively lock or unlock doors and windows from the inside, reach objects from afar, and other cool spy-psion moves.\r\n\r\n> **JINX**: You inflict some incidental ‘bad luck’ on your opponent, whether by literally jinxing them or just sweeping a leg with some well-placed telekinetics! Roll 1d8, and divide the result by 2 (rounded down):\r\n\r\n> 1. The target trips and becomes **[Floorbound]**.\r\n> 2. The target accidentally hurts themselves, and takes **1 [Drag]**.\r\n> 3. The target’s sylladex malfunctions, spitting out all of their items onto the floor. It takes an action to pick an item up, and you can do it too.\r\n> 4. The target farts or otherwise **[Embarrasses]** themself, and there’s not much more to say about that. This lasts **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **LEVITATE**: You YOINK an item from your opponent’s sylladex and wave it aloft, just out of reach! Better jump for it! A successful PCHOOOOO SWASHBUCKLE result’ll return the stolen possession to your opponent... until then, though, it can be used as in a TELEKINETIC STRIKE. When it is, the item takes **3 [Somatic]** damage from the force of the impact; if it’s still in one piece afterwards, the opponent can pick it up as an action like usual.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Oh, that went off without a hitch! You’re pretty good at this tricksy psion stuff. You get a **GOOD**, and give the target **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You’re a regular psi-phantom thief! They never saw it coming. You can take two **GOOD** effects instead of just one, or just one **GOOD** effect while also giving an opponent **2 [Drag]**.'),
('extremeCouponer', 'EXTREME COUPONER', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'Aha! After months of saving, you\'ve managed to save up for stuff you really want! Once a week, you can roll a d8. If you get a 7 or 8, you can purchase an item of up to **Rich** Wealth with a BIG BUY without using Treasure (**Ultrarich** if you have the DECENT WAGES move). You can instead choose an item you can normally afford anyway for **1 VP** less (min. 1) with this effect.'),
('facelessMinions', 'FACELESS MINIONS', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Boss]', 'What kinda boss doesn\'t have a workforce? You have a private army of GOON, who may do as you order them to. You can buy a GOON with **LUX**; **1 LUX** buys a level 1 NPC, **2 LUX** buys a level 2 one, and **3 LUX** buys a level 3 one. You can have an infinite amount of GOONs, but when one is killed, they\'re dead forever. You can give GOONs the following jobs; they will do the listed commands their turns. You can order them to follow you, or stay somewhere until you call upon them.\r\n\r\n> **GUARD**: The GOON patrols an area. If an opponent approaches, the highest level GUARD automatically rolls PROBLEM SLEUTHING, +1 for every other GUARD present. If they get a **GREAT**, they alert you immediately, and will roll to GRIEF on turns afterwards. If there are at least 8 GUARDS present, they form an ANGRY MOB **[Hazard]**.\r\n\r\n> **CHAUFFEUR**: The GOON will drive a vehicle for you, even bringing one to an encounter. The CHAUFFEUR is always **[Talented]** at VEHICULATE. While you have a Chauffeur, all VEHICLE upgrades cost **1 LUX** less.\r\n\r\n> **SPIES**: The GOON attempts to break into an area unnoticed, steal an item or information, and leave. It may roll SWASHBUCKLE to YOUTH ROLL into an area, SHENNANIGANS to YOINK an item or PROBLEM SLEUTHING to learn information, and then ACT FAST to ABSCOND, all with a single **[Downtime]** roll. If it fails any of these, the SPY is captured, and the captor decides what to do.\r\n\r\n> **HENCHMEN**: These GOONS cheer you on in combat, using their turn to use WORDPLAY to cheer you on. You may command them to GRIEF instead, but you may not **[Strife]** while they do. They get **1 action** a turn.\r\n\r\n> **DRUDGE**: Labourers, workers, grunts. The highest level DRUDGE rolls MONEYMAKERY using your wealth once per week for you, +1 for every DRUDGE you employ. This does not take you a **[Downtime]** action.'),
('faceTheMusic', 'FACE THE MUSIC', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Open][Recharge: 2][Manipulate]', 'For so long, you\'ve avoided taking any and all consequences, no matter what. You\'re learning though that maybe, sometimes it\'s better to face your mistakes head on and not look away. Hell, maybe even take the blame for someone else getting in trouble, like a friend of yours revealing that they\'re Cullbait or something. When you want to put yourself in harm\'s way to avoid others getting rocked, roll **+GRA**.\n\n**MIN**: OH NO! A SEAGOAT APPEARS! SOMEHOW! It\'s hostile to everyone present, you especially.\n\n**BAD**: They don\'t really give a shit. Sorry.\n\n**OK**: Ummm… keep talking? You can roll this move again on your next action. Maybe it\'ll work then!\n\n**GOOD**: Hey! If you\'re gonna hit anyone… hit ME! All targets can only target you next turn, even if they normally could not due to TEAM STRIFE positioning. This doesn\'t let Standby Trolls **[Strife]** you. \n\n**GREAT**: Whoa… they really think you\'re a piece of shit. That\'s great! You get a **GOOD**, but your targets can\'t even aid each other! They\'re so full of distaste for you! \n\n**MAX**: Their fury… SCREWS EM OVER! You get a **GREAT**, but all roll against you are **[Inept]** as you stand there and take it unflinchingly!'),
('fadeAway', 'FADE AWAY', 'VOID', 'VOID', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Void]', 'Sometimes, it feels like nobody cares enough to come looking for you when you’re missing. You feel like a stranger even among friends, and if you vanished… would anyone realize? People’s PROBLEM SLEUTHING rolls to spot you when you’re **[Hidden]** gain the following effects instead of the usual ones:\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: They get the sense you might be nearby, but aren’t sure. They can use **[Physical]** or **[Strife]** rolls on you, but they all take a **-2 [Nerf]** as you\'re still a little indistinct.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: They don’t see you, but get a sense of your general whereabouts. They can use **[Physical]** or **[Strife]** rolls on you, but they all take a **-1 [Nerf]** as you\'re still a little indistinct. This still excludes **[Verbal]** **[Strife]**s, as in the normal **[Hidden]** description.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Oh, finally! There you are. They dispel the **[Hidden]** condition and gain **2 [Boost]** from the satisfaction of finally spotting you.'),
('fanbaseCelebrity', 'FANBASE CELEBRITY', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Fanyatic]', 'You did it! You\'re a niche online microcelebrity, and EVERYONE loves you! Life can\'t get better than this! You gain access to HERO MODE through your RESPLENDENT RASCALITY. On top of that, you can spend a **[Lengthy]** **[Tech]** action to summon a FLASHCON to your location. This acts as a STAMPEDE **[Hazard]**, except rather than lusii, you summon a FUCKTONNE of rabid fans who charge through and run around, setting up a huge convention. Once the **[Hazard]** has ended, the following rules become true: \r\n\r\n> **SILLY ATMOSPHERE**: If you don\'t blend in, you\'ll look like a freak! As such, all trolls lose their original **[Talent]** to become **[Talented]** at **+RAS**.\r\n\r\n> **MERCH**: All participants in the encounter can purchase items on the fly from vendors. Nobody can buy the same item as something someone else has already purchased. Out of stock!\r\n\r\n> **COSPLAY CONTEST**: Any targets who were damaged by the STAMPEDE find themselves in a randomly selected FASHION COLLECTION. How did that happen..? They don\'t get to keep it after the encounter.\r\n\r\n> **PANELS**: There\'s lots of experts here you can ask for help! All PROBLEM SLEUTHING rolls are **[Tiered Up]** if they\'re made **[Lengthy]**.\r\n\r\n> **PUBLIC SETTING**: Everyone can see you now; if you were gonna do something fucked up, maybe reconsider!\r\n\r\n> **BALLPIT**: There\'s a BALLPIT. Standing in it gives you great power, but there\'s only room for one person. If you\'re standing in the BALLPIT, all rolls take a **+2 [Buff]**, but you can\'t make **[Physical]** rolls that may require movement without giving up your spot. Being knocked **[Floorbound]** removes you from the BALLPIT.'),
('fandomCat', 'FANDOM CAT', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Passive][Chicanery][Unlock: Fanyatic]', 'Oh my gawsh! I like your shoelaces! Did you get them from Her Imperious Condescension? Heheh! You\'re a freaking fanyatic, a proud warrior for fandoms everywhere! From consuming content and making fanwork (WHICH IS TOTALLY COOL AND AWESOME BY THE WAY, JUST SAYING) to cosplay to shipping wars to insatiable drama to the funniest Grumblr hellposts! You love fandom so much! You are **[Talented]** at **+RAS**. You gain access to the following SHENANIGANS effects.\r\n\r\n> **FEELING SO ATTACKED RIGHT NOW**: You just came out to have a good time, too! You make the target feel **[Sad]** with guilt for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **CONDYPOCALYPSE**: HAHAHA! YOU PLASTERED CONDY\'S FACE EVERYWHERE! PEAK COMEDY! All trolls on the field who attempt to use an item for the next 3 turns must roll 1d8; on a 1, they pull out some Condy masks or other garbage with her face on it you threw everywhere.\r\n\r\n> **HNNNNNG**: TOO… CUTE! HNNNNG! You make a show of thinking the target is CUUUUUTE as can be! They\'re such a cinnamon roll! You **[Stress]** the target for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **I CAN\'T EVEN**: You\'ve got too many feels! You flap your hands and exaggerate your emotions; your opponent can\'t make a **[Chicanery]** roll against you next turn as they pause like \"what… is happening..?\" \r\n\r\n> **FIGHT ME!!!**: Hold my flower! Grumblr taught me how to hide a body!! Your opponent can only make **[Strife]** rolls against you next turn, or only target you with rolls in a group strife.\r\n\r\n> **THE DISCOURSE**: LISTEN UP, SLURRY-SLORE. I BET A MILLION CAEGARS YOU DON\'T KNOW A THING ABOUT FISHING BOAT PROCEEDS, BUT IT\'S A SERIOUS ISSUE AND YOU SHOULDN\'T MAKE FUN OF IT. All people on the field become **[Out-Of-Control]** for **3 turns**, but can only make JAB rolls to **[Strife]**. Everyone becomes **[Talented]** at WORDPLAY. This is a **[One-Off]**.'),
('fangirlOfTheNight', 'FANGIRL OF THE NIGHT', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Jades are unfairly stereotyped as being Rainbow Drinker crazy in the media. It’s a little unflattering; while all Rainbow Drinkers are jade, the opposite is not true! Even if you really, really wish it was. Okay, fine, you admit it. You love Rainbow Drinkers, and wish you could be one. You gain access to one move from the Rainbow Drinker list (except for VESTAL VAMPYR or LESFERATU), even though you are not one; you just like to roleplay sometimes, and you’ve got a tonne of cosplay and combat materials that would let you replicate these moves! Unfortunately, it sucks compared to the real thing. You do not gain the **[Eerie]** or **[Cullbait]** tags. You cannot take this move if you are a Rainbow Drinker, and automatically retrain out of it if you become one whilst having this move. Actually drinking blood makes you **[Disgusted]**, but also makes you **[Enthusiastic]** because… hey, it\'s kinda cool, right?'),
('farApart', 'FAR APART', 'VOID', 'VOID', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Coping, Not Coping!][Locked: Void]', 'Sometimes, it’s like there’s… a wall between you and everyone else around you that keeps them distant from you. Whether it’s one you’ve built yourself with your habits and mannerisms, or one you simply have to live with like your place in society, you’re a naturally distant person, and sometimes it’s very hard to know what to make of you. All **[Analyze]** rolls against you take a **-2 [Nerf]**.'),
('fashionFauxPas', 'FASHION FAUX PAS', 'OTHER', 'HAUTE_CLAWTURE', '[Template][Basic][One-Off][Locked: Haute Clawture]', 'What is your opponent wearing? No. Nope. Nuh-uh. Not on your watch. That horrendous thing is SO out of style, it would make you laugh if you weren’t physically repulsed. As a **[One-Off]**, you can remove one piece of the target’s **[Equipment]** and gain **+1 WHAM**.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('fashionStatement', 'FASHION STATEMENT', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Passive][Locked: Subcultist]', 'Nobody can pull off a look as well as you can. I\'m serious, certain fashion combos just literally do not work on others. All fashion items cost half as much as normal. You gain access to the following exclusive fashion collections depending on your subculture.\r\n\r\n**Scene**: THE MIS-EN-SCENE (SCENE HAIR, GRAPHICALLY VIOLENT TEE, JJEANS, or ETHEREAL TINKERBULL DRESS, HEAVY MAKEUP) **[+2 RAS, +2 IMG, -1 GRT, -1 HUB, -1 PSP, -APP]** You definitely don\'t take yourself seriously, but that\'s okay! Yaaay, glittergore! When you gain an emotion, you may roll 1d8; on a 1-4, the emotion is **[Heightened]**. On a 5-8, you get the emotion\'s opposite. \r\n\r\n**Decora**: THE CUTEST SHIT YOU\'VE EVER SEEN (LIL BEANIE, GRAPHICALLY VIOLENT TEE, ACCESSORY OVERLOAD, JJORTS, or ETHEREAL FAIRY BULL DRESS) **[+2 PLC, +2 IMG, -1 GRT, -1 HUB, -1 APP, -1 PSP]** You are so cute it\'s unreal. God fucking damn. When a troll wants to roll LET\'S STRIFE to beat you up, you can choose to make them roll 1d8 at the start; on a 6+, they are **[Charmed]** by you.\r\n\r\n**Lolita: PRIM AND PROPER GARB (STATELY WEAR and any three of the following**: BIG OL\' BOW, BOOTIFUL BOOTS, UMBRELLAKIND Strife Specibus, MOONHAT, FASHIONABLE BAG, HAIR EXTENSIONS) **[+2 GRA, +1 PLC, +1 HUB, -2 APP, -2 RAS]** You are beyond unflappable. You just have this look to you that… flaps the beholder back. When you would gain a negative **[Emotion]**, roll 1d8. On a 7 or 8, the person who would give it to you gains it themselves instead.\r\n\r\n**Cybergoth**: INDUSTRIAL FUCKSTORM (CYBERGOTH HEADGEAR, FINGERLESS STRANGLERS, BOOTIFUL BOOTS, SEADWELLER NETS) **[+2 APP, +1 HUB, +1 RAS, -2 PSP, -2 GRA]** You could easily be mistaken for a bodymodding gold, but no— you\'re here to RAAAAAVE! You use **+APP** to FRAYMOTIF, and the **[Build-Up]** is reduced to 0. On a successful FRAYMOTIF, opponents are **[Blinded]** for a turn.\r\n\r\n**Metalhead**: MOSHPIT BRAWLKIT (METALHEAD TEE, JJEANS, FINGERLESS STRANGLERS, BRACE-4-BRACELETS) **[+2 GRT, +2 APP, -2 PSP, -1 RAS, -1 PLC]** Y\'know, metalheads are actually usually pretty chill, so the stereotype about them being modern barbarians is innaccuraaAAAAAAAAAAARGHHHH. You can become **[Enraged]** for **[Free]** when you first take more than 1 damage in a turn, and you have 2 extra HP, even though **+APP** from fashion items doesn\'t usually do that.\r\n\r\n**Punk**: TRUE PUNKASS BITCHWEAR (PUNKASS DEATHHAWK, LUSUSLEATHER COAT, GRAPHICALLY VIOLENT TEE, JJEANS or SEADWELLER NETS) **[+2 HUB, +2 GRT, -2 PLC, -2 PSP]** You\'re no poser! This is what REAL punk looks like! You do +1 damage against robots and items, and trolls wearing the PUNKASS BITCHWEAR collection immediately feel **[Embarrassed]** around you because of how much of a poser they are.\r\n\r\n**Goth**: HAUNTING PROFANE (BLASPHEMOUS PENDENT, HEAVY MAKEUP, BOOTIFUL BOOTS, NIGHTMAREWEAR) **[+2 PSP, +1 GRA, +1 IMG, -2 RAS, -1 GRT, -1 APP]** You are the bitch cloistered jades tell horror stories about. Cloistered Jades, Juggalos, and Orthodox Decompositionists feel **[Dread]** around you, and you feel **[Peaceful]** around them.\r\n\r\n**Alt**: ONE HELL OF A LOOK (ALTFASHION PIECE and 3 other Fashion Items) **[+2 IMG, +2X, -2Y or -1 Y and -1 Z]** Wow! That\'s a fashion collection you\'ve got going! You gain the collection effect of one other collection from this move.'),
('fastForward', 'FAST FORWARD', 'TIME', 'TIME', '[Aspect][Basic][Buildup: 3][Locked: Time]', 'You don’t have all day here, guy. Whether the encounter you’re in is a waste of time, or whether you’re just trying to get to the end of the story, you know how to fight quickly and without hesitation. To hell with the consequences- you’re getting through this, and you’re getting through it fast, whether you win or not. When you use this move, everyone on the field does **1 extra damage** on **[Strife]** moves and gains an extra action for the rest of the encounter. This effect stacks with **[Quickened]**.'),
('fateUnchanged', 'FATE UNCHANGED', 'OTHER', 'MAGE', '[Class][Basic][Reaction][One-off][Locked: Mage]', 'Absolutely not. No. How dare they come into your hive, onto your court, and try to play ball like they have any idea what they\'re doing? This isn’t right! This isn’t what you’re meant to be doing! When someone tries to **[Manipulate]** you, even using a **[Control]** move, your naturally set-in-its-ways mind recoils and stands its ground, fighting back with all it has. If the **[Manipulate]** move is not a rolled move, flip a coin. On a 1 or ‘heads’ the move simply does not take. On a 2 it works as normal. Otherwise, when you want to stare someone down and tell them to fuck off with their shitty suggestions roll **+HUB**. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: You... do what they say. Maybe they\'re right, or maybe you just don\'t care anymore, no one ever listens anyway. Their move **[Tiers Up]**, even to a **MAX**. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: You\'re stubborn, but also you\'re tired. Nothing changes, as usual. \r\n\r\n**OK**: You can\'t be serious... really? They get a -1 **[Nerf]** to their roll. \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You apply every backtalk strategy housed in your considerable mental library of them, and their move is made at a -2 **[Nerf]**. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You grit your teeth, stare them down and go kicking and screaming. Their move **[Tiers Down]**, and if they still succeed, any future moves you make to resist **[Manipulation]** by them **[Tier Up]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Fuck. Off. You spit in their eye, metaphorically or literally, whatever you want, I don\'t own you, no one owns you, especially not this IDIOT. You entirely throw off their attempts to **[Manipulate]** and cannot be **[Manipulated]** by this person ever again without them rolling a **MAX** to do so.\r\n\r\n'),
('faunaflora', 'FAUNAFLORA', 'OTHER', 'HORTICULLTURIST', '[Template][Basic][Downtime][Locked: Horticullturist]', 'Yes… YES! IT\'S ALIVE! You’ve done the most idiotic thing a plant breeder could do, and bred a plant with a lusus. Why did you do that..? You just watched a plant swallow up a lusus, and spit it out and also spit out a weird plant lusus hybrid, and your first thought was “aw jeez I better tame it”. What the fuck..? When you… want to do that..? Roll **+PSP**?\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Hi Prizeberry Plant! Please, approach me! Help me make a cool plant hybrid for my next battle- **[NOISES OF TERRIBLE, INDESCRIBABLE AGONY]**. You start your next **[Strife]** with **-2 HP**. If this fight involves a plant monster, you feel **[Dread]** as your past experience comes back to haunt you. No… NO..!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You spend your whole night sitting in the woods looking like a freak. At least you didn\'t die…?\r\n\r\n**OK**: The horrible plant lusus (plusus?) died. But at least it’s tasty, and you can sell it! You make **1 LUX**, I guess?\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Okay, well. You tamed it. Big whoop..? You get a **GOOD** **[Hold]** for the results of the Bronze Summoner move, XENODRUID, except that your monster is also a Plant. As such, it takes **1 extra damage** when hit by Fire **[Energy]** attacks, but becomes **[Quickened]** when the target is **[Bloodied]**. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: As a **GOOD**, but with a **GREAT** **[Hold]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: As a **GOOD**, but with a **MAX** **[Hold]**!'),
('favoredFiend', 'FAVORED FIEND', 'OTHER', 'CTHONOMANCER', '[Template][Ultra][Passive][Last Stand][Magic][Locked: Cthonomancer]', 'You’ve sacrificed trolls. You’ve done rituals in the scorching light. You know the chants. You’ve seen the gaps between the shapes that allow you to understand where in the sky They are. You have proven yourself. You must have. You must have! You haven’t come this far for nothing! At long last the Horrorterrors have noticed you, and you can feel their presence at all times. It’s not as comforting as you expected, almost… predatory. But your powers have grown to levels unforeseen nevertheless. \r\n\r\nYou are **[Talented]** in **[Magic]** as you finally master the most dangerous arts, and **[Drag]** taken from WARPSTORM is reduced by 1, to 0 if possible. The effects of DARK MAGICKS grow in severity, allowing **[Boost]** gained to be reduced to 0, and expanding the moves it can be applied to into all rolls as Something takes an active interest in your life. Should you fall in battle now, the dark forces you have welcomed into your mind will seize control and revive you at 4 HP, temporarily gaining the GONE GRIMDARK and TENDRILS Grimdark moves. Should you face a HEROIC or JUST Death regardless, a dark mimicry of yourself will rise as an Ambient Grimdark soon after, becoming a Ghost regardless of caste and maintaining this Template alongside it. Rather than immunity, the Entry only grants you 1 [Somatic] [Resistance]; on the other hand, you only have 1 [Weakness] to [Holy] and [Freaky] damage. You\'re not a real ghost, after all, just a semiphysical shadow clinging to life.\r\n'),
('fearless', 'FEARLESS', 'RAGE', 'RAGE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Rage]', 'You aren’t an easy one to scare; you’re so dead-set on your goals that fear is alien to you! You become immune to the **[Scared]** and **[Dread]** conditions altogether; when you would feel them, you can instead choose to be **[Hopeful]** as you clutch to your determination and refuse to back down from your convictions.'),
('feedOnFear', 'FEED ON FEAR', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Passive][Psionic][Locked: Haunted]', 'NOM… NOM… NOM… delicious soul energy! You fucking love eating ghosts! When you need a little pick-you-up, the terror in the hearts of others sustains you. When you grab someone\'s face and scream in it, you can suck in their panicked screaming response and feel much better. You can remove the **[Scared]** condition from others as an action, **[Healing]** yourself **1 HP** or giving you **2 [Boost]**. The **[Terrified]** condition restores you **2 HP** or gives you **3 [Boost]**. Yummy~ When you use POLTERIFICATE on a ghost, you may activate this move too, doing **1 damage** less on a **GREAT**/**MAX** to **[Heal]** yourself **1/2 HP**.'),
('felineFriends', 'FELINE FRIENDS', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Passive]', 'There\'s a reason that Olivebloods are so associated with cats— the majority of lusii with the same blood colour as you are felines! From mighty BOULDERTIGERS to meek FUZZORBS, most Olives are raised by cats, and adopt mannerisms according to the type that raised them. You are always **[Talented]** at ALTRICIALIZE rolls (see Chapter 11: Custodians). Select one of the following effects.\r\n\r\n> **CARACAL**: With pointy, tufted ears and VERY powerful legs, lusii like the SNARLCAL or SWERVAL can jump like, a bajillion feet in the air. And so can you! You have a **-1 [Nerf]** to hit **[Flying]** targets instead of an **[Ineptitude]**, cuz you\'ve learned how to jump VERY high.\r\n\r\n> **FELIS**: A kitty cat! Oooooogh! You\'ve got a lil domesticated cat lusus, like a NIGHTPURR or a FUZZORB. So cute! So CUTE! You gain the following WORDPLAY effect… \r\n\r\n> **KITTY CAT EYES**: Your eyes water and sparkle, **[Charming]** the target for 2 rounds on a **GOOD**, 3 rounds on a **GREAT** and **[Fascinating]** for **3 rounds** on a **MAX**.\r\n\r\n> **LEOPARDUS**: Small, spotted jungle cats like the AWECELOT or the MARSLAY (but ironically, no leopards, those are panthera) raised you. SPOT rolls against you are always **[Tiered Down]**, you\'re just too sneaky!\r\n\r\n> **LYNX**: These shaggy furred mountain cats like the SLYNX or the HOBCAT are the unquestioned kings of cold climates. You are immune to the SNOWSTORM **[Hazard]**, and take **1 less damage** (min. 0) from attacks that deal **[Frost]** damage.\r\n\r\n> **PANTHERA**: Sleek! Fast! Mighty! The KINGS of cats. Your lusus is a CAVERNLION, a PURRBEAST or some other predatory big cat. You can roll **[Strife]** rolls twice in the same turn, but your second one is **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n> **PUMA**: ZOOOOOOM! You were raised by the fastest cats, such as SKREETAHS or BOULDERTIGERS. Whenever you roll LET\'S STRIFE, your opponents LET\'S STRIFE rolls on the same turn are **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n> **FURBAIT**: Your lusus is bipedal and muscular as fuck! Wow! They must give great hugs, and it isn\'t weird for this wholeass man to sleep in your recupracoon with you. It just isn\'t! Opponents **[Analyze]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**, because as soon as they figure out your lusus is something like a INCINERAWR or a BARACAT they get kinda weirded out..?\r\n\r\n> **NOT A CAT**: What the fuck! Your lusus, somehow, isn\'t feline. What is this, a crocodile? Fucking bullshit. The Cavern Jades gave you a real stinker. You gain the CUSTODIAN COMPANION Perfectly Generic Move, but your lusus gets 6 **[Features]**, not 4.'),
('fiduspawnMaster', 'FIDUSPAWN MASTER', 'OTHER', 'FIDUSSPAWNER', '[Template][Ultra][One-off][Locked: Fiduspawner]', 'Whoooaoaoaaoaoo! You’re unbeatable! Guitar riff! You did it. You made it. You turned your hat backwards so many times. You’ve defeated a bunch of guys in shorts. You’ve stolen so many animals. You’re the best, like no one ever was. And you have the most powerful Fiduspawn to show for it. As a **[Free]** action, when you summon a Fiduspawn or captured monster, you can push it beyond its limits, allowing it to temporarily evolve one more time. Your Fiduspawn grows beyond GIANT, and slightly alters its form. In this state, you and your monster’s HP increases by 2, and gets a +1 to all stats, which stacks with the normal stat arrays, as well as gaining a third temporary TYPE from the type list above. This can be used on captured monsters as well. This effect lasts for the duration of the encounter, or until you’re knocked out. None of this changes the name of your monster- It’s still the same ferocious fire dragon under there! Just now he’s bigger! Awwww.'),
('fightDirty', 'FIGHT DIRTY', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'Living life at the bottom of society has taught you lots. Mostly, the exact right way to get out of a situation, and how to do it without being culled. And you’re willing to do pretty much whatever japery it takes to keep you alive. You get the following SHENANIGANS effects:\r\n\r\n> **BITE**: CHOMP. You bite that motherfucker! Your target takes **2 [Drag]** now, and 1 more for every turn until they successfully make a YOUTH ROLL SWASHBUCKLE move to shake you off. If they were **[Flying]**, so are you.\r\n\r\n> **CHEAP TRICK**: POCKET SAND! Yeah, it’s dirty, but it works! You **[Blind]** the opponent for a turn.\r\n\r\n> **DUMPSTER BOMB**: You kick up a cloud of trash and junk, obscuring you in garbage fog. Everyone in the area becomes **[Hidden]**. \r\n\r\n> **VANDALISM**: Hah! Hah! Wham! You kick the fender off a scuttlebuggy, or something! The opponent is briefly distracted; if they don’t spend an action fixing the damage you just did (for shame!), they lose ALL their **[Boost]** as it weighs on their conscience. If they had no **[Boost]**, they take **2 [Drag]**.'),
('fightForYourHonour', 'FIGHT FOR YOUR HONOUR', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Open][Last Stand]', 'When the going gets tough… a fire lights up inside of you. If you lose here, that means you\'re letting your legacy be tarnished. What would your descendents think? No way! You\'re a champ! You\'re a warrior! You\'re an INDIGO! When you first hit **3 HP** or lower, you can choose to enter a BLAZE OF GLORY, becoming **[Out of Control]** or **[Hyperfocused]** (your choice) and **[Exhausted]**. You need to defend your title, no matter the cost!'),
('fightTheCurse', 'FIGHT THE CURSE!', 'OTHER', 'MOONBARK', '[Template][Advanced][Reaction][Eerie][Mental][Physical][Locked: Moonbark]', 'Ngh- not now, dark magic in your blood! This is an EXTREMELY inconvenient time to beast out! With practice, you\'ve been able to push back against your curse and keep yourself from hulking out. When you want to stop yourself from being forced to MOONFRENZY, roll **+GRA**. If you were already in MOONBARK mode, this move is **[Tiered Down]**.\n\n**MIN**: KILL KILL EAT KILL MURDER KILL EAT DIE KILL. You beast out so, so bad. You activate MOONFRENZY, and are **[Quickened]**. If you have allies nearby, you attack them first.\n\n**BAD**: GRRR BARK BARK BARK.\n\n**OK**: You slow the transformation… but you don\'t stop it. At the end of your next turn, you enter MOONFRENZY. Uh oh!\n\n**GOOD**: Hrnnnhhh- and swallow it. Okay. You\'re good. You don\'t activate MOONFRENZY now, but next time you take damage, you do. You\'ll need to roll this move again!\n\n**GREAT**: Stop the curse in its tracks! You deactivate MOONFRENZY entirely.\n\n**MAX**: Not only do you stop the curse… you control it! You deactivate MOONFRENZY, but you become **[Talented]** in **+GRT** anyway.'),
('finalBoss', 'FINAL BOSS', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Ultra][One-Off][Locked: Boss]', 'You are a force to be reckoned with; a true, looming boss battle! NOBODY fucks with you or your MASSIVE statblock. You\'ve worked hard, you\'ve built a name for yourself, you live in a castle or a dungeon or whatever… and you know how to KICK ASS. You gain access to HERO MODE through your MYTHIC MANGRIT, and are **Ultrarich**. As an action, you can enter BOSS MODE. While in BOSS MODE, you become **[Slowed]** and lose any talent to **[Strife]** rolls. In exchange, your HP increases by 5, and any damage you do is increased by 1. Your HP and damage increases by an additional +1 for every enemy present beyond the first, but you only begin benefiting from this bonus if your enemies outnumber you and your opponents. For instance, in a 2v2, you do not benefit, but in a 2v3, you benefit once. When you make a **[Strife]** roll, your attacks can hit up to 3 targets in one roll, or only 2 if you have allies. GOONS do not count as allies for this effect. You probably get like, cool fucking boss music too, which intimidates the hell out of the opponent; anyone around you while you are in BOSS MODE is **[Scared]**. Your enemies cannot activate HERO MODE against you, and you can use HERO MODE every **3 turns**. Once you activate BOSS MODE, you can’t turn it off, and you forfeit the use of all **[Last Stand]** moves, so choose when you use it wisely!'),
('finalDestination', 'FINAL DESTINATION', 'DOOM', 'DOOM', '[Aspect][Ultra][Recharge: 3][Locked: Doom]', 'You finally understand the truest strength of the Doom aspect of your personality; you are destined to suffer, and you are destined to succeed. If there were only darkness, you wouldn\'t be pushing so hard towards the light! Bad things happen just as often as good, yes, which means good things happen. You don’t need to let the bad rule your life. The truth is… fortune and misfortune are kind of the same thing? What’s unlucky for one person is lucky for someone else. By understanding that everything is balanced, not simply stacked against you, you’ve finally realized your place in the world. And with this understanding... sometimes you can give fate a little nudge. All your **BAD** rolls are **[Tiered Down]** to **MIN**, and all your **GREAT** rolls are **[Tiered Up]** to **MAX**. The same is true of your opponents in any given encounter. This effect has the **[Recharge: 3]** tag for both of you; after you gain a **MIN** or a **MAX** in this way, the effect is suppressed for 3 rounds. Whenever you get a **MIN** roll, you gain a **[Hold]** that lets you forgo rolling a move and receive a **MAX** result; whenever the opponent gains a **MAX** roll, you gain a Hold that lets you turn one of their rolls into a **MIN** result. You can stockpile as many of these **[Holds]** as you like, but using them does deal **2 damage** to you as reality whiplashes against your prodding.'),
('finalGambit', 'FINAL GAMBIT', 'OTHER', 'FIDUSSPAWNER', '[Template][Advanced][One-Off][Last Stand][Locked: Fiduspawner]', 'Beep beep. Beep beep. Beep beep. Hear that? That’s you being on your last legs because you’re getting your ass handed to you. Luckily, you have an ace in the hole. A move so strong it was banned from tournaments all across the planet. You guessed it. \r\nIt’s… EXPLOSION!!! Everyone dies. Okay, okay, just kidding. But you do have a powerful move in your back pocket! When you and your Fiduspawn drop below 1/8 HP, you can use this as a last resort. This move can be used with captured lusii. If the ability you select here matches with either TYPE your Fiduspawn has, you gain a +1 [Buff] to roll this move.  When you want to ruin lives, roll +IMG.\r\nMIN: Wow. You really do explode. Your Fiduspawn blows up. I don’t know what to tell you, man. Everyone in the encounter takes 4 [Unblockable][Somatic] damage, and your monster is unusable for the rest of the encounter, if you wouldn’t already be knocked out. Be lucky you aren’t also unusable now.\r\nBAD: You do a cool pose and everything and… You just kind of stand there looking like an idiot! Nothing happens.\r\nOK: You shout out the name of your finisher, and while it doesn’t actually do anything cool, you sure do feel rad as hell. You gain 1 [Boost]!\r\nGOOD: You call out your monster\'s name, it responds with a digitized mess of sounds. Oh yeah. This is it. Choose one effect from the list below when you take this move; That\'s the special move you have access to now.\r\nBULK UP BEATDOWN: Your monster flexes its muscles, and then just beats the shit out of someone. You deal 2 [Somatic] damage, and gain 1 [WHAM]. \r\nPSYCHIC SCREECH: SKRREEE!! You warp the opponent’s mind. They become [Confused] for 2 rounds and take 1 [Psychic] damage. \r\nSCORCHING SUNBURST: You sort of do explode! But in a good way. You release a blast of flame that can hit multiple targets! If the target fails a GOOD or higher LET’S STRIFE roll, they\'ll take 1 [Somatic] damage every round for 2 rounds. Otherwise, they dodge out of the way!\r\nFLASH FREEZE FREEZE DRY: Brrr! That\'s cold! There\'s a flash of white and suddenly everythings covered in icicles or something. This can hit multiple targets. Your target becomes [Slowed] for 2 rounds, and you gain 1 [Boost] every round this is active. \r\nMUNDANE MUTTERANCE: It’s honestly kind of… You aren’t sure. Creepy? Cute? Exciting? How normal this thing is. Choose 1 [Base] Emotion. This is now what your target is feeling at this moment. You can target yourself with this.\r\nGAILFORCE GRAVITY: Your monster lifts the opponent into the air, causing them to begin [Flying] for 1 round, before being dropped. They take 2 [Somatic] damage and become [Floorbound].\r\nVOLATILE VOLTSHOCK: The sky crackles with thunder and lightning strikes the area. This is your element. Your opponent becomes [Stunned] for 1 round, while you become [Quickened] for the same amount of time.\r\nLASER LIGHTSHOW: Pew pew! Wow! It’d almost be super pretty if it wasn’t so eye meltingly bright. Your target becomes [Blinded] for 1 round, and takes 1 [Somatic] damage from the blast.\r\nTOXIC TAKEDOWN: Uh oh… You don\'t feel so good. What was in that tea? You release an onslaught of [Poison] at your target, as well as giving them an immediate 2 [Drag].\r\nHAUNTING HARBINGER: A thick fog emanates from your monster. It’s enough to land your opponents 1 [Drag], and then [Terrifying] them, because g-g-g-g-ghosts! This can affect multiple targets.\r\nMAKE BELIEVE MAYHEM: Awwww, look at all the pixies! Is that a tinkerbull? AAAWW!! Aw- Aw shit. Oh no. Oh god. You lure your opponent into a false sense of security, before showing them how scary fae creatures really are. Roll 1d18, which corresponds with this list. Whatever you roll is the ability you use instead.\r\nDARKNESS DESOLATION: The shadows around you grow thicker and darker, enveloping you in darkness. You go [Hidden], and your opponent gains a -1 [Nerf] when trying to find you.\r\nTECHNO TAKEOVER: What\'s better than summoning monsters? Having your monsters summon things as well. Your monster hacks into some nearby inventors closet, summoning a LEVEL 1 ROBOT NPC to fight alongside you! It has its own turn, and only 3 HP, but it acts immediately after you in initiative. You\'re the minions master. \r\nFLORAL FRENZY: Your Fiduspawn digs its roots deeper into the soul, while simultaneously wrapping them around your opponent. You [Heal] 1 HP, while your target takes 1 [Psychic] damage from the energy drain. \r\nROCKSLIDE RECKONING: My god is that an earthquake? Where’d that mountain come from? Your opponents fall [Floorbound] and take 1 [Somatic] damage until they get up. \r\nDRACONIC DESTRUCTION: Your monster beats its powerful wings, or swings a hefty tail! All [Physical] moves targeting you take a -2 [Nerf] for 1 round as they just can\'t make it through. This can affect multiple targets. \r\nSICKENING SWARM: The familiar sound of a swarm of locusts fills the air. Ah, the imminent droning of death. You summon a BEE SWARM [Hazard] that doesn’t target you.\r\nOCEANIC OVERTURE: Your Fiduspawn summons a titanic wave of water, and just fucking drowns everyone. Yeah. You activate the FLOOD [Hazard], which affects everyone except you. This includes allies.\r\nGREAT: AAAHHHH!! You both get really into it! You’re in sync. There’s no way you can lose! All numerical values from the GOOD result increase by 1, and you gain 1 [Boost]. For SICKENING SWARM, you increase damage by 1. For OCEANIC OVERTURE you simply deal 1 [Somatic] damage upon activation.\r\nMAX: You ever stop and think about how having these monsters that control the fundamentals of the world could lead to catastrophic devastation? Yeah, me neither. So anyway, you kill everyone. All numerical values increase by 2, and you gain 3 [Boost].'),
('finalStretch', 'FINAL STRETCH', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Buildup: 4][Locked: Tunnelwarden]', 'Different battles call for different approaches— so when the end of a fight approaches, you give it your all! When you are fighting, you can spend an action to either GO ON THE OFFENSIVE or HUNKER DOWN. When you GO ON THE OFFENSIVE, you hit hard, trying to end an altercation as quickly as possible; you deal **+1 damage** on all attacks, but after **3 rounds**, you tire yourself out and this effect ends, and become **[Exhausted]**. On the flip side, HUNKERING DOWN gives you **2 [Resistance]** against all types of damage (including **[Unblockable]**), but you become **[Slowed]**.'),
('findAWorkaround', 'FIND A WORKAROUND', 'LIGHT', 'LIGHT', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Light]', 'There’s always more than one path to the correct solution to any problem, and you’re able to follow those paths and adapt your usual techniques when the need arises. You can spend an action to shuffle your **[Talents]** to different stats for **3 rounds**. If you have the **[Ultra]** for a move that allows you access to HERO MODE, you can temporarily swap that around, too. RESPLENDENT RASCALITY? Mmm… no thanks! I feel GLORIOUSLY GRACEFUL today. Doing so gives you **3 [Boost]** as you prepare yourself for a fresh state of mind and way to tackle any problem at hand!'),
('firmIdeals', 'FIRM IDEALS', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'Your whole life, you\'ve just been a propaganda machine for the Empire, eating up the ideals they\'ve fed you. But after the things you\'ve seen and done, you\'ve formed your own opinions of the world. Maybe they\'re still awful and hemoist ones, but if you don\'t suck ultimate bulge, maybe you\'ve learned there are other things out there to value. You gain the following **GOOD** PROBLEM SLEUTHING effects.\r\n\r\n> **GAUGE HEART**: You figure out… is this person on the side of the Empire, or the side of the people? If you like the answer, become **[Peaceful]**. If you don\'t, take **1 [WHAM]**. This is a **[One-Off]** for that particular troll unless something changes.\r\n\r\n> **SEEK SOLUTION**: Is there a way your money could solve this for someone? If the answer is yes, you can attempt to do so, with a **[Tiered Up]** SQUIDILLIONAIRE, PHILANTHROPIC INVESTMENT, or similar roll. If the answer is no, you gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **HARD STARE**: Why are they acting like this? What\'s the root of the problem? If there\'s some deep ingrained personal reason, gain **1 [Hold]** to **[Tier Up]** a **[Manipulate]** roll for **[Free]**. If there isn\'t, and they\'re just like that, gain **1 [Hold]** to **[Tier Up]** a **[Strife]** roll. This is a **[One-Off]**.\r\n\r\n> **VOTE OF CONFIDENCE**: Is this the right thing to do? Your allies all vote privately on a decision you\'re making, and you decide whether to go through with it. If the vote was decided and you all go with it, everyone takes **1 [Boost]**. If the vote is decided, but you don\'t go with it, everyone takes **1 [Drag]** except you, who gets **3 [Boost]** as you push yourself to do it. Both of these are increased by 1 in all counts if the vote was unanimous aside from you.'),
('fishyFeatures', 'FISHY FEATURES', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Passive]', 'You hail from the deep, deep seas! As such, you\'re gonna have some features that somewhat resemble certain creatures that live down below. Select one that you resonate with, look familiar to, or otherwise are kinda like. \r\n\r\n> **ACTINOPTERYGII**: You… are a fish with bones, plain and simple. Seriously, this is 95% of all Seadwellers, and 50% of all life on Alternia. If you don\'t think you\'re themed after anything, it\'s DEFINITELY Actinopterygii you\'re thinking of. Anything from Glubtuna to Rapierfish to 2DFish to Hippocampi to… you get the idea. Your LET\'S STRIFE rolls underwater are **[Legendary]**.\r\n\r\n> **MOLLUSCS**: Jellykrakens, choleraclams, or scuttlefish, that\'s your area of expertise! You\'re a slippery son of a bitch; you automatically get up when you\'re **[Floorbound]** when your turn starts without needing to spend an action.\r\n\r\n> **CETACEANS AND PINNIPEDS**: Skywhales, sealphins, and porcupoises… marine mammals are your dealio. You\'re inherently a little smarter than your peers; your **[Analyze]** rolls can not be **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]**, or **[Nerfed]**.\r\n\r\n> **CRUSTACEANS**: Arr arr arr arr! You love those pinchy, plated boys, from slobsters to megacrabs! Your SHENANIGANS rolls to GRAB people are **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n\r\n> **CHONDRICTHYES**: Do you have sharp teeth, rough skin, and a bad reputation? Well, you may just be a cousin to the fangrays, titansharks, or chainsawheads. When a target is **[Bloodied]**, you have a **+1 [Buff]** to **[Strife]** rolls against them. \r\n\r\n> **SOMETHING ELSE**: Perhaps you\'re more of a sea sponge or pelagic flapbeast guy? Got coral or anemones growing out of your ears? Oh, god, are you one of those Deepsea Violets whose very existence defies this move? Well… choose an effect from above, and flavour it around your truth, dude.'),
('fisticuffsaficionado', 'FISTICUFFSAFICIONADO', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Physical][Strife][Unlock: Bully]', 'Every piece of media these days has em! The rude, crude jerk with an attitude (and a heart of gold). You\'ll push someone in a locker! You\'ll give ‘em a swirly! You\'ll EAT THEIR LUNCH MONEY! But at the end of the day, it\'s your toughness and hidden soft side that will help your friends kick an alien butt! You\'re especially good at kicking butt, now that you mention it. Your fists hanker for a good ol\' fight; you are **[Talented]** at **+GRT**. The following part of the move is called AGGRESS, so roll **+GRT** when you wanna do that.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Oh no! YOUR ass is being kicked! Aeeeiioooough… you do a **GOOD**… to yourself! The opponent gets to do a **GREAT** of this move to YOU!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Okay, yeah, that sucked for you. You take **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You missed… but now you\'re getting all worked up! You gain **1 [WHAM]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: BULLYPUNCH! You do **1 [Somatic]** damage! \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: BULLYPUNCH FOLLOWED UP BY CLASSIC JAPES! You either do **2 [Somatic]** damage, or 1 and one of these options…\r\n\r\n> **NOOGIE**: Ouch oof yeowch urff! You rub your knuckles over their scalp, and it hurts! The target becomes **[Confused]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **WEDGIE**: YANK! That\'s embarrassing! Your target becomes **[Embarrassed]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **LUNCH-MONEY\'D**: GIMMIE THAT! You knock an item out of their hand. It takes an action to retrieve it.\r\n\r\n> **CHORTLE**: Awww, gonna cry?! You taunt the target between attacks, **[Heightening]** an **[Emotion]** they have for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Oh gosh. Maybe you went too far..? NAHHHH. PBBTTBBTT SCREW YOU NEEEERD! The target takes **3 [Somatic]** damage, or **2 [Somatic]** damage and one **GREAT** effect.'),
('fitCheck', 'FIT CHECK', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][One-Off][Analyze][Manipulate][Mental][Locked: Subcultist]', 'You\'ve got an eye for how people dress, and, to be frank… you can\'t stand how slobby some people are. It\'s so… dull! Slobby! Uncool! You have to let people know how uninspired they dress— or, on the rare occasion that they dress well, take some notes of how you could stea— ah, take inspiration from them! When you want to vibe check someone\'s fashion tastes, roll the stat you became **[Talented]** in through COUNTERCULTURIST.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You make an idiotic snap decision so obviously wrong even the target thinks you\'re full of shit. You are **[Humiliated]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You pass a poor judgement! Oh no! You become **[Embarrassed]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: They\'re clothes. It\'s whatever.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Hmmmm… does it pass the check? Look at the stat you rolled this move with, and look at their stat. If they have a +3 or higher in the stat, they pass. If not, they fail. If they fail, you snort derisively and comment on their outfit, making them feel insecure; they take **2 [Drag]**. If they pass, you\'re actually a little impressed. You take **2 [Boost]** and jot some ideas down. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Wow, you feel some intense feelings on their clothes! You get a **GOOD**, but if the target fails, they\'re **[Embarrassed]**. If they pass, you\'re **[Enthusiastic]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: GRUBDAMN, YOU HAVE OPINIONS, DUDE. You get a **GREAT**, but the emotions are heightened!'),
('flailWildly', 'FLAIL WILDLY', 'OTHER', 'PAGE', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Page]', 'Not that you\'re, like, pitiable or anything, but you are kinda used to taking your licks here and there. Life is rough! Everybody makes mistakes! You\'re just a little more used to it than others sometimes and that\'s ok. So when the going gets tough… you go NYEH!!! And just, try whatever. The physical embodiment of button mashing in a game when you have no idea what to do. Sometimes it works out to your advantage, though. Whenever you hit ¼ HP, you gain a **+2 [Buff]** to all moves you make for the next 2 rounds as you really try to roll with the punches.\r\n\r\n'),
('flashStepFirebrand', 'FLASH STEP FIREBRAND', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Ultra][Passive][Physical][Locked: Cool Kid]', 'What’s cooler than being cool? Being completely imperceptible to the human eye! You’ve mastered the art of the Flash Step, using sudden bursts of speed to effectively teleport around in circles around your opponent in an effort to completely overwhelm them. Are you over here? Over there? Who knows, dude; all you know is you’re about to break some fucking bones. When you enter a fight, you start to dash around the opponent, leaving only shadowy after-images in your place. You gain access to HERO MODE through your HARDCORE HUBRIS. You can begin FLASH STEPPING as an action. Whenever an opponent attempts a move that would deal **[Somatic]** damage to you while you’re FLASH STEPPING, they must first roll 1d8. On a 1, the opponent misses you entirely; on any result other than an 8, the opponent’s incoming roll has a -2 **[Nerf]**. On an 8, the opponent’s roll cannot be lower than a **GOOD**. While FLASH STEPPING, you are **[Quickened]** and you get a **MAX** on **[Strife]** rolls on a result of 17 and up, but you have **2 [Weakness]** to all **[Somatic]** damage. You can stop FLASH STEPPING as an action.'),
('flavoursOfAwesome', 'FLAVOURS OF AWESOME', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Passive][Locked: Mary Sue]', 'Different types of super cool awesome characters exist out there, okay? And YOU are one of them! Select an option from below and gain the associated benefit that you have when you are above half HP, and a second benefit that activates when your HP drops below half.\r\n\r\n> **EDGY**: Heh… nothing personal… kid… you are a cool badass and everyone around you thinks you’re so fucking scary and cool. You are **[Talented]** at all **[Strife]** moves, and gain any one **[Strife]** move from another caste. When you are **below half HP**, you lose the move, but you are still **[Talented]** at **[Strife]**.\r\n\r\n> **MAGICAL**: Waaaaow! Look at you go, with all those cool wizard powers and shit! You gain any one **[Basic]** **[Psionic]** or **[Magic]** move, though it always is **[Magic]** instead of **[Psionic]** when you use it. When you are **below half HP**, you lose access to this move, but FRAYMOTIF rolls **[Tier Up]** to **MAX**. You aren’t giving up on magic that easy!\r\n\r\n> **SEXY**: You’ve got a body like… well, it’s something. How do those proportions… work..? Anyway, you gain access to HERO MODE through your PERFECT PULCHRITUDE while **above half HP**. When **below half HP**, you gain **[Resistance]** against **[Verbal]** damage; yeah, yeah, you know. Bully away, jerks, you’ve heard it all before.\r\n\r\n> **GENIUS**: Yeah, you basically figured out how to make a Perpetual Motion engine. You’re only 6 sweeps old, yes. Yes, you did it alone. It wasn’t hard. You gain access to the SCIENTIFIC PROWRESS Inventor Indigo move when **above half HP**. When **below half HP**, you get a **+1 [Buff]** to **[Analyse]** rolls.\r\n\r\n> **COOL**: You’re so cool, even the stuff above can’t define you! But you know what every cool guy has? WINGS! SPARKLY RAINBOW ONES, OR SOMETHING! You can start **[Flying]** when you’re **above half HP**. When you’re **below half HP**, your frustration at your objective awesomeness being disrupted slowly grows; you can choose to become **[Enraged]** as you fight your hardest for your honour.'),
('flawlessTraining', 'FLAWLESS TRAINING', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Admiral]', 'NOBODY knows how to wield a weapon like you do. NOBODY. Under no circumstances are your **[Strife]** rolls **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]** or **[Nerfed]**. In fact, when you would ordinarily be up against an enemy\'s effect that does that, you get a **+1 [Buff]** to your roll. Just to rub it in.'),
('flaydayNightSmackdown', 'FLAYDAY NIGHT SMACKDOWN', 'OTHER', 'MUSCLEMANIAC', '[Template][Physical][Strife][Unlock: Musclemaniac]\r\n', 'Here at the Alternian Annihilation Entertainment group, we believe in one thing and one thing only. SHREDDING ABSOLUTE SHIT IN FRONT OF A LIVE AUDIENCE!! You’re a FIGHTER, BABY!! Whether you’re acting as a tough breakneck loudmouth or actually enjoy pummeling people into the ground, all eyes are on you. Your fighting style is more performance than actual mangrit- all your damage is nonlethal, since you actually need your opponent to survive so you can beat each other up again. When you want to wrestle the dice, roll **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You fucked up. Not only did you miss, you completely broke character, disillusioning the crowd. You take **1 [Psychic]** damage and your next **[Flourish]** roll is **[Tiered down]**, even to a **MIN**. Additionally, any spectators feel **[Dread]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You missed, dipshit. Or maybe that was intentional? Definitely an intentional miss for the drama. Regardless, nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**OK**:  The crowd is on your side. Your next roll of FLAYDAY NIGHT SMACKDOWN is **[Tiered up]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You’re definitely on the offense! You do **1 Nonlethal [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: SUPLEX! The crowd goes absolutely wild at whatever dramatic bullshit you pull. You deal **2 Nonlethal [Somatic]** damage, or **1 Nonlethal [Somatic]** Damage and your next **[Flourish]** roll is **[Tiered up]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: IT’S GRYMBL WITH THE STEEL CHAIR! You’re a fucking legend. You deal **3 Nonlethal [Somatic]** damage, or **2 damage** and your next **[Flourish]** roll is **[Tiered up]**, even to a **MAX**. Any spectators of your fight feel **[Hopeful]**!'),
('flipTheFuckOut', 'FLIP THE FUCK OUT', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Open][Free][One-Off]', 'Things ALWAYS go your way— and when they don’t, you lose your actual shit. Aw, you lost a bet? KNIFE. You tripped and fell? TANTRUM. No more soda in the soda stream? Oh, you best believe that the soda stream is already halfway out the upstairs window. On a **MIN** or **BAD** roll, you can become **[Enraged]**.'),
('flyAwayCagedBird', 'FLY AWAY CAGED BIRD', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Posh]', 'You know what? You aren\'t perfect! Not even a little. You\'re a flawed, mortal person, and that\'s okay! You like that. You LOVE it, even! Here, you\'re able to escape all the pressures of Earth and really, truly be yourself. Of course, having money is nice, and you learned many skills from your experiences… but now, on Alternia, you have the chance to stop being what everyone else wanted, and be yourself. You gain access to HERO MODE through your GLORIOUS GRACE. Whenever you gain **[Boost]**, you gain **1 additional [Boost]**; similarly, it takes **2 [Drag]** to lower your roll results. You\'re just that much more confident now! Finally, if you have the GREAT EXPECTATIONS move, you aren\'t just **[Talented]** at the specific move; you are **[Talented]** at the whole stat associated as you find new ways to do things with your old skills, like a ballerina realising she\'s great at kickboxing or a poet becoming a freestyle rapper. You can also take up to **3 [Open]** moves with that stat from any caste, so long as it isn\'t **[Psionic]**!'),
('followMe', 'FOLLOW ME!', 'OTHER', 'ROGUE', '[Class][Basic][Free][Recharge: 2][Locked: Rogue]', 'You spend much of your time giving your companions your expertise, focusing on aiding them in their path rather than furthering your own. Quick, this way! Do as I do! You can let someone else roll using your own stats rather than theirs (for example, roll your **+GRA** of +3 rather than theirs, a 0). This switch lasts til the end of your next turn.\n\n'),
('followTheLeader', 'FOLLOW THE LEADER', 'OTHER', 'MAID', '[Class][Passive][Unlock: Maid]', 'Ever since you can remember, you\'ve just followed someone else\'s lead! Whether that guidance is from a caretaker, a workplace, or even just societal messaging - it helps you get by, having some kind of structure in your life. It sure is draining, doing everything just so, but... it\'ll all pay off in the end, surely! You start each encounter with 5 **[Drag]**, but can only ever be forced to use a maximum of 2 **[Drag]** at a time. See, all it takes is a little discipline! This **[Drag]** cannot be reduced by any source other than being made to use it or gaining **[Boost]**. Sometimes that discipline comes from having to just... grin and bear it!\r\n'),
('followThePath', 'FOLLOW THE PATH', 'OTHER', 'MAID', '[Class][Advanced][Locked: Maid]', 'You have learned that you don’t always need to follow someONE, you can simply follow someTHING. You can observe a path or plan that someone else has taken or used and realize, “Hey! I don’t need to trace each and every step to the exact letter! All I need to do is simply get to the end.” That freedom has lifted a lot of the weight off your shoulders. Routine is helpful, and if you can optimize it to the beat of your own drum, it can be a lot less grating on you. The **[Drag]** you start with from **FOLLOW THE LEADER** is reduced to 3, and when made to use **[Drag]**, you can only be made to use 1 **[Drag]** at a time. You are done being pushed around and led astray by those who only think of themselves. You have a path, and you’re sticking to it!'),
('followYourHeart', 'FOLLOW YOUR HEART', 'PROSPIT', 'PROSPIT', '[Sway][Passive][Locked: Prospit]', 'You tend not to overthink things you do; to you, it’s better to follow your instincts and do what feels natural. Any time you use a **[Reaction]**, you gain **1 [Boost]** as doing something without thinking about it and having it pay off makes you feel accomplished. You don’t even need to succeed at the **[Reaction]**!'),
('foolishBeliefs', 'FOOLISH BELIEFS', 'OTHER', 'BARD', '[Class][Basic][Reaction][One-Off][Locked: Bard]', 'You have EXTREMELY strong beliefs that others regard as… strange. Sure, man, the Horrorterrors were the original Mirthful Messiahs. Yeah, I totally believe that Wizards are real too. Aliens on the moon from a different dimension? Whatever you say. Either way, your wacky beliefs (which will never shatter and lead to an aspect crisis ever) are surprisingly solid, and it lets you power through some exceptional circumstances. Once per thread, you completely ignore the outcome of one action your opponent takes and treat it as a **BAD**.\n\n'),
('foragersBounty', 'FORAGER’S BOUNTY', 'OTHER', 'GOREMAND', '[Template][Basic][Locked: Goremand]', 'A good chef knows how to get their ingredients from any source. A great chef knows how to fight tooth and nail for their ingredients. After winning a Strife against a monster, you can find rare ingredients from your opponent that’ll grant a special **[Buff]** after your next Cullinary Pursuit result. Roll 1d8.\r\n\r\n> **1**: You get a really weird part, like a tooth or foot. Oh well, into the pot it goes! You gain a temporary +1 IMG to your next encounter.\r\n\r\n> **2**: Okay, this isn’t *as* weird as it could be, but it’s still strange. Maybe a psion eyeball is a delicacy in some places? You gain a temporary +1 RAS to your next encounter.\r\n\r\n> **3**: Alright, you could make something good with this cut. A little of this, a little of that, and this shoulder’s raring to go! You gain a temporary +1 GRA to your next encounter.\r\n\r\n> **4**: Oooh, yes, please! A hearty cut from the ribs! Some barbeque sauce could send this straight to heaven. You gain a temporary +1 GRT to your next encounter.\r\n\r\n> **5**: Nobody can resist the melt-in-your-mouth texture of meat from the hindquarters. Your mouth’s just watering thinking about it! You gain a temporary +1 PLC to your next encounter.\r\n\r\n> **6**: You can’t believe everybody else looked over this bit. Honestly, with the right care, the pollution liver can be a fabulous ingredient. You gain a +1 PSP to your next encounter.\r\n\r\n> **7**: This is a seriously rare part! The delicate flesh around the poison sack is always the most delicious, but rarely cut right. You gain a temporary +1 HUB to your next encounter.\r\n\r\n> **8**: Oh sweet Mother Grub. This is a prime cut of meat, straight from the tenderloin! Thick and tender, you ought to treat this with care. You gain a temporary +1 APP to your next encounter.'),
('forceOfPersonality', 'FORCE OF PERSONALITY', 'BLOOD', 'BLOOD', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Blood]', 'Despite your flaws… you’re a very likeable person. Maybe, to an extent, it’s because of your flaws; maybe the worst parts in you help bring out the parts of you that really count! Your **[Manipulate]** rolls cannot be negatively affected by others’ moves (such as to **[Tier Down]** or make them **[Inept]**). Additionally, when a troll chooses to listen to you when you get a **GOOD** or better WORDPLAY roll where you use the Request option, they gain **5 [Boost]**, or reset their **[Drag]** to 0, whichever is higher.'),
('forfend', 'FORFEND', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Physical][Strife][Locked: Tunnelwarden]', 'There comes a time in every Tunnelwarden\'s career when it becomes clear violence is the only universal language. Alas, you\'ve trained hard and become fluent in it. When you want to protect the weak, roll **+GRT**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: OUCH! You seriously injure yourself! You take **2 [Somatic]** damage and **-1 [Nerf]** to all **[Physical]** rolls for the encounter.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Oof! That hurt yourself! You take **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Swing and a miss! The heft your attack had is startling; the target takes **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: A solid blow! You do **1 [Somatic]** damage!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: CRUNCH! That\'s an attack that\'s gonna leave a mark! You do **2 [Somatic]** damage, or 1, and give the target a **-3 [Nerf]** to all **[Physical]** rolls for a turn!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: A loud snap marks that you may have broken bone! Maybe this will disable the target and end the fight..? Probably not, but hey, worth a shot. You do **3 [Somatic]** damage, or 2 with a **-3 [Nerf]** on their next **[Physical]** roll, and then a **-1 [Nerf]** to all **[Physical]** rolls for the encounter.'),
('forgeYourOwnPath', 'FORGE YOUR OWN PATH', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Posh]', 'Your life may be pretty sweet, but a gold cage is still a cage. You\'re tired of adhering to what you used to be once upon a time; you want to be something true to you, something authentic, not something your guardians picked out or something you\'re good at because you\'ve thrown money at it! By choosing to be true to yourself, you actualize yourself much faster than others you know; you gain access to your **[Basic]** Class moves now, and gain 3 immediately. If you already had all the **[Basic]** Class moves, you can take **[Advanced]** ones too. If you had all of them already, then goddamn, take Aspect moves. If you had all of THEM, then you get 3 moves of any type you have access to, I guess..?');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('forGreatJustice', 'FOR GREAT JUSTICE', 'TIME', 'TIME', '[Aspect][Advanced][Free][Locked: Time]', 'You’re very familiar with wanting revenge… but you know that it’s hard to keep level headed when you’re fighting to retaliate against evil deeds that happened to you. But when someone else steps in and fairly, swiftly and level-headedly punishes evil-doers for their wicked ways… THAT’s justice. When you encounter someone who has hurt a friend before, and you know it, you can choose to become **[Enraged]** as you deliver sweet justice right to their front door. You do not gain the drawbacks associated with being **[Enraged]** in this state; only the positives.'),
('formerDreamer', 'FORMER DREAMER', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Passive]', 'Once upon a time, you dreamed of a strange moon. Maybe it was Gold, populated by charming chess people. Maybe it was purple, inhabited by bitter pawns. One way or another though, ever since getting to Alternia, those dreams… stopped. But you never forgot the lessons you learned there. When you take this move, you gain **1 [Advanced]** Aspect or Class move of your choosing, lowering the level gate for **[Basic]** moves to Level 1. You must have the appropriate entry move to take this move. At Level 6, you can take this move again to take **one [Basic]** Sway move from the opposite Sway (for example, a Derse dreamer gaining a Prospit move) as you subconsciously remember lore you learned in your dreams.'),
('formVioletron', 'FORM VIOLETRON', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Lengthy][Locked: Pilot]', 'Come on, guys! We can\'t do this alone! Let\'s TRANSFORM! You yell out to any allies inside vehicles (preferably Mechas, but hey, you\'ll take a Scuttlebuggy if needs be) and create a new, stronger Mecha together  This new Mecha has all the upgrades its components had, has HP equal to the highest HP vehicle, **+2 HP** for each vehicle in the mix. You have the highest HORSEPOWER of any vehicle present, the largest size of any vehicle present, and all pilots may roll to VEHICULATE this amalgamech. None of the pilots take damage when the mech takes damage. However, when the mech hits **0 HP**, it explodes, dealing 15 **[Somatic]** damage to all pilots. Ejecting from the Mecha before it\'s destroyed does **3 damage** to it, and gives a **-1 [Nerf]** to all VEHICULATE rolls to control the Mecha. Don\'t bail on your friends while you\'re piloting a Megazord! You can\'t return the Mecha to its components until combat ends; this takes about half an hour in character.'),
('fraybattle', 'FRAYBATTLE', 'OTHER', 'MUSICREANT', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Musicreant]', 'The only dancing that\'ll be done in this give is dancing to MY beat! You may roll a special version of FRAYMOTIF; this version affects the opponent as you play music that totally wraps them in your own music! You gain the following options you may replace in a regular FRAYMOTIF.\r\n\r\n> **TIME**: Your high tempo song winds the opponent up to a breaking point. Your opponent is **[Quickened]** twice over and **[Inept]** at **+GRA**. Additionally, they roll all moves as **[Inept]** as they go too… too fast!\r\n\r\n> **SPACE**: Experience the vast… through the power of chill beats! Your opponent\'s **[Reaction]** moves are **[Inept]** as you mess with their sense of space.\r\n\r\n> **LIFE**: Relaxing, huh? Makes you just wanna… curl up and forget about everything. Your opponents all become **[Tired]**, and cannot **[Heal] HP**.\r\n\r\n> **DOOM**: This is the EXACT kind of music that gives your opponents a panic attack! Hell yeah! Your opponents immediately feel **[Dread]** and **[Scared]**.\r\n\r\n> **HOPE**: How can you not like this song? It\'s a classic! Let\'s play it again! Every turn, the opponent must roll at least one non **[Strife]** or **[Chicanery]** move they rolled last turn or take **3 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> **RAGE**: [LOUD, ANGRY MUSIC RIPS YOUR SENSES TO SHREDS] Your opponent becomes **[Deafened]** and **[Blinded]** as music overwhelms them.\r\n\r\n> **BREATH**: Guitar solo! Diddly-diddly-diddly-dew! You play so loud and inspiringly, that the opponent can\'t do anything of their own! Their **[Magic]** and **[Psionic]** rolls become **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n> **BLOOD**: You might die here… but through the fire and the flames you carry on! Any time the opponent does more than 3 damage to you, they take **1 [Psychic]** damage back.\r\n\r\n> **LIGHT**: Here\'s to you, pal! You sing a song aaaaall about the opponents. They cannot become **[Hidden]** or ABSCOND while you\'re singing to them. Any time they take **[Drag]**, they take 1 extra. This stacks with OHOHO.\r\n\r\n> **VOID**: You want to fade into obscurity? Alright. Here\'s your outro. Any opponent who hears this song play for more than five turns falls **[Unconscious]** until the song ends; after which point they become **[Tired]**.\r\n\r\n> **HEART**: Encore, encore! Anytime your opponent uses a Universal Move while you’re singing, you can choose to take the same result they got as a **[Reaction]** and throw their skills right back at them. This activates **[Recharge]**, if applicable.\r\n\r\n> **MIND**: You sing a song that puts you at peace, and puts everyone else… well, not at peace. Your opponent’s **[Analyze]** rolls are **[Inept]**, and on a successful roll of this type, they become **[Stressed]** as they still feel like they’re… missing something.'),
('fraymotif', 'FRAYMOTIF', 'OTHER', 'UNIVERSAL', '[Physical][Magic][One-Off][Buildup: 3]', 'The power of music and the arcane blessing of the stars you were hatched under flows through your very soul. You can tap into these energies to boogie it up and get funky. A Fraymotif is a powerful dance move that unleashes the inherent abilities of your aspect, allowing you to boogie to the boss music in style. Allies who witness you start to dance may make a **[Reaction]** to dance too. When you want to dance out your frustrations, roll **+IMG**.\n\n> **MIN**: You, uh. Uh. You mess it up. You fall **[Floorbound]** and become **[Agitated]** as the stars laugh at you, and the magic disperses.\n\n> **BAD**: You don\'t boogie woogie. In fact, your dance only increases your frustrations! You become **[Stressed]** as you stumble your dance.\n\n> **OK**: You don\'t quite get anything going, but you definitely felt something empower you. You don\'t trigger this move\'s **[One-Off]** effect.\n\n> **GOOD**: You manage it! The power of your aspect and your sweet moves flow through your sign and into the battlefield. Play some music that fits your dance— probably some video game OST. You gain a powerful bonus from your aspect, as follows…\n\n> **TIME**: You dance a dance that transcends tempo. You become **[Quickened]**.\n> **SPACE**: You dance with the stars. You start **[Flying]** as ethereal steps appear under your feet wherever you go. If you were already able to **[Fly]**, you can\'t be knocked **[Floorbound]**.\n> **LIFE**: You dance away your troubles. You restore **1 HP** on your turn.\n> **DOOM**: You dance while you still can. You gain **1 [Resistance]** to all damage and **[Drag]**.\n> **HOPE**: You dance because you\'ll never give up. You gain **2 [Boost]** every turn.\n> **RAGE**: You dance with heavy stomps and gritted teeth. You gain **1 [WHAM]** every time you get a **GREAT** roll, and can\'t lose your **[WHAM]** til you spend it.\n> **BREATH**: You dance no matter what others say. You become immune to **[Physical]** Status Conditions.\n> **BLOOD**: You dance with the whole world around you. You receive the **[Talent]** of another troll present. If there are no trolls with a **[Talent]** you don\'t already have, your rolls for that stat **[Tier Up]** instead.\n> **LIGHT**: You dance like a flame that will never go out. You are immune to **[Drag]**, **[Inept]** and **[Tier Down]** effects.\n> **VOID**: Your dance is quiet and quick moving. All **[Psionic]** and **[Mental]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**.\n> **HEART**: You dance the dance that\'s truest to yourself. You may give a +2 **[Buff]** a roll you make as a **[Free]** action every round.\n> **MIND**: You dance a dance that\'s one step ahead of your opponents at all times. You may **[Tier Down]** an opponent’s roll that targets you as a **[Free]** **[Reaction]** every round.\n\n**GREAT**: Your dance sweeps up others in its sway. So long as you are dancing you may, as a **[Free]** action at the start of your turn, COMBO with another combatant. You dance together, gaining both of your aspects together. The target only benefits back if they also roll a **GREAT** **FRAYMOTIF** roll and chooses to COMBO you on their turn. Any allies using a **[Reaction]** to dance with you have their rolls **[Tiered Up]**.\n\n**MAX**: Your dance makes you appear as an ethereal being. You gain access to all **[Aspect]** moves for your Aspect, including the **[Ultra]**. If you already had all of them, gain all **[Class]** moves for your Class. If you already had all of them, your opponents are **[Dumbfounded]** by your beauty. Any allies using a **[Reaction]** to dance with you have their rolls **[Tiered Up]** twice, even to a **MAX**.'),
('fraynumber', 'FRAYNUMBER', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Fanyatic]', 'HONEY WHATCHA WAITIN’ FOOOOOR!~ If you\'re gonna make it big in fandom spaces, you\'re gonna have to get real into musicals, one way or another. I don\'t make the rules. When you do a FRAYMOTIF, you gain the following effects, removing the **[Magic]** tag and rolling with **+RAS**:\r\n\r\n> **TIME**: You’re-never-gonna-stop-til-you-make-‘em-drop-and-burn-‘em-up-and-scatter-their-remains! RAP? IN A SHOWTUNE? The opponent is **[Confused]** because how are you singing so quickly?\r\n\r\n> **SPACE**: On the outside, always looking in- will you ever be more than you\'ve always been? Your song is achingly lonely, making the target feel **[Numb]**.\r\n\r\n> **LIFE**: The sun will come up… TOMORROOOOOOW… you sing an emotional song about wanting a better future. Your target is **[Disgusted]** in themselves for trying to stop you.\r\n\r\n> **DOOM**: SIIIIIING MY ANGEL OF MUSIC! Your haunting song makes the opponent feel **[Dread]**.\r\n\r\n> **HOPE**: Grey skies are gonna clear up- put on a happy face! You sing a chipper and upbeat song that reminds targets about the good things in life. Maybe a little too much. The target becomes **[Proud]**.\r\n\r\n> **RAGE**: ENPECE! Open the- open the door please, Enpece open the door-! Your song is intense and frightening; the target is **[Scared]**.\r\n\r\n> **BREATH**: There’s nothing here holding you down- the world is out, tell the whole town you\'re bouncing! You sing a song that hypes the fuck out of the audience! Your target becomes **[Overwhelmed]**.\r\n\r\n> **BLOOD**: They could use a buddy! Don’t they want a pal? (Yes they do! Yes they do!) You sing a song that makes the opponent consider teaming up with you, in spite of themselves. The opponent is **[Charmed]**.\r\n\r\n> **LIGHT**: IT’S… A… MUUUUSICAL! A MUUUUSICAL! You sweep the target into your act. They start **[Giggling]** (more like humming, really) as they try to hold themselves back from singing along.\r\n\r\n> **VOID**: MEEEEMORY… all alone in the MOOOOONLIGHT… your song is passionate and raw, and it makes the opponent **[Sad]**.\r\n\r\n> **HEART**: Everything about them is so terrible. Everything about them makes you wanna die! You berate the target’s flaws in musical format, suggesting they be more like you. The target can\'t use **[Flourish]** moves until your song ends.\r\n\r\n> **MIND**: How do you write like you\'re running out of time? That\'s right, a second Hamilton reference, I can\'t take this any more. You urge the opponent to think hard about their next move, making them **[Focused]**.'),
('frayvocalize', 'FRAYVOCALIZE', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Honkpostle]', 'Music is a holy part of the Clown Church, stemming back to ancient performances rumored to be held by the Messiahs themselves. So when you rap those hallowed beats, you gain their blessing. Rather than dance, your FRAYMOTIF can instead spit hot and holy fire, rapping out holy hymns and dishing out altered bonuses. Others may choose to benefit from your options if they COMBO with you. Your FRAYMOTIF options are as follows:\r\n\r\n> **TIME**: All your moves lose the **[Lengthy]** tag, and the total **[Recharge]** needed for a move is dropped by 1.\r\n> **SPACE**: Whenever you gain **[Boost]** or **[WHAM]**, all allies do too.\r\n> **LIFE**: You become immune to **[Drag]** and gain **1 [Boost]** instead whenever you are given **[Drag]**.\r\n> **DOOM**: Your opponents cannot benefit from **[Boost]**, and gain **1 [Drag]** when they would gain it.\r\n> **HOPE**: You become **[Out-Of-Control]** and gain **[Resistance]** to **[Somatic]** damage.\r\n> **RAGE**: You become **[Serene]** and give 1 random target **[Weakness]** every **2 turns**.\r\n> **BREATH**: You become immune to enemy moves that would **[Nerf]**, **[Tier Down]** your moves, make them **[Inept]** or make them immune to them.\r\n> **BLOOD**: You become **[Inspired]** and **[heal]** an ally or or yourself **1 HP** every **2 turns**.\r\n> **LIGHT**: When you take damage from an opponent, your allies gain 3 **[Boost]**.\r\n> **VOID**: You become **[Permablind]**, and have a **+2 [Buff]** to **[Strife]** rolls.\r\n> **HEART**: You become immune to all negative **[Emotions]**, losing them now.\r\n> **MIND**: You become **[Enlightened]**, and all enemies become **[Confused]**.'),
('freakyEye', 'FREAKY EYE', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Control][Psionic][Unlock: Mastermind]', 'One or both of your eyes has an irregular amount of pupils. These pupils swirl with psionic might, and allow you to control the minds of others as if they were your own! KYAHAHAHAHA! While many Ceruleans have this odd mutation, you in particular have trained it, making yourself a frantically powerful psion that NOBODY can stand up to. You are **[Talented]** at **+IMG**. When you want to Manipul8 someone, roll **+IMG**.\n\n**MIN**: Ah, fuck. They know what you just tried to pull, and they’re not happy. You gain **1 [Weakness]** to the target\'s **[Strife]** rolls, and you are **[Humiliated]**.\n\n**BAD**: The sheer lack of a response is beyond embarrassing. You are, nonetheless, **[Embarrassed]**.\n\n**OK**: It doesn’t QUITE work, but they’re more open to helping you than before. Your **[Psionic]** rolls against this specific troll are **[Tiered Up]** until either they take damage or you get a **GOOD** or better result.\n\n**GOOD**: Got them! You can force the troll to roll any one move they have against any target you choose, giving them a **GOOD** result automatically. This does not take an action on their turn; it happens now, according to YOUR will.\n\n**GREAT**: They’re really part of your web now, huh? You get the effects of a **GOOD**, except the roll is automatically **GREAT**.\n\n**MAX**: Pitiful flies! They bend to your superior will. Maybe even forever! Muahahahahah! You get a **GREAT** result, except the mind control lasts for 2 rounds or until the target takes 3 damage of any type, whatever happens first. If this is being used narratively, then the mind control can last indefinitely. Just check with your target and make sure both sides agree on how long it will last.'),
('freeAsTheWind', 'FREE AS THE WIND', 'BREATH', 'BREATH', '[Aspect][Advanced][Free][Locked: Breath]', 'There are no shackles on you! You’re a free spirit, through and through, and nothing can slow you down. Any time you would gain the **[Slowed]**, **[Stunned]**, **[Trapped]**, or **[Floorbound]** conditions, you can choose to instead catch yourself and keep going, gaining **2 [Drag]** which ignore the effects of EASY BREEZY. This move does not take effect for self-inflicted Status Effects, however.'),
('freeWilly', 'FREE WILLY', 'OTHER', 'WYLDERDRUID', '[Template][Advanced][Magic][Locked: Wylderdruid]', 'Lusii should be more than just caretakers, right? Right? It’s kind of against your beliefs to put so much of your emotional energy in the hands (or paws, or flippers) of your lusus. You’ve established yourself as one of the most advanced practitioners of your faith by willingly parting with your lusus, encouraging them to return to nature rather than look after a member of a species that won’t even further their own bloodline. Maybe they’ll find another charge, but that’s their choice. Intentionally disowning yourself from your mom might massively suck for you, and makes you soft **[Cullbait]** if people find out about your “orphan” status. However, this also earns you respect from Alternia\'s wildlife, allowing you to call upon their help at will. You’re no longer a child of Slothdad… you’re a child of the forest. You gain **CUSTODIAN COMPANION** if you didn’t have it already, and your **ALTRICIALIZE** rolls **[Tier Up]**. Additionally, you can pick any effect you want from the list of **ALTRICIALIZE** effects when you use it; after all, you’re not actually calling upon a specific lusus, just... whatever the nearby wildlife may be.\r\n'),
('friendleader', 'FRIENDLEADER', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][Passive][Recharge: 2]', 'By now, you\'ve learned that having a good support system can keep you flourishing in a world that\'s meant to hate you. The power of friendship will save the day, basically, and you gotta remember that. You are **[Talented]** at all QUALITY TIME **[Downtime]** rolls. You can take an action to give an ally another action now, pointing out and asking them to work!'),
('friendleadership', 'FRIENDLEADERSHIP', 'OTHER', 'HEIR', '[Class][Advanced][Free][Locked: Heir]', 'You’ve spent so long accidentally sweeping people up in your aspect, bringing them along on whatever wild rides you’ve wound up on… it’s about time that you try your hand at intentionally leading the way! In a friendly kind of way, you know? When you use **BUTTERFLY EFFECT**, you can choose one of the following modes to add onto it:\r\n\r\n> **LEADER’S GUIDANCE**: You’ve learned how to express your most special insights - you can share an **[Advanced] [Aspect]** move with a teammate.\r\n\r\n> **POWER OF FRIENDSHIP**: There’s enough of your aspect for everyone! All allies gain access to the move you choose, not just one.\r\n'),
('friendshipIsMagic', 'FRIENDSHIP IS MAGIC', 'OTHER', 'WITCH', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Witch]', 'Being in complete control of everything isn’t as fun as you thought it would be- mainly because people are more fearful than thankful towards you. Something about being scared shitless that one small slip up and you’ll change their life for the worse. Yeah, you’ll admit it’s not a great look. So, from here on out you’ve decided to tone down the Maleficent vibes a scooch. You can use your powers for good as a benevolent god... Nay! A friend! You gain the following **SHENANIGANS** effects: \r\n\r\n> **ALLEY-OOP**: You throw your ally (or enemy?) up into the air so far that they\'re considered [Flying] for one round! This cannot be used on yourself; however, you can use it to help you hit a **[Flying]** target with no penalty for your next move.\r\n\r\n> **DISAPPEARING ACT**: You obscure an ally from view. When the enemy looks again, GASP! You’ve made the ally **[Hidden]**!\r\n\r\n> **I CARE YOU**: You reassure your ally that this encounter will go just fine, thank you very much! Your reassurances make them feel **[Peace]**! How could you lose?\r\n'),
('friendshipStarved', 'FRIENDSHIP STARVED', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'What\'s up? You got— YOU GOT INVITED TO A TEA PARTY?? YOU? Huh! Turns out, if you don\'t threaten to cut people up, they\'ll be willing to let you chill with them. That… feels really nice? You\'ve spent a long time being mad, bad and dangerous to know, but now… being known isn\'t too bad! Allied moves are **[Talented]** on you, and have a **+1 [Buff]** if they were already **[Talented]**. Any shred of validation helps!'),
('friendsListenClosely', 'FRIENDS, LISTEN CLOSELY', 'OTHER', 'MAGE', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Mage]\r\n', 'You won\'t say this twice, hope\'s running out and we haven\'t much time… Ah, sorry, were you going a bit overboard again? You’ve learned to cool it with the doomsday prophecy talk. It takes a lot of energy out of you, and sometimes you’re not even right! People even seem more willing to listen to you, as you don’t talk down to them for not immediately believing the worst would happen. When you use **BEARER OF BAD NEWS**, you no longer take **[Drag]** as you take deep breaths to reassure yourself that things are not as dire as you think. Additionally, you may pass on a **SWASHBUCKLING** effect onto an ally using **BEARER OF BAD NEWS**, as people are more comfortable in you guiding them through! This option is **[Recharge: 3]**.'),
('fromAnotherWorld', 'FROM ANOTHER WORLD', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Passive][Locked: AU]', 'Magic and psionics don\'t… work on you like one might expect. Maybe you, on a molecular level, are altered by the world you walk on the edge of, and paraphysics freak out when applied to you. **+IMG** rolls against you are **[Inept]**; on a **BAD**, rather than the normal effects, the opponent is **[Confused]**, and on a **MIN**, they\'re **[Dumbfounded]**.'),
('funkyEyes', 'FUNKY EYES', 'OTHER', 'MUTANT', '[Mutant][Cullbait][Passive]', 'Your eyes are reminiscent of the mutations that appear on ceruleans, whether you have a whole bunch of them, funky compound bug eyes or they’re just the kind not seen on trolls not belonging to the cerulean or gold castes. Choose two caste bases, excluding limes and violets, which have access to **[Psionic]** moves. You gain the ability to take **[Entry]** and **[Basic] [Psionic]** abilities from both castes as level up options, but do not gain any now and only gain the **[Psionic]** abilities from the moves, not any **[Talents]**, **[Unlocks]** or other benefits. These psionics are at a **-2 [Nerf]** since the inability to practice them to their full potential leaves them weak. Their appearance will generally match with the type of eye mutation you have, such as a gold\'s eye beams giving your eyes a filled in neon color, but are visibly identifiable as out of the Alternian norm and as such you probably have to hide them with reflective glasses, goggles or one of those edgy emo haircuts where your hair covers your eye. You know the one.\r\n'),
('furthestRingwraith', 'FURTHEST RINGWRAITH', 'OTHER', 'ADULT', '[Eerie][Locked: Adult]\r\nREQUIREMENTS: Cthonomancer', 'Space. Some would call it an empty void, but you know better. No, like all voids, space is full to bursting - with the unknowable and the cryptic. The unfathomably powerful. All that time, confined on your little ball of rock, you thought you understood the Dark Ones. But you have to see the endless ocean for yourself before you can even comprehend what may lurk in the fathoms. The sacrifices MUST continue. All Entity Monsters are unconditionally loyal to you, and will not harm you - rather, if they are not already your minions, you may directly command their next turns as an action, gaining 2 **[Boost]** whenever you do as your mental link is strengthened by The Ones Beyond. You may summon **LEVEL 2 ENTITIES** with THEY SEE YOU as ever-greater minions heed your call. If you have **FAVORED FIEND**, you will always die a JUST death when struck down after revival as the universe strains against you… but your ambient grimdark will always condense back into physical form so long as you so choose. You only take the Ghost **[Template]** if you so desire, remaining a \'normal\' adult otherwise.\r\n'),
('fusillade', 'FUSILLADE', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Physical][Strife][Locked: Vagabond]', 'PEW PEW PEW! Guns are, obviously, the best weapon. As such, you\'ve trained to use them and make great use of \'em! When you wanna open fire, roll **+RAS**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: JAMMED! Your firearm blows up, which is REAL shit for you! You take **2 [Somatic]** damage, and can\'t use this move for the encounter.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Okay, misfire! Yikes! You take **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**OK**: D\'oh, you missed it! You deal **1 [Somatic]** damage to a random troll other than your target. If there\'s only you and one enemy, nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: BANG! You got \'em good! The target takes **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: BANG BANG! You shoot that motherfuck hard! The target takes **2 [Somatic]** damage, or 1 and the opponent is **[Bloodied]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: BANG BANG BANG BANG BANG! Shootout, baby! You do **3 [Somatic]** damage, or 2 and **[Bloodied]**.'),
('gadgetCollection', 'GADGET COLLECTION', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Espiacrooner]', 'Go-Go Gadget Powerdrill! A spy is only as good as the tools they bring to the field, right? Your **VP** increases by 4, and you gain access to the following items.\n\n> **FRAMING TOOLS (1 VP)**: Some hair, maybe some cologne that smells like them, a scrap of paper… Hey, was Enpece here?! You can use this **[Consumable]** item to leave \"evidence\" of a troll\'s presence. It takes a **GREAT** SPOT roll to figure out it\'s bogus.\n\n> **SECRET DOCUMENTS (1 VP)**: Let\'s see what we have here… these **[Consumable]** items can be used to get a **GOOD** PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll without rolling or triggering **[Recharge]**.\n\n> **KEY CARD (1 VP)**: With this item, you can unlock any door. Even ones without card readers, somehow. \n\n> **SUPER SECRET CAR DEPLOYER (2 VP)**: HAHAHA, POCKET SPORTS CAR! LET THE CHASE BEGIN! You can decaptchalogue a VEHICLE, no matter the size, and take it with you everywhere. Its features must be worth 6 **LUX** at most. No, you can’t start shooting people with your 40 **LUX** warship. No pockets are that big.\n\n> **TRICK WEAPON (2 VP)**: This weapon… it’s a FAKE! The real weapon… is INSIDE OF IT! You crack open your weapon, revealing a separate weapon. Your **STRIFE ABSTRATA** can have two **ABSTRATA UPGRADES** in a single encounter, not one. This second **ABSTRATA UPGRADE** still costs **LUX**, and it\'s applied to your weapon automatically while in your inventory. If someone ever steals it, they can apply it to their own weapon for **[Free]**, unless it already has an **ABSTRATA UPGRADE**.\n\n> **HEMOCONDIMENT POUCHES (2 VP)**: This is it. You’re done for. You’ve been stabbed, right in the kidney! There’s blood! Blood everywhere!!! And it smells oddly like… ketchup? This **[Consumable]** item prevents **[Bloodied]**, though it takes a **[Reaction]** to activate. Alternatively, you can eat one to **[Heal]** 1 **HP**.\n\n> **HELICOPTER HAT (3 VP)**: SMELL YA LATER, GOOFBALLS! You **[Fly]** away. This counts as a 1 HORSEPOWER TINY VEHICLE that uses **+RAS** to pilot.\n\n> **MASK OF MISDIRECTION (4 VP)**: Whether it\'s cleverly applied makeup, a different outfit, or even a literal mask, you have ways of making sure people don\'t recognize you. All **[Analyze]** rolls targeting you are **[Tiered Down]**. But watch out! If an opponent tries to **YOINK** something from you and retrieves this, they’ll probably be able to tell you’re a spy!'),
('galacticGibberish', 'GALACTIC GIBBERISH', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Passive]', 'The, uh, the– hey, what about SPIDER… KILL… QUEEN… THE SLAYER? Spiderkillqueen the Slayer. Ever hear of her? Oh, she’s super popular? You knew that! You’ve come to realize that… man, you can just make shit up on Alternia, and people will believe you! Just mince words together, and if the nouns are scary enough, it becomes believable. Your **[Manipulate]** rolls are never **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]** or **[Nerfed]** against trolls. You can pick up one **[Open]** move that gives you WORDPLAY effects when you take this move, usually from a caste you have a close friend in.'),
('galahadToDoItToEm', 'GALAHAD TO DO IT TO EM', 'OTHER', 'KNIGHT', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Knight]', 'If you’re going to be a negativity sponge for others for the sake of helping your loved ones, it helps to still have good vibes. Nobody should see that you’re cracking beneath the surface and taking the blows to heart. You’ve gotta play it cool, kid. When you\'re hit, you may retain up to half your **[WHAM]** rounded down, to a minimum of 1. Consecutive hits from multiple parties stack, but you always retain at least **1 [WHAM]** until your next turn.\r\n\r\n'),
('galaxyBrain', 'GALAXY BRAIN', 'MIND', 'MIND', '[Aspect][Ultra][Locked: Mind]', 'You’ve accepted that intelligence comes from many different places; the academics, the empaths, the crafters, the instinctual— all forms of intelligence are equal to one another in different ways. And while perfection is wonderful, it’s also difficult to obtain, so being willing to let things not work perfectly is a big step to making it perfect in the long run. You’re able to wind up a perfect plan while you’re multitasking; you can spend the last action of your turn to gain **1 [Hold]**. This **[Hold]** acts as a special kind of **[Boost]** that acts as a **[Tier Up]**; **one [Hold]** spent alone **[Tiers Up]** once, **two [Hold]** **[Tiers Up]** twice, **three [Hold]** **[Tiers Up]** three times, etc. You can stack these **[Holds]** up as much as you like, even pushing into **MAX** rolls; however, just like **[Boost]**, you must spend it all at once. An opponent can choose to reduce your **[Holds]** by 1 by making you use your **[Drag]**; this takes an action to do, and can’t be done when you trade in your **[Hold]** for **[Tier Ups]**, working at an exchange rate of 2 **[Drag]** : 1 **[Hold]**.'),
('gamersRiseUp', 'GAMERS RISE UP', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Psionic][Locked: Battery] \r\n', 'What? You think you’re going to walk on the ground? Like some kind of NORMIE? You’ve harnessed your laserlike energy to hoist you into the air, silhouetting you with crackling power. It’s actually quite terrifying! You are able to use an action to begin **[Flying]**. You think that you look COOL as FUCK like this and gain **1 CHARGE** upon gaining the **[Flying]** condition.'),
('gayBabyJailer', 'GAY BABY JAILER', 'KID', 'KID', '[Template][Basic][Free][Locked: Kids on Bikes]', 'Stop that! Cut it out! What the hell do you think you\'re doing! Where did you get a chainsaw! You can\'t just run around having a \"villain arc\", you\'re a human child! Alternia has a bad effect on some kids, and... Yeah, this is insane. You\'re taking them back to the moon and putting them in time out. When you defeat a Kid in a strife, you can choose to bring them back to the moon and, with the approval of other neighborhood watch members, put them in timeout. While in timeout, they can\'t leave the school for a month, stuck in detention. They don\'t have access to weapons or items, just boring textbooks and food. That\'s what you get for burning down Macy\'s. You know how much Buildgrist we\'ll need to remake that? Additionally, you can mark another Kid as a TROUBLEMAKER, which if confirmed by Kids on Bikes high command (the adults!) will grant all Kids on Bikes a **+2 [Buff]** against this opponent until they are brought to detention or the situation is resolved through another manner.'),
('gazeBack', 'GAZE BACK', 'OTHER', 'SEER', '[Class][Basic][Free][Reaction][Locked: Seer]', 'Ohhoho… I notice that you noticed that I noticed you noticing me! Whenever someone rolls **[Analyze]** on you, you can choose not to **[Tier Down]** their roll if you have POKER FACE, letting them get a proper read on you. In exchange, you may use one of your next turn\'s actions to receive the same result on PROBLEM SLEUTHING without needing to roll yourself. This triggers any additional benefits you would normally get when **[Analyzing]** as well if you have them.\r\n\r\n'),
('genealogicalHero', 'GENEALOGICAL HERO', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][One-Off][Mental]', 'Do you know what basically all other trolls don\'t have that you do? Uh, a living ancestor. Violetbloods are basically immortal, and guess what— you\'re 90% sure you know who your last exact genetic copy is, cuz they\'re still out there and kicking, lol! Fuckin\', Indigos or whatever, who act like it\'s some spiritual achievement to find your Ancestor, lmao. It\'s not even hard for you! Violets are EXTREMELY well documented. Your Ancestor is cool and awesome and amazing, so yeah!!!! Sweet! Select a phrase that best suits who your Ancestor is— WARMONGER, TYRANT, BEAST, NOBILITY, MARTYR, or WITCHMASTER. When you want to emulate how cool and awesome your descendant is, roll **+GRA**.\n\n**MIN**: You remember a war crime your Ancestor did, or some other problematic action. NOOO! You feel **[Despair]** for **3 turns**. \n\n**BAD**: You\'re pretty sure that your Ancestor apologized for the war crime. Still, you feel **[Dread]** for **3 turns**.\n\n**OK**: Wait, who\'s your Ancestor again? Ah, the moment has passed. Nothing happens.\n\n**GOOD**: YOUR ANCESTOR? YEAH, YOU\'RE JUST LIKE THEM. THEY\'RE A REAL…\n\n> **BEAST**: More monster than man, really! Your SPOT rolls are **[Talented]** and **[Tiered Up]**, even to a **MAX**, for the rest of the encounter. \n\n> **MARTYR**: They died… for a heroic, noble cause! Whenever you take more than **2 damage** in a turn for the rest of the encounter, you take **1 [Boost]**.\n\n> **NOBILITY**: Yup! Your Ancestor rules entire planets, dude! Your **[Manipulate]** rolls **[Tier Up]**, and opponent **[Manipulate]** rolls **[Tier Down]**.\n\n> **TYRANT**: Oh god. Yeah, uh, your Ancestor also rules entire planets. But they\'re, uh, less interested in ruling, and more in… punishing people who didn\'t wanna be ruled. Yikes. Whenever an enemy uses **[Boost]**, you get **1 [WHAM]**.\n\n> **WARMONGER**: Oh gracious. Your Ancestor doesn\'t even care about the ruling. They just love to fight. Whenever someone gets **[WHAM]** around you, so do you.\n\n> **WITCHMASTER**: Okay, you. Your Ancestor does some weird fuckshit. You become **[Talented]** at **[Magic]** for the encounter. If you already were **[Talented]** at **[Magic]**, your moves become **[Tiered Up]**.\n\n**GREAT**: JEGUS, you love your Ancestor. You get a **GOOD**, but this move is **[Free]**. \n\n**MAX**: Not just your ancestor— but your ancestor\'s ancestor, and their ancestors before them! You recall your entire heritage, and get a **GREAT** with two options, not just one. The second option isn\'t set in stone like the first.'),
('gestaltPlayer', 'GESTALT PLAYER', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Passive]', 'You know what? Yeah, you don\'t really get yourself. Why do you do some of the dumb shit things you do? Who fucking knows! But you\'re willing to lean into it and do even more dumb shit, because fuck it, right? And why be one thing when you can be TWO! BITCH!!!!!!!! Choose one **[Zodiac]** choice such as Aspect or Class that you do not belong to. You take one move from this Aspect or Class. You can take this move twice, but only ever from one aspect, one class, or both, and only ever **[Basic]** moves.'),
('getAwayFromThem', 'GET AWAY FROM THEM!', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Passive]', 'NOBODY TOUCHES MY FRIENDS! You’re channeling that innate ferocity you were trained from hatching to have into beneficial places– namely, protecting your loved ones. Fiercely, even! Whenever an opponent gets a **GREAT** roll against an ally in a TEAM STRIFE, you have a **+1 [Buff]** on rolls against them next turn. What the FUCK is up, bitch? They wanna hurt your friends? Sleep with one eye open!'),
('getCreative', 'GET CREATIVE', 'SPACE', 'SPACE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Space]', 'Why stick to the traditional? Try something new! Instead of fighting through pure force, you might try to silly it up! Instead of setting up goofs for the sake of goofs, try wrestling your opponents into tight spots! Choose two moves, like SHENANIGANS and GRIEF— or moves you have from other sources— that use two different stats to roll, and swap their stats. This is a permanent change as you let your art forms swap up the way you face the world!'),
('getHecked', 'GET HECKED', 'OTHER', 'PRINCE', '[Class][Basic][Free][Locked: Prince]', 'Sometimes the best attack isn\'t the one that does the most harm, but the one that ensures victory will come later. You\'ve mastered the art of toying with your food and leaving them open to attack, debilitating them with each blow. On a **GREAT** or **MAX** **[Strife]**, you may choose to gain **1 [Drag]** in exchange for inflicting **1 [Weakness]** of your choice (i.e. **[Somatic]**, **[Mental]**, **[Psychic]**) on the enemy for 2 turns. This only stacks up to 2 per **[Weakness]** type. \r\n\r\n'),
('getInTheRobot', 'GET IN THE ROBOT', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Passive][Unlock: Pilot]', 'Wow! Cool robot! You are a pilot, and the things you pilot are the single most deadly vehicle on all of Alternia: a motherfucking mecha. The purpose of the mecha is manifold; to protect underwater dwellings from seamonsters. To prepare for leading colonization efforts off-world. To flex on the poorbloods who can\'t afford a motherfucking mecha. You get the idea. Piloting a MECHA takes some serious bulge; you are **[Talented]** at **+HUB**. You have a MECHA, a special type of Vehicle that is used exclusively in combat. The MECHA has 1 HORSEPOWER, can carry a single passenger (that\'s you!), and is about 16 feet tall. The design is otherwise up to you; maybe it\'s a giant robot troll with a sword. Maybe it\'s a mechanical spider crab with a swiveling torso. Maybe it\'s a mechaseagoat. Who knows! You can call your MECHA down from orbit to assist you as an action. It automatically scoops you up and lets you pilot it when you do. As with other vehicles, the only **[Physical]** moves you can make inside a MECHA is VEHICULATE or SWASHBUCKLE. Your MECHA always has **10 HP**; unlike regular Vehicles, you also take the damage the MECHA takes in combat, thanks to the neural link you have with the vehicle. Rolling GUTSUCKERY only heals you, not the Mecha. Upon the MECHA being destroyed, you are safely launched out and can fight on if you have the HP for it. You don\'t need to STEER to RAM an opponent who isn\'t inside a vehicle. You can apply ABSTRATA UPGRADES to your MECHA, as if it was your own weapon. A **MIN** VEHICULATE roll only damages the MECHA, nobody else. Physical conditions apply to your MECHA while you are piloting it. Finally, you can upgrade your MECHA’s engine or features as if it were a regular Vehicle. Throw your money at this ridiculously expensive weapon, go for it! If your MECHA is destroyed, it is repaired at the end of the encounter. Be sure to give your MECHA an over-the-top, ridiculous name.'),
('getOutOfMySchool', 'GET OUT OF MY SCHOOL', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Passive][Locked: Bully]', 'Ohhhhhhhrrghhh YESSSS. The single best trope: the tough bitch catches feelings for the softie!! AND THEY DON\'T KNOW HOW TO PROCESS IT!! SO THEY JUST LIKE, THEY FIGHT OFF BAD GUYS FOR THEIR CRUSH, AND THE CRUSH IS LIKE \"wow bully you saved me\" AND THEY GET ALL RED IN THE FACE AND GO \"HAHA NO PROBLEM!!!!\" AND THEN THEY DON\'T ADDRESS THE TENSION BETWEEN THEM BUT THEY OCCASIONALLY SHOOT EACH OTHER LOOKS AND (buries face in pillow). Choose another person you may or may not have romantic feelings for, or otherwise a close quasiplatonic bond. You are **[Enthusiastic]** any time you are around this person, or if they/a specific thing they like (coffee, skateboards, etc; choose ONE thing when you take this move) are mentioned. This becomes **[Passionate]** if the person takes any damage. GET AWAY FROM THEM, JERKWAD!'),
('getReal', 'GET REAL', 'DERSE', 'DERSE', '[Sway][Passive][Locked: Derse]', 'People are too happy-go-lucky and saccharine, sometimes. Get real! Grow up! Your pessimistic nature hampers people’s enthusiasm; if they have **[Boost]**, they lose 1 point of **[Boost]** every **3 turns** as their enthusiasm slowly saps away. This move stops when they hit **0 [Boost]**, meaning that the counter only starts again once they have gained **[Boost]**.'),
('getTechnical', 'GET TECHNICAL', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Recharge: 3][Manipulate][Locked: Penpusher]', 'Let’s face it: you’re a desk jockey. You’re a bureaucrat. You’re a sales rep, or an accountant, or an administrator— and you LOVE it. Wanna hear your sweet elevator pitch for a new product? Hey, you look like you could use some know-how on personal boundaries in the office. The funny thing about insurance is there\'s no LAW that says you can\'t extort people. When you want to talk about what you know, roll the stat you gained from WORKPLACE WHIZ.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: I mean, it’s pretty obvious, right? The reason is… wait… no, was that… hmm… you’re… not actually sure? You become **[Confused]**!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You try to go off on a tangent and explain to them in great detail about some archaic law that’s barely related. They really don’t give a shit. Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Jegus, you can drone on, huh? Your target takes **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: They make the mistake of listening to you, but don\'t absorb anything. Either they take **2 [Drag]**, or you gain **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Oh, gog, they not only listen, they try to understand you. Either take the effects of a **GOOD**, make the target **[Overwhelmed]**, or you become **[Enthusiastic!]**\r\n\r\n**MAX**: They really, reeeeeally try to understand you. And it doesn’t work. The target experiences **[Sensory Overload]**. You\'ve only just entered the depths of your interest; you\'re **[Passionate]**!'),
('getThroughMeFirst', 'GET THROUGH ME FIRST', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Open][Recharge: 3][Physical]', 'You might be able to survive a shopping mall being thrown at you… but your friends super can\'t! Not everyone has had access to the same care and training as you have, so you\'re gonna step up and protect your allies. When you want to take damage for them, roll **+GRT**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: YOU PUSH YOUR ALLY INTO IMMEDIATE PERIL. DIPSHIT. Your ally takes **2 [Somatic]** damage!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: No, don\'t— ouch. Great work. Your ally takes **1 [Somatic]** damage thanks to your interference.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Oh no… you didn\'t get there in time! Such a shame…\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You throw yourself in the way, blocking incoming damage for your ally. You gain **1 [Hold]** you can spend for **[Free]** when someone attacks an ally. You take the hit instead of them, **[Tiering Down]** the **[Strife]** roll, and taking all effects that would have occurred to them. This happens regardless of your position in a TEAM STRIFE.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You really throw yourself into the damage, huh? This act of heroism inspires your ally; you get a **GOOD**, but the ally gains **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: GET THAT WEAK SHIT OUTTA HERE! You don\'t even take the hit— you knock the attack flying! You take no damage, and deal **2 [Somatic]** damage to the enemy instead. Your ally gains **3 [Boost]**, wowed by this!'),
('giddyUp', 'GIDDY UP!', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][One-Off][Locked: Draquestrian]', 'Faster, my beautiful dragon! To glory! With a few whispered words of encouragement, your Snazzard speeds the fuck up. It becomes **[Quickened]** and **[Proud]** for **two turns**. You are not affected by these conditions, just your Snazzard. This increases your HORSEPOWER by 1, stacking with ACCELERATE if needed.'),
('giftedTealSyndrome', 'GIFTED TEAL SYNDROME', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Passive]', 'For sweeps, your test results have always been the top of the top, and promised you great things. Now life is harder, and said promises seem like cruel mockery. But that\'s not actually a super bad thing. It means you\'ve grown, you\'ve changed; you\'re not just the perfect little specimen Schoolfeeding wanted to make out of you. You\'ve stopped forcing yourself to never fail. It\'s okay to fuck up, because in the end, the experiences you live are the ones that shape you, not the experiences theorised on an exam. When you get a **MIN** roll, your next roll is **[Tiered Up]**, even to a **MAX**, and when you get a **BAD** roll, your next roll has a **+2 [Buff]** to it.'),
('giftOfTheGab', 'GIFT OF THE GAB', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Passive][Locked: Folklorist]', 'You are an eloquent person! You\'d have to be, to be able to pick up the little bits and bobs left by lowbloods and collect them into a solid culture. You gain the following WORDPLAY effects.\r\n\r\n> **LISTEN**: Sometimes, the best way to start a conversation is to say nothing. You let the other person go ahead, and hear what they say. The target must roll a **+PLC** move next turn, targeting you; on a **GREAT**, this lasts **2 turns**, and on a **MAX**, they have no choice but to start a full conversation with you, turning this into a WORDPLAY encounter where no **[Physical]** rolls can be made.\r\n\r\n> **LEARN**: Just by hearing the target speak, you learn a fact about their beliefs and ideologies. You can **[Tier Down]** their next **[Manipulate]** roll as you figure out what they\'ll likely say next. This gives you **1 [Boost]** on a **GREAT** and 2 on a **MAX**.\r\n\r\n> **GOSSIP**: Word of mouth is a powerful thing! You can give false information to any one **[Analyze]** roll the target gets this encounter, but they don\'t know when. You can also avoid the target knowing if you\'re lying on a QUESTION roll. You can do this twice in a **GREAT** and thrice on a **MAX**.\r\n\r\n> **ARGUE**: It\'s like JAB, but you can keep doing it, even after combat starts!'),
('gimmieGimmie', 'GIMMIE GIMMIE', 'OTHER', 'PAGE', '[Class][Advanced][Free][Recharge: 2][Locked: Page]', 'Oh wow! It seems a lot of people like you! Or at the very least have come to pity you enough that they’ll begrudgingly help you. It’s really no difference to you, you’ll take help wherever you can get it! You’ve picked up that acting bumbling or plucky actually gets you a lot in life, and now can do it a bit more purposefully to get the things you want. Your friends willingly offer their help to you... And if they don’t? Well you know how to do a mean puppy dog eyes brother! Oh, pwease won’t you shware? Blink blink blink... When one of your allies gains **[Boost]**, **[WHAM]**, or an **[Emotion]** that you would like to benefit from too, you can gain it alongside them. You cannot use this move on a troll you\'re already getting **[Boost]** from, like in the case of moves such as **BROTHERS IN ARMS**.\r\n'),
('glaresplosion', 'GLARESPLOSION', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Psionic][Strife][Locked: Draquestrian]', 'Your Snazzard\'s crimson eyes glow, and… PTEW! Lasers! If looks could kill— OH WAIT YES THEY CAN! Your Snazzard grows in power, and becomes **[Talented]** at **+IMG**. When you want to PTEW PTEW your opponent, roll **+IMG**. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: AUUUYIIOOUUUGGGHHHH— a flash of blinding light dazzles you, the rider. In a tragic accident, you are **[Blinded]** and take **2 [Laser]** **[Somatic]** damage. In high stakes RP, the effects may even be permanent..?\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Augh, fuck, that\'s bright. You take **1 [Laser]** **[Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Cool laser light show! No hits, though! You gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: PEW!! A direct hit! That\'s **1 [Laser]** **[Somatic]** damage. Very nice!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: PEWWWW!! An even director hit! That\'s **2 [Laser]** **[Somatic]** damage, or **1 [Laser]** **[Somatic]** damage that **[Blinds]** the opponent for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: GODDAMN. You practically sear this motherfucker’s eyeballs! That\'s **3 [Laser]** **[Somatic]** damage, and the opponent is **[Blinded]** for **2 turns**. Maybe forever, if it\'s cool for the story...'),
('glassHalfempty', 'GLASS HALF-EMPTY', 'DERSE', 'DERSE', '[Sway][Passive][Unlock: Derse]', 'You’re more of a skeptic than some of your peers. How can you be certain that things are going to be okay? You prefer to show a little bit of caution, always suspicious of a worst case scenario; at worst, you’re well-prepared, and at best, you’re pleasantly surprised. When you make someone use **[Drag]**, you can choose how much of it they use; for example, if they have **4 [Drag]**, you can choose to only make them spend 2 of it, keeping another 2 in reserve. Just in case.'),
('glassHalffull', 'GLASS HALF-FULL', 'PROSPIT', 'PROSPIT', '[Sway][Passive][Unlock: Prospit]', 'You always look on the bright side of life! Things aren’t so bad, and it’s okay to smile, even in the darkest situations. So be happy and don’t worry! When you use **[Boost]**, you can choose how much of it you use; if you have **4 [Boost]**, you can choose to only spend 2 of it, keeping another 2 in reserve, just in case!');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('gloriousGrace', 'GLORIOUS GRACE', 'OTHER', 'HEROMODE', '', 'Speed, dexterity and poise; these are the attributes you prioritise in life. You are a creature of beautiful elegance mixed with frightening speed, and others would do well not to cross you! When you enter **HERO MODE**, select one of the following benefits.\n\n> **BURST OF MOVEMENT**: Flip, swing, kick, roll! You push yourself to the max! For the next 2 turns, all your **[Physical]** moves use **+GRA**.\n\n> **UNTOUCHABLE**: Skip to the side, bend over backwards, do a frontflip and SUPERHERO LAND! Nobody can hit you! For the next 2 turns, all **[Physical]** moves and **[Strife]** moves that deal **[Somatic]** damage against you are **[Godawful]**.\n\n> **BULLET-DODGE**: Ha! What they just hit… was an AFTER-IMAGE! You retroactively turn the opponent\'s last **[Physical]** move into a **MIN**. They also take 3 **[Drag]** in frustration.\n\n> **OUTPACE**: \"React\"? The opponent doesn\'t have TIME to react! For the next 3 turns, your opponent can\'t use **[Reactions]**.\n\n> **PERFECT POISE**: Just like you can move extremely fast, you also know how to hold yourself perfectly still. You stop moving, forgoing all of your actions for a number of turns of your choosing. You gain 4 **[Boost]** and 1 **[WHAM]** each turn you don\'t act. You can\'t lose **[Boost]** or **[WHAM]** while staying still. You don\'t speak, and your eyes are closed as you focus hard. You become either **[Serene], [Numb]** or **[Out-Of-Control]** when you finally open your eyes and attack!'),
('glubglubbery', 'GLUBGLUBBERY', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Recharge: 3][Psionic][Strife][Locked: Deep-Sea]', 'Your kind has a strange connection to G\'lbgolyb, the Fuchsia Lusus, and guardian to the heiress. Perhaps her influence is why Violets in the deep are able to change like you are, the whispers of ancient gods coiling your form… or maybe it\'s nothing but a coincidence! Regardless, your physiology has been able to replicate a much smaller and less apocalyptic Vast Glub, which you can use in combat! You can\'t apply **[WHAM]** to this move. When you want to cause some doom, roll **+GRT**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: YOU\'VE DOOMED YOURSELF, IDIOT! You take **3 [Freaky]** **[Psychic]** damage immediately.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You\'ve doomed yourself again! It\'ll take some time to hit, but you\'re still DOOMED! In **3 turns**, you take **3 [Freaky]** **[Psychic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Cough cough. Wait, try that again. You don\'t set off your **[Recharge]**, but nothing else happens.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Doooooom! Your voice glubs out an echoing portent of The Rift\'s Barnacle. Every opponent who hears you takes **3 [Freaky]** **[Psychic]** damage in **3 turns**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Your gills flutter and your throat burbles out an awful, unknowable sound I dare not repeat. Every opponent who hears you takes **4 [Freaky]** **[Psychic]** damage in **3 turns**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: The sound begins in your buoyancy sac, then rises like bile into a horrible song, the music of the things that scourge the trenches of deep underwater. Oh, ye gods, have mercy! Every opponent who hears your song takes **5 [Freaky]** **[Psychic]** damage and becomes **[Blinded]** in **3 turns**. Ia! Ia!'),
('goldenKid', 'GOLDEN KID', 'OTHER', 'HEIR', '[Class][Passive][Unlock: Heir]', 'Hey, check yourself out! You\'re pretty on top of things, aren\'t you? Your aspect, specifically - you\'re all about it, pretty much without trying to be. So while those other classes bumble about, all busy with their \'moves per level\' and their \'gradual character development\'... you\'re mostly just breezing on through. When you take this entry, you automatically get your **[Aspect]**’s **[Unlock]** move, as well as two **[Basic]** moves and an **[Advanced]** move from your **[Aspect]**- all for free! Life\'s good, and it can only get better from here!\r\n'),
('goldInTheShell', 'GOLD IN THE SHELL', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Ultra][Recharge: 3][Locked: Cyberpunk]', 'With the amount of modding you\'ve done to your body, are you even a troll anymore? The memories you have- they feel real, but are they actually? Could they be implanted with code that you made yourself to forget the pain? Are you even you? Was it better to live life as you did before you started \"upgrading\" yourself? The answer to all the above is LOL NAH you\'re fine. Hey, look, you\'ve modded it so that you\'ve got a built-in voice changer in your larynx! **BEEP BEEP CHECK IT OUT**. Hilarious! You gain HERO MODE through the stat you became **[Talented]** at from NEONLIBERAL. You also get the following upgrade based on what **[Talent]** you took with NEONLIBERAL. \r\n\r\n> **GOOFINATOR (+RAS)**: You\'re a silly goofy funny cyborg with stretchy limbs and a preprogrammed laugh track. You gain access to all moves that give new SHENANIGANS effects in the game, even **[Locked]** ones (though you only gain SHENANIGANS effects, no additional ones). You gain 1 now.\r\n\r\n> **VIRTUAL.SOUL (+PLC)**: You aren\'t just coated by your hologram anymore… you ARE the hologram. Seriously, the real you is at home projecting this hard light hologram around, it\'s kind of crazy. When you send out a hard light hologram of yourself into the world, **[Physical]** moves against you are **[Inept]**. You can still take damage like this, though— it\'s real enough that you can feel it. Your **[Physical]** moves are similarly **[Inept]** like this.\r\n\r\n> **AEROBUILD (+GRA)**: You\'ve got wings now. That\'s really all I gotta say about that. You can **[Fly]** at will; your speed lets you act as a VEHICLE with 4 HORSEPOWER and can carry one other passenger. You use **+GRA** to VEHICULATE. If you had an INSTALLED Vehicle, you can refund it and upgrade yourself now.\r\n\r\n> **ENTROPYCYCLER (+APP)**: You\'ve got a micronuclear plant inside you where your squigglysloosh used to be. Who even needs internal organs? You can spend **2 [Boost]** to roll GUTSUCKERY past its first use, ignoring the **[One-Off]** tag as you fire up your inbuilt energy source and run a self-repair subroutine.\r\n\r\n> **TEMPORUNNER (+HUB)**: Everything is the matrix to you, thanks to this sweet implant that connects to your visual cortex and speeds your brain up to match your body\'s chrome reflexes. As a **[Free]** action, you can push yourself into hyperspeed - you are **[Quickened] twice for the turn**, and opponents can\'t **[React]** to you as you move so fast they hardly see it. At the end of the turn, though, you take **1 [Unblockable] [Somatic]** damage, plus an extra 1 damage for every other time you\'ve used this effect in the encounter, as your tech strains and overloads.\r\n\r\n> **TITANBORG (+GRT)**: You are so fucking big and scary it\'s unbelievable. When you hit **4 HP** or lower, you become **[Out-Of-Control]**, but you can control your actions as normal, and you take **1 less damage** (min. 1) from all sources, even **[Unblockable]**. Hulk out! \r\n\r\n> **FUTURESCANNER (+PSP)**: You are, basically, omniscient. With these new mechanical eyes, you can see timelines unfold before you. It\'s kind of sick. At the start of every turn, your opponent must declare what they\'re going to roll on their next turn, and can\'t deviate from that. \r\n\r\n> **REALITYDRIVE (+IMG)**: Reality, schmeality! You\'ll replace it with your own, thanks to your heavily altered nervous system that glows through your skin. All of your +IMG Rolls **[Tier Up]**, but all opponents **[Tier Down]**. This only happens on the first turn of TEMPOSLINGER in HERO MODE if you try to use it then. Nice try.\r\n'),
('goneGrimdark', 'GONE GRIMDARK', 'OTHER', 'GRIMDARK', '[Template][Passive][Eerie][Unlock: Grimdark]', 'Something really traumatic has happened to you in the past. Something even more so than usual- your quadrants killed each other, you witnessed a genuine atrocity or were forced to do something truly horrific. But in your lowest moment, your soul reached out and struck a dark, dark bargain with the only forces black enough to understand the hole in your heart: The Horrorterrors. You are permanently **[Numb]** and can no longer benefit from or be penalized by any other Emotions, ever. As a single action, you may enter A MODE MOSTE GRIM. Your skin turns black, your hair turns white, your eyes glow with cold, unearthly light. When you speak, it\'s not in any tongue a mortal can comprehend. You are beyond them now. All parties around you take the **[Despair]** and **[Scared]** conditions, aside from TIT or BUSTIN\' trolls. You do **+1 [Freaky] [Psychic]** damage with all attacks and may begin **[Flying]** as an action. Upon activation of A MODE MOSTE GRIM, a countdown begins, lasting 5 turns. At the end of these 5 turns, a PARANORMAL ACTIVITY **[Hazard]** is summoned - the ghosts of your long dead emotions, your past, your relationships, all that was once good in your life rise up and begin to subsume you and those around you in painful, clawing regret. Optionally, and only if agreed on out of character, this can instead summon any number of Bustin\' trolls in place of the GAGGLE, dispatched to deal with the spike in eldritch energy detected.'),
('gonnaGetcha', 'GONNA GETCHA', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Subjugglator]', 'Where the hell do you think YOU’RE going? HONK HONK HONK. You refuse to let prey get away, no matter what. Your LET’S STRIFE rolls to CAN’T ABSCOND, BRO use your **+GRT**, not your **+GRA**. You also count as a 2 HORSEPOWER vehicle, meaning you can chase down bitches who try to get away via vehicle… ON FOOT. Your HORSEPOWER increases to 3 if you are **[Enraged]**, and 4 if you are **[Out-Of-Control]**. VEHICULATE uses **+GRT** rather than **+HUB** while you are running. Obviously, you can’t use Vehicle Upgrades on yourself, but you CAN carry a smaller troll on your back if you reduce your HORSEPOWER by 1.'),
('goodListener', 'GOOD LISTENER', 'BLOOD', 'BLOOD', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Blood]', 'You know that despite your own life being difficult… you really ARE a great person to talk to about your problems. Like, sure, bluh bluh look at you, you can’t take your own advice, but… sometimes you don’t need to take your own advice, or give any out. Sometimes, you just need to talk to someone and let them tell you what needs to be told. Here, let’s sit backwards in a chair to communicate that your presence in the conversation is humble and nonthreatening, and yet frank and attentive. You can take an action to invite someone to talk about their problems to you, which costs them a **[Lengthy]** action; they can either accept or deny. Accepting gives you 3 free **GOOD** PROBLEM SLEUTHING questions as you listen closely to their grievances and figure out how to help them; the target gets **5 [Boost]**.'),
('goodsbreakers', 'GOODSBREAKERS', 'OLIVE', 'ADULT', '[Olive][Locked: Adult]', 'Creatures far and wide, you\\\'re gonna want these powders! Powders, powders for sale here! You\\\'re a merchant getting your start here in this part of the universe. Whether it be selling artisanal goods you\\\'ve crafted yourself or being the middleman for some colder-blooded corporate entity, a Goodsbreaker can and will sell anything. So for the love of grub, please buy these powders before your higher ups notice you haven’t sold a thing.\nYou gain a new **GOOD WORDPLAY** result. So long as you have something in your sylladex, you can force someone to \\\'buy\\\' it off of you. It\\\'s one of a kind! They want it so bad! They want it so bad that if this item would make a person go over the amount of **VP** they can hold, they must throw out things until they can fit the item in their sylladex. If you use this as a **GREAT WORDPLAY** result, you can also request **LUX** or Treasure. Roll a 1d8. On an odd number, they owe you 1 **LUX** or **Treasure I**. On an even number, they owe you 2 **LUX** or **Treasure II**. If they\\\'re unable to pay this, they become **[Sad]** as they think about how horrifically poor they are.'),
('goodVsEvil', 'GOOD VS. EVIL', 'HOPE', 'HOPE', '[Aspect][Basic][Just Like Discord Debates!][Locked: Hope]', 'The world is black and white. Everyone in it is either a hero or a villain. There are no middle grounds, and you more than anyone else are keenly aware of that. Only a hero deals in absolutes, after all! You can take an action to tell whether or not a target would sooner identify as a hero or villain- that is to say, someone who agrees with your morals or not. If they are like you, you trust them completely, no questions asked. Their **[Manipulate]** rolls against you **[Tier Up]**, and you gain **2 [Boost]** now and at the start of every encounter with them. If they are not like you, they cannot be trusted! Their **[Manipulate]** rolls against you **[Tier Down]**, and you gain **1 [WHAM]** now and at the start of every encounter with them. This effect lasts until extraordinary proof to the contrary. You can manually assign a target as “like you”, even if they’d choose to count themselves as “unlike” you as you completely overlook their flaws. Not the other way, though; your friends can do no wrong.'),
('goodWithGrubs', 'GOOD WITH GRUBS', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Passive]', 'You\'ve spent a lot of time being raised to know how to help out with wrigglers, even if you don\'t really do it these days. As such, you have a good feel for how to deal with everyone, since all trolls are just… big wrigglers. Your **[Manipulate]** rolls are never **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]** or **[Nerfed]**.'),
('gottaCatchEmAll', 'GOTTA CATCH EM ALL', 'OTHER', 'FIDUSSPAWNER', '[Template][Physical][Basic][One-Off][Locked: Fiduspawner]\r\n', 'At its heart, Fiduspawn is a collecting game. Of course, this was easier to do when the game was entirely for bronzes who can speak to lusii with ease, but that didn’t stop them from making it accessible to everyone, and the only obvious solution… Is theft. That’s right. When you’re in an encounter with a lusii, monster, rival fiduspawner, etc. you can try and steal that data to make your own version of it! You can send this captured creature out in place of your normal fiduspawn. It stays with you across encounters until defeated. You can have up to 5 of these collected at a time, though you can only send out one at a time in an encounter. It takes an action to swap them out. When you want to steal Fiduspawn, roll **+HUB**.\n\n**MIN**: Hah! You did… Not do it, actually, oh god. You copied its data in your oogonibomb, but it hatched immediately! And angry! You make a copy of whatever it was you were trying to, but it is immediately deployed and hostile towards only you. Both it and the original become **[Enraged]**.\n\n**BAD**: You throw your ball and… It bonks them on the head harmlessly, but it can choose to become **[Enraged]** because ow!\n\n**OK**: You weakly toss out the captured egg and… It’s enough to make a weak monster not freak out? You copy the data of a LEVEL 0 Monster, which you can later hatch and tame as your own, following the MY LITTLE MONSTER rules. If this was used against anything other than a LEVEL 0 Monster, nothing happens.\n\n**GOOD**: Now we’re talking! You threw your data egg and it began copying over all it needs to create a perfect copy of a LEVEL 1 or lower Monster, as well as other Fiduspawn without the HYPEREVOLUTION move. Otherwise, nothing happens.\n\n**GREAT**: Critical capture! Nice! You snag yourself something powerful to use later. You can capture a LEVEL 2 or lower Monster, as well as Fiduspawn without the HYPEREVOLUTION move!\n\n**MAX**: Did you just use a Master Oogonibomb on this one?? You manage to capture a LEVEL 3 or lower Monster, or a HYPEREVOLVED Fiduspawn for your own personal use! Jeez!'),
('gotYourBack', 'GOT YOUR BACK', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'Hey! Relax. You don\'t need to take everything on yourself. We\'re a team, remember? It\'s okay to rely on others, sometimes. That\'s what the team is for! You\'ve come to appreciate that you don\'t always need to lead others; you can let them lead you too. When you are in a TEAM STRIFE, increase your team\'s HP by 2.'),
('governmentAgentEnemies', 'GOVERNMENT AGENT ENEMIES', 'KID', 'KOB', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Kids on Bikes]', 'You have a single adversary: Government Agent Enemies. You abbreviate this to the GAEs.  The best way to overcome the oppressive fascist government (America/Alternia) with scary government officials (The CIA/The CIS) from dissecting aliens (Aliens/You) is through sheer japery. Just like in the movies. Your **[Chicanery]** rolls against Org trolls or Drones are **[Talented]**. If they were already **[Talented]**, you are **[Quickened]** against these enemies'),
('grandGodmodder', 'GRAND GODMODDER', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Ultra][Magic][Locked: Mary Sue]', 'The target rushes you… SLASH! That\'s it. A definitive kill. They got you. But what\'s this..?\r\n\r\n\\*It\'s a Hologram.\\*\r\n\r\nGoddammit! That\'s bullshit, what? Sorry, but the thing is… you want to feel strong. To feel awesome! And that comes before anything else— before fairness, before logic, before reality. You bend the rules to follow you, and that\'s that! You gain access to the HERO MODE for any one stat— not necessarily one you are **[Talented]** in. On top of that, you get two **[Holds]** at the start of every encounter. One **[Hold]** lets you immediately **[Tier Up]** any **OK** roll of yours to a **MAX**, and the other lets you retroactively make a **OK** roll of your opponents into a **MIN**. These both happen as you godmod the fuck out of the situation, revealing you actually have an immunity to bullets or some shit out of nowhere. You can\'t use these **[Holds]** if you aren\'t in your powered up form! Finally, your beliefs are especially firm; you only return to a regular troll when you hit a quarter of your max HP, not half.'),
('grandorphaner', 'GRANDORPHANER', 'VIOLET', 'ADULT', '[Violet][Locked: Adult] REQUIREMENTS: Orphaner', 'What? Did you think they ever stopped orphaning people? Gl\\\'bgolyb’s ravenous hunger demands both the carcasses of prey and the diligence of Her hunters taking down ever greater and more terrible opponents. As such, many Orphaners or violets frantic to evade the draft graduate into interstellar service in Her name, eschewing the expected duties of admiralty or royalty to travel the stars on a hunt that never ends; returning to Ringholme to bring back exotic beasts they have captured, small planets worth of meat or word from the furthest reaches of space they have heard of on their adventure. When defeating a level 2 or lower Lusus Monster, you may spare its life and capture it instead. At the expense of 6 **VP** you may bring it into battle alongside you at a later date; sharing **HP**, actions, **[Boost]** and **[Drag]**. The lusus uses your max **HP** and you may only capture one monster at a time. If the lusus is **[Overwhelmed]** or rendered **[Out-of-Control]** it will break out of your control, becoming hostile to everyone on the field.'),
('greatAdvice', 'GREAT ADVICE', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Open][Recharge: 3][Manipulate]', 'Hey, come on! Is that all you’ve got? You’ve seen ‘em all; people who don’t know how much what they’ve got is worth, people who know and don’t care how lucky they’ve got it… by now, you’ve learned some good advice on basically everything. When you want to call upon your business experience to advise people, roll **+APP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: TERRIBLE ADVICE! The target is set **[Ablaze]**. What did you do?!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Poor advice… better luck next time?\r\n\r\n**OK**: It’s not… the BEST advice, but they derive something from it! The target takes **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: That advice was actually pretty good! Your target cannot roll beneath a **GOOD** on their next turn; if they would have gotten lower, they take **2 [Drag]**. If they get a **GOOD** or higher anyway, they take **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: That wasn’t just good advice; it was **GREAT**! Your target cannot roll beneath a **GREAT** on their next turn; if they would have gotten lower, they take **2 [Drag]**. If they get a **GOOD** or higher anyway, they take **3 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: WHOA! That… was so fucking insightful and life-changing, holy shit! Did you write that out in advance?! Your target does not need to roll their next roll; it’s a **MAX**.'),
('greatExpectations', 'GREAT EXPECTATIONS', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Passive][Locked: Posh]', 'That\'s what everyone around you has for you! Which, uh. Is stressful! But at least you\'ve figured out how to play a sweet violin. Select a talent, and become **[Talented]** at the associated Universal Move. \r\n\r\n> **Scam Arts or Performing**: SHENANIGANS\r\n> **Acting or Art**: WORDPLAY\r\n> **Business or Cuisine**: GUTSUCKERY\r\n> **Fencing or Sport**: GRIEF\r\n> **Adventure or Nobility**: SWASHBUCKLE\r\n> **Literature or STEM**: PROBLEM SLEUTHING\r\n> **Music or Dance**: FRAYMOTIF'),
('greatImmuneSystem', 'GREAT IMMUNE SYSTEM', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive]', 'Hey man, you don’t wanna roleplay your troll being sick. No worries! You can just say “no” to roleplaying someone who’s ill! When you take a **[Slowburn]** AFFLICTION, you can instead say “nah I really don’t wanna” and become **[Exhausted]** instead. Nice work, body!'),
('greenThumb', 'GREEN THUMB', 'OTHER', 'HORTICULLTURIST', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Horticullturist]', 'Boy oh boy oh boy, you love being a menace and causing trouble with your great great friends, the plants! You’ve made a habit of feeding plant food to any plants in your vicinity, and now they do as you command sometimes, aiding you in your encounters. You gain the following **GOOD** SHENANIGANS effects.\r\n\r\n> **AM-BUSH**: Nope! Noooo! No you don’t!! Your opponent cannot go **[Hidden]** for **2 turns**, as plants immediately push them back into your line of sight. Thanks, guys!\r\n\r\n> **TATTLE-TILL**: Hey, hey! Have you heard about the Manchineel tree? What about the effects of eating castor oil plant seeds? Your opponent becomes **[Scared]** for **2 turns**, because… oh, god, why would you say that?!\r\n\r\n> **COMICALLY PLACED RAKE**: Whoa! What was that?! Your opponent steps on a rake and it hits them in the face, just like cartoons! They take **1 [Somatic]** damage and **[Embarrasses]** them for **1 turn**. This has the **[Strife]** tag.\r\n\r\n> **ROOTBOUND RUNNER**: Hk-! Something snags your opponent’s leg, whether it be a vine or a particularly sticky leaf, and trips them, rendering them **[Floorbound]**.'),
('grief', 'GRIEF', 'OTHER', 'UNIVERSAL', '[Strife][Physical]', 'Sometimes, words fail you. The natural order of things after that is to try to kill the other person really fucking hard. When you get into a physical fight, roll **+GRT**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You fuck up so horribly that you seriously hurt both your body and your pride. You take **2 [Somatic] damage** and **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You tumble around and, through your buffoonery, you take **1 [Somatic] damage**. Nice going, dipshit.\r\n\r\n**OK**: While you missed, you aren’t letting up, and you’re keeping everyone else on their toes. You gain **1 [WHAM]**!\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You hit ‘em! You do **1 [Somatic] damage** to the opponent! Nice!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Yikes! You hit them, and you hit them HARD. That’s **2 [Somatic] damage**!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Through terrifying force or sheer luck, you hit the target so hard that it could be considered a war crime on kinder planets. You do **3 [Somatic] damage**.\r\n'),
('grinAndBearIt', 'GRIN AND BEAR IT', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Open][Recharge: 2][Mental]', 'One of the best traits an umber troll like you can have is mental fortitude. You gotta take stuff in stride and put off the things on your mind until it\'s slightly more convenient. Mostly microaggressions. Also macroaggressions. When you want to exert your willpower, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: A… AAAARGHHHH- YOU\'VE JUST GOT SUCH A BIG BLOODPUSHER, NNNNOOOOO, IT HUUUURTS, AAAAGGGHHHHH. You gain the **[Heightened]** version of the incoming Emotion. If the incoming Emotion was already **[Heightened]**, you gain the stacking effect for that emotion.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Hrnnnhhh okay yeah no you feel it. \r\n\r\n**OK**: You put off the Emotion... Nnnnnmmmhhh, for only a moment, you got a lot of feelings. Okay, fine, fuck. The **[Emotion]** comes back in two turns. You take **1 [Drag]**.  \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Yeah, okay. You remove an **[Emotion]** effect in exchange for **1 [Drag]**. Take it on the chin and all that.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Pfft. Is that the best you can do, bud? The **[Emotion]** is cancelled entirely. You\'ve just heard it all before!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Pshhaw! Let\'s see how you like it, dipshit! You\'re so visibly unaffected that you get the opposite **[Emotion]**.'),
('growingFondness', 'GROWING FONDNESS', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'Your social skills are still maybe a little stunted, but… there\'s a few people you care about, and they care about you. Perfection and history aren\'t everything, you know— you need to make friends, too! Whenever an ally gives you **[Boost]**, they get that same **[Boost]** right back as you smile appreciatively at them, letting them know that you\'ve got their back too!'),
('grrBarkBarkBark', 'GRR BARK BARK BARK', 'OTHER', 'MOONBARK', '[Template][One-Off][Eerie][Unlock: Moonbark]', 'An ancient curse has entered your blood, and it has selected you to bear its face. You become a Lycantroll, the host to an evil magic that takes the form of an animal with your body- usually, a hellbarker, but other Moonbarks exist. Moonsharks with aquatic features, Moonlarks with piercing beaks, Moontigers with claws and the inability to rhyme… once per encounter, you can engage MOONBARK mode, trading some of your control to the evil spell in return for power, but not so much that you lose control! As an action, you gain the following effects:\r\n\r\nYour skin turns a dark thundercloud grey, and your fangs and nails look supernaturally white. You betray some signs of your hellish heritage, like a weird nose, shark fin, etc. You look more wolfman than werewolf right now, basically. You gain the **[Cullbait]** tag.\r\n\r\n> You gain SHARPKIND Claws and Fangs.\r\n> You are **[Talented]** in **+GRT**.\r\n> Any non-**[Eerie]** trolls who see your transformation become **[Scared]**.\r\n\r\n> When you are knocked to half HP, you enter a MOONFRENZY. Your curse refuses to let its host die, and instantly transforms you into a creature more monster than man. Shit. \r\n\r\n> You go from dark grey to bright white, like a lusus, and show monstrous changes. Fur, scales, reconstructed skeletal features- you name it. You gain the **[Cullbait]** tag, but trolls who did not see the transformation won\'t recognize you. Effects that affect Lusii also affect you.\r\n\r\n> You become **[Talented]** at **+GRT** (if you already were, you get **+1 damage**) and become **[Out Of Control]**.\r\n\r\n> You get the same Strife Abstrata as above; on a **GREAT** with your fangs, you can choose to do one less damage and expose the target to the MOONBARK MUMPS **[Affliction]**. Asshole.\r\n\r\n> You get **1 [Resistance]** to **[Somatic]** damage, immunity to **[Verbal]** damage and **1 [Weakness]** to **[Psychic]** damage.\r\n\r\n> You cannot flee from a fight- you continue fighting until knocked **[UNCONSCIOUS]** or all trolls around you are dead (or at least seem so).\r\n\r\nYou can escape MOONFRENZY mode with the help of a Quadrant you are in an Established Relationship with. They simply need to use an action as they either kiss, pap, slap, or talk you out of your frenzied state, leaving you **[Exhausted]** but otherwise normal.'),
('guardianihlator', 'GUARDIANIHLATOR', 'JADE', 'ADULT', '[Jade][Passive][Locked: Adult]', 'Guardianihlators are a pseudo-militia formed of jadebloods through the Alternian Empire’s civilian space far from the frontlines. You and your fellow members act as mediators between the Empire’s law enforcement and the public at large, in addition to aiding in the protection of colonies from wild beasts and terrors. Basically, you keep trolls safe… from the world around them, and their own foolish actions. On the first turn, you and your allies have 1 **[Resistance]** to ALL damage, which turns into 1 **[Somatic]** and **[Psychic] [Resistance]** for only you every other turn. Whenever you score a **MAX [Strife]** roll or knock an enemy down to half **HP** (rounded up), you gain **[Brave]** for 2 rounds. If you get a **MAX [Strife]** roll and knock the opponent under half **HP** in the same action, you become **[Heroic]** for the same duration.'),
('guardSlog', 'GUARD SLOG', 'VIOLET', 'ADULT', '[Violet][Locked: Adult]', 'The Empress does not need guards. She is a nigh-on god of a troll who has seen more than you and lived through worse than you could even imagine. If some idiot were somehow able to face her, they would die quicker than Zaraga Kuflon. Which is why no one is able to face her. That\\\'s what you\\\'re here for. Guard Slogs make weak foes abandon their plans, cull strong foes, and give anyone who overcomes them false confidence. You and your fellow Slogs have all partaken in a ritual of supping upon the waters from Gl\\\'bgolyb\\\'s personal brine pool, an event that has marked and changed you from within, so drink deep and be reborn unto a perfect soldier for the Empress. When in an encounter, you make all foes **[Terrified]** of you, bypassing immunities. You take a +1 **[Buff]** to rolls against **[Terrified]** enemies as you capitalize on their weakness, which increases to a +2 **[Buff]** if you already have a move which automatically makes enemies **[Scared]** or **[Terrified]**. Enemies lose **[Terrified]** if they deal damage equal to half your **HP** (rounded up). Additionally, choose one **UNIVERSAL MOVE**. Your ritual has made sure that you can never roll below an **OK** for this move.'),
('guidePride', 'GUIDE PRIDE', 'OTHER', 'SYLPH', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Sylph]', 'It\'s important to take pride in your accomplishments, and when your accomplishments are 90% making sure everyone around you is accomplishing accomplishments, your own accomplishments are left by the wayside!! There is!! Some vicarious pride that\'s going to have to take place! When any of your allies rolls a **MAX**, you automatically become **[Smug]** in response.\n\n'),
('guiltersGaze', 'GUILTER\'S GAZE', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][One-Off][Manipulate]', 'Is this really what you want? To hurt? Every troll on the planet is at some point cared for by Jadebloods; to attack them is to open yourself to a fucking complex and a half. You\'ve learned that the history of your caste does not just affect you, it affects everyone… and that can really help you in a bind. If you are **[Bloodied]** or take 3 or more damage from a single source, the **[One-Off]** tag resets and becomes a **[Recharge: 3]**. When you want to make someone feel bad, roll **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Haha! You look WEAK! The opponent gains **2 [WHAM]**, and you don\'t get to reset GUILTER\'S GAZE **[One-Off]** from this damage.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: They don\'t even care a little bit.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You make them feel… kinda shitty, but they\'ll get over it. They take **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Oogh. That\'s a pit in their stomach. The target takes a **-2 [Nerf]** to all **[Strife]** rolls for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You grasp your wound, cry out in pain, and then slowly look up at the aggressor with tears in your eyes. They HURT you. How could they? The target is **[Inept]** at all **[Strife]** rolls for **2 turns**. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: THEY FEEL TOO GUILTY. THE TARGET STARTS **[Crying]**. They\'re also **[Inept]** at all **[Strife]** rolls for **2 turns**.'),
('gutsuckery', 'GUTSUCKERY', 'OTHER', 'UNIVERSAL', '[Heal][Mental][One-Off]', 'You can\'t lose! You WON\'T lose! Alternia is a world that isn\'t going to play gently. So if you wanna get what you want, sometimes, you need to push yourself that little bit harder. Fight through the pain, satiate that hunger for battle! When you want to take a deep breath and keep fighting, roll **+APP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Okay, so turns out, the specific injury you had was worsened by you taking a deep breath. You take **2 damage**. Fuck!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You don\'t have time to recover! Keep hustling, bud! You waste this action.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Okay, you didn\'t do it very well this time, but ideally you\'ll feel better soon! You can attempt **GUTSUCKERY** again in **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You\'ll get what you desire! You\'re sure of it! You **[Heal]** **1 HP**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Victory is within sight. You WILL satiate your hunger for victory! You either heal **2 HP**, or any one **[Status]** effect of your choice.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: What\'s greedier than outliving all those who would beat you? Goddamn! You either heal **3 HP**, or lose all **[Status]** effects and **[Drag]**.'),
('habitualGloater', 'HABITUAL GLOATER', 'MIND', 'MIND', '[Aspect][Basic][Locked: Mind]', 'Nyahahah! Maybe if they were as SMART as you, this wouldn’t happen! Your intelligence brings with it some misplaced pride, and it’s grating to everyone. Any time you use a **+PSP** roll, you can spend an action cackling and gloating to gain a number of **[Boost]**; 2 for a **GOOD**, 3 for a **GREAT** and 4 for a **MAX**. Doing so gives everyone who witnessed this happen **1 [Drag]**.'),
('habitualSneak', 'HABITUAL SNEAK', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Advanced][Passive]\r\n', 'While you aren’t as afraid to exist in a space anymore, you have also learned when it’s time to keep a low profile. In order to be able to continue expressing yourself, you need to survive towards another night. You can choose to start an encounter **[Hidden]**, because you are just watching your opponent. While doing so, your rolls are all at a +1 **[Buff]**. In addition, when a combat encounter starts, you can make a **[Free] [Reaction] DUCK AND COVER** roll to instantly duck out of sight, if you have the move.\r\n'),
('halfdead', 'HALF-DEAD', 'OTHER', 'SHADOWDROPPER', '[Template][Passive][Eerie][Last Stand][Unlock: Shadowdropper]', 'Your body is wracked with the curse of Dropshadow Syndrome. Braaaains… braaaaaaaains… Nobody’s entirely sure of the source of your plight- weird magic? A virus? The fucking sun? Something else? Who knows! One way or another, you’re a zombie now, and you’re very hard to actually kill. Unless an opponent sets you **[Ablaze]**, you cannot be killed, and continue being conscious until you hit **-5 HP**, after which point your body is way too beaten up to go on. Jade Shadowdroppers do not retain their immunity to **[Ablaze]**. You’re also immune to **[Bloodied]**- all you have is a weird black goop. This stuff is the opposite of appetizing to Rainbowdrinkers. No blood here! They take the **[Disgusted]** condition when you would have become **[Bloodied]**, if present. You’re immune to the DAYTIME **[Hazard]**. On the flipside, you’re **[Slowed]** when you hit **0 HP** as you shuffle along at a slow and menacing gait, and cannot be **[Healed]**.'),
('halftimeComeback', 'HALF-TIME COMEBACK', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Passive][Locked: Jock]', 'Sure, just putting your opponent right in the dirt is flashy for a while, but everyone loves a late-game comeback, and you know how to put on a show. When you fall below half health (rounded down), the spirit of the classic underdog story seizes you. You gain an automatic **1 [WHAM]** at the start of every turn so long as you remain under half-health.'),
('hallowedHeroism', 'HALLOWED HEROISM', 'OTHER', 'HEROMODE', '', 'Limits schlimits! You are capable of the impossible, able to do things you never thought possible. Let\'s be frank— you\'re a big deal, and you are amazing. So let\'s do something amazing! When you enter **HERO MODE**, you may choose one of the following benefits.\n\n> **LIMIT-SMASH**: You pull off the ultimate move!! For one turn only, you only need to roll a 17+ to get a **MAX** move. If you don\'t get this **MAX**, you get 3 **[Boost]** as an apology.\n\n> **LAST MINUTE RECOVERY**: Can\'t fall here! You **[Heal]** 2 **HP** and lose any **[Physical]** conditions.\n\n> **TRY AGAIN**: Your stubbornness makes you a mighty opponent. You may use a **[One-Off]** roll you got an **OK** or lower at again.'),
('hallucinomancy', 'HALLUCINOMANCY', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Recharge: 3][Chicanery][Psionic][Locked: Haunted]', 'Whoah, check this out! You\'re able to do all sorts of spooky ooky stuff..! WOOGAH WOOGAH WOOGAH WOOGAH! People are already on edge around you; a little subtle psionic suggestion and here, a little illusory misdirection there, and bam, you\'ve got a fun little prank that\'ll really give people goosebumps! When you want to unnerve folks, roll **+RAS**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: …aw, cockbiters… you summoned a PARANORMAL ACTIVITY Hazard that is extremely pissed at you specifically… that\'s not a good prank… uh oh…\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You just kinda fumble, and it\'s not scary at all. Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You shout WOOGAH WOOGAH WOOGAH, that\'s gotta count for something. The target takes **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You jump up and hover for a moment, you stick your thumbs by your ears and waggle your palms, you stick out your tongue and your eyes glow white! This makes the target instantly piss and shit everywhere. Choose one of the following effects…\r\n\r\n> **BUMP**: Did you hear that..? You create an auditory hallucination which sounds pretty unsettling. The target loses one positive **[Emotion]** they have.\r\n> **BEHIND YOU..!**: You vanish from sight, only to appear directly behind the target, scaring the shit out of them. The target takes **2 [Drag]**.\r\n> **EYEFOG**: ALWAYS WATCHING NO EYES ALWAYS WATCHING NO EYES. You fill your target\'s vision with static, **[Blinding]** them.\r\n> **JUMPSCARE**: You start to shudder and shake… then your neck snaps to an impossible angle, your eyes go staticy black and you glide insanely quickly towards them while screaming. Fucking terrifying!!! The target becomes **[Overwhelmed]** for **2 rounds**.\r\n> **WOOGAH WOOGAH**: You warp your face and proportions in some Beetlejuice level bullshit. The target is **[Disgusted]** by this! \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA!!! You get a **GOOD**, and the **[Recharge]** of this move is only 1 now. You\'re raring for another scaring..!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Hey— hey, maybe relax..? This looks like… maybe too much?! You get a **GREAT**, but you also fuck their minds up real bad. They are under the effects of the DIMMING STARS Hazard.'),
('handOfAnanias', 'HAND OF ANANIAS', 'OTHER', 'SYLPH', '[Class][Basic][Recharge: 3][Heal][Locked: Sylph]', 'Your friends often rely on you to take care of you for the dumbest shit. Trip down some stairs and hurt your leg- the Sylph will fix it! Get into trouble with a drone? The Sylph will fix it! Talk to a Ghost who glows so bright it straight up blinds you? Ah, not to worry, the Sylph will fix it. And every time, you do, bailing your allies out of trouble. Maybe someday you\'ll leave them to learn from their mistakes… ah, but not today. The healing from this stacks with your HEALING AURA. You CANNOT use this move on yourself. Roll Roll **+PLC**, **PSP**, or **+IMG**.\n\n**MIN**: Oh dear. You accidentally cut yourself on a scalpel, stick your fingers together with wound glue, bonk yourself in the face with the medicalizer, or something else **[Humiliating]**. You take **1 damage** in addition to being too mortified to try and heal anyone with this move again for the encounter.\n\n**BAD**: Oh no, that\'s not what you meant to do- they won\'t hold still!! \n\n**OK**: Well, you can\'t heal them right now- what are you going to do, give them stitches in the middle of the fight?- but you can toss them a bottle of ibuprofen and either give them **+2 [Boost]** or take away up to 3 **[Drag]**.\n\n**GOOD**: Hello kitty band-aid, activate! You heal them for a flat **1 HP**.\n\n**GREAT**: Oof, time for the medicalizer. You heal them **+2 HP**. \n\n**MAX**: You are a full blown combat medic now, you guess. Hold still while you perform the world\'s fastest bullet extraction. They heal **+2 HP**, and either lose all their **[Drag]** or gain **+3 [Boost]**.'),
('handsOffApproach', 'HANDS OFF APPROACH', 'OTHER', 'SYLPH', '[Class][Advanced][Locked: Sylph]', 'You\'re learning that hovering over your allies might actually sort of be... a hindrance, rather than a help, so you\'re going to try something different. Something new. You\'re going to give them the best start you can, and then let. them. be. independent. Oh god this hurts you just to say, please don\'t make you regret this. When you heal an ally, you can choose to convert **2 HP** worth of healing into giving them **1 [Resistance]** of your choice instead. This lasts for the rest of the encounter. This effect stacks with armor, and can only be applied once to each ally. After you apply this **[Resistance]**, you may not target them with another **[Heal]** effect for **3 rounds**.\r\n\r\n'),
('happen', 'HAPPEN', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Recharge: 3][Chicanery][Locked: Goofball]', 'You see a lot of luck. Not always good luck, but hey, it’s luck! Stuff just seems to… HAPPEN when you’re around. Banana Peel? HAPPEN. Laptop explosion? HAPPEN. Falling down the stairs? HAPPEN. When you want to test your luck and see if something HAPPENs, roll **+RAS**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: OH NOOOO! Something HAPPENs… to YOU! Roll 1d8 from the **GOOD** table, and apply the effect to yourself.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Nothing HAPPENs. \r\n\r\n**OK**: Something extremely minor HAPPENs, and they just take **1 [Drag]**. Darn.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: H A P P E N! Roll 1d8, and apply the effect to the opponent.\r\n\r\n> 1. TUMBLE TUMBLE TUMBLE! The target hits the deck and becomes **[Floorbound]**.\r\n> 2. An embarrassing incident occurs! The opponent can’t use their last move again for **3 turns**!\r\n> 3. OOPS! All the opponent’s items are decaptchalogued onto the floor by an accidental misclick! \r\n> 4. Something really fucking funny happens, and the opponent is distracted for a moment. They are **[Stunned]**!\r\n> 5. Oop, someone is getting a phone call. The opponent gets **1 [Drag]** every turn until they decide to answer their phone, taking an action to do so.\r\n> 6. Something falls on the opponent from a height! They take **1 [Somatic]** damage. \r\n> 7. The opponent BARELY avoids accidentally seriously hurting themselves, and are **[Scared]** for **3 rounds**!\r\n> 8. Wait, hey, did you see that? You accidentally did something really cool! You gain **2 [Boost]**, and your opponent gets nothing.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Whoa! That’s like, multiple HAPPENs! You roll 2d8 and take 2 effects!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: EVERYTHING HAPPENS SO MUCH! You roll 3d8 and take 3 effects!'),
('hardcoreHubris', 'HARDCORE HUBRIS', 'OTHER', 'HEROMODE', '', 'You\'re kind of the best. That\'s all there is to say on the matter, frankly. You\'re so insanely skilled, talented and awesome that frankly, you\'re willing to take risks no sane person would. So come on— let\'s take a risk. When you enter **HERO MODE**, you may select one of the following benefits.\n\n> **GAMBIT**: You want it all, or you want nothing. For the next 3 turns, all **GOOD** and **GREAT** rolls become **MAX**, but all **OK** or **BAD** rolls become **MIN**.\n\n> **BURNOUT**: COME ON! YOU HAVE GOT THIS! JUST… KEEP… TRYING! All rolls use **+HUB** for the rest of the encounter, but you are also **[Exhausted]** as you push yourself way too hard. \n\n> **POWER-UP ROAR**: You start charging up your might while screaming like a deranged baboon. You stop acting for several turns, but gain 2 **[WHAM]** each turn. This effect is ended if your target attacks you, and you lose **[WHAM]** as normal. You can\'t be **[Hidden]** while charging up. The target is **[Deafened]** as you roar.\n\n> **SWASHFLURRY**: OHOHOHO! CHECK THIS SHIT OUT! You roll **SWASHBUCKLE** three times in the same action. You make individual rolls for each attempt.\n\n> **UNLIMITED LUCK!!!!!!!!**: NOBODY CAN STOP YOU NOW! (pause) OH NO! You gain 10 **[Boost]**. Once the 10 **[Boost]** is used up or depleted by other means, you gain 10 **[Drag]**.'),
('hardyHealth', 'HARDY HEALTH', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Passive]', 'Lowbloods are generally more susceptible to illness, thanks to Alternia making healthy solutions be out of their reach. Good thing that you\'re weirdly healthy! Any rolls you make against disease-based **[Afflictions]** are **[Talented]**.'),
('hatchmates', 'HATCHMATES', 'OTHER', 'MUTANT', '[Mutant][Passive]', 'Like siblings! As the name would imply, hatchmates are different trolls that hatched from the same egg. Hatchmates can be identical or fraternal and can be of any caste. Hatchmates can be played by one or more players; in the case of more than one, each player creates one troll and spends levels to upgrade them as you would any other troll. Each twin may take one non-**[Advanced]**, non-**[Ultra]**, non-**[Psionic]** move that the other has access to, thanks to their being together so much. This does NOT include beginning **[Unlock]** moves, though they can take other **[Locked]** moves. These twins can separate without discomfort and still benefit from their caste as it is a legal mutation. You can have triplets, though be careful; you take **1 [Drag]** passively every **3 turns** for every encounter you’re without your sibling.'),
('healbot', 'HEALBOT', 'LIFE', 'LIFE', '[Aspect][Basic][Heal][Recharge: 3][Locked: Life]', 'Don’t worry, guys! This is the move everyone wants from you, haha! You got this, everyone! You’re great at healing people and curing what ails ‘em, though in your darker moments you worry that that’s the only reason people put up with you— that they don’t actually care about you at all. When you want to heal someone with kind words and some metanarrative power that works simply because it does, spend an action to roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: It doesn’t work, and before you’re able to process it, you feel **[Despair]** wash over you— everyone’s going to abandon you because of this, surely.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Your power merely peters out, and you don’t restore any wounds. \r\n\r\n**OK**: You only heal a scratch, nothing more. You heal the target for **1 HP**. \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Your touch heals their wounds; you heal the target for **2 HP**. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: The inherent life-force in your target recovers; you heal the target for **2 HP** and you can remove any 1 negative condition they have. If you use this for **[Drag]**, you take away a max of **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Sweet baby Jegus- healing energy overflows from you, bolstering life forces to unprecedented heights. You heal the target for **3 HP**, and you can remove any 1 negative condition they have; if you use this for **[Drag]**, you take away a max of **3 [Drag]**.'),
('healingAura', 'HEALING AURA', 'OTHER', 'SYLPH', '[Class][Free][Recharge: 3][Unlock: Sylph]', 'You take on the role of a teacher and a guide among your allies. You are the Troll Beatrice to their Troll Dante, aiding them through the depths of hell (adolescence). Frankly, they would be lost without your keen insight and clever input. You know this, because every time you leave them to their own devices they all start getting themselves hurt! With a quick quip, you remind people the right way to tend to themselves. Healing effects applied to yourself or your allies grant an additional **+1 HP**.\r\n\r\n'),
('healingTouch', 'HEALING TOUCH', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][Recharge: 2][Cullbait][Heal][Psionic]', 'Your very touch brims with a physical manifestation of pathokinesis that encourages the body to heal faster. You can use this to subtly recover the stamina of those around you… or yourself! When you want to heal up, roll **+PLC**. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: AAEGGHHH! You feel agonising pain tear through you as your empathy powers show you how bad it could REALLY hurt! You take **3 [Psychic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Nghk-! You amplify the target\'s pain, dealing **1 [Psychic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Weh… you don\'t heal them, but you make them feel a little bit better. You give them **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Vwoop! Nice, you take the pain away! The target **[Heals] 1 HP**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: It\'s all okay! Don\'t worry. The target **[Heals] 2 HP**, or **[Heals] 1 HP** and removes **1 [Emotion]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: IT\'S ALL GONNA BE OKAY! NOW LET\'S DO IT! The target **[Heals] 3 HP**, or **[Heals] 2 HP** and removes all negative **[Emotions]**.'),
('healThyself', 'HEAL THYSELF', 'LIFE', 'LIFE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Life]', 'Hey, Docterror, you big nerd! Maybe you should practice some self care! You’ve learned that anything you give to others, you should make sure you give to yourself as well. It’s important not to be left in the dust, after all! Any time you heal a target or give them **[Boost]**, you siphon some of the latent life-force energy that flows through everything into yourself, gaining **1 HP** or **1 [Boost]**, respectively. Always make sure you’re getting the care you need before you give it to others!');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('heavenlyHoroscopist', 'HEAVENLY HOROSCOPIST', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Nyastrologist]', 'You might not look unassuming… but within you there is an innate understanding of all that there is out beyond the stars. Every day, a wriggler is born, and their aspects, class and sway will guide them to their destiny. Many Nyastrologists who get to your level pursue further careers as Astrosorcers or (heaven forbid!) Cthonomancers, who look at the horrible creators of the stars themselves… but many are just comfortable to stay running Horoscope Blogs on Pringle. You are now **[Talented]** at **+IMG**, and gain access to HERO MODE through both your PERFECT PULCHRITUDE and your INCREDIBLE IMAGINATION, though you can still only enter HERO MODE once! Whenever you enter a FRAYMOTIF, you can add the following effect to your dance, depending on if your allies are COMPATIBLE or INCOMPATIBLE with one another. All dancing trolls gain these effects, based on their relationship with you or each other. If you are dancing alone, you gain the effects of COMPATIBLE. \r\n\r\n> **COMPATIBLE**: Whenever a Compatible Dancemate gets an **OK** or lower roll, you\'re filled by a desire to see them do better. Their next roll is **[Tiered Up]**!\r\n\r\n> **INCOMPATIBLE**: Whenever an Incompatible Dancemate gets an **OK** or lower roll, you are filled with scorn and schadenfreude. Trust a Gemlo to screw that one up! You gain **1 [WHAM]**.'),
('heavyLoads', 'HEAVY LOADS', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Passive][Locked: Labourer]', 'A huge part of your job is carrying heavy stuff to and fro. Bags of grain, huge steel beams, lumber… you name it, and you can carry it. And it\'s so useful in many situations, too! You gain the following effects for the following moves so long as you have some HEAVY LOADS, items which cost **1 VP** each. You use up a HEAVY LOAD when using these effects.\r\n\r\n**SHENANIGANS**:\r\n\r\n> **PINNED**: And where do you think YOU\'RE going? You **[Trap]** the target.\r\n\r\n**LET\'S STRIFE**:\r\n\r\n> **LAY FIELD**: Hup Hup Hup Hup! You throw down some stuff to mark out the battlefield. This acts as CAN\'T ABSCOND BRO, but it lasts for the encounter.\r\n\r\n**GRIEF**:\r\n\r\n> **BATTERED**: SWIIIIING! On a **GREAT** GRIEF roll, you may choose to do 1 damage less and knock the target **[Floorbound]**. You can hit **[Flying]** targets with this option as you hurl your heavy loads HARD.\r\n\r\n**SWASHBUCKLE**:\r\n\r\n> **MAKE COVER**: You throw down a wall of your HEAVY LOADS to duck behind. Targets who spend an action to DUCK here make **[Physical]** rolls against them **[Inept]** but can\'t make **[Physical]** rolls themselves until they leave.'),
('heavySuspicions', 'HEAVY SUSPICIONS', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Rusts live dangerous lives under the watch of the Drones, the Clown Church, the Evil Empire, the Ghosts in the Cullpits, the Beasts in the Trash Cans, that one guy from the Subgrubs who wants to talk about seagoat butter but you don’t even know what that is so you gotta nod your head in disbelief as they talk to you. What I\'m saying is there\'s a million ways to get your ass kicked… so use your head and avoid trouble! You gain the following PROBLEM SLEUTHING options.\r\n\r\n> **TRUSTWORTHINESS CHECK**: Is this person cool? Or are they, like, not? If they\'re cool, you become **[Hopeful]**. If they\'re not, you become **[Stressed]** but gain a +2 to all **[Strife]** rolls. You can\'t roll this on someone obviously aligned with you or against you, and lose the effect of Not if you stop being **[Stressed]**.\r\n\r\n> **ESCAPE ROUTE**: You quickly identify any ways out of where you\'re at. Opponents ABSCOND and CAN\'T ABSCOND BRO rolls are **[Inept]** for the encounter.\r\n\r\n> **HESITATE**: Ask the Clouder or other player \"am I gonna regret this?\" before doing an action. If the answer is yes, then uh, maybe don\'t do that. You gain **3 [Boost]** if you do it anyway. Jackass. If you don\'t do it, you reduce an **[Emotion]** by 1 stage.\r\n\r\n> **SQUINT**: You lyin\'? If they are, you gain **1 [WHAM]**. If they\'re being honest, you gain **2 [Boost]**.'),
('heelfaceTurnabout', 'HEEL-FACE TURNABOUT', 'OTHER', 'MUSCLEMANIAC', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Musclemaniac]\r\n', 'Performance fighting is characterized by good and bad guys. It’s all pretty black and white. The guys running this whole thing are probably hope players or some shit. Regardless, you are either a FACE (a good guy) or a HEEL (a bad guy) in the ring. This doesn’t necessarily have to correspond with your real-world moral alignment- you can be a face who’s a complete bulgehead in real life or a heel who needlefelts puppies in their spare time. It’s just your wrestling persona! When you take this move, choose to be either a FACE or a HEEL and gain the corresponding effects. Additionally, when taking this move, you gain the ability to optionally expose spectators to your fight to the SIMPTOMS affliction for free at the end of a match. If you’re a HEEL, it’s just pitch-flavored.\r\n\r\n> **FACE**: You’re the good guy, the hero of the story. You follow the rules. People swoon over your biceps. Once per encounter, you can **[Tier Up]** one of your rolls as a free action. Additionally, you gain the following good SWASHBUCKLE effect**:\r\n\r\n> **ENDLESS SEA OF BITCHES**: People like you. Of course they do. You’re hot. You’re nice. Maybe you crush a watermelon between your thighs on stage and make everyone swoon. You become **[Smug]**.\r\n\r\n> **HEEL**: You’re the bad boy. Rules mean nothing to you. Friendship? Tch. Once per encounter, you can **[Tier Down]** one of your opponent’s rolls as a free action. Additionally, you gain the following SHENANIGANS effect**:\r\n\r\n> **BREAK THEIR ACTUAL BONES**: What kind of fucked-up monster are you? What sort of game lets you inflict bleeding on a silly shenanigans roll? Stop playing 4e. Your target becomes **[Bloodied]**.'),
('heirsConditioning', 'HEIR\'S CONDITIONING', 'OTHER', 'HEIR', '[Class][Advanced][Buildup: 3][One-Off][Magic][Locked: Heir]', 'There’s more to heirs than just their aspect. This move cannot be used on the same turn as you activate HERO MODE in the usual way. When you want to make the most of your untapped potential, roll **+ANY** (any stat of your choice).\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You lose a use of HERO MODE and access to your **[Aspect]** moves for 1 round. Yeesh!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Something’s gone wrong. You lose your **[Aspect]** moves for 1 round.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Despite your aspect being all around, nothing happens. Guess you tapped into your potential already.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You use a HERO MODE option, either from HALLOWED HEROISM or from READY PLAYER ONE; this does not use up your usual uses of HERO MODE.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You get the effects of a **GOOD**, and can also access the HERO MODE options of the stat you rolled this move with.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You get the effects of a **GREAT**, and your next move **[Tiers Up]**, even to a **MAX**.'),
('hellHathNoFury', 'HELL HATH NO FURY', 'OTHER', 'SYLPH', '[Class][Basic][Locked: Sylph]', 'I’m a healer, but- *CHAINSAW NOISES* |\r\n\r\nThat’s IT. That’s it, you’re done, you try so hard to be nice to everyone and keep this hive in order and make sure that everyone gets along and everyone is safe and healthy and instead it\'s just one crisis after another and you don’t get a single ounce of respect, no one stops to listen to you or think about you, you can’t TAKE IT ANYMORE! When ~~your poor emotional self care catches up to you~~ it all gets to be too much, you may instantly choose to become **[Enraged]** for **[Free]**. Someone else can pick Mercy for a change. '),
('hellsHenchtroll', 'HELL’S HENCHTROLL', 'OTHER', 'SERVICESQUIRE', '[Template][Template][Ultra][Recharge: 3][Locked: Servicesquire]', 'You are simply… one hell of a butler. Like, seriously.  So much so that you can simply follow practically any order given, ever, like a terminator in a smart suit and bowtie. You have learned to do basically all the tasks your boss does; if your boss has an **[Ultra]** move from their Caste Tree, you gain it. You can attempt moves usually exclusive to your Boss; you may roll any non-**[Psionic]**, non-**[Ultra]**, Caste, **[Basic]** Class or PERFECTLY GENERIC move on your Boss’ sheet at a **[Recharge: 3]**. Your Wealth increases to match your boss’ Wealth, and while in an encounter with your Boss, you can choose to take damage aimed at your Boss as a **[Reaction]**.'),
('helmstroll', 'HELMSTROLL', 'GOLD', 'ADULT', '[Gold][Recharge: 3][Locked: Adult]', 'You’ve achieved apex ability as a battery psion. Even pre-adulthood, you likely could level subgrubs with your power; now, you will receive the ultimate reward- getting used as a living battery to power the FTL drive of an Imperial warship, yahoo! In the past, this was historically done by physically grafting your body to the ship, reducing you to nothing but an agonized lifeless husk. This made it... difficult... to recruit, so newer Imperial warships have sacrificed 0.008% of their power to give battery golds some level of autonomy. You can plug yourself in and out, and it\\\'s still kind of awful, but you can like... actually visit the ship canteen on break like everyone else. Like it or not, you\\\'ve become used to converting your literal life force into psionic power. Your **HP** now becomes a resource for you to draw from; you can sacrifice 2 **HP** as an action to either gain 3 **WHAM** (the WHAM cap still applies), or to prepare a psionic burst that will cause your next attack to damage to all strife participants other than yourself.'),
('helpingHand', 'HELPING HAND', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Mental][Reaction][Recharge: 3]', 'You care very much about your friends, and watching them succeed. When an ally makes a roll that you want to help out with, roll **+PLC** to assist them!\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You fucked up. You were not encouraging or friendly at all! Oh, woe is you! You **[Tier Down]** your ally\'s roll, and you gain the **[Despair]** condition.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You give your ally a **-1 [Nerf]** on their roll as you fail to hype them up.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Nothing happens, and neither of you want to talk about it.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You give them a **+1 [Buff]** on their roll as you effectively encourage them to try!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Wow! Friendship really does pay off! You give them a **+3 [Buff]** on their roll as you pat them on the back and give them a thumbs up.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Your ally\'s roll is **[Tiered Up]**, even to **MAX**, because the power of friendship and love truly is unbeatable. Your bond is beyond words. You are soul brothers. Or soul sisters. Soul siblings.'),
('helpMeHelpYou', 'HELP ME, HELP YOU', 'OTHER', 'SYLPH', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Sylph]', 'You’ve learned that sometimes, the best way to help your friends... is to help yourself! **SHARING IS CARING** and **HAND OF ANANIAS** work on you, as you’ve realized teamwork includes everyone. Additionally, your **HEALING AURA** is extended; you and allies in your presence lose 1 **[Drag]** each turn, and the **[Recharge]** is reduced to **[Recharge: 1]**.\r\n'),
('hemoanalogue', 'HEMOANALOGUE', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive]', 'Prerequisite: Must not be Hemoanon \r\n\r\nWhat? You want to wear grey... and not give up your actual caste\'s stereotypical path in life and the skills you\'ve picked up from it? You want to keep doing what you\'re doing and still be a hemoanon? They call that being a neoliberal up in Fogblister, but you do you, hemobuddy. As an alternative to the Hemoanon tree you may select this move when you wish to take being hemoanonymous a little less seriously. **[Analyze]** rolls to identify you are at a **-2 [Nerf]**; or a **-1 [Nerf]** if you are a Violet- as you cover yourself up in greys or however else you disguise yourself. If your Wealth Level was not **Poor** or lower already, it becomes **Poor** now as the Empire simply refuses to let you sign off for your allowance or highblood tax breaks in that gaudy grey mess. You may keep your current Caste Tree.'),
('hemoanalyze', 'HEMOANALYZE', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Advanced][Analyze]', 'A stupid Anon is a dead Anon, and you’ve made it this far. Therefore, you’ve had to learn a variety of techniques to scope your situation and survive. You gain access to the following **PROBLEM SLEUTHING** options.\r\n\r\n> **HUNKER DOWN**: You don’t even have to ask if this guy wants to rock your shit. You’re anon! Everyone wants to rock your shit! No, what you’re most concerned with is who will hit the hardest and how to take that hit without keeling over dead. Choose one opponent, you have 1 **[Somatic]** and **[Verbal] [Resistance]** against them until your next turn as you brace for the worst.\r\n\r\n> **OLLIE OUTIE**: Oh Jegus, yeah that’s… a drone. Go to your happy place! And by that you mean a nice shadowy alleyway! You look around your surroundings for the best hiding spots, your next **DUCK AND COVER** roll is **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n\r\n> **PAY ATTENTION**: You’ve now been around the metaphorical block many times, and you know well enough when it’s time to keep an eye on the situation at hand. You become either **[Insightful]** or **[Focused]**.\r\n\r\n> **CHROMATIC COORDINATION**: Help me help you, buddy. Hemoanons only make it as far as they do through working together with others. Pick an ally, you each plan out your next move. Attacking the same enemy, patching each other up, getting the hell out of there. As long as you act as one, you both **[Tier Up]** your move. If for whatever reason one of you goes back on this plan, you both take 3 **[Drag]** as you fumble into each other. WHAT THE HELL MAN!? I SAID GO LEFT! NO YOUR LEFT! AUGH!'),
('hemoandrogyny', 'HEMOANDROGYNY', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Basic][Passive][Locked: Full-Time]\r\n', 'It’d be... A little hard to hide your caste identity if the only moves you could take were from your “true” caste, right? You’ve picked up some skills typically associated with other castes, further making it harder to pin down what you “akshully” are. When you take this move for the first time, you may select two castes other than your true caste. Additionally, whenever you take this move, you may take one **[Open]** move from one of your newly selected castes. You cannot take this move if you have the **SUBCASTE** mutation, and can only take this move a total of 4 times.\r\n'),
('hemohamper', 'HEMOHAMPER', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Basic][Chicanery]\r\n', 'No one\'s quite sure who the originator of the iconic HEMOHAMPER style of shenanigans is, but two things are for sure: they were a hemoanon and they\'ve inspired many other hemoanons to employ the same tricks in order to survive. You gain access to the following **SHENANIGANS** options.\r\n\r\n> **BLOOD REVEAL PARTY**: Since they’re so insistent on wanting to find out your blood color, you decide to give them a little box that you PROMISE will reveal your blood. It’s actually a spring-loaded boxing glove, which renders them **[Floorbound]** if they open it.\r\n\r\n> **EMERGENCY SHOCK DEVICE**: What self-respecting anon doesn\'t have a way to suddenly make their pursuers jolt and stutter? Using a taser, loose wires, or a particularly nasty static shock, you render the target **[Overwhelmed]**!\r\n\r\n> **PAINTED**: Paint the town rainbow? Don’t mind if you do! You spite those who aim to reveal YOUR precious blood and throw a tin of paint at them, rendering them **[Blinded]** for 2 turns! Reveal THIS!\r\n\r\n> **THE SLIP**: You give it to them! By scattering marbles or spilling soap or whatever, you inflict 2 **[Drag]** when you knock an enemy **[Floorbound]** within 2 rounds as they hit the ground hard.'),
('hemoluminescence', 'HEMOLUMINESCENCE', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Psionic][Manipulate][Recharge: 3][Locked: Deep-Sea]', 'Your blood carries heavy amounts of luciferin, a chemical that reacts with oxygen to create bioluminescence. Biology facts! It\'s technically not Psionics, but it\'s close. You can take a deep breath and cause your veins to pulse in colour beneath your skin, allowing you to soothe targets or agitate them as you please. When you want to try to use your biology to trigger a reaction in those around you, roll **+GRT**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Oh no! You breathed in too MUCH oxygen, and your body isn\'t used to it! You are **[Bloodied]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: A dull glow pulses from your skin for a moment… but it isn\'t really that impressive, to be honest. Get good!\r\n\r\n**OK**: Your glow is, at most, slightly attention-grabbing. You can give the target **1 [Boost]** or **[Drag]**, your choice.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You pulse hypnotic patterns through your veins, altering your target\'s brain waves as they look at you. The target feels either **[Numb]**, **[Charmed]**, **[Peaceful]** or **[Scared]**, your choice. You can select multiple targets with this effect, but they all gain the same Emotion. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Your glowing and flashing are particularly bright, even in direct moonlight. As well as the above Emotions, you also give the target **2 [Boost]** or **2 [Drag]**, your choice. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: You have total control of the exact hypnotic patterns you give off, flooding the target\'s synapses with your message! The target starts **[Dissociating]**, feels **[Serene]** or **[Fascinated]** or is **[Terrified]**, as well as taking **2 [Boost]** or **2 [Drag]**, your choice. This **[Drag]** isn\'t affected by **[Terrified]**.'),
('henchmantagonizer', 'HENCHMANTAGONIZER', 'BRONZE', 'ADULT', '[Bronze][Locked: Adult]', 'Yeaaah, gettem boss, gettem! You know those throwaway henchmen that helped out the villains of those Superscoundrel shows? Yeah, that\\\'s basically your job now. Henchmantagonizers aren\\\'t just helpers to high-ranking trolls, they\\\'re also well trained disruptors, saboteurs… and act as good meat-shields when needed. When in an encounter with allies, you can deem one as Da Boss. Typically this is someone who\\\'s a higher caste and rank than you, but strained circumstances can have you force leadership on anyone you deem competent enough to follow. When Da Boss is around, you can spend an action to transfer up to 3 **[Boost]** or 3 **[WHAM]** to Da Boss. Additionally, when you roll a **GREAT [Chicanery]** roll against a target, you can also render them **[Agitated], [Dumbfounded]**, or **[Humiliated]** for 2 turns. Each emotion is a **[One-Off]** and you cannot apply another of the listed emotions like this if they are still experiencing a different emotion this way. Finally, as a **[Free] [Reaction]**, Da Boss can direct any effect targeting them your way.'),
('heraldCaller', 'HERALD CALLER', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Ultra][Buildup: 3][Magic][Locked: Cloistered]', 'Your teachings as a priestess to your religion have reached paramount; you are as pure as they come. The Mother Grub has recognized you for your loyalty, and gurgled out something that sounded vaguely like your name once; a blessing that you will keep near and dear to your heart forever. You gain access to HERO MODE through your INCREDIBLE IMAGINATION. You may call up a celestial avatar of the Mother Grub to aid you in times of need. As an action, you call out to the holy virgin goddess of the caves, and a writhing, celestial worm digs from the earth beneath you. You summon a CELESTIAL GRUB from Chapter 12b: FRIENDS & FOES, with the exception that it shares its HP, **[Boost]**, **[Drag]**, and **[WHAM]** with you. You command the CELESTIAL GRUB as if though it were an extension of yourself; as such, when you take damage, so does it, and vice versa. The awesome power or the CELESTIAL GRUB allows you to smite **[Eerie]** trolls, bestow **[Hope]** on the innocent and even resurrect dead Jades as Rainbowdrinkers— see their Statblock for more!'),
('heraldricHerald', 'HERALDRIC HERALD', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'Indigos are a strange caste; the highest caste to not be blessed with the near infinite lifespan available to Purples and Violets. It is your duty— your privilege— to study those great warriors of sweeps long since past to keep their memory alive in a world that so often censors history. Thorough study has finally uncovered a single, notable figure that matches your genetic code perfectly. That is to say… you\'ve discovered significant lore on your Ancestor, the last troll in history to effectively be an exact biological copy of you. What did they do? What did they accomplish? How did they shape the culture you now find yourself in? As an Indigo, questions like this are yours alone to firmly undertake. After all, while all others live in the present, it is you who looks back on the lessons learned by the past. You may give up one of your two **[Template]** slots in order to gain a third **[Ultra]** slot as you study how to be the perfect descendant for your once great Ancestor.'),
('heresyEradicationTaskforce', 'HERESY ERADICATION TASKFORCE', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'HET', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: HET]', 'Prerequisite: Must be a Cerulean.\r\n\r\nYou are a member of the Heresy Eradication Taskforce, the propaganda and rebel eradication wing of the Empire\'s Color Guard overseeing the governance of Alternia. With the great honor of serving your Heiress and Empress, you additionally carry their voice through your own. Which means everyone has to listen to you if they know what\'s good for them! ... At least, if you can justify your orders as Org related. You have a conditional authority over all non-Org trolls, and Drones will not target you while in your ORG Uniform, which you gain now for free, as well as a flair on all social media marking you as a member of the JR. HET. You gain the following new WORDPLAY effects.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**:\r\n\r\n> **DECLARE**: You don\'t insult. You state explicitly the Imperial line. You gain the effects of the JAB option, but you can roll it after a fight breaks out. This shares a **[Recharge]** with JAB.\r\n\r\n> **SPONSORED AD**: Buy it right now or you\'re a rebel that hates giving Condy money. Choose a move the target must roll at a **-1 [Nerf]** next turn.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**:\r\n\r\n> **LOG OFF**: You should log off Chittr right now. Because you\'re probably about to die if you don\'t. Go on. Click the X. Your target can either exit the current social media thread, or take **3 [Verbal]** Damage immediately and begin an online **[Verbal]** Strife. This is a **[One-Off]** effect. If your target is a fellow HET member, they can inflict it back on you as a **[Reaction]**. When using this effect, remember OOC Courtesy and ask first!'),
('hermitWisdom', 'HERMIT WISDOM', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Passive][Locked: Nyanarchist]', 'The streets have not claimed your heart; you live in the wilderness, and you’ve learned to run wild through it in ways that nobody else can. Depending on the environment you now call hive, you’ve learned some neat tricks to keep yourself safe there, and in the face of opponents too! Choose a biome from below which you are most accustomed to:\r\n\r\n> **WASTELAND**: You’re used to the scorching sun. You are immune to the **[Ablaze]** condition from normal sources, and the DAYTIME **[Hazard]** takes an extra turn before it starts affecting you.\r\n\r\n> **TUNDRA**: Cold? What cold? You bundle up tight, giving you **1 [Resistance]** against **[Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n> **JUNGLE**: Poisonous flowers, deadly lusii, quicksand, malaria… You didn\'t survive wrigglerhood by being a slowpoke. When you would take any penalty from a **[Hazard]**, roll 1d2. On a two, you simply don\'t take the penalty that turn. \r\n\r\n> **SWAMP**: Ak ak ak ak… you’re a silly little swamp witch, or something! You are immune to the **[Poisoned]** condition, and you regain **+1 HP** the first time you **[Heal]**.\r\n\r\n> **WOODLANDS**: Gotta stay alert when you’re romping around in the forest- who knows when danger will strike first! Lusii **[Legendary]** rolls are just **[Talented]** against you. \r\n\r\n> **MOUNTAINS**: Rocky cliffs are your home! The ROCKS FALL **[Hazard]** has no effect on you, and you can\'t be made **[Floorbound]**.\r\n\r\n> **DEEPSEA**: How\'d you even get here? You some kinda catfish? You have supplies that make you immune to the DROWNING **[Hazard]**, and you do **+1 damage** against aquatic lusii.\r\n\r\n> **CITYSCAPE**: Hey now! What are you doing in civilization, still? Ah, you\'re an urban druid type, living in treehouses and caring for urban life like moss, lichen and birds. Your **[Analyze]** rolls are **[Talented]**, and can never be made **[Inept]**, **[Nerfed]** or **[Tiered Down]**.'),
('heroicOutlaw', 'HEROIC OUTLAW', 'OTHER', 'ROGUE', '[Class][Passive][Unlock: Rogue]', 'Your life is not an easy one, despite appearances to the contrary. You have untold levels of stress, inferiority complexes and imposter syndromes that choke you ‘til you\'re dizzy. In fact, the only thing that truly keeps you going… is your allies. They\'re worth fighting for, even if you yourself are not. You may roll the SHENANIGANS YOINK effect on your friends’ and allies’ **[Drag]**, taking it onto yourself. You may take one point on a **GOOD**, up to half of their total rounded down on a **GREAT**, and as much as you want on a **MAX**. You are always **[Talented]** at YOINK rolls.'),
('heroSubSandwich', 'HERO SUB SANDWICH', 'OTHER', 'GOREMAND', '[Template][Basic][Locked: Goremand]', 'You know how to make some grub on the go! Using the magic of a portable cooking station and spice rack, you can whip up a snack for yourself or your allies during a thread! You unlock different, unique dishes to your specialization taken in your Entry which you can create mid-encounter, allowing yourself or your allies to use them for **[Free]**. You unlock the following items, each of which costs **3 VP**.\r\n\r\n> **BAKING or MIXING**: The Hero Sub Sandwich, the reference we all know and love and the title of this move, even! It\'s a veritable treasure trove of good eating. On the next turn, you will **[Heal] 2 HP**, but will also redirect all damage to yourself if you have allies present. If you have no allies present, you instead gain **1 [Weakness]** for the round.\r\n\r\n> **GRILLING or FRYING**: Wagyu Subsnazzard Steak is hard to come by and even harder to cook, but you\'ve figured it out. This is something that only the most honorable and justice-driven trolls can eat safely. Decide if your troll is LAW-ABIDING or CRIMINAL-CODED when they eat the meal at the time of consumption. \r\n\r\n> **LAW-ABIDING**: If they are LAW-ABIDING, they are imbued with the power of subsnazzards, **[Tiering Up]** their Problem Sleuthing rolls and giving them the **[Magic]** tag for 3 Rounds, removing the **[Recharge]**. \r\n> **CRIMINAL-CODED**: If they are CRIMINAL-CODED, the delicious flavor strikes back against the wrongdoer. They become **[Talented]** and gain a +2 **[Buff]** at ACT FAST, even to a 5d8 if possible, as they prepare to run from the law.\r\n\r\n> **BAKING or FRYING**: Hundred Layer Donuts, for when you decide the only way to improve upon perfection is to make it bigger! This mother of all donuts puts a smile on anyone’s face and a spring in anyone’s step. All **[Base]** negative emotions are reset and you cannot gain any **[Heightened]** negative emotions for the duration of the encounter. Should you already have a **[Heightened]** negative emotion, it becomes **[Base]** instead.\r\n\r\n> **FRYING or BOILING: Thrice-Fried Troll French Fries are a crowd pleaser enjoyed by everyone everywhere. It doesn’t even have to be potato-based; with enough imagination, anything can be fried!  Share it with your friends! Roll 1d7**: on an even, you heal **3 HP**. On an odd, you summon the SCREEGULL SWARM **[Hazard]** as a flock of angry scavengegulls prepare to eat your fries and your face!\r\n\r\n> **BOILING or MIXING**: Aquatic Scavengebeast Curry, the ultimate flavor experience! Bitter turmeric, spicy cayenne, sweet coconut milk, and savory aquatic scavengebeast come together for a meal worthy of highest praise. All seadwellers in the encounter become **[Charmed]** by the consumer and all rolls **[Tier Up]** against them. If the target was already **[Charmed]**, they gain the SIMPTOMS **[Affliction]**. However, eating any other dish in the encounter instantly removes this effect and affliction.\r\n\r\n'),
('hexslingery', 'HEXSLINGERY', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Downtime][Psionic][Locked: Haunted]', 'You\'ll show them..! You\'ll show them all..!! You are perhaps at your most dangerous when left alone for a few hours as you curse those who have wronged you. You\'ll make them pay..! Slowly, but certainly! When you want to make your enemies\' lives suckier, roll **+RAS**.\n\n**MIN**: YOU CURSED YOURSELF! OH, YOU FOOL! NOOOO! You give yourself a **[Slowburn]** **[Affliction]**! Aeeeioooughhh…\n\n**BAD**: You larp being a wicked witch for an hour or two, then give up and go play video games.\n\n**OK**: The spell… is working… maaaaaaybe? Roll again, without your **[Talent]**.\n\n**GOOD**: Hah! There you go! You give any one troll a **[Slowburn]** **[Affliction]**! Whether it\'s willing ghosts to perform a HAUNTING, cursing them with MOONBARK MADNESS or even inconveniencing them with THE SNIFFLES, you\'re really ruining their day. You can also cure **[Affliction]**s like this by giving them a nice curse… once they\'ve learned their lesson!\n\n**GREAT**: The curse was exceptionally strong. The target automatically moves to Stage 1.\n\n**MAX**:  Whoa! You cursed them so hard that they\'re already on the floor and crying! It\'s been like 20 minutes! The target automatically moves to Stage 2.'),
('heyChat', 'HEY, CHAT', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Mental][Tech][Locked: Streamer] ', 'You are accompanied at all times by your trusty CHAT, viewers of your stream who admire and cajole you. They are like swine, hungry for content, and you are the corpulent farmer who brings them their slop. It\'s a symbiotic relationship. You may, as a **[Free]** action, ask Chat to decide what you\'ll do next instead of choosing yourself. If you don\'t do what chat asks, they grow raucous and bitter; you take **3 [Drag]** as your numbers dip. Roll 1d8. \r\n\r\n> **1. VIOLENCE**: Chat hungers for bloodshed. You can make a **[Tiered Up] [Physical] [Strife]** roll on your next action.\r\n\r\n> **2. DO A SEXY POSE**: Chat just keeps saying this over and over again..? Uh, **[Tiered Up]** SWASHBUCKLE?\r\n\r\n> **3. NOW KISS**: Chat wants ROMANCE. Either FLIRT using WORDPLAY and expose the target to SIMPTOMS if it succeeds, or use any other WORDPLAY roll with a **+1 [Buff]** in an attempt to fool CHAT into thinking you\'re flirting.\r\n\r\n> **4. START A CULT**: Chat has suddenly started a cult around some insignificant thing in the background of your stream. They believe that the Ugly Old Lamp in your hive is the third Mirthful Messiah, or some shit. Make a **+IMG** or **+RAS** roll involving the object to appease chat and gain **3 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **5. PRANK EM**: You already know. Chat wants GOOFS! Wants CHAOS! You may make a **[Tiered Up]** SHENANIGANS Roll.\r\n\r\n> **6. DO SOMETHING DANGEROUS**: Chat has rallied to demand you do something very stupid. \"Do a kickflip,\" they spam. You don\'t know how to. Make any one **[Inept]** roll; if you do it, you gain **3 [Boost]** regardless of your roll result afterward.\r\n\r\n> **7. HYDRATE**: Chat screams, demanding to know if you\'ve drank water lately. You can make a GUTSUCKERY roll, even if you\'ve already used your **[One-Off]**.\r\n\r\n> **8. HAVE FUN AND BE YOURSELF :)**: Aww. How wholesome. Chat reminds you they\'re here for you, not the dumb stuff they make you do. You get **1 [Hold]**; spend it for **[Free]** to be **[Talented]** at any one roll.'),
('hideAndSeek', 'HIDE AND SEEK', 'VOID', 'VOID', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Void]', 'You’ve spent a lot of your time hiding, both from other people and yourself. But hiding can’t solve everything! You’ve made the mistake of internalizing all your troubles, and you don’t want to see other people do the same. As such, you’ve gotten pretty good at spotting when people are hiding things from you. Your PROBLEM SLEUTHING rolls to find **[Hidden]** targets **[Tier Up]**, and when you want to see if someone’s hiding something from you, you don’t need to roll PROBLEM SLEUTHING; instead, just spend an action to receive a **GOOD** result. This does not activate IT’S A MYSTERY.'),
('hideyhue', 'HIDEY-HUE', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Free][One-Off]', 'Your blood is TOP SECRET!!! You refuse to let anyone know the truth, and you take some serious precautions to keep yourself from spilling the secret. If you become **[Bloodied]**, you can immediately slap a bandage on your wound before the target can see what caste you are, ending the **[Bloodied]** condition but giving yourself **1 [Drag]** instead. If you were to start **[Crying]**, you can force yourself to avoid it, instead gaining the **[Agitated]** condition as you bottle up your feelings and remember that tears could spell certain doom.'),
('highbloodRage', 'HIGHBLOOD RAGE', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[One-off]', 'Prerequisite: Must be a Cerulean or higher.\n\nAs a highblood, you have a temper. A real bad one. It gets worse the higher in caste you are, but all highbloods can draw upon the innate rage. When you enter a highblood rage, your eyes turn orange and you go into a fury. You can become **[Enraged]** as an action, and if you already are when you activate the move, you become **[Out of Control]**.'),
('highlyLogical', 'HIGHLY LOGICAL', 'MIND', 'MIND', '[Aspect][Basic][Free][Manipulate][Recharge: 3][Locked: Mind]', 'Some trolls act according to their heart, not their brain, and you don’t care for that shit at all. Here— let you tell them the only sensible way forward. This might come off as inflexible to others, but you know you’re just on the right path, and they’re not. When you advise someone on the correct path forward by telling them the next move they should roll, and they use the move you advised, their next roll becomes **[Tiered Up]**; any other move is **[Tiered Down]**. This does not stack with any other **[Tier Up]** or **[Tier Down]**.'),
('hiss', 'HIIIIIISSSSSSSSSSS', 'OTHER', 'RAINBOW_DRINKER', '[Template][Basic][One-Off][Eerie][Locked: Rainbow Drinker]', 'You’re like, actually super scary. With glowing yellow eyes, pure white skin, long fangs and nails, you’re the LAST troll anyone wants to piss off— and when you jump on your prey and hiss, you scare the shit out of them. You can hiss and activate BLOODHYSTERIA of your own accord, making the opponent **[Terrified]** and giving them **3 [Drag]**, because, like, holy shit. Your damage increases by 1 when you’re in a self-imposed BLOODHYSTERIA.'),
('historyWatchesYou', 'HISTORY WATCHES YOU', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Passive]', 'Violetbloods have an infinite life expectancy thanks to the impossible medical care they receive… which means one day, you\'ll have a descendant that looks up to you just like you look up to your Ancestor. You want to set a good example for them, right? You gain the following effects for GENEALOGICAL HERO based on how you wish to be perceived in the future. If you don\'t have GENEALOGICAL HERO, you can use the move, but only with these options. Once you pick an option, it\'s the only one you can use unless something changes.\r\n\r\n> **HERO**: You plan on fighting to save all those who can\'t be saved! When in a TEAM STRIFE, if you\'re the STRUGGLER, you have a **+1 [Buff]** to all rolls. While on STANDBY, you have a **-1 [Nerf]** to all rolls. \r\n\r\n> **WANDERER**: You will travel the stars, and learn things nobody else has ever learned. You become **[Legendary]** at **[Analyze]** rolls.\r\n\r\n> **POLITICIAN**: You\'ll change the system from the inside, maybe! Your **[Manipulate]** rolls become **[Talented]** and can\'t be turned **[Inept]**, **[Nerfed]** or **[Tiered Down]**. If they were already **[Talented]**, you get a **+2 [Buff]** to these rolls. \r\n\r\n> **STAR**: You\'ll bring your talent to whole new worlds, and inspire the masses! You become immune to negative **[Emotions]**.\r\n\r\n> **MOGUL**: Business will be YOUR business. Your **VP** limit raises by 2, and you can buy items on the fly as you search through your sylladex for stuff you\'ve stored in the nooks and crannies.\r\n\r\n> **JUST THE WORST**: DANGIT! YOU\'RE STILL AWFUL! Whenever someone around you gains a negative **[Emotion]**, you gain the opposite positive **[Emotion]**.'),
('hitbutler', 'HIT-BUTLER', 'OTHER', 'SERVICESQUIRE', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Servicesquire]', 'A job’s a job, and you do whatever your job entails… even killing. Any time you are in an encounter with or because of a request made by your Boss, you are **[Quickened]** on the first **two turns**. Additionally, you are equipped with multiple minor murder tools to help you do your job better. You may pull out a BUTLERKIND Strife Specibus with typical hitman tools; garotte wire, poison, silenced pistol, etc. This specibus may have up to two ABSTRATA UPGRADES on it. If you already had a move that granted a similar effect, you may increase this to three ABSTRATA. Wow!'),
('hitTheBricks', 'HIT THE BRICKS', 'OTHER', 'KNIGHT', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Knight]', 'There are times in your life where you have to stand your ground, yes. But other times? It’s more important to make sure you and your allies survive to see another night. Protecting your friends doesn’t always mean making a sacrifice. Sometimes it’s just… RUNNING AWAY! AAAAAA!\r\nWhenever any **[Hazard]** begins, you and your allies are not affected for the first round and gain one of two options for the rest of the **[Hazard]** duration: either a +1 **[Buff]** to **[Strife]** OR a +1 **[Buff]** for everyone’s rolls to either **[Abscond]** or become **[Hidden]** as you guide them the hell out of there!'),
('hiveImprovement', 'HIVE IMPROVEMENT', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Passive]', 'Your hive isn\'t perfect; ramshackle doesn\'t even begin to describe it. But it\'s yours, and no empire nor bandits are gonna stop you from making your hive more habitable. You gain access to the following HIVECRAFTING UPGRADE depending on your tree for free now.\r\n\r\n> **Junker**: You build a SCRAPYARD. If you have a SCRAPYARD, you can turn **LUX** into temporary extra **VP**, where **1 LUX** becomes 1 free **VP** added to your total cap. Items with this extra **VP** must be **[Consumable]**, and when they\'re used, their **VP** is lost too.\r\n\r\n> **Labourer**: You build a PRODUCTIONZONE. Whether it\'s a farm, a forge, or a factory, you MAKE stuff here. Your MONEYMAKERY rolls all produce **1 LUX** extra. \r\n\r\n> **Summoner**: You build a LUSUS RANCH, a place where lusii can come to rest. You gain a second CUSTODIAN; further ones cost **4 LUX**. You can only summon one CUSTODIAN per encounter. \r\n\r\n> **Vagabond**: You build a SPEAKEASY. A tavern? A bar? A hideout? This place is what you make of it! Drones cannot enter your hive, and anything said here cannot be reported to the authorities, even if you really really want to. Sorry, you signed a waiver promising you wouldn\'t!\r\n\r\n> **Folklorist**: You build a PRIVATE BOOKHIVE; it\'s like a regular bookhive, but all the books are by you! All of your RUMORHUNGER **[Downtime]** moves are **[Tiered Up]**, even to **MAX**.\r\n\r\n> **Other**: Now boy what the hell are you doing. \"Alternate\" \"Path\"? Goodness gracious. You gain a HIVECRAFTING UPGRADE of your choice for free.'),
('holdThisForMe', 'HOLD THIS FOR ME', 'OTHER', 'ROGUE', '[Class][Basic][One-off][Locked: Rogue]\r\n', 'Hey would you just hold this for me for a sec- great, thanks, lemme just- oh and hold this. Cool now stand over here? Stellar, now if you could just roll this SWASHBUCKLE for me that would be just the best, you\'re the best, thank you~ <3 Once per encounter, you may force an enemy to roll a move for you, using their own stats, talents, tier-ups, etc.\r\n'),
('honeytech', 'HONEYTECH', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Passive][Psionic][Locked: Beekeeper]', 'Turns out, if you put basic components together, you make something new! You have figured out how to make technological marvels out of basically nothing. It\'s great! Your increased baggage when it comes to tech means that you have **12 VP**, not 8, and you have access to the following items.\r\n\r\n**HONEYHUSK (2 VP)**: A palmhusk, husktop, or another computer-centric device. Because of its wholly organic nature, it is invulnerable to hacking; your **[Tech]** rolls can\'t be deactivated or negatively affected, and you get **+1 [Buff]** on rolls using **[Boost]** on them. However, also due to the wholly organic nature, there\'s a chance it just slops apart after being used; roll 1d8 before using it, and on a 1, it breaks.\r\n\r\n**NEUROGOGGLES (2 VP)**: These goggles show you the electric pulses in someone\'s body… even through walls and shit, if you tune it right! Your SPOT PROBLEM SLEUTHING rolls are **[Tiered Up]**. You automatically know if the target has a way to deal **[Energy]** damage.\r\n\r\n**SCRAMBLER (2 VP)**: This handy little device interferes with the electric pulses and pheromones of other pieces of tech! While active, all **[Tech]** rolls are **[Inept]**. You can also do this to open electronic locks, wipe data from husktops, etc.\r\n\r\n**TRACKERBUG (2 VP)**: Sticking this onto someone lets you track their whereabouts from a distance as well as hear their audio live. It\'s a **GOOD** SHENANIGANS roll to attach it without them noticing. \r\n\r\n**DRONECAM (3 VP)**: This large bee is in fact a robot! You can control it from a distance and roll **[Mental]** and **[Manipulate]** rolls through it without you being at risk of being hurt. If you deploy it out of sight, it is automatically **[Hidden]**, and can film and stream stuff as you choose. On the flip side, it has **1 HP**.\r\n\r\n**3D-WAXER (4 VP)**: Yeah, yeah yeah yeah! This **[Consumable]** item creates any single item exclusively out of wax and propolis— even items you can\'t buy! You can effectively purchase any item that isn\'t **[Rare]** or edible from any wealth level, though it always uses 4 **VP**, has **1 HP**, and requires a 1d8 roll before using. If you roll a 1 on this 1d8 roll, it crumbles.'),
('hopesAndStreams', 'HOPES AND STREAMS', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Passive][Unlock: Streamer]', 'Life can be a little grim at times. The prospect of life post-ascension is scary, the prospect of life here on Alternia is scary, the wild lusus in your hive that takes care of you is kind of scary… but at the end of the day, you can always lose yourself in the virtual world. You are an avid user of Stitch.TV, a streaming platform for anything from video games to 24/7 live blogging. Your dream is to become a famous streamer one day— obviously, you\'ll never be quite as important as a Violet Influencer, but maybe you\'ll be able to make other lowbloods feel a little less grim with you. You are **[Talented]** in **+PLC** thanks to your magnetic charisma. You gain the following WORDPLAY effects:\r\n\r\n> **PLUG**: And remember to support small streamers! You make sure an opponent can only roll moves against you on their next turn. On a **GREAT** WORDPLAY, you gain **1 [Boost]** too, cuz yay, attention! On a **MAX**, you gain **3 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **SUB**: You offer the opponent a handful of coins. They do 3 less damage (min. 1) on their next turn in exchange for **1 LUX** or TREASURE.\r\n\r\n> **COLLAB**: Hey, hey, help me with this! You give an opponent a chance to make a roll as a **[Free]** action. On a **GREAT**, their roll gets a **+2 [Buff]**; on a **MAX**, it\'s **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n\r\n> **RAID**: Hey, let\'s all look at that guy now! You distract everyone from paying attention to you, allowing you to slip away and become **[Hidden]**. On a **GREAT**, their first roll to find you is **[Inept]**, and on a **MAX**, it’s **[Godawful]**.\r\n\r\n> **SNIPE**: You use cutting words to hurt your opponent! This functions as Jab, but you can only use it after a **[Strife]** breaks out, instead of before.\r\n\r\n> **STIR DRAMA**: LMAO, I\'m not naming names, but… you insight some violent intent in your target. If they have a **[Negative]** Emotion, it\'s **[Heightened]**. On a **GREAT**, you give **1 [Drag]** too; on a **MAX**, **2 [Drag]**.'),
('hornless', 'HORNLESS', 'OTHER', 'MUTANT', '[Mutant][Cullbait][Passive]', 'Haha, hornless! Candy corn horns are the most iconic part of trollkind and you just... don\'t have them. This would just be an embarrassing quirk of yours if it weren\'t actually illegal for some reason. You have to wear fake horns to fit in, like some sort of fankid- **[Head] [Fashion]** items cost **one extra LUX** for you as you need to get custom versions with convincingly realistic fake horns built into them, and if your lack of horns is discovered, you\'re toast! On the plus side, the chitin that would have gone into making your horns ends up making the rest of you a little sturdier as a whole! Opponents can only use a maximum of **1 [WHAM]** on any **[Strife]** roll against you what with your strong, resilient candy corn-colored bones.\r\n'),
('hornswogglery', 'HORNSWOGGLERY', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Chicanery][Mental][Physical][Locked: Meowchant]', 'You\'ve gotta be able to pull the occasional fast-one on your customers. No hard feelings, of course, of course! But people can be… difficult at times! You\'ve got heaps of stories about that, you know! When you want to use your wits, roll **+APP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: OKAYOKAYOKAY, HEY HEY HEY RELAAAAX, YOU\'RE JUST A LIL  MERCHANT, C\'MAAAAAWN! The target either becomes **[Out-Of-Control]** or takes **2 [WHAM]**, their choice.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Hey, hey, come on! No need to get upset! The target either becomes **[Enraged]** or takes **1 [WHAM]**, their choice.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Nh— okay, didn\'t go according to plan, but you caught yourself before you screwed up. \r\n\r\n**GOOD: MWEEHEEHEEHEE! TRICKERY! You gain one of the following effects**:\r\n\r\n> **VANISH**: Puff! Aeeiiough, their eyes! You \"vanish\" in a puff of smoke that\'s extremely painful for other trolls. The opponent is **[Blinded]** for a turn!\r\n\r\n> **POCKET PEEP**: You take a quick peek into their Sylladex without them noticing. You know, in character, what the opponent has in their inventory, and how much **VP** they currently have.\r\n\r\n> **SABOTAGE**: While they aren\'t looking, their items seem to be in disrepair! You make an item in their Sylladex unusable for 3 turns. It appears to be broken, unless they find out otherwise by using PROBLEM SLEUTHING.\r\n\r\n> **PURRSUADE**: Hey, c\'mon, just listen! You get the effects of a REQUEST WORDPLAY, but it doesn\'t have the **[Manipulate]** tag. It\'s still **[Mental]**, though, so it doesn\'t work on monsters.\r\n\r\n> **CURSE YOU!**: You curse your opponent! At the end of the encounter, they\'re exposed to a random **[Slowburn]** Affliction. That\'s what they get for messing with a spooky shopkeeper! This is a **[One-Off]** effect.\r\n\r\n> **SWINDLE**: You subtly change the price of an item by **2 VP** after the customer agrees to buy it. Surely they won\'t notice! After 1d8 turns, they notice, and become **[Enraged]** every time they see you, until they give up or kick your ass. Or, y\'know, you kick theirs. This automatically triggers LET\'S STRIFE, but anyone unaware of your swindlery automatically gets a 1.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Ooohoohoo, it goes off without a hitch! You get a **GOOD**, but you either become **[Smug]** or **[Charm]** the target. After you choose one of these, further **GREAT** rolls always just give you **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: MAAAAAAXIMUM HORNSWOGGLERY! You get a **GOOD**, but you either become **[Supercilious]** or **[Fascinate]** the target. You can do this as many times as you roll **MAX** results.'),
('horrifyingHonk', 'HORRIFYING HONK', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Free][Recharge: 3][Manipulate]', 'HOOOOOONK! No sound instills a greater fear in trolls than the sound of an incoming Juggalo. Even if you do it in delight and glee, it still shoots alarm bells through people\'s heads! Do you even know how scary you are?! Each clown has their own honk; maybe it sounds like a squeaky bike horn, maybe it’s an airhorn, maybe it’s you just saying “honk” in a low and sultry voice. Pick what kind it is and write it on your sheet. When you make someone use **[Drag]** and want to make it even worse, roll **+GRT**.\n\n**MIN**: That was adorable! You made them feel much better. Your target loses all **[Drag]** without making it lower their roll. D\'oh!\n\n**BAD**: You choke on your honk… and the target doesn\'t use their **[Drag]** on this roll. Uh oh!\n\n**OK**: Nothing happens, but you don\'t trigger your **[Recharge]**; they use **[Drag]** as normal.\n\n**GOOD**: There we go! When the target finishes using their **[Drag]**, they gain 1 back immediately.\n\n**GREAT**: Wow! You\'re keeping the pressure ON, huh? The target gains back half the **[Drag]** you just made them use, rounded up, minimum 1!\n\n**MAX**: HOLY SHIT! That honk ECHOED through the walls! Your target gains all the **[Drag]** back immediately, and all opponents gain half of this **[Drag]**.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('horrorterrorsLittleTerror', 'HORRORTERROR\'S LITTLE TERROR', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'ORPHANER', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Orphaner]', 'Those in service to Gl\'bgolyb can take many forms. Some find themselves drawn to the depths by Her voice in youth, descending into the ocean and returning as warped deepsea violets. Others find themselves donning the uniform of the Orphaners. Both are touched by the literal horrorterror in different ways. Your continuous exposure to the immense dark powers of a god has meant that most other magic just... slides off you now, very easily. The first **[Magic]** roll against you in an Encounter automatically becomes a **BAD** as Glub Glub\'s latent energies lash back against it, and every **[Magic]** roll afterwards takes a **-1 [Nerf]**.\r\n\r\n'),
('hostileWorkEnvironment', 'HOSTILE WORK ENVIRONMENT', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Recharge: 2][Chicanery][Locked: Worker]', 'When you\'re feeling particularly… exhausted with your work environment, you sometimes do stuff you really shouldn\'t. Normally, this would run the risk of getting you culled, or worse, fired, but you\'ve proved yourself a valuable asset, and it\'d be a pain to find a replacement… this time. Just don\'t let it happen again! Roll the stat you became **[Talented]** at in AT YOUR SERVICE.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: OH NO! Your antics attracted the attention of a HORDE OF ANGRY BABOONICLES! You cause a STAMPEDE Hazard like a fucking idiot. Your rolls against it are **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: At least the Baboonicles don\'t devour you. \r\n\r\n**OK**: You think some pretty mean thoughts, and while you don\'t do anything about it, you do get **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You DID IT! You did labour! Nice work! Select one of the following options...\r\n\r\n> **SNAP**: You do what we all wish we could, and you just... you fuckin\' slap them. They\'re **[Enraged]** by your audacity, and can\'t gain any other emotions while **[Enraged]**.\r\n\r\n> **\"ACCIDENT\"**: Whoops! You spilled stuff everywhere! The target’s sylladex unloads on the floor; they must spend an action to pick their shit up. Effects that involve stealing such as Yoink or LARCENIZE are **[Tiered Up]** until they do so. \r\n\r\n> **DEAD SMILE**: The target is **[Charmed]**, lulled into a false sense of security by the familiar dead-eyed customer service smile. You\'re going to kick their ass.\r\n\r\n> **RUSH**: CHOP CHOP, FIVE MINUTES ON THE CLOCK! The target is **[Stressed]** as you hurry them.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Hahaha! It worked! NICE! You get a **GOOD** result and feel **[Confident]** about yourself for once as your ballsiness pays off. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: YOU ARE UNBEATABLE. HAHAHAHAHAHAHAHAH. Your hubris overwhelms you as you feel cooler and cooler. You get a **GREAT**, but your **[Confidence]** makes you roll better at **+HUB**, too!'),
('howItsDone', 'HOW IT\'S DONE', 'OTHER', 'MAID', '[Class][Advanced][Free][One-Off][Reaction][Locked: Maid]', 'Are... are they serious? You listen to them and take their advice to heart, and then they turn around and just... beef it like an amateur??? Buddy, stand back. You\'re gonna show \'em HOW. IT\'S. DONE. If the person you’ve designated as your leader with **WORKING RELATIONSHIP** rolls an **OK** or lower on their turn, you can needle them and ask just HOW they could\'ve possibly messed that up. The next time they roll that move, it’s **[Talented]**. If they get a **GOOD** or above, the other person gains 2 **[Boost]** as they succeed vicariously through your advice. Push them to be better, just like they’re doing for you. Classic Maid tricks.'),
('humbleHero', 'HUMBLE HERO', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Passive][Unlock: Tunnelwarden]', 'Stay back! You won\'t let them get hurt! Jades tend to be… very self-sacrificial. Almost martyrly at times. Though this isn\'t always a boon, it is of utmost importance in the Jade-run schoolfeeding blocks of the Auxiliatrices. Here, Tunnelwardens act as security, ensuring lusii being trained as caretakers don\'t eat babies, fending off underground monsters that follow grubcarts up, and even handling more dangerous issues to stop drone involvement. Even among Cloistered Trolls, a select few Tunnelwardens help protect their hallowed classmates from the creatures that hide in the Deepestcaverns. You are **[Talented]** in **+GRT**. You can always choose whether your team in a TEAM STRIFE is the CHALLENGER or CHAMPION, regardless of levels. You gain the following options for both.\r\n\r\n> **(CHAMPION) BASTION AGAINST THE DARKNESS**: You stand tall against evil foes! You and all your allies become immune to **[Scared]** or **[Dread]** for the encounter, and can only have **[Drag]** activated against any one of you once per turn. \r\n\r\n> **(CHALLENGER) FOR GREAT JUSTICE**: You won\'t go down! You cannot! If you have a **[Last Stand]** move, it applies to the whole team, not just you.\r\n\r\n> **(CHAMPION) PROTECT FROM DEVASTATION**: You\'re used to tackling big monsters, and you won\'t let them hurt your friends! If your opponent is a monster, not a team of trolls, your team\'s **[Strife]** rolls are **[Talented]**, or have a **+1 [Buff]** if they already are. \r\n\r\n> **(CHALLENGER) TYRANT TOPPLER**: You can\'t abide by evildoers! So let\'s fight on! Your entire team gets **1 [Boost]** every time the party takes damage.'),
('hunterOfAchievements', 'HUNTER OF ACHIEVEMENTS', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'CULLSCOUT', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Cullscout]', 'Proving that you can push things to the limit is one thing. Collecting SETS of MEDALS is another. You gain access to the following special MEDAL collection.\r\n\r\n> **THE BIG ONES**: YES! You\'ve collected all 8 UNIVERSAL MOVES MEDALS. This means you\'re specifically better than everyone else. HOOYAH. You gain a new **[Talent]** of your choosing.\r\n\r\n> **CULTURE CONNOISSEUR**: YEAAAAH. YOU KNOW INDIGOS BETTER THAN ANYONE. You\'ve collected all Indigo Tree moves, and gotten **3 MEDALS** from Indigo caste moves. Whenever you roll higher on average than another Indigo present on a given turn, you gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **PUNCH THE RAINBOW**: This VERY special medal comes from showing everyone the Hemospectrum was RIGHT. You must defeat a Rust, Bronze, Gold, Olive, Jade, Teal and Cerulean troll in combat, fight another Indigo troll and lose in combat to a Purple and Violet troll. Once you\'ve done this, your **[Manipulate]** rolls against trolls of a lower caste than you **[Tier Up]**. \r\n\r\n> **BAIT CULLED**: GOTTA CULL \'EM ALL! To earn this MEDAL, you must uphold the sacred duty of all good Imperial devotees, and that means CULLING SOME BAIT. You must defeat a Ghost, Shadowdropper, Rainbowdrinker, Moonbark, Grimdark and Mutant in combat. Defeating a Limeblood, Surface-Bound Cloistered Jade or other Cullbait Troll not listed allows you to remove one of the listed types. You\'re doing your duty! Once you\'ve done this, all your moves against **[Cullbait]** trolls **[Tier Up]**!\r\n\r\n'),
('huntersSenses', 'HUNTER\'S SENSES', 'OTHER', 'MOONBARK', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Eerie][Locked: Moonbark]', 'You have heightened senses, even while not in beast form. Rolls to find **[Hidden]** opponents are **[Tiered Up]**, or gain a **+2 [Buff]** if you already had an effect that did that, and you can automatically find **[Hidden]** trolls as an action in MOONFRENZY MODE.'),
('huzzahAWizard', 'HUZZAH! A WIZARD', 'OTHER', 'ASTROSORCERER', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Recharge: 2][Locked: Astrosorcerer]\r\n', 'You get all sorts of excited when you see other practitioners of magic. Ahhhh! I see you are a troll of CULTURE! When someone uses a **[Magic]** move around you, you become **[Enthusiastic]** and **[Proud]**.'),
('hyperadaptability', 'HYPERADAPTABILITY', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Nyanjutsu]', 'When someone pulls something on you… you don\'t let them pull it on you twice! When a troll rolls a move with the **[Analyze]**, **[Manipulate]**, **[Chicanery]**, **[Flourish]**, **[Control]** or **[Magic]** tag against you that doesn\'t have the **[Strife]** tag too, you take careful note. If they roll a move with the same tag again next turn, that roll is **[Inept]**. Stay on your toes! Shake it up!'),
('hyperevolution', 'HYPEREVOLUTION', 'OTHER', 'FIDUSSPAWNER', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Fiduspawner]', 'This is it. You’ve sat around and waited for who knows how long for this pseudo animal of yours to evolve at a slightly expedited, but still excruciatingly slow rate, and finally, the moment is here. Your fiduspawn is evolving! Your fiduspawn typically grows during evolution, allowing you to change the SIZE of your fiduspawn if you choose when you take this move. Your monster also gains a new permanent +2 to any stat you choose. Finally, your fiduspawn gains a secondary TYPE from the list above. Your newly evolved companion’s name changes with this evolution as well, reflecting its new SIZE, as well as placing the two TYPE suffixes next to each other. So your beloved LOTUFORCH evolves into a ENOTUFORCHICITY! Bigger name means better Fiduspawn, right?'),
('hypervigilance', 'HYPERVIGILANCE', 'OTHER', 'HACKERMAN', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Hackerman]', 'Ok ok ok listen yeah, any asshole can ‘borrow’ Troll Adobe Imageslice off the internet and get no more than a slap on the wrist. It’s like. A thing. But some of the stuff you’re doing could land you in deep shit if caught. Therefore, you gotta hide behind 4 proxies, 3 VPNs, 5 firewalls, and one extra cool husktop background. You become immune to the CIS WATCHLIST effect unless you do it to yourself, and all chat clients you use are hidden from outside detection. Well done, gamer! Speak your truth!'),
('hypnoempathics', 'HYPNOEMPATHICS', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Passive][Locked: Mastermind]', 'You\'ve learned to more subtly introduce emotions into the target rather than simply wrestle the steering wheel out of their grip, making them more easy to manipulate in the traditional sense. You may introduce the following **[Emotions]** into a target by using FREAKY EYE; on a **GOOD**, it lasts for **two turns**. On a **GREAT**, it lasts for the encounter. On a **MAX**, it\'s heightened, and lasts for a week.\r\n\r\n> 1. **[Charmed]**\r\n> 2. **[Tired]**\r\n> 3. **[Overwhelmed]**\r\n> 4. **[Enraged]**\r\n> 5. **[Peaceful]**\r\n> 6. **[Confused]**\r\n\r\n'),
('hypnoticGaze', 'HYPNOTIC GAZE', 'OTHER', 'RAINBOW_DRINKER', '[Template][Advanced][Control][Eerie][Magic][Locked: Rainbow Drinker]', 'Look into your eyes… Some Rainbow Drinkers are known to have hypnotic powers which work well on people who would be attracted to them. The most famous example is sapphic drinkers luring the gays back home for an honestly chill wine party and maybe some light consensual drinking, but it actually just works on any troll who looks into your eyes. When you want to manipulate someone, roll **+IMG**.\n\n**MIN**: They suddenly realize what you are and you have to scramble to cover up. Whaaaaat? Rainbow Drinker? Who, you? What are you talking aboooout? You gain the **[Dread]** condition.\n\n**BAD**: They aren’t looking into your eyes, dumbfuck!\n\n**OK**: They still aren’t looking into your eyes, but a few sweet words are buttering them up. Your **[Manipulate]** rolls against your target **[Tier Up]** unless they realize what you are.\n\n**GOOD**: Ahh… my sweet… just relax. Breathe in… breathe out. Your target will do any request you ask, no matter how dangerous; if it’s too extreme, however, they’ll remember afterwards and realize what you are.\n\n**GREAT**: Yessss… come with you… you’re going to have some sick wine and some cheese and grubbiscuits you bought at Wholegrubs… your target does whatever you say, giving you the benefits of a **GOOD** roll, and when they’re relinquished, they don’t remember anything clearly. Was that a dream..? \n\n**MAX**: The target unknowingly becomes your thrall. Any time you want to use WORDPLAY on them, you don’t need to roll; you simply get a **GOOD** result. They’ll willingly let you drink their blood, and they’ll never think this is weird!'),
('ichor', 'ICHOR', 'FUCHSIA', 'FUCHSIA', '[Fuchsia][Basic][Passive]', 'The ground itself recoils from holding your spilled blood. You do not gain any mechanical penalties from being **[Bloodied]**, and all trolls who see you become so are **[Terrified]**.'),
('identityTheft', 'IDENTITY THEFT', 'HEART', 'HEART', '[Aspect][Basic][Free][Locked: Heart]', 'It’s hard to be your own person, sometimes. Isn’t it easier to just mirror people around you? They seem to know what they’re doing, certainly! At the beginning of an encounter, you can pick an ally (or enemy, if no allies are available) and choose an effect.\r\n\r\n> Gain access to one of their **[Talents]** for **1 round**.\r\n> Gain access to one of their **[Open]** moves for **2 rounds**.\r\n> Get a **+2 [Buff]** to your rolls that involve their highest stat for **3 rounds**.'),
('idiotSandwich', 'IDIOT SANDWICH', 'OTHER', 'GOREMAND', '[Template][Advanced][One-Off][Manipulate][Locked: Goremand]', 'Like any good Goremand, you try to surround yourself with a good team who knows what they’re doing. Unfortunately for you, sometimes you end up surrounded by idiots. And these idiots need someone to keep them in check. Whenever you need to strike fear into the hearts of other trolls, roll **+GRT**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Not only does your target ignore your chiding, they believe what they’re doing is better! The target becomes **[Smug]** and gains **+2 [Boost]**. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: Yeah, yeah, okay dipshit. The target delights on seeing you falter at their dismissive nature and gains **+1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Eugh… fine, they’ll do better next time. They listen, but neither one of you is particularly affected.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Oh jegus. You say some pretty mean things that leave them a little shaken up. The target gains **+1 [Drag]**. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You fucking donkey, you’re forgetting the basics! What, am I going to have to schoolfeed you on the battlefield?! The target becomes **[Sad]** at your berating and gains **+2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: IS THIS YOUR EXCUSE FOR A BATTLE? HONESTLY, YOUR LUSUS COULD DO BETTER, AND IT DOESN’T EVEN HAVE OPPOSABLE THUMBS! WHAT ARE YOU? AN ABSOLUTE IDIOT SANDWICH IS WHAT. The target starts **[Crying]** uncontrollably and gains **+3 [Drag]**.'),
('iFightForMyFriends', 'I FIGHT FOR MY FRIENDS!', 'BLOOD', 'BLOOD', '[Aspect][Ultra][Free][Updated: Blood Player Rights][Locked: Blood]', 'At the start of an encounter in which you\'re paired with one or more allies, you\'re emboldened by your ties with them, whether they\'re your quadrants or just some guy you made friends with five minutes ago because you shared some chicken nuggets- choose 1 of their **[Talents]**. You become **[Talented]** in that stat for the duration of the encounter. If you have more than one ally you\'re fighting with, then you can choose 1 **[Talent]** from each, to a maximum of 3. If their only **[Talent]** is something you’re already **[Talented]** in, pick an ally and “share” a talent with them. This CANNOT be something they use a 4d8 for. If you happen to share a talent with everyone in the encounter, you simply gain a **+2 [Buff]** to a stat for every ally you can’t talent-share with. Conversely, when you are fighting alone, you are always grasping for bonds with others, even going to the extent to form them with your enemies, be it as friendly rivals or simply in the made up spirit in your head with which you truly, passionately, want to kick their ass. You can choose 1 **[Talent]** to gain from your enemy the same way you would from an ally. Unlike the maximum for your allies, if you are a madman fighting four or more people on your own, then, well... you probably need those extra **[Talents]**, my good bitch!'),
('ignoranceIsBliss', 'IGNORANCE IS BLISS', 'PROSPIT', 'PROSPIT', '[Sway][Passive][Locked: Prospit]', 'All problems have multiple solutions; there isn\'t always a right answer! A lack of knowledge isn\'t always a bad thing- sometimes life is more exciting when it\'s not all planned out. When you fail an **[Analyze]** roll (receive an OK or lower), you gain **2 [Boost]**.\r\n'),
('imagineering', 'IMAGINEERING', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][Passive][Magic]', 'Intentionally or not, your caste’s eccentric creativity leaks out onto the world around you. Whether you’re using a banana as a literal telephone, patching up a wound with a Warkraft single or inexplicably using a can of tab as a fully functional spyglass, items work in strange and mysterious ways around you! When you buy an item, you can give it one of the following tags in exchange for spending **1 VP** extra. \r\n\r\n**Phone**: That frog is a phone! Nice! You can use this item to do **[Tech]** stuff, and you get a **+1 [Buff]** to **[Tech]** rolls to do so.\r\n\r\n**Medicine**: Slap a sandwich onto that gash in your back, and it doubles as a bandaid! This **[Consumable]** item can also be consumed to **[Heal] 1 HP** and remove a condition.\r\n\r\n**Fashion**: Wow! Your medicalizer fits as a sweet pair of sneakers, too! You merge the items into a Fashion item. Items like this don\'t count towards collections. \r\n\r\n**Vehicle**: SKRRRRT! The item doubles as a Tiny Vehicle! \r\n\r\n**Tool**: Your item does… something! Maybe it\'s a key, or a frisbee, or whatever. This lets you use the item in strange narrative ways, but has no mechanical benefit and doesn\'t cost **1 VP** extra.\r\n\r\n**Magic as Fuck**: Huh? Oh, this rice maker is actually an ancient artefact. You buy a **[Rare]** item rather than a normal one, though it appears completely mundane.'),
('imGonnaWrassleEm', 'I’M GONNA WRASSLE ‘EM', 'OTHER', 'BEAST_BRAWLER', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Physical][Locked: Beast Brawler]', 'Taking down a Colossus is a terrifying proposition for anyone with good sense. Luckily, you wouldn’t be in this business if you had good sense! Some people see a giant bird with a deadly beak that could slice you in two like tissue paper and just really, really wanna try and wressle it. When fighting each colossi, you gain a unique and crucial bonus. Additionally, any LOOT obtained from a colossi you help take down is automatically a little… better. :) \n\n**MARBORASSQUALE**: Touching the OH SHIT ooze does not render you **[Trapped]**. PUTRID BREATH **[Tiers Down]** against you on a **GOOD** or a **GREAT**. \n\n**AVIONIHILLATOR**: Rolls to RIDE THE WINDS are **[Talented]**, and **[Tier Up]**. The Avionihillator stays on the ground for one more **[Strife]** before LORD OF THE SKIES takes effect. \n\n**CHAORYBSCYLLIS**: You are completely immune to the weakening effects of TRACES OF THE DEEP. \n\n**IMPERIAL ARMADA ERADICATION DRONE MK III: Nothing :) This is not a monster :) Perish as the others perish **:)'),
('imIn', 'I’M IN', 'OTHER', 'ROBOT', '[Template][Basic][Tech][Locked: Robot]', 'It’s a pretty introductory skill to be able to hack into systems left and right. It’s pretty much the first lesson at robot school. It’s made especially easy when people don’t make their connections private. Morons. You gain the SCRIPT GRUBBIE HACKERMAN entry move upon taking this, although you do not unlock the rest of the template and it does not take a template slot. If you already had the HACKERMAN template, you instead gain a **+1 [Buff]** to rolling this move.\r\n\r\n'),
('imMe', 'I’M ME', 'HEART', 'HEART', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Heart] \r\n', 'You’re you! You’re not willing to change that; you have this fiercely independent self-image that won’t just change because of other people’s influence. Any **[Manipulate]** roll against you is **[Inept]**, because nobody really knows how to convince you to do anything any way but your own. It’s a little draining at times…'),
('immovableObject', 'IMMOVABLE OBJECT', 'BLOOD', 'BLOOD', '[Aspect][Basic][Free][Locked: Blood]', 'You are VERY set in your ways, and you don’t like being told to change. When someone rolls to **[Manipulate]** you, you can give a conditional BUT WE’RE DOING IT MY WAY! to your manipulator. This counts as a **GOOD** or **GREAT** WORDPLAY roll to **[Manipulate]** right back at the target. If the target refuses to do as you say, their **[Manipulate]** roll also fails, and they gain no associated benefits from a successful **[Manipulate]** roll. If you reject someone’s WORDPLAY roll either from them rolling poorly or you rejecting a **GOOD** roll, you gain **2 [Boost]**, because heh, take that.'),
('impactEntropy', 'IMPACT ENTROPY', 'OTHER', 'HEIR', '[Class][Advanced][Locked: Heir]', 'Ow! Wait, that didn’t actually hurt? It’s clear someone just hit you, but you barely felt a thing. Turns out when you embody your entire aspect, things related to it get absorbed as well like some aspect black hole. When you take the move, you gain 1 **[Resistance]** against a damage type of your choice. The type of damage must make sense aspect wise, such as a Heir of Rage resisting **[Somatic]** damage or a Heir of Mind resisting **[Psychic]** damage.\r\n'),
('imperegent', 'IMPEREGENT', 'VIOLET', 'ADULT', '[Violet][Locked: Adult]', 'Did you really expect HIC to have her hands in every single colony she (and nobody else) has conquered? No way! Somebody has to watch after all these places and \\\'gently\\\' guide them into becoming perfect colonies. That\\\'s where you come in. Thankfully, the Condesce is far too busy to bother you so really? You\\\'re in charge now. You have subjects. You have resources. And so long as you can keep your appearance just Condensce-loyal enough? Free reign to reign. Choose an option below. This indicates the type of colony you rule over and the benefits you gain from it.\n\n> **ARMORY**: Blades, blasters, and booms are the specialty of your colony. You can have 2 Abstrata on your specibus and can switch one of them on the fly as a **[One-Off]** action.\n\n> **DATACENTER**: Future’s made of virtual insanity, and by the Empress you are ill. Your **PROBLEM SLEUTHING** options are now on **[Recharge: 1]** and a **BAD** result simply does nothing.\n\n> **FORGE WORLD**: Not all drones can be procured on Alternia, so that’s what your colony is here for. You can call in a **DRONE STRIKE [Hazard]** that you and your allies are immune to.\n\n> **VACATION RESORT**: Massage drones, nutrient rich spas, NO RESPONSIBILITIES... yeaaah, this is the life. You always start an encounter **[Happy]** or **[Peaceful]** and ignore the first two times someone would affect you with **[Drag]**.'),
('imperialDictation', 'IMPERIAL DICTATION', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'HET', '[Template][Basic][Manipulate][Locked: HET]', 'Your job is to keep society where it is, now and forever. Whether it\'s by clubbing that history has ended over a rebel\'s head until they stop moving or by convincing the public of the same, you have been trained to ensure it. You gain the following WORDPLAY effects as **GREAT** options, unique to the caste of each target.\n\n**HEMOANON**: It\'s time to stop playing around and show your blood, coward. Your target must state a caste they belong to or take 2 **[Drag]** as you lash them with threats for breaking from the norm. They surely wouldn\'t lie!\n\n**RUST**: Are you doing your part? Your target must transfer you 1 **[Boost]** they have, or take 1 **[Drag]**.\n\n**BRONZE**: It\'s honest work, you have to admit that much. Your job is to take it. Your target must use a **[Heal]** on you, healing 1 HP on any result better than an **OK** or when using an item. If they lack any themselves, they may use your items for **[Free]**. If neither of you possess a method of **[Healing]**, nothing happens.\n\n**GOLD**: They\'re so lucky to have barely escaped being helmed by being hatched just slightly to the left of being a perfect battery, aren\'t they? You should tell them! ... Oh, did that one get the battery assignment on the job quiz anyways? Your bad, you definitely didn\'t look that up beforehand. Your target experiences **[Dread]**, the Emotion **[Heightening]** on a **MAX**.\n\n**LIME**: They are not supposed to exist. You must correct this immediately. You both take 2 **[Drag]** in the panic, but the target also loses the ability to ABSCOND until this effect is off **[Recharge]** or you are **[Stunned]**.\n\n**OLIVE**: Olives are still trolls. You know this. You very much do. It\'s still really funny to go kitty kitty nya nya at them and watch them fluster in frustration at it. Your target takes a -2 **[Nerf]** to **[Mental]** rolls for 1 Turn.\n\n**JADE**: You... okay, the Empire doesn\'t actually put many hit pieces out on jades. You don\'t have much here. But you do have a close relationship with the CIS, which means you get a whole lot of second hand gossip! You get a **GOOD** Problem Sleuthing result now for free, becoming a **GREAT** on a **MAX**. The question must relate to the target, the caverns or similar.\n\n**TEAL**: Paperwork is paperwork, and you have better things to do. You order the target to roll a move of your choice aimed at a target of your choice. \n\n**CERULEAN**: You know these spiderpunks better than anyone else. Same streets, same kinds of lusii, same caste. You don\'t need any fancy training to push these buttons. Your target becomes either **[Hopeful]** or experiences **[Dread]**, with the Emotions becoming **[Heightened]** on a **MAX**.\n\n**INDIGO**: Indigos create culture, but you\'re the ones that spread it for them. You can imitate the poshness well enough. Your target becomes **[Charmed]** with your understanding of intricate indigo culture. The Emotion is **[Heightened]** on a **MAX**.\n\n**PURPLE**: Now wouldn\'t it be a shame if you distracted this big scary clown from you by pointing out the totally legit heresy over there? 1 Damage inflicted on you by them next turn is redirected to a victim of your choice, or an NPC.\n\n**VIOLET**: You know, it\'s soo unfortunate that landdwellers pour so much toxic waste into the ocean from the factories. It\'s like, totally lame. Isn\'t it? Your target becomes either **[Enraged]** at being told they live in industrial waste or **[Smug]** as you give a tongue lashing to your fellow squishy landlubbers. The Emotions become **[Heightened]** on a **MAX**.\n\n**FUCHSIA**: Oh, little heiress! ... Or big Empress! 50/50! You transfer all **[Boost]** you have to your target.\n\n**FANKID**: They aren\'t supposed to exist either! Little does anyone know, but the HET is also the first line of defense against alien invaders! Other than the drones! Your target becomes **[Scared]** as you list off the 7468 Declaration Of Alternian Supremacy Over Xenolifeforms to them, as per the right of all sentient beings to know why the Empire is about to blow them up. On a **MAX**, the Emotion is **[Heightened]**.'),
('imposingPresence', 'IMPOSING PRESENCE', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Oh, GOD. It\'s a seadweller. Fuck. Look at them, they\'re so insanely strong and confident. FUCK. That\'s the feeling people get when you\'re around. But, y\'know, it\'s kind of a lonely life, sometimes. Everyone\'s low-key kinda scared of you. When you enter an encounter, you can choose to make all trolls **[Stressed]**. This **[Stress]** ends after you are made to use **[Drag]**, as everyone goes \"oh lol, they\'re not that scary\".'),
('impressiveHorns', 'IMPRESSIVE HORNS', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Passive]', 'There\'s no way not to be immature about this move. You have exceptionally large or exceptionally hard horns. Even the shortest horns of a Bronze are much tougher than those of other trolls. Yup, one way or another, your horns sure are big and impressive. You can replace the **GREAT** or **MAX** of a **[Strife]** roll with this effect.\r\n\r\n**TOSS**: SEEYA LATER, STINKY!! You throw that motherfucker into the air with your horns. They are **[Flying]** for a turn and then land **[Floorbound]**. They take **1 [Somatic]** damage then, and only then!'),
('improvise', 'IMPROVISE', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Basic][Physical][Strife][Locked: Full-Time]\r\n', 'Anondom comes with its own funky little quirks, including the fact that you’ve forfeited your right to the safety your birth caste gave you. Which means you know. Your butt can get kicked at any opportunity if you sneeze the wrong way. Thankfully though, you’ve learned how to take a tricky situation and make do with what you’ve got. Roll the stat you gained [Talent] in from SYSTEMIC SPITE.\r\n \r\n**MIN**: AUGH! This is what you get from taking fighting tips from the internet! You take 2 **[Somatic]** damage and for one turn gain 1 **[Resistance]** to… **[Boost]**?! BLUH!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You misstep and strain something, taking 1 **[Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Okay well you missed, and this is bad. But hopefully being on edge will help keep you alive! You gain 1 **[Resistance]** to **[Drag]** for one turn, as your adrenaline refuses to let you be bogged down.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Holy shit that worked? That worked! Deal 1 **[Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: That opponent of yours is going to regret trying to pick on you now. WHAM! Deal 2 **[Somatic]** damage, or 1 **[Somatic]** damage and gain 2 **[Resistance]** to **[Drag]** for one turn as your blood is truly pumping now!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Call it skill, call it destiny, but you refuse to fall just yet… Your opponent will, though! Deal 3 **[Somatic]** damage, or 2 **[Somatic]** damage and either gain 2 **[Resistance]** to **[Drag]** for one turn or steal 2 **[Boost]** from an enemy.'),
('incantationOfIncentive', 'INCANTATION OF INCENTIVE', 'OTHER', 'WITCH', '[Class][Advanced][Free][One-Off][Magic][Locked: Witch]', 'There are many ways to get the results you\'re after. Brute force, wits, coercion and most importantly, incentivisation! Why would you wear yourself out trying to command everyone at once? It’s much more efficient to change just one little rule and watch everyone funnel into what you want willingly! As a **[Free]** action at the start of an encounter, choose one group of moves from the list below. Then decide if everyone in the encounter, including you, will gain 1 **[Boost]** or 1 **[Drag]** when they roll a **GOOD+** result on a move with that tag. This **[Boost]/[Drag]** only goes to the person who rolled the move. Will you reward others for following your design? Or punish them for straying from it?\n\nMOVES:\n- **[Mental]**\n- **[Psionic]** but not **[Strife]**\n- **[Physical]** but not **[Strife]**\n- **[Manipulation]**\n- **[Reaction]**'),
('incredibleCuriosity', 'INCREDIBLE CURIOSITY', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'You thought you\'d seen it all. From rampaging clowns to wailing lusii, nothing much surprises you now. But occasionally… huh, that\'s new! Interesting… amazing! Curious, even! Maybe there\'s more to life than the same old! You become either **[Smug]**, **[Proud]**, **[Insightful]**, or **[Enthusiastic]** when you roll a **GREAT** PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll for the first time in an encounter (**[Heightened]** if you get a **MAX**) as you satiate your burning curiosity!'),
('incredibleImagination', 'INCREDIBLE IMAGINATION', 'OTHER', 'HEROMODE', '', 'Your imagination is so powerful that it can practically create entire new worlds. Whether it\'s through your force of willpower, your mysterious magical acumen or your unbelievable psychic might, you can make the unreal real. When you enter **HERO MODE**, you may select one of the following benefits.\r\n\r\n> **MIRACLE**: Something impossible and out of your control happens. Whether your deity has blessed you, your magic has done the impossible or you\'ve pushed reality to its limit, it happens, and it\'s inspiring. You make SOMETHING coincidentally happen that doesn\'t mechanically affect you, but does grant a deep wish of yours. You **[Heal]** 2 **HP** and become **[Inspired]** by this turn of events.\r\n\r\n> **SPELLBLENDING**: You push to your limits... and BEYOND! Your ability to affect reality with your mind is uncanny. You roll two **[Psionic]** or **[Magic]** rolls in one action. They both get the same roll result. \r\n\r\n> **TEMPOSLINGER**: Come on, it\'s time to dance! You begin a Fraymotif that\'s, frankly, so much more intense than any normal one. Pick a song from the Homestuck Discography, and play it during this strife. Based on the main characters associated with this song, you decide the Aspect you benefit from, rather than using your own. All participants, even enemies, receive a **MAX** result on Fraymotif, even if **[Buildup]** hasn\'t been met. All of your rolls for the rest of the encounter use **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n> **ARCHMAGE\'S MAGIC**: You pull deep from the most ancient laws of the stars and your soul, and draw upon powers you could never dream of. Make any one **[Magic]** roll in the game, even if you would have no way to access it, such as the magic of an Astrosorcerer, a Juggalo or an Aspect other than your own. You have access to this move for the encounter.\r\n\r\n> **TRUE POWER**: Your psychic abilities... ARE UNLEASHED! YAAAAAARGH! You begin **[Flying]**, have glowing white eyes, and temporarily gain access to any one **[Psionic]** move in the game you wouldn\'t be able to use normally for the encounter. If you don\'t HAVE **[Psionics]**, this is a **[Magic]** effect, and rather than glowing eyes, you\'re encircled by runes.\r\n'),
('indecisiveDecision', 'INDECISIVE DECISION', 'SPACE', 'SPACE', '[Aspect][Basic][Recharge: 2][Locked: Space]', 'You have a hard time picking out decisions… choice paralysis is a common foe of yours, because you’re so often overwhelmed by the sheer infinity of choices you could make. When you want to step back and see what happens, roll 1d8. You get a **GOOD** result on the move you roll as you don’t actively use it yourself; it just kind of happens. Ignore all effects that would prevent you from using the relevant move. If you land on GUTSUCKERY at **full HP**, you may **[Heal]** above your max HP. While you\'re **[Slowed]**, this move is **[Free]**.\r\n\r\n> 1. LET’S STRIFE (YOU GET TO ROLL IT TWICE)\r\n> 2. GRIEF\r\n> 3. GUTSUCKERY\r\n> 4. PROBLEM SLEUTHING\r\n> 5. SHENANIGANS\r\n> 6. SWASHBUCKLE\r\n> 7. WORDPLAY\r\n> 8. CHOOSE ONE OF THE ABOVE RESULTS\r\n\r\n'),
('indignantHowlOfTheScornedEducaterror', 'INDIGNANT HOWL OF THE SCORNED EDUCATERROR', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Auxiliatrice]', 'There is literally nothing fucking scarier than an angry teacher. It means they\'re at their wits’ end, and they\'ve got nothing to lose. The patient, pleasant demeanor is a cracked mask, and I\'m pretty sure— yeah, I definitely pissed my pants in fear. Whenever you get a **BAD** or a **MIN** roll, you may become **[Out-Of-Control]** for **[Free]**, and your **[Talent]** in **+PLC** turns to **+GRT**. All trolls who witness this are **[Terrified]**.'),
('indigoExceptionalism', 'INDIGO EXCEPTIONALISM', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'CULLSCOUT', '[Template][Basic][Locked: Cullscout]', 'You want those MEDALS. You NEED them. You CRAVE them. So sometimes you push yourself to your limit in order to prove how great you are. It\'s healthy! You can become **[Icarian]** as an action.\n\n'),
('individualThoughtPatterns', 'INDIVIDUAL THOUGHT PATTERNS', 'OTHER', 'BARD', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Recharge: 2][Locked: Bard]', 'They don’t understand you. Some people don’t even recognize you. But, as you always say… who actually gives a shit??? They aren’t in your mind, YOU are! Silly silly fools, don’t bother trying to keep up. They could never traverse the halls of your mind like you can. Choose which **[Aspect]** represents most of your thoughts when you take this move. If it’s your opposite **[Aspect]**, you have 1 **[Psychic] [Resistance]** and gain 2 **[Boost]** when you succeed at **[Mental]** and **[Flourish]** rolls, since you’re used to your thoughts coming from unexpected angles and places that you’d rather bury away or just ignore. If it’s your true **[Aspect]**, you have 1 **[Somatic] [Resistance]** and gain 2 **[Boost]** when you succeed at **[Physical]** and **[Chicanery]** rolls, since you embrace the thoughts that naturally come to you based upon your lived experiences, whether they’re welcome or not. Additionally, when you score a **MAX** with one of the types of rolls associated with your choice, others that share the same **[Aspect]** as that choice become **[Confused]** for 2 rounds since they’ve never seen their aspect portrayed in your chaotic and unique way.\r\n'),
('indomitableStrength', 'INDOMITABLE STRENGTH', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Passive]', 'Perfection! It is the GOAL of all good Indigos. And not just in what you do and what you say; you need to have the PERFECT physique. You need to be RIIIIIIPPED. It takes a true academic understanding of the body to transfer strength to Subgrubs And Snazzards Sixth Edition stat points! Your stat cap for **+GRT** increases to +5, and you may reduce another stat by 1 to a minimum of 0 now and add it to your **+GRT** now.'),
('infiniteExperiences', 'INFINITE EXPERIENCES', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Passive][Locked: AU]', 'Who knows the life you lived in your own world? There\'s an unending amount of universes out there, so who\'s to say how you lived in yours? You may select any **[Basic]** **[Open]** move of your choice. If it requires a stat to roll, it uses the one you had from ALTERNATE UNIVERSE. Be sure to pick something that makes sense to your world, not something rancidly strong! In no universe is powergaming okay!'),
('infiniteFoolsmastery', 'INFINITE FOOLSMASTERY', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Goofball]', 'Whether you intend it or not, you are the funniest person around. Your hijinks, your misadventures, your twerpery… you\'re an extremely likable and genuinely charming person, at the end of the day, and people like that about you. You gain access to HERO MODE through your RESPLENDENT RASCALITY. But it does not end there! Your JOKESTER\'S PORTFOLIO is not limited to merely traditional pranks! You gain a second activation of HERO MODE, with which you can use ANY HERO MODE (from INCREDIBLE IMAGINATION to GLORIOUS GRACE), except any rolls made using it involve **+RAS**. Let the sea of goofs surge! Finally, you get a **MAX** on **+RAS** rolls on a 17+.'),
('infinityMatrix', 'INFINITY MATRIX', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Ultra][Passive][Psionic][Locked: Network]', 'You are one with the internet now; everything you do, it does, and it does back to you. You\'ve pondered that perhaps your own mind and soul might not really exist, just a reflection of the content put on by users. Ultimately, it doesn\'t matter. The Cloudmind isn\'t just all Network Golds. It\'s everyone who uses a computer ever. You just get to see deeper than they do. Till death do us part… You gain access to HERO MODE with your PRECISE PERSPICACITY. Your **[Psionic]** moves can never be **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]**, or **[Nerfed]**; they\'re literally all of what you are. Finally, you can manifest your true power in an EXTREMELY flashy show. As a **[One-Off]** **[Buildup: 3]** action, you can cause a CYBERSTORM Hazard, a Hazard unique to you. It functions as follows. For the purpose of this move, a phone has 1 HP. \n\n**ROUND 1**: Huh. All your devices are heating up. And the internet was cut out. That\'s strange. Nobody can access the internet around you. Network Golds in the area are exposed to the PSIBURN Affliction, and non-Network Golds who may have been given access to Network moves are immediately disconnected.\n\n**ROUND 2**: OH, FUCK! Your phone DISCHARGES, blasting out streams of electric power! Everyone with a functioning phone takes **1 [Electric] [Somatic]** damage.\n\n**ROUND 3**: Jesus Christ, what\'s happening?! Add up every single thing in the encounter that could feasibly connect to the internet; functioning phones, items in people\'s inventories and even robots. Then, divide it by the number of trolls present. Everyone takes that much **[Electric] [Somatic]** damage. After this round, robots may take an action to switch their wifi off and trolls may roll **[Strife]** to destroy any items connected to the internet.\n\n**ROUND 4+**: Round 3 repeats until all devices are destroyed, or the PSIBURN affliction ends on all Network trolls. Anyone brought to **0 HP** or lower during this Hazard is exposed to the DOUBLE MOBIUS REACHAROUND VIRUS Affliction.'),
('influenctigator', 'INFLUENCTIGATOR', 'VIOLET', 'ADULT', '[Violet][Locked: Adult]', 'Some folks command armies or vassal states. You? You command movements and culture, what trends from trolls and conquered people make it in this empire. Yes, you are the reason wheels never caught on in Alternian society. You earn this influence not only by being fabulously wealthy, but competing with other Influenctigators for attention and favor. Maybe one night you will be trendy enough for the Empress to say she likes your shoes. And you\\\'ll be thankful, as will the many little goldfish living in your trendy aquarium high heels. Anytime you roll a **GREAT+** result with any stats you have **[Talent]** in, you gain 1 **[Boost]** as you feel affirmed in your ability to manipu- AHEM, influence the people around you. Additionally, as a **[One-Off]** action you can inflict someone with the **SIMPTOMS [Affliction]** as you flatter them with the idea that those gaudy tattoos could just be the next big thing!'),
('infodump', 'INFODUMP', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Mental][One-off]', 'You just REALLY love something. Maybe it\'s a special interest, or maybe a hyperfixation. Regardless, you love something, and you want to talk about it NOW. Even if you\'re in a fight, you just want to do it! Roll **+PSP** as you start to infodump on your favorite topic.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You get a crucial detail wrong, and you gain the **[Despair]** condition. What is wrong with you? Isn\'t this your entire personality? Loving this interest? How could you fail like this?\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You just mumble a little bit. Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You ramble for a moment, either giving your opponent **1 [Drag]** as they\'re distracted, or yourself **1 [Boost]** as you talk about something you love.\r\n\r\n**GOOD: Choose one of the following effects**:\r\n\r\n> You become **[Focused]**, spewing information left and right.\r\n> The target becomes **[Deafened]** because you\'re rambling over their thoughts. \r\n> You make an ally **[Enthusiastic]** as they listen to your cool facts!\r\n\r\n**GREAT: Choose one of the following effects**:\r\n\r\n> You become **[Hyperfocused]** as you speak.\r\n> Your enemy becomes **[Deafened]** and takes **1 [Psychic]** damage, getting a headache from how quickly you\'re speaking. \r\n> Your ally becomes **[Passionate]** while they start to love your interest too!\r\n\r\n**MAX: Choose one of the following effects**:\r\n\r\n> Your enemy becomes **[Deafened]** for the rest of the encounter and takes **1 [Psychic]** damage because you do not stop talking.\r\n> You become **[Hyperfocused]** and **[Passionate]** as your love for this topic courses through you.\r\n> Your ally becomes **[Excited]** and **[Passionate]** while they listen to you!'),
('inPlainSight', 'IN PLAIN SIGHT', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Passive]', 'Limes shouldn\'t exist. That sucks! You don\'t like not existing. But in the eyes of the general populace, you\'re all meant to be extinct, and seeing you is grounds to immediately cull you. Cuz, y\'know, **[Cullbait]**. But you have found ways to blend in with the general populace, and make yourself part of the world again! Both of these options hide your caste, but if you become **[Bloodied]** or use a **[Cullbait]** move, you reveal yourself.\r\n\r\n> **DIAGETIC DISGUISE**: You use the world around you to hide who you are. You can take another caste’s non-**[Psionic]** (Rust, Bronze, Gold or Olive) tree as a Template. You can only take **1 [Basic]** or **[Advanced]** move, not both. You gain the **[Entry]** now, and can feasibly take the **[Ultra]**, but you don\'t get their **[Talent]** or HERO MODE. You disguise yourself as someone of this caste, wearing their clothes, colours and taking on their culture. When people see you use a **[Magic]** roll, roll 1d8. On a 1, you\'re figured out! Otherwise, people are confused by what you did, but don\'t understand it.\r\n\r\n> **GO INCOGNITO**: You dress in greys, hiding among other anonymous caste trolls who use the cancer family of signs as an act of rebellion… except you, of course, wear your true sign. You take the Hemoanon Template… except you can still take a tree! That\'s so nice for you. You don\'t change your **[Talent]**, though.\r\n\r\n> **WALKING COGNITOHAZARD**: You walk outside in full caste colours, openly use meta powers, and don\'t even worry about it. What? It\'s fine, nobody is making a big deal out of it. You lose all **[Cullbait]** tags on Lime moves. This **[Magic]** effect acts as a sort of personal chameleon matrix, meaning that you can just walk around without people realising you\'re Lime unless it\'s actively pointed out to them. As such, **[Analyze]** rolls against you are **[Godawful]**. They physically can\'t think too hard about you!'),
('inquisitorsJudgement', 'INQUISITOR\'S JUDGEMENT', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Slayer]', 'Not all monsters! One of the most important lessons of a good hunter is to distinguish between the good and the wicked. You aren\'t some highblood with a vacuum cleaner destroying any unnatural entity that you come across; you\'re a cleanser of evil. And being a monster doesn\'t make you evil by default. Just look at Troll Alucard or Troll Casper. When you encounter and interact with an **[Eerie]** Troll, you can decide between the two following Judgements as a **[Free]** action, which can be changed as a **[Lengthy]** action. This is a permanent effect.\r\n\r\n> **JUDGMENT OF VIRTUE**: Ultimately, this monster is pretty chill. So long as you two are in an encounter together, the target\'s **OK** rolls **[Tier Up]** to a **GOOD**. \r\n\r\n> **JUDGMENT OF WICKEDNESS**: NASTY LITTLE CREATURE! PERISH! You curbstomp the fuck out of this guy. All of their **BAD** rolls **[Tier Down]** to **MIN**.'),
('insanelyCool', 'INSANELY COOL', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'Okay, so here\'s the thing? You\'re fucking AWESOME is the problem. Like, SUPER FUCKING COOL. Yeah, you stumble sometimes! Yeah, you make mistakes! But shit GOES YOUR WAY, and that\'s fucking SWEET, okay?! So let\'s get out there and WHOOP ASS! You get a **MAX** on any rolls on an 19+, not a 20+. Whenever you get **MAX**, all allies gain **1 [Boost]**, and all enemies get **1 [Drag]**.'),
('insectnomancer', 'INSECTNOMANCER', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Beekeeper]', 'BZZZZZZ! The power of technology BENDS to your will! From the smallest computer hexachip to the largest processing hive, you are a master of all things hardware. You gain access to HERO MODE through your RESPLENDENT RASCALITY. You have forged an empathic link with all things Apidae, including the majority that lives inside technology. Insects of the bee or wasp variety won\'t attack you unless prompted. In fact, so empowered by them are you, that when you are in the presence of a BEE SWARM Hazard, they aid you rather than harm you! While in the middle of a BEE SWARM, you can start **[Flying]** as an action. Rather than **[Confused]**, you become **[Hyperfocused]** in the presence of a BEE SWARM. You can choose to stop your BEE SWARM from attacking certain allies, too. Finally, if you sacrifice items from ELECTRIC ENTOMOLOGY or have RAW MATERIAL from the EXPEDITED ENGINEERING move, you can spend **VP** from it to have your bee swarm pull off the following…\r\n\r\n**REPAIR TECH (1 VP)**: The bees fix an item that was destroyed earlier in the encounter! Hooray!\r\n\r\n**BUILD WALL (2 VP)**: Your bees create a wall of beeswax for you to hide behind! If you spend an action to duck behind this wall, you can become **[Hidden]**. The wall has **2 HP**; anyone who breaks it reveals all **[Hidden]** trolls as if they found them through SPOT.\r\n\r\n**CONTINUE BUZZING (3 VP)**: Don\'t leave yet! You scatter food for the bees, causing them to keep it up! They last an additional round, repeating ROUND 3 of the Hazard.\r\n\r\n**MASS HACK (4 VP)**: Your bees swarm out in every which way to spread total chaos! Your next SWARMWARE roll affects multiple targets at once.\r\n\r\n**CHANNEL ELECTRICITY (5 VP)**: All trolls in the area gain **[Electric]** damage to their weapons as the bees humming and buzzing charge up a storm! This lasts for the Hazard.\r\n\r\n**TECHNOLOGICAL MAYHEM (6 VP)**: AEEEIIOOOUGH! Your swarm causes something INSANE to happen! They chew into the fusebox and start a fire, they cause trash compactors to spit up garbage and make rocks fall from the sky, you name it! Any one HAZARD spawns. You, uh, aren\'t immune.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('inShiningArmor', 'IN SHINING ARMOR', 'OTHER', 'KNIGHT', '[Class][Basic][Mental][Physical][Reaction][Recharge: 2][Locked: Knight]\r\n', 'When your friends are in danger, there’s usually a way to solve the issue. Talking the threat down, running, prayers… but you don’t subscribe to many of them when danger is happening right in front of you. Instead, you thrust yourself into the situation in hopes it does something good. TO ARMS! This move cannot be self targeted. When you want to jump in front of a bullet, roll **+PLC**, **+GRT** OR **+HUB**. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: They get hit, and also you get hit. Your ally takes damage as normal, and you take the same amount as both of you get in the way of each other and you make everything worse. Way to go, hero. If they would only take **1 damage**, you take 1 more each.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You sure did make an attempt. That movie thing happens where tragic music plays and you’re running for them yelling ‘noooooooooooo’ in slow motion while they get hit anyway. And then they probably slap you in the face just for good measure. You take **1 damage** too.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You don’t manage to fully protect your target, but you do throw them off a little. The opponent’s **[Strife]** roll takes a -2 **[Nerf]**, and you take **1 damage**. \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Nice! You jump in the way, raise some arms, and block the incoming attack! The opponent’s **[Strife]** roll result deals **-1 damage** (even down to 0!) or is -2 **[Nerf]**, whichever is more helpful, and you take 1 **[Unblockable]** damage in return.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: The target **[Strife]** roll deals **-2 damage** (even down to 0!) and you deal **1 damage** back to them as you lash back, taking **1 [Unblockable]** damage in return. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: Wow that was actually a good call? You deflect the **[Strife]** entirely, and deal 2 **[Unblockable]** damage back to them immediately. Take no damage yourself, as you’ve prepared a perfect parry.\r\n'),
('inspiringLeadership', 'INSPIRING LEADERSHIP', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Open][One-Off][Manipulate]', 'Hey, here\'s a concept! What if you used your leadership training… to actually lead? Rather than tyrannizing those below you, you\'ve learned how to rally your companions into getting the job done well. When you want to lead your friends to victory, roll **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Oh. Oh, dear. You\'ve really insulted everyone present. All allies become **[Godawful]** at rolls for **3 turns**. Nice work.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Oof. Your attempt to lead makes everyone wince, but they get over it. All allies\' next rolls are **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: AHEEM HEEM. BLEH. BWEH. OKAY. You had something in your throat.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Let\'s do our best! All allies gain **2 [Boost]**. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: GIVE \'EM HELL! All allies gain **2 [Boost]**, and then become **[Brave]** for **2 turns**. This includes yourself. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: Oh… my god? That\'s the most incredible speech you\'ve ever given. All allies gain **3 [Boost]** and then become **[Heroic]** for the encounter. This includes yourself.'),
('installedItems', 'INSTALLED ITEMS', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Passive][Locked: Cyberpunk]', 'Sylladex? What\'s that? You don\'t store your items in an extradimensional space (y\'know, unless you need to). Instead, you get your stuff straight up installed into your body. Got some soda? You dispense it from the drink tap in your arm. A sweet dress? Part of your body. A car? (Transformers noise). You can give any item you own the INSTALLED tag. INSTALLED items cost **LUX** rather than **VP**, and are permanently part of you. They cannot be destroyed (though damaging it up to its HP does briefly deactivate it), and if it\'s a **[Consumable]**, it comes back after **3 turns**. **LUX** items can also be INSTALLED, but they cost 50% extra. This lets you bring **LUX** items like VEHICLES (no larger than Medium), FASHION items or even HIVECRAFTING UPGRADES to encounters and activate or deactivate them at will. You may only purchase 6 items like this, though. You’d need to download more RAM to run any more at once.'),
('instinctualIntuition', 'INSTINCTUAL INTUITION', 'OTHER', 'SEER', '[Class][Basic][Passive][One-off][Locked: Seer]', 'Not all of your knowledge is from book smarts. Some of it is just… Gut feelings and givens. Rust subgrub suddenly getting dronestruck even though they did nothing wrong? In other news, water is wet. Pitch partner coming over for a sudden tussle? Oh you would pull some horsepiss like this. At the very beginning of an encounter, roll a 1d4. The number that comes up is the round in which you will receive a flash of instinctive intuition into what you\'re doing. If, say, the number was a 3, then all your rolls in the third round of combat are **[Tiered Up]** as you just… intuitively know the right actions to take.'),
('instrumentOfMurder', 'INSTRUMENT OF MURDER', 'OTHER', 'MUSICREANT', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Musicreant]', 'You’ve heard of people calling a guitar an axe… well, you treat yours like one! Your instruments are also weapons which let you battle bands and bitches alike. You can choose ONE of the following Strifekind Abstrata to have on a strife specibus:\r\n\r\n> **STRINGKIND**: **[Active]** Guitars, basses, lutes… Your instrument doubles as an excellent heavy weight object on a handle! You can make a heavy swing that does +1 damage with this item, but you gain **1 [Weakness]** to all damage on your next turn as you leave yourself open.\r\n\r\n> **MICKIND**: **[Passive]** Fuck you. You just want to be special, huh? You can’t buy MICKIND with **LUX** like the rest of us not-Musicreants? Fine. You can have MICKIND on one of your weapons in combination with another Abstrata.\r\n\r\n> **BLOWKIND**: **[Active]** TOOT TOOT BLAM! Your trumpet, flute or whatever is able to shoot shit at opponents! This acts as a RANGEKIND weapon, but opponents with Emotion effects take an equal amount of **[Drag]** when they take damage.\r\n\r\n> **DRUMKIND**: **[Active]** Boom-chka-boom-boom! While using this item, you damage all opponents on the field equally, but can’t move around much; your non-**[Strife]** **[Physical]** moves are **[Inept]** and your **[Reactions]** are **[Godawful]**. You also cannot use **[WHAM]** with this weapon, and must take an action to switch away from it unlike other strife decks. \r\n\r\n> **KEYBOARDKIND**: **[Active]** Are you fucking serious. You want to use a Piano as a weapon. Fine. You AND your allies FRAYMOTIF **[Build-Up]**s can be satisfied by spending two actions playing with this weapon. You can drop it on someone using your preferred **[Strife]** roll as a **[One-Off]** that does **2 damage** on a **GOOD**, 3 on a **GREAT**, and 4 on a **MAX**.'),
('insufferableAttitude', 'INSUFFERABLE ATTITUDE', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'You are… difficult, sometimes! You overcompensate for your potentially short lifespan, psionically painful existence, or low societal standing with jokes and quips that are sometimes… too much. Seriously, shut up. Whether you\'re a horrible little goblin, a prissy e-bitch, or a weird little freak, other trolls **[Manipulate]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**.'),
('internetTroll', 'INTERNET TROLL', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Open][Chicanery]', '>be you\r\n>some dipshit starts an encounter with you\r\n>lmfao \r\n>realize they\'re kinda strong\r\n>ohfuck.amv\r\n>reveal your epic trolling skills and fuck with them for clout and internet fame\r\n>go home and tell strangers online about your awesome victory\r\n\r\n**You gain access to the following SHENANIGANS effects**:\r\n\r\n**NEPROLL\'D**: You make it extremely obvious you\'re going for a left-hook- OH SNAP, YOU ACTUALLY PUSH AN IPOD WITH A VIRAL VIDEO UP TO THEIR EAR! GOD, that\'s loud! The target is **[Deafened]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n**ROFL**: You make a genuinely funny quip… or one that\'s genuinely so stupid they can\'t help but laugh. The target starts **[Giggling]** for **2 turns**; if they were already **[Giggling]**, they become **[Floorbound]** and **[Giggling]** for an extra turn if **[Giggling]** had a duration; otherwise, they start **[Laughing]**.\r\n\r\n**YOU DON\'T KNOW DAT BOI?!**: What the fuck are you talking about. Shut the fuck up. You reference a REALLY obscure meme, and it\'s frustratingly hard to decipher what you just said. The target\'s **[Mental]** rolls **[Tier Down]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n**FFFFUUUUUUUUUUUU-**: You seriously piss off the opponent.  I\'m serious, shut the fuck up. They become **[Out-Of-Control]**. You\'ve won the **[Chicanery]** war, it seems!'),
('interrogationTactics', 'INTERROGATION TACTICS', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Legislacerator]', 'Lies are all but criminal; they do nothing but waste time and pervert the course of justice. So when you notice someone\'s lying, such as through PROBLEM SLEUTHING or a WANTED POSTER, you get kinda pissed. You wouldn\'t want to have to beat the information out of someone, would you? You may automatically HUNT the liar, gaining the same benefits you would against your original HUNTED target without losing your resources. The look on your face is generally pretty distressing, and the target becomes **[Scared]**. Opponents who are under the effect of this move and are knocked to **2 HP** are **[Exhausted]**, and much more willing to cooperate with your WORDPLAY REQUESTS for information as a result.'),
('interrorvestigator', 'INTERRORVESTIGATOR', 'CERULEAN', 'ADULT', '[Cerulean][Locked: Adult]', 'Becoming an adult has either impressively advanced your psionics and made them even more scary, or latent psionic powers have now been awakened which allows you to peer into others heads and gain crucial information for your job. Interrorvestigators are psionic warmongers who know that knowledge is not just half the battle, it is the playing field for the entire war. Many a lying rebel and duplicitous soldier has been caught in the throes of an Interrorvestigator’s meddling. You are **[Talented]** in **[Psionic]** moves and gain access to the move **COMPULSATE**. If you already have this move, then you always **[Tier Up]** an **OK** to a **GOOD** and gain 1 **[WHAM]** on top of that. Additionally, you can roll **PROBLEM SLEUTH** with **+IMG**, which gives it the **[Psionic]** tag. See what’s happening in there, find out what they are hiding from you.'),
('interstellarCullmunicator', 'INTERSTELLAR CULLMUNICATOR', 'GOLD', 'ADULT', '[Gold][Recharge: 3][Locked: Adult]', 'In an empire where trolls are scattered across hundreds of planets and thousands of spacecraft, it may be perigees AT BEST before you even SPEAK to your friends and loved ones again. That\'s where you come in. You are tasked with being the interrornet for your people. There is much more weight to your role now as you send battle plans, information and messages across the vast cold maw of space. \r\nAs an action you can scour databases and find out EVERYTHING about a target. This includes their name, hemocaste, their loyalty status and all mechanical information about them. You can use this move on anyone, no matter if they are right next to you or lightyears across the damn galaxy as long as you know they exist. In addition to this, when you roll **PROBLEM SLEUTHING** you can pass off the benefits of your roll to someone else as a **[Free] [Reaction]**. What’s the point of knowing everything if you can’t tattle about it? You cannot do this with **MAX** result, however, as explaining that much information to someone who isn’t a giga brain like you will…! Probably get you shoved in a locker for being such a geek, all things considered.'),
('inTheCourtOfTheFuchsia', 'IN THE COURT OF THE FUCHSIA', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Passive][Recharge: 2]', 'Yes, you\'re a close confidante of the Heiress! You\'re her best friend. Her right-hand troll. Her silly rabbit. Okay, you met her like, once maybe, but that was an INCREDIBLE honour, and all other Violets who haven\'t shared this honour are like, crazy impressed. You\'ve gotten as high as you can go in Alternian Society. When you would be made to use **[Drag]**, roll 1d8. On a 7, you only use half the **[Drag]** intended with the rest of it vanishing, and on an 8, the **[Drag]** vanishes without a trace. Thanks Heiress!'),
('inTheSpotlight', 'IN THE SPOTLIGHT', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Recharge: 3][Manipulate][Locked: Circusfolk]', 'Whenever an unplanned and grievous accident occurs at the circus, distraction acts commonly sweep in and demand the spotlight to help the audience forget what they saw. You apply this concept to battle, swinging the spotlight to you to give your allies time to plan! When you want to distract all others, roll the stat you gained a **[Talent]** in from ROLL UP, ROLL UP!\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You choke on your own tongue, making a huge stupid idiot of yourself. You are **[Humiliated]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You still look like an idiot, and are therefore **[Embarrassed]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Nobody really pays any attention to you, which is… annoying, but you\'ll cope. \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: LADIES AND GENTLETROLLS, ALL EYES ON YOU! All opponents can only roll moves that affect you next turn.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You brace for impact as you call attention to you! You get a **GOOD**, but all rolls have a **-2 [Nerf]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Your charisma is almost hypnotic! You get a **GOOD**, but all rolls are **[Inept]**!'),
('intimidatingGrin', 'INTIMIDATING GRIN', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Passive][Locked: Bully]', 'You\'re a bitch!! That\'s just part of who you are. You\'re mean, and scary! One might even say that you\'re rude, buster! And when you smile, it\'s a smile that makes people say \"aw fuck I don\'t wanna mess with this guy\". **[Chicanery]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**.'),
('intoTheDungeon', 'INTO THE DUNGEON', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Downtime][Unlock: Dungeoneer]', 'Scavenging is a big part of Rust culture. But you do it better than anyone else. How? You plunder the most dangerous tombs of all; the tombs of historical eras themselves. See, Alternia has a habit of building on top of itself; layers upon layers of underground, defunct cities forgotten by time await those who seek them out. And there\'s a tonne of shiny TREASURE inside as well! There\'s also monsters, ghouls and horrible secrets, but you mostly care about the treasure. Your bravery and guile is unmatched only by your foolishness; you are **[Talented]** in **+HUB**. You have a **[Downtime]** move called PLUNDER. Generally, the stuff you find is ancient, even if it functions as a normal item, such as stone mask CLEVER DISGUISES or healing salve MEDICALIZERS. When you want to loot ancient dungeons, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Aw shit, the dead super didn\'t like that you fucking disturbed them, actually. You are exposed to the HAUNTING **[Affliction]**, and immediately move to Stage 1.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You found some fucking bones! Whooooooogh. This is totally worthless, but you figured it would maybe rile up some ghosts if you continued so you, uh, didn\'t.\r\n\r\n**OK**: It\'s not… terrible! You find a **Poor** item of some description for **1 VP** less than normal.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Nice! You find a **Treasure I**! Maybe it\'s a cursed gemstone, or something you can trade in for a DVD or something.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: NOW we\'re talking! You find a **Treasure II**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: THE MOTHERLOAD! Look at this sweet loot haul you found in the arms of a skeleton! You find a **Treasure IV**!\r\n\r\n'),
('invincible', 'INVINCIBLE!', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Passive]', 'All Violets are renowned for their tough skin which makes them practically unkillable. Through training, growth, or the classic “throw money at it until it works” approach, your resilience is uncanny. Someone could probably, like, throw a shopping mall at you, and you\'d be fine (though your ego might be a little hurt). Opponents cannot use **[WHAM]** to harm you. Instead, one **[WHAM]** becomes **2 [Drag]** when they hit you with it. The attack doesn\'t hurt, but it sure winds you.'),
('ironGuts', 'IRON GUTS', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'Life gives you the short end of the stick no matter where you are. There’s always something to run from, whether it’s drones in the city, bandits in the country, or apex predators in the forest. You\'ve survived after sweeps of toughening yourself up, and you won\'t go down easy! You gain another **GOOD**, **GREAT**, and **MAX** GUTSUCKERY EFFECT to choose instead of regular ones! \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: HNNRRRK… you toughen yourself and prepare to get got. You gain **1 [Resistance]** to a damage type of your choice for **1 turn**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You got this… you got this! You\'re tougher than them, c\'mon! You gain **1 [Resistance]** to a damage type of your choice for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: IS THAT ALL YOU\'VE GOT? C\'MON, TRY HARDER! You gain **1 [Resistance]** to a damage type of your choice for **3 turns**.'),
('isThereABreeze', 'IS THERE A BREEZE?', 'OTHER', 'WITCH', '[Class][Basic][Free][One-Off][Locked: Witch]', 'You could have sworn that you just felt a weird draft… Oh? What was that? You tried to knock me down? You tried to **[Stun]** me just now? Maybe set me **[Ablaze]**? Oh, well, HA HA, YOU MISSED, SUCKER! You FAILED! Once per encounter, you may completely ignore any one status effect inflicted on you as you simply power through opposition through sheer force of will.\n\n'),
('itsActuallyFine', 'IT\'S ACTUALLY FINE', 'OTHER', 'SYLPH', '[Class][Advanced][Locked: Sylph]', 'It really wasn’t fine, back then. You just wanted to help, but breaking your back by carrying the world doesn’t help anyone when you’re too hurt by the time they need you. Your coping mechanisms aren’t just for lifting burdens, it’s for helping to live with them when they are unavoidable. You have actualized what your ‘fine’ actually is. **IT’S FINE** no longer removes the **[Emotion]** limit. When you reach your limit, you clear all of your **[Emotions]** and **[Drag]**. Deep breath in… deep breath out. It’s fine. YOU’RE fine. You promise this time! You must have **IT’S FINE** to be able to take this move.\r\n'),
('itsAMystery', 'IT’S A MYSTERY', 'VOID', 'VOID', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Void] ', 'Mystery solving is your forte! You don’t mind not being presented with the full facts when you ask a question— actually, you get much more out of solving vague answers than you do getting them handed to you! Any time you get a **GOOD** **[Analyze]** roll, you get particularly excited at the prospect of the unsolved, and gain **1 [Boost]**; when you get a **GREAT** roll, you can instead choose to get **2 GOOD** results (including **1 [Boost]** per answer) and a **MAX** can give you **3 GOOD** results (still including **1 [Boost]** per answer).'),
('itsFine', 'IT’S FINE.', 'OTHER', 'SYLPH', '[Class][Basic][Free][Reaction][Locked: Sylph]', 'It’s fine, you’re a little bit better at coping with your own emotions than the rest of your friends and it just makes sense if you’re the one who takes care of all of this mess. Perhaps that is the true duty of the guide; to clean up the mistakes of others rather than to lead. Go ahead and play dear, you’ll sort this out. When an ally is inflicted with an **[Emotion]**, you can choose to jump in as a **[Free] [Reaction]** and give them a quick word or soothing pat or emotional validation to cut that spiral off at the pass- and take that effect onto yourself instead. You can do this once per round, and you no longer have a maximum number of **[Emotion]** so long as you are fighting alongside at least one ally. If you reach the typical 3 **[Emotion]** limit, you take 1 **[Psychic]** damage, then start **[Disassociating]** as you buckle under the mental strain of taking their problems for yourself. It\'s… fine.'),
('itsHighMoon', 'IT\'S HIGH MOON', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][One-Off][Locked: Vagabond]', 'You and your opponent stare each other down, exchanging a few badass words. Your hands hover over your weapons, and… STRIFE! You may offer the opponent a SHOWDOWN as a **[Free]** action. If they accept, this becomes a **[Lengthy]** action for both of you. In a SHOWDOWN, both you and the opponent stare at each other, and then make a **[Strife]** roll. The higher **[Strife]** roll becomes a **MAX**, and the lower becomes a **MIN**. In the event of a tie, both **[Strife]** rolls resolve normally, but both parties become **[Hopeful]**. Not bad, pal.'),
('itsNotNothing', 'IT\'S NOT NOTHING', 'OTHER', 'PAGE', '[Class][Basic][Free][Buildup: 4][Locked: Page]', 'You\'re known for your ups and your downs! You aren\'t really well known for your sorta okays, though? Like, don\'t get me wrong, sometimes you do land in a weird middle ground area, but... well, y\'know. It takes a little bit of time to get into your groove, but you\'re putting your all into this, okay! You\'re really playing with your luck here. Instead of rolling a **BAD** on a 7 or lower, it\'s an 8 or lower- but you also roll a **GOOD** on a 10-13 instead of an 11-13! You must state that you\'re using this move for it to activate.\r\n'),
('itsNoUse', 'IT’S NO USE!', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Reaction][Psionic][Locked: Psychic]', 'Fool! Your puny attacks will never penetrate my psionic field! You\'re incredibly skilled with your psionics, and you\'re now that smug son of a bitch who catches bullets in midair with only your mind. As a **[Reaction]**, you can use any number of **ESP** to reduce incoming damage by an equal amount, even to 0 (**-1 damage** for **1 [Hold]**, **-2 damage** for **2 [Holds]**, and so on). '),
('iveStudiedTheBladeAndYourBullshit', 'I\'VE STUDIED THE BLADE AND YOUR BULLSHIT', 'OTHER', 'BLIGHTSMITH', '[Template][Basic][Physical][Reaction][Recharge: 3][Locked: Blightsmith]', 'You’ve had your hands on weapons of all types. Swords? Spears? Guns? You know that shit. You patented that shit. While that’s useful for making weapons, it’s also useful for avoiding weapons. I know your blind spot! Try hitting this! Whenever you want to dodge, roll **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Aha! You thought you could hit me like that? You should know, you need to aim 2 more degrees west to compensate for the wind! ...Why did you say that aloud? The incoming attack **[Tiers Up]** as you help your opponent beat your shit in.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You\'re too busy calculating the exact trajectory of the weapon and the movements required to dodge that you take too long and get hit anyway while completely defenseless. The incoming attack gains a +2 **[Buff]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: The incoming attack lands as planned. Shit, who knew weapons could hurt?\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Hey hey, I\'m standing over here! The incoming attack gains a -2 **[Nerf]** as you bend out of the way. What? Did they expect you to stand there and take it?\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Don\'t even try it. You calculate the trajectory in your head, you check the wind... aha! You should dodge this way! The incoming attack **[Tiers Down]** as you dodge the attack as best as someone can in a split-second decision.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You thought you could hit me with that piece of shit? You know every part of that weapon. Even if you didn\'t, you\'ve made so many that you know the rough design of it and exactly how to counter it. The incoming **[Strife]** is completely reflected onto the attacker as you use whatever bullshit they had planned against them. If you made the weapon they are using, this does +1 Damage of the appropriate type.\r\n'),
('jargonography', 'JARGONOGRAPHY', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Open][Passive]', '\"The revocation by these Regulations of a saving on the previous revocation of a provision does not affect the operation of the saving in so far as it is not specifically reproduced in these Regulations but remains capable of having effect.\'\" What? What the fuck are you saying? Your use of long, very definitely smart words makes it hard to pinpoint your goals sometimes. All **[Analyze]** rolls made against you are **[Inept]**.'),
('jesterdinal', 'JESTERDINAL', 'PURPLE', 'ADULT', '[Purple][Locked: Adult]', 'Hello. Welcome! We are glad you are here. Tonight\\\'s sermon will be a special one. There will be music and mirth and sound and faith and honks and slams and mirth and joy and honks and notes and faith and mirth and mirth and slams and. The Messiahs. The Messiahs! Yes, THE MESSIAHS! Your devotion has proven true and given you rewards beyond compare. You are a Jesterdinal. You are the faith made real. Go. Spread the gospel in holy honks. Bring cheer by pulverizing the heretical and the faithless. When you witness any non-purpleblood use a **[Psionic]** or **[Magic]** move, you gain a +1 **[Buff]** to any **[Magic]** move used against that target. Additionally, if you are present with at least two other church loyal clowns, you may use a **[One-Off] [Reaction]** whenever you witness a non-clown use a **[Magic]** move that has rolled a **GREAT** or **MAX**. When you use this **[Reaction]**, you and your fellow clowns may spend a collective 8 **[Boost]** to instantly turn the roll into a **MIN**.'),
('jollyOlJester', 'JOLLY OL\' JESTER', 'OTHER', 'BARD', '[Class][Basic][Free][Locked: Bard]', 'Whoops! Hey, c\'mon, what are you guys looking at me like that for? Can\'t make an omelette without breaking a few cluckbeast ovums and all that! Sometimes your team doesn\'t appreciate your gifts. Or your sense of humor. Or the problems you cause on purpose. But that omelette\'s comin, guys! Every time you or your party fails a roll- that is, rolls a **BAD** or a **MIN**- you gain one **[Hold]**. This **[Hold]** can be spent once per round in the following ways for the following costs:\r\n\r\n> **1 Hold**: Everyone on your team gains 1 **[Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **2 Hold**: Everyone on your team gets a +1 **[Buff]** to **[Strife]** for 5 rounds. \r\n\r\n> **3 Hold**: Everyone on your team gains 1 **[WHAM]**.\r\n\r\n> **4 Hold**: Everyone on your team gains a new **[Hold]**, which can be spent as a **[Free]** **[Reaction]** to increase one failed roll to a **MAX**.'),
('jousting', 'JOUSTING', 'OTHER', 'KNIGHT', '[Class][Basic][Physical][Strife][Recharge: 3][Locked: Knight] ', 'Self sacrifice is the name of the game. Your greatest worth is how much you can protect others, after all. Otherwise, why would they want to keep you around? Right? So protect them you shall, by whatever means necessary. They can thank you for it later. When you want to help others by throwing yourself into the fray for their sake, Roll **+PLC**, **+GRT**, OR **+HUB**. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: WHY DID YOU EVEN DO THIS? NOW EVERYONE’S MAD AT YOU. You take **2 [Somatic]** damage and become **[Stunned]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Not very good. You managed to let them get a hit in. Take **1 [Somatic]** damage and become **[Stunned]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You manage to get a hit in, but not without sacrifice. You deal **1 [Somatic]** damage, but take **1 [Somatic]** damage in return.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Decent hit! You deal **2 [Somatic]** damage, and take only **1 damage** back!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Fabulous defending! You deal a whopping **3 [Somatic]** damage, and take **1 damage** back!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Sometimes we forget that medieval knights often literally murdered each other, and then you remind us that they did. You inflict **5 [Somatic]** damage, and only take **2 damage** in return. '),
('judgeOfCharacter', 'JUDGE OF CHARACTER', 'SPACE', 'SPACE', '[Aspect][Advanced][One-Off][Locked: Space]', 'Being distant doesn’t mean you’re cold. Sometimes, your impartiality lets you get a take on situations— and people!— that others might overlook. You can take a single action to scope a troll out; you get a good read on them and see whether or not they’re trustworthy. If they’re not, you immediately get **1 [WHAM]**, and you’re not about to drop your guard. You can usually only use this on a troll once ever; however, you can reuse it on them if they suggest or offer you something that might require a new reading.'),
('juicelord', 'JUICELORD', 'OTHER', 'RAINBOW_DRINKER', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Eerie][Locked: Rainbow Drinker]', 'You\'ve become so well accustomed to drinking the blood of others that you\'ve begun to take on certain natural advantages resembling the caste you last drank from. You take a **+2 [Buff]** to the stat they gained from their Caste entry while you have the JUICELORD bonus (for example, drinking the blood of a Mastermind Cerulean troll buffs your **+IMG** rolls).'),
('kaboomerate', 'KABOOMERATE', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Physical][Strife][Locked: Junker]', 'BLAM! PEW PEW! K-CHOONMP! You LOVE a good explosion! The beauty of ignition, the devastation of the aftermath, the GLORIOUS sounds! Yup... you\'re kind of a guru when it comes to explosions. And you have so many explodable parts on your person, that really, it\'s not that hard for you to just... kinda... jury rig your weapons into grenade launchers? Yeaaaah. When you want to welcome people to Jackass, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Predictably, you blow yourself up. Dumb shit. You do **4 [Somatic]** damage to yourself. You have no one but yourself to blame for this.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Again, you blow yourself up. Come on, man, explosions have a radius. You do **1 [Somatic]** damage to yourself.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You burn your hand, which is... better than blowing yourself up, but yeah. You take **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: BOOM! You do **1 [Somatic]** damage to your opponent. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: KA-BOOM! You do **2 [Somatic]** damage to your opponent, or **1 [Somatic]** damage and **[Deafen]** all enemies for a turn. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: KRAKABOOM, BABY, YEAHHH! You do **3 [Somatic]** damage to your opponent, or **2 damage** and **[Deafen]** all enemies for a turn, or 4 to everyone present, yourself included. Worth it!'),
('keepComingBack', 'KEEP COMING BACK', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Last Stand][Locked: Subjugglator]', 'You know in horror movies, when you kill the bad guy, and breathe a sigh of relief, and turn your back, and then the camera shows the bad guy sitting up in the background? You know in horror movies, when you think “THERE’S NO WAY THE KILLER SURVIVED THAT TRUCK CRASHING INTO THEM” and then true the flames, out they come, wielding a machete as their face burns? You know in horror movies, even if the bad guy seems to have been beaten forever, they always come back for a sequel? Call that Joker Immunity, baby. You’re a living motherfucking horror movie. Whenever you are knocked to **0 HP**, you collapse in a pile on the floor. And then… you get the fuck back up. Honk honk honk. **1 Round** after you are defeated in combat, you rise again with **1 HP** like a clownish terminator. Can’t keep down the clown. You may get up earlier if **[Healed]** by allies. When you get back up, you are **[Enraged]**. If you do it again, you are **[Out-Of-Control]**. If you do it AGAIN, you gain **1 [WHAM]**. Each time you get knocked to 0 **HP** the time it takes to come back increases by **1 Round**. Monsters with an instant death feature, such as the Snazzard’s SCION OF JUSTICE move, ignore this ability once you’ve used it once. Get deaded.'),
('keepGoing', 'KEEP GOING!', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][One-Off][Last Stand][Locked: Tunnelwarden]', 'You can’t lose now! There are so many people depending on you! When you’re about to be defeated, you think about everyone who relies on you— and you keep going, even if only for a moment. When you would be reduced to **0 HP** in a fight, you are instead left at **1 HP**, and keep going for a little bit longer. Make it count, junior!'),
('kindaBadass', 'KINDA BADASS', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Passive]', 'Some Teals (like Legislacerators) are born badass. Some (like everyone else) are… less so. But you have your moments either way, where you do something and everyone stops and is like \"wow… that\'s kind of incredible!\". Whenever you get a **MAX** roll, you and all allies become **[Hopeful]**. This can stack into **[Inspired]** and up.'),
('kindaConfident', 'KINDA CONFIDENT', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'You know what? You… actually feel kind of okay about yourself! Like, not always, sure. But you aren\'t overcompensating as hard as you might have once with jokes and bits. Will you still make the pog face when someone falls over? Yes. Is it because you\'re desperate for others to find you funny? Not as much! Mostly because it\'s actually funny. The first time in an encounter you would gain **[Drag]**, you don\'t! You take it in stride and keep going.'),
('kindOfADrag', 'KIND OF A DRAG', 'DERSE', 'DERSE', '[Sway][Reaction][Locked: Derse]', 'Uuuugh, miss you with that peppy glass half full bullshit. You can list at least five reasons off the top of your head why what they’re about to do is going to backfire hilariously. Your **+PSP** stat becomes a supply of **[Drag]** you can pull from to inflict on someone as an action. If you have **+4 PSP**, you can inflict up to **4 [Drag]** over the course of an encounter. Each **[Drag]** costs an action.'),
('kingdomBuilder', 'KINGDOM BUILDER', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Locked: Royal]', 'Your FIEFDOM is expanding to include buildings that would normally be practically unheard of! You can buy the following Hivecrafting Upgrades, which may either be a part of your palace or independent buildings on your land.\r\n\r\n> **MONSTERMAZE (LUX varies)**: Whether it\'s a dungeon with a terrible creature inside, an arena full of monsters, or a maze with beasts in it, you put monsters here to fight your foes! It costs **2 LUX** to build, and **2, 5, or 8 LUX** to imprison a Level 2, 3, or 4 monster in it. You control the monster in fights here; challengers may attempt to fight the creature. If the challengers win, they win a number of Treasure equal to twice the monster\'s level to share between them. If you win, you gain a number of **LUX** equal to twice the monster\'s level. You can double the amount promised to both sides by activating BLOODSPORT MODE; whoever dies in this encounter has a JUST or HEROIC death. As an additional 4 **LUX**, you can initiate a Hazard in the fight.\r\n\r\n> **BARRACKS (3 LUX)**: You have built up a military presence, whether composed of trolls, robots, or monsters. Your army grows in size alongside the FIEFDOM; it starts with **10 HP +GRT, +2 GRT, +2 HUB, and +2 PSP**, is **[Talented]** at **+GRT**, and has up to three moves from Level 1 NPC sheets, the Robot Template, or Level 1 Monsters. Every **10 LUX** you invest into your FIEFDOM, your army gains a +1 to 1 stat, **1 HP**, and gains 1 new move. By **20 LUX** , you can access Level 2 monsters or NPC moves, and by **50 LUX** level 3. Once you hit **100 LUX**, you can even use Level 4 monster abilities. You can spend a number of **LUX** equal to your army\'s level to have them attack a troll in a **[Strife]**, or an enemy Royal Violet army. If you win the encounter, you get the **LUX** back— or twice the **LUX** if it\'s an opponent army!\r\n\r\n> **ALLEGIANCEBLOCK (2 LUX)**: You build a home or room for a notable member of your estate. They may contribute to Hivecrafting in your FIEFDOM too, and may control things like an army or MONSTERMAZE.\r\n\r\n> **MEDICULLBLOCK (3 LUX)**: Hospitals are generally banned on Alternia, since they promote the survival of the weak. Your FIEFDOM though, your rules! All trolls that stay in your MEDICULLBLOCK are **[Talented]** on rolls for **[Slowburn]** Afflictions during their stay. Trolls who die a JUST or HEROIC death can be rushed here to have a few final goodbyes. Once they\'ve said their last words, they can roll **+APP**; on a **GREAT** or **MAX**, they survive somehow! You can also turn trolls into SOULBOTS or CYBORGS here, and buy prosthetics for free.\r\n\r\n> **RESTRAINTBLOCK (3 LUX)**: Uh-oh! You wound up in prison, dumbshit! A troll who is beaten unconscious can be thrown into a RESTRAINTBLOCK. While in a RESTRAINTBLOCK, they can\'t use any move but the Universal Moves. It takes a **GREAT** **+HUB** roll to escape, which you can only attempt once a day. Increasing the **LUX** spent on this to 8 **LUX** makes this **+HUB** requirement a **MAX** instead. Every time an opponent attempts an escape, you lose **3 LUX** and your prisoner is set free should you be unable to pay the price. Maybe talk it out and see what compromise you can come to instead?\r\n\r\n> **KANGAROOFISH COURT (3 LUX)**: Jolly good show! A place where Splattorney Teals can duke it out! You are always the judge and can handpick the jury, the defendant, and lawyers for any trial. All participants but you gain **Treasure I** at the end of a trial you are satisfied with, so they better aim to please you!'),
('kissedAnAlien', 'KISSED AN ALIEN', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Passive]', 'YOU TOUCHED LIPS WITH AN ALIEN.\r\n\r\nWHORE.\r\n\r\nThe romance culture of Alternia is… so insanely different to what\'s on Earth. People have multiple romantic partners. Girls can like girls. Do you like girls??? Did the aliens turn you gay? Not everything on Alternia is great, but the inherent queerness of this place compared to what it was like back home is one thing you could get used to. You get the following ride-on effects for your QUADRANT moves; see Chapter 9: QUADRANTS.\r\n\r\n> **Matesprit**: It\'s just like having a partner on Earth! Except, you know, they\'re a horned alien and maybe the same gender as you?! When you give each other gifts, the item you give them takes up **1 VP** less than normal, though the both of you can only have 1 gift like this at a time. You both gain **1 [Boost]** when you give them a gift for the first time. \r\n\r\n> **Kismesis**: Oooogh-! That!! You!! No! This troll just gets on your nerves! Why is it so hot? When around them, you can choose to become **[Enraged]** as an action. \r\n\r\n> **Moirail**: It\'s like a best friend, but you pat each other, cuddle, and sometimes kiss depending on who it is?! When in an encounter with your moirail, you can take an action to remove a **[Negative]** emotion. Phew!\r\n\r\n> **Auspice**: You don\'t get this one. People have explained it to you in varying ways, and you thiiiink it\'s like, a third wheel between someone and another thing also they might kiss you sometimes? Trolls like kissing. A lot. When around your auspices, none of you can be made to use more than **3 [Drag]** at once.'),
('knifeInTheDark', 'KNIFE IN THE DARK', 'VOID', 'VOID', '[Aspect][Advanced][Recharge: 2][Locked: Void]', 'You\'re very, very sneaky. If you were a DnD character, you might be, like, a rogue or something! Not the Homestuck Rogue class, necessarily, that\'s different. You\'re always ready to get the drop on somebody when they aren\'t expecting it. Or maybe they are expecting it, but they aren\'t expecting you from... OVER HERE!!! Whenever you use a **[Strife]** move that would reveal you from **[Hidden]**, you can use one of your weapon\'s **[Active]** Abstrata without sacrificing the damage as you have a little more time to plan your attack and execute it while the enemy isn\'t looking!'),
('knifetongue', 'KNIFETONGUE', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Your words are SHARP. Teal lives are ones of constant arguing and bickering, so when interfacing with others, sometimes you say things that are MUCH more cutting than other castes are used to. You gain the following **GOOD** WORDPLAY effects.\r\n\r\n> **MOCK**: You say some really hurtful, really mean and hurtful things! :( You heighten an opponent’s negative **[Emotion]**. On a **GREAT**, they take **1 [Drag]** too, and on a **MAX**, they take 2. This **[Drag]** isn’t increased by emotions.\r\n\r\n> **REBUFF**: Alright, well screw you too, man! Your opponent’s **[Recharge]** for a WORDPLAY effect increases by 1. You can’t apply this to JAB.\r\n\r\n> **CHORTLE**: Pfft. You act unimpressed by the target. They take **1 [Drag]**!\r\n\r\n> **BLAHBLAHBLAHBLAH**: Man- MAN! SH! Jegus!! You can talk REALLY fast and REALLY loud when you need to. You get 2 WORDPLAY choices, but you become **[Tired]**.'),
('knowItAllBitch', 'KNOW IT ALL BITCH', 'OTHER', 'SEER', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Seer]', 'You\'re just a smarmy little know it all bitch, aren’t you? Yes, you are. You act like you’re above feeling such intense emotions that the petty rabble stoops to. That, or you’re actively gloating to them how much better you are than them with all your knowledge. Bitch. You begin all encounters as either **[Smug]** or **[Peaceful]**.'),
('knuckleCrack', 'KNUCKLE CRACK', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Open][One-Off][Physical]', 'Alright, fuck this. It\'s not worth playing nice with some people, no matter how much trouble it gets you in. When you want to remove your earrings or roll up your sleeves, maybe even crack your knuckles, roll **+GRT**.\n\n**MIN**: AGH, YOUR KNUCKLES! FUUUCK. OUCH… you do **1 [Somatic]** damage to yourself and are **[Clumsy]** for **3 turns**.\n\n**BAD**: You crack your knuckles, and… yeah, nothing happens. Whoops?\n\n**OK**: You psych yourself up, but the target isn\'t impressed. You get **1 [WHAM]**.\n\n**GOOD**: Alright, motherfucker, let\'s throw down! You become **[Enraged]**.\n\n**GREAT**: Hmmm. Maybe you\'re scarier than the target thought. You become **[Enraged]**, and the target becomes **[Stressed]**.\n\n**MAX**: OKAY YEAH YOU ARE DEFINITELY A PROBLEM FUCK FUCK FUCK. You become **[Out-Of-Control]**, and the target becomes **[Agitated]**.'),
('landlubberSeafarer', 'LANDLUBBER/SEAFARER', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Passive]\r\n', 'There are two schools of thought as far as ruling the world goes. On the one hand, having your hive in the sea puts you in the heart of violet country, thus securing your place as the rightful nobility of the planet. On the other hand, living among those you subjugate and rule means you can rule them yourself and see things you wouldn\'t in your home underwater. The choice is in your hands. Select an option.\r\n\r\n> **LANDLUBBER**: You aren\'t as posh as other Violets, and you willingly spend your life on dry land for the most part. Your **[Analyze]** rolls against non-Violet trolls have a **+2 [Buff]** as you\'ve come to understand them fairly well, and other Violets have a **-2 [Nerf]** to **[Manipulate]** rolls against you.\r\n\r\n> **SEAFARER**: You wouldn\'t dream of living somewhere so… unmoist. After all, you\'re a seadweller! It\'s only right that you dwell in the sea. Your home is beneath the waves, and you make a LOT of money down there. Your VP increases by 2.\r\n\r\n'),
('largerThanLife', 'LARGER THAN LIFE', 'OTHER', 'THIEF', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Seek Therapy][Locked: Thief]', 'You’re the one everyone should be listening to. You\'re large and in CHARGE, baby! You don’t have this giant ego for nothing, after all, and everyone knows it! The way your very shadow just oozes charisma… who wouldn\'t love you? TASTELESS PEOPLE, THAT\'S WHO! All your **[Manipulate]** and **[Control]** moves ignore any other moves that would **[Tier Down], [Inept]** or **[Nerf]** your result.'),
('lastRites', 'LAST RITES', 'OTHER', 'DECOMPOSITIONIST', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Decompositonist]', 'Prerequisite: Must not be **[Eerie]**. \r\n\r\nThe undead are a pitiful sort, denied the final rest that they were refused even in life. Often forced into dark paths and darker actions by ostracization and vile magic, few offer them the kindness to allow them a dignified rest. You may choose to have a **+PLC** **[Talent]** over your Tree’s **[Talent]**. You may always roll **[Verbal]** **[Strife]** moves against **[Eerie]** trolls, and your **[Verbal]** Damage is not considered **[Non-Lethal]** against these targets. You speak not to abuse or chastise, but to offer them a way out. It is ultimately their choice to pass on, but you can help guide them there without pain. Should you take **3 damage** total by any **[Strife]** move that is not **[Verbal]** by an **[Eerie]** troll you may choose to abandon these benefits for **[Free]** as you allow yourself to fight back in full, gaining **1 [WHAM]** per turn instead. You are gentle, not passive. You additionally ignore **1 [Resistance]** that **[Eerie]** trolls possess; you know how to exorcize your targets, one way or another.'),
('lastSaneTroll', 'LAST SANE TROLL', 'OTHER', 'PRINCE', '[Class][Basic][Free][One-Off][Locked: Prince]', 'You\'re right. You\'re right, and you\'ve always been right, and they can do whatever they want to you but it won\'t change the fact that you. Are. Right. When you gain more than three **[Emotions]** in one fight, **[Base]** or **[Heightened]**- or if you would be given a conflicting set of emotions- instead of becoming **[Numb]** or canceling your **[Emotions]** out, you instead clear ALL **[Emotions]** you are feeling and replace them with your choice of **[Enraged]**, **[Serious]** or **[Focused]** as you go to a place where what you feel doesn\'t really matter.\r\n\r\n\r\n'),
('latentPsionics', 'LATENT PSIONICS', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Passive][Psionic]', 'Even rusts who AREN\'T actively psychic have some mild psychic powers. Usually just enough to like, bend a spoon or something. Obviously, then there\'s psions who can throw planets with enough practice, but yeah! Whether you\'re a master psychic or a psionic debutant, you have latent psionics that are always at least kind of there. You immediately know if an opponent has **[Psionic]** or **[Magic]** moves (other than FRAYMOTIF) just by being around them. If they do, you gain **1 [Boost]** at the start of the encounter as your hairs stand on end. If you didn\'t have any **[Psionic]** moves before, you\'re now able to gain the PSIBURN **[Affliction]**.'),
('lawOfRetaliation', 'LAW OF RETALIATION', 'TIME', 'TIME', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Time]', 'An eye for an eye, a horn for a horn. What goes around comes around. You’re a big believer in karma; and when someone hurts you, you definitely don’t let that sit. Any time you deal damage using **[WHAM]**, you heal **1 HP** as you feel like justice has been served.'),
('lazyDay', 'LAZY DAY', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Yaaaawn… no need to over-exert yourself, right? Sometimes, you just wanna… sit on your ass and do not much else. After all, the future is confusing, and stressful, and scary… so sometimes you just need to rest and forget about it. When an ally would gain the **[Tired]** condition, you can take it for **[Free]**. Yawns are contagious, y\'know! While **[Tired]**, any **[Healing]** you take is increased by 1, or by 2 if you\'re **[Exhausted]**. However, when you **[Heal]** while **[Tired]**, roll 1d8… on a 1 or 2, you get **[Tired]**, heightening to **[Exhausted]** or **[Unconscious]**.'),
('learningFromTheBest', 'LEARNING FROM THE BEST', 'OTHER', 'THIEF', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Thief]', 'You\'re so fucking cool and good at everything you do. Whenever you\'re in an encounter with allies, they can see how well you shine and follow your lead! You\'re downright inspiring! How could they not want to be like you? As a **[Reaction]**, whenever you gain a status effect of some kind, an ally can choose to gain the same effect. This only works once per ally per encounter, and it\'s their **[Reaction]**, not yours.\n\n'),
('legalTraining', 'LEGAL TRAINING', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Passive][Locked: Splattorney]', 'You\'re prepared for the horrors of a court case, and are ready for basically anything at this point. You can roll to JAB even after a fight breaks out. You can assume the following stances (equipped at the start of an encounter) when you use JAB.\r\n\r\n> **DEFENSE ATTORNEY**: Your JAB rolls can do **1 less damage** on a **GREAT** to make their next WORDPLAY roll **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n> **ATTACK ATTORNEY**: Your JAB rolls can\'t be made **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]** or **[Nerfed]**.\r\n\r\n> **TANK ATTORNEY**: Your JAB rolls can do **1 less damage** on a **GREAT** to **[Heal]** yourself by 1. Outside of a trial, this has **[Recharge: 3]**.\r\n\r\n> **HEALER ATTORNEY**: Your JAB rolls can be used to **[Heal]** others; outside of a trial, this has **[Recharge: 3]**.\r\n\r\n> **BARD ATTORNEY**: Your JAB rolls can do **1 less damage** on a **GREAT** to give the target **2 [Drag]** as you annoy the fuck out of them by bursting into song.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('legendaryAdventurer', 'LEGENDARY ADVENTURER', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Ultra][One-Off][Passive][Magic][Locked: Dungeoneer]', 'Come rest a moment by the bonfire— let\'s take a moment to gather our wits. You\'re one of the most accomplished adventurers around, making your way into dungeons so deep they\'re practically alien worlds. You gain access to HERO MODE with your HARDCORE HUBRIS. Your Wealth Level increases to **Decent**, and you have **12 VP**, not 8. All thanks to the treasure you keep bringing home! On top of that, you have access to some secret magic tricks that allow you a modicum of control over embers. You can create a little fireball in your hands, which you can use to light torches, bonfires and OH SNAP your weapons. Every weapon you have has the BURNKIND Abstrata Upgrade, even ones that already have an ABSTRATA UPGRADE. If you want to just throw fireballs at bitches, consider picking up a FIREBALLKIND (Burnkind Rangekind Strife Specibus). **[Strife]** rolls with this effect are **[Magic]**, and each hit you make with these weapons count as two in terms of triggering **[Blaze]** weaknesses in monsters. Some Dungeoneers may use other **[Energy]** types to do their thing, but because ice and acid don\'t light torches, they\'re generally considered huge posers. Finally, you can light a BONFIRE in a dungeon for your party to rest around; this heals everyone to full HP and allows them to make **[Downtime]** rolls without leaving the dungeon. Just in case!'),
('lesferatu', 'LESFERATU', 'OTHER', 'RAINBOW_DRINKER', '[Template][Ultra][Eerie][Flourish][Magic][Locked: Rainbow Drinker]', 'Poise. Grace. Fangs. You are the Profane Angel that the Cloistered Jades warned you about. Dripping in seductive charm and also blood, you\'ve mastered ALL the techniques known to the scholars of daywalkers. Hell, some poor schmuck down there in the libraries of the Undercaverns is probably writing suggestive fabrication about you to pass off as a holy text right now. You are the night. Whenever you reveal your true nature, your opponents are **[Disgusted]**, whether of fear or disgust of your abominable nature. Your oozing charisma supersedes any need to overcompensate; you may roll SWASHBUCKLE with **+PLC** instead of **+HUB**, if you choose. If you were not **[Talented]** at whichever you decide to use, you become **[Talented]** now. Finally, you gain the following SWASHBUCKLE effects:\r\n\r\n**GOOD**:\r\n\r\n> **MISTY ABSCONSCION**: Seeya! You get the fuck out of there. You ABSCOND, and the opponent can\'t use CAN’T ABSCOND BRO on you because you literally turned into a puff of smoke.\r\n> **WONK**: Ohhhhrrgghh… sexy… you put all those around you at unease, which is funny to you. You become **[Smug]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**:\r\n\r\n> **FLIGHT**: WHOOSH! Whether through levitation or surprise moth wings, you take flight! You begin **[Flying]**.\r\n> **SHAPESHIFT**: Whoa! Terrifying! You turn into a wild lusus of some description. You gain the stats and appearance of a Level 1  or 2 Lusus, though you may flavour it to be more… goffik. I\'m no pigeon! I\'m a SQUEAKFLAPPER! You keep your current HP and retain access to all your Rainbow Drinker moves, though no others, and can return to normal as a [Free] action.\r\n\r\n**MAX**:\r\n\r\n> **CHILDREN OF THE NOON**: THOSE FOOLS! THEY STAYED OUT TOO LATE, AND NOW DAYLIGHT IS UPON THEM! The DAYTIME **[Hazard]** begins. You can\'t use this effect if you already caused a **[Hazard]** this encounter.\r\n\r\n> **DEEP MAGIC**: Ohhhhhh nooooo. You swing around a finger, and a churchbell clangs. What the fuck? There aren\'t even churches around here, except Clown Church, and they use horns, not- OH MY GOD THE STARS ARE GOING OUT. You cause the DIMMING STARS **[Hazard]**. You can\'t use this effect if you already caused a **[Hazard]** this encounter.\r\n\r\n> **MUDA MUDA MUDA**: You strike a confidently condescending pose before unleashing pure hell the next turn. On your next turn, you are **[Quickened]** if you weren\'t already and can make up to three **[Strife]** rolls, including multiple of the same move if you so choose. However, the second and third ones are at a **-1 [Nerf]** and **[Inept]** - make this flurry count! '),
('lessonsLearned', 'LESSONS LEARNED', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'Yes! You remember this one from schoolfeeding! Or maybe, you remember it from your experiments, or from your time out on the field, or… look, the point is, you’re from a caste of loregatherers, compiling knowledge and secrets from the annals of history like there’s no tomorrow. It’s only natural that some of those lessons will have taught you how to critically puzzle out a problem yourself. You gain access to the following **GOOD** PROBLEM SLEUTHING results.\r\n\r\n> **STRATEGIZE**: What would the greats of sportsball and battle alike do in your situation? You deactivate a move of the opponents that makes other moves **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]** or **[Nerfed]** for **2 turns** and figure out their weak points, mentally or physically. \r\n\r\n> **ULTRASMART**: HA! GOT YOU! You think REAL hard, getting two PROBLEM SLEUTHING rolls at once. This makes you **[Tired]** afterwards, though.\r\n\r\n> **MIND GAMES**: In the words of Troll Sun-Tzu, fuck with them. You figure out an insecurity of the target, and play on it, making them **[Stressed]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **CULTUREGAZE**: You get a read on them, their heritage, and the shit they do. All of their tree’s moves are **[Inept]** for a turn.'),
('letFateDecide', 'LET FATE DECIDE', 'OTHER', 'HEIR', '[Class][Advanced][Locked: Heir]', 'Sometimes you’re in a situation where some of your aspect abilities aren’t too useful. You’ve learned in those situations that you can let some of your abilities go and channel them into something else. As an action, you can choose as many of your **[Aspect]** moves as you like. You then lose access to all the selected moves for 2 rounds, gaining 1 **FP** for each move you choose. If one of the selected moves has been shared through **BUTTERFLY EFFECT**, those who have gained access to it also lose the move for 2 rounds.\r\n'),
('letMeTellYouASecret', 'LET ME TELL YOU A SECRET', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Advanced][Passive]\r\n', 'The acts of self-care and self-love include knowing when you should engage with others towards full expression, and when no matter what you do the other will not share the same morals. When you first tell someone your birth caste, immediately gain 3 **[Boost]** and 2 **[WHAM]** in preparation for the worst. If they have a positive reaction, you lose both and instead become **[Hopeful]**. If they react negatively, you keep your **[WHAM]** and **[Boost]**, and gain a permanent +1 **PROBLEM SLEUTHING [Buff]** for the rest of the encounter as you keep your wits about you.\r\n'),
('letsSkedaddle', 'LET\'S SKEDADDLE!', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Passive]', 'No fucking way are you getting caught! When you wanna run, you wanna RUN! Every moment in public is dangerous for you, so you\'re always ready to make a break for it. Your LET\'S STRIFE rolls to ABSCOND are **[Legendary]**.'),
('letsStrife', 'LET\'S STRIFE!', 'OTHER', 'UNIVERSAL', '[Physical][Free]', 'Outpace! Outrun! When a fight breaks out, the most important thing is to use your reflexes and instincts to get going and FAST! When you want to begin a combat encounter or alter the ebb and flow of an ongoing fight, roll **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Your slow reflexes put you in a tough spot— you take **2 [Drag]** and become **[Exhausted]**. You can only select the **ORDER UP** **GOOD** result.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You try to move quickly, but it just doesn’t pan out for you. You take **1 [Drag]** and become **[Tired]**. You can only select the **ORDER UP** **GOOD** result.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You don’t get to do what you want… but you’re able to reposition yourself before you face any negative consequences. You can only select the **ORDER UP** **GOOD** result.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Woosh! You are FAST on your feet! Select an option from the list below…\r\n\r\n> **ORDER UP**: Your fighting instinct propels you into an encounter! When combat breaks out, all trolls must roll **LET\'S STRIFE** to order up, unless they have a move that always puts them first. The turn order is decided by whoever rolls highest to lowest. If you are unable to roll **LET\'S STRIFE** when combat starts, you get a result of 1. You can\'t roll this outside of when combat starts.\r\n\r\n> **ABSCOND**: GET OUTTA HERE! You leave a combat encounter, saying peace out. If nobody tries to stop you and there\'s no **[Hazard]**, you don\'t even have to roll; you can get this result for an action immediately. If you\'re carrying somebody, they come with you. As **[Reactions]**, your allies can join in and come along with you, letting your entire team leave as a group. But be careful, because someone might say…\r\n\r\n> **CAN\'T ABSCOND BRO**: You can\'t get away! When someone rolls to **ABSCOND**, you may attempt to block their exit with this move. Whoever has a higher numerical roll in this event is the winner, and either escapes or prevents escape. If your target\'s allies **[Reacted]** to join the **ABSCOND**, their **[Reactions]** are refunded in the event you succeed, and do not affect the roll off between you and the original abscondee. They cannot attempt to **ABSCOND** for **1 turn** afterwards, as you have already blocked them once this turn already!\r\n\r\n> **DELAY**: Wait for the right moment! You delay your turn to be after someone else\'s for this turn only.\r\n\r\n> **SPUR**: You step on the opponent\'s toes, screwing them up and forcing them to act before they\'re ready! If the target used **DELAY** or **SPLIT ACTIONS**, you force them to take action directly after your turn ends rather than when they were waiting. \r\n\r\n> **REORDER**: Gotta get into position… but it won\'t work unless we try our best! You alter your **LET\'S STRIFE** roll, and therefore position in the turn order, by 2 up or 2 down. Opponents with a move that lets them always go first have an effective **LET\'S STRIFE** roll of the next highest roller +1.\r\n\r\n> **RUSH**: You push yourself to your limits, moving as fast as you can manage. You become **[Quickened]** for **2 turns** and **[Tired]**; the Emotions from this effect are **[Unblockable]**, and cannot be removed.\r\n\r\n> **SPLIT ACTIONS**: Wait for the right moment… twice! You become **[Slowed]**, but roll **ORDER UP** a second time, giving you a second turn for this round of combat. You return to normal next turn unless you roll again. You can’t use this effect if you’re already **[Slowed]** or **[Quickened]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: So fast, so cool! Amazing! You get a **GOOD**, plus **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: INCREDIBLE SPEED! You get a **GOOD** and are **[Quickened]** for a turn. Your rolls can\'t be affected by SPUR. And you get **1 [Boost]**!'),
('lifeblood', 'LIFEBLOOD', 'OTHER', 'TRICKSTER', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Eerie][One-Off][Locked: Trickster]', 'Candy syrup in your veins, sugar in your heart!! You are practically MADE of sweetness, and it affects you on a base level. If you ever become **[Bloodied]** and spill your sweet life-force, an ally of your choice is instantly healed **2 HP**! Those guys you\'re fighting deserve some lovin too, now that you think about it. They become **[Revolted]** as they’re hounded by your Lifeblood. :)\r\n\r\n'),
('lightsCameraDronestrike', 'LIGHTS, CAMERA, DRONESTRIKE!', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'HET', '[Template][Advanced][One-Off][Lengthy][Tech][Locked: HET]\r\n', 'When the going gets tough, that’s when the drones are deployed to give a helping minigun to the cops in cerulean. As a **[Lengthy]** action, you may summon the TERROR BOMBING **[Hazard]** to an Encounter.\r\n\r\n**TERROR BOMBING\r\n[Physical][Mental]**\r\n\r\nThe HET has access to drones like any other Org, although they use theirs a bit more spectacularly. Their field agents are more than capable of matching the brawn and brain of rebels, so their drone support takes a more auxiliary point. Of making an example of everyone in the area for what happens when you force the HET\'s hand. \r\n\r\n> **FIRST ROUND**: The humming of drone engines and the wail of sirens strikes terror in your bloodpusher. All non-Org trolls gain the **[Scared]** condition, and Org trolls are unaffected by all following rounds.\r\n\r\n> **SECOND ROUND**: The Terrordrones land, and chaos reigns. All living things not currently **[Hidden]** take **1 [Somatic]** damage that ignores **[Resistance]**. The Terrordrones prioritize making a show over killing targets, dropping bombs and blasting at anything they see while giving support to their Org counterparts. All targets additionally gain **2 [Drag]** in sheer fright of the discriminately indiscriminate madness. Moves that stun or halt **[Mechanical]** creatures make them jump forward a round. The **[Hazard]** has **12 HP** for every target troll present, and can technically be bested in combat with enough luck, but resisting the **[Hazard]** other than to **[Hide]** causes them to do **+1 damage** every round, stacking as it goes.\r\n\r\n> **THIRD ROUND**: The terrordrones continue to open fire on anything that moves, and anything that doesn\'t. BRAKABRAKABRAKA! Round 2 repeats.\r\n\r\n> **FOURTH ROUND**: God, they\'re determined, huh? Round 2 repeats. All living things become **[Terrified]** as they continue the assault.\r\n\r\n> **FIFTH ROUND**: Alright, by now everyone is definitely traumatized. The Terrordrones pull back into the distance ominously. Trolls still openly showing resistance take **2 damage**. The Terrordrones additionally will allow any Org trolls to ABSCOND immediately by hitching a ride on them should any need to leave, and will be taken to safety if they are unconscious.\r\n'),
('likeMe', 'LIKE ME', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Passive][Psionic]', 'To a lime, it’s easy to tell when you’re in the company of someone who hides their identity. Whether it’s an innate **[Psionic]** sense, or just keen observation of a fellow secret-holder’s behaviour, you instantly recognize any other trolls with the **[Cullbait]** tag, though you don’t immediately know what their deal is, just that they’re like you. You can immediately tell if a troll is trustworthy enough to reveal your secret to with an action, but you gain no context; just a simple Yes or No.'),
('likeThis', 'LIKE THIS!', 'OTHER', 'PAGE', '[Class][Advanced][Free][Reaction][Recharge: 3][Locked: Page]', 'You’ve grown... but you haven’t done it alone! Your allies have helped you every step of the way, even if it was paired with some grumbling and awkward back-and-forth glances. You’ve come far enough that you’re not going to take their guidance for granted, whether it’s to help you or them! You can give yourself or an ally the chance to re-roll something as you quickly help correct a mistake in the making, allowing you (or them) to take the higher result.\r\n'),
('lilAlchemist', 'LIL ALCHEMIST', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Passive]', 'Hey, this Alchemy thing isn’t that hard! You’ve gotten better at Alchemizing a variety of things with the help of the weird tech that got you here in the first place. You put your flashlight and your dad’s car together to make… A LIGHTHOUSE MOTORCADE! Or some shit. You can merge items together, adding up the two items **VP**, dividing it by 2 and subtracting 2 (min. **1 VP**). Pretty nifty, if I do say so myself!'),
('lilExorcist', 'LIL EXORCIST', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'BUSTIN', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Bustin’]', 'You aren’t gonna let the ghosts haunt YOU! Get outta here, ghosts! FUCK OFF! Your rolls against the PARANORMAL ACTIVITY **[Hazard]** and the HAUNTING **[Affliction]** are always using your Caste **[Talent]**. You can also attempt to make rolls for someone else afflicted by the HAUNTING **[Affliction]** to exorcise them.\n\n'),
('lilHorrorterror', 'LIL HORRORTERROR', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Ultra][Psionic][Locked: Deep-Sea]', 'You didn\'t think this was natural, did you? The evolution of your form goes beyond what is plausibly natural into a true scion of the ancient deeps. Troll kind was not naturally created, and you are proof of their awful heritage. You gain access to HERO MODE through your INCREDIBLE IMAGI- huh? Through your INCREDIBLE IMAGINATION, but all rolls use **+GRT** rather than **+IMG**. How curious… you may choose to take the Rust Psychic tree, the Bronze Summoner tree, or the Cerulean Mastermind tree as a Template. If you do so, you can only take the **[Entry]**, one **[Basic]**, and one **[Advanced]**. Any **[Psionic]** move you take from these trees are powered through your eldritch psionics and freaky blood. All these trees use **+GRT** for you. You do not gain the **[Talents]** from these **[Entry]** moves. Finally, your unnatural psionics have an eternal link to the roiling sea below. Whenever you get a **MAX** **[Psionic]** roll on a target, they are exposed to the CH**OK**ING Affliction as water spews from their lungs, manifested by your power.'),
('lilShopOfWonders', 'LIL SHOP OF WONDERS', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Meowchant]', 'Finally! After pouring blood, sweat and a considerable amount of investment, you were able to afford your own little store! Whether you sell zodiac charts, hot chocolate or anime figurines, you’ve finally made it. You gain a **[Swanky]** BUSINESSFRONT with a **[Swanky]** STORAGE PIT as seen in the HIVECRAFTING chapter. Your Lil Shop of Wonders needs a name… after all, all vehicles of its caliber do. THAT\'S RIGHT, YOUR SHOP HAS GOT LEGS. Or maybe it\'s got magic that lets it float, or giant trundling wheels… or maybe it\'s straight up an actual vehicle, like a whimsical merchant train! Point is, it\'s an XXL VEHICLE with 1 HORSEPOWER, and it can go where you please. Finally, you can buy items in the middle of encounters so long as your LIL SHOP OF WONDERS is present.'),
('limeLanguage', 'LIME LANGUAGE', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Passive][Psionic]', 'It’s nigh impossible to have an open conversation about lime business with other trolls in public; as such, many of your caste have mastered the art of non-verbal communication with one another. If only one of you has this move, you can pass on no more than 3 words worth of communication per action without speaking, whether it’s through hyper subtle body gestures or vague psionic influence. If both of you have this move, you’re able to hold full conversations with one another saying what you mean; combining shrugs, filler words and eye movements into a complex sentence, or just full on reading each other’s minds. Doing this under direct scrutiny from a troll rolling to **[Analyse]** you might uncover that something’s fucky. Your FRAYMOTIF rolls with other limes lose the **[Buildup: 4]** tag and instead gain the **[Buildup: 2]** tag.'),
('literallyAnAlien', 'LITERALLY AN ALIEN', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Passive]', 'Look, dude, you… you\'ve got zero point of reference sometime as to what the FUUUUCK is going on on Alternia. You nod like you understand, but you super don\'t! When a troll\'s move would give you a negative **[Emotion]**, you can choose to replace it with another one of your choosing. For example, rather than being **[Scared]** of the evil murder clown, you might just be really **[Confused]** by it.'),
('litigate', 'LITIGATE', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Strife][Locked: Legislacerator]', 'You can bring them in warm or cold, you don\'t really care that much. Targets rarely come with you willingly once you\'ve started tracking them down, but eh. Eh. You like a challenge. When you want to hook \'em and book \'em, roll **+GRT**. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: You\'ve hooked and booked yourself! How could this happen?! You\'re such a fool! You do **3 [Somatic]** damage to yourself, and you become **[Stressed]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: This isn\'t a clean arrest at all! You become **[Stressed]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You missed… this time. You gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: SOLID HIT! You do **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You attack their body and soul both! You either do **2 [Somatic]** damage, or do **1 [Somatic]** damage and **[Stress]** them for **2 turns** as you accuse them of an increasing number of crimes. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: You\'re REALLY freaking them out, dude! You either do **3 [Somatic]** damage, or do **2 [Somatic]** damage and **[Agitate]** them for **2 turns**, after which point they become **[Stressed]** for the encounter.'),
('lodestarYouth', 'LODESTAR YOUTH', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Passive][Unlock: Cool Kid]', 'SKRRRTTTT. Oh, that? That’s the sound of you skateboarding in. Yeah, you board. Oh, you’re also playing The Black Eyed peas on your iPod Shuffle. Yup, you’re kind of what people would call a Cool Kid. This kind of stuff just comes naturally to you; or maybe it’s an extremely forced front that you use to distract people from the existential terror all teens feel. Like a boss. Whether you\'re actually genuinely a cool and collected person or only an ironically cool one, you\'re not afraid to take risks; you are **[Talented]** at **+HUB**. So cool are you that your **[Boost]** and **[Drag]** do not affect one another. If you had **2 [Boost]**, and were to gain **1 [Drag]**, you would just track them separately, meaning you can have **[Boost]** and **[Drag]** at the same time, rather than having them subtract and add against each other. You can choose to spend **[Boost]** to reduce your **[Drag]** for **[Free]** if you choose, trading **[Boost]** in to remove an equal amount of **[Drag]**.'),
('lolcat', 'LOLCAT', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Open][Free][One-Off]', 'Whoops! You saw a pickle, jumped five feet in the air in your startled state, drop-kicked a drone, made it crush someone, causing someone to slip in the viscera and tumble head first into a pile of whoopee cushions. Uhhh… act like a ditz and hope nobody gets mad? Once per thread, you may treat a **BAD** or **OK** **[Flourish]** roll as **GREAT**. It was absolutely not on purpose though, and you’re actually a little confused by what happened- you become **[Overwhelmed]** for **3 turns**.'),
('lonemate', 'LONEMATE', 'OTHER', 'MUTANT', '[Mutant][Passive]', 'Wow! Congratulations! You, through your immense competence and bravery, let the one person who would stand by your side for your whole life in the whole world die. You are all alone now. That isn\'t a complete downside. Ignore the big list of downsides you\'re about to see, you get some upsides! When you gain this move, remove PSIMATES or HATCHMATES and gain one of the following effects.\r\n\r\n> **PSIMATE**: The other beneficiary of your shared psychic pool has perished, leaving you to carry the burden of that energy. This, put simply, sucks like fuck. Your head never stops burning, you feel something missing in your chest. Thanks to having to tough it up, you no longer have your HP split, instead merely having **-3 HP** overall. You are perpetually experiencing **[Dread]**, **[Confused]** or **[Scared]** and cannot lose it. Choose which upon taking the move. The immense **[Psionic]** energy once split between two people comes crashing down onto your lone vessel as well. You are now **[Legendary]** at **+IMG**. However, the first time you roll a MAX **[Psionic]** move, you immediately gain the PSIBURN **[Affliction]** as all that excess power makes you sick.\r\n\r\n> **GHOSTMATE**: So, you were supposed to have the one up there but you lucked out with your other body managing to create a ghost and possess you? You really do manage to escape all consequences of your inactions. With your other parts of your soul reunited, you at least manage to escape the infinite yawning dread of being without a full soul! Likewise, your HP is no longer split between two bodies, now simply having **-3 HP** overall. However, the process of merging has... effects on your once great **[Psionic]** energy. All that power not only spilling into your body uncontrolled but also being recombined, for lack of a better term, burned you out like a lightbulb. You lose access to all **[Psionic]** moves, the destabilizing effect rippling out further to cause a permanent **-2 [Nerf]** to all **[Psionic]** rolls in your presence as well.\r\n\r\n> **HATCHMATE**: Your bro died... dude... not cool... This, fortunately, sucks massively less than losing a psimate does, but it still sucks massively. You keep any moves you had from HATCHMATE prior to your sibling\'s death, and may take one additional now in memoriam if possible. Using these moves from your departed sibling inflicts **1 [Drag]** as it crungles your emotions.'),
('lookingForTrouble', 'LOOKING FOR TROUBLE', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Passive][Unlock: Delinquent]', 'You? You\'re the REASON Ceruleans have the rotten reputation they do. You\'re a rough, tough ruffian and it\'s just better for everyone if people don\'t get in your way. And Mothergrub below have mercy if someone messes with you. Try anything funny and SHANK! AW SHIT, WHAT\'S ALL THIS STUFF IN YOUR HANDS, OH MY GOD IT\'S SOMEONE\'S INTESTINES, CUZ YOU KILLED THEM! BITCH!!!!!!!! You are **[Talented]** at **+GRT**. If someone rolls a **[Chicanery]** move against you you may become **[Enraged]** for free. This can stack up to become **[Out-Of-Control]**, even! While **[Enraged]**, further **[Chicanery]** rolls are **[Inept]**, even if they\'d have an ability that\'s like \"nuh-uh I can\'t be **[Inept]** at that\".'),
('lookingGoodAsHell', 'LOOKING GOOD AS HELL', 'OTHER', 'HAUTE_CLAWTURE', '[Template][Advanced][Locked: Haute Clawture]', 'What’s the point of making all of this delightful clothing if you can’t wear it and feel awesome? You are your own best model for your skills, after all! Whenever you wear a full outfit (**[Head]**, **[Top]**, **[Bottoms]**, **[Feet]**, **[Gloves]**, and **[Accessories]**) of your custom designed clothing, you start off your next encounter feeling **[Smug]**. On top of that, when you get your first **GREAT** or better in a Strife, you can **[Heighten]** that emotion to **[Supercilious]**.'),
('loosenUp', 'LOOSEN UP', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Passive]', 'Hey, whew! It\'s nice to… relax. Stop worrying so much, you know? Loosen up, even! You don\'t need to hold yourself up to such high standards, right? You gain an effect based on your tree!\r\n\r\n> **AUXILLATRICE**: You\'re much laxer than you once were now when it comes to teaching. From a middle school teacher on their first day to a seasoned college lecturer, you know? Whenever someone in an encounter gets a **BAD** or lower **[Mental]** roll, you get **1 [Boost]** as you note the problem and figure out how to help without getting all wound up.\r\n\r\n> **CLOISTERED**: Hmmm… sneaking up to the surface feels wrong, but… it kind of feels awesome, too! You\'ve gotten very good at blending in on the surface, and only have the **[Cullbait]** tag on the surface if you slip up and let people know you\'re a Cloistered troll!\r\n\r\n> **SLAYER**: Maybe… you can relax. Unwind. Not everything is about the horrors of the night. Sometimes… it\'s about a vampire slayer buying shit at the grocery store and going \"hrnnn\" at the price of grubjuice. **1 VP** items cost **½ VP** instead as you remember to live a more mundane life. Items from your tree don\'t use this discount. It\'s for mundane stuff! Not bombs!\r\n\r\n> **SUBCULTIST**: You don\'t gotta prove your interests are cool or worthwhile to nobody. So long as you like them, that\'s all that matters! You can give allies the abilities granted to you when you\'re wearing a complete **[Fashion]** Collection (but not the stat boosts).\r\n\r\n> **TUNNELWARDEN**: No need to keep throwing yourself into danger! Others can fight for themselves too. You got this! Whenever you are on STANDBY in an encounter, you get **1 [Boost]** every turn that you don\'t otherwise gain **[Boost]**; you can\'t increase this **[Boost]** with **[Emotions]** or other effects. \r\n\r\n> **SOMETHING ELSE**: Oh, well aren’t YOU special? You don’t even have a Jade tree. Take one of the above effects and flavour it to your liking.'),
('lootOfTheDamned', 'LOOT OF THE DAMNED', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Chicanery][Physical][Locked: Dungeoneer]', 'This may be bad, but you know how to make it worse. Thanks to your quick and easy access to a multitude of artifacts you most definitely shouldn’t have, you have the unique ability to cause problems for your foes with a twist. You can buy the following exclusive **[Rare]** items with your Treasure…\r\n\r\n**ANCIENT RUNES (2 VP)**: These runes burned onto linen wrappings will probably keep you safe, maybe! When someone uses a **[Magic]** roll on you, the runes burn away, but the roll becomes **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n**FLASK OF EMBERS (2 VP)**: Slug em down, baby! This bottle of multicolored embers keeps you safe in combat. You take **1 less damage** from attacks that do **[Energy]** damage for **2 turns** (min. 1).\r\n\r\n**STRANGE AMULET (2 VP)**: This amulet glows blue when you\'re in the presence of an **[Eerie]** troll. Spoooooky! You, uh, don\'t know who it is though. Just that there\'s one around.\r\n\r\n**RING OF SAFEGUARDING (3 VP)**: This makes you just a lil sturdier. Which is good, frankly. You gain **2 extra HP**!\r\n\r\n**SPO**OK**Y PENDULUM (3 VP)**: The hypnotic swinging of this cursed amulet is.. fascinating … Yaawwwn. The target becomes **[Tired]**. After it is used, it is destroyed.\r\n\r\n**URN OF PHANTOMS (4 VP)**: HAHA! I RELEASE THEE! Bitch! I call upon the ancient spirits of get FUCKED. You smash an ancient artifact at your feet and summon the PARANORMAL ACTIVITY Hazard. You are also caught in it. Dipshit.'),
('loreSeeker', 'LORE SEEKER', 'LIGHT', 'LIGHT', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Light]', 'Information is what makes the world go round. It doesn’t matter whether you got it logically or not; all that matters is that the more you know, the more complete you feel. Plus, that lore should be shared with others! You can forgo rolling an **[Analyze]** move and, as an action, get a **GOOD** result; if you have a move with the same effect, you can choose to instead get **two GOOD** results. Additionally, whenever you share your findings with someone, you get **1 [Boost]** per **[Analyze]** result shared.'),
('loresplain', 'LORESPLAIN', 'OTHER', 'MAGE', '[Class][Basic][Free][Reaction][Locked: Mage]', 'So many lessons, so little time. You know a lot and therefore have a lot to ponder and a lot to explain. You\'ll have your friend\'s attention for 5 blips here, so you\'re going to have to get out the ultimate moral about this experience FAST. Accordingtoallknown lawsofaviationthereisnowayastingwingshouldbeabletofly. When you roll a **GOOD** or **GREAT** result on PROBLEM SLEUTHING or WORDPLAY roll you can choose to get two results instead of one. This makes you **[Tired]** as you definitely overloaded even yourself there...urk. This doesn\'t work when you roll a **MAX** as you might keel over dead if you info dump that hard.\r\n\r\n'),
('loudmouthLowblood', 'LOUDMOUTH LOWBLOOD', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'ALRIGHT, YOU\'VE HAD IT UP TO HERE! Bronzes are infamous for being loud and boisterous, and while it\'s a grossly overexaggerated trait, it\'s oh so fun to let off some steam and YELL. Whether it\'s a slurry of words directed at a target, a ranting tirade of curses, or just… a really loud shout of wordless frustration, you don\'t fear speaking (or roaring) your mind! You gain the following WORDPLAY effects:\r\n\r\n> **YELL**: MY EARS! You roar out really loudly. The opponent is **[Deafened]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **SLANGSLING**: You spew out an incomprehensible barrage of words. The target is **[Confused]** for **2 turns**. On a **GREAT**, they\'re **[Dumbfounded]** for **2 turns**; on a **MAX**, they\'re **[Dumbfounded]** for the encounter.\r\n\r\n> **THREATEN**: You\'d best do what I say! The target is **[Scared]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **MOCK: You laugh and spit out something inflammatory. That hurts :( The target is **[Embarrassed]** for **1 turn**.'),
('loveAChallenge', 'LOVE A CHALLENGE', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Passive]', 'Oh, is that what they’ve got in store for you? Some kinda defenses? Aw, they’re REAL tough, huh? Well, good thing that you’re getting real tired of winning without trying, honk! You’ve had victory over victory, terrifying beast of a juggalo that you are, and it’s all gotten so booooring. So… when you see something that looks tricky… boy, you just can’t wait to get ‘em. When a target has an ability that makes a certain type of move **[Inept]**, **[Nerfed]** or **[Tiered Down]** against them… you can’t help but want to try it for yourself. If you roll a move of that kind, you get unusual additional effects. On a **MIN**, you can’t help but laugh. How silly, huh? You got your ass whooped there! Isn’t that FUNNY? HONK HONK HONK! All your **[Buildup]** and **[Recharge]** hits 0, and you gain **1 [WHAM]**. On a **BAD**, you gain **1 [WHAM]**. On an **OK**, nothing happens. On a **GOOD**, you get **1 [Boost]**. On a **GREAT**, you get **2 [Boost]**. On a **MAX**, you get **5 [Boost]** and **2 [WHAM]** as you DECK THE ABSOLUTE SHIT OUT OF THEM DESPITE IT ALL. How did you fucking manage that, huh?'),
('lovelorn', 'LOVELORN', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'It\'s not so easy being an Auxillatrice or Tunnelwarden in love. You work hard every day, surrounded by a caste that encourages pining. As a result, many jades feel an intensified longing compared to other trolls. All your quadrant benefits start a stage early; for example, when you start dating someone, you gain the ESTABLISHED RELATIONSHIP benefits rather than the NEW QUADS, and you gain the NEW QUADS benefit with your crush before you even make it official. You are the only one who gains this advanced bonus; your partners still gain the regular ones. When you become Quadbonded, you gain access to one **[Open]** move on your partner\'s sheet. If you are ever **[Charmed]**, you immediately become **[Hopeful]** too… and replace that with **[Enraged]** if **[Charmed]** wears off.'),
('lovelyAssistants', 'LOVELY ASSISTANTS', 'OTHER', 'WITCH', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Witch]', 'Over your journey you’ve amassed a great deal of power. Anything you desire, right at your fingertips. But how worthwhile is it all… when you have no one to share it with? Yeah, turns people don’t really appreciate your talents if all you’ve done is pushed your own will onto them. Huh. Well, you’re a witch, after all, and like all good witches,you can change! Hopefully this time for the better! You’ve listened to the people around you - no longer are they familiars but lovely assistants in your marvelous magic acts! The **[Drag]** you and an ally receive from **COMMAND FAMILIAR** is reduced to 1. Additionally, when you **[Tier Up]** someone’s move they gain a **[Hold]**. With this they may spend a **[Free] [Reaction]** to **[Tier Up]** one of your moves as you let them meddle with you like you do to them.\r\n'),
('lowbloodOverload', 'LOWBLOOD OVERLOAD', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[One-Off][Psionic][Buildup: 4]', 'Prerequisite: Must be a Limeblood or lower.\n\nSometimes, you just really want to lay on the hurt, no matter the cost. When rolling a **[Psionic]** move, you can forgo rolling and receive a **MAX**, creating extremely easy to detect effects (massive sound burst, light, shaking ground, etc). After you use this move, you gain the **[Despair]** tag for the rest of the encounter; you cannot get rid of it through any means. Should you be defeated in combat, you will automatically come back as a Ghost later.'),
('lowkeyLusokinesis', 'LOW-KEY LUSOKINESIS', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Passive][Psionic]', 'Fully-fledged lusokinetic psionics are rarer than one might expect. Of all lowblood psionics, they\'re definitely the rarest to show up consistently! That being said, many Bronzes have much more low-key versions of the psionic gene that lets them understand lusii better… and vice-versa! Whenever you or an ally gain an **[Emotion]**, you may give a lusus present this **[Emotion]** too. If you did not previously have a **[Psionic]** move, you may gain the PSIBURN Affliction, but it only gives you a terrible headache. You become **[Confused]**.'),
('luckBeASpider', 'LUCK BE A SPIDER', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Passive][Unlock: Gamblignant]', 'Fortune favours those who test it! You are training as a Gamblignant, a troll who will one day run one of the many casinos across the galaxy aiming to force aliens into massive debts to the Empire. Whether you\'re a game show presenter, a high roller at gambling events or one of those freaky magicians with the weird cards, you know the ones, you currently have a single goal; tame luck and make it your little bitch. You are **[Talented]** at **+APP**. Once per week, you may roll 1d8 as a **[Downtime]** roll to see how your time gambling has treated you. \r\n\r\n> 1. Curses! You drop two Wealth Levels! You gambled much too hard!\r\n> 2. You lost a little bit of money, yeah. You drop a Wealth Level.\r\n> 3. You just about break even. Nothing happens. \r\n> 4. You won a prize, but not what you were looking for. The first item you buy this week is 1 **VP** less than normal.\r\n> 5. Winning! You gain **Treasure I**.\r\n> 6. WINNING X2! You gain **Treasure II**.\r\n> 7. SUPER WINNING COMBO! You gain **Treasure III**. \r\n> 8. SUPER TURKEY BALL WINNING STREAK IV! You become **Ultrarich** for a week, and then become **Well-Off** again. You gain **Treasure III**.'),
('luckBringer', 'LUCK BRINGER', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Free][One-Off][Passive]', 'Who needs to be good, or even great, when luck’s got your back! Olives have a strange knack at getting lucky at things when you’d least expect it. As a **[Free]** **[One-Off]**, when someone rolls on a dice table something that isn’t a move (such as a 1d8 for a random effect, a Gambligant’s FLUORIDE OCTETS or a Scienceling’s CONCOCTIOMANCY), your very presence either brings them good luck or bad luck. They roll twice, and you choose the effect!'),
('luckyBreak', 'LUCKY BREAK', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive]', 'Whoah! That\'s really great! You just came into possession of a lot of **LUX**, how awesome is that? You gain a number of **LUX** equal to a **MAX** MONEYMAKERY **[Downtime]** roll +2. You can take this move multiple times.'),
('luckyMerchant', 'LUCKY MERCHANT', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Passive][Locked: Meowchant]', 'Hey, hey, c\'mon into my store! You wanna buy some stuff? It\'s good luck to purchase from you, you know. And BAD luck not to! You\'re like a lil Maneki-Neko here! When you offer someone the chance to PERUSE YOUR WARES, you may bless them or curse them with your strange, strange fortune. When someone buys an item from you, they can take a **[Hold]**. This **[Hold]** lets them become **[Hopeful]** for **[Free]** at any point in the next two weeks. If they refuse to buy from you, then a curse upon them! You give them a **[Hold]** that you can activate within the next two weeks to make the target feel **[Dread]** for **[Free]**.'),
('lumeblood', 'LUMEBLOOD', 'OTHER', 'MUTANT', '[Mutant][Cullbait][Passive]', 'The issue is, unfortunately, not that you have a different color of blood than the twelve castes— the issue that lies with you is that it glows. Your blood is luminescent, like a cracked glow stick that never burns out. It would be a pretty cool thing to look at if it wasn’t something that the Empire wanted you dead for. The first time you become **[Bloodied]** in an encounter, all other people in the encounter are **[Blinded]**- whether friend or foe. You aren’t, of course, as this is something you’ve dealt with your entire life. Deepsea Violets and Rainbow Drinker Jades are **[Immune]** to these effects as such a luminescence is something they’re already used to. Whenever you become **[Bloodied]** or begin **[Crying]** you experience **[Dread]**, and this heightens to **[Despair]** if your opponent reacts poorly to your blood color. Additionally, you are **[Inept]** at all rolls to become **[Hidden]** and those who are trying to spot you have a **+2 [Buff]** to their rolls. It sure does suck being able to see the luminescence of your blood through your veins!'),
('lususWhisperer', 'LUSUS WHISPERER', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Passive][Psionic][Locked: Summoner]', 'You have the uncanny ability to understand lusii. Whether it manifests through knowing what they want or what they need, or through physically translating the noises they make into your language, you understand lusii. Lusii can speak to you, and conversely, you can roll **[Manipulate]** rolls on them and speak back. WORDPLAY rolls on Lusii use **+IMG**.'),
('madeManMaker', 'MADE MAN MAKER', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'HET', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Recharge: 1][Locked: HET]', 'By every mean, the HET is the third lowest in the Color Guard totem pole, above the TIT and CIS, but below their higherblooded counterparts. However, they are the only Organization to have an organized, effective public outreach wing. Because they ARE the public outreach wing! Masters of bending the rules, shouting loud enough to bury the ones they don\'t like and shaping the public opinion on matters. The careers and even lives of higher castes rely on the HET\'s continued goodwill, and the HET is not shy to exploit this to punch above their caste like any other ceruleans would. Wouldn\'t it be a shame if that well respected indigo politician-in-training had leaked they were dating a rebel...? \r\n\r\nWhen a highblooded troll fails to live up to the expectations of indestructibility and power your propaganda extols by possessing 5 or more **[Drag]** total, you pounce on the weak link. You gain **1 [Boost]** per turn until they reduce their **[Drag]** to 0. The **[Boost]** gained increases by 1 for every 5 **[Drag]** the opponent possesses.'),
('madeOfSteel', 'MADE OF STEEL', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Last Stand][Locked: Labourer]', 'Holy SHIT, how are you still GOING? No matter what the world throws at you, you just… power through it. All in the name of getting your work done, huh? When you GET TO WORK, it\'s startling how difficult it is to down you. You can reduce incoming damage, even to 0, as a **[Free]** action. However, for every point of damage you ignore, you clock down the timer before you fall **[Unconscious]** from BACKBREAKING LABOURER. For example, if you took 4 damage and reduced it to 2, you\'d count as if an extra 2 rounds had passed. You can also ignore **[Physical]** conditions in this way. However, when you would fall **[Unconscious]** through sheer exhaustion, you don\'t— instead, you are immediately reduced to **1 HP**, **[Exhausted]** as you try to give it one last shot. You can\'t **[Heal]** in this state.'),
('madMechanist', 'MAD MECHANIST', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Passive][Craft][Unlock: Junker]', 'What do you get when you cross mechanical innovation with low budgets? Some ESPECIALLY wild builds! Bronzes are often expected to become engineers upon ascension, but are simultaneously not given the support or resources to work on advanced scientific projects. As such, most improvise by cannibalizing the carcasses of machines to create something new. See this palmhusk? It\'s made from a scuttlebuggy engine, an old husktop, and a drone\'s brain. Works great! You are **[Talented]** at **+HUB**; it\'s more important to be gutsy than smart here. Your crafting starts on a small scale; you can craft items on the fly in the middle of an encounter, effectively buying items with your **VP** mid-combat. Unlike other on-the-fly purchase moves, you can use the same item more than once, though there\'s a **[Recharge: 2]** on such creations. Obviously, you can\'t make wholly organic items like food. Additionally, you add one of the following tags to items purchased like this. Items you buy in **[Downtime]** can also have these tags.\r\n\r\n> **Unstable**: This thing is fit to blow at any moment. Watch your fingers! Whenever this item takes damage or breaks, it explodes. Dealing **2 [Somatic]** damage to all opponents and immediately destroying the item.  This effect has the **[Strife]** tag, cause you threw it at the bad guys before it blew up.  You did chuck it before it blew right? Oh god. \r\n\r\n> **Weaponized**: In the hands of an unsupervised child, anything can be a weapon, like this weapon.  Sure you can use it as a not-weapon, but it\'s definitely a weapon. You add a single ABSTRATA UPGRADE to the item, though it costs an additional 2 **VP**.\r\n\r\n> **Jury-Rigged**: You duct tape two items together, like troll Frankenstein, combining their tags and effects, allowing you to use both as a single action, but making the resulting item extremely flimsy quality. The resulting item uses a number of **VP** equal to the two individual items\' **VP** added together, divided by 2, minus 2. However, whenever you use it, roll 1d8. On a 1 or a 2, it falls apart before you can activate it. \r\n\r\n> **Reuseable**: Squeeze just a little bit extra out of it! If the item is **[Consumable]**, roll 1d8 after using it. If you roll a 4+, it doesn\'t get used up! Every time you use this, the number range on this d8 goes up by 1.\r\n\r\n> **Transfigurable**: Okay, jam it sideways, twist, and… tada! Your flashlight is now a grappling hook! You can permanently transform an item with this tag into another item with equal value as a **[Free]** action. You can\'t do this more than once.\r\n\r\n> **Flawed**: Not the best, but it\'ll do the trick! The item becomes **[Consumable]**, breaking after it is activated once, but it costs **2 VP** less (min. 1). Obviously, you can\'t give this to a **[Consumable]** item.'),
('maelstromNeglect', 'MAELSTROM NEGLECT', 'OTHER', 'BARD', '[Class][Advanced][Magic][Passive][Locked: Bard]', 'Don\'t work. Doesn\'t matter. Don\'t work. Doesn\'t matter! It\'s fun to see everything go directly to hell, even stuff others keep telling you you\'re good at. You think I\'m a determined, justice seeking person beneath it all? Nahhh! Fuck it all, right? You don\'t care anymore, and your lack of caring is like a swampy pit that slowly consumes the very narrative itself. When you first get knocked to below **5 HP**, you activate the following effect based on your aspect automatically. Because fuck this whole aspect thing, remember? It\'s all just a joke. The effect ends if you climb above **5 HP** again, and works on you and allies as well. \r\n\r\n**TIME**: Time begins to hiccup and everyone\'s pace is jumbled up. Every troll present becomes **[Slowed]**.\r\n\r\n**SPACE**: The way that distance works seems to be difficult to track suddenly. Moves that rely on Rangekind are **[Inept]** and moves that affect multiple targets affect only one. Everyone **[Flying]** becomes **[Floorbound]** and everyone **[Floorbound]** becomes **[Flying]**. Don’t think about it too hard. \r\n\r\n**LIFE**: Every time a **[Heal]** move is used, roll 1d2. On a 2, any HP that would have been gained instead turns to **[Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**DOOM**: The laws of the universe fracture and skew. **[One-off]** moves are no longer **[One-Off]**, but each use of an already used **[One-off]** in this state costs **6 [Drag]** or **2 HP** to use. \r\n\r\n**HOPE**: Idols burn and the many scream. All **[Positive]** Emotions turn to **[Out Of Control]**, including any gained after this. \r\n\r\n**RAGE**: The pulses of the many slow to a grim calmness. All current **[Negative]** Emotions are transformed into **[Serene]**.\r\n\r\n**BREATH**: Freedom flits out of control and disappears, leaving only imprisonment where it lies. All trolls present only benefit from half the **[Boost]** they spend, rounded down.\r\n\r\n**BLOOD**: Friendship? Ha! What a joke! Nobody out there really cares! Moves that buff allies are **[Tiered Down]**, or disabled if they\'re **[Passive]**.\r\n\r\n**LIGHT**: Destruction through and of knowledge as truth overloads the world and burns it to dust. All trolls become **[Confused]**.\r\n\r\n**VOID**: Don\'t stop thinking, learning, seeing, becoming, see that which exists and hides no matter what- all trolls become **[Focused]**. \r\n\r\n**HEART**: The self is a husk and a sham. **[Emotions]** are disabled for the fight, save for **[Numb]** and **[Dissociating]**.\r\n\r\n**MIND**: HHHHNNHHGGHHAAAAAGH! I FEEL! I FEEL! All trolls present become **[Icarian]**, and gain a random **[Heightened]** Emotion whenever they would gain an Emotion. Roll randomly to select the emotion.\r\n\r\n');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('magicalImplements', 'MAGICAL IMPLEMENTS', 'OTHER', 'ASTROSORCERER', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Astrosorcerer]', 'You\'ve spent long enough studying the arcane that you\'ve become a true practitioner of all things magic… including the magical implements used by the warlocks of days of old. You gain access to each of the following ABSTRATA UPGRADES, which cost 1 **LUX** each.\n\n**STAFFKIND**: **[Active]** The ancient and reliable staffkind, what is there to say about it that is not obvious? It\'s big, it\'s cumbersome, and it\'s fucking wicked for casting magic with. You can spend an action before rolling a **[Magic]** move to stabilize your spell, preventing it from being **[Drag]**ged or **[Tiered Down]** in exchange for gaining 1 **[Drag]**.\n\n**WANDKIND**: **[Active]** Just like in Troll Wizards of Waverly Place! This small, unassuming stick lets you cast magic far quicker and more sexily than a loser. On a **MAX**, you may deal 1 less damage in order to roll a **[Magic]** move for **[Free]**. Your quick spellflinging comes at a cost though, as it will be **[Inept]** when you roll it!\n\n**GLYPHKIND**: **[Passive]** Whether it\'s mystical tattoos across your body, gauntlets of armor with arcane symbols etched into it or merely hand wrappings with hastily scribbled astrology mumbojumbo strewn across it, you\'re ready for a magical adventure. On any turn you **[Strife]** with this weapon, you gain 1 **[Boost]** if you also use a **[Magic]** move first as your powers strengthen!\n\n**BROOMKIND**: **[Passive]** Neh heh heh heh… you can hop on this bad boy and fly instead of attack! You can start **[Flying]**.\n\n**GUNKIND**: **[Passive]** You cast bullet. Roll 3d28 Piercing Radiant damage. Haha, wrong system, but that\'s the idea here. Some losers might stick to pre-Condesce rituals and lore, but you\'re a modern astrosorcerer in a modern world. You may use any **[Physical]** **[Strife]** move with **+IMG**; these moves gain the **[Magic]** tag rather than **[Physical]**. However, you need to load special magic bullets into this thing; you take 1 **[Drag]** when you use a **[Strife]** move like this as you hurry to load them between shots. This attack can hit **[Flying]** targets with no problem.'),
('magicAnon', 'MAGIC ANON', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][One-Off][Chicanery][Magic][Psionic][Locked: AU]', 'Canon is a funny thing; infinite versions of infinite AUs exist, and if you know how to pull the metanarrative strings right, you can shuffle your opponent’s reality too. After all, why should you have all the fun? When you want to make someone try a new AU, roll **+IMG**; even if you aren\'t **[Talented]** at **+IMG**, you are at this roll.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Hnnnrkh-! God, your head feels like it\'s melting!! You experience **[Sensory Overload]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: A bad headache runs over you… you are **[Overwhelmed]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Nothing happens, but you don\'t trigger the **[One-Off]** of this move yet.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: It\'s... good, but the power you need to break dimensions like that are way more than just good! You **[Overwhelm]** the target for a round; you don\'t use the **[One-Off]** of this move yet.\r\n\r\n**GREAT: REALITY BREAKS DOWN BENEATH YOU! Choose one of the following effects**: \r\n\r\n> **BLOODSWAP**: You shift them through an AU where they\'re a different caste! Your target loses all their **[Caste]** moves; they may instead use any moves from a different caste of your choosing, and a tree of their choosing. They have the same number of **[Basic]**, **[Advanced]** and **[Ultra]** moves as they did in their original tree and caste. Feel free to pick moves on the fly, but track how many you have used! Their personality and design might change severely in the process, but they have the same memories. This lasts for the encounter. \r\n\r\n> **TROLLSWAP**: You turn a Kid into a Troll! This uses the effects of Bloodswap, except it completely alters your species.\r\n\r\n> **HUMANSTUCK**: You guessed it— you turn a Troll into a Kid! Same rules apply, but inverse. Yes, these are all the same effect, but the names have got fandom history behind them and are extremely versatile, so yeah. How about that?\r\n\r\n> **GUARDIANSTUCK**: Great heavens! You\'re swapped out with a troll version of your lusus! You\'re an entirely new character with a new Statblock and potentially a different tree, though you\'re generally of the same caste. Whack!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: And a little extra! You don\'t shift just one person— you shift everyone! All trolls present are affected by the same AU you shunt them into— yourself included, though you keep your Lime moves!'),
('magnificentCollection', 'MAGNIFICENT COLLECTION', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Open][Downtime]', 'Holy shit! A shittonne of golden spoons? Vases made of obsidian? Sportsball awards? Damn— you have really built up a collection of incredible items, huh? You devote a lot of time to building and perfecting your collection, and for good reason, you know. You can amass a pool of COLLECTIBLES. These COLLECTIBLES instill in you a supreme confidence and feeling of accomplishment unlike anything you\'ve had access to before; they\'re a confirmation that you really are that bitch. For every 5 COLLECTIBLES you have, you get a CONFIDENCE POINT, which you can spend on various boons. However, if you ever go down a Wealth Level, lose a strife in your hive or let someone steal or destroy your COLLECTIBLES, you lose half of your pool. Don\'t let this happen to you! When you want to expand your collection, roll **+APP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Shit shit shit SHIT! Bandits target your collection, and you lose EVERYTHING, and drop a Wealth Level! Noooo!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Ngh-! You lose half your COLLECTIBLES. What happened?!\r\n\r\n**OK**: You… get **1 COLLECTIBLE**. Maybe like, a 3rd place medal, or a really small robot or something…\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: That\'s the stuff! You get **2 COLLECTIBLES**. Remember, for every **5 COLLECTIBLES** you have, you gain a CONFIDENCE POINT, which you can use for **[Free]** to…\r\n\r\n> 1. **[Tier Up]** an **OK** roll to a **GOOD**.\r\n> 2. **[Tier Up]** a roll of 19+ to a **MAX**.\r\n> 3. Reduce the timer on a negative condition affecting you for X rounds by 1.\r\n> 4. Remove a condition that requires an action to be rid of, like **[Floorbound]** or **[Ablaze]**.\r\n> 5. **[Tier Up]** a **+APP** roll.\r\n> 6. Be **[Talented]** at a **+GRA** roll.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Wow, that\'s some RARE stuff! You get **3 COLLECTIBLES**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: IS… IS THAT THE RARE AND HIGHLY SOUGHT AFTER MCGUFFIN? WOW! You get **5 COLLECTIBLES**!'),
('maidSeeMaidDo', 'MAID SEE, MAID DO', 'OTHER', 'MAID', '[Class][Basic][Locked: Maid]', 'Whenever you\'re in a fight with allies, you sometimes take cues from them, looking to their leadership to determine what to do! Whenever your ally uses a non-**[Strife]** move, you may choose to roll the same move on your following turn with a +2 **[Buff]** as you follow in their footsteps. This can be a non-**[Ultra]** move you don’t have access to so long as it makes sense (an olive cannot roll a burgundy **[Psionic]** move), but must be a rolled move.\r\n'),
('makeAKilling', 'MAKE A KILLING', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][One-Off][Locked: Mafioso]', 'Look… you can\'t always be the one getting your hands dirty, y\'know? The Clutch is clowns only, but other castes can always be hired to do jobs for you too. Typically, this will be Teal Legislacerators or Cerulean Espiacrooners, but really, anyone who wants to take a job can take it. You can make a BIG BUY to pay a non-Mafiose troll to do a job. For every level of Wealth you sink into them, they get **4 [Boost]** or **2 [WHAM]** they can use in a future encounter to complete this job, as well as **Treasure I**. Whether the job is \"steal the holy relic\", \"intimidate these guys\" or \"murder the fuck out of this douchebag\" is up to you. If you have the MAFIALADDER move, you can use this move on trolls lower on the ladder than you, and they get **2 extra [Boost]** for free.'),
('makesMeFeelGood', 'MAKES ME FEEL GOOD', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'BUSTIN', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Bustin’]', 'Prerequisite: You are Purple, but not a Mafioso.\r\n\r\nMessiahs have mercy, you’re about to BUST! You’re a member of the Bustin’ Brigade, a group of trolls who track down and eliminate phantoms, ghouls and other spooky specters. Mostly Ghosts. You have conditional authority over all non-Org trolls, and Drones will not target you while in your ORG Uniform, which you gain now for free, as well as a flair on all social media marking you as a member of the Bustin’ Brigade. You have access to special, Churchmade POLTERBUSTERS, special weapons which always do **[Holy]** damage on top of all other damage. This holy damage manifests as weird, pink-white lightning. You know, like the beams in Ghostbusters (1984). You can have two ABSTRATA UPGRADES on your weapons instead of just one as you customize the ultimate Bustin’ Regalia, and you gain the following PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll.\r\n\r\n> GHOSTS? You sniff the air, use weird tech, or otherwise determine if there is a ghost in the area, or if there was one around recently. If there was, you gain **1 [WHAM]**, and your SPOT rolls to find **[Hidden]** targets become **[Tiered Up]** for the encounter.\r\n\r\n'),
('makesTheDreamWork', 'MAKES THE DREAM WORK', 'OTHER', 'PRINCE', '[Class][Advanced][Free][Recharge: 1][Locked: Prince]', 'ARGHHH!! YOU FUCKING IDIOT!! YOU’RE MESSING UP, YOU’RE GOING TO RUIN THIS WHOLE FIGHT, YOU’RE-\r\n…Okay. Deep breath. You say a lot of things you don’t really mean sometimes, especially to your friends, but you’re trying to get better. Whenever an ally rolls a **BAD** or a **MIN** on a UNIVERSAL MOVE, you can give them some guidance on your turn and grant them a +2 **[Buff]** to their next roll of that move. Just like that! Good job! '),
('makeupMayhem', 'MAKEUP MAYHEM', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Passive]', 'Purples MUST wear makeup. This isn\'t an option. The rare few that refuse to do so don\'t make it past a few sweeps as other clowns hunt them down for their infidelity to the Mirthful Messiahs. Makeup is a sign of allegiance to the Church, and a way to avoid lethal encounters with your fellow clown. Thankfully, it\'s also a great way of expressing yourself! Select an option that best describes your makeup.\r\n\r\n> **EMOTIVE**: Your makeup makes a second face under your own! It looks like :D or X( or QoQ or some other shit. Select an **[Emotion]**; when you gain this **[Emotion]**, it either **[Heightens]** or you gain its opposite, your choice. \r\n\r\n> **ANIMALISTIC**: Your facepaint looks like an animal, from a cute skittycat of a terrifying snazzard. You gain the CUSTODIAN COMPANION Perfectly Generic Move, but you can have 6 Features, not 2.\r\n\r\n> **VIBE**: Your facepaint isn\'t a thing, it\'s more like… a feeling. An atmosphere, you know? The stat limit for **+IMG** raises to +5, not +4. You may reduce an existing stat by 1 to increase your **+IMG** immediately.\r\n\r\n> **SMEARED**: Your facepaint WAS something once. It\'s no longer that, and you go to great pains to keep the smear present. When a troll uses **[WHAM]** on you, you gain **2 [Boost]** per **[WHAM]** as you savour the pain. Ooogh…\r\n\r\n> **VEIL**: You don\'t wear facepaint! Instead, your face is covered by cloth, a mask, or something else. When you buy a **[Fashion]** item, you get 1 for free.\r\n\r\n> **SOMETHING**: I dunno, man, it\'s something. Select an option from the list above and reflavour it.'),
('maliciousMockery', 'MALICIOUS MOCKERY', 'OTHER', 'MAGE', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Recharge: 4][Locked: Mage]', 'YOU… PIG IGNORANT, FATUOUS MORONS! Cereal IS a soup! UGH! You still have some trouble having your words get through to people. Especially when it’s people who oppose you but you still hope could change. Okay, perhaps all you need to do is change your delivery. Afterall, sometimes the best kind of insult is the kind that takes a moment to settle in. When you roll a **GREAT** or **MAX** **[Verbal] [Strife]** move, you can choose to do 1 less damage in return for putting together the kind of clever, scathing insult that takes a little while to sink in before they realize just how hard you\'ve dragged them. They take 2 **[Drag]** each turn for 3 turns, at the end of which they figure it out and take 1 **[Psychic]** damage.\r\n'),
('manajeer', 'MANAJEER', 'INDIGO', 'ADULT', '[Indigo][Free][Locked: Adult]', 'What does it mean to be a leader? Many have asked themselves this question, but very few have proved its potential in practice. You are one of the few trolls who truly understands leadership in the workplace and knows how to wield it like a finely-sharpened blade. After sweeps of understanding TRUE leadership, you’re ready for the next step, and it looks like the higher-ups agree. You’ve ascended directly into the coveted echelons of Upper Management to become a Manajeer, the first and final voice in any important decision. This company, this organization, this FAMILY is yours to command. The best Manajeers go down in history as the real movers and shakers of the business world, creating new opportunities for the Alternian Empire to assert its dominance. The worst? Well, let’s just say the board takes “firing” very literally. On your turn, you can grab one of your allies and force them to listen as you lay out your plans. You! Boy! It’s your destiny to punch that troll right in the bulge. Get to it! Choose the moves that an ally will make on their next turn. So long as they follow the plan you’ve made, those rolls **[Tier Up]** as they follow your clear instructions. You can only use this once per ally. They’re still individuals, you know!'),
('maniacalLaugh', 'MANIACAL LAUGH', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Reaction][Mental][Locked: Marquis]', 'The signature of a stylish rich Cerulean is the intimidating laugh. It strikes fear in the bloodpushers’ of feeble opponents, and is frankly quite cathartic. When you use **[Boost]**, you may spend a **[Reaction]** laughing maniacally. Roll **+HUB**.\n\n**MIN**: W- aw, dunk, you pissed yourself, or had some other embarrassing thing happen to you! That\'s not very intimidatingly rich at all! You gain double the amount of **[Boost]** you just used as **[Drag]**, and you\'re **[Embarrassed]** to boot!\n\n**BAD**: Your laugh is… laughable, honestly. You gain an amount of **[Drag]** equal to the amount of **[Boost]** you just used. \n\n**OK**: It\'s more of a sensible chuckle than an evil laugh, honestly. You don\'t use up your reaction. \n\n**GOOD**: KYAHAHAHA! Your evil laugh is striking, and it makes you feel great! You regain half the **[Boost]** you just used (min 1), or you make the opponent **[Scared]**.\n\n**GREAT**: A flash of well timed lightning and a maddened look in your eye REALLY sells this laugh. You regain half the **[Boost]** you just used, and the opponent becomes **[Scared]**.\n\n**MAX**: A crawling sense of dread overcomes those who oppose you as you cackle, and they realise there\'s something seriously wrong with you. You regain all the **[Boost]** you just used, and the opponent becomes **[Terrified]**.'),
('martialProwess', 'MARTIAL PROWESS', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'Sometimes, you stumble and mumble in social encounters. Sometimes, you say the wrong thing. But in a fight? Oh boy, in a fight, you are as sharp as a blade. You\'ve trained extensively, more so than nearly any of your peers, and you now have access to some pretty intense COMBAT STANCES. You gain the following LET\'S STRIFE options.\r\n\r\n> **ON GUARD**: You raise your weapons or arms into a defensive stance, ready to make it harder to hit you. While in this stance, you have a **-2 [Nerf]** to **[Strife]** rolls, but enemies have a **-2 [Nerf]** to **[Physical]** rolls against you. You can\'t roll LET\'S STRIFE next turn.\r\n\r\n> **ATTACK!**: You surge forward, leaving yourself open to attack but doing some serious damage too. While in this stance, you have a **+2 [Buff]** to **[Strife]** rolls, but enemies have a **+2 [Buff]** to **[Strife]** rolls against you. \r\n\r\n> **STRAIGHTEN UP**: Oh, okay, we\'re entering debate mode. Got it got it got it. Ahem; BITCH? You become **[Supercilious]** until you roll LET\'S STRIFE again.\r\n\r\n> **CHARGE**: WRAAAAAUGH! You ram into the target! You can make two **[Strife]** rolls per turn in this form, but the second one is **[Inept]**.'),
('mascotMania', 'MASCOT MANIA', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Passive][Locked: Jock]', 'Every school has a mascot; to you, they are a symbol of everything you stand for. The reason you fight; the reason you WIN. THIS SLAM DUNK IS FOR YOU, SNAZZLORD SOPHIKUS! Select the school you are attending; you gain the associated benefit when you are in combat, and the listed colours for your sports kits.\r\n\r\n> **Cullscout Superior\'s School For Incorrigible Scamps**: THE MISSUSTAUR. You hate the Missustaur! She\'s this douchey minotaur who wears formal wear and reminds you of the rules of the game as toy play! Fuck her! When you roll an **OK** or lower **[Chicanery]** roll against someone, your next one is **[Tiered Up]**. You wear Greys and Blues.\r\n\r\n> **Soulglimmer\'s College of the Indisputably Beautiful Arts**: MADAM SWANNTRO. This absolutely beautiful swan mascot reminds you to look great and never look ugly while you play! You may purchase two Fashion Items for the price of one, and no matter the item, you can always rework it to look like your sports uniform. You wear Whites and Blues.\r\n\r\n> **Sweetlace\'s School of Exceptional Dances and Performance**: LADY SWEETLACE. This goat ballerina spins in approval during all your matches. You like to spin too! Your FRAYMOTIF rolls use **+GRT**! You wear Cyans and Blues.\r\n\r\n> **The Caegerkrieg Monopolist Institute**: DOCTOR HEAVYPOCKETS. A flexing bear in a business suit, Doctor Heavypockets rewards you well when you win! After every **[Strife]** you win, you gain **1 LUX**. You wear Gold and Blues. \r\n\r\n> **Lord Armourdent\'s University of Larpic Warfare**: PIGGUSTUS LARD. The oldest of all the mascots, legend says this mighty swine invented Sportsball when he carved out his own bladder and blew it up like a balloon to make the very first brawlball. His sacrifice reminds you to never show weakness; you are immune to the **[Floorbound]** and **[Trapped]** conditions. You wear Blacks and Blues.\r\n\r\n> **The Honorable Theodact’s Royal Military Academy**: SNAZZLORD SOPHIKUS. This mighty two headed Snazzard wants no gold, no prisoners; only VICTORY! You may become **[Enraged]** as an action. You wear Silvers and Blues.\r\n\r\n> **The Pondermuse Seminary for Theoretical Existence**: BRAINBULB THE MIGHTY. It\'s a giant floating brain, and it loves you more than your own lusus. Whenever you roll PROBLEM SLEUTHING, you gain **1 [Boost]** from your mascot\'s approval. You wear Pinks and Blues.\r\n\r\n> **Whisperwind\'s Phrontistery for Students of the Naturally Dubious**: AN UNKNOWABLE MASS OF FLESH AND TENTACLES. What a scamp! You can\'t look at your mascot, because doing so makes your brain short circuit, but it\'s fine! You have **1 [Resistance]** against **[Psychic]** damage. You wear Lilacs and Blues.'),
('maskOfYourOwnFace', 'MASK OF YOUR OWN FACE', 'HEART', 'HEART', '[Aspect][Passive][Unlock: Heart]', 'Identity is very important to you, and you’re very particular about how you portray yourself to other people. Whether it\'s as a furry roleplayer, a megavillain, or an online memelord, you work hard at cultivating a specific identity for yourself. Choose a new **[Talent]** based on your identity. You get this in addition to your original **[Talent]**. When you take this move, however, you lose interest in pursuing things unrelated to your persona, losing 1 stat point permanently.'),
('masterOfAllMinds', 'MASTER OF ALL MINDS', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Ultra][Flourish][Psionic][Locked: Mastermind]', 'Your mind control is beyond the grasp of the posers beneath you.  Where others struggle to control lone trolls, you can amass a posse of obedient flies ensnared in your web, weaving in other trolls simply by having them be in your presence. All in all, you\'ve got a LOT of people under your sway at any one time. You gain access to HERO MODE through your INCREDIBLE IMAGINATION. You have crowds of trolls in your psionic speed dial, ready to pull them in to aid you at a moment\'s notice. You get the following effects you may use with FREAKY EYE; these effects do not target the opponent, but rather your crowds of hapless servants. Each of these effects can only be used once, so choose wisely! On a **GREAT**, they don\'t activate FREAKY EYE’s **[Recharge]**, and on a **MAX**, you reset the options used so you can activate any all over again. Opponents may choose to target the crowd rather than you; in this case, it takes **2 damage** to remove a random option from you. You do not take this damage.\r\n\r\n> **SING YOUR PRAISES**: You gain **2 [Boost]** as people cheer you on.\r\n> **SWARM**: You deal +1 damage on your next **[Strife]** roll as your opponent is held in place.\r\n> **WEB UP**: Your opponent takes **3 [Drag]** as the crowd literally begins to drag them down.\r\n> **BODY SHIELD**: You gain **2 [Somatic]** **[Resistance]** against the next damage you take.\r\n> **CHEER**: You **[Heal]** 2 damage as the crowd lifts your spirits and tells you you\'re great.\r\n> **SEEK**: FIND THEM! You search out a **[Hidden]** troll automatically.\r\n> **BOO**: HISSSS! Your opponent\'s **[Mental]** rolls are **[Godawful]** for **2 turns**.\r\n> **TROLLISH PYRAMID**: This gives you the effects of **[Flying]** for **3 turns** as you walk atop their bodies.'),
('masticate', 'MASTICATE', 'OTHER', 'SHADOWDROPPER', '[Template][Basic][Eerie][Physical][Strife][Locked: Shadowdropper]', 'YOU EVER SEE A TROLL THROW THEIR SKULL AT SOMEONE AND BITE DOWN? NO? YOU WANNA? You disconnect your head from your shoulders and hurl it at the opponent to chomp the fuck down! This acts as a RANGEDKIND weapon. When you want to fuckin\' GNASH, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: AAAAAAAAAAAAAUuuuurrrgh- you fucking miss, and your head is lost for a while. You are unable to make any **[Mental]** rolls, you are **[Blinded]**, and you can\'t use this move again for the rest of the encounter.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: OWCH! You hit a wall! That hurt! You take **1 [Somatic]** damage. \r\n\r\n**OK**: You miss, but your head rolls back in a timely manner.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: SCREEEE!!! Your head lands, bites, and does **1 [Somatic]** damage. It then falls off and rolls back to you.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Oh, you dig in DEEP, huh? You bite down as your head lands, and holds on. The opponent takes **2 [Somatic]** damage, and until they take an action to pry your head off, they take **1 [Somatic]** damage a turn as you chomp. You are **[Slowed]** until your head is returned.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Your teeth push in deep enough to touch bone. Fucking OUCH! You get a Great, but removing your head is a **[Lengthy]** action and the opponent is **[Bloodied]** as soon as they pull your teeth out.\r\n\r\n'),
('matripreacher', 'MATRIPREACHER', 'JADE', 'ADULT', '[Jade][One-Off][Locked: Adult]\r\nPrerequisites: Cloistered Jade', 'Occasionally, the Grandmother Grub will birth a Holy Virgin Mother Grub, which carry Matriorbs within themselves. These Mother Grubs are taken to the Jade Planet of Solitude in secrecy, acting as the last resort should the worst happen to Her and Her children on the Breeding World. As a Cloistered Nun that personally attends to and serves these divine grubs you have learned to call upon their power more directly, channeling it through a SACRED MATRIORB. As the product of a divine creature as well as a vital tool for restoring the trollic people from the brink of destruction, it is extremely powerful and highly important. Wielding this makes you **[Brave]** and gives you a +2 **[Buff]** to your **[Magic]** rolls. If you are ever hit with a **MAX [Strife]** roll, roll a 1d8. On a 1 or 2, the SACRED MATRIORB is destroyed. You lose your benefits and all trolls become **[Scared]**. No no no no no not like this, NOT LIKE THIS...'),
('mavenMonstrocity', 'MAVEN MONSTROCITY', 'OTHER', 'BEAST_BRAWLER', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Beast Brawler]', 'NO I\'M NOT A FURRY! STOP! IT\'S A SURVIVAL TACTICS OF NATURE’S CREATURES AND NECESSARY TO MY JOB, I SWEAR! Through your adventures, you’ve learned the natural behaviors of beasts and their methods of survival and you can almost perfectly mimic them to your advantage. Which to be frank.. is very freakish. You may choose one of the following beasts and gain the following move from it. See (17b: Monsters) \r\n\r\n> **EXORPHIAN**: You cover yourself in muck and jarred exorphian mucus! Gross! You gain MLEM.\r\n\r\n> **HONKDEMON**: You’ve studied the impish habits of the honkdemon, and in the process have learned how to charm people easily. You gain TO-DO LIST. \r\n\r\n> **CARNIVOROUS MOOCREATURE**: You cover your weapons in moocreature milk! You weirdo. You gain MAD-COW DISEASE. \r\n\r\n> **PURRBEAST**: Hewwo :3 You’ve learned how to be agile and sneaky like the adorable purrbeast, much like the most iconic members of the olive caste. You gain STEALTHY STALKER.\r\n\r\n> **BARKFIEND**: You’re just a furry. Sorry. You gain AROOOOOO; this has a **RECHARGE: 2** for you.'),
('mcatlikeReflexes', 'MCAT-LIKE REFLEXES', 'OTHER', 'DOCTERROR', '[Template][Advanced][Reaction][Recharge: 2][Heal][Locked: Docterror]', 'You’re actually getting to the point where calling yourself a docterror doesn’t trigger a raging bout of laughter or imposter syndrome. You’re good at this! You can help people! You may roll any **[Heal]** move as a **[Reaction]**, intervening when a player would go unconscious or take a particularly debilitating effect before it can do any damage.'),
('meanGreenGardenerFromOuterSpace', 'MEAN GREEN GARDENER FROM OUTER SPACE', 'OTHER', 'HORTICULLTURIST', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Horticullturist]', 'Maybe you collect flesh-eating succulents or tend to a blindly malevolent orchard. Maybe you have cute little flowers in pots that don’t do anything harmful, like some kind of edgy goth weirdo. No matter what kind of plants you collect, you collect them, and odds are you have a favorite type. Choose one type of garden from the list below:\r\n\r\n> **BEESKNEEZER**: Your specialty isn\'t flesh-eating monstrosities or anything like that! You focus on pollinating the environment. You gain access to the items listed in the BEEKEEPER Gold Tree entry. If you already have access to it, you can purchase them for **1 VP** less (min. 1).\r\n\r\n> **HERBALLIST**: Back! Back, I say! You? You actually fucking HATE plants. You hunt them down, from little baby Herocrunchers, to… maybe MARBORASSQUALE, one day! You are immune to **[Poison]**, and your attacks against Plant monsters get a **+1 [Buff]**.\r\n\r\n> **PLANTWHISPERER**: Shhhh… shhh… rockabye seedling, in the plant pot… you\'ve spent your whole life around plants, and speaking to them is as simple as communicating with other trolls- hell, maybe it\'s easier! You can **[Manipulate]** and **[Analyze]** plant monsters as normal. On a **MAX** roll of either type against a plant, you gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **GREENGROSSER**: Money doesn\'t grow on trees, but with the way you live, it may as well! You sell plants, whether it’s pretty bouquets for quadbonding ceremonies or beebombs for goldbloods in a tight spot. Your **VP** increases by 2, because you need so much extra room to carry around your products. \r\n\r\n> **SAGESAGE**: You grow healing herbs and tasty vegetables for trolls who need a bite to eat! You and your allies\' rolls to fight off **[Afflictions]** and **[Hazards]** are at a **+2 [Buff]**. The latter **[Buff]** only applies to nature-related **[Hazards]**- knowing about plants won\'t help you escape from a dronestrike.\r\n\r\n> **LANDSCATHER**: For you, it\'s all about the aesthetic. Who cares if this plant represents death? What does it matter? You just want things to look pretty. HIVECRAFTING UPGRADES cost **1 LUX** less for you.\r\n\r\n> **BIOTRAMPLER**: Why don\'t you go hoe some BITCHES?! You\'re a big fan of the symbolism and unique language that comes with flowers. You can **[Strife]** with WORDPLAY even after the battle has begun, although it deals **[Psychic]** damage instead of **[Verbal]** as you annoy them with ridiculous facts.\r\n\r\n> **ROCKLOVER**: This template is about plants- oh. Oh, no, you really want to take this. Okay. Well, that\'s your problem, not mine. You gain access to the following WORDPLAY effect because you\'re just sooo special and outside the box.\r\n\r\n> **GEOWHATEVERIST**: Yeah, I\'m a geobiologist! You know, like... pet rocks in little pots and stuff! Soil cover has to come from somewhere! You can make an opponent **[Embarrassed]** for one turn as they\'re forced to sit there all uncomfortable listening to your rambling, but they can choose to take **[Enraged]** when it wears off. SHUT! THE FUCK! UPPPPPPP!!!! YOU\'RE USING THE TEMPLATE WROOOOOONG!!!!'),
('mechaantics', 'MECHA-ANTICS', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Recharge: 2][Chicanery][Tech][Locked: Pilot]', 'Look, dude, let\'s be real. You\'re in a motherfucking mecha. And everyone else isn\'t. And to be frank, if they DO have one, their motherfucking mecha probably sucks bulge compared to you. Empowered by your pride, you kick ass inside this thing. When you want to kick butt from inside your Mecha, roll **+HUB**. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: You hit the self-destruct button by accident. Your Mecha will explode and do **10 damage** to you if you\'re still inside by the start of your next turn. Uh oh.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Nobody\'s impressed by your toy robot, dude. You take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You don\'t pull off whatever you were trying, but that\'s okay. :)\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Outplayed, bitch! Choose one of the following options:\r\n\r\n> **PROPERTY DAMAGE**: Piloting a giant robot through streets designed for trolls sometimes leads to some issues… like rubble, **[Trapping]** an opponent! \r\n\r\n> **CACKLE**: WAHAHA! I AM THE ONE IN A MECH! MEEEEE! You give the opponent **2 [Drag]**, because they feel inadequate.\r\n\r\n> **FLICK**: You just kinda… knock \'em over. So easy when you\'re this big… they become **[Floorbound]**.\r\n\r\n> **GOUTS-A-FLAME**: PSCCHHWWWWEEEWWW. You set the target **[Ablaze]**. This is a **[One-Off]** effect.\r\n\r\n> **ZAP**: KZZZZTCKHK! You **[Overwhelm]** the opponent for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **SMACK DOWN**: Get outta the sky, fool! You whack a **[Flying]** opponent. They stop **[Flying]**, take **1 [Drag]**, and can\'t **[Fly]** again for **1 turn**. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Heh. Done like a pro. Not a surprise, considering how awesome you are. You get a **GOOD**, but the opponent takes **1 [Drag]**, and you get **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You probably pop out of your mech for a moment to laugh. LAUGH at the opponent. That\'s how funny this is. You get a **GREAT**, but It\'s **3 [Boost]** and **[Drag]**, not 1.'),
('mechanicalMan', 'MECHANICAL MAN', 'OTHER', 'ROBOT', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Robot]', 'Whether it be through self-modification, or the literal need to become a mech to keep living, you have delved into the world of robotics. Not making them, mind you, but becoming them. You gain the **[Mechanical]** tag, as even the smallest step into this world permanently alters the way you’re wired. Literally, probably. Upon taking this move, choose an option below based on what kind of robot you are. This template can not be taken with **[Eerie]** templates. All of the options below can have more than three PROSTHETICS at a time.\r\n\r\n> **ROBOT: Nothing fancy or wild going on here. No haunted machine, and no limb enhancement surgery needed- You’re just a basic ass bot. Whether made in a factory with state of the art technology, or just some bronze’s passion project, the bottom line is, you’re made of pure metal, wires, and caste-colored oilblood. While you may take a caste tree as normal, you lose access to any **[Psionic]** or **[Magic]** your caste would otherwise have access to. In exchange, all **[Psionic]** and **[Magic]** effects that target the mind, such as Cerulean FREAKY EYE or Purple CHUCKLETERRORS instead **[Stun]** you as you don’t really have a mind to control. Being stunned like this has a **[Recharge: 3]** for you.  \r\n\r\n> Additionally, there\'s also cases where robots are...well, built different, we\'ll say. Specifically, their oilblood is not regulation color! If you want, you may have the Type One SUBCASTE or CUSPBLOOD Mutations as the oilblood you have is tweaked and modified to be wacky and wild. How? Who knows! Maybe not even you! You\'re just the robot with weird candy red blood. Which is, by the way, still SUPER **[Cullbait]** if you\'re Subcaste. Hate the sin and the sinner, as they say. \r\n\r\n> **SOULBOT**: So you died. Oh well. The end. Game over. Burn your character sheet because there’s no second chances here. …Okay, fine. If you were a troll of a **[Psionic]** caste (Rust, Bronze, Gold, Lime, Cerulean, or Purple), you may be eligible for financial compensation. And that just means your ghost gets to inhabit a robot body now! You must now use 1’s and 0’s in your quirk, instead of L’s and O’s. You retain the ability to use **[Psionic]** moves from your caste, though your new mechanical hull leaves you.. Lacking in the emotions department. You can choose to not feel a **[Heightened]** **[Emotion]** as a **[One-Off]**. 0_0 \r\n\r\n> Thanks to their ability to pass as a simple automaton to avoid upsetting the normalcy the Empire cares about-- and being able to make particularly loud highbloods be a little more quiet about the longevity of their quadrants, Soulbots do not count as **[Eerie]** or **[Cullbait]**, although Cloistered Jades and practicing members of the Mirthful Church do not differentiate between the undead floating around and the undead possessing metal and are unlikely to have anything nice to say about you. Just don\'t leave your robot body. Ever. Or the Bustin\' Division will be on your ghost ass.\r\n\r\n> **CYBORG**: You head to the doc and they look you over and prescribe you one heaping dose of a new arm. Good job, moron. You got your shit rocked so hard you no longer have a heart. You automatically take this **[Template]** option if you ever have more than two PROSTHETICS attached. Because of your sick metal limbs, you can reduce incoming damage by 1 as a **[Free] [Reaction]**. This can’t make the damage 0. This is a **[One-Off]** ability- Don’t want to scratch up your cool parts too bad!\r\nAlso, you know how this template is called \'Robot\' and it says \'no **[Eerie]** templates can be taken\' and stuff like that? Well...for as many wires and metal plates and maybe even life-saving implements you have bolted into your body, you\'re still a living, breathing, bleeding thing. There\'s still a soul in this body, surrounded by technology. You\'re just as alive as everyone else, and just like everyone else, you can be changed. You can be corrupted and turned into something monstrous...but you can still be reasoned with, taught to control yourself, \'saved.\' You aren\'t metal installed into flesh, you are metal AND flesh, working in tandem to power a machine of life. With this option, you can still take **[Eerie]** templates as long as it\'s not Ghost because. I mean did you not just read what I said there? About all the flesh and stuff? Yeah.\r\n'),
('medalCollector', 'MEDAL COLLECTOR', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'CULLSCOUT', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Cullscout]', 'Prerequisite: Must be Indigo.\r\n\r\nMedals! They prove your worth to everyone around you! That\'s why you\'ve got SO DARN MANY! Where did you get them? From the CULLSCOUTS! Your duty is to prove that highbloods are invincible and incredible, and you do that, again, by collecting MEDALS. You have conditional authority over all non-ORG trolls, as long as you can justify your orders as ORG related. Drones will not target you while in your ORG uniform, which you now gain for free as well as a flair on all social media. Every time you roll a **MAX** on a move, you earn a MEDAL. This MEDAL proves you\'re the best and greatest at what you do, so get out of the way, cuz you ROCK. You can\'t get a MEDAL for the same move twice, so track what MEDALS you\'ve earned. You get special benefits for how many MEDALS you\'ve earned.\r\n\r\n> **0 MEDALS**: You have to prove yourself! Your **[Tier Up]** effects **[Tier Up]** even to a **MAX**.\r\n> **1 MEDAL**: Yes! You\'ve proved you\'ve got it! You lose your 0 MEDAL effect, but instead gain **+1 HP**.\r\n> **5 MEDALS**: You\'re on your way now! You can become **[Hopeful]** as an action.\r\n> **8 MEDALS**: YEAH! That\'s an IMPORTANT NUMBER. You start every encounter with **2 [Boost]**.\r\n> **12 MEDALS**: LOOKING RIIIIIIPPED. You gain **+1 HP**. For every **6 MEDALS** you gain from here on out, you gain an extra **+1 HP**.\r\n\r\n'),
('medicalMalpractice', 'MEDICAL MALPRACTICE', 'OTHER', 'DOCTERROR', '[Template][Basic][Strife][It\'s Not Like You Had Insurance Anyway][Locked: Docterror]', 'Whoopsies, did I cut the wrong tube? Oh no, oh grub, well that’s just such a shame- oopsie! There goes your sacral nerve! Messy. Well not to worry, shitting yourself is normal in this kind of procedure! If you so choose, after SUCCESSFULLY rolling for EMT Training, you can take the opposite result (removing the **[Heal]** tag from this use of EMT Training, and allowing you to use another **[Heal]** move on the same turn if you so choose). A **MAX** becomes a **MIN**, a **GREAT** becomes a **BAD**, a **GOOD** deals **1 [Somatic]** damage to the target. Let’s do some damage with those physiological charts you memorized, hm?'),
('meekWords', 'MEEK WORDS', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Ummm… have you considered being nice and kind, maybe..? Please? You know you aren\'t necessarily going to kick any asses with your pitiful lowblood self, but maybe you can use the power of communication to help you out! You gain the following WORDPLAY effects.\r\n\r\n> **BEG**: NNNOOOO, PLEASE, I’M JUST A RUST BLOOD, I WON’T DROP ANY GOOD LOOT, PLEASE SPARE MEEEE! Your opponent feels kinda bad for you, and their next **[Strife]** roll is **[Inept]**. On a **GREAT**, it\'s **[Godawful]**, and on a **MAX**, it\'s also **[Tiered Down]**.\r\n\r\n> **MAKE EXCUSES**: It\'s not your fault! Honest! It was… that guy! Over there! You point and make excuses, **[Confusing]** the target for **2 turns**.  \r\n\r\n> **NEENER NEENER**: BWEEEEEH! Screw being meek! You say some disrespectful shit instead! Your target is **[Enraged]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **SNIFFLE**: You start… crying, oh my god. Ugh. That’s pathetic, and also super manipulative and crafty. The opponent’s moves that disable or negatively affect **[Manipulate]** rolls are disabled for **3 turns**.'),
('meetTheTeam', 'MEET THE TEAM', 'OTHER', 'NADS', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: NADS]\r\n', 'What rebellion would be complete without the scrappy bands of rebel pals trying to make a difference? You can add up to 3 other characters with this move to your Team. When you take this move, choose one of your [Talents] to determine your Team Role; a Team can have multiples of the same roll, of course, since you’re basically just a friendgroup with a shared interest in rebellion.\r\n\r\n> **+HUB, +PLC**: You’re not their leader, you’re their FRIEND! There is a big difference. Either way, as a **[One-Off]**, FRIENDLEADERS can make any one SWASHBUCKLE or WORDPLAY roll as a RALLYING CRY - any benefits from that roll that would affect at least one member of the Team are spread to all members of the Team present.\r\n\r\n> **+APP, +GRT**: You’re the strong one. The HEAVYRUMBLER. Or maybe you’re just greedy, but like, in a Greed from Troll FMAB way where you care deeply for your found family. Either way, you can take a hit - and take one for those that can’t, too. As a **[Reaction]**, you can take a single instance of **[Somatic]** damage for another member of your Team, jumping in front of an attack as inspirational anime BGM plays in the background.\r\n\r\n> **+GRA, +RAS**: Keeping an eye out for trouble’s more important than ever now, and you’re just the RUMPUSSCOUT to do it. When you’re in an encounter with other members of your Team, you and your Team-mates can roll LET’S STRIFE to ORDER UP using your +GRA OR +RAS stats and talents as you give them a timely heads-up.\r\n\r\n> **+PSP, +IMG**: MEDIC! Wait, no, you are the MEDIC now. Technically. ALLEYMEDIC is the correct term. You’ve watched a ten-minute video on how to use a first aid kit, you’ve got this. You can roll the EMT TRAINING Docterror move with your choice of **+PSP** OR **+IMG** on another member of your Team. If you were already a Docterror, you get a **+1 [Buff]** to rolling EMT TRAINING on your Team-mates.\r\n'),
('megapunch', 'MEGAPUNCH', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Recharge: 2][Physical][Strife][Locked: Boss]', 'You did not get to where you are today by being nice. You got here by being EXTREMELY good at destroying any opposition to your command. Yes, all Indigos pack a good punch… but the way you throw yours is just awe-inspiring! When you want to punch someone into next week, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You throw ALL your weight into this single blow, and when you miss, that weight SLAMS your fist into a wall! You might not show it externally, but MAN THAT HURTS? A single tear goes down your face, and you take **2 [Somatic]** damage and **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You punch the wall, but in a kinda badass way anyway? You do **1 [Somatic]** damage to yourself.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You barely miss, and it’s enough to make the target shit themselves a little. They take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You sock ‘em GOOD, and it HURTS! The target takes **1 [Somatic]** damage and **2 [Drag]**. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: A devastating blow! You SLAM your target in the gut, and it makes them wheeze in pain. They take **2 [Somatic]** damage and are **[Stunned]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: That Finishing Zoom from when you score a killing blow in Ultra Thrash Hatchmates happens in real life; there’s a spark, a sound effect, and a slow-mo zoom before your punch WHOLLOPS the target flying. You might have broken something, frankly? Your target takes **3 [Somatic]** damage and is **[Slowed]** for **two rounds**. You take **2 [Drag]** too, because that shit isn’t easy!'),
('mercy', 'MERCY', 'TIME', 'TIME', '[Aspect][Advanced][Free][One-Off][Locked: Time]', 'Sometimes, you can tell a fight isn’t worth fighting anymore. Your target is clearly distressed about something, and you’re not a monster. When an opponent\'s below half **HP** and you get the sense you should stop whooping your opponent’s ass, you can lower your weapon and offer to listen to their problems. They can either accept, and give you the benefits of a **MAX** PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll as they spill their feelings and hardships to you and finish the fight there, or they can refuse to give up. If they refuse, you gain **3 [WHAM]**, and you can choose for all your damage to be **[Non-Lethal]** for the rest of the encounter as you resolve to make this quick, and put them down. Maybe you’ll offer them a gummy worm or something when they’re a little calmer.'),
('mercyForTheMirthless', 'MERCY FOR THE MIRTHLESS', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Passive]', 'Hey… this fucker is clearly outmatched. They\'re terrified, they\'re beaten up, and… this doesn\'t feel like a challenge anymore. It just feels excessive. You\'ve made friends outside of your caste, and have come to realize that despite the teachings of the Church, every soul you meet is their own person. Maybe… you don\'t gotta finish them off. You can offer someone MERCY if they\'re at **4 HP** or lower, and you have at least **6 HP**. The target can choose to accept your offer, and join you, giving you a **[Hold]** you can use for a **MAX** WORDPLAY roll on them that you can keep indefinitely until you spend it. If your MERCY is refused, you gain **1 [WHAM]**. They had their chance.'),
('metagamingMaster', 'METAGAMING MASTER', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Ultra][Recharge: 2][Magic][Psionic][Locked: Metagamer]', 'Your power has grown to such heights that you can affect the world beyond the Fourth Wall as much as it affects you. When people say your name out there, you hear it, and your metaknowledge approaches near omniscience. But it\'s more than that— you know how to change your very fundamentals. It\'s so simple: your mind, body and soul, all your attributes… they\'re all stored in writing in one single place. Your character sheet. You don\'t understand it exactly, but you know that by focusing on this pinpoint of existence— this soul— you can change basically anything about you. You gain access to HERO MODE through your INCREDIBLE IMAGINATION. Your psionics can reach out and alter your very being (though the effect this has on your actual body and mind are minimal; consider it more like skewing your luck). You may use the following effects as an action; these changes last until you change them again, even after the encounter ends.\n\n> 1. Swap 2 of your stats around.\n> 2. Change your Strife Abstrata.\n> 3. Buy a new item.\n> 4. Level up.\n> 5. Swap out a move with an equivalent substitute (Replace caste basic with caste basic, advanced aspect with advanced aspect, etc) that you have access to.\n> 6. Retcon parts of your backstory.\n> 7. Remove a condition.\n> 8. Add a condition (for emotions, this must be a base emotion).'),
('metaphorically1984', 'METAPHORICALLY 1984', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'HET', '[Template][Advanced][Recharge: 3][Control][Tech][Locked: HET]', 'Turn your eyes to the screen! Everywhere on Alternia, there are screens. Computers, TVs, billboards, even the camera lenses. Everything can be turned to a makeshift mind control station in a pinch. Although taking **3 Damage** total or being ZAPPED will likely snap them out of it pretty fast, and the Empire has yet to figure out how to force **[Cullbait]** or other criminals to out themselves to certain death. When you want to turn the full might of the Empire\'s artifimindcontrol on an unsuspecting target, roll **+PLC**\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You looked at the screen yourself, you fool! You fall victim to your own message that you were about to inflict, and take **3 [Drag]** from the guilt of somehow forgetting to close your eyes.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: That trick doesn\'t work if you telegraph it, dumbass. \r\n\r\n**OK**: They tear their eyes away before it can sink in. The swirling graphic is a pretty obvious deal, actually.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: They stared at it a moment too long! Send a message to rewrite the target\'s beliefs for **three turns**, from \'you are vocally supportive of violets\' to \'you want to buy so much expensive stuff right now\'. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: That was amplified! Send a message to rewrite the target\'s beliefs for the rest of the encounter, from \'you are Empire supportive\' to \'you are a secret ORG plant that just had their hidden training activated\'\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You... you can stop staring. It\'s kind of creepy to keep staring at the mind control screen, guy. Send a message to rewrite a target\'s beliefs to whatever you deem fit at the moment, lasting until they are snapped out of it one way or another.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('metayoink', 'METAYOINK', 'OTHER', 'ROGUE', '[Class][Advanced][Magic][Locked: Rogue]', 'Life isn\'t fair! Subjugation, oppression and pain surround you. But does it have to be that way? Sometimes, an act of charity, whether willing or not, can make all the difference. You can help people, and as backwards as it might feel to say it… maybe you have to help yourself… first. Before you can help others. It’s getting harder to steal from the metaphorical rich and give to the metaphorical poor when you’re… the metaphorical poor too, sometimes. Wild? The following list can now be stolen as normal **YOINK** effects for you, depending on your **[Aspect]**, and can be distributed to yourself OR your allies as a **[Free]** action when you do. When you want to use your special little effect, you can roll YOINK with **+RAS, +APP** or **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n> **TIME**: If your enemy becomes **[Quickened]**, you can **YOINK** 1 round worth of their **[Quickened]** on a **GOOD** and 2 rounds worth on a **GREAT**, lessening it for them. On a **MAX** you can completely take the effect from them.\r\n\r\n> **SPACE**: You **YOINK** one of their caste or other extra **[Chicanery]** effects for yourself. They no longer have it for the encounter.\r\n\r\n> **LIFE**: You **YOINK** their **[Heal]** as a **[Reaction]**, to a max of **2 HP**, with the enemy keeping at least 1 **[Healing]** point.\r\n\r\n> **DOOM**: Choose one of their **[Basic]** **[Passive]** effects from a move to **YOINK**. You have that now. Not them. Life sucks, doesn’t it?\r\n\r\n> **HOPE**: You **YOINK** 1 **[Positive]** Emotion for yourself! Ha ha, mood drop!\r\n\r\n> **RAGE**: You may **YOINK** 1 **[WHAM]** from the enemy as a **[Reaction]** before they can use it on you.\r\n\r\n> **BLOOD**: When someone applies a bonus to one of their friends, like giving them a **[Passive]** **[Boost]** from **BROTHERS IN ARMS**, you can roll to **YOINK** it as a **[Reaction]**.\r\n\r\n> **BREATH**: You may roll a **[Reaction]** to **YOINK** a tier off a move your enemy makes- their roll **[Tiers Down]**, and you or an ally gets a **[Tier Up]** **[Hold]**. You can\'t have more than one of these **[Hold]**s at a time. \r\n\r\n> **VOID**: You may **YOINK** a single stat point from an enemy. This cannot be distributed to yourself or others, it just poofs into the void. Kiss your +4 GRT goodbye, sucker!\r\n\r\n> **LIGHT**: You can **YOINK** up to 3 **[Boost]** from an enemy.\r\n\r\n> **HEART**: You **YOINK** someone’s **[Talent]**, friend or foe, and swap it with your own! This cannot be done with **[Legendaries]**.\r\n\r\n> **MIND**: As a **[Reaction]** you can **YOINK** away SOMEONE ELSE’S **[Reaction]** before they get to make it. Kehehe, you were five steps ahead! \r\n\r\n\r\n'),
('meticulouslyCraftedExplosiveDevice', 'METICULOUSLY CRAFTED EXPLOSIVE DEVICE', 'OTHER', 'NADS', '[Template][Advanced][Recharge: 4][Craft][Mental][Locked: NADS]\r\n', 'To call YOUR explosives improvised would be an insult. And as they say, the best insults are the ones rooted in truth. So, uh. Yeah you sure can make some improvised weapons now. It takes a separate action to use any of the 3 VP [Consumable] items created by this move, and if you don’t use them by the end of the encounter, they become useless - you’re not Troll Macgyver, you watched a five-minute Spewtube video on how to make common hivehold chemicals explode. Roll +HUB OR +PSP to bust out some duct tape and put something together!\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Yeah, you blow yourself up. Is anyone surprised by this one? You immediately take the self-inflicted effects of whichever item you would’ve made based on your WEALTH LEVEL.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Wow!! You bought everything at the same department store! Everybody saw this one coming - the move becomes a **[One-Off]** as you’re blacklisted from department stores around the city, and put on several federal watchlists! Why didn’t you heed the advice of our dear mutual friend, Waltuh? If you would have found a crowbar on a **GOOD** or higher, this result instead just becomes an **OK**. Nobody really cares all that much about whatever it is you’re doing.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You sure did just put some parts together! It’s mostly just a WIP, but this move’s only on **[Recharge: 2]** while you figure out what you want to do with it! \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: With everything you’ve cobbled together, you’re able to put together something that vaguely resembles an improvised weapon, building one of the following items based on your WEALTH LEVEL:\r\n\r\n> **DESTITUTE**: It’s a pipe bomb. You can throw this at pretty much anyone and it’d do something catastrophic. Using it deals **2 [Somatic]** Damage and renders the target **[Deafened]** for **2 turns**!\r\n\r\n> **POOR, DECENT**: This is a crowbar. You didn’t make this. This isn’t an improvised weapon, you just found this lying around somewhere. ‘Using’ it to bash someone’s kneecaps deals **1 [Somatic]** Damage to the target and makes them **[Clumsy]** for **2 turns**. This is still **[Consumable]** - if you want to hit someone with a crowbar that badly, just use CROWBARKIND.\r\n\r\n> **AVERAGE, WELL-OFF**: Oh, huh. This... this is just a bomb. No pipe is involved whatsoever. It’s kind of just dangerous honestly. Using it deals **2 [Somatic]** Damage to everyone in the encounter, yourself included, and makes them **[Bloodied]**.\r\n\r\n> **RICH, ULTRARICH**: It’s a pipe bomb... with the Troll Supreme logo on it. This is worth more caegars than most rusts will ever see in one place. Somehow it’s actually worse than a regular pipe bomb though?? Using it deals **1 [Somatic]** Damage and makes the target **[Confused]** for **1 turn** if they have a lower WEALTH LEVEL than you, as they try to wrap their head around how much money you just wasted.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: This doesn’t just resemble an improvised weapon, it IS one. You take the effects of a **GOOD** and additionally become **[Proud]** for **2 turns** as you flex your cool new DIY project that is also a bomb. If you found a crowbar, you only get **1 [Boost]**. Good for you I guess.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Holy shit you made two bombs at once. Or, uh, found two crowbars, which is a lot less impressive but look it’s better than nothing. You gain the extra bonus from a **GREAT**, and make two of the item from your WEALTH LEVEL; they still only take up one **3 VP** space in your inventory until both are used.\r\n'),
('miCasaEsSuCasa', 'MI CASA ES SU CASA', 'OTHER', 'ROGUE', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Rogue]', 'Even if you come into possession of wealth, your thoughts are never those of enriching yourself, but rather aiding others. As such, you insist that other people make use of your fortune. Friends, please use my garage! My pool! Raid my fridge, I insist! Up to four people you deem close to you- whether it be a friend, a quadrant, a hatchmate, or someone else- can benefit from any hive upgrade you have, and roll **[Downtime]** as if they own that upgrade themselves.\r\n\r\n\r\n'),
('midbloodMediocrity', 'MIDBLOOD MEDIOCRITY', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive]', 'Prerequisite: Must be an Oliveblood, Jadeblood or Tealblood.\n\nBetter to barf in the shower than to shower in the barf. Wouldn\'t you agree, Enpece Trolid? Sometimes, not sticking out is the best thing you can do. When you would get a **BAD** roll, you can **[Tier Up]** to an **OK** for **[Free]**; but you take a number of **[Drag]** equal to the difference between your original roll and the **OK** roll result you now find yourself with.'),
('middlingMidblood', 'MIDDLING MIDBLOOD', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Nothing special. Good but not great. Kinda whatever. You\'ve been told your whole life that you\'re just kind of average. Now, whether that\'s true for you specifically or just an unfair stereotype pushed onto your caste or the fact that sometimes, you’re just REALLY unlucky doesn’t really matter, but sometimes you can\'t help but wonder if you really are that. Whenever you get an **OK** roll, you gain **1 [Boost]** as you settle for average. Maybe one day, you\'ll be something great…'),
('mightyMount', 'MIGHTY MOUNT', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'No self-respecting Indigo would allow themselves to have anything but the most well trained of custodians, and yours is no exception. Strong, powerful snarlwolves, towering steelstags and of course, the gracious and noble flexquine with its glistening manes and their mighty muscles. You gain the CUSTODIAN COMPANION Perfectly Generic Move, except you can also ride (or be carried) by your custodian as if though it were a Vehicle. Your ATRIACLIZE and VEHICULATE rolls with your custodian both use **+GRA** or **+HUB**, your choice.'),
('mildOrWild', 'MILD OR WILD', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Passive]', 'Olivebloods are a caste of contradictions. They\'re widely considered the normal, every day trolls who make up the majority of cities, while also being the ones most in touch with their bestial nature. This is true even in situations you mightn\'t expect; an Olive living in a cavehive in the jungle might be perfectly domestic, but the one sending you violent death threats on Grumblr… probably isn\'t. Select an option from the list below.\r\n\r\n> **DOMESTIC**: What a pussycat! You\'re fully tamed, a perfectly polite kitty who is comfortable with others thinking you\'re cute and harmless. It\'s cuz you are! When you go first in an encounter, you can choose to make it a WORDPLAY encounter, meaning all trolls can only use JAB to **[Strife]**, and can\'t make **[Physical]** rolls. Let\'s be civil!\r\n\r\n> **FERAL**: SCRATCHA YOU! CLAW CLAW CLAW! You aren\'t some lameass kittypet, drinking the highblood milk left out to placate you! You\'re RUDE! You\'re NASTY! You like running around and causing trouble! Teeheehee! **[Manipulate]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**. Nobody\'s taming YOU!'),
('mindOverMatter', 'MIND OVER MATTER', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Recharge: 3][Psionic][Locked: Psychic]', 'Did you know you could do more with your powers than just smash stuff?  Like man, that thing sure is on a high shelf, lemme just go get a ladder and- SCREW THAT I CAN MOVE THINGS WITH MY MIND. Any time you roll at least a **GREAT** on a **[Psionic]** roll, you begin **[Flying]** as you levitate off the floor. As an action, you can roll any one **[Physical]** move using **+IMG** as you focus your psionics to do it instead of waving and flopping your body around like some sort of casual. This effect has a **[Recharge: 3]** because making sure all that spoon twisting power doesn\'t accidentally twist your spine takes a lot of control!'),
('miracleGro', 'MIRACLE GRO', 'OTHER', 'HORTICULLTURIST', '[Template][Advanced][Lengthy][One-Off][Locked: Horticullturist]', 'You bring your plants with you everywhere you go, and that includes on the battlefield! You can grow a plant to help you in a strife. When you want to call for some extra help, roll **+APP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You whip some seeds out from your sylladex and tenderly plant them in the ground and OH MY GOD HOLY FUCKING SHIT!!!! YOU SUMMONED A CREATURE AND IT HATES YOU! You feel **[Dread]**, and at the start of your next turn, a SPEARSLAUGHTER plant shows up. It’s hostile to everyone in the area.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: OH NO!! OUR PLANT.. IT’S BROKEN…… While you were fumbling around grabbing the seeds out of your pocket, you accidentally crushed one or two of them. You start **[Crying]** and can\'t use this move for the rest of the encounter. \r\n\r\n**OK**: You waste your actions doing fuckall. You can try again next turn.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Now we’re talking! You summon a PLANT MINION with 6 HP and a +1 to all stats. It can only roll UNIVERSAL MOVES. You can spend an action to heal it by **1 HP**, but this is a **[One-Off]**- you can only prune so many dead parts off a plant before it gets too miserable.\r\n\r\n> **MOSS**: Your HP\'s all mossed out! This plant can heal you by **1 HP** as an action… or **2 HP** if you\'re willing to take an action to tear a chunk off and eat it. Rude! This counts as a **[Heal]** effect, and the latter deals **2 [Damage]** to the moss. What did you expect?\r\n\r\n> **ALOE VERA**: Ah, nature\'s medicine! Whenever you would become **[Ablaze]**, you can call out to your plant companion to put you out for **[Free]**. However, every time it does this, it takes **1 [Damage]**.\r\n\r\n> **DANDELION**: Slow and steady wins the race… after three rounds or when the plant hits **0 HP**- whichever comes first- the dandelion bursts into seeds and inflicts all opponents with the SNIFFLES **[Affliction]**. This doesn’t affect **[Mechanical]** enemies.\r\n\r\n> **HUMONGOUS FUNGUS**: There’s fungus among us! As a **[Recharge: 1]**, you can spend a **[Reaction]** to duck behind your plant friend and have it take the damage from an enemy **[Strife]** roll instead of you. How selfish…\r\n\r\n> **RAFFLESIA**: Ugh! This plant is downright… gross!! Anytime an opponent attacks it, they take **1 [Drag]**. If the opponent is hit by a **MAX** **[Physical]** roll by the plant at any point, they become **[Disgusted]**. Oh, god! Get away from me!!\r\n\r\n> **VENUS FLYINGTRAP**: I am a normal plant with jaws and teeth. Go further away from me, I won’t hurt you. This plant can target **[Flying]** enemies with no nerfs, and receives a **+1 [Buff]** to target opponents with this condition.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Yay! You get the effects of a **GOOD**, and it only takes you one action!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Whoa. This is powerful… yeah, you totally meant to do that! You get the effects of a **GREAT**, and the action it takes to heal your plants becomes a **[Recharge: 2]** instead of a **[One-Off]**.'),
('miracleMaker', 'MIRACLE MAKER', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Recharge: 2][Flourish][Magic][Unlock: Honkpostle]', 'The Juggalo Church of the Mirthful Messiahs (Clown Church) is a cult of worship to the unknowable twin clownish gods your faith is named after. It is your goal to know them. You are a devout apostle of your Twin Deities, preaching and praying the silly, violent doctrine of your church, emulating them in your every act. You are **[Talented]** in **+IMG**. When you want to say a quick prayer, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Ah, Crisis of Faith! You take **2 [Psychic]** damage and feel **[Despair]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: The Gods can’t hear you! You feel **[Dread]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You feel some divine energy entering you… keep believing, brother, keep it up! You gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD: The Messiahs are on your side! You gain a boon from those wicked clowns in the carousel in the sky. Choose one of the following options, either for yourself or an ally**:\r\n\r\n> **HOLY POWER**: You gain **1 [WHAM]**.\r\n> **DIVINE INSIGHT**: You get a **GOOD** PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll.\r\n> **THE STRENGTH TO GO ON**: You gain **2 [Boost]**.\r\n> **LOURDES BUT AWESOME**: Remove a Status Effect.\r\n> **MIRACULOUS RECOVERY**: You **[Heal] 1 HP**.\r\n> **SOOTHING PRESENCE**: Remove **1 [Negative]** Emotion.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You pray loudly, and are rewarded for your faith. You get 2 **GOOD** results. You may take options multiple times, or disperse to multiple targets.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: HOSANNA IN THE HIGHEST, BITCHES! You get 3 **GOOD** results as your prayer bolsters to the core!  You may take options multiple times, or disperse to multiple targets.'),
('mirrorTrick', 'MIRROR TRICK', 'OTHER', 'WITCH', '[Class][Basic][Magic][Recharge: 2][Locked: Witch]', 'Turn that frown upside down- or that **MIN**! Turn that **MIN** upside down! Sometimes failure is just another state of victory! When you\'re about to roll something you\'re not quite so amazing at, or hell, when failure is actually looking pretty good right now, declare that you are applying a MIRROR TRICK before you roll. For that one roll, all result tiers are reversed. A **MIN** becomes a **MAX**, a **MAX** becomes a **MIN**, etc.\n\n'),
('mirthraider', 'MIRTHRAIDER', 'PURPLE', 'ADULT', '[Purple][Locked: Adult]', 'The Mirthful Messiahs are a truly territorial duo of gods, and the depths of space have yet to be claimed by their righteous japes and jokes. Alien gods infest the heavens and hells that the endlessly growing Dark Carnival spreads into; and the Paradise Planet has yet to be born from the tendrils of Horrorterrors that corrupt what lies between dreams and reality. As a Mirthraider you have been given the holy duty to strike down all things unholy and vile that threaten the Messiahs, going on an endless crusade with your sibs to raid into alien territory and strike down foes both **[Holy]** and **[Eerie]**. You may always deal both **[Freaky]** and **[Holy]** Energy Damage, shorthanded as **[Freaky/Holy]**. When below half **HP**, the Messiahs imbue you with a righteous fury; allowing you to spend 2 **[Boost]** to add 1 **[Psychic]** Damage as well.'),
('miseryMeat', 'MISERY MEAT', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'If you die, you die. You\'re staring down a mayfly\'s lifespan filled with nothing but servitude and subjugation. You’re kinda burned out on all this constant danger thing, so why bother caring? You can choose to feel **[Numb]** as an action, letting your ennui swim over you. While you have **[Numb]**, all **[Mental]** effects are **[Inept]**, because like… eh… sure, kill you, you guess..?'),
('mishmashAesthetics', 'MISHMASH AESTHETICS', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Passive]', 'Yeah, let\'s see, uhhh… got a vampire slaying kit here… a pile of Cerulean treasure there… what is this, a pipe bomb? You\'ve built up quite the collection of garbage, huh? You have all the riches in the world by now, but you don\'t necessarily care to… curare it, like a violet would? All this money and you\'re still a clown. You can take any move from any caste Indigo and lower, including moves that aren\'t **[Open]**, that give you a new item to purchase with **VP** or **LUX**. These items always cost **1 VP** or **LUX** more than usual, however. You can\'t take other Purple moves through this. You gain one of these moves now. When taking these moves you only gain access to the **VP** or **LUX** options available; you do not gain a **[Talent]**, access to trees or other similar benefits presented in the move.'),
('miskatonicMaster', 'MISKATONIC MASTER', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Esotericist]', 'You know All. At this point, that\'s not even an exaggeration. The sheer amount of tomes you\'ve consumed, the objects you\'ve collected and created, the boundaries you\'ve crossed… yeah, it\'s suffice to say that you\'ve broken the unknowable into an exact science. You gain access to **HERO MODE** through your **PRECISE PERSPICACITY**. If you are a clown and ever take the **CTHONOMANCER** Template, you do not gain the **[Cullbait]** tag thanks to the Church’s protection. If you’re anything else… that’s pretty illegal! What are you doing with those powers! Your library of curiosities has expanded quite significantly; you have **13 VP** instead of 8, though these additional **5 VP** can only be used to carry **[Rare]** items or potions. Finally, you\'ve unlocked true, twisted magic through your implements; when you wield a  relic from SCHOLAR OF SECRETS, you gain a Class **[Entry]** move of your choice from the list below.\r\n\r\n> **AUGURY**: Seer/Mage\r\n> **HEALTH**: Sylph/Witch\r\n> **LUCK**: Heir/Maid\r\n> **MESMERISM**: Rogue/Thief\r\n> **WARDING**: Page/Knight\r\n> **VANQUISHMENT**: Bard/Prince'),
('misplacedPotential', 'MISPLACED POTENTIAL', 'OTHER', 'PAGE', '[Class][Free][Epic Fail][Unlock: Page]', 'You have a complicated relationship with confidence and potential. You either firmly hold that you\'re the most awesome, coolest kid on the block despite your actions to date proving otherwise, or you\'re shatteringly insecure... Despite your actions to date proving otherwise. No matter what you do, though, you\'ll never change your view of yourself- that you know for sure! And look, you\'re willing to prove it! Choose one stat to make permanently **[Inept]**. Any time you get a **GOOD** on a roll with this stat, you get **3 [Boost]**. A **GREAT** on this stat gives you **5 [Boost]** and a **MAX** gives you 10.\r\n\r\n'),
('mixedMuscularArts', 'MIXED MUSCULAR ARTS', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Physical][Chicanery][Locked: Jock]', 'Alongside your usual studies, you have by now learned to combine all sports into one exceptionally dangerous fighting style! Each individual option from this move has a **[Recharge: 3]**. When you want to show off your moves, roll **+GRT**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: CRAMP!!! You take 3 **[Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You fail to pull your target into your grasp, and waste your time trying it.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You don’t do your cool trick, but you DO flex really hard, and you look great. You get **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: WHOLLOP! You pull off a sick move! Choose one of the following effects.\r\n\r\n> **GIRL LOOK AT THAT BODY**: You go to the gym. You look \\*good\\*. You give them your signature wink and a subtle flex, maybe even a \'kachow\'. They are **[Charmed]**. \r\n> **LOW BLOW**: You deck the guy in the bone bulge, and that’s all there is to say on that. The target is **[Stunned]**.\r\n> **BOO**: You pick up a projectile, like a rotten tomato, and hurl it at your opponent. They take **2 [Drag]** as you bean them in the head.\r\n> **SUPLEX CITY**: OVER THE SHOULDER CONCUSSION! The target is **[Tired]** for 2 turns. \r\n> **TACKLE**: You LUNGE for them, knocking them **[Floorbound]**!\r\n> CHAAAAAARGE! You tackle… and you don\'t stop running. You two leave the location you\'re at, entering a new one. Hazards, NPCs, Monsters, etc, do not follow.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: COMBO MOVE! HWUAH! Two at once, baby! Choose two **GOOD** effects.  \r\n\r\n**MAX**: SPORTS! VICTORY! 2016!!! YEAHHHH, BABY, LET\'S GO! 2016!!!!! You can combine three **GOOD** options.'),
('mobyDickReferenceName', 'MOBY DICK REFERENCE NAME', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'ORPHANER', '[Template][Advanced][Locked: Orphaner]', 'Don’t ask about the name, too busy hunting that inflated sharkfoul. Wait, thar it blows! Every Orphaner has that one monster that they failed to catch, that one creature that eludes them. Maybe it’s a specific beast. Maybe it’s just a species they’re particularly bad at fighting. Choose a type of Beast to be your Moby Dick.\r\n\r\n**AQUATICS**: Maybe it’s because they can swim too? You gain a **+1 [Buff]** to all rolls while in the water to make up for it. \r\n\r\n**FLIERS**: Damn flaprats! Stop flapping! Your attacks are unaffected by **[Flying]** opponents, but unless you could hit them ordinarily you gain **1 [Drag]** exerting yourself!\r\n\r\n**WEIRDOS**: Like, Moonbarks? Those are technically under your jurisdiction too. And the floating eyeball jpegs that show up… stuff like that. You can sense when something **[Eerie]** is in the area; including Entity type Monsters.\r\n\r\n**HORSES**: Fuck those things are just freaky!!! You cannot roll below an **OK** when targeting a horse or anything that looks like a horse, like meese. Indigos start Encounters with you with **1 [Drag]**. They can smell your sin.\r\n\r\n**GENERICS**: Generics; also known as those extremely abnormal creatures that appear to be a normal beast like a Slithering Hopfiend, but split in half! Like something that \\*only\\* slithers! Or \\*only\\* hops! What strange creatures. The wide variety means you have to be adaptable; at the start of an Encounter you can subtract a point from one stat to add to another. \r\n\r\n**COLOSSI**: Ah yes, the story everyone knows about. The big bad orphaner thinks they can tussle with a colossus and loses a limb. Happens once a perigee. Almost as common as the ones that die! You pierce **1 [Resistance]** with your attacks on a **[Recharge: 2]**. Just don’t die, badass.\r\n\r\n**TOO COOL TO HAVE ONE**: You lost to a Squeakhopper didn’t you? It’s fine, you don’t have to admit it. You get to start Encounters **[Smug]** at your above average record on hunting. This dissipates the first time you fail a roll a **BAD** or worse.\r\n\r\n'),
('mollycoddle', 'MOLLYCODDLE', 'LIFE', 'LIFE', '[Aspect][Heal][Unlock: Life]', 'Don’t hurt yourself! Play it safe! There’s no point in getting yourself hurt if you can avoid it. You know that the best way to avoid danger is to not put yourself in danger in the first place!! When you use **[Drag]**, instead of lowering your target’s roll result, you can lower incoming damage to you. Their damage is reduced by 1 for every **2 points of [Drag]** they had (min. 1) as you duck out of dangerous positions. On the other hand, you can use your **[Boost]** to **[Heal]** yourself as an action, playing it safe rather than rushing in - this converts **3 [Boost]** into **1 HP**, up to a max of **3 HP [Healed]** at a time.\r\n'),
('moneyCat', 'MONEY CAT', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Free][One-Off][Unlock: Meowchant]\r\n', 'Olive has wares, if you have coin! You are one of many following in the ancient paths of the Olive Merchant, travelling vast expanses of land with a huge bag on your back, seeking to procure rare stuff and sell it for $$$. That, or you have a really nice Greedbay Store that sells cute Kaijuball trading cards. You are **[Talented]** at **+APP**. You also have **10 VP** rather than 8, and have the Well-Off Wealth. You can sell items to people for profit, profit, profit! You may offer someone a chance to PERUSE YOUR WARES. The items you sell continue to take up your own VP, not theirs, until they use or discard the item - keep in touch with your customer base! You gain a Treasure level equal to the amount of VP they spent. If the item you are selling is a **[Big Buy]**, you gain an additional Treasure level. It doesn\'t count as a **[Big Buy]** to purchase items outside of a troll\'s normal wealth level from you. This can be done online, or in person, as you prefer; you can\'t sell items that are exclusive to Templates or other move groups, though. You need a Food Handler\'s Permit to sell that, goremand!\r\n'),
('monochromeWaltz', 'MONOCHROME WALTZ', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Advanced][Passive]', 'It may come as a surprise, but a handful of hemoanons are quite skilled at FRAYMOTIFING. After all, Anons have spent sweeps carving out their identities with their communities they’ve found in going gray, and FRAYMOTIFS express this in their purest form. Anonymity doesn\'t have a guideline, so express yourselves as you please! Can you feel the Jazz? Or the beautiful Ballet? How about a Tango? Or maybe some Rock\'n\'Roll? Whatever your style, your deeper sense of self powers up your **FRAYMOTIF** and allows you to choose from these following options.\r\n\r\n> **TIME**: The inevitable future being pushed upon you cannot control your present. You have the strength to break through your given path and forge your own. All opponents gain 1 **[Weakness]** to your **[Strife]** moves.\r\n\r\n> **SPACE**: What you do does matter in the grand scheme of everything, and you have the power to shape what that ‘everything’ looks like. Every turn, you reduce all **[Recharge]** by 1 to a minimum of 1.\r\n\r\n> **LIFE**: You have seized control of your destiny; this life you lead is your own. You separate your **[Boost]** and **[Drag]** into two separate pools, which cannot affect one another.\r\n\r\n> **DOOM**: You’ve spent long enough living by the rules pushed upon you. Time to live by your own code. Anytime an opponent uses **[Tier Down]** on your roll, their immediate next roll is **[Tiered Down]** in retaliation.\r\n\r\n> **HOPE**: You’ve grappled with the ideals that led you to become anon and if they’re worth believing in. In the end? You’ve found the thing you needed to believe in most was yourself. **[Magic]** and **[Control]** moves against you are **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n> **RAGE**: The false identity that this world has forced upon you has been torn down, and left behind only the foundations. From there you can rebuild yourself in a more truthful way. When someone uses **[WHAM]** against you, it instead converts to an equal amount of **[Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> **BREATH**: If people try to hold you down? That’s a bad decision on their part. Because nobody’s going to keep you back from what you want to do or who you want to be. When an opponent gives you **[Drag]**, they receive equal **[Drag]** in return.\r\n\r\n> **BLOOD**: Being a hemoanon rebelling against the stereotype of your blood can be a painful path… But it is not one you must travel alone. You get a **[Free] WORDPLAY** roll at the start of every turn.\r\n\r\n> **LIGHT**: Your importance in this world has been cruelly defined by others for too long. You now know you shine just as brilliantly as anyone else. When an enemy **[Tiers Up]** one of their rolls, you may **[Tier Up]** a roll on your turn as a **[Free]** action.\r\n\r\n> **VOID**: Instead of seeing your lack of presence as a burden, you now see the truth: it is the ability to be anything. Choose a stat. You may use that stat’s modifier on another Universal Move besides **GRIEF**.\r\n\r\n> **HEART**: You realize that you can be the persona you have cultivated unironically. If people won’t accept you, then they’re missing out. When you roll a **GREAT+** result with any stats you have **[Talent]** in, you gain 1 **[Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **MIND**: Instead of letting the infinite choices in front of you paralyze you, you’ve learned to take it all one step at a time. If your enemy gains **[Boost]**, you also gain half that amount of **[Boost]** rounded down. This cannot go lower than 1 **[Boost]** gained.\r\n'),
('moralAlignment', 'MORAL ALIGNMENT', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][Passive][Magic][Locked: Protagonist]', 'People in the real world can be pretty complicated. A good person can do bad things, a rational person can do unpredictable things… but in fiction, it\'s sometimes helpful to tell someone\'s morals with a single glance. Enter the Alignment Chart— Lawful Good, Chaotic Evil, all that good stuff. You are keenly aware of the alignments of yourself and others, and they do too so long as you stay near them. All characters in an encounter with you gain two of the following traits, depending on what their alignment is.\r\n\r\n> **GOOD**: You do +1 **[Psychic]** damage to EVIL characters.\r\n> **EVIL**: You do +1 **[Psychic]** damage to **GOOD** characters.\r\n> **LAWFUL**: You are **[Talented]** at SWASHBUCKLE rolls in the presence of a CHAOTIC character.\r\n> **CHAOTIC**: You are **[Talented]** at SHENANIGANS rolls in the presence of a LAWFUL character.\r\n> **NEUTRAL**: No effect.'),
('moreMedalsThanYou', 'MORE MEDALS THAN YOU', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'CULLSCOUT', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Cullscout]', 'You know when you\'re better than someone. Whenever you get a **MAX** in an encounter, you immediately become **[Smug]**. When someone else gets a **MAX**, you become **[Enraged]**. Look, point is— you\'ve DEFINITELY got more MEDALS than anyone else here, and that\'s what matters!\n\n'),
('moreToGoAround', 'MORE TO GO AROUND', 'OTHER', 'THIEF', '[Class][Advanced][One-Off][Locked: Thief]', 'While stealing things is fun, it’s made you realize something important. If you steal everything, there’s never anything left for anyone else to use. There’s no one to cheer you on and no strong enemies to fight. So maybe when you steal things, you can leave a little for them too. Choose one person in an encounter, ally or enemy. You can gain access to any one **[Open]** move they have as you open the gates to using it a little wider. Sure, it’s yours… but let me in! If this is a rolled move, you both get a +1 **[Buff]** when rolling it as you show each other new ways of doing things. \r\n'),
('morningStarlet', 'MORNING STARLET', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Passive][Unlock: Posh]', 'You\'ve got your whole life ahead of you! A good future, rich family, upper class background… well, you\'d have all that if it weren\'t for this whole Alternia business! The point is, you\'re the kind of kid who once went to dance recitals, math tutelage and violin practice all on the same day. It was a lot of pressure, sure, but coal diamonds and all that. Look at you now! You are **[Talented]** at **+GRA**. You can never accept failure; you are immune to enemy effects that make your rolls **[Inept]** or **[Tiered Down]**. Instead, you take a **-2 [Nerf]** to rolls affected by this. If you succeed in spite of such an effect, you gain **1 [Boost]**; as always, you succeed at everything! Additionally, you have the **Rich** Wealth level rather than the **Average** one, thanks to your previous wealth on Earth.'),
('mostlyUsedToAliens', 'MOSTLY USED TO ALIENS', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive]', 'You’ve spent time around those weird “humans” enough now to be able to… mostly deal with them pretty okay! Your **[Manipulate]** and **[Analyze]** rolls against Kids are no longer **[Inept]**.'),
('musicalSoul', 'MUSICAL SOUL', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Passive]', 'You’ve started looking into less… distressing aspects of the Clown Church, and one of the biggest aspects is music. With heavy percussion, calliope organs and of course, so many horns and honks, music is a big part of Clown Culture that’s often overlooked. So… why not give it some time to shine? FRAYMOTIF rolls while you are present are always **[Talented]**. The **[Buildup]** of FRAYMOTIF is reduced to **[Buildup: 2]** for all trolls, and if you ever take the MUSICREANT **[Template]**, you are **[Talented]** at all moves.'),
('mutagenicAdaption', 'MUTAGENIC ADAPTION', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Deep-Sea]', 'Hm. That\'s strange. One Day you awoke, and… you had changed again. Peculiar. Your early life being formed by the crushing pressures of the sea has made you able to go through generations of evolution in the span of a few months. You may choose any one non-Subcaste, Psimates, or Hatchmates Mutation from the Mutations chapter. Obviously, these aren’t real mutations, and do not make you **[Cullbait]**. However, if your blood isn’t violet, nobody can be really sure if you’re merely adapted or a filthy mutant! You cannot take Subcaste or Paleblood. Alternatively, you may take a second option from SUBPHOTIC VARIANT.'),
('myAbstrataIsMyBuddy', 'MY ABSTRATA IS MY BUDDY', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'Chop! Chop! Chop! Chop! Swing! Swing! Swing! Swing! By now, you\'ve made quite the name for yourself… especially with that iconic weapon of yours. How many people has it felled? Messiahs know, dude! Point is, it takes time for a weapon to have gained this kind of reputation… but you\'ve spent that time, honk honk. You designate a weapon of yours as an ICONIC WEAPON. You can have two ABSTRATA on this weapon. You get **MAX** **[Strife]** rolls on an 18+ with your ICONIC WEAPON, and when you get **MAX**, the target always becomes **[Scared]** on top of other results.'),
('myLittleMonster', 'MY LITTLE MONSTER', 'OTHER', 'FIDUSSPAWNER', '[Template][Unlock: Fiduspawner]', 'So here you are. You’ve raised an egg for an undisclosed amount of time, you’ve hatched the egg, the egg turned out to be a horrifying insectoid monster that laid an entirely separate egg into a host plush, and now the host plush is hatching. It’s time. Pick one option from each category below to create your monster. Each option has a set of letters associated with it, which in the end will create your fiduspawn’s name. You can summon your fiduspawn as an action. You can give up one, both, or all of your actions to have your fiduspawn fight for you, though they can only use UNIVERSALS and moves from the FIDUSPAWNER **[Template]**. Thanks to Gamenormal’s coding of the game, you share a link with your fiduspawn, causing you to share conditions, HP, **[Recharges]**, damage, etc. If one of you gains a **[Buff]**, you both do, if one of you takes on an **[Emotion]**, you both do, etc. If you die in the game, you die in real life. Got it? Now make your monster!'),
('myMachinations', 'MY MACHINATIONS!', 'OTHER', 'MAGE', '[Class][Basic][Free][Locked: Mage]', 'Of course you’re the authority. You know all about this plan you’re about to dish out. Every single aspect of this is in your wheelhouse, there’s absolutely NO way this could go wrong… At any point, you may create a plan as to what moves you will be rolling and in what order as a **[Free]** action. You must declare at least three, though there is no maximum. For each move you plan, roll, and successfully execute past the first two, you gain a stacking +1 **[Buff]**. Therefore, on your third called roll, you gain a +1 **[Buff]**. On your fifth, you gain a +3. You have no modifier limit for this **[Buff]** and can stack it as high as you like past +5. **[Reactions]** automatically break your streak if they were not planned. Any failed roll automatically breaks this streak. HOW COULD YOU HAVE NOT ACCOUNTED FOR THIS!? AUGH…'),
('myMomCouldBeatUpYourMom', 'MY MOM COULD BEAT UP YOUR MOM', 'FUCHSIA', 'FUCHSIA', '[Fuchsia][Advanced][Passive]', 'Your mom is the coolest primordial being on the planet. You love her so much. She doesn’t give you curfews, she doesn’t care who you have over, and sometimes she gives you omens and powers from the dark gods that inhabit the furthest realms of the universe. Upon taking this move, you gain the CUSTODIAN COMPANION move, except it has ALL abilities and all trolls who see Gl\'bgolyb feel an overwhelming **[Despair]**.'),
('myReality', 'MY REALITY', 'SPACE', 'SPACE', '[Aspect][Ultra][Locked: Space]', 'For the longest time, you were lonely and afraid- you didn’t seem to matter to anyone or anything, just an infinitesimal troll in an infinite universe. But that’s okay! Everyone is infinitesimal, and everyone experiences the world at their own pace. You don’t need to wait for reality to grant you permission to do what you want— you can just do it! \r\n\r\nEvery move you have can be made as a **[Reaction]**; you can interrupt someone mid-**[WHAM]** buildup to roll GRIEF on them, you can use WORDPLAY to convince someone to turn around and look over their shoulder just before they try to PROBLEM SLEUTH you— turn order, schmurn order. Entropy reigns supreme in a world where everything eventually changes, no matter how far away it is! \r\n\r\nIf you use a move that would ruin the flow of the opponent’s move— like the aforementioned “what’s that behind you!” WORDPLAY before a PROBLEM SLEUTHING— the opponent’s roll is **[Tiered Down]**. Additionally, INDECISIVE DECISION becomes **[Recharge: 1]** for you.'),
('mysteriousFigure', 'MYSTERIOUS FIGURE', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Espiacrooner]\n', 'You are a puzzle, wrapped in an enigma, shrouded in riddles, lovingly sprinkled with intrigue, express mailed to Mystery, Alaska. You\'re so good at keeping questions at bay that generally, folks can\'t even put together the concept that you may be misleading them! You gain four more ESPIACROONER LEVELS, as you’ve spent plenty of time exercising your skills. Additionally, you gain access to **[Unlock]** and **[Basic] [Class]**, **[Aspect]** and **[Sway]** moves from your own sheet, as long as you present your disguise as having these same attributes. These do not cost ESPIACROONER LEVELS to add to your sheet and therefore use. '),
('mysteriousMagic', 'MYSTERIOUS MAGIC', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][Passive]', 'You aren\'t going to live your life in a cage. You\'re going to be true to who you are! By now, you\'ve probably used your metapowers in front of others. But the way that your strange magic looks varies on the practitioner! So… how do you present your mysterious magic? Select one of the following effects that triggers the first time in an encounter someone sees you use a **[Magic]** or **[Psionic]** roll. Emotions from this move can\'t be **[Heightened]**.\r\n\r\n**FREAKY**: Oooogh… that\'s so creepy… bweeeeh… your magic is unnerving! All opponents are **[Scared]** for **2 turns**. \r\n\r\n**FLASHY**: Whoa! You don\'t care about stealth at all, huh? Your magic is all flashy and glowy, damn! All opponents are **[Blinded]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n**MYTHIC**: Your magic hints at something so much bigger than any of us. All trolls (yourself and allies included) become **[Stunned]**.\r\n\r\n**BIZARRE**: Even seeing your magic is hard to process! Ugh, headache… all opponents are **[Confused]** for **a turn**.\r\n\r\n**SOOTHING**: Your magic feels… safe. Calming. All allies and yourself lose **4 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**EMPOWERING**: Your eyes glow and you float a foot off the floor, hair whipping in the wind as you use your magic. God, you\'re cool. You gain **1 [Boost]**.'),
('mythicMangrit', 'MYTHIC MANGRIT', 'OTHER', 'HEROMODE', '', 'You. Are. STRONG! You are TOUGH!! You are, above all else, MIGHTY!!! NONE can get in your way, on account of just how BUFF you are. I mean, look at you! God motherfuckin\' damn! You\'re RIIIIIIIIPPED. When you enter **HERO MODE**, you may select one of the following benefits.\r\n\r\n> **ULTRAPUNCH**: You focus on preparing an insanely powerful blow that will probably send your targets to another dimension. You can\'t lose **[WHAM]** for two turns.\r\n\r\n> **ORAORAORAORA**: Or Mudamudamuda or Dorarara, depending on your tastes. Point is, as a **[Lengthy]** action you make three **[Strife]** rolls, which can include multiple uses of the same move, but you are **[Exhausted]** at the end.\r\n\r\n> **UNBELIEVABLE STAMINA**: How do you keep pushing through everything like this?! You reset your **[Drag]**, **[Physical]** conditions and **[Recharge]**/**[One-Offs]** for **[Physical]** moves to 0.\r\n\r\n> **MASTER OF COMBAT**: You know how to mimic any fighting style. Your **GREAT** and **MAX GRIEF** rolls can do 1 less damage and in return give any one **[Physical]** condition of your choosing.]\r\n\r\n> **RUMBLECHALLENGE**: You came here for a FIGHT, not for WEAKSAUCE BABY HOUR! So FIGHT! WITH YOUR MAAAAAAANGRIT! You call upon your target to fight you one on one, making them use **GRIEF [Strife]** rolls rather than any other they may have. If they refuse, you are emboldened; you do +1 **[Somatic]** damage on every **GRIEF** roll until they inflict 3 damage to you. This damage is **[Unblockable]**.'),
('mythseekingMarvel', 'MYTHSEEKING MARVEL', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Folklorist]', 'You\'ve traveled far and wide, you\'ve filled many books with handwritten notes, and you\'ve illustrated more monsters, cultural artifacts, and ideas than could be kept in a single gallery. Your efforts to study the unstudiable have been fruitful, and everyone sees you as a true scholar of society. You gain access to HERO MODE through your PERFECT PULCHRITUDE. You gain an effect based on your YARNCHASER choice.\r\n\r\n> **Faeries & Magic**: You\'ve studied enough spellbooks to learn quite a few interesting abilities! You take **3 [Magic]** **[Basic]** or **[Advanced]** moves, even if they are **[Locked]**. Entity-type monsters are usually not hostile to you and your allies unless provoked. Thanks, weird fey!\r\n\r\n> **Beasts & Creatures**: No sense letting body parts go to waste! When you kill a monster, you may take a part of their corpse and fashion it into an item worth a number of **VP** equal to their level. You can use one move that monster had, subject to Clouder\'s approval.\r\n\r\n> **Beliefs & Religions**: Truly incredible… you\'ve uncovered a dead religion that went extinct aeons ago, and studied it extensively! You may take a second aspect or class as a Template, flavouring it as power from a dead faith. You can take **2 [Basic]** moves, **2 [Advanced]** moves, and the **[Ultra]** only, as if it were a regular template. You gain the **[Entry]** now. All **+IMG** rolls instead use **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n> **The True Meaning of Holidays in General**: IT\'S CRAMPLESLINK EVE! Every time you beat someone in an encounter, they are exposed to SIMPTOMS for your favourite holiday. Your emotion from YARNCHASER may be **[Heightened]** if you so choose.\r\n\r\n> **Foodways & Cuisine**: MOOOOOOOORE RECIPES! You can make the following TAPAS…\r\n\r\n> 1. Revive a recently dead person lol\r\n> 2. Gain an **[Emotion]**.\r\n> 3. Reset the **[One-Off]** of a move. Ironically, this is a **[One-Off]**.\r\n> 4. Reduce incoming **[Energy]** damage by 1 (min 0).\r\n\r\n> **Proverbs & Language**: Your mastery of all forms of speech is truly incredible. You can use **[Manipulate]** rolls on any creature, even ones that don\'t normally speak, as you find a pidgin language you both get. You have a vague understanding of what they attempt to communicate to you.\r\n\r\n> **Music & Dance**: You\'re EXTREMELY good at making sounds that swing you off your feet! FRAYMOTIF rolls have no **[Build-Up]** for you.\r\n\r\n> **Art & Literature**: The creativity you put into your work is astounding. You can create items on the fly as if you were purchasing them as you create homemade masterpieces or write poems with similar effects on the mind.'),
('nah', 'NAH', 'VOID', 'VOID', '[Aspect][Basic][Reaction][Unblockable][Recharge: 2][Locked: Void]', 'No. As a **[Reaction]**, you can counteract the effects of a **[Passive]** move that would interfere with something for a round; an effect that makes the opponent’s move **[Tier Up]** or **[Talented]**, or that would make you **[Tier Down]** or **[Inept]**, etc.'),
('naturalWeapons', 'NATURAL WEAPONS', 'OTHER', 'MUTANT', '[Mutant][Cullbait][Passive]', 'You are the weapon. It’s true! You have something dangerous built into your body, whether it be something like protruding claws or built-in vines reminiscent of those that everyone’s favorite pop-cullture idol has. These types of weapons function differently than typical abstrata, in which they cannot be destroyed or taken from you. However, using these weapons immediately outs you as a mutant, so you must be very careful while using these. You deal **+1 [Somatic]** Damage while using these weapons, but have a **-1 [Nerf]** to +GRA. Choose one of these effects:\r\n\r\n> **RAZORKIND**: **[Active]** Your weapons are sharp; and the damage you can deal with them can be excruciating. You inflict **[Bloodied]** as a **[Free]** action on a **[Recharge: 2]** as you slice into the opponent with ease.\r\n\r\n> **POISONKIND**: **[Passive]** Your weapons are reminiscent of a jellyfish’s venom. As a **[Reaction]** to an enemy’s **GREAT** **[Strife]** roll, you can inflict POISON that is so painful, they can’t help but feel **[Dread]**. On a **MAX** **[Strife]** roll, it is instead **[Despair]**.\r\n\r\n> **ACIDKIND**: **[Active]** Ohh, you just like being an acid-spitter. A xenomorph. It’s okay, bud, happens to all of us. You can bite, spit or otherwise slap some acid on someone, which causes the target to become **[Ablaze]**. Removing this is a **[Lengthy]** action.\r\n\r\n> **ANOMALYKIND**: **[Passive]** This is more than illegal; this is downright horrifying. It’s just something about you. Your face is distorted to the people around you, or maybe you just have a ghostly frame at all times but you’re still alive and… Regardless, your **+IMG** moves are at a **+2 [Buff]**, and everyone in the encounter with you becomes **[Scared]**.\r\n\r\n> VINEKIND: **[Active]** Vines - whether they’re slick with barbs, smooth against the surface or something else - are hidden away in parts of your body. This functions as RANGEKIND, granting you the ability to make a target **[Floorbound]** and **[Stunned]** as you hit them really fucking hard on a GREAT, whether they’ve been **[Flying]** or not. You deal **-1 [Somatic]** damage when applying these effects.\r\n\r\n> **BURNKIND**: **[Passive]** Have you ever touched something so hot or so cold that it genuinely burned you? That’s you. You’re that sensation, all over your body. You gain ICEKIND for **[Free]**, but it activates only on an enemy’s **MAX** **[Physical]** roll. Additionally, the enemy takes **1 [Somatic]** damage every time they first apply **[Somatic]** damage to you.'),
('nauticalNightmare', 'NAUTICAL NIGHTMARE', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Passive][Unlock: Admiral]', 'Quiver, disgusting land-dwellers! You are a future captain of space armadas, bringer of terror, and overall big fucking douchebag. You peddle weapons, death, and maybe some other stuff on your online stores; who knows, dude. The emphasis is on your military training— and your LOVE of weapons! You are **[Talented]** at **+GRA**. Your mastery of weapons is noticeable; you can have up to 3 ABSTRATA UPGRADES on a single weapon, and you gain 1 for free now. Finally, you get the following effects you can add to a **GREAT** or **MAX** GRIEF roll in exchange for doing **1 less damage**.\r\n\r\n> **RAZE**: You attack everyone indiscriminately! Die die die die! Your attack damages all targets.\r\n> **RUPTURE**: Oh snap! The target is **[Bloodied]**.\r\n> **WEAK POINTS**: Aha! You count your attack as an **[Energy]** damage of your choosing. \r\n> **CRACK**: PEW! You do **3 damage** to an item they have!');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('navalFleet', 'NAVAL FLEET', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Recharge: 2][Flourish][Locked: Admiral]', 'What kind of shitty admiral DOESN\'T have an armada? Lowblood soldiers with highblood commanders, and there\'s you at the tippy top. You have an army who will support you wherever you go, assembling as soon as you roll LET\'S STRIFE in tanks, blimps, and other vehicles to help you win your battles. When you want to enforce your military might, roll **+GRT**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Danger close doesn\'t mean SHOOT AT ME! Your bad orders lead to you being peppered with bullets yourself. You take **2 [Somatic]** Damage and become **[Bloodied]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: They miss. They suck. Nothing happens except the sting of incompetence giving you **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Nothing concrete, but suppressive fire is suppressive fire! Your target takes **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD: Now you\'re letting someone else do the cooking! Choose one of the following **GOOD** options**:\r\n\r\n> **SUPPORTING FIRE**: GRATATATATA! Your troops open fire! Their aim isn\'t great, but it\'s enough to throw people off guard. Your **[Strife]** rolls can\'t be **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]**, or **[Nerfed]** for **2 turns** as you strike true!\r\n\r\n> **CANNONADE**: On my mark… BOOM! Your troops wait before firing at the target exactly as you signal it (through also hitting them.) Just make sure you don\'t confuse your troops by missing! You gain **1 [WHAM]**.\r\n\r\n> **MEDIC!!!**: A lovely medic from a dark corner someplace tosses you an EpiPen for your allergic reaction to being stabbed. You **[Heal] 1 HP**.\r\n\r\n> **MOUNT UP**: Your troops bring you your VEHICLE (if you have one) and you hop right in!\r\n\r\n> **NOBLE SACRIFICE**: GET DOWN, ADMIRAL! You retroactively **[Tier Down]** a **[Strife]** roll that would have hit you, having it instead hit a noble soldier. God bless.\r\n\r\n> **WAR CRY**: YAAAAAAARGH! You become **[Out-Of-Control]** for **2 turns** as your fleet bolsters your confidence.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Actual competence shines through. It fills you with determination. You get a **GOOD**, but also gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: My god. The horrors of war. Do they mean nothing to you? You either get a **GOOD** and **3 [Boost]**, or the following option.\r\n\r\n> **NOW WE\'RE ALL SONS OF BITCHES**: A team of NPCs with an ordinance no teenagers should ever even be allowed to launch something your way. Everyone, including you, takes **6 [Somatic]** damage and becomes **[Stunned]**.'),
('nebulitchcraft', 'NEBULITCHCRAFT', 'OTHER', 'ASTROSORCERER', '[Template][Advanced][Recharge: 3][Chicanery][Magic][Locked: Astrosorcerer]\r\n', 'You\'ve sufficiently advanced your magic to a point where you can not only bring blessings from the stars to you and your allies, but curse your enemies with the deep magic of the cosmos. That\'s what they get!\r\n\r\nYou gain a unique spell based on your Sign, based on your Caste, your Sway and your Aspect, much like the one presented in ASTROSORCERY, except this one uses the naming convention of CURSE OF THE X rather than INCANTATION OF THE X. It is still called this, regardless of whether you use your own sign or your opponent\'s sign, as per the Sway options. When you want to curse someone, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n> **MIN**: aaAAAAAAAAAAOOOUURRRGHHH… you take the effects of a **GREAT** yourself!\r\n\r\n> **BAD**: YOU ACCIDENTALLY BLESSED THEM. You give them 2 **[Boost]**. Dumbass. \r\n\r\n> **OK**: Nothing happens because magic isn\'t real you fucking idiot.\r\n\r\n> **GOOD**: You cast a lesser hex! You do the curse, but only the ASPECT and SWAY sections. You know the drill.\r\n\r\n> **GREAT**: Bubble, bubble, toil and trouble… Your curse does the ASPECT, SWAY and CASTE options.\r\n\r\n> **MAX**: The perfect punishment! You either choose anyone in the encounter\'s Caste and Aspect to calculate results, independent of who your actual target is, or get a **GREAT** and inflict **2 additional [Drag]** upon your target.\r\n\r\nSPELL MODULES\r\n\r\n**SWAY**:\r\n\r\n> **PROSPIT**: Using your opponent’s Caste and Aspect to calculate effects (or your own, if they have none)…\r\n> **DERSE**: Using your own Caste and Aspect to calculate effects… \r\n\r\n**ASPECT**:\r\n\r\n> **TIME**: You remove all of the opponent\'s **[Resistance]** for **2 turns**, or give them 1 **[Weakness]** for **a turn** if they have none…\r\n> **SPACE**: You prevent the opponent from benefiting from the actions of allies for **2 turns**, or prevent them from using **[Flourish]** or **[Heal]** moves on themselves for the duration if they are alone… \r\n> **LIFE**: You cause the opponent to become **[Bloodied]**, ignoring effects that usually prevent it…\r\n> **DOOM**: You reset the **[Recharge]** of all the opponent\'s moves currently on recharge to full, and if there are none, you choose one to put on **[Recharge]** now… \r\n> **HOPE**: You make the opponent feel **[Dread]** for the guilt in their soul…\r\n> **RAGE**: You do **1** (**GOOD**)/**2** (**GREAT**/**MAX**) **[Psychic/Somatic]** damage to the opponent, and…\r\n> **BREATH**: You **[Trap]** and **[Floorbound]** the opponent and… \r\n> **BLOOD**: You disable the opponent\'s FRAYMOTIF, and…\r\n> **HEART**: You decide one of the opponent\'s next moves and… \r\n> **MIND**: You make the opponent\'s **[Mental]** rolls **[Godawful]** for **2 turns**, and… \r\n> **LIGHT**: You disable one of the opponent\'s **[Talents]** for a turn, and...\r\n> **VOID**: You **[Blind]** the opponent, and… \r\n\r\nCASTE\r\n\r\n> **RUST**: …then increase the max **[Recharge]** on any one **[Chicanery]** effect by 2 for the encounter.\r\n> **BRONZE**: …then make retrieving an item from their Sylladex an action rather than **[Free]** for **3 turns**.\r\n> **GOLD**: …then make them **[Tired]** and overexerted. \r\n> **LIME**: …then disable all their Class, Aspect or Sway moves for **2 turns**.\r\n> **OLIVE**: …disable their **[Reactions]** for **2 turns**.\r\n> **JADE**: …set them **[Ablaze]**, even if they would normally be immune.\r\n> **TEAL**: …proclaim the target GUILTY. All **[Strife]** moves against them get a **+1 [Buff]** for the encounter.\r\n> **CERULEAN**: …cause the opponent to take **1 [Drag]** each time they deal **1 damage** for the encounter.\r\n> **INDIGO**: …they become pitiful. They\'re **[Godawful]** at **[Physical]** rolls for **a turn**. \r\n> **PURPLE**: …make all **+IMG** rolls **[Inept]** for **2 turns**. If they have no **[Psionics]** or **[Magic]** other than FRAYMOTIF, they take **2 [Psychic]** damage.\r\n> **VIOLET**: …you make them **[Godawful]** at **+HUB** for **2 turns**.\r\n> **FUSCHIA**: …select any of the other Caste options as you please.'),
('necromanticDebutant', 'NECROMANTIC DEBUTANT', 'OTHER', 'SHADOWDROPPER', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Eerie][Magic][Locked: Shadowdropper]', 'You\'ve started researching what makes you different from, say, other Shadowdroppers. Why can you think? Why are you even undead? Turns out the truth is drenched in all sortsa spooky magic. You are **[Talented]** at **+IMG**, but **[Inept]** at **+GRT**; as you continue to push your limits and learn more about what you really are, you begin to slowly wither away whatever strength you once had. Your very body is cursed- anytime somebody in an encounter with you would gain **[Drag]**, they gain one extra. This includes you. Finally, you immediately take any one **[Basic]** or **[Advanced]** **[Psionic]** **[Strife]** move from any caste, but it gains the **[Magic]** tag instead of **[Psionic]**.\n\n'),
('neighborhoodWatchkid', 'NEIGHBORHOOD WATCHKID', 'KID', 'KOB', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Kids on Bikes]', 'You\'re a kid on a bike, a member of the Kids on Bikes, the junior neighborhood watch group established on the Green Moon! Humans aren\'t terribly welcome anywhere in this weird, new galaxy, and tend to be immediately and brutally killed by anyone who sees them. And since the proliferation of literal, arcane teleportation technology cannot be stopped thanks to this weird \"SBURB\" game still being functional, albeit offline, that means alternatives to simple isolation must be made. Thus; the Neighborhood Watch! Your duties are to help the sheriff, teachers, civil servants and other remnants of the old world\'s stability in the Green Moon Town in making sure that the moon doesn\'t turn to murderous mayhem like the planet below. You gain the following totally radical kicks.\r\n\r\n> **When you **[Strife]** a troll, that troll\'s attempts to use CAN\'T ABSCOND BRO against your allies **[Tier Down]** for a round when you roll a **GOOD**, **GREAT** or **MAX**, allowing your friends a chance to flee in safety. This is on a **[Recharge: 3]**.  \r\n\r\n> You get a bike, a small VEHICLE for free! If it is destroyed you may get a new one. Your VEHICULATE rolls on your bike are always **[Talented]**, but you always have 1 HORSEPOWER less than normal. Trolls who see this strange, foreign wheeled vehicle gain **1 [Drag]** in mild bewilderment at such a concept however. Wheels? On a vehicle? Unbelievable.'),
('neonliberal', 'NEONLIBERAL', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Passive][Unlock: Cyberpunk]', 'Wake the fuck up, gutterblood. We\'ve got circuits to meaninglessly insert into stuff. When living in poverty, with propaganda shoved in your face telling you that you\'re worthless and the heiress\' latest designer boot brand is being sold for more money than you can legally have, you turn to the only escape from this capitalistic nightmare that you can access: MODDING YOURSELF LIKE A BEHEADSDA GAME. Cool robot arms, central cortex systems in your spine, hell yeah! Not that it accomplishes anything countercultural, but it looks cool. Your teeth glow, dammit! Choose one of the following mainframes.\r\n\r\n> **CHUCKLEMATRIX (+RAS)**: You cybernetically got \"funny\" installed, and you\'re like, triple-jointed now. You are immune to **[Floorbound]** and **[Trapped]**, and any time an enemy gains the **[Giggling]** emotion around you, it heightens to **[Laughing]**.\r\n\r\n> **HOLOLIVER (+PLC)**: You\'re a V-Tuber! Literally! You project a holographic cartoon version around yourself at all times. You always have a CLEVER DISGUISE on hand, without using **VP**. \r\n\r\n> **FIBULASKATE (+GRA)**: Feet? Cringe! You\'ve got deployable WHEELS! You always go first in an encounter without rolling LET\'S STRIFE. You are **[Quickened]** on this first turn.\r\n\r\n> **GUTCORTEX (+APP)**: Your teeth are metal and have neon lights installed that go all the way to your stomach! Whenever you **[Heal]**, you gain a number of **[Boost]** equal to your HP **[Healed]**.\r\n\r\n> **SWAGMETER (+HUB)**: Hm? Oh, yes. You ARE fresh as fuck. What gave it away? The cool neon spine? The multicoloured flames you can light from your fingers? The weapons that are literally built into your arms? Yeah. Whenever you would gain **[Drag]**, roll 1d8. On an even number, you don\'t.\r\n\r\n> **CYBERTISSUE (+GRT)**: Your muscles are enhanced to be way tougher than your average Gold… and also, you\'re like, 7 foot tall, half as wide, and covered in cybernetic tattoos. Hot. On a **[Recharge: 2]**, whenever you take **[Somatic]** damage, you gain **1 [Somatic] [Resistance]** for **1 round** as your muscles harden in response to physical trauma. \r\n\r\n> **GENIUSCRANK (+PSP)**: The top half of your head has translucent plastic that shows people your brain, which is by the way FULL of computer chips. You can take other caste\'s **[Open]** moves that give PROBLEM SLEUTHING options when you level up; you get one now.\r\n\r\n> **DREAMERENGINE (+IMG)**: You\'ve got a little camera in your forehead that projects your thoughts into holograms! Sweet, huh? You can roll WORDPLAY using **+IMG** by displaying holograms and pictograms to prove your points.'),
('nerdHobbies', 'NERD HOBBIES', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Yeah, you have interests that people would consider dorky. So what? Even the greatest legislacerator probably FLARPs sometimes. Shut up. Shut up, you don’t care. Stop bothering you. Select a hobby from the list below.\r\n\r\n> **ANIME**: You love watching East Alternian Cartoons, and are a vehement supporter of Dubbed Superiority. **[Psionic]** rolls against you are at a **-2 [Nerf]**; you’ve learned how psions fight easily thanks to your anime watch history! (It’s just like in Snazzard Sphere X…) \r\n\r\n> **CARD GAMES**: Collect ‘em, battle ‘em, do it on motorcycles! Card games RULE. To you, at least. When in a GROUP STRIFE, whenever you use an item, you gain **1 [Boost]**, because decaptchaloguing stuff feels like drawing cards from your deck, or something.\r\n\r\n> **COMIC BOOKS**:  Superscoundrels! Personally, you love them. You know all about fights of epic proportions; so when someone else in an encounter gains **[WHAM]**, you can too as a **[Reaction]**!\r\n\r\n> **COMPUTERS**: You spend a lot of time on the computer, either on forums or actually working on hardware stuff. Your HAXX-ATTAXX **[Downtime]** rolls are **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n\r\n> **MINIATURES**: You spend a lot of time painting small statuettes, from spaceships to mechas. Not planes, those don’t exist. Items that cost **1 VP** instead cost **½ VP**, because you’re used to working on the small scale.\r\n\r\n> **ROLEPLAY**: Playing pretend RULES, okay?! You LOVE to FLARP. Any **[Zodiac]** moves you roll are **[Talented]**.\r\n\r\n> **VIDEOS GAME**: You truly are one of the most oppressed trolls out there. You may become **[Enraged]** as an action. RRRAAAARGH! This does not stack with the calming effect of SEETHING SMILE, though it can be used to **[Heighten]** the **[Enraged]** effect from that move to **[Out of Control]**.\r\n\r\n> **SOMETHING ELSE**: God, there’s infinite lame things a NERD like you could do. What do you do, make fursuits or something? CRINGE! You get a **[Template]** **[Entry]**; the **[Template]** uses a stat you are already **[Talented]** in.\r\n\r\n'),
('neuromeddling', 'NEUROMEDDLING', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'TIT', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: TIT]', 'You have toyed with various brews of Amnesticizor fluid in search of the perfect mind control serum. No reason, it’s just a fun hobby. In the meantime, however, your neurostudies have led you down an interesting path indeed; different ways of forgetting. Rather than reset a troll’s stats to **3 turns** ago, you may choose one of the following effects.\r\n\r\n> **MUSCLEWIPE**: Ah- hey, shit, how-? You disable all **[Passive]** moves the opponent has for **2 turns** as their muscle memory fumbles.\r\n\r\n> **MOVEBLOCK**: BZZT. Don’t do that again. You disable the opponent’s last non-**[Strife]** move for **2 turns**. \r\n\r\n> **CULTUREWALL**: You briefly cloud your opponent’s societal belonging. They lose their Caste tree’s **[Talents]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **LONG-TERMICBARRICADE**: You make no stat modifications, but remove one event that can be summed up in 5 words from the target’s mind from up to a week ago.\r\n\r\n'),
('neutralFaceOfDispleasure', 'NEUTRAL FACE OF DISPLEASURE', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Recharge: 3][Mental]', 'You… are an intimidating person! Even when you aren’t trying to be! So naturally, people are a little scared of you, especially when it comes to displeasing you. Maybe you don’t even intend on looking a particular way, but your face when you don’t look pleased with a situation is… I’ll be real, it’s goddamn nerve wracking. When someone upsets you (or an ally is about to upset you by doing poorly), roll **+HUB**. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: Ha! They relish in your displeasure! Their next roll is **[Tiered Up/Down]** in a way that doesn’t favour you!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: If anything, your expression only fuels them. Their next roll is **+1 higher**/**lower** in a way that doesn’t favour you.\r\n\r\n**OK**: They didn’t actually see you make the face. :I\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Your expression throws the opponent off balance. If they roll a **GOOD** or **GREAT** on their next turn, it’s **[Tiered Up/Down]** in a way that favours you. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Oh no! Guilt crushes them, whether they realize it or not! Their next roll is automatically **GREAT**/**BAD**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: tt he yd iddnt mean t o upse t y you? P le ase gont be a,nrgy;;., Their roll becomes a **MIN**/**MAX** roll.'),
('neverStopGoing', 'NEVER STOP GOING', 'OTHER', 'KNIGHT', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][One-Off][Last Stand][Locked: Knight]', 'An epiphany has come upon you, a revelation from either your inner self or a higher power: if you’re all fucked up and don’t take care of yourself, how does that actually help your friends? There won’t be any more heroics if you’ve removed yourself from the picture. More importantly, your friends would lose a loved one. And this world is better with you in it. You’ve got to care for yourself too. When you are first dropped to 0 **HP** or below, you instead remain at 1 **HP** as you refuse to give up so early! **GUTSUCKERY** loses its **[One-off]** tag for you after this move triggers, instead becoming **[Recharge: 2]**. If you already had a move that removed **GUTSUCKERY’s [One-Off]** tag, your **GUTSUCKERY** rolls become **[Talented]** when said effect is activated.'),
('newHorizons', 'NEW HORIZONS', 'OTHER', 'MAGE', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Buildup: 5][Magic][Locked: Mage]', 'While it can be painful to admit at times, your perspective is not the only one there is. Time spent with allies and enemies alike have taught you to see your aspect in a bright, new way. Why limit yourself to the same ol’ traditions? Let’s apply a bit of what you’ve learned. You may exchange **[Buildup]** to gain a **[Hold]** to apply an effect to a **[Strife]** move. The following bonuses based on your aspect: \r\n\r\n> **TIME**: If your **[Strife]** roll succeeds, it **[Slows]** the opponent for 3 turns.\r\n\r\n> **SPACE**: If your **[Strife]** roll succeeds, enemy rolls against you have a -2 **[Nerf]** for 3 turns.\r\n\r\n> **LIFE**: Instead of applying this to a **[Strife]** roll, your **[Hold]** allows you to add **[WHAM]** into any **[Heal]** action used on one ally instead.\r\n\r\n> **DOOM**: If your **[Strife]** roll succeeds, it **[Tiers Down]** the next two moves your opponent rolls, even to **MIN**s. \r\n\r\n> **HOPE**: If your **[Strife]** roll succeeds, you become **[Enthusiastic]**.\r\n\r\n> **RAGE**: You gain 3 **[WHAM]** for your next **[Strife]** roll. This does not go over the 3 **[WHAM]** cap with **VICIOUS VINDICATION**.\r\n\r\n> **BREATH**: If your **[Strife]** roll succeeds, add the effect of any one **GOOD SHENANIGANS** effect you have access to.\r\n\r\n> **BLOOD**: If your **[Strife]** roll succeeds, your allies each gain 1 **[WHAM]** as they watch you charging into battle. \r\n\r\n> **LIGHT**: If your **[Strife]** roll succeeds, it is automatically **[Tiered Up]**. This stacks with other **[Tier Up]**s and can be pushed to a **MAX**. \r\n\r\n> **VOID**: Your **[Strife]** roll ignores the effects of **[Hidden]**.\r\n\r\n> **HEART**: If your **[Strife]** roll succeeds, you can choose to inflict **[Despair]** to your opponent as an **[Unblockable]** effect. The **[Despair]** cannot be removed.\r\n\r\n> **MIND**: If your **[Strife]** roll succeeds, the damage it does is **[Unblockable]**.'),
('newWorld', 'NEW WORLD', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Free]', 'Not everything on Alternia is good. Far from it, it’s a fascist alien blood planet. But… the good you’ve found here and there… it makes you wonder, was Earth much different? You’ve come to appreciate the small things that Alternia has that home didn’t, and you’ve become a little more comfortable on this dystopian hellrock. Whenever a troll would give you a positive **[Emotion]**, you can gain any other **[Emotion]** of your choosing. For example, an ally who intends on making you feel **[Hopeful]** might make you **[Peaceful]** instead as you feel soothed by their presence.'),
('nicheInterests', 'NICHE INTERESTS', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Passive]', 'Hey, y\'know… you actually read up a forum on that once. It was kinda neat! Cool, even! You study pretty niche topics and have picked up a skillset that you\'re not as embarrassed to show off as you once might have been. You can take the **[Entry]** to a Template that revolves around a hobby such as MUSICREANT or SERVICESQUIRE without locking yourself into the Template. You can\'t access the rest of the tree, and certain templates such as ORG ones, **[Magic]** ones, or **[Eerie]** ones are similarly off-limits. If you ever meet a troll with the full template, you gain **1 [Boost]**; you know about this kinda thing! When you take this move, you gain **1 [Entry]** now.'),
('nineLives', 'NINE LIVES', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][One-Off][Last Stand]', 'Heroic? Justified? You have to laugh. You’re just too lucky to go down like that! You’ve had so many close encounters in the past, that you don’t really go down easy! When you would be knocked to **0 HP**, you can instead stay up at **1 HP** and wreck some shop, nya!'),
('ninjaCat', 'NINJA CAT', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Chicanery][Flourish][Physical][Unlock: Nyanjutsu]', 'Life on the streets isn’t easy, nothing for you in this world is easy, your life\'s a war, and every night is a battle, and since you were a wriggler, you’ve been training yourself to fight, rawr >:3c. Either by training at an actual martial arts dojo, or just watching spewtube tutorials of guys swinging swords, you’ve learned fighting techniques that outpace any challenger. It’s your kitty ninja way. You are **[Talented]** at **+GRA**. When you wanna show off your moves, roll **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You eat shit on the floor. You are the world\'s worst ninja. You become **[Floorbound]** and **[Bloodied]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You avoid falling too hard. You are just **[Floorbound]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You didn\'t even fall!\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: WOOSH! You gain one of the following effects.\r\n\r\n> **DOUBLE TEAM**: SHFF SHFF SHFF- You move so quick, you leave your opponents chasing afterimages! You become **[Hidden]**.\r\n\r\n> **CHAKRA DISRUPTION**: THIP THIP THIP! You strike your opponent’s pressure points with precise blows, leaving them feeling sluggish and drained. They are **[Poisoned]** as you fuck up their vital energy.\r\n\r\n> **SUBSTITUTE**: BOOMF! You quickly dodge away and leave an object to take the blow! You can sacrifice an item from your sylladex to negate the **[Somatic]** damage of an incoming attack. This item is immediately destroyed, causing you to become **[Sad]** as you lose another casualty to the war called life. This effect is a **[One-Off]**.\r\n\r\n> **WALL RUN**: WOOSH! You leap across trees, run up a cliff, dash across water super fast....parkour! You start **[Flying]** as you zip and leap around. At the start of every subsequent turn, you must make a **[Free]** **GOOD** or higher **+GRA** roll to keep **[Flying]**.\r\n\r\n> **KI BLOCK**: THWACK! You aren’t about to wait for your opponent to charge up their special move. Quit that! You **[Tier Down]** your opponents\' next **[Magic]** or **[Psionic]** roll as you interrupt their hand signs or smack them between the eyes.\r\n\r\n> **HEART OF DARKNESS**: RWAR RWAR SHUT UP RWAR! You gain **1 [Hold]**; when you fail your first roll with this **[Hold]**, you swing wildly in frustration, swiping at anything in your way! You deal **1 [Somatic]** damage to a target, but take **2 [Drag]** as your little tantrum tires you out. This effect does not have the **[Strife]** tag. Using the **[Hold]** is **[Free]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Lightspeed, baby! You get a **GOOD**, and **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: HOLY SHARINGAN! You get a **GOOD**, but you also get **2 [Boost]**. This move doesn\'t take an action!'),
('ninjaWay', 'NINJA WAY', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Passive][Locked: Nyanjutsu]', 'You aren’t like all these other wannabe martial artists, you actually know real fighting techniques now! You’re super deadly and dangerous for real! You’re still doing this in a super cool and not at all dorky way. You have a preferred way of fighting, and have chosen to follow one of many Nyanjutsu paths. Choose one of the options below:\r\n\r\n> **SHINOBI**: Stealth. Reconnaissance. Disguises. Subterfuge. You’re a master in the art of tip-toeing around and rolling behind stuff. Any damage you deal while **[Hidden]** is **[Unblockable]**.\r\n\r\n> **KENSEI**: While they were writing fanfics, you studied the blade.  While they were making shipping charts, you were still studying the blade. While they were sleeping, you guessed it, you continued to study the blade. You can use the effects of any **[Energy]** ABSTRATA UPGRADES\' **MAX** effect on a 17+, not a **MAX**.\r\n\r\n> **TOUCH OF DEATH**: Weapons? Pfft, who needs them? Your bare hands are registered with the empire as lethal weapons. When using UNARMEDKIND, you can choose to deal **[Psychic]** damage as your practiced strikes disrupt your opponent’s spirit energy flow. Whenever you YOINK an item, you can use it immediately for **[Free]**. You can apply ABSTRATA UPGRADES to your hands.\r\n\r\n> **SHARINGAN: You have SPECIAL EYES. Okay not really, you’re just incredibly good at reading the movements of others. As a **[Reaction]**, you can **[Tier Down]** any **[Physical]** roll as you catch onto your opponent’s predictable movements. You also gain the following NINJA CAT effect**:\r\n> **COPYCAT**: HWAH! You mimic the movements of others to use their own tricks against them! You can use your NINJA CAT roll to use a **[Physical]** move used by someone else during the previous round!\r\n\r\n> **MERCY-NARY**: You’re a killer but…pulls out bandaid. Not all of martial arts is about beating the shit out of other people. You’re a student of anatomy, and the various ways to heal……and also break the body. You gain the Docterror Template **[Entry]** without having to take the template itself, and the action cost of using an item with the **[Heal]** tag is reduced by 1.  Whenever an opponent is given a **[Status]** effect, it’s extended for one extra round. \r\n\r\n> **BUSHIDO**: AYO, CHECK OUT THIS SWEET NYAMURAI ARMOUR! You get a suit of armour from the Indigo Paladin **[Entry]**, but you only select **3 damage** sources.'),
('noblePerfection', 'NOBLE PERFECTION', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Free][One-Off][Manipulate][Locked: Royal]', 'As a royal, you can\'t afford to be anything less than utterly perfect. And if other people are less than perfect… well, you gotta flex on \'em a lil. When an opponent gets an **OK** roll on a move you have access to, you may attempt to roll the same move with the following additional effects. If they got a **BAD**, this roll always uses **+APP** as your perfection kicks in. On a **MIN**, your roll is **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Whoa! Even rich people can be unbelievably shit at things, too?! That’s so inspiring! Your target’s rolls on that move **[Tier Up]** for **3 rounds**. When that wears off, they keep a **+1 [Buff]** for the rest of the encounter. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: Hey, that makes me feel a little better about myself. Thank you, rich dude! Your target’s rolls on that move receive a **+1 [Buff]** for the encounter.\r\n\r\n**OK**: It doesn’t register with your opponent that you’re flexing on them. Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Ah, jeez. This makes me feel inept! Your opponent receives a **-1 [Nerf]** on rolls for that move for the encounter.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Incredible! Now I’m completely miserable. Your opponent’s rolls on that move receive a **-2 [Nerf]** for the encounter.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Well fuck. The opponent is so blown away by how good you are, that they consider just giving up and never trying again. Extreme disillusionment, baby! Your opponent’s rolls on that move **[Tier Down]** for **3 rounds**. When that wears off, they keep a **-2 [Nerf]** for the rest of the encounter.'),
('noCapes', 'NO CAPES', 'OTHER', 'SUPERSCOUNDREL', '[Template][Basic][Locked: Superscoundrel]', 'WHERE IS YOUR SUPER SUIT?! Technically, there\'s no laws against saving or ruining the day in a hoodie and jeans. But let\'s be real- the difference between an amateur and a super is all about PRESENTATION! You get your very own **[Soulstuck]** super suit for free to show off your personal brand. While the stats are predetermined on the suit itself, the +1 and -1 may be flipped to fit your type of super! While wearing your super suit, all Problem Sleuthing rolls against you to figure out your identity are **[Inept]**. The super suit can also be equipped underneath regular Fashion items, but the effects do not stack.\r\n\r\n> **SUPER MASK OF SECRETS**\r\n> **[Hat][Soulstuck]**\r\n> Keeping your identity secret while going above and beyond the call of duty is a must. After all, showing your entire face could mean someone recognizes you, putting your loved ones at risk! Better safe than sorry.>\r\n> +1 HUB / -1 PSP\r\n> **SUPER OUTFIT OF KICK YO BUTT**\r\n> (SUPER MASK OF SECRETS, SUPER SUIT OF BADASSERY, SUPER BOOTS OF NYOOM) Pretty fly for a super guy! Choose 1 **[Physical]** HAZARD to be **[Immune]** to. This cannot be changed later.\r\n\r\n> **SUPER SUIT OF BADASSERY**\r\n> **[Bottom][Soulstuck]**\r\n> HERE\'S your super suit! This is the greatest good you are ever gonna get, no matter what your quadrant says. Nothing feels impossible when you look this good!\r\n> +1 GRT / -1 APP\r\n> SUPER OUTFIT OF KICK YO BUTT\r\n> (SUPER MASK OF SECRETS, SUPER SUIT OF BADASSERY, SUPER BOOTS OF NYOOM) Pretty fly for a super guy! Choose 1 **[Physical]** HAZARD to be **[Immune]** to. This cannot be changed later.\r\n\r\n> **SUPER BOOTS OF NYOOM**\r\n> **[Feet][Soulstuck]**\r\n> Holy shit! You\'re so fast! So graceful! So stylish! Much wow! Look at you go!!\r\n> +1 GRA / -1 RAS\r\n> SUPER OUTFIT OF KICK YO BUTT\r\n> (SUPER MASK OF SECRETS, SUPER SUIT OF BADASSERY, SUPER BOOTS OF NYOOM) Pretty fly for a super guy! Choose 1 **[Physical]** HAZARD to be **[Immune]** to. This cannot be changed later.\r\n\r\n> **UTILITY BELT**\r\n> **[Accessory]**\r\n> Well, you’ve gotta put all your cool gadgets somewhere! This item does not function as an extra sylladex slot. You can, however, narratively put cool rocks in it!\r\n> +1 APP / -1 HUB\r\n\r\n> **POWER GLOVES**\r\n> **[Gloves]**\r\n> Super cool and thick gloves! For doing the tasks your bare hands can’t handle, like lifting buildings or dropping someone into a volcano. The possibilities are endless!\r\n> +1 GRT / -1 IMG\r\n\r\n> FLAPPY CAPE\r\n> **[Accessory]**\r\n> Yeah, the move’s name is ‘NO CAPES,’ buuuut this one is pretty sweet! Just make sure to avoid any spinning blades.\r\n> +1 PLC / -1 GRA\r\n\r\n'),
('noCompromise', 'NO COMPROMISE', 'RAGE', 'RAGE', '[Aspect][Basic][Free][Locked: Rage]', 'It’s your way or no way, got it?! When someone rolls to **[Manipulate]** you, you can give a conditional BUT ONLY IF… to your manipulator. This counts as a **GOOD** WORDPLAY roll to **[Manipulate]** right back at the target. If the target refuses to do as you say, their **[Manipulate]** roll also fails, and they gain no associated benefits from a successful **[Manipulate]** roll. You, in turn, gain **1 [WHAM]** and **1 [Boost]** as you revel in righteous disdain.'),
('noExceptions', 'NO EXCEPTIONS', 'DOOM', 'DOOM', '[Aspect][Basic][Reaction][Unblockable][Locked: Doom]', 'Break the rules? No. When your opponent activates an ability that would allow them to circumvent a **[Nerf]**, **[Buff]**, or **[Emotion]**… it doesn’t work. You can’t just decide you’re not affected, that’s not how the world works.'),
('noGodOnEarth', 'NO GOD ON EARTH', 'FUCHSIA', 'FUCHSIA', '[Fuchsia][Basic][Reaction]', 'There’s only one thing in this universe that you fear, and she’s not here. Nothing can touch you. Nothing dares to try. You can choose to reverse the flow of Emotion effects back to the person who tried to give them to you. Shoo. Get away. All hail the queen.\n\n'),
('noNeedForAlarm', 'NO NEED FOR ALARM', 'OTHER', 'SERVICESQUIRE', '[Template][Basic][One-Off][Manipulate][Locked: Servicesquire]', 'Now now, let’s remember- there’s no need to get upset! How about a nice cup of tea? Anyone? Tea? There. Much better, right? This move can be used on yourself, and you can choose to exclude targets from the move. When you want to calm everyone down, roll **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Apparently, there is a need for alarm. Carry on! Any **[Negative]** or **[Neutral]** Emotion felt by trolls present (yourself included) is **[Heightened]**. If there are trolls present without a **[Negative]** or **[Neutral]** Emotion effect, you make them **[Enraged]**. Blast. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: Nobody’s listening to you. Terrible butler! Stupid!\r\n\r\n**OK**: Well… it’s not what you were going for, but everyone feels slightly encouraged. Any allied troll present with an Emotion effect gains **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Everyone takes a deep breath. If a troll present was experiencing an Emotion, it lowers by one stage, removing the Emotion if it wasn’t **[Heightened]**. Those without any Emotional conditions become **[Peaceful]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Your words are comforting and zen. Every troll with an Emotion instead becomes **[Peaceful]**. Trolls without an Emotion become **[Serene]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You’re right, Jeeves. I will calm down. What should I do? Every troll present becomes **[Serene]**, and you get the effects of a **MAX** WORDPLAY roll on any troll who wasn’t experiencing an Emotion.'),
('nonstop', 'NONSTOP', 'TIME', 'TIME', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Time]', 'You don’t ever drop your guard, and you don’t ever wait for other people to get the drop on you. You always go first in a fight— always. Even if there’s no way you should be able to, like when a **[Hidden]** target is about to jump out at you and you’re unaware of their presence… you just get this urge to move, to DO something about it. If you have a move which would already let you go first no matter what in an encounter, you gain **1 [WHAM]** at the start of a fight.'),
('noRush', 'NO RUSH', 'SPACE', 'SPACE', '[Aspect][Basic][Free][Locked: Space]', 'When it comes to the journey versus the destination… you much prefer the journey! Why would you want to get to the destination, if the destination means it all ends..? You’d rather just float aimlessly and let worlds pass you by. When a strife begins, you can choose to go last; if you do this, you get a **[Free]** **GREAT** PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll against all other combatants as you take a moment to carefully observe what’s going on before you act.'),
('notAsIDo', 'NOT AS I DO', 'BLOOD', 'BLOOD', '[Aspect][Basic][Locked: Blood]', 'You’re pretty solid at giving advice, which would rule if you could follow it yourself and fix your absolute trainwreck of a life. You can voluntarily fuck up a roll in order to absolutely eat shit and set a bad example for others, **[Tiering Down]** your result; anyone present who witnesses it can do the same roll on their next move, **[Tiered Up]** as they learn from your mistakes. However, if they roll anything else, their result is also **[Tiered Down]** as they’re overwhelmed by pity for your terrible situation. This can only be used to **[Tier Down]** UNIVERSAL MOVES. Don’t make a troll pity you for not having psionics! No! Bad goldblood!'),
('notFromAroundHere', 'NOT FROM AROUND HERE', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Passive][Locked: Deep-Sea]', 'You are—! That is to say, um. Well… it\'s hard to really say! Deep-Sea Violets are rare to see in any civilised place, considering they so often lurk in total solitude at the depths of the ocean. So, uh… people generally aren\'t used to you! And though you\'re not all that used to them, either, you think you\'ve figured out how you relate to the rest of society. When you take this move, choose one of the following options:\r\n\r\n> **FIT IN**: You are so so normal so regular. Look, you even engage in conventionally acceptable seadweller activities, like a regular violet and not some kind of swampbeast that just crawled out of the primordial ooze! You take the **[Entry]** move of one other Violet tree now - you don\'t gain any **[Talents]** from it, though, and don\'t unlock any other moves from the tree since you are still, in fact, mostly a swampbeast. Your Wealth also decreases to RICH, and if you pick DIVINE RIGHT OF FISH, your FIEFDOM can only grant you abilities up to the **20 LUX** mark - geez, it costs a lot to maintain a lifestyle every other violet\'s spent their whole life gradually assembling.\r\n\r\n> **STAND OUT**: You\'re not like other trolls! You are... actually incredibly different from other trolls, and you aren\'t getting any closer to being like them, either. All **[Analyze]** and **[Manipulate]** rolls against you are **[Inept]** as people struggle to figure out what your deal is. You may also take a second option from SUBPHOTIC VARIANT, leaning more into the eldritch side of your heritage.'),
('noTimeToLose', 'NO TIME TO LOSE', 'TIME', 'TIME', '[Aspect][Passive][Unlock: Time]', 'You’re not the kind of person to sit back and let things happen; you’re a goal driven, action-seeking person. Whoever said the journey is more important than the goal is full of shit- it doesn’t matter how much you suffer or enjoy yourself in the process. The finished project is all that matters. When you enter a fight, you are always **[Quickened]** on your first turn as you rush to get to action. If you were already **[Quickened]**, you gain an extra action anyway.'),
('notOfThisWorld', 'NOT OF THIS WORLD', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Ultra][Psionic][Locked: Haunted]', 'You sometimes feel like… you aren\'t meant to be from around here, are you… like you\'d be more at home in the realm of the dead… hehehe… that\'s okay… Rusts die so easily that… you won\'t need to wait long… right..? You gain access to HERO MODE through your RESPLENDENT RASCALITY. You gain access to the GHOST template even though you aren\'t dead; instead, you may take an action to astrally project your spirit from you as an action. When you GO GHOST, you count as a ghost, but only while separate from your body. You may take an action to return to your body and return to normal. You do not count as **[Cullbait]**, as you are useful to the empire as a future bullet resistant foot soldier. You gain the **[Unlock]** and one **[Basic]** move when you gain this move and this does not count towards your **[Template]** limit. If you spend levels to take more moves, the **GHOST [Template]** then counts towards the limit, but the **[Template] [Ultra]** does not count towards your **[Ultra]** cap. If you already have an **[Eerie] [Template]** you may only gain the **[Unlock]** and the **[Basic]** moves. Rather than taking on the full immunity to **[Somatic]** damage of ghosts, you gain **1 [Somatic] [Resistance]**. The spirit world seems to know you have one foot in the world of the living and dead, after all… All rollable moves in the template use **+RAS**. If you die… you don\'t actually become a ghost. You just get up later. You are immune to death, whether Just or Heroic; you simply wake up the next day, as if awakening from a beautiful dream. If your killer sees you, they\'re immediately **[Terrified]**. Hello again… old friend… remember me..?'),
('notScientificallyPossible', 'NOT SCIENTIFICALLY POSSIBLE', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Scienceling]', 'Hold on a moment. You\'re pretty sure magic isn\'t fucking real. There must be some misunderstanding here. Not to worry; this is a fringe case, and can easily be noted as an anomaly. Perhaps some kind of bizarre psionics..? Whatever, this is clearly an anomaly, and one you need to cover up quickly. All **[Magic]** rolls are **[Inept]** against you. Stop that.'),
('notWorthYourTime', 'NOT WORTH YOUR TIME', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'C\'mon, dude. It\'s just a rustblood. Who cares? There\'s like, a million of them. That\'s the vibe you try to give to people definitely trying to rock your shit. LET\'S STRIFE rolls to ORDER UP against you are **[Inept]** because of how unkempt or tired you look, and your WORDPLAY rolls on the first turn of combat are **[Tiered Up]**. Hey, hey, let\'s talk about this!'),
('notYourTime', 'NOT YOUR TIME', 'OTHER', 'DECOMPOSITIONIST', '[Template][Ultra][Passive][Last Stand][Locked: Decompositionist]', 'Nobody decides when you die except you. That is the conviction that your faith in death has given you, and one that is bolstered by the dead that speak to you. One day, you shall know sleep, but now you stand awake and appreciating life as you have it. You gain an additional amount of HP equal to your **+PLC**. If you are **[Talented]** at the stat, you gain access to HERO MODE through your PERFECT PULCHRITUDE. If you weren\'t, you become **[Talented]** now. Finally, the dead won\'t accept you coming to them soon, and rally to your aid; a ghostly choir of dead Decompositonists rise as you fall. When you hit **0 HP**, you are healed for **2 HP**, and you immediately summon the PARANORMAL ACTIVITY Hazard. Clean your wounds and allow the deceased to save you.\r\n\r\n'),
('noveltysWornOff', 'NOVELTY’S WORN OFF', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][One-Off][Manipulate]', 'Ooooh, a violet death ray! So scary! Oh, let me guess– the villains are gonna be a group of Juggalos in some weird death ritual for Insane Clown Posse, right? You’ve been to Alternia a couple of times now, and you cease to be impressed by some of the tropier aspects. In fact, hell, you’ll be blunt, and call out uncreative stuff to the alien murder princes faces, if you need to! When you want to tell someone to get new material, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Oh no! You give them some great ideas, and they put them into effect! Your target is **[Passionate]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Yeah… they really don’t give a shit.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Huh… that hurt their feelings. The target takes **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Owch! The target doesn’t take this well! They feel **[Sad]** for **2 turns**. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Hit them where it STINGS. The target is **[Sad]** for the encounter.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Damn, dude, did you, like… mean to go that hard? The target breaks down **[Crying]** for the encounter.'),
('noYouDont', 'NO YOU DON\'T', 'OTHER', 'PRINCE', '[Class][Basic][Reaction][Strife][Locked: Prince]\r\n', 'Are they pulling out a… a turret? HAH. Did they really think you would just stand around sucking your thumb and watch them build a robot like this is turn based combat? When an opponent (or even an ally if you\'re really that much of a bulgewad, I don\'t control you) takes an item from their sylladex, you may spend a **[Reaction]** to make an immediate **[Strife]** roll against that object. They do not have to tell you what the item is before you do this. On a **MAX** you may choose to knock the item out of their hands instead of dealing normal damage.\n\n'),
('nyassassinate', 'NYASSASSINATE', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Physical][Strife][Locked: Nyanjutsu]', 'Living on a planet as dangerous as Alternia brings the risk of meeting all sorts of lethal murderers. Or maybe YOU’RE the lethal murderer, a paid assassin ready to strike at a moment’s notice! One way or another, you use a combat style that doesn\'t need to hit hard, just accurately. When you want to attack someone with deadly precision, roll **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Not only do you miss, but you stumble around and lose your momentum too! That’s terrible! You take **1 [Somatic]** damage and **3 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You whiff your attack completely, and while you avoid hurting yourself, you lose some of your accuracy. You take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You don’t hurt the opponent much, but you do graze them! Next time, you can hit them in the same place for a more punishing blow; you gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: THWONK! You do **1 [Somatic]** damage to the opponent.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You get them right in a weak spot, and it smarts! You do **2 [Somatic]** damage, or do 1 damage and give them **1 [Weakness]** to **[Somatic]** damage for a turn!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Your weapon strikes your opponent so hard they start looking like they’re from a cheesy East-Alternian samurai movie, what with how much blood they’re gushing. You do **3 [Somatic]** damage, or **2 damage** and cause them to become **[Bloodied]**.'),
('oathkeeper', 'OATHKEEPER', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Passive][Locked: Paladin]', 'As a guardian of the Empire, its subjects and of the cultural history of the Trollic race, you have sworn an oath to uphold the values befitting someone of your stature, as have all the rest who walk in your footsteps. You live by these words lest your honor be run ragged and your classmates make fun of you behind your back at the student council meetings. Choose an oath from the list below to specialize yourself in your path forward.\r\n\r\n> **OATH OF STABILITY**: Society marches onwards, but it is a march. Not a sprint. Dangerous, radical ideas must be fought back to allow them to disseminate properly without chaos in the streets. All **[Strife]** rolls against **[Mechanical]** targets such as ROBOTS or toasters have a **+3 [Buff]**.\r\n\r\n> **OATH OF STEWARDSHIP**: While it is known that the high rule and the low serve, \"rule\" does not mean \"exterminate\" despite the beliefs of some of the seadwelling aristocracy. When acting in defense of the weak, such as lowbloods simply serving dutifully, the ill or the desperate, you may spend a **[Lengthy]** action to nullify all damage they take for a turn on a **[One-Off]**.\r\n\r\n> **OATH OF MIRACLES**: Magic is a mysterious force that has wicked, if beautiful effects on society. Some reject its existence, some wield it to further faith, and you walk the middle line of ensuring neither takes the advantage over the other. Nevertheless, you still get blasted by magic sometimes. All **[Magic]** moves are **[Inept]** against you, and you get **+1 [Boost]** if someone uses a **[Magic]** effect around you.\r\n\r\n> **OATH OF PURIFICATION**: Peppersteak is your dish of choice, and the spirits are howling. Dark forces creep across Alternia, and the Church cannot be relied upon solely for it. You gain **1 [WHAM]** every **3 turns** when in combat against **[Eerie]** trolls, Entities or Purple Esotericists as you push the darkness back.\r\n\r\n> **OATH OF BEASTSLAYING**: BACK, YON FIEND! To allow Gulchscourge to be sacked by monsters is something you simply can\'t stand by! Snazzards, Grublords, the lot of them… you must keep them from entering the city walls with your might! Your attacks against creatures with a vulnerability to **[Energy]** damage count as 2 in terms of triggering that vulnerability, and you have a **+2 [Buff]** to **[Strife]** rolls against Lusii and Moonbarks.\r\n\r\n> **OATH OF REALITY-ANCHORAGE**: Unreality is a terrible thing, and you won\'t stand idly as it is torn asunder! Whenever you witness a troll using **[Zodiac]** abilities or **[Glitchy]** attacks, you gain **1 [WHAM]**.'),
('objectionFunk', 'OBJECTION FUNK', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Passive][Locked: Splattorney]', 'Ob-ob-objection! You gotta be able to use the buzzwords that get the jury (see: audience) pumped at your trials, or nobody is going to give all that much of a shit about it. That\'s a bad thing! As such, you\'ve picked up some VERY useful phrases that make everyone think you\'re hot shit. You gain the following WORDPLAY effects.\r\n\r\n> OBJECTION! You deny an opponent\'s statement, shouting loud and distracting everyone from what they just said. You retroactively **[Tier Down]** an opponent\'s WORDPLAY roll. On a **GREAT**, they take **1 [Drag]** too, and on a **MAX**, they take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> HOLD IT! Now what did you mean by that..? No, no, go on. You corner the opponent, pushing them to keep talking. The opponent must use WORDPLAY on their next turn. On a **GREAT**, they are **[Inept]** at their WORDPLAY roll. On a **MAX**, they are **[Godawful]**.\r\n\r\n> TAKE THAT! You whip out an item from the opponent\'s Sylladex, linking it into the case somehow. You must make up something about the item in one sentence; for example, presenting a Medicalizer and stating that they used it to heal their injuries after committing a murder. You then pocket the item, adding it to your own Sylladex. On a **GREAT**, the target is **[Confused]** for a round, and on a **MAX**, **[Confused]** for the encounter.'),
('oblivious', 'OBLIVIOUS', 'HOPE', 'HOPE', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Hope]', 'To put this delicately… You are a dreamer. To you, the world is perfect— or at least, is pretty close to it, so long as your friends are on your side! As such, you tend to… avoid reading between the lines, whether you realize it or not, in order to keep your illusions intact. You gain **1 [Resistance]** against all **[Verbal]** damage as you take insults at face value and refuse to analyze them.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('obtainBogle', 'OBTAIN BOGLE', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Passive][Locked: Esotericist]', 'In many ancient texts you\'ve procured, there are instructions on how to summon a BOGLE, a familiar who will guide your magical studies. And you\'ve done just that! Whether it\'s a creature you summoned from another world, an entity you crafted through alchemical experimentation, or just a frog you evolved with runestones, your BOGLE is YOUR best friend when it comes to occult rituals! Your BOGLE has **2 HP**; if slain, it dissolves into slime, and resurrects at midnight. You can give your BOGLE the following commands, which they follow until otherwise commanded:\r\n\r\n> **HEEL**: Your BOGLE hides in your pockets, becoming immune to all damage.\r\n> **SCOUT**: Your BOGLE goes to a location you command. You see through its eyes.\r\n> **FETCH**: Your BOGLE retrieves you an item! You steal back an item that has been removed from your inventory by an enemy, and gives opponents who try to take items a **-2 [Nerf]**.\r\n> **HARANGUE**: Your BOGLE gnaws some ankles, giving a target a **-1 [Nerf]** to every other roll.\r\n> **DISTRACT**: Your BOGLE **[Fascinates]** a target who was not in combat with you.\r\n> **EMPOWER**: Your BOGLE gives you a **+1 [Buff]** to every other **[Magic]** roll you make.'),
('officeHierarchy', 'OFFICE HIERARCHY', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Passive][Locked: Penpusher]\r\n', 'Ambition is the name of the game, amigos. You\'re always looking to prove yourself a real catch to the empire, but since there\'s not exactly… a boss to suck up to in the fake made up offices Teals LARP work experience in on Alternia… the only way to figure out how good you are at your job is to see HOW MANY FIGHTS YOU WIN. You have a pool of points called **OFFICE REP**, which track your losses and victories in a **[Strife]** from here on out. Every time you win a **[Strife]** encounter, gain **1 OFFICE REP**. Every time you fail one, lose 1. This is tripled against other Penpusher trolls. You gain the following benefits depending on how many OR points you have. \r\n\r\n> **FIRED!!! (-3 OR)** AW, JEEZ! You suck at fighting, and now your peers have ousted you! You become Destitute and **[Inept]** at **[Strife]** rolls. Other Teals will always know your mark of shame. Unless, like, you win some fights. You can\'t be fired unless you previously had a position of GRUNT WORKER or higher.\r\n\r\n> **TRAINEE (0 OR)** Everyone has to start somewhere, and your first lesson is: mediocrity is better than failure! You get OK rolls on a 6-10 instead of an 8-10.\r\n\r\n> **GRUNT WORKER (3 OR)** You\'re pretty rank and file at this point. And you\'ve perfected doing perfectly average rather than exceptionally poor. You lose the previous effects, and get a GOOD roll on a 9-13 instead of an 11-13.\r\n\r\n> **SENIOR EMPLOYEE (10 OR)** Is that… a glint of ambition in your eye..? Surely you don\'t intend on… climbing above and beyond your peers? You lose the move\'s previous effects, and get a GREAT roll on a 12-19 instead of a 14-19.\r\n\r\n> **OFFICE SUPERVISOR (20 OR)** You\'re doing it! Now even SENIOR WORKERS are below you! You\'re really doing it! You lose the move\'s previous effects, and get a GOOD on a 9-11, and a GREAT on a 12-19. \r\n\r\n> **DEPARTMENT LEAD (50 OR)** Good heavens. Now you\'re one of the biggest, baddest, most experienced workers in your department, and everyone hates you. This rules. You keep the effects of the previous move, and are now **[Talented]** at all **[Strife]** rolls. If you were an INSURANCE AGENT, you give targets **1 [Drag]** on a GREAT GRIEF roll.\r\n\r\n> **EXEC (100 OR)** This is it. You\'re basically the king of the office right now. All other Teals rolls against you are **[Tiered Down]**, except for other EXECs. You now have the Rich Wealth level.\r\n\r\n> **SUPER-EXEC (150 OR)** AW SHIT WE\'RE IN EGO-TERRITORY NOW. Only other Super-Exec rolls aren\'t **[Tiered Down]** against you. Every time you win another 50 fights, add an additional SUPER to your title, update which Teals aren\'t **[Tiered Down]** against you. For example, if you had 500 OR, you\'d be a SUPER-SUPER-SUPER-SUPER-SUPER-SUPER-SUPER-SUPER-EXEC, or SUPER^8-EXEC, and only other SUPER^8-EXECs would be immune to your **[Tier Down]** effect. Phew!\r\n'),
('ohohoho', 'OHOHOHO', 'LIGHT', 'LIGHT', '[Aspect][Basic][Free][Recharge: 1][Locked: Light]', 'You can’t help but gloat when someone isn’t doing as well as they’d thought they would. You might not mean it in a vindictive way, but it can certainly come across as that if you’re not careful. When someone would take **[Drag]**, you can let out a dry and derisive remark, a witty jab or an anime villain laugh as you watch destiny forsake them. They take an extra **1 [Drag]**.'),
('ohPsyche', 'OH PSYCHE', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Recharge: 3][Locked: Cool Kid]', 'Oh no! You\'re about to fuck up immensely! This is the WORST POSSIBLE THI— OH PSYCHE! You didn\'t do the fuck up! You survived to fuck up another day instead! Your quick reflexes mean you aren\'t prone to failure; if you made a poor roll on your first action (or even second if you are **[Quickened]**), you can retroactively give yourself and use an amount of **[Boost]** you\'d need to turn your previous roll into a **GOOD**. You gain double the amount of **[Drag]** in return. For example, if you rolled a 7 on your previous roll, you could raise it to a **GOOD**, but take **4 [Drag]** back. It\'s like **[Boost]** credit.'),
('ohSoInfamous', 'OH SO INFAMOUS', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'You leave a hell of an impression on people when you\'ve whooped some ass, and by now, you\'re kind of known by most people now. Not always for good shit, but hey, who cares, right? Being known is its own reward, and if you really want to fix your reputation, you\'ve got time. When people want to learn facts about you through **[Analyze]** rolls, secretly roll a 1d8. On an odd result, you can lie about what they know, giving them rumours about the things you\'ve done or failed to do, whatever benefits you most. Additionally, when in a combat encounter with someone you\'ve beaten in a fight before, you start with **2 [Boost]**. This only works the first time after that fight that you rematch. After all, you\'ve got a reputation to uphold here!'),
('olReliable', 'OL\' RELIABLE', 'HOPE', 'HOPE', '[Aspect][Basic][Locked: Hope]', 'If it ain\'t broke, why fix it? You have learned to stick to the methods that you know work and are likely to succeed. While leaving things up to chance has the possibility of doing amazing, it also has the possibility of failure, and that\'s not a possibility you\'re willing to risk. Choose a Universal Move that you are already **[Talented]** at. You can forgo rolling this move and simply spend an action to get a **GOOD** result.'),
('omnidisciplinaryScientist', 'OMNIDISCIPLINARY SCIENTIST', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Free][Mental][Unlock: Scienceling]', 'They call you mad! Like, all the time! Presently, even. It\'s bullshit, you\'re totally sane. Anyway, wanna see a brain hooked up to a speaker so it can scream in agony? You\'re a Scienceling, training to one day be a Sciencelord of the Alternian Fleet. You\'re good at ALL science, and you\'re a fucking genius. You are **[Talented]** at **+PSP**. Whenever you get a **GREAT** or **MAX** **+PSP** roll, you gain **1 EUREKA**, a type of **[Hold]**. You spend your EUREKAS in any amount and combination at the start of your turn. You can spend EUREKAs to gain the following effects…\r\n\r\n> **ACCELERATED CHARGING**: Decrease a move\'s **[Recharge]** by 1. This costs **1 EUREKA**.\r\n> **ENTROPY NUDGE**: Get a +2 on a roll you just made. This costs **2 EUREKA**.\r\n> **CAREFUL CALCULATION**: You see what you can see… you roll PROBLEM SLEUTHING twice. This costs **2 EUREKA**.\r\n> **REGENERATIVE WHEEZE**: Reduce damage of an attack you took last turn by 1. This costs **3 EUREKA**.\r\n> **BLOAD UP**: Do +1 **[Glitchy]** damage on a **[Strife]** roll. This costs **3 EUREKA**.\r\n> **EFFICIENCY BREAKTHROUGH**: Use a move that you\'ve already used the **[One-Off]** for. This costs **4 EUREKA**.'),
('onBeat', 'ON BEAT', 'TIME', 'TIME', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Time]', 'Go. Go. Go. GO. GO. GO. There is no stopping, there is no smelling the roses. You don\'t even see the roses, just this guy you really need to have been on the ground about five minutes ago so you could get to the next one. **[Analyze]**, **[Chicanery]**, **[Flourish]**, and **[Strife]** moves all have a rhythm of their own, and you can tap into that rhythm to hit harder (better, faster, stronger). When you roll a move of one of these types that you rolled the previous round, you gain a **+1 [Buff]** to your next roll of a move of that type. The effect dissipates if you break your streak. This does not stack and cannot be active for more than one type (**[Analyze]**, **[Chicanery]**, **[Flourish]**, and **[Strife]**) at a time - You. Just. Do. This. One. Thing. Again. And Again. And Again. And Again. And Again.'),
('oneLittleLie', 'ONE LITTLE LIE', 'MIND', 'MIND', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Mind]', 'For whatever reason, you have to compensate sometimes by stretching the truth. Maybe you put up a persona in your day to day life that’s comically obvious; maybe you hide the fact that you’re the kismesis of a garbage man clown. Either way, choose to be either an excellent liar or a terrible one. If you are an excellent liar, any **[Analyze]** roll to figure out if you are lying is **[Inept]**; meanwhile, if you are a terrible liar, the first time in an encounter someone tries to roll an **[Analyze]** move on you, they merely note that you’re definitely lying about something irrelevant and obvious, even if that’s not what they were asking. Like, no shit you don’t actually need those glasses, you only wear them when you’re trying to look smart!'),
('oneOfAKind', 'ONE OF A KIND', 'RAGE', 'RAGE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Rage]', 'You take some pride in your originality; your refusal to conform to well-accepted methods and ways of doing things has actually unearthed some more experimental approaches to everyday life. Choose two Universal moves that both are either **[Physical]** or **[Mental]**; you can swap the stats associated with them (for example, rolling **+RAS** to GRIEF as you play dirty and **+GRT** to SHENANIGANS as you force your effects through). If either Universal Move\'s stat is a +0, you gain a **+1 [Buff]** to roll it.'),
('onetrollWorkforce', 'ONE-TROLL WORKFORCE', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Labourer]', 'Nothing will EVER stop you. You\'re a walking factory, the backbone of your farm, etcetera etcetera. You never quit, never rest, and work until your bones break. Maybe it\'s a point of pride? Maybe it\'s because you have to. Whatever the case is… you work to earn the right to work, and you work HARD. You gain access to HERO MODE through your AWESOME APPETITE. Your **VP** increases to 12, letting you carry even more stuff with you at all times. When you GET TO WORK, you reeeeally GET TO WORK. Your timer no longer goes down on its own— hell, you could GET TO WORK for weeks on end if you needed to! Instead, it clocks down whenever you get an **OK** or lower roll. So long as you keep succeeding, you\'ll never stop, you little Stakhanovite, you. Using MADE OF STEEL still counts the timer down. While you GET TO WORK, you can access RESPLENDENT RASCALITY, MYTHIC MANGRIT, GLORIOUS GRACE, and HARDCORE HUBRIS as well as AWESOME APPETITE, except all rolls here use **+APP**. Using these other HERO MODES count your timer down by 2. You may be a one-troll workforce, but know the risks of such neverending labour!'),
('onlineSexytroll', 'ONLINE SEXYTROLL', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Passive][Locked: Fanyatic]', 'Cosplay? More like cosbae! Fandoms are full to the brim with the iconic SEXYTROLLS, fan favourite characters who can make anyone\'s heart flutter. And it is YOUR sacred duty to amass outfits based on these enigmatic rogues and dress up as them! You gain access to the SEXYTROLL STYLE Fashion Item which gives +1 RAS and -1 HUB, which can be worn on any part of the body. Once you fill out every single fashion item slot, you can turn it into the following Fashion Collection: \r\n\r\n> **TRUE SEXYTROLL**: (All fashion item slots used, including SEXYTROLL STYLE) **[Stat changes remain the same, but any stats that go over stat cap are now reassigned as normal for a Fashion Collection]** You\'re a living, breathing SEXYTROLL! You may change your **[Talent]** to the highest stat you have with this cosplay, including the HERO MODE if applicable. If your highest stat is **+RAS**, the stat cap there is changed to +5, not +4. When you beat someone in a fight, they are exposed to SIMPTOMS for your fandom.'),
('onlineSlang', 'ONLINE SLANG', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'WWWWWWW XD GGWP every1! J/K J/K u ppl SUX lololol get pwned N00bz! KYS ASAP ROFL lol anyway bbl cya! Huh? Oh, sorry, you were on headset with some other Golds. What\'s up? The internet has its own language, and you are fluent in it. You gain the following WORDPLAY options.\r\n\r\n> **LEETSPEAK**: //47(|-| 0(_)7 |-|3\'5 907 2 //|-|4|/|! What the fuck? You say a load of numbers and letters, and nobody understands… aside from anyone else with this move or the Hackerman template! Good for secret messages… sometimes..? You get **3 [Boost]** if someone actually understands you.\r\n\r\n> **HURTFUL JABBERING**: KYAHAHA! You **[Heighten]** the target\'s **[Negative]** emotion. \r\n\r\n> **W.PLAY**: You abbreviate everything you say, and say it fast! You get two WORDPLAY effects but are **[Tired]** afterward.\r\n\r\n> **LOUD GIBBON LIKE SHRIEKING**: Oh god. What is it now? You retroactively **[Tier Down]** the target\'s last WORDPLAY roll, so long as it was made the last turn.'),
('onTopOfThings', 'ON TOP OF THINGS', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Passive]', 'How’s THIS for average, huh? After being dismissed so many times, you’ve found that you’ve actually got a real skill in places people might not expect you to. That’ll show them for making assumptions! You become **[Talented]** at a **[Downtime]** move of your choosing, so long as you weren’t already **[Talented]** in it.'),
('oraclintelligence', 'ORACLINTELLIGENCE', 'JADE', 'ADULT', '[Jade][Passive][Locked: Adult]\r\nREQUIREMENTS: CIS', 'Welcome to the Commissary of Intergalactic Security; the CIS. You don\\\'t need to have been a member of the junior division; if you\\\'re here now, then the Empire has recognized your talent for spying. As a member of the Trollic Empire\\\'s internal security system, you act as a shadow of the Empire, operating within the shadows of outer-space (there’s a lot of those, actually) and by extension are skilled in espionage - as such, you may borrow the **SUSPICIOUS STRANGER** entry move and one other move from the HET **[Template]**. Any free space in your sylladex is filled with Spybugs from the move **BUGGED BUGS**, even when in a disguise. After all, what better way to keep an eye on someone than to bug them yourself? Your rolls against enemies on the **CIS WATCHLIST** are given a +2 **[Buff]** as well, as even the ruthless lawlessness of space is under your careful eye. '),
('orderInTheCourt', 'ORDER IN THE COURT', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Splattorney]', 'And that, ladies and gentletrolls, is how you get a verdict. You are famous for your pristine record, people all over tune in to watch your cases, and let\'s be clear here: you\'re kind of a big deal! Nobody in their right mind wants to go up against you; you ALWAYS make trials go the way you want. You gain access to HERO MODE through your… PRECISE PERSPICACITY? Except you use **+PLC** in all rolls affected by the HERO MODE. Huh. I suppose being a force of deduction is more important than being pretty in the courtroom. Regardless,  your fame lets you push your weight around pretty substantially in the courtroom in ways you wouldn\'t be able to if you weren\'t at the level you\'re at. Whenever votes are called upon in a SHOWTRIAL, you may also vote, and you may advise the JUDGE on the punishment the guilty party receives, allowing the JURY to vote between the JUDGE’s option and yours. Finally, you can cycle through the stances from LEGAL TRAINING as an action. Be ready for anything!'),
('organicVariant', 'ORGANIC VARIANT', 'OTHER', 'MUTANT', '[Mutant][Cullbait][Passive]', 'Your anatomy is different from what is most commonly seen. You may have multiples of the same organ or missing ones, your blood may be laced with acid or even syrup; maybe your anatomy decided to go the extra mile and give you a mouth on your stomach or even feelers on your hands reminiscent of the deadly toxin of a Gympie plant. Maybe you have scales like a shark’s! Regardless, the possibilities are truly endless. Choose an option below that fits your mutation.\n\n> **TOUGH STUFF**:  Whether it be hardened skin or an extra blood pusher, you\'re harder to kill than most! When above half your **HP** you have +1 **[Somatic] [Resistance]**. Once you go below half **HP**, you lose the resistance for the rest of the encounter, even if you **[Heal]** back up. You also have a - 2 **[Nerf]** to all **PLC** rolls as your strange appearance is unsettling!\n\n> **EXTRA LIMBS:** You\'re a one troll army with all those arms! Or perhaps you have a tail? No matter what it is, you get +1 **[Buff]** to **[Strife]** and **[Chicanery]** rolls, though you are given a -2 **[Nerf]** on **+GRA** rolls as your body wasn\'t built to keep balance with these add ons!'),
('originalCharacter', 'ORIGINAL CHARACTER', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Passive][Cullbait][Unlock: Mary Sue]', 'You\'re the coolest ever. \r\n\r\nThis is no exaggeration; you are simply the coolest bitch on Alternia. You have so many quadrants, you’re so good at fighting, and you have the coolest one-liners anyone can think of! Even the strongest, toughest people out there better watch out, because you’re basically perfect!\r\n\r\n…\r\n\r\nOkay, fine, you’re probably a depressed teen in a basement. Look, let’s get some stuff out of the way. You’re a Lime, and Lime lives kinda suck. Sometimes, you just wish that you did live this cool life, where everyone has romantic feelings for you, and you’re immune to bullets and stuff like that. When people make super strong awesome characters everyone likes because they want to imagine themselves being that. It’s escapism, it’s wish fulfilment, and it’s written for the enjoyment of the writer, not the reader. You’re like that, except with, y’know. Reality itself. You are so awesome that you are **[Talented]** at **+RAS**. Oh, also, you gain any one **[Ultra]** caste move, which does not take up an **[Ultra]** slot. No, this is not a joke. You gain all benefits of the move, including access to the HERO MODE listed in the move. You gain benefits of other moves only if they are listed and upgraded in the **[Ultra]**. If your chosen **[Ultra]** would give you **[Cullbait]** or **[Eerie]** Templates or moves that lack the respective tags, you still do not gain **[Eerie]** or **[Cullbait]** as per the move as the effects you gain are transparently fake. That Gone Grimdark is bright purple! That third limb is a fake! When your HP is above half, you look garishly fake, with weirdly coloured hair or eyes, strange clothes or other very obvious signs of your wish fulfilment. If you are ever brought down below **half HP**, you lose all benefits from the **[Ultra]** immediately, and return to your normal appearance (depressed basement teen, that’s you!)'),
('orisonics', 'ORISONICS', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Magic][Strife][Locked: Cloistered]', 'You have gained the power of MAGIC, divine and true, powered by the holy power of her Wriggling Matriarch. Bound in ancient tomes that look, to many, like old, trashy magazines about outdated boy bands, the secrets of the universe bend to these sweet spells you can cast! Magic is real as shit, dude! And it’s all thanks to the holy worm who lays eggs nonstop forever! When you want to cast a holy spell, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: IMPURE! Your holy tome’s connection to the mystic link of the Mothergrub short circuits, and your powers backfire against you! You take **2 [Psychic]** damage and are **[Stunned]**. Self-smite!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Are you RIGHTEOUS enough to wield this power? Huh, infidel? Suck on that for a moment as your magic burns you.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Oops! You just read an article on Troll Nick Carter instead of a spell. Your opponent takes **1 [Drag]** regardless, cuz hearing that sucked.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Glory be to the worm queen! You deal **1 [Holy]** **[Psychic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: HOSANNA IN THE DEEPEST! Your holy magic wracks the opponent, dealing **2 [Holy]** **[Psychic]** damage, or doing **1 [Holy]** **[Psychic]** damage and **[Overwhelming]** the opponent for a turn.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: IA! IA! PH\'NGLUI MGEPOG EPAGLOGG OT ALTH\'ERNIA FHALMA GR\'UB AH FHTAGN! Whoa. That was weird. Anyway… your magic surges and you become a divine conduit for the earth for a moment, unleashing the wrath of worms on your opponent. You deal **3 [Holy]** **[Psychic]** damage, expose the target to **[Sensory Overload]** for **2 turns** and leave them **[Overwhelmed]** afterward.'),
('orphan', 'ORPHAN', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive]', 'YOUR LUSUS WAS KIIIIIILLED! You live a life sans lusus; it’s a risky one, and technically could get you in some hot water if you were found out (trolls without lusii are often considered cullbait, and hunted as such); but you’ve learned to cope. Decide how you’ve coped by selecting one of the effects below:\r\n\r\n> **CLOSED OFF**: You don’t trust anyone. **[Manipulate]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n> **PITY POINTS**: Boo-hoo-hoo! Your life sucks, and everyone should be nice to you because of it. People who would usually have benefits that counter **[Manipulation]** don’t get them against you.\r\n\r\n> **TRICKSY**: Life isn’t easy— and you’ve learned to do your best no matter what. Any time you roll a **+RAS** move, you gain **1 [Boost]** on a **GOOD**, **GREAT** or **MAX**.'),
('ouchOofOw', 'OUCH OOF OW', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Aw jeez, internal bleeding again? Oh well. You\'re pretty used to the whole injury thing, and you just kinda roll with it. When you\'re **[Bloodied]**, you can **[Heal]** as normal; until you do **[Heal]**, however, you take **1 extra [Drag]** every time you get a **BAD** or **MIN** roll. Ouch, oof…'),
('outshined', 'OUTSHINED', 'OTHER', 'THIEF', '[Class][Advanced][Reaction][Recharge: 4][Locked: Thief]', 'That was a pretty nice roll someone did there. Maybe a little too nice. You’re in a bit of a pinch, they’re not, so does it matter much if you share in their victory too? After all, they have plenty to go around. As a **[Reaction]**, you can gain the same result/effect of a move that your opponent just rolled on any UNIVERSAL MOVE, or your subsequent **[Strife]** roll if applicable. The rules of having no duplicate **[Strife], [Chicanery], [Flourish]** moves on a single turn still apply to this. \r\n'),
('overclocking', 'OVERCLOCKING', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Reaction][Recharge: 2][Psionic][Locked: Battery]', 'Sometimes, you really don’t wanna leave things to chance, so you absolutely give it your all, turning yourself into a living nuke. You charge your body with your psionics, making your body a living weapon that\'s dangerous to touch... and to inhabit. Overclocking is bad for your computer, dumbass. As a **[Reaction]** to a **[Physical]** attack, you can cause their attack against you to deal **2 [Electric]** **[Somatic]** damage to your opponent, but you take **1 extra [Electric]** **[Somatic]** damage in return.'),
('overtime', 'OVERTIME!', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Worker]', 'Going above and beyond is your specialty, not that you chose that! When the going gets tough, you push yourself to your absolute limit. Whenever you have **4 or less HP** left, you may choose to push into OVERTIME. While in OVERTIME, you become **[Overwhelmed]**. Any move that ISN\'T **[Inept]** becomes **[Talented]**. Any **BAD** roll **[Tiers Down]** to **MIN**, and any **GREAT** roll **[Tiers Up]** to **MAX**.'),
('overwhelmingPresence', 'OVERWHELMING PRESENCE', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][One-Off][Manipulate][Locked: Boss]', 'You know when you’re playing a board game, and the GM says “make a fear save” or something? Yeah. Whether it’s in the way you hold yourself or the stern look in your eyes, people know better than to cross you. Do you really want to throw hands with someone this imposing?! When an opponent tries to fuck with you, you can take an action to loom. The opponent must roll **+APP** as a **[Free]** action.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: They basically shit themselves in fear. Oh, oh god, you’re WAY stronger than they are. They are **[Terrified]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Oh, this was a mistake, wasn’t it? The target becomes **[Scared]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Your size and command of the situation is unnerving, but not debilitating. They take **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: The target keeps their cool, and nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Oh yeah, tough guy? I’m not scared of you! The target gains **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: The target refuses to back down, even in the face of adversity! They gain **3 [Boost]** and become **[Hopeful]**.\r\n\r\n'),
('pactbroker', 'PACTBROKER', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Lengthy][Magic][Locked: Esotericist]', 'Ahh, the contract of power. Once a highly feared tool of the ancient order of Teal Fiendpreachers, but they\'re long erased from polite history. Nowadays, only scholars of the occult know these ancient practices. You draft up some arcane legalese and hand it to an ally, having them sign it. You two enter a pact together; you trade two things of equal value. A pair of **[Basic]** moves? **[Advanced]** ones? Giving one person your **[Boost]**, and taking an equal amount of **[Drag]**? Splitting your HP equally? If you can argue it, and the trade makes sense, you can carry it out. There IS a slight chance this causes a DIMMING STARS Hazard (next time this encounter either of you roll a **MIN**), but hey, what\'s the likelihood of that?'),
('paleblood', 'PALEBLOOD', 'OTHER', 'MUTANT', '[Mutant][Cullbait][Passive]', 'Your blood is a desaturated version of a legal caste, which sometimes leads to lighter horns and nails. Your pastel blood leads to powerful psionics that are a massive detriment to the Empire. They are very strong, yet they are hard to control; and the illegality of such power means that you don’t usually get the chance to learn to control them. Your psionics can be impressive, though, and as such you are **[Talented]** at **+IMG**. If you were already **[Talented]** in **+IMG**, you get **+2 [Buff]** to every **+IMG** roll. With enough practice, your psionics have the potential to match with the strongest telekinetic rusts or Alternia’s most promising golds. This mutation grants you the rust EXTRASENSORY TRICKS move upon creation. However, your blood and psionics are seen as a threat to the Empire; you feel **[Dread]** if you become **[Bloodied]**. Additionally, when using your psionics in combat, your opponent can optionally summon an ANGRY MOB **[Hazard]** of empire-loyal trolls as a **[Reaction]** that will arrive in 5 turns after you first unleash your psionic power.'),
('panachePoints', 'PANACHE POINTS', 'OTHER', 'PAGE', '[Class][Basic][Locked: Page]', 'Look, everyone makes mistakes. That\'s true. But, like, the greatest heroes, uh, learn from their mistakes! They bounce back up from their failures and save the day! And you\'d like to think that you\'re one of those heroes… so you\'ve invented a little confidence booster for yourself. A way to count your failures and remember, hey, you\'re due for a victory sooner or later! You call them Panache Points, which henceforth you\'ll refer to as PP. And let me tell you, you\'ve got the best PP around! You take PP all day!...hey, why are they laughing? Please stop laughing! It\'s making you insecure...Every time you get a **GREAT+** result on a roll, you gain 1 **PP**, which you can spend for success in the future. A **MIN** gives you 2 & a **BAD** gives you 1. Instead of rolling, you may spend these to automatically get a **GOOD** with 2, a **GREAT** with 3, and even a **MAX** with 5.\r\n\r\n'),
('papThat', 'PAP THAT', 'OTHER', 'QUADRANT', '[Quadrant][Physical][Manipulation]\r\n', 'So you\'ve got a moirail! Congratulations, and welcome to the exciting world of taking personal responsibility for someone else\'s crying fits and rages. When in an encounter with your moirail, you gain access to a special ability called PAP, costing one action! Instead of rolling, the effect of PAP strengthens depending on how strong your bond is. \r\n\r\n**NEW QUADS (1-4 IRL WEEKS)**: You may remove one Emotion effect from your moirail, or change a **[Heightened]** Emotion to a **[Base]** one. \r\n\r\n**ESTABLISHED RELATIONSHIP (1-11 IRL MONTHS)**: You remove two Emotion effects, or one **[Heightened]** Emotion.\r\n\r\n**ROCK SOLID (1 YEAR+)**: You remove two Emotion effects, or one **[Heightened]** Emotion, OR break the effects of CHUCKLEVISION or mind control as a **[Reaction]**.\r\n\r\n**QUAD BONDED**: You remove two Emotion effects, or one **[Heightened]** Emotion, break the effects of CHUCKLEVISION or mind control as a **[Reaction]**, OR you can snap them out of BOSS MODE, PRINCELY DETERMINATION mode, or any other non-exitable effects.\r\n'),
('paradigmShift', 'PARADIGM SHIFT', 'OTHER', 'BARD', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Bard]', 'YOU’RE NOT OKAY! (YOU PROMISE!) Fuck it! Fuck it all! Sure! You’re not an agent of chaos, you are at the whims as much as everyone else! BUT AT LEAST YOU WERE HAVING FUN WITH IT! But now, THEY will see just how much you were holding back in your haze of carelessness. When you use moves from the **[Aspect]** you have less moves of, you gain 1 **[Hold]** up to a max of 3. When you use a move from the **[Aspect]** you have MORE moves from, you immediately spend all **[Hold]** and cause a certain number of effects to happen based on the amount of **[Hold]** you had. One **[Hold]** gives EVERYONE a -1 **[Nerf]** to all rolls for 3 rounds. Two **[Holds]** causes everyone to become **[Stressed]** along with the one **[Hold]** effect. Three **[Holds]** knocks everyone **[Floorbound]** and makes yourself **[Stunned]** as you waste an action howling indignantly, as well as giving everyone the one and two **[Hold]** effects. SEE WHAT FUCKING HAPPENS WHEN YOU REACH THE BREAKING POINT?!\r\n'),
('parentalGuidance', 'PARENTAL GUIDANCE', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Passive]', 'Wow! You’ve finally bothered your parent or parental figure enough to come visit you on Alternia, sometimes! You gain the CUSTODIAN COMPANION move, with only 2 features (both of which need to be ones your parent could feasibly do). They generally won’t communicate with trolls; not that it matters, considering that… well, trolls are fucking terrified of them. It’s true! Your parent’s very presence is enough to turn the blood of a troll cold. Something about adults being scary on Alternia? When you first use ATRIACLIZE in an encounter, all trolls become **[Terrified]** for **2 turns**. AAAARGH!'),
('partnerLusus', 'PARTNER LUSUS', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'You don\'t go anywhere without your trusty **[Custodian]**! You love ‘em too dang much! You gain the CUSTODIAN COMPANION Perfectly Generic Move if you didn\'t already have it; your **[Custodian]** has 6 Features, not 4, and you are **[Talented]** at ALTRICIALIZE.'),
('passionForFashion', 'PASSION FOR FASHION', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Passive]', 'Jades have a longstanding culture of dressing nicely. Out of all trolls, perhaps, you are among the most fashionable, even if you aren\'t a Subcultist. Whether you sew your own outfits or just know where to get them, you\'ve built up enough of a style to really express yourself out there in the big bad world! Whenever you buy a **[Fashion]** item, you get a second one for free.'),
('pastTheFourthWall', 'PAST THE FOURTH WALL', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Analyze][Cullbait][Magic][Psionic][Unlock: Metagamer]', 'You are a character made using the Subgrubs & Snazzards TTRPG System. On some level, you\'re aware of that. Understand it? Maybe. Be able to word it beyond a vague feeling? Not necessarily. But be aware of it? Sure! For example, you\'re aware that all stories are influenced by their context— the world around them that gave birth to them. You are to some degree conscious of this world, and you can interact with it in ways nobody else can. You are **[Talented]** at **+IMG**. When you want to peer beyond the fourth wall, roll **+IMG**.\n\n**MIN**: TOO MUCH KNOWLEDGE! AEIIIOUUGH! You experience **[Sensory Overload]**.\n\n**BAD**: Agh… put the wall back up! You\'re **[Overwhelmed]**.\n\n**OK**: You gain one piece of information about Real Life Pop culture and it is not relevant at all. At least it’s kinda cool?\n\n**GOOD**: You peer through a crack in canon! You can ask any one question, even if you shouldn’t be able to know from mere observation. The answer tends to be mysterious, cryptic or to not give the full context. BE SURE TO GET OTHER PLAYER\'S CONSENT HERE. They decide what you learn, not you. If they don\'t want you to know something, you don\'t learn it. Don\'t like, actually cheat.\n\n**GREAT**: What fourth wall? Ask any one question that you should have no way of knowing; anything from “this character’s secret caste” to “the answer to this puzzle” to “stuff the other person has in their pocket”. The world is your valvemollusk. If you tell your target what you know, they are **[Confused]**, **[Hopeful]**, or **[Scared]**, depending on the context.\n\n**MAX**: Canon opens itself up to you and unfurls into neat, easy to read threads. You get a **GREAT**, but your answer is in excruciating detail and the emotions are heightened.'),
('pathokinesis', 'PATHOKINESIS', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][One-Off][Control][Psionic]', 'Limeblooded trolls have the innate power to change someone\'s heart; it\'s this original power that caused the empire to eliminate you all in the first place. Other powers have since manifested in your caste through the power of canon-twisting metamagic, but pathokinesis has remained part of you. When you want to change someone’s emotions, roll **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Ngh— gah-! Your psionics malfunction, and shoot emotional responses through you. If targeting an enemy, you gain the **[Emotion]** you had intended to give them, and heightened. If you were targeting an ally, you gain the opposite of the **[Emotion]** you were going to give them, and heightened.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Agh— shoot! You gain **1 [Drag]** as you over-exert yourself. \r\n\r\n**OK**: They feel a quiet tingling… the target either gains **1 [Boost]** or **1 [Drag]** (your choice!) and you don\'t trigger the move\'s **[One-Off]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: How are you feeling, friend? Your target suffers from an **[Emotion]** effect of your choice for **3 rounds**. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Your psionics might have uncovered a soft spot? Your target gains the **[Emotion]** effect of your choice for the rest of the encounter.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Whoa! You uncovered a real landmine of pent-up emotions, huh?! Your target experiences the heightened version of your selected **[Emotion]** effect for the encounter!'),
('patienceLimit', 'PATIENCE LIMIT', 'OTHER', 'BARD', '[Class][Basic][Reaction][Locked: Bard]', 'Uhhhhhhhh I mean. Sure, change is healthy and all that, but y\'know, this is really working for you? And you\'re good here. Really, thanks, but nah. Stop pushing. STOP IT. When someone tries to inflict you with a **[Negative] [Emotion]**, roll 1d8. On a 1-2, they laugh in your face and you receive the **[Emotion]** as normal. A 3-7 makes you snap at them and inflict the same **[Emotion]** they tried to give you back onto them. On an 8, you lash out VIOLENTLY and also deal 1 **[Somatic]** damage in addition to throwing the **[Emotion]** back at them, because YOU! ARE! FUCKING! FINE! FUCK OFF!\r\n\r\n\r\n'),
('paupersPush', 'PAUPER\'S PUSH', 'OTHER', 'PAGE', '[Class][Basic][Free][Reaction][Recharge: 2][Locked: Page]\r\n', 'You haven\'t got a whole lot going on, despite your bluster, and it shows. As such, you\'ve worked really, really hard, to sometimes be good at certain things, maybe? You… you can\'t tell me what to do! Nyeh! If someone has a move that would **[Tier Down]** your roll, you can ignore it- whether it\'s out of genuine effort or, more likely, your opponent just… shaking their heads at you a little in pity. You can\'t use this on effects you give yourself, dipshit.'),
('peacockSmartypants', 'PEACOCK SMARTYPANTS', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Passive][Unlock: Bookworm]', 'What can you say? You\'re a smart kid. A veritable Lil\' Curie, even. You\'ve always got your nose buried in a book, or a computer, or maybe a mystery! The point is, you\'re one of the brainier ones among your peers. You are **[Talented]** at **+PSP**. You\'re not particularly strong or fast, but goodness, you\'ve got brains for days! You can roll **[Analyze]** rolls multiple times in the same turn. When you do so, you get **1 [Boost]** as the gears in your head start concocting an idea; this increases by 1 for every **MAX** you get. You can transfer any **[Boost]** you gain from this move to someone else as you quickly explain your idea to them, helping them get you guys out of trouble!'),
('peculiarPerformance', 'PECULIAR PERFORMANCE', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Recharge: 3][Physical][Manipulate]', 'Hey, sssh, don\'t cry! Watch this! Hee-honk, you say, grabbing your nose and making a weird noise. Pretty funny, right? Who made you cry— that guy over there? WOOGAH WOOGAH WOOGAH, you say, pulling your head off and making it spin 720 degrees! You\'ve learned now that not everyone who\'s on top should stay on top, and sometimes, the little guy needs a hand. Your performances cheer up the weary and humble the rowdy when you roll **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: YOU DID IT IN THE WRONG ORDER! FUCK! You get a **MAX**, but do the teams in the wrong order.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Still— still the wrong order, man! You get a **GOOD**, but swap the ally and enemy with each other. \r\n\r\n**OK**: You do a cool flip! Nice!\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You cartwheel from a reassuring performance for an ally to a terrifying one in your opponents face! You move **2 [Drag]** from your ally to an opponent. If your ally has no **[Drag]**, they gain **[Boost]** instead.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Bravo! Bravo! AAAARGH! You get a **GOOD**, but increase the **[Drag]** to 3.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: This is… the most ridiculous and simultaneously terrifying performance you\'ve ever seen! Good lord! You get a **GREAT**, but the **[Drag]** increases to 4, and affects ALL allies and enemies.'),
('pentup', 'PENT-UP', 'BREATH', 'BREATH', '[Aspect][Basic][Free][Locked: Breath]', 'Just… just shut UP for once, okay?! All that keeping yourself polite and carefree and approachable can really wind you up hard sometimes— and when you’re wound up too much, you can kind of lose it at people, lashing out and acting in a volatile way as you just trounce everyone around you. Maybe you should try expressing your emotions more often before it comes to this…? Any time you gain the **[Enraged]** condition, you can choose to become **[Out Of Control]**, except you can also use WORDPLAY to **[Strife]**. You act as if you were only kinda peeved, but your anger is a lot deeper than that.'),
('pepTalk', 'PEP TALK', 'HOPE', 'HOPE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Recharge: 2][Heal][Locked: Hope]', 'Sometimes, people just need a little pick-me-up. You know how to make people understand that things will be okay, and that you care— and this kind of thing can really soothe the nerves. Sometimes, you’ll even give yourself a good pep talk and remind yourself that things are gonna be okay! When you want to show that you care, spend an action and roll **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You stumble over your words and call them a slur, or something. That isn’t nice at all! They start **[Crying]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Your reassurance rings hollow; nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You mildly reassure them. The target loses **1 [Drag]** or gains **1 HP**, your choice. This can not give the target **[Boost]** if they have **0 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Hey, chin up! You’re doing amazing. The target heals **2 HP** or loses **2 [Drag]**. This effect allows you to gain negative **[Drag]**; consider this a shield over your **[Boost]**, which must be reduced to 0 before **[Drag]** starts reducing your **[Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Your words strike true; your target gains both effects of a **GOOD**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Your words truly inspire your target to never give up! They heal **3 HP**, lose **3 [Drag]** and gain **3 [Boost]** as they strive to do the very best they can!'),
('perfectPulchritude', 'PERFECT PULCHRITUDE', 'OTHER', 'HEROMODE', '', 'It\'s basically impossible to not be even a little impressed by you. You have a magnetic charisma, a way with words and a heart that shines through everything you do. When you enter **HERO MODE**, select one of the following benefits.\r\n\r\n> **REALITY DISTORTION FIELD**: This is a real thing used to describe Steve Jobs\' charisma. Basically, it describes your \"ability to convince yourself, and others around you, to believe almost anything with a mix of charm, charisma, bravado, hyperbole, marketing, appeasement and persistence.\" TL;DR: you can make people believe anything you say, because that\'s how magnetic you are. When someone uses an **[Analyze]** or **[Manipulate]** roll against you in an encounter, as a **[Reaction]** you can turn it into a **MIN** and make the same roll right back at the source. YOU are in control here.\r\n\r\n> **WAY WITH WORDS**: You talk fast, when you need to! You make three **[Manipulate]** rolls in one action; these can include multiple uses of the same move.\r\n\r\n> **FORCE OF PERSONALITY**: No… no, you can\'t lose here! You come back from the brink of defeat, glittering like the most beautiful Rainbow Drinker. You **[Heal]** 2 **HP**, lose all **[Drag]** and any negative emotions. You immediately gain 2 **[Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **THAT LOOK IN YOUR EYES**: Ngh… it\'s hard to even want to hit you. There\'s something about you that… that makes you feel too important to hurt. You make the opponent\'s next **[Strife]** roll against you **[Godawful]**, and the one after that **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n> **P-PRETTY**: You are insanely attractive, and that\'s just how things are. On a **GOOD WORDPLAY** roll to **FLIRT**, the target is exposed to **SIMPTOMS**. On a GREAT, they are automatically on Stage 1, and on a **MAX**, they\'re at Stage 4. This can also be reflavored as simply being very persuasively friendly.\r\n'),
('persistenceOfMemory', 'PERSISTENCE OF MEMORY', 'OTHER', 'ABOMINARTIST', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Abominartist]', 'Even if you hardly consider yourself an artist, you still have access to the same stuff the pros do. You have **10 VP** instead of 8, and you can buy the following items. You can flavor the items themselves to fit your artistic path, but the mechanics remain the same.\r\n\r\n**NOTEBOOK (1 VP)**: How… simple. It\'s every little kid\'s first creative outlet, other than restaurant menus and homework assignments. You can spend an action to mull over your notebook and give your next **+IMG** or **+PSP** roll a **+1 [Buff]**. This has a **[Recharge: 2]**.\r\n\r\n**BAG OF SUPPLIES (1 VP)**: Let\'s see here, all your books on various techniques, spare brushes/chisels/spraycans, backup gun in case you need to give a rival artist the business...yep, all set! You got all you need in this bag, though it\'s a bit heavy lugging it all around. As a **[One-Off]** action, you can make someone **[Bloodied]** as you swing this thing around and knock out a tooth or break their nose. Just hope you don\'t break something in there...\r\n\r\n**WIP PROJECT (2 VP)**: You look at this unfinished work and realize...unless you keep going, you\'ll never make your dreams a reality! You\'ll finish this if it\'s the LAST THING YOU DO! You can pull out a WIP PROJECT to make yourself **[Hopeful]** for two turns. You can\'t use it again because looking at it again just makes you realize how long you\'ve put it off, oh god is that really from half a sweep ago ah shit-\r\n\r\n**DIRT WATER (2 VP)**: AUGHH! FUCKING GROSS! You throw some kind of muddied water at the target, whether it be full of paint or clay residue, or even just cold tea that you put your gross troll cooties all over, rendering them **[Disgusted]** for two turns.\r\n\r\n**FINISHED PROJECT (3 VP)**: Hey, buddy! You like this piece? Wanna see it up close? WHACK! You hit your opponent with your lovingly crafted artwork, dealing **1 [Somatic]** damage. This is a **[Consumable]** item, because… it\'s not exactly gonna survive when you fucking beat someone over the head with it.'),
('phantomlyPhenom', 'PHANTOMLY PHENOM', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Psionic][Passive][Unlock: Haunted]', 'Hey… over there… come a little closer… let me ask you a question. Do you think ghosts are real..? You don\'t..? Heheh, yeah… that white hand on your shoulder probably isn\'t real either. You are a necropath, a troll with an inherent psionic connection to the supernatural. Unlike cthonmancers or liches, these powers aren\'t considered **[Cullbait]**. This is because while they answer to a higher dark power, you still answer to more mortal things. Like the need for food, water... and the government sanctioned paycheck to buy them. Maybe it\'s because rusts have such a short lifespan that it\'s only natural that you\'re able to see them; maybe it\'s because you have a latent psychic power that lets you see them. Whatever the case, you\'ve got a real knack for seeing things nobody else can see. It really doesn\'t bug you, though; you kind of don\'t feel fear ever at this point. You are **[Talented]** at **+RAS**; while you have **[Psionics]**, you mostly rely on the deceased to pull spooky japes! You are immune to the **[Scared]** and **[Dread]** conditions. Any time you would gain them, you instead feel **[Happy]** or **[Joy]** as you giggle. Oh, this situation is meant to be frightening? That\'s so fun, heheh..! Other people\'s fear, meanwhile, empowers you; when around a target who is **[Scared]**, feeling **[Dread]** or has the **HAUNTING** Affliction, you can start **[Flying]** as an action.'),
('phantomThief', 'PHANTOM THIEF', 'OTHER', 'THIEF', '[Class][Passive][Unlock: Thief]', 'Let\'s face it. To call you ordinary would be a complete disservice. You\'re not just a troll; you\'re BEYOND that. You have a mystique to you that leads to a grandiosity that elevates you over others… and elevates you over the rules. Rules like… hey, you can\'t do that! Because OH YES YOU CAN! You can use the **SHENANIGANS** effect **YOINK** with a **[Recharge: 1]**. You are always **[Talented]** at this effect, and items you swipe like this take up **1 VP** less than normal.\r\n\r\n'),
('philanthropicInvestments', 'PHILANTHROPIC INVESTMENTS', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Passive]', 'You don\'t… need all of this money. You don\'t even necessarily want it. The most fun you\'ve ever had with others wasn\'t cuz of your vast riches, it was fighting Megatoads in Subgrubs with your friends. And people like your friends… probably need this much more than you. As such, you\'ve been much more willing to sink money into things that don\'t directly benefit you, but seriously help others. Of course, you probably pretend it\'s some crazy good investment to your seadwelling comrades, but… yeah. You get the following **[Big Buy]** options.\r\n\r\n> **PUBLIC INVESTMENT**: You spend money on things you won\'t even use for yourself. You can build a building or facility, and you get HIVECRAFTING UPGRADES you have access to worth no more than **6 LUX** total. You give this to another person, or to a group of people, and they can use it as a spot for strifes, encounters etcetera. You are **[Hopeful]** whenever you\'re in an encounter with the recipients, and this emotion can\'t be dispelled under any circumstances until you return to **Ultrarich**. Trolls can further upgrade this area if they so choose. \r\n\r\n> **SWEET GIFT**: Hey, go have fun with it! Don\'t even worry about it. You purchase an item or group of items worth no more than **4 LUX** for someone else. Both you and the target start your next encounter together with **2 [Boost]**. \r\n\r\n> **MEDICULL TREATMENT**: You want the best medicine caegars can buy, curse you! You completely end a troll\'s **[Slowburn]** **[Afflictions]**, potentially give them access to the Robot **[Template]**, and any prosthetics they might want. The target is **[Tired]** but **[Hopeful]** for a week.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('pickYourSide', 'PICK YOUR SIDE', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Basic][Passive]', 'There comes a point in everyone\'s life where you have to nail yourself to the metaphorical wall of ALIGNMENT. And as much as you hate to do it, it’s terribly vital. Being Hemoanonymous isn’t all it’s technically set out to be, because yeah, the Empire doesn’t particularly like you hiding your precious blood. How do you feel about that?\r\n\r\n> **Rebel**: You’re aligned primarily with the rebels! You don’t want to put up with the Empire in any fashion, and rightly so! Any rolls you make against a drone are at a +1 **[Buff]**, and your weapon may have the **VOLTKIND** Abstrata in addition to any others.\r\n\r\n> **Civilian**: You’re just a little guy, it’s your hatchday come on! You’ve aligned yourself to a more neutral standing, you can probably see both sides, and yeah, you’re technically the lowest of the low as you are, but living this way is better than whatever you had before. That being said, you’d rather stand out of the line of fire. Rolls to become **[Hidden]** now have a **[Tier Up]**.\r\n\r\n> **Empire**: What the fuck do you MEAN you’re aligned with the empire? Why would you ever do this? Oh wait, you’re like. Spying for them or something. Or are resolved to keep the empire’s agenda for whatever reason. Either way, you’re used to stealthing into communities. Any time a troll has a move that would let you sense if you are empire loyal or would harm cullbait, the opponent must roll 1d8. On odds, they succeed in being suspicious of you, but you gain 1 **[WHAM]** and a **[Strife]** roll as a **[Free] [Reaction]** as you prepare to get got. On evens, you succeed in fooling them.'),
('pierceTheTrenches', 'PIERCE THE TRENCHES!', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Passive][Locked: Pilot]', 'Believe in the Clouder that believes in you!! Go beyond the impossible and kick reason to the seafloor! ROW! ROW! FIGHT THE POWER! It takes a certain kind of someone to make a Pilot. Seriously, you can’t pilot one of these unless your brainwaves are exactly the kind needed to sync with the nuclear core. The one trait that unites all pilots? They’re bulgey as hell. Seriously, do you guys not fear ANYTHING? You are immune to the **[Scared]** emotion, and can always take an action to throw out a volley of cool speeches and become **[Proud]**. You can make this a **[Lengthy]** action to become **[Icarian]**. You know. If you aren’t chicken.'),
('pioengineer', 'PIOENGINEER', 'INDIGO', 'ADULT', '[Indigo][Locked: Adult]', 'Your job may not be conquering nations and battlefield glory. That being said, your name will go down in history books all the same! Golds supply the galaxy\\\'s software and power, but you supply the purpose. The reason. The STUFF! Everything and anything that has been created by the empire has passed through the hands of a Pioengineer or two in the pursuit of developing society. Sliced bread, laser guns, anything and anything came to be because of the ideas of you and your peers. And most of all, with your position? You decide what other inventions are worthy of surviving millenia. All items you purchase with **LUX** now cost 1 **LUX** less (minimum of 1) as you simply make them yourself. You also gain a **ROBOT KIT**. This item takes up 1 **VP** and is in your sylladex. If it gets stolen, tough luck! The **ROBOT KIT** which allows you to make a Level 1 NPC other than Lime NPCs as an action. This robotic creation does not share any stats with you, but seeing as it was made on the go it is permanently **[Slowed]**. However, whenever the robot gets a **GOOD+** on a roll, its creator gains 1 **[Boost]**. Yeah! That’s my little guy that did that!  '),
('pipeGunPioneer', 'PIPE GUN PIONEER', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Junker]', 'They said you were a madtroll. They said it couldn\'t be done. \"You can\'t reverse the polarity of a flamethrower to make it an ice thrower.\"  They said, \"Flamethrowers don\'t even have polarity.\", but they were WRONG.  ALL WRONG, YOU JUST PROVED THEM ALL WRONG. Your innovative mind has made you an expert at crafting your own weapons and firearms. You can add up to three ABSTRATA UPGRADES to a single weapon. You gain one for free when you take this move.'),
('pirate101', 'PIRATE 101', 'OTHER', 'RAPSCALLINEER', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Rapscallineer]', 'So, you’ve decided to join the rapscallineer’s life, eh, matey? Before you can start your life of epic piracy, you’ll need a crew or I’m afraid you’re not much better off than some chump in a scuttlecraft brandishing a knife at merchants. Your crew is your life when you’re aboard a pirate ship- they’re your friends, annoyances and siblings-in-arms all in one. Maybe you all sleep in a polyamorous puddle? Regardless, everyone on your crew has a role which transcends caste, social status, and everything else as you settle into life aboard the ship. You may optionally choose to take the **[Talent]** of the role you pick as the crew member in place of your tree\'s talent.\r\n\r\n> **Cap’n [+GRA]**: You are the pirate captain, the head honcho! Being the Cap’n is a tough job that demands a lot of respect and composure, whether you rule with an iron fist or just act like your crewmates’ glorified lusus. You can roll WORDPLAY with **+GRA** as you guide with solid composure and power rather than charisma. Additionally, you gain **+1 HP** for every crew member you have, up to a max of **+4 HP**.\r\n\r\n> **Quartermaster [+PLC]**: You may not be THE leader, but you definitely put in the work for it. You’re the organizer, the Second-In-Command who does a little bit of everything. You can roll GUTSUCKERY with **+PLC** as your inspiring words convince even yourself that everything is fine and going to get better.\r\n\r\n> **Navigator [+PSP]**: You are the mapmaker and the helmstroll (Not like what they do to battery golds! You just steer the wheel. With your hands.). You probably know what a sextant is. You can roll SWASHBUCKLING with **+PSP** as you’re able to substitute facts and diagrams for bravado and bluster. Look! I have a map right here showing where the idiot in the room is! It’s you!\r\n\r\n> **Steward [+APP]**: You’re in charge of cooking, which is a lot harder and more important than it sounds. No matter what you cook you can just about guarantee that it’ll end up in a crewmate’s digestion bladder in some way or another. You can roll all DOWNTIME rolls with **+APP** as you leverage your meals over the rest of the crew for them to do all of your petty day-to-day activities for you.\r\n\r\n> **Engineer [+HUB]**: You’re located in the engine room, putting out fires and constantly repairing the engine, probably the most dangerous part of the ship- besides the cannons, obviously. You can roll PROBLEM SLEUTHING with **+HUB** as you sus out problems and fix them on the fly, probably with duct tape and a quick prayer.\r\n\r\n> **Powder Monkey [+RAS]**: You’re in charge of the EXPLOSIONS! GUNPOWDER! ATTACKING PEOPLE! This is all very fun for you. You can roll LET’S STRIFE with **+RAS** as your battle strategy relies less on strength, and more on setting things on fire in a mischievously scallywag way. \r\n\r\n> **Sailor [+GRT]**: You hoist the sails, swab the deck, and really do just about everything not specified in the above crew positions. You can roll FRAYMOTIF with **+GRT** as you turn your dance into an incredibly masculine sea shanty, swinging on ropes and cartwheeling across the decks as you sing along a song.'),
('planOfAction', 'PLAN OF ACTION', 'LIGHT', 'LIGHT', '[Aspect][Advanced][Lengthy][Recharge: 2][Locked: Light]', 'You’re excellent at coming up with plans, and with the information you’ve gleaned, the plans you make can help solve any problem! You can spend a **[Lengthy]** action thinking out an elaborate plan to undo the opponent. Choose 4 moves and string together a plan using them (for example, “I’ll knock them down using SHENANIGANS, then do a sweet flip in the air using SWASHBUCKLE, then land right on their chest with GRIEF and then duck out of sight while they’re down using ACT FAST”). This planning gives you a **[Hold]**; when you decide to set your plan into action, you trade in your **[Hold]** and use all 4 of the actions you planned. Using this **[Hold]** takes your full turn. **[Recharge]** for this move kicks in after you use your **[Hold]**; until you do, you cannot use this move again.'),
('playgroundWarlord', 'PLAYGROUND WARLORD', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Bully]', 'YEAH, THAT\'S RIGHT! BE AFRAID! You\'re the toughest bitch on the block, and don\'t you forget it! Now SCRAM! You\'ve got quite the reputation as a troublemaker, a rabblerouser and a massive cu— a massive friend to all who need it. You gain access to HERO MODE through your MYTHIC MANGRIT. The length of time that your **GREAT** effects from FISTICUFFSAFICIONADO\'s AGGRESS is lengthened to **3 rounds**, not 2; you know how to leave a lasting impression, after all! Your vibe is immediately pretty harsh; enemies are **[Scared]** when you fight them alone. However, when your friends are around, you fight for THEM. You get **+1 HP** for every ally in an encounter, to a max of +3. You\'ll take the hits so that they don\'t have to! POW!'),
('playPossum', 'PLAY POSSUM', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][One-Off][Reaction][Chicanery][Mental][Locked: Gutterblood]', 'HNRK-! And with this… YOU DIE… AEIOUGH… just kidding! Playing dead is an art, and it\'s one you\'re very experienced at. Whether it\'s hamming up your demise to win pity points or pretending to play dead to avoid a confrontation, you\'ve mastered the art of going down before it\'s time. When you want to fall victim to a \"deadly\" incoming **[Strife]** roll, roll **+APP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You\'re not even a little dead, dipshit. Go to hell. Not only are you **[Floorbound]**, you\'re **[Slowed]** for a turn, and your target gains **1 [WHAM]**. Asshole.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You don\'t fool them, but you don\'t waste time trying to fool them either. You\'re **[Floorbound]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You consider it, but decide against it. You gain **1 [Resistance]** against the incoming attack anyway.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: HRK-! You drop to the floor, and the target thinks you\'re dead. This is usually enough to ward off NPCs, intelligent HAZARDS or antagonistic player characters. Interacting with you, like shaking your body in concern, is enough to prove you\'re alive, though people actually out to hurt you usually won\'t check. Metagaming scum. Your next **[Physical]** move is **[Tiered Up]** as you prepare yourself to unexpectedly strike!\r\n\r\n**GREAT: You ham your death the hell up! You get a **GOOD**. Choose one of the following effects**: \r\n\r\n> **HEARTBREAKING**: NOOO- YOUR… MOIRAIL… YOU CAN\'T LEAVE THEM… aw man, your dying words really bum the target out. They\'re **[Sad]** now.\r\n> **GRUESOME**: Oh— dear god, that\'s a violent, bloody death, and definitely not the blasagna you keep on you for just such an occasion splattering everywhere. The target is **[Disgusted]**.\r\n> **OVERDRAMATIC**: ET TU, ENPECE? AEI— AEIOIGH— MY LUSUS… OHHHH… your death is believable, but hammy. Do people really die like that..? The target is **[Confused]**.\r\n> **SILENT**: And with a glassy eyed stare, your life is snuffed out. Feels hollow. The target is **[Numb]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You put your ALL into that death. And it pays off! You get a **GREAT**, but the target\'s emotion is **[Heightened]**.'),
('pleasantlyOblivious', 'PLEASANTLY OBLIVIOUS', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Man! Sometimes you don\'t even realize how fucked up your life is. Why do people scrunch your nose at your canned slugs that you eat? Why do people look sad when you offhandedly mention that lusus that took care of you a few sweeps back before it got eaten? It\'s fiiiiiine. You can cope. You can\'t gain more than **2 [Drag]** at a time.'),
('plotArmour', 'PLOT ARMOUR', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Free][One-Off][Magic][Locked: Protagonist]', 'Certainly, you may encounter hardships on your journey… but your story would be so tiring if it was always realistic in its depictions of failure! As such, the world gives you an out even in your darkest moments. Once per encounter, when you roll a **MIN** or a **BAD** on any roll, you can still gain the effects of a **GOOD** on top of the other results.'),
('plotPainPoints', 'PLOT PAIN POINTS', 'OTHER', 'MUSCLEMANIAC', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Musclemaniac]', 'You\'ve learned how to woo the crowd and turn your fights into an epic play-by-play saga of hero vs. villain, and you know where to hit where it hurts at the points in the story where it\'s thematically appropriate. Take the following benefit depending on whether you are a FACE or a HEEL.\r\n\r\n> **FACE**: You\'re an underdog, and you fight best when you\'re on the brink of being defeated yourself! Your **[WHAM]** cannot be dispersed by being hit when you have 1/2 or less of your health.\r\n\r\n> **HEEL**: You\'re a scary bastard and you get your hits in early. Your **[WHAM]** cannot be dispersed by being hit when you have 1/2 or more of your health.'),
('pocketChange', 'POCKET CHANGE', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Passive]', 'Okay! You’ve gotten a hold of some Caegars! That’s pretty great! Now you can take part in THE ECONOMY down on Alternia. You have the **Average** Wealth Level, though your Clouder may allow you to take more or less depending on how you procured this wealth. Effects that alter your Wealth Level do not affect your buying power for **[Earth]** items, since they don’t really affect your Caegarscore one way or another.'),
('pocketPlane', 'POCKET PLANE', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][Passive][Cullbait][Magic][Psionic]', 'Behold! An extradimensional portal! Your hive is its own realm, bigger on the inside and with confusing architecture and geometry that couldn\'t exist in our own world (what do you MEAN your corridor has 8 left turns?). You can access your hive from anywhere with a door. Open a door, a window, a box… and hey presto, it\'s a POCKET PLANE! Only people you choose to allow into your Pocket Plane may enter, and HIVECRAFTING UPGRADES cost **1 LUX** less than normal for you (min. 1). You can also use this move to bring vehicles out from your Pocket Plane!'),
('pogblood', 'POGBLOOD', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Open][Free][Reaction][Recharge: 2]', 'As a lowblood often reduced to internet jester status, you’ve learned that one of the best coping mechanisms is finding humor in everything- even when it’s you being owned! When someone in an encounter with you- ally or enemy- rolls a successful **+RAS** roll, you can gain **2 [Boost]** as a **[Reaction]** because holy fuck that was funny as shit actually. You gotta point and laugh now.'),
('pogcaster', 'POGCASTER', 'GOLD', 'ADULT', '[Gold][Recharge: 3][Locked: Adult]', 'Goldbloods have a lot of opportunities, whether that means losing your personhood to become a battery or becoming some elite hacker typing on a million holo screens to blow enemy ships to smithereens. You… sit in a large gamer office owned by a highblood boss, who lets you do your thing in exchange for sponsoring their experimental gamer juice on stream. And of course, spewing propaganda! You are GREAT at getting people to look at whatever is on your screen! As an action, you can inflict a -2 **[Nerf]** on an enemy’s **[Mental]** rolls as you distract them. LAUGH AT MY BITS, BOY!!! They may spend an action to remove this effect as they pry their eyes away from your holoscreens; when they do, only then will the move’s **[Recharge: 3]** activate.'),
('poisonApple', 'POISON APPLE', 'OTHER', 'PRINCE\r\n', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Prince][Locked: Life] \r\n', 'The forces of life and death are the oldest forms of destruction in the universe. \r\n\r\nAll of your opponent’s **[Heal]** effects apply a **[Poisoned]** condition that cannot be **[Healed]** away and lasts for **3 turns**. This effect can stack if your opponent foolishly keeps **[Healing]** themself; i.e. 2 counts of **[Poison]** dealing **2 [Drag]** per turn, 3 dealing 3, etc. \r\n'),
('pokerFace', 'POKER FACE', 'OTHER', 'SEER', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Seer]', 'It’s remarkably hard to tell your true feelings. When someone rolls an **[Analyze]** roll on you, you can tell that they\'re trying to get a read on you and react accordingly - stonewalling them. Hey. Hey. YOU\'RE the knowing bitch around here. The opponent’s roll is **[Tiered Down]**.\n\n'),
('polaritycrossingKamikaze', 'POLARITY-CROSSING KAMIKAZE', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'BUSTIN', '[Template][Advanced][Buildup: 4][One-Off][Locked: Bustin’]', 'These ghosts have almost got the best of us, huh? Only one thing for it… we’ll blow ourselves up! Faithful to a fault, Busters are willing to knock themselves down in order to knock down everyone around them. Two Bustin’ trolls can smash their weapons into each other as a **[One-Off]**. This immediately renders both **[Unconscious]**, and does an amount of **[Holy][Psychic]** damage equal to their remaining HP to everyone present. BOOM!'),
('polterificate', 'POLTERIFICATE', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Psionic][Strife][Locked: Haunted]', 'Boo! Nyeheheheh! Your psychic powers are boosted by your latent spookiness, giving you the haunting ability to slam shit around like you’re some… some kind of… weird… german ghost, or something. You use it to stack chairs and scare the shit out of children, fuck with televisions, or more commonly, slam your opponents around! When you want your target to have a haunting experience, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You overexert yourself, and your lifeforce flickers, reminding you how thin the line between life and unlife is. You take **2 [Freaky][Psychic]** damage, and gain **1 [Weakness]** to **[Psychic]** attacks as you become slightly ethereal.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You exert your full psionic strength… and somewhere, somehow, a spoon bends. Nothing else happens.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Your spooky energy fucks with the target’s anxiety, but doesn’t hurt them; they gain **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: BOOOO! HUHUHUHU! Your terrifying presence looms over your target. The target takes **1 [Freaky][Psychic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA!! Genuinely terrifying! Your target either takes **2 [Freaky][Psychic]** damage or takes **1 [Freaky][Psychic]** damage and becomes **[Scared]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Your eyes turn white, and you start floating a few feet off the floor, your words repeating backwards. Fucked up! Your target either takes **3 [Freaky][Psychic]** damage, or takes **2 [Freaky][Psychic]** damage and becomes **[Terrified]** for **2 turns**.'),
('possession', 'POSSESSION', 'OTHER', 'GHOST', '[Template][Advanced][Eerie][Magic][Locked: Ghost]', 'You miss being corporeal, sometimes! Nice body you got goin’ on… mind if you… snatch it? You can possess a low-level NPC troll or Level 1 and lower lusus as an action, gaining their body and their measly stats and moves. You cannot use any of your own moves in this form, other than Ghost moves, nor can you access your Sylladex. When you want to possess another player and gain much greater power, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You swoop inside them, and… they stay in control!? Lemme out! Lemme out! They gain all your GHOST template moves for the rest of the encounter, or at least until they forcibly eject you. You are trapped inside them until then.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: They don’t let you possess them! Rude!\r\n\r\n**OK**: You possess them… but only for a moment. You can make them do any one action before they forcefully expel you.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You’re in! You gain control of the opponent, and they’re trapped inside their own mind. They can still communicate with you, and roll any moves they have that can inflict **[Psychic]** damage or are **[Magic]** against you, but cannot do anything with their own body until you are expelled. Damage inflicted by a **[Psionic]** or **[Magic]** attack immediately yeets you from your haunted target. People who know your target immediately recognize something is wrong; maybe you should stop spinning your head in 360 degree circles?\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: #HAUNTED! You’re in, and you’re in deep. You get the effects of a **GOOD** result, except you must take at least **3 damage** from a **[Psionic]** or **[Magic]** source to be expelled, and people who know your troll only get a vague sense something is off, not enough to act on.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Your haunting is so perfect, it’ll take a while for anyone to realize something is terribly wrong. You get the effects of a **GOOD** roll, except nobody has any inkling you’re different (and might like the new you even more), and you’re only expelled when you’re defeated by **[Psionic]** or **[Magic]** attacks. Your target’s moves in your headspace are all **[Tiered Down]**.'),
('poweredBySpite', 'POWERED BY SPITE', 'OTHER', 'MAID', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Maid]', 'You don\'t like to fail! You especially don\'t like to fail when someone else specifically wants you to fail. Even if you DO fail, you’re going to come back and do even better (and also probably your nay-sayers) out of pure spite. Any time you get a **BAD** or a **MIN** on a move, you gain a +1 or +2 **[Buff]** respectively to use the next time you roll that move.'),
('powerLevel', 'POWER LEVEL', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Passive][Locked: Battery]', 'You have an innate sense that lets you understand how strong someone is with a mere glance. You in character know the level of any opponent you encounter (pray you don\'t ever meet someone with a power level of 9,000). If you meet a character of a lower level than you, you are **[Smug]**. If they are 12 levels lower than you, you also start with **2 [Boost]**. If you meet a character at a higher level than you, on the other hand, you prepare for a challenge and are **[Brave]**. If they\'re 12 levels higher than you, you’re a little shocked and focus up your psionic might; at the start of your first turn, you gain either **2 CHARGE** or **1 [WHAM]**, your choice.\r\n'),
('powerUp', 'POWER UP', 'OTHER', 'SUPERSCOUNDREL', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Superscoundrel]', 'What’s a super being without super powers? Legally, super powers are grounds for culling, which is why you rely on replication technology! However, after you take your first 8 damage, this technology fails and its power cannot be activated for the rest of the thread. It also cannot be repaired with healing items. Choose one of the powers from the list below:\r\n\r\n> **Flight**: It’s a squawkbeast! It’s an imperial bombing drone! No wait, it’s you! Soaring through the air like a majestic eagle… piloting a blimp. You can use an **[Action]** to begin **[Flying]** during an encounter. \r\n\r\n> **Energy Blast**: PEW PEW, BITCHES! Whether it’s through LASER EYES or bursts of energy from palm arc reactors, you can release bursts of pure energy. On all **GREAT** **[Strife]** rolls and above, you have the option to also make your enemy **[Blinded]**.\r\n\r\n> **Super Strength**: Forget indigoes, YOU are the epitome of strength! Just don’t let the surface pressure of being the strongest get to you. You become **[Talented]** at **+GRT**. If you were already **[Talented]**, you get **+1 [Boost]** anytime you use a move requiring **+GRT**. \r\n\r\n> **Super Speed**: WHADDAFUCK WAS THAT. OH GOD YOU’RE HERE. YOU’RE THERE. YOU’RE EVERYWHERE! You are **[Quickened]**. If you were already **[Quickened]**, you instead gain **+1 [Boost]** any time you use a roll requiring **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n> **Super Healing**: No longer do you have to scream “I NEED HEALING” and pray someone hears you. You’re a big troll who can heal themself! You automatically heal **1 HP** every two rounds. This effect does not stack with other healing moves and items used in the same turn.'),
('powerWord', 'POWER WORD', 'FUCHSIA', 'FUCHSIA', '[Fuchsia][Advanced][Passive]', 'You have the sharpest tongue on all of Alternia. No, trust us. We checked. And also we killed any other qualifiers. You’re good. You do not need to roll WORDPLAY- you always get a **MAX**. There are no exceptions. You also cannot be affected by any **[Manipulate]** roll above a **GOOD**- no one has that kind of power over you except other fuchsias.'),
('practicallyPerfect', 'PRACTICALLY PERFECT', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Recharge: 3][Flourish][Locked: Posh]', 'Never failing is only part of the battle! You need to ensure that your opponents don\'t get the better of you, either! When you want to ensure nobody knocks you down, roll **+GRA**!\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You\'re knocked down! LITERALLY! Oh, cruel fate! You are knocked **[Floorbound]** and take **2 [Drag]**!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Ngh— you aren\'t doing as well as you\'re meant to! That\'s awful! You take **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Oop— not PERFECT, but… I mean, you get **1 [Boost]**!\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: There! That\'s what you like to see! You take one of the following effects…\r\n\r\n> **DUCK-N-ROLL**: You jump out of the way when the target tries to punk you! **[Chicanery]** rolls are **[Inept]** against you next turn. \r\n\r\n> **OUTPERFORM**: You put in so much work into what you\'re doing that people need to work extra hard if they wanna beat you! All opponent\'s **[Flourish]** rolls are **[Inept]** for a turn.\r\n\r\n> **DEEP BREATH**: You hold yourself, bracing your mind. Can\'t fuck with me, alien psychic! **[Psionic]** rolls are **[Inept]** against you next turn.\r\n\r\n> **INSCRUTABLE SMILE**: Those people are looking at you funny. Give ‘em the ol\' Mona Lisa and make them doubt themselves! **[Analyze]** rolls are **[Inept]** against you next turn.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Oh wow, you timed that out exactly, huh? You get a **GOOD** as a **[Hold]**; you spend this **[Hold]** as a **[Free]** **[Reaction]** the next time someone uses the effect you chose against you, rather than only applying it to your next turn.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: WOW. You are prepared for ANYTHING. You get a **[Hold]** as a **GREAT**, but you don\'t need to decide now which you take— only choose when you activate it.'),
('practicalStudy', 'PRACTICAL STUDY', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][One-Off][Manipulate][Locked: Student]', 'Learning from books is all well and good, but sometimes, you want to put what you\'ve learned into PRACTICE! When you want to see how much you\'ve learned, roll the stat you gained **[Talent]** in from PRIVATE SCHOOL PRODIGY.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Oh no! You stumble over and get an F-. You are **[Humiliated]** by this.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: A D+? No, no, no! That\'s terrible! You are **[Embarrassed]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: It\'s a C. Could be worse. Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Guess you could say you SCHOOL em! Choose an effect from the list below.\r\n\r\n> +RAS: PRANKED! Your expert hijinks just make the target **[Overwhelmed]**.\r\n> +PLC: Is that really the best you can do? Scathing critiques cut the target, making them feel **[Dread]**.\r\n> +GRA: You dance, twirl and outpace the target, leaving the target **[Confused]**.\r\n> +APP: Get hyped! The target listens to your get-rich-quick plan designed to bankrupt people. They become **[Proud]**.\r\n> +GRT: HUWAAAARGH! Your ancient troll battlecry **[Scares]** the shit out of them.\r\n> +HUB: HEAR MY DECREE. Jegus, okay, fuck, sorry! So loud! Your target is **[Stressed]**.\r\n> +PSP: Curious, isn\'t it? Hmmmm. Your target gets swept up in thought too, making them **[Focused]**.\r\n> +IMG: PCHEW! YOU CAST A SPELL! Huh?! This is a **[Magic]** effect; roll 1d8, and choose an emotion from this list. If you get an 8 for **+IMG**, just reroll it. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: EXTRA CREDIT, BABES! You get a **GOOD**, but the **[Emotion]** is **[Heightened]** for a turn.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: A+++! You get a **GOOD**, but it\'s **[Heightened]** for the encounter!'),
('prankstersGambit', 'PRANKSTER\'S GAMBIT', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Passive][Locked: Goofball]', 'The tide of battle shifts constantly back and forth between you and your allies. The goal: tilt the tide in your favour to push out even heftier prankz. At the start of an encounter, all combatants start with a PRANKMETER of 0. Every time someone gets at least a **GOOD** at a SHENANIGANS roll, you add 1 to your PRANKMETER. In a 1v1 encounter, the combatant with the higher PRANKMETER is the PRANKLORD, and the combatant with the lower PRANKMETER is the PRANKSERF. In a group strife, the team with the collectively higher or lower PRANKMETER gets the associated roles, and becomes the CHAMP or the CHALLENGER respectively. \n\n**PRANKMASTER**: HEHEHEH! YOU\'RE INVINCIBLE! YOU\'RE A GENIUS! MEHEHEH! You become **[Supercilious]**.\n\n**PRANKSERF**: D\'oooohhhh! That rascally PRANKMASTER! You\'ll get them yet!! If you have the Goofball Tree, you become **[Enraged]**; if you don\'t, you are **[Stressed]**.'),
('prayerPower', 'PRAYER POWER', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Recharge: 2][Heal][Magic][Locked: Cloistered]', 'Mumbling passages from the consecrated rainbow drinker romance novels fills you with reassuring power… or damns you to blasphemy, if you think too hard about sexy vampire JILFs kissing! By connecting with your holy faith, you ask for guidance and protection, and roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: IMPURE! YOU IMAGINED TONGUES, DIDN’T YOU? You take **2 [Psychic]** damage and feel **[Agitated]**. Repent!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Stop it! You’re supposed to focus on the allegorical meaning of rainbow drinking, not the pretty girls! You take **1 [Psychic]** damage and feel **[Stressed]**, because gg girl pre tyy...\r\n\r\n**OK**: You start thinking about how bad blood probably tastes, which isn’t like, blasphemous, but it is weird. You become **[Numb]** until the recharge of this move ends.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Ommmm… divine peace falls over you, and you are one with the eulogy of the drinker. Much like the ancient drinker was placed in the caves to protect the Mother Grub as her profane angels, so too shall you. You **[Heal]** **1 HP**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Holy, holy, holy… you’re able to think about lesbian vampires making out, and not feel even a little bit flustered. It’s the art of the worms, is it not? You **[Heal]** **2 HP**, or 1 and become **[Peaceful]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Angelic choirs sing from the dirt! Blood pumps through the veins of all life, which shall one day pass into the earth once more and spawn further grubs! GAY! VAMPIRES! IN LOVE! You feel **[Serene]** and restore **3 HP**.'),
('precisePerspicacity', 'PRECISE PERSPICACITY', 'OTHER', 'HEROMODE', '', 'You see things as they really are. The truth is always within your grasp, and you are quite frankly a genius. At the forefront of our times, your mind is one of the greatest out there, and none can claim to be brighter than you! When you enter HERO MODE, you may select one of the following benefits. \r\n\r\n> **PERFECT DEDUCTION**: You are very rarely wrong. You make 3 **[Analyze]** rolls in one action; these can include multiple uses of the same move. You gain information from all of them, but only the mechanical benefits of the best roll. \r\n\r\n> **SEE IT COMING**: You know exactly what moves your opponent is about to make, and plan accordingly. Your opponent must name out and stick to their next 6 moves, even if it would be unwise to do so. You may change up your strategy accordingly, but if you make one of their moves impossible to use then they may improvise that action.\r\n\r\n> **OUTWIT**: You don\'t need willpower or charm to overwhelm your opponent when you know how their mind works! For the next 3 turns, all non-**[Strife] [Mental]** rolls use **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n> **UNREADABLE**: You\'re able to hide your tells perfectly, making you downright impossible to outfox. For the next 3 turns, all **[Mental]** rolls against you are **[Godawful]**.\r\n\r\n> **EXPLOIT WEAK POINTS**: Your keen eye can find the parts of your person that are most vulnerable to attack. You get a +2 **[Buff]** to all your **[Strife]** rolls for 2 turns and cannot have your **[Strife]** moves **[Dragged]** for the same amount of time.\r\n'),
('preciseToAFault', 'PRECISE TO A FAULT', 'LIGHT', 'LIGHT', '[Aspect][Basic][Locked: Light]', 'You seek lore, history, arcana, science, whatever— you seek it ALL! You don’t like vague details one bit, and you are willing to give up any momentum you had to find out more. Drop everything; you NEED to solve this. When you ask a question with an **[Analyze]** move, you can spend **2 [Boost]** to press for more details, acting as a second, **[Free]** **GOOD** **[Analyze]** result.'),
('predictable', 'PREDICTABLE!!!', 'OTHER', 'SEER', '[Class][Advanced][Reaction][Recharge: 5][Locked: Seer]', 'You have a preternatural sense for where someone is going to be, when they are going to strike. It’s almost eerie… See there they go, really, you saw that coming a mile away. At least try. When someone makes a clumsy, juvenile **[Physical]** **[Strife]** swing at you like they think it\'s actually going to hit you, roll **+GRA, +PSP**, or **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You may have miscalculated slightly. It hits, and it\'s **[Tiered Up]**, even to a **MAX**. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: Maybe it wasn\'t so clumsy- you didn\'t take it seriously enough to dodge. Their move does **+1 damage**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You see it, but you aren\'t fast enough to dodge. \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You juke out of the way, mostly. Their move does **-1 damage** to a minimum of 1. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You dodge entirely, and laugh as they hit only air. Their move is **[Tiered Down]**. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: You casually sidestep their attempt at combat, and metaphorically backhand them in return. Maybe you actually do backhand them! Whatever damage would have been done to you, they take instead.'),
('premonition', 'PREMONITION', 'OTHER', 'SEER', '[Class][Free][One-off][Unlock: Seer]', 'You see things as they are presented before you, and you see clearly. Likewise, your memory is equally clear on what you\'ve seen in the past. But sometimes, your mind gives you access to this little flash of... something. Intuition, or a gut feeling… It’s kind of like the hit Gisney Channel series In Which a Young Teal Named Rayven Ceases to Perceive Time As a Linear Construct and Gains Insights Into the Future While Simultaneously Attempting to Navigate the Foibles of Secondary Schoolfeeding, Attempts To Secure Governmental Dispensation For Her Budding Career As a Fashion Designer, and General High-Single-Digit-Sweep-Age Adolescent Life. Or, y’know. Something like that. It’s not magic! Just intuition! Once per encounter, you may make one **[Free]** **GOOD** **[Analyze]** roll.'),
('preparedForAnything', 'PREPARED FOR ANYTHING', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Passive][Locked: Bookworm]', 'You know that it always pays to be prepared, no matter what! Who knows what situations can arise out there? Gosh, you wish you had a Bandaid right now! Bonk, you do. This Juggalo will only let you pass if you give him some Sopor? Boom, you had a feeling. You can buy items on the fly in an encounter, stating that you already had them in your inventory for just such an occasion. You can\'t buy the same item more than once, however!\n\n'),
('primAndProper', 'PRIM AND PROPER', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'You have such a way with words! That’s not always a good thing- sometimes you just sound like you’re reading from a script, and sometimes the words you say are… odd. But you really, really know how to talk, you know? You gain the following **GOOD** WORDPLAY effects.\r\n\r\n> **HASTY INTERRUPTION**: AH- WHAT MY COMPANION MEANT TO SAY IS… you know some people talk before they think. They probably haven’t even rehearsed what they want to say a million times in their head! This is terrible. As a **[Free]** **[Reaction]**, you jump in and stop an ally from saying more, and **[Charm]** the person they were talking to for **2 rounds**. On a **GREAT**, you **[Charm]** them both for **2 rounds**, and on a **MAX**, you **[Fascinate]** them both. Unwind the situation!\r\n\r\n> **REALLY MEAN WORDS**: If you know etiquette, you know the inverse too. So yeah, you know how to be a MASSIVE bitch when you need to! You know how to command your tone like a blade, which can slay even the mighty Snazzard. This move is identical to JAB, except that you can roll it after a **[Strife]** begins, and even creatures immune to **[Manipulate]** are affected by your attacks.\r\n\r\n> **YOU KNOW WHAT I’VE HEARD…** You spin some salacious gossip about someone… oooogh! You get the effects of a PSYCHOANALYZE roll of a troll not present, and share the narrative fluff with the target. Both you and the target are **[Inept]** at **[Mental]** rolls for **1 turn**, because how juicy!\r\n\r\n> **OVERSHARE**: Okay, ew! You say something that… while it might be fine by Indigo terms, is a little too sweaty and gross for other castes. Come on, man! The target is **[Disgusted]** for **2 turns**.'),
('princeparry', 'PRINCEPARRY', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Chicanery][Physical][Locked: Royal]', 'SWISH SWISH SWISH SWISH! You always look so INSANELY graceful that it hurts. You need to be a shining example of perfection, and you hold yourself dearly to those standards. And that means people can\'t step on your toes! When you want to act perfect, roll **+APP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: AUGH— GOD FUCKING— DAMMIT! You hurt yourself and— AUGH! You take **2 [Somatic]** damage and are **[Clumsy]** for the encounter. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: You avoid fucking up at the LAST second! Goddamn! \r\n\r\n**OK**: You\'re on the offensive, and making progress! You gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You advance on the target, looking nothing less than beautiful throughout!! Select one of the following options.\r\n\r\n> **AUTORETORT**: The best offense is a good defense! You get yourself into a prime defensive stance; the first person to make a **[Strife]** roll against you before your next turn takes **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n> **ADVANCE**: You get WAY too close, way too quick! The opponent can\'t roll a **[Mental]** roll next turn.\r\n\r\n> **DUKE DODGE**: You dart from side to side, making it very hard to hit you. Opponents who make **[Physical]** rolls against you until your next turn automatically take **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> **DISARM**: With a quick thrust, you lunge forward, destroying an item worth **2 VP** or less as you shatter it with a decisive blow!\r\n\r\n> **PERFECT FOCUS**: You stop moving, staring down the opponent, and psyching them out. Choose a target; their **[Psionic]** rolls against you next turn are **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n> **WEAVE**: You keep the pressure up, cycling in and out over and over. Your opponent can\'t gain **[Boost]** on their next turn.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Perfect form! You get a **GOOD**, and take **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: GODDAMN! You are untouchable today!! You get a **GOOD**, and take **3 [Boost]**!'),
('princesConquest', 'PRINCE’S CONQUEST', 'OTHER', 'PRINCE', '[Class][Advanced][Physical][Strife][Recharge: 5][Locked: Prince]\r\n', 'Tch. Out of your way! You’re a Prince, and that means you’re dangerous. You’re stubborn, a little bit negative, but for the most part, the word you’d use to describe yourself is… adamant. Your relationship to your aspect is a strange one- while you still adhere to your aspect on a basic level, the way you present yourself to the world can sometimes come across a little more like your aspect’s opposite- like a Prince of Hope acting like a Ragebound troll, or a Prince of Life acting like a Doombound one. But none of that matters- you have a job to do, and if people get in your way, that’s their problem. When you want to wreck shop, roll **+HUB, +PSP** or **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: NGH! Your plan backfires, and your narrative energy short circuits back into you- and it stings. You take **2 [Somatic]** damage and **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Tch. You fail. How uncharacteristic…\r\n\r\n**OK**: It didn’t work as you’d hoped, but you’re not wasting any time. The move gains the **[Recharge: 1]** tag instead of **[Recharge: 5]** this time as you mount another attack.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: WHAM. Your aspect splinters around you as you make a decisive blow! Choose an effect based on your aspect…\r\n\r\n> **TIME**: The target’s sense of time is wounded. The target cannot become **[Quickened]** and all their **[Free]** moves cost an action for **3 rounds**.\r\n> **SPACE**: Stop fucking around. Your target can’t use **[Chicanery]** moves for **3 rounds**.\r\n> **LIFE**: Ouch!!! Your target can’t **[Heal]** their HP for **3 rounds**.\r\n> **DOOM**: Your caveats can’t help you now. The target cannot use **[One-Off]** moves or benefit from **[Last Stand]** effects for **3 rounds**.\r\n> **HOPE**: Fuck your aspirations! Your target loses all **[Positive] [Emotions]**, and can’t gain any for **3 rounds**.\r\n> **RAGE**: Their fury pales compared to yours. Your target loses all **[WHAM]**, and can’t gain any more **[WHAM]** for **3 rounds**.\r\n> **BREATH**: To hell with your freedom. The target becomes **[Slowed]** for **3 rounds**.\r\n> **BLOOD**: Sever the bonds! Your target loses any Mechs, Buggies, Mounts, or other non-player assistance, including access to their Lusus, and stops FRAYMOTIF if they had one going, for **3 rounds**.\r\n> **LIGHT**: Destiny crumbles beneath your target. They lose all **[Boost]**, and can’t gain any more **[Boost]** for **3 rounds**.\r\n> **VOID**: GET OUT OF THERE and fight me barehanded like a real troll! You force your targets to face the music and show themselves. Your target loses all **[Resistances]** for **3 rounds**.\r\n> **HEART**: Back to square one, dipshit. Your target loses all **[Talents]**, and all their **[Legendaries]** instead become **[Talents]**, for **3 rounds**.\r\n> **MIND**: Posit on this, poindexter. Your target’s **[Mental]** rolls are inverted for **3 rounds**; MIN = MAX, GREAT = BAD, GOOD = OK, and vice versa. Any rolls that are still somehow successful are **[Tiered Down]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Your conquest hurts! You get the effects of a **GOOD**, and do **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: FUCK! You ravage the opponent in pain everlasting. You do **2 [Somatic]** damage, gain the effects of a **GOOD**, and the effects last for an extra round. '),
('privateSchoolProdigy', 'PRIVATE SCHOOL PRODIGY', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Passive][Unlock: Student]', 'Indigos are the academics and scholars of troll kind, dabbling in art, philosophy and studies that most would sooner ignore than study in any depth. But to get good at that kind of thing, one must learn it. You attend one of the many prestigious Studyheart Academies that surround the richer sides of town, wear a sweet uniform and study the history and culture of Alternia so that it may live on through you. Choose an academy, which gives you a **[Talent]** and an ability.\r\n\r\n> **Cullscout Superior\'s School For Incorrigible Scamps (+RAS)** You are a troublemaker, assigned to this school at a young age for your already obvious tomfoolery. **[Manipulate]** rolls against you are **[Godawful]**. If someone attempts to **[Manipulate]** you, all your **[Chicanery]** rolls become **[Tiered Up]** for **3 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **Soulglimmer\'s College of the Indisputably Beautiful Arts (+PLC)** Art, food, music… you make things that are gorgeous. You gain access to the ABOMINARTIST, GOREMAND, HAUTE CLAWTURE, or MUSICREANT Template, get the **[Entry]** and **1 [Basic]** now, and it does not count towards your Template limit. All rolls in this use **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n> **Sweetlace\'s School of Exceptional Dances and Performance (+GRA)** You know how to perform for a crowd better than you know how to breathe! You may roll FRAYMOTIF with **+GRA**, and it is **[Buildup: 3]** instead of 4.\r\n\r\n> **The Caegerkrieg Monopolist Institute (+APP)** You\'re a business major. A major GENIUS when it comes to financing, that is! Ho ho ho! You are **Ultrarich**, and you have **12 VP**, not 8.\r\n\r\n> **Lord Armourdent\'s University of Larpic Warfare (+GRT)** You go to a school that encourages the study of history through larping, including exceptionally dangerous weapons and combat. You gain access to one of the following ABSTRATA UPGRADES now; further ones cost **1 LUX**.\r\n\r\n> **ANCIENTKIND [ACTIVE]**: On a **MAX** **[Strife]** roll, you can do 1 less damage in order to **[Slow]** the opponent for **two turns**.\r\n> **MEDIEVALKIND [ACTIVE]**: On a **GREAT** roll, you can do 1 less damage to deal an equal amount of damage to another target present.\r\n> **WARKIND [ACTIVE]**: As a **[Lengthy]** action, you can load this old firearm and take careful aim to gain **1 [WHAM]**.\r\n\r\n> **The Honorable Theodact’s Royal Military Academy (+HUB)** You study politics, tactical combat and warfare, with the goal of one day being a great leader. Whenever you are at **4 HP** or below, you become **[Hopeful]** and can no longer lose your **[WHAM]** until you spend it.\r\n\r\n> **The Pondermuse Seminary for  Theoretical Existence (+PSP)** You think, therefore you think. Science, math, philosophy… academia, baby! You can never be **[Inept]** or **[Tiered Down]** with your **+PSP** moves.\r\n\r\n> **Whisperwind\'s Phrontistery for Students of the Naturally Dubious (+IMG)** You are a student of the occult, taking classes like automatic writing, augury and math. Whenever you are around an **[Eerie]** troll, an **[Entity]** monster or witness an opponent using a **[Magic]** effect, you become **[Enthusiastic]** and gain **1 [Resistance]** to **[Psychic]** damage.'),
('prizedHunter', 'PRIZED HUNTER', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'ORPHANER', '[Template][Advanced][Recharge: 2][Strife][Locked: Orphaner]', 'Orphaners can’t waste time dealing with fretful things such as “trolls defending their parents.” When the world is in your decadent, royal hands, there’s no time to waste! And that means scaring the rabble away from your real targets! When you want to utilize shock and awe, roll **+HUB**.\n\n**MIN**: Your attack not only fails to intimidate, it fails to even hurt. Them, at least. You take **1 [Somatic]** Damage and the **[Recharge]** becomes **[Recharge: 3]** until it can be next used. \n\n**BAD**: You wave your hunting equipment around, but they already kinda figured you were here to orphan.\n\n**OK**: Your attack whizzes by, and it’s kinda freaky. Next turn your target will have any **[Negative]** Emotions inflicted become **[Heightened]**.\n\n**GOOD**: It’s not a fantastic hit, but it’s a hit that hurts. Your target takes **1 [Somatic]** Damage.\n\n**GREAT**: Now git! Go! You put on a show of striking your target, and it’s a good reason to get out of here for anyone watching. Your target takes **2 [Somatic]** Damage. Their allies ABSCOND rolls become **[Legendary]** for a turn; if they don\'t attempt to ABSCOND, they take **1 [Drag]**.\n\n**MAX**: Not a good idea to get in between Glub Glub and her food, stranger! You put all your mall-crushingly tough guyness into the blow, and it looks painful if nothing else! Your target takes **3 [Somatic]** Damage. Their allies ABSCOND rolls become **[Legendary]** for a turn; if they don\'t attempt to ABSCOND, they take **4 [Drag]**.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('problemSleuthing', 'PROBLEM SLEUTHING', 'OTHER', 'UNIVERSAL', '[Analyze][Mental]', 'You are feeling particularly hard boiled tonight. Alternia isn’t always upfront and honest, so sometimes you gotta put your thinkpan to work and get investigating. Each individual **PROBLEM SLEUTHING** option has its own **[Recharge: 2]**. When you want to use information to your benefit, roll **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You dumb piece of shit. You\'re wrong as fuck, and you don\'t even know it. You totally misinterpret your surroundings. Your next 3 rolls are **[Tiered Down]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Hmmmmm. Yeah, chief, you don’t know about this one. Your next roll is **[Tiered Down]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Okay, you haven’t quite picked up on what the fuck is going on, but you’re putting the clues together. Your next **PROBLEM SLEUTHING** roll is **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Eureka! You’ve figured it out! Select one of the following results.\r\n\r\n> **PSYCHOANALYZE**: You delve deep into the psychology of the opponent; you may ask a question about them like their intention, their abilities or their actions. Your next roll with the target is **[Talented]**.\r\n\r\n> **INVESTIGATE**: You find something interesting, like an alleyway to hide in, a swinging vine or a loose banana peel. This allows you to add a narrative device to the encounter that you could feasibly use to your advantage to further the story (\"Hey, I\'m gonna swing from that vine I saw earlier to chase the bad guy!\"). You get **1 [Hold]**, letting you get a **+2 [Buff]** on a roll involving this object or location. You might also use this to figure out how to use a machine, solve a puzzle, etc.\r\n\r\n> **PREPARE**: Okay, so here\'s the plan… you take a moment to iron out any flaws in your risky strategy and prevent the worst. If your next roll is a **BAD** or **OK**, it **[Tiers Up]**. If it\'s a **GOOD** or **GREAT**, you get **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **SPOT**: I can see you, bitch! You remove the **[Hidden]** condition from a target. This option has no **[Recharge]**.\r\n\r\n> **REASSESS**: Sometimes you need to back up and ask \"what am I doing wrong?\". Like you just did now! You reduce your **[Drag]** by **3**; this does not give you **[Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **SCOUT**: You look around, getting a feel for what your surroundings are like; you ask about how many trolls are around, what dangers there might be, etc. Your **ORDER UP** roll for **LET\'S STRIFE** is **[Talented]** whenever it pops up.\r\n\r\n> **OUTSMART**: Not so fast!! You think and act faster than the target, chipping away at their advantage. The target loses **3 [Boost]**; this does not give them **[Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> **EVALUATE**: Can you take this bitch? You look a target up and down, and figure out their character level, **[Talent]** and one of their moves. If you\'re a higher level than them, you become **[Smug]**. If they\'re a higher level than you, your **ABSCOND** rolls become **[Talented]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You sleuth the shit out of this problem! You get a **GOOD**, and gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: LIGHTNING FAST! This mystery completely unravels before you! You get a **GOOD** plus **3 [Boost]**.'),
('problemSolver', 'PROBLEM SOLVER', 'TIME', 'TIME', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Time]', 'You understand by now that problems aren’t always solved by charging right in; sometimes, figuring out all angles of the issue can really open up some doors. Any time you use a rolled **[Analyze]** move, you gain a **[Hold]**; a **GOOD** **[Hold]** when you get a **GOOD**, a **GREAT** for a **GREAT** and a **MAX** for a **MAX**. You can use this **[Hold]** to automatically take that result on a single roll that relies on narrative information gleaned from the **[Analyze]** move. Ie.: I know their weak point, so I’ll **[Strife]** \'em hard! I know their morals, so I’ll use that to **[Manipulate]** them! I know what they have in their pocket, I’ll YOINK it!'),
('productPlacement', 'PRODUCT PLACEMENT', 'OTHER', 'MAID', '[Class][Advanced][Locked: Maid]', 'Patent that shit, cuz this is one-of-a-kind! You’ve gotten very used to problem solving by now, and have even developed your own type of items that help you with all your clever tricks and solutions. You gain an item based on your **[Aspect]**. It is 0 **VP**, cannot be **YOINKED**, is **[Consumable]**, and refreshes at the beginning of a thread. It takes an action to use your item.\r\n\r\n> **TIME**: TEMPO items keep you on beat and on track! You ignore the next **[Slow]** or **[Stun]** you would receive.\r\n\r\n> **SPACE**: UNIVERSAL items can be used for a variety of things, meaning you have a solution for almost every problem! You get a +2 **[Buff]** to your next non **GRIEF UNIVERSAL MOVE** roll.\r\n\r\n> **LIFE**: FLOURISHING items are just what you need to make yourself feel good as new! Your next **[Heal]** either ignores **[Bloodied]** or gives you +1 **HP**.\r\n\r\n> **DOOM**: GROUNDING items are there for you to keep you focused. All things will pass, including the bad. You clear all **[Negative] [Emotion]**s.\r\n\r\n> **HOPE**: BLESSED items make you feel blessed to be alive, despite it all! You feel **[Peaceful]**.\r\n\r\n> **RAGE**: DRIVING items makes you feel FUCKING ENERGIZED! RAAAAAH! If you\'re **[Enraged]** or **[Out Of Control]**, you gain 3 **[Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **BREATH**: LIGHTWEIGHT items keep you light on your feet, breezing past your troubles. You become **[Quickened]** for 3 rounds. \r\n\r\n> **BLOOD**: INVIGORATING items get your blood pumping and staves off doubt! You clear all **[Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> **LIGHT**: SIGNATURE items are your brand and put YOU in the spotlight! You become **[Confident]**!\r\n\r\n> **VOID**: LOWKEY items are simple, but always there for you. You clear all debilitating Status Effects.\r\n\r\n> **HEART**: SENTIMENTAL items are here to remind you what it\'s all about in the end. You become **[Happy]**.\r\n\r\n> **MIND**: FOCUSED items bring mental clarity and the energy to succeed at a plan. You ignore the next **[Nerf]** or **[Tier Down]** that targets you.'),
('properPosture', 'PROPER POSTURE', 'OTHER', 'SERVICESQUIRE', '[Template][Advanced][Free][Reaction][Locked: Servicesquire]', 'Not so fast! Adversaries may try to enforce terrible conditions on you, but you’re not about to just fall over like some kind of uncouth normie! After all, you’ve trained in being able to run through a warzone with a cup of tea without spilling it. Whenever you are subject to a physical status effect, you can choose to ignore it, taking **3 [Drag]** instead. You’d rather have back pain than something worth worrying about, like bleeding to death!\r\n\r\n'),
('protagonistSyndrome', 'PROTAGONIST SYNDROME', 'HOPE', 'HOPE', '[Aspect][Basic][Free][Recharge: 1][Locked: Hope]', 'The world revolves around you. That\'s not you being proud, or narcissistic— whether you like it or not, you genuinely believe that you are the main character of your story. Therefore, it\'s on you to do the hard jobs no one else can take. No, this doesn\'t weigh you down! Ever! You can voluntarily choose to **[Tier Up]** any of your rolls by one tier, but you gain an amount of **[Drag]** equal to how much higher the next tier would have been. For example, if you rolled a 13, you can make it a 14 and therefore a **GREAT** for **1 [Drag]**. However, if you had rolled an 11, you would gain **3 [Drag]** to make it a 14. Your opponents can’t make you use this **[Drag]** until your next turn.'),
('protectiveInstincts', 'PROTECTIVE INSTINCTS', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Physical][Locked: Draquestrian]', 'Teal Offices Manager: young enpece you are GROUNDED!!!! you are not allowed to compete in the snazzard competition\r\n\r\n**enpece: no teal offices manager please *runs away and almost gets hit by a train but then the snazzard pushes it out of the way*\r\n\r\nTeal Offices Manager: fucjkfidnb maybe that\'s a good snazzard after all\r\n\r\nYour Snazzard is well accustomed to keeping you out of danger. When you want your Snazzard to protect you, have it roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Uh. It, uh. It attacks you. Sorry. You take **2 [Somatic]** damage as your Snazzard mauls you.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: It jostles you around, and you take **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Inspiring… your Snazzard kinda protects you. Not very well, though. You take **1 [Boost]**. \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: OKAY FINALLY IT PROTECTS YOU. Choose one of the following options.\r\n\r\n> **BODY BLOCK**: No hitting master! Your Snazzard throws itself in the way of an attack meant for you! While you both take damage, your Snazzard takes the extra effects of a **[Strife]** roll you just took, such as **[Drag]** or a status condition.\r\n\r\n> **SNAP**: NO BUFFING IN THE SNAZZARD\'S REACH. Your opponent\'s **[Flourish]** rolls are **[Inept]** next turn.\r\n\r\n> **BUGGYFLIP**: No running away! Your Snazzard flips a Large or smaller VEHICLE over, making it impossible to use until you BUGGYFLIP it back, or several beefy trolls do it for you.\r\n\r\n> **TAIL WHIP**: CRACK! GET BACK! No coming too close! **[Chicanery]** rolls against you are **[Inept]** next turn.\r\n\r\n> **RAAAAAWR**: You roar, but in a graceful kind of way. Also, the target is **[Deafened]** for **2 turns** because of you. No hearing things!\r\n\r\n> **ESCAPE**: DASHDASHDASHDASH! You ignore the normal roll requirement for a Hazard, using this instead. No falling to terrible disasters!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: That\'ll do, dragon. That\'ll do. You get a **GOOD**, and **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Holy shit, dragon! You get a **GOOD**, and **3 [Boost]**!'),
('protectiveWards', 'PROTECTIVE WARDS', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Slayer]', 'Congratulations! If you\'ve gotten this far as a Slayer, that means you\'ve survived longer than most others. That\'s because unlike most others, you know to protect yourself. Carrying around magic talismans, special herbs, all that good shit, you protect yourself from the most dangerous of situations. You gain one of the following immunities depending on your target of choice.\r\n\r\n> 1. **VAMPYRS**: **[Bloodied]**.\r\n> 2. **LYCANTHROPES**: **[Bloodied]**.\r\n> 3. **PHANTASMS**: **[Negative]** Emotions.\r\n> 4. **WIGHTS**: Disease **[Afflictions]**.\r\n> 5. **VVITCHES**: **[Control]** effects.\r\n> 6. **CAVITIES**: **[Quickened]** opponents (you keep them at your pace).\r\n'),
('provachancelor', 'PROVACHANCELOR', 'CERULEAN', 'ADULT', '[Cerulean][Locked: Adult]', 'How does one deal with an unknown society of aliens? The answer is you. Provachancelors are sent in to infiltrate and just. Go do what they do best. Which is muck around, fuck around, and find out. They cause a bit of chaos to gauge how hostile enemy politics are. What better way to find out if guns or diplomacy are more a nation\\\'s style? Plus, it gives you an outlet for some of your more destructive tendencies. Win-win. Whenever you roll **WORDPLAY**, you can do it with **+GRT** instead. No, you didn’t see me, and if you did I’ll make sure you didn’t. Understood? Cool. Your **REQUEST** and **RILE** rolls also **[Tier Up]**, and for **REQUEST** rolls the **[Drag]** inflicted from refusing to follow orders is 2, not 1 as you throw in a couple extra threats.'),
('psideySense', 'PSIDEY SENSE', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Passive][Psionic]', 'Adept psion or not, part of being a member of a caste of walking founts of energy means you kinda get a sense for the psionic fields people give off. It\'s hard to explain to non-psions. It\'s just, like, the vibes of the static you can feel around certain people, you know? (They don\'t.) You can immediately identify if a troll is part of a **[Psionic]** tree and what tree they\'re a part of- I see you, cerulean mastermind pretending to be a regular spiderpunk! **[Psionic]** trolls\' rolls to become **[Hidden]** from you are inept. This move flat-out doesn\'t work on lime psionics and doesn\'t reeeeally work on psionic mutants. You can kinda tell that something\'s off with their vibes, though, even if you don\'t know what, exactly- your **[Analyze]** rolls against Psions can never be **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]** or **[Nerfed]**.'),
('psimates', 'PSIMATES', 'OTHER', 'MUTANT', '[Mutant][Psionic][Passive]', 'You are a unique variation of siblings- you were not just born from the same egg, but draw from the same pool of psionic energy as well! You are unique individuals with your own personalities, aspirations and minds, but your psychic bond means that your powers all draw from the same shared psionic core- additionally, emotions will easily leak across this bond from one psimate to another. Someone gives you a wedgie and calls you a weenie? Your psimate across the schoolfeedingroom is probably feeling pretty **[Humiliated]** right now even if they weren\'t paying attention at all! \r\nMechanically, psimates share a move economy, which means that being a psimate does not allow you to roll the same move twice in a turn. Psimates are permanently **[Quickened]**, giving the pair a total of **3 actions** per turn. Additionally, psimates are **[Talented]** in **+IMG**, and if they were already **[Talented]** they’d take a **+2 [Buff]** as well to every psionic move. Psimates share HP, which is split between the two bodies. If it’s an uneven number, choose a psimate to have more HP. If one psimates gains an **[Emotional]** condition, the other also has it. Psimates cannot be apart without experiencing immense psychic pain, so you must thread with both nearby each other at all times. You can take this further, having triplets with HP split between the three of them. You can only take this mutation if you are a Rust, Bronze, Gold, Lime, Cerulean or Purple.'),
('psionicEruption', 'PSIONIC ERUPTION', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Passive][Psionic]', 'FACE… YOUR TRUE POOOOWEEEEER! KYAAAAAAAH! When you drop below half your max HP, gain a **[Heightened][Emotion]** or get **3 BAD** or lower rolls in a row, as a **[Free]** **[Reaction]** you can choose to gain the PSIBURN **[Affliction]** and start at Stage 1, so long as you have the ability to use **[Psionics]**. You become **[Talented]** at **+IMG** for the **[Affliction]** if you weren\'t. If you didn\'t have a **[Psionic][Strife]** move, you can use GRIEF with **+IMG** and the **[Psionic]** tag instead of the **[Physical]** one; this move does **[Psychic]** damage and is called PSISPLODE. You can only use PSISPLODE during PSIBURN.'),
('psionicGaze', 'PSIONIC GAZE', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Passive][Psionic]', 'Your psionic tricks have grown in power! You gain an extra selection of effects from SEEING DOUBLE. If you do not already have SEEING DOUBLE, you cannot gain this move.\n\n> **JUST REGULAR FUCKING EYES**: Despite not having cool and interesting eyes, you\'ve picked up some extra psionics! Select two options from VISION TWOFOLD.\n\n> **RED**: STOP RIGHT THERE. You can **[Trap]** opponents with a PSIGRAPPLE, freezing them in place!\n\n> **ORANGE**: You overload a gadget with potential energy, and… ITEMSPLODE! You do **2 [Psychic]** damage to an item.\n\n> **YELLOW**: Whatcha thinking about? You figure out the target\'s next 2 moves; they must use these moves, even if it would be stupid to after you and some allies set up.\n\n> **GREEN**: Take THAT! You tilt your head and your opponent feels weak thanks to your ENERGY SAP. You take 2 of their **[Boost]** for yourself.\n\n> **BLUE**: HOPE YOU LIKE PAIN, BITCH! You ELECTROLOCK the target, meaning **[Strife]** rolls that deal **[Electric]** damage can\'t be lower than a **GOOD** against them for **2 turns**.\n\n> **PURPLE**: FOOOORCE FIELD! You raise a hand and block your allies with a purple bubble, making attack rolls against a designated target **[Inept]** next turn.\n\n> **GREY**: Heal… heal… heal… the numbing static of your gaze **[Heals]** the target **1 HP**.'),
('psionicMagnet', 'PSIONIC MAGNET', 'OTHER', 'VOIDROT', '[Template][Advanced][Free][Reaction][Recharge: 2][Locked: Voidrot] \r\n', 'Your energy-draining abilities have grown precise enough that every once in a while, you can just. Simply snatch up some psionics that were meant for someone else. Trying to make a friend spill the beans? Enjoy this cringe anime kinlist! Or just, jump in front of some eye beams, I guess?? As a **[Free]** **[Reaction]**, you can redirect a **[Psionic]** **[Strife]** move meant for someone else onto you, or shield yourself from one already coming your way. In the latter scenario, it deals **-1 point of damage**, which is converted into **1 [Reserve]** for you as your powers eat away at it.\r\n\r\n'),
('psiwrangle', 'PSIWRANGLE', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Recharge: 3][Control][Psionic][Locked: Summoner]', 'You get lusii on a level nobody else does thanks to your innate connection to them. That means you GET lusii. That also means you can GET lusii, you know what I mean? When faced with a lusus you aren\'t controlling, you can attempt to bring them under your spell. If you\'ve met a particular lusus before, you can attempt to control that specific lusus from a distance. Roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Oh you motherfucker. The lusus is **[Out-Of-Control]**, prioritizing attacking you before anyone else. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: They didn\'t like that you did that! The lusus is **[Enraged]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Not terrible! You can choose the Lusus\' next target, but little more than that.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Aha! You sway it! You control the lusus, making it do any 1 action of your choice. If used on a **[Custodian]**, they use their Feature as a **GOOD** ALTRICIALIZE roll. If the **[Custodian]** belongs to an enemy, it doesn\'t trigger the Feature\'s **[One-Off]** for the enemy, just for you.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Whoo-ee! Skip that Lusus\' next turn, cuz you decide what it does if anything! If used on a **[Custodian]**, they use their Feature as a **GREAT** ALTRICIALIZE roll.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Gods swim at your feet. You get a **GREAT**, but you do this for **3 turns**! If used on a **[Custodian]**, they use their Feature as a **MAX** ALTRICIALIZE roll.'),
('psuperiorPsionics', 'PSUPERIOR PSIONICS', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Mastermind]', 'Your mind is a fortress, and you cannot, WILL NOT, humour those who would lay siege to it! In other words, NYEHHHH, your psionics rule, and theirs DROOL! You exude a latent telepathic web of supression that causes all enemy **[Psionic]** rolls to be **[Inept]**.'),
('psychicDoubleReacharound', 'PSYCHIC DOUBLE REACHAROUND', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Passive][Psionic][Locked: Mastermind]', 'Your psionics have grown to be particularly powerful, to the extent that you don’t need to have someone look into your eyes for your manipulation to influence them. If you have rolled FREAKY EYE on an opponent within the last week, you focus and see through their eyes, giving you the ability to use FREAKY EYE as if you were present. They can hear your voice as you \"suggest\" things to them, and may roll WORDPLAY on them. Doing so is draining for you; you are **[Tired]** for an hour after using this move.'),
('publicityStunt', 'PUBLICITY STUNT', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][One-Off][Locked: Celebrity]', 'Sometimes, things are NOT going your way! Like, at all! This is supposed to be YOUR show, so why are the others more popular than you right now?! This can\'t be! There\'s only one thing for it… you need to totally shake up the airwaves! YES, it\'s risky, but fame as a whole is a risk, darlings, so let\'s leave behind a beautiful corpse! You can choose to make a roll **[Tiered Down]** and **[Godawful]**; if you don\'t roll a **MIN**, then… surprise! You did it for attention! As you clap your hands and your loyal fans gasp, everyone wonders if you\'ve been doing intentionally poorly on purpose throughout! Genius! Now nobody knows what to believe! All trolls must roll 1d20, and their POPS are reassigned based on how above or below a 10 they got. For example, rolling a 7 puts them at **-3 POPS**, but rolling a 19 puts them at **9 POPS**. You get to roll twice and take the higher result!'),
('punchingUp', 'PUNCHING UP', 'OTHER', 'PRINCE', '[Class][Advanced][Reaction][Recharge: 4][Locked: Prince]', 'In the past you’ve picked on and screwed over those you saw as beneath you. Mainly… to make yourself feel good as some weird fucked up coping mechanism. It’s hard, but you’re trying to unlearn such habits. And hey! It doesn’t mean you can’t screw people over anymore! Rich douches, crypto pros and villains alike are free game for bullying. Who better to knock them down a few pegs than someone who had to be knocked down a few pegs? When someone rolls a **GREAT** or **MAX** in front of you, you may step in as a **[Reaction]** after their attack and deal an immediate 1 **[Unblockable]** damage to them. Not so high and mighty now, huh shitlips?\r\n'),
('punishTheWicked', 'PUNISH THE WICKED', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Passive]', 'You\'ve read the Clown Bible many times now, and have discovered the original teachings of the Messiahs, while still violent, were not… as senseless as you\'ve been led to believe. It\'s all about killing people who REALLY suck, like perverts, bigots or what have you. Which is WILDLY warped compared to what you\'re told these days! You really think people would just… lie about the things a major religion preaches to further their own hateful purposes? That\'s awful! Point is, you\'ve got your own vigilante beliefs about the Messiahs now, and your violence is more narrowly targeted. You can roll PROBLEM SLEUTHING to JUDGE THE WICKED. You find out, from the Clouder or other players perspective, if the character you\'re judging has a clean conscience, and if they\'re more likely to have a JUST or HEROIC death. You can only JUDGE THE WICKED against a target once, until something happens that might make you change your mind. This effect is otherwise permanent.\r\n\r\n> **HEROIC**: Hrrrm. They\'re not as bad as you might think. You become **[Hopeful]**, and your WORDPLAY rolls on the target **[Tier Up]**.\r\n\r\n> **JUST**: Uh oh. Looks like someone needs to be punished, whoop whoop! Your **[Strife]** rolls against this target can\'t be affected by **[Drag]**, they can\'t be **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]** or **[Nerfed]**, and they can\'t make you feel negative **[Emotions]**. They\'ve got this one coming!'),
('pupilPeril', 'PUPIL PERIL', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Passive][Psionic]', 'Cerulean genetics are rife with minor eye mutations that give them unusual psychic abilities. Not all Ceruleans have them, but you might! You can roll a specialized version of SHENANIGANS called HYPNOGAZE, which loses the **[Physical]** tag for the **[Psionic]** one, and uses **+IMG**. Select two of the following options, one for each eye, or select the one option twice and decrease your HP by 1. You can have additional eyes; each additional eye you have decreases your total HP by 1. Watch out! \r\n\r\n> **0 PUPILS**: Your blank eye can DREADSPIKE the target; if they have a negative **[Emotion]**, it becomes **[Dread]**. Ooogh… \r\n\r\n> **1 PUPIL**: That\'s just a regular eye, fool! Your PROBLEM SLEUTHING rolls to SPOT are **[Tiered Up]**. This is not a HYPNOGAZE roll, and you are not **[Psionic]**. You can’t have this option more than once (unless you have more than 2 eyes) if you’re a Mastermind troll.\r\n\r\n> **2 PUPILS**: Your pupils invert and revert in a TRIPPYQUENCE, **[Disgusting]** the target on a subconscious level. \r\n\r\n> **3 PUPILS**: HAAAA! You VERTIGOGOGO your target, giving them zero balance! They can\'t get up from being **[Floorbound]** unless they succeed on a PCHOOOOOOOO SWASHBUCKLE roll for **2 turns**. \r\n\r\n> **4 PUPILS**: Huh? Whuh? Where\'d they go? With your PEEPERDEFOCUSIZATION you can make people\'s eyes unfocus really hard, going **[Hidden]** and making their first SPOT roll against you **[Lengthy]**. If they were **[Giggling]**, or otherwise can\'t make **[Lengthy]** moves, the roll is **[Tiered Down]**.\r\n\r\n> **5 PUPILS**: Nnnngh! Headache! Your MIGRAINEBOMB gives the target a splitting headache, making their next **[Mental]** or **[Psionic]** roll **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n> **6 PUPILS**: Huuuuh? What just happened? Your AMNESIAWINK can erase the memories of those around you, increasing the **[Recharge]** of a move by 1.\r\n\r\n> **7 PUPILS**: Bad luck, bitch!! Your NEUROJINX makes the target **[Clumsy]** for **2 turns**. If they were already **[Clumsy]**, this effect stacks.\r\n\r\n> **8 PUPILS**: Your OCULOLURE eye makes the target **[Charmed]** as they\'re lulled into a state of compliance. Classic!'),
('putYourselfFirst', 'PUT YOURSELF FIRST', 'LIFE', 'LIFE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Life]\r\n', 'You’ve learned it’s no good constantly putting others’ needs before your own, and you’ve been taking baby steps in getting your own needs taken care of before anyone else’s. Sorry, you can’t help, you’re practicing self-care! While you have allies with more current HP than you, when you **[Heal]** yourself you gain **1 [Boost]** for each point of HP you regain - it feels pretty great to put your needs first for once!\r\n'),
('quantumFlicker', 'QUANTUM FLICKER', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][One-Off][Magic][Psionic][Locked: AU]', 'You aren\'t from around here… in fact, you have one foot on the other side! You can blink in and out of reality, appearing and disappearing like a faulty lightbulb. When you want to dip back home, roll the stat you became **[Talented]** in through ALTERNATE UNIVERSE.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Oof, grounded!! You can\'t move! Your opponent\'s next **[Strife]** roll against you is a guaranteed **MAX**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Yikes, this is gonna hurt! You flicker right into someone\'s attack. Your opponent\'s next **[Strife]** roll is **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: It… kinda works? You get a **GOOD**, but it only lasts **one turn**. Oops!\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Flickerflickerflicker! You vanish in and out of reality, hopping back and forth between worlds. Every time your target rolls a **[Strife]** roll at you, roll 1d8. On a 1, the roll immediately fails, **[Tiering Down]** to at least an **OK**. This lasts **3 rounds**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Whoa, you\'re flickering a LOT! You get a **GOOD**, but the opponent fails on a 1 or a 2.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Holy dimension drifting! You\'re barely even here! You get a **GREAT**, but the opponent fails on a 1, 2, 7 or 8!'),
('quarterbackQuonquerer', 'QUARTERBACK QUONQUERER', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Passive][Unlock: Jock]', 'You are a fan of the competitive arts: Muscle Theatre. Kaijuball. Golf Without Limits. You are STRONG, you are ENTHUSIASTIC and you’re a little less intelligent than some of your peers, but that’s okay, because you don’t need brains, you have BRAWN! You are a star athlete, most certainly taking part in the Studyheart Champiolympics, interschool leagues of all types of assorted sports. You LOVE sports, and you LOOOOVE leagues! Bless your heart, you little thembo. You are **[Talented]** at **+GRT**. Any time you roll the same move as an opponent directly after them, you gain **1 [Boost]**, because you just have to show them you’re the better one here, buddy! Moves with the **[Strife]** tag can be rolled after any other **[Strife]** move for this purpose; for example, if a Gold Cyberpunk uses TRUNCTUATE on their turn, you may still take your bonus if you roll GRIEF on your turn. This **[Boost]** increases to 2 if you roll higher than them, numerically! GO HOOFBEASTS!'),
('questgiver', 'QUESTGIVER', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Magic][Locked: Narrator]', 'Do you know what an inciting incident is? It\'s the thing that kick-starts a story, the introduction of something NEW into a character\'s life that will take them on a journey. While it can often be anything from \"your friend has been kidnapped by an evil Snazzard!\" to \"a strange noise is coming from your kitchen\", you specialise in the art of giving quests. You may give a QUEST to a single troll or a group of them; retrieve a particular item for me, slay a monster, break into this dude\'s hive, etc. The QUEST cannot be completed in the same encounter as the one you are presently in; it must be its own thing, and you can\'t join them on this QUEST. You can psionically view participants remotely, and even communicate to them (though only cryptically and vaguely, as if narrating their tale). You can use any of your Narrator moves on participants of your QUEST from a distance, but you only get **1 action** every **2 turns** if you participate in this fashion.\r\n\r\nThe QUEST can\'t be something the party was already planning on doing, in character or out— that\'s just cheating! Use this move to introduce NEW quests to players! The target gets a +1 to all their rolls while completing the quest, and at the end, you can give them **Treasure I**. You gain this Treasure too!'),
('quickAdjustments', 'QUICK ADJUSTMENTS', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Recharge: 2][Locked: Inventor]', '**OKAY— HOLD ON, NO, I\'VE GOT THIS— You\'re used to machines going a little haywire in your hands. You\'ve also gotten used to solving problems the moment they arise! When you want to salvage a move you just rolled this turn, roll **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: AW FUCK, YOU MADE IT WORSE. You retroactively turn your last roll into a **MIN**; if it was already a **MIN**, your opponent gets a free **MAX** result. That\'s what you get for playing god!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: MYEH! Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Stable? Stable. You guess. Your last roll retroactively becomes an **OK** roll. \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: C\'MON, WORK— AHA! IT WORKED! Your last roll retroactively becomes a **GOOD**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Yes, there, okay! See? All according to plan. Your last roll retroactively becomes a **GREAT**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: (that one choir note from gangsta\'s paradise blares) YOU DID THE IMPOSSIBLE. Your last roll retroactively becomes a **MAX**.'),
('quixoticBoast', 'QUIXOTIC BOAST', 'OTHER', 'PAGE', '[Class][Basic][Free][Recharge: 2][Locked: Page]', 'It\'s, uh, all in the presentation! Yeah! Watch, if you act like you know EXACTLY what you\'re doing... As a **[Free]** action, you may attempt to make one of your rolls better, but it\'s risky. Roll a 1d8. On an even number, your next roll **[Tiers Down]**, which can possibly become a **MIN**. On an odd number, your next roll **[Tiers Up]**, which could possibly become a **MAX**!\n\n'),
('ransack', 'RANSACK', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Physical][Strife][Locked: Dungeoneer]', 'Look man! There\'s a LOT of monsters in the winding passages beneath the surface. You think that you can become an expert Dungeoneer just by running fast? Wrong, dipshit! You gotta STRIFE! When you want to fight for your life, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You fool! You throw yourself into the jaws of danger, but you don\'t have a backup plan! You take **2 [Somatic]** damage and become **[Bloodied]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Okay, that was kinda super stupid, not gonna lie, but you got out before any real harm was done. You take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Not great, but you don\'t put yourself in any danger. You take **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: WHAM! That\'s what I\'m talking about! You do **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: CLEAVE! You do **2 [Somatic]** damage, or **1 [Somatic]** damage and give yourself **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You\'re unstoppable! Did you see that? You cut through like a rock, and it split in two! That\'s AWESOME! You do **3 [Somatic]** damage, and give yourself **3 [Boost]**.'),
('rantRantRant', 'RANT RANT RANT', 'RAGE', 'RAGE', '[Aspect][Basic][Locked: Rage]', 'You don’t need to be smart or eloquent about your words; you just need to say them with enough force that they stick. You can use your **+HUB** to use WORDPLAY rolls to **[Strife]**. When you use WORDPLAY like this, you can choose to do **1 less damage** against the target on a **GREAT** roll to give them the **[Dread]** condition as they feel overwhelmed by your angry lecturing. If someone throws a punch during a WORDPLAY duel, you can immediately become **[Enraged]**.'),
('razzledazzle', 'RAZZLEDAZZLE', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Physical][Strife][Locked: Circusfolk]', 'Violence and bloodshed are not uncommon in the ring. It\'s what the people come for! To be entertained! And if you\'re still here, why, you must be an excellent entertainer. When you want to show your moves, roll the stat you gained a **[Talent]** in with ROLL UP, ROLL UP!\r\n\r\n**MIN**: YOU SLIP ON A BANANA PEEL! HOOOONK… you take **3 [Somatic]** damage and fall **[Floorbound]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Your reckless tomfoolery just gets you hurt! You take **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**OK**: While it isn\'t a hit, you still put on a passable show! You take **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: WHOOMP! That\'s a hit! The target takes **1 [Somatic]** damage!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: KAWHOOOOMP! You hit hard, and make a show out of it! You deal **2 [Somatic]** damage, or **1 [Somatic]** damage and the following effect based on your trick…\r\n\r\n> **COMEDIAN (+RAS)**: You crack wise while doing your thing, and you think you\'re very funny. Your next SHENANIGANS roll gets a **+2 [Buff]**.\r\n> **ANIMAL TAMER (+PLC)**: SIC EM! Your monster **[Bloodies]** the target.\r\n> **ACROBAT (+GRA)**: FLIPFLIPFLIPFLIPFLIP— you **[Tier Up]** your next SWASHBUCKLE roll.\r\n> **CARNY (+APP)**: You don\'t fuck with people trying to outplay you! If the target makes a **[Chicanery]** roll next turn, it\'s **[Godawful]**.\r\n> **STRONGMAN (+GRT)**: You toss the target so hard they go flying, and get **[Trapped]** in their impact crater!\r\n> **DAREDEVIL (+HUB)**: You crash and flip and do all kinds of shit! Your target is **[Agitated]** for a turn.\r\n> **RINGMASTER (+PSP)**: IT SEEEEMS YOU COULD NOT MAKE IT TO MY SHOW! Your voice booms as you demean the target, **[Deafening]** them for **2 rounds**. \r\n> **MAGICIAN (+IMG)**: Is this your card? You swap out up to **3 VP** of items in your Sylladex for an equal amount of item **VP** from theirs.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Now THAT\'S show business, baby. You do **3 [Somatic]** damage, or 2 and the effect from your trick.'),
('readLikeABook', 'READ LIKE A BOOK', 'OTHER', 'SEER', '[Class][Advanced][Reaction][Locked: Seer]', 'Predictable. You sometimes have flashes of déjà vu so powerful it\'s like a perfect premonition. It can feel at times that every action that will ever happen has already happened, or that you\'re simply skipping forward a few pages and reading them in advance. This reaction\'s triggers vary based on your aspect. When you want to foresee a target\'s actions, roll **+GRA, +PSP** or **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Oh, that\'s fun. You foresee your entire life, past and present, in a single brief, pathetic blip. Oh, you\'re **[Dissociating]**, that\'s fun. And you took **2 [Psychic]** damage? Oh joy!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You don\'t foresee shit, boy! You waste your **[Reaction]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You get only a split second to react. Your opponent does what they want, but takes **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Exactly as expected. Your target does what you expect, and you react accordingly. You gain one of the following effects…\r\n\r\n> **TIME**: You foresee the target attempting to change tempo, and you change to match. If your target becomes **[Quickened]**, this reaction makes you **[Quickened]** too for as long as they are.\r\n\r\n> **SPACE**: You refuse to allow common bullshittery to catch you by surprise. When the target rolls **[Chicanery]** against you, it becomes **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n> **LIFE**: You almost had me, didn\'t you? When you are about to be knocked to 0 **HP**, you immediately heal back up 1 **HP**. \r\n\r\n> **DOOM**: Cute. You\'re going to die too, some day. You know that, don\'t you?When someone is about to knock you to 0 **HP**, you deal 1 **[Unblockable] [Somatic]** damage. If you knock them out with this roll, you don\'t go down.\r\n\r\n> **HOPE**: I\'ll do my best too, if you will! Whenever the opponent uses **[Boost]**, you can use this reaction to gain an amount of **[Boost]** equal to half the amount they used rounded up. \r\n\r\n> **RAGE**: Yeah, hit me, I bet you fucking wanna. When the opponent uses **[WHAM]** on you, you gain an equal amount of **[WHAM]** right back as a **[Reaction]**. This does not apply to FINISHING MOVE.\r\n\r\n> **BREATH**: Interpersonal accountability? You don’t know her. When an opponent tries to roll a **[Control]** or **[Manipulate]** against you or an ally, you may spend a **[Reaction]** to **[Tier Down]** the result.\r\n\r\n> **BLOOD**: The power of friendship, huh? When an ally tries to roll a **[Control]** or **[Manipulate]** against you or an ally, you may spend a **[Reaction]** to **[Tier Up]** the result.\r\n\r\n> **LIGHT**: I know you\'re trying to succeed here, darling, but have you considered that I am too? When an opponent **[Tiers Up]** a move, as a **[Reaction]** you can **[Tier Down]** the same move immediately to cancel it out.\r\n\r\n> **VOID**: Oh, my, I don\'t think I\'ll be fading into obscurity on your terms. When an opponent **[Tiers Down]** one of your moves, as a reaction, you can **[Tier Up]** the same move immediately to cancel it out.\r\n\r\n> **HEART**: Have you ever read Troll Joseph Campbell? His thesis on how there\'s only so many character archetypes in the world seems to have some meat to it… when an opponent rolls an **[Aspect]** move against you, you can make it **[Inept]** as a **[Reaction]**.\r\n\r\n> **MIND**: Tactics? Used to best me? I think not! You unravel an opponent\'s plans and instantly counter them. When an opponent rolls a **[Class]** move against you, you can make it **[Inept]** as a **[Reaction]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Heh, it’s like they WANTED you to counter them! you gain a **GOOD** effect and 2 **[Boost]**. If your option gives a benefit like **HP** or damage, it increases by 1.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: FUUUUUUTUUUREEEEE! You get a **GOOD** result, 4 **[Boost]**, and this move becomes **[Recharge: 3]**. If your option gives a benefit like **HP** or damage, it increases by 2.'),
('readyPlayerOne', 'READY PLAYER ONE', 'OTHER', 'HEIR', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Heir]', 'Whether you’re dark and brooding or lucky and plucky, you’ve got a leading role in life, even if you’ve never realized it (and yeah, you probably haven’t). All that to say, well - being fate’s preferred protagonist has its perks! You gain access to HERO MODE now, and can use both the **HALLOWED HEROISM** options as well as a unique option from this move:\r\n\r\n> **CALL TO ADVENTURE**: You are the hero - it’s you! You gain the effects of a **GOOD FRAYMOTIF** roll, and your next roll **[Tiers Up]**, even to a **MAX** if possible - if it doesn’t go to a **MAX**, you get 2 **[Boost]** anyways! This **HERO MODE** option can be used once your **[Buildup]** for **FRAYMOTIF** has been satisfied, rather than waiting until three turns have passed.'),
('realityCheck', 'REALITY CHECK', 'LIFE', 'LIFE', '[Aspect][Advanced][One-Off][Locked: Life]', 'You hate to say it but… sometimes, you just need to stop sugarcoating things! Sure, it’s okay to worry about how people will take your advice, but the right thing to do is know when to be nice, and when to lay people’s faults out in a way that’s constructive, not critical. When you roll WORDPLAY to **[Strife]**, you can give the target a Reality Check; you still do damage as you lay out some seriously important life advice. The target can then make a choice; agree to follow said Reality Check, and lose all conditions that were affecting them and heal any damage they just took, or refuse, and take an additional **3 [Drag]**.'),
('rebelWithACause', 'REBEL WITH A CAUSE', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Subcultist]', 'You didn\'t get this far by abiding by THE RULES, you know. In fact, you know what? You\'re gonna say it. The rules… DROOL! PBBBTBBT (That\'s the sound of you blowing a raspberry), SMACK SMACK SMACK (That\'s the sound of you waving your ass around and smacking it), BWEHHHH (That\'s the sound of you pulling at your eyelid and sticking your tongue out, which is apparently called an akanbe). You gain a benefit depending on your subculture of choice.\r\n\r\n> **Scene**: SCREW BEING CLASSY! You don\'t want to look dignified, you wanna have FUN! You can become **[Enthusiastic]** as an action.\r\n\r\n> **Decora**: SCREW GROWING UP! You don\'t need to become grim and boring when you stop being a wriggler. You can still feel wonder! You can become **[Hopeful]** as an action.\r\n\r\n> **Lolita**: SCREW YOUR EXPECTATIONS! You aren\'t going to be some kind, loving mother to wrigglers because of your blood. You\'re reclaiming grace, and nobody can stop you. You can become **[Peaceful]** as an action.\r\n\r\n> **Cybergoth**: SCREW BLENDING IN! You don\'t care about how many heads you turn… you dress as audacious as YOU choose. You can become **[Smug]** as an action.\r\n\r\n> **Metalhead**: SCREW MASS APPEAL! You don\'t care about commercialist bullshit or doing the same as everyone else! You do what YOU like! You can become **[Enraged]** as an action. \r\n\r\n> **Punk**: SCREW THE ESTABLISHMENT! The fat fish at the top of the ladder can suck it, it\'s time to riot on the streets! You can become **[Smug]** as an action.\r\n\r\n> **Goth**: SCREW CONFORMITY! You won\'t dress like a pretty little lady, you won\'t buy all that religious shit… you\'re going to scandalise people! You can become **[Insightful]** as an action. \r\n\r\n> **Alt**: SCREW ALL THAT! YEAH! You have something you believe in! Or something you hate! Select one **[Emotion]**. You may become that as an action.'),
('rebirth', 'REBIRTH', 'OTHER', 'GRIMDARK', '[Template][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Grimdark]', 'For the first time in so, so long, a tiny flicker of emotion makes itself known in your bloodpusher. You had forgotten what it feels like. Love. \r\n\r\nIn rare cases, a Grimdark may be saved through the patience, kindness, and love of another. In such cases, the horrorterrors release their grip on their heart and sink disappointed back into the darkness from whence they came. The ex-Grimdark returns to the state they were in before, and regains the ability to feel emotions, ready to heal from their trauma in a healthy way. Upon taking this move, you lose all prior moves from this template and retain only this one, gaining back the levels you spent. This does not count as a second Ultra, allowing you a third, and no longer locks you out of other templates. You are Healed. \r\n\r\nYour time with the terrors has not left you unchanged, however. Your new appreciation for your own emotions leaves some stronger than others: **[Hopeful]**, **[Peaceful]**, and **[Dread]** all automatically become **[Inspired]**, **[Serene]**, and **[Despair]**, respectively. You\'re a little sensitive, from here on out. Additionally, when you begin a thread with the person or persons who pulled you from the darkness, you start with the **[Serenity]** emotion for free.'),
('reddestGlare', 'REDDEST GLARE', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive]', 'Your eyes are fucked. Maybe you were born with it; maybe you stared into the sun like some kinda chump. One way or another, though, you have learned to cope with your lack of sight; you’re **[Permablind]**.'),
('reddestGlear', 'REDDEST GL-EAR', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive]', 'You are deaf, Deaf, or hard of hearing. Whether you were born like this or just spent too much time around explosions, you are **[Permadeaf]**.'),
('redshirtmunition', 'REDSHIRTMUNITION', 'RUST', 'ADULT', '[Rust][Locked: Adult]\r\n', 'No one likes being shot full of bullets… but as the lowbie, you’ve automatically drawn the shortest straw, so off you go, champ! You were never lucky enough to be recognized for any skill that let you rise beyond cannon-fodder, and as such will live the rest of your (likely short) life on the front lines of a war that will not remotely benefit you for the empire to win. Pretty great, right? Because you’re so used to being thrown around and the fact you will die soon, you try to look at the bright side of things. The first time you receive a **[Negative]** emotion in an encounter, you also receive the corresponding **[Base] [Positive]** emotion. When you lose the **[Negative]** emotion that triggered this move, you also lose the **[Positive]** emotion. If someone is K.O.’ed around you, you gain 1 **[Boost]** for every ally remaining. \r\n'),
('refuseToDie', 'REFUSE TO DIE', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Reaction][Last Stand]', 'You’ve come so close to dying so often that you just kinda… don’t? Maybe it’s your underdog protagonist syndrome. Whatever the case, when you’re at 4 HP or below, roll **+GRT** as a **[Reaction]** to an opponent’s **[Strife]** roll. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: RIGHT IN THE WEAK SPOT! You’re instantly knocked out, and cannot be revived for the rest of the thread without use of a Swanky healing item.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You take the hit, and if it knocks you out, it knocks you out. \r\n\r\n**OK**: You take the blow, but you’re able to tough it out, if even only a little. You gain **1 [Resistance]** for the incoming attack. \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: WEAK! You remain standing and conscious, with **1 [Resistance]** to the incoming attack, leaving you at 1 HP at the very least. You become **[Tired]**. This can stack into **[Exhausted]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: The same as a good roll, but something about the way the hit lands hurts the opponent, doing **1 damage** of the same type back to them! You become **[Tired]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Oh, jeez. That’s kinda freaky. You take no damage from the incoming attack, and your refusal to die surprises them. All foes who see this take **1 [Drag]**. The person who damaged you takes **2 damage** of the same type as you grab at em! Eurgh!'),
('reinforcedWillpower', 'REINFORCED WILLPOWER', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Passive]', 'Wow. Your mind is all but impossible to fuck around with, huh? This MUST be a symptom of your perfect blood, and not an effect of Violet Wriggler Schoolfeeding forcing psionic pressure onto kids with tech-helmets designed to stress test them from a young age to perpetuate the hemoist myth of \"Violets are inherently stronger\"! **[Control]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**.'),
('relentless', 'RELENTLESS', 'TIME', 'TIME', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Time]', 'They can’t stop what’s coming! You never give up, no matter what! Whenever you take **[Drag]** from or are **[Stunned]** by an opponent’s effect, you gain **1 [WHAM]**. If you are **[Slowed]** by an opponent’s effect, you gain an additional point of **[WHAM]** at the start of every turn you are **[Slowed]**. You cannot gain more than **2 [WHAM]** from this move in **1 round**.'),
('relicWeaponUnlocked', 'RELIC WEAPON UNLOCKED', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Passive]', 'Whew… it took a LOT of sifting through crafting recipes… but you did it! You unlocked a RELIC WEAPON. Alchemized through the power of friendship and obsolete code from SBURB, you’ve created a weapon of legend that never existed or had even been heard of until this exact moment. Name your RELIC WEAPON something stupid and pretentious, and describe its design. It does **2 [Energy]** types, including the option of **[Holy]**, and either does **[Somatic]** or **[Psychic]** damage, and can have one other ABSTRATA UPGRADE of your choosing, though if it’s an **[Energy]** one, you don’t get an extra **[Energy]** type, just the extra effect it gives you, such as an extra ability on a **MAX**.'),
('remarkableReflexes', 'REMARKABLE REFLEXES', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Open][Free][Reaction][Physical]', 'Whoa! A regular troll wouldn\'t be able to pull off a quadruple backflip like THAT, huh? Rather than suppress the natural instincts instilled by your lusus to fit in, you have learned to use them to your advantage! When you take a physical condition from an enemy effect, roll **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Urgh! You made things SO MUCH WORSE for yourself! Not so remarkable now… you take **5 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: It\'s still… bad. Pretty bad, yeah. No sugarcoating this. You take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Seriously, this is a risky move. You need to be sure you can do it. You take **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Alright! You avoid the bulk of the problem… for now! You don\'t gain the incoming **[Condition]**, and instead take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: WHOA! Jeeez, so fast! You get a **GOOD**, but no **[Drag]**!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: SUPER FAST REVERSAL GOOOO! You get a **GREAT**… but the opponent gains the **[Condition]** instead!!');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('rememberThePolarBears', 'REMEMBER THE POLAR BEARS', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][One-Off][Reaction][Heal][Mental]', 'YOU CAN’T DIE HERE. YOU’RE ONE OF THE ONLY PEOPLE ON THIS PLANET WHO KNOWS ABOUT POLAR BEARS, DUDE. There’s nobody who knows meemaw’s blueberry pie recipe on Alternia except for you! If you get smoked by some big mean murder robot… who’s gonna be around to think about Mythbusters?! You may roll this move for **[Free]** the first time you hit **4 HP** or lower in a **[Strife]** encounter. When you want to fight on for the sake of planet Earth, roll **+GRT**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: HRK-! You fall over, **[Unconscious]**, you giant fucking weenie.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You… aren’t really… doing that hot, dude… you take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Still pushing yourself a little hard. You take **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Yeah… the polar bears… you can’t give up here! You **[Heal]** **1 HP**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Ngh… RAAAARGH! YOU REMEMBER THE POLAR BEARS! AND YOU WON’T GO DOWN HERE! You **[Heal]** **1 HP** and become **[Brave]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: YOOOOOOU! YOU ARE AN AVATAR OF THE POLAR BEARS! YOU REMEMBER THE MYTHBUSTERS, AND MEEMAW’S BLUEBERRY PIIIIIE! Goddamn, dude. You **[Heal]** **1 HP** and become **[Heroic]**!'),
('remoteRewiring', 'REMOTE REWIRING', 'OTHER', 'ROBOT', '[Template][Advanced][One-Off][Control][Tech][Locked: Robot]', 'Your robot ability doesn’t end with simple palmhusks or drive thru electronic menus. No. You’re capable of so much more. Your leet skillz have allowed you to move up to the big guns. Literally, sometimes. You can now hack into other actual robots. When you want to take control of someone else’s robot butler, roll **+PSP**.\n\n**MIN**: Wow, these firewalls are ass. Psh. Easy peas…y…? Oh no. Why can’t you move? What the fuck. Did you hack into yourself?? You did, you moron. You gain **1 [Somatic]** **[Weakness]**, leaving yourself wide open to attack! You are also **[Slowed]** for **2 rounds** as you try to get yourself back to full power.\n\n**BAD**: Your internal computer goes into overdrive trying to crack the password and… Nothing. Nice try.\n\n**OK**: Hhhhrrnnggg. Whiirrrrrr. Your fans are going crazy, but you’re so close! This move instead goes on **[Recharge: 2]**, as you wait to try again!\n\n**GOOD**: You can see their code. You can grab it, and you wrangle it like a cowboy. Yeehaw, but imagine it’s in binary. You’re able to give the robot you hacked one command to do anything you’d like. The target of this has to listen to the command, even if it’s to its own detriment. \n\n**GREAT**: Wow, this thing really had no virus protection, huh? You get the effects of a **GOOD**, and deal **1 [Psychic]** damage to them as you blast through their firewalls with ease.\n\n**MAX**: You’re on some real Mr. Robot type shit, huh? Who knew hacking into the billboards across town would allow you to pull this type of stunt. Your target takes **1 [Psychic]** damage. You gain some sort of permanent hold over the target. For the duration of the encounter, you can use one of your actions to instead make your target do something for you. This does not use the target’s action, but it does use yours.'),
('repeatExam', 'REPEAT EXAM', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Passive][Locked: Student]', 'Ugh. Sometimes, you do less than perfect as a result. But as you have been told many times, no matter what Studyheart Academy you attend… never settle for anything BUT perfect! When you get an **OK** or lower on a **[One-Off]** move, you may attempt it a second time later, as if it didn\'t have the **[One-Off]** tag. You may only do this for an individual move once.'),
('reproductician', 'REPRODUCTICIAN', 'BRONZE', 'ADULT', '[Bronze][Locked: Adult]', 'Life out on the range can\\\'t be replicated by hydroponics labs and artificial greenhives, but at least it\\\'s like 20% safer without having to worry about bandit attacks. Most of the time, anyways. Regardless, many consider this to be one of the luckier jobs if you aren\\\'t gung-ho about glory and fighting and all that considering you just wake up and feed the empire. You make sure that the freshest and most high-quality of foods get sent off to be used in the grand highblood feasts while preventing everything else from getting too rotten so it can be turned into rations. Whenever you are in an encounter, **GUTSUCKERY** for you and your allies is on a **[Recharge: 2]** rather than a **[One-Off]** as you pass out free snacks. Succeeding on a **GUTSUCKERY** roll also gives extra **[Boost]** (1/2/3 for a **GOOD**/**GREAT**/**MAX** respectively). You and your allies can also **[Tier Up]** their next **GUTSUCKERY** roll and gain either +1 **HP** to all results or cause the healing to ignore **[Bloodied]** in exchange for upping the timer to a **[Recharge: 4]**.'),
('researcheraser', 'RESEARCHERASER', 'TEAL', 'ADULT', '[Teal][Recharge: 3][Locked: Adult]', 'An empire cannot survive on brute strength alone. No, a key part of conquering is to understand what makes the opponent tick, and using that against them. Which is where you come in. All those sweeps of education and research have brought you here, where you can strike fear into the enemy through science and systems beyond their control… but not yours. Whenever you get a **GREAT** or **MAX** on a **+PSP** roll against an enemy, you can choose to apply 1 **[Weakness]** of any type as you pinpoint their flaws. This **[Weakness]** lasts 2 rounds. Whenever you get a **GREAT** or **MAX** on a **+PSP** roll against an ally, you do the opposite. Your ally gains +1 **[Resistance]** of any type as you share your analysis of how to cover their flaws and only show the best version of themselves they can be. This **[Resistance]** only lasts 2 rounds.'),
('respectfulNod', 'RESPECTFUL NOD', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Open][One-Off]', 'You\'ve spent your life being told that you\'re greater than anyone else. But in the words of the great scholars of old, real recognise real. When another troll suitably impresses you, whether through doing well in combat or showing off their own talents and skills, you are willing to acknowledge a worthy opponent. But don’t mistake that as giving up! With a nod and some reaffirming words, you can take an action to give both yourself and the opponent **2 [Boost]** and the **[Proud]** condition. You can only use this on an opponent, not an ally. Now, let’s see who truly is the better combatant!'),
('resplendentRascality', 'RESPLENDENT RASCALITY', 'OTHER', 'HEROMODE', '', 'Your wit, charm and timing leave you as one of the most amicable people around. Whether you are a trickster, a survivor or a madcap, none can deny that luck seems to always be on your side when you need it most. When you enter **HERO MODE**, you may choose one of the following benefits.\r\n\r\n> **SCHAUDENFREUDE**:  Nothing is funnier than opponents screwing up their own actions! You retroactively give the target a **MIN** on a roll they rolled last turn.\r\n\r\n> **CONVOLUTED PRANK**: Your japes are far more complex than you might think! On a successful **SHENANIGANS** roll, you may choose two effects rather than one.\r\n\r\n> **UNCANNY LUCK**: Don\'t like that roll you just did? Don\'t worry about it! As a **[Reaction]**, you may reroll your move once, and **[Tier Up]** the final result.\r\n\r\n> **INSANELY FUNNY**: Whether you\'re intentionally funny, or your serious attitude makes funny things even funnier, you can sometimes say something that breaks the wits of your targets. Your opponent starts **[Laughing]** and **[Crying]** at the same time.\r\n\r\n> **STAIRS**: YOU WARNED THEM DOG! Unbeknownst to your opponent, they happen to be standing by a flight of stairs that will almost surely break their asses. Successfully making the target **[Floorbound]** will shoot them flying down the stairs, stopping them from rolling any **[Physical]** moves, doing 2 **[Somatic]** damage and 1 more each turn they don\'t get up (requiring a **GOOD** or higher **ACT FAST** roll) and leaving them [Embarrassed] at the end. You also can\'t roll any **[Physical]** moves against them, because they\'re falling down a flight of stairs, but your **WORDPLAY** rolls to **BANTER** are **[Tiered Up]** as long as they\'re falling as you remind them you warned them. :y'),
('retcon', 'RETCON', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][One-Off][Magic]', 'Oh GOD, you messed up! Oh, this is terrible! Something really, really bad has happened! Luck did not go your way, and everything has gone to hell. If only you could just go back and try again— oh wait! You can! With a wave of the hand, you tell the narrative that THAT shit didn’t happen. You rewind the encounter back by **2 rounds**, causing everyone to forget what they saw, know or did. Woooo!\r\n\r\n\r\n'),
('returnToBug', 'RETURN TO BUG', 'OTHER', 'WYLDERDRUID', '[Template][Magic][Unlock: Wylderdruid]', 'You are a Wylderdruid, a magic user who draws power from the primal forces of nature governing the plants and animals of Alternia. You’ve learned to tap into the wellspring of power inherent to every beast and branch inhabiting the planet… but in true Alternian fashion, you have to earn respect from the wilds before you can use it. When you defeat a level 1 LUSUS or PLANT MONSTER without killing it, you earn its respect and can create a **WYLDERPACT** with it. This pact grants you some of its beastly traits, manifesting as spectral features resembling the creature you made a pact with. A **WYLDERPACT** gives you access to one move or **[Passive]** ability that the monster has- these abilities have the **[Magic]** tag. You cannot have more than three active **WYLDERPACTS** in a strife, and the pacts are consumed after being used in two strifes. The noble honkbeast grants you its power - use it wisely!\r\n'),
('returnWithElixir', 'RETURN WITH ELIXIR', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Ultra][Passive][Magic][Locked: Protagonist]', 'You\'re at your strongest at the end of your journey, having bested trials, survived tribulations and come back changed. But does your journey ever truly end? What is the end of an adventure if not the prologue of another? The tale never ends; it just builds to a new chapter, and you\'ll have learned from the last. You gain access to HERO MODE through your GLORIOUS GRACE. When you defeat an opponent, the fight changes you as their story lives on with you; when you help defeat an enemy, you select any one move  from their sheet and temporarily add it to yours. This can be a **[Locked]**, **[Advanced]** or **[Psionic]** move, but it cannot be an **[Ultra]**.  You can only access **[Advanced]** **[Class]** moves at Level 18, the normal access level. You keep this move until you defeat another troll, whereupon you gain a new move from this character. You cannot regain the same move more than once until you\'ve taken 12 other moves first. Get it? Like, the 12 steps of the hero\'s journey, the 12 castes… yeah. That\'s what we in the business call thematic imagery. When you first gain this move, you can access any one Lime move or any one move from an ally you\'ve assigned an archetype with ARCHETYPIST. Finally, you can choose to instead gain an item from an opponent you\'ve bested; a paradox copy of the Legendary Ahab\'s Crosshair, just for you! Any items or moves you use in this way have the **[Magic]** tag as you summon the narrative power of the self to aid you in your adventure.'),
('reveeeeenge', 'REVEEEEENGE!!', 'OTHER', 'THIEF', '[Class][Basic][Free][One-Off][Locked: Thief]', 'Did they… hit you?! Excuse you? No, no! Go to hell! How DARE you! Do they even know who you are? Fuck this, you\'re going to fight past your wounds and GET YOUR REVENGE!!! When someone deals **[Somatic]** damage to you, you can choose to gain **1 [WHAM]** and delay the damage you received for **2 turns** so you can deal your vengeance. Once those **2 turns** are up, you take the damage as you finally feel the effects of your wounds and take **3 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n'),
('reverseJunkineering', 'REVERSE JUNKINEERING', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Junker]', 'Who needs a budget? With the genius you\'re showing, you can build half the shit highbloods make, but for half the price! Of course, it\'s a lil shoddy at times, but hey, who cares if it\'s pretty so long as it works? You can craft items up to the **Well-Off** Wealth level with MAD MECHANIST. These items do not trigger BIG BUYS for you. You can still only make mechanical items, not organic ones.'),
('rideOfTheHippocampi', 'RIDE OF THE HIPPOCAMPI', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Admiral]', 'What\'s that on the horizon? It\'s you! In an extremely decked-out war machine! Your bombs cost more than the hives you\'re gonna destroy, and it\'s almost sickening how much of an advantage you\'ve got! YAAAAAHOO! You gain a VEHICLE, with **5 LUX** worth of upgrades. Your VEHICULATE rolls use **+GRA**. You gain access to the following VEHICLE UPGRADES, which can be applied to any vehicle. \r\n\r\n**FORGED FOR WAR (1 LUX)**: Flying vehicles and seabound vehicles are a staple for you! You can purchase the FLYING or WATER upgrades for **1 LUX**.\r\n\r\n**EVERYTHING PROOF (2 LUX)**: While inside this vehicle, you are immune to all HAZARDS.\r\n\r\n**WEAPONIZED (3 LUX)**: BOMBS! MISSILES! CANNONS! YAHAHAHAHA! You can roll any **[Physical]** **[Strife]** roll you have with this vehicle, and it automatically has the RANGEDKIND ABSTRATA UPGRADE, allowing it to hit targets within 2 VROOMs. You can add up to 2 other ABSTRATA UPGRADES with enough **LUX**.'),
('righteousFury', 'RIGHTEOUS FURY', 'RAGE', 'RAGE', '[Aspect][Ultra][Buildup: 6][Lengthy][One-Off][Strife][Locked: Rage]', 'You’ve learned to accept your anger and control it. You understand now that while wanton destruction and fury for the sake of fury is bad, constructive anger is actually really beneficial; you use it to push your causes forward, not just destroy other people’s progress. Your fury is a tool, and it’s one you can use to build with instead of destroying with. You are permanently under the effects of being **[Enraged]**, except you do not gain the downsides of being **[Enraged]** or **[Out Of Control]**, only the benefits; you only show signs of external anger when you choose to. Your anger is a part of you, one you can coexist with now- being **[Enraged]** or **[Out Of Control]** doesn\'t cancel out being **[Focused]** or **[Hyperfocused]**.  If you gain any other **[Emotion]**, you can shrug it off after 3 of your turns and return to your passionate state of revolutionary determination. Once per encounter, you can use a **[Lengthy]** action to let out a bellowing roar that shakes the foundations of buildings and creaks the roots of trees. Roll **+GRT**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You roar and scream, and your self-control slips. You become **[Out Of Control]**, with only the downsides, and you also gain **2 [Drag]** from exerting yourself.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Your howl of fury simply strains your own voice, causing you frustration. You gain **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Your roar fails to uproot opponents, but it does intimidate them; they gain **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: The force of your roar knocks the targets back and causes them stress; they take **1 [Somatic]** damage and **2 [Drag]**. Allies gain 1 **[Boost]** as your impressive display inspires them!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Your screams blast the targets from where they stand, terrifying them! You deal **2 [Somatic]** damage and either **3 [Drag]** or the **[Scared]** condition, you choose. Allies gain either **2 [Boost]** or the **[Hopeful]** condition.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Your voice seems to rip through reality; dark clouds swirl, and your targets see visions of their sins blasting through their minds. They take **3 [Somatic]** damage and either **4 [Drag]** or the **[Terrified]** condition, you choose. Allies gain either **3 [Boost]** or the **[Inspired]** condition as they see visions of a brighter tomorrow unfurling.'),
('rightHandTroll', 'RIGHT HAND TROLL', 'OTHER', 'SERVICESQUIRE', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Servicesquire]', 'At your service, boss. You’re the reliable attendant of a troll with far greater power than you. Whether you’re a lowly rust sadly sweeping up the mess after your clown boss threw a hell of a party, or that same clown working for a much stronger violet prince sweeps later, you take care of someone else, and that’s really it. You can select a troll you know of any higher caste to serve as your BOSS. Your BOSS gives you various benefits as you progress the Servicesquire **[Template]**. You practice your butlery business around them, tending to their needs and learning to do the tasks they normally do. You can change your **[Talent]** to be the same as your Boss’ **[Talent]**. You can also combine sylladexes with them, meaning you have an extended amount of **VP** at your disposal, and can temporarily borrow items from their **VP** sylladex or vice-versa, even when you’re not in an encounter together. Your starting wealth is increased by 1 stage. You can change your boss and your **[Talent]** with a day of **[Downtime]**. If you do not have a Boss, you are in LOOKING FOR WORK mode; you become **Destitute**, but your **[Manipulate]** rolls are **[Talented]**. Please, shawty, hire me!'),
('rightToRepair', 'RIGHT TO REPAIR', 'OTHER', 'BLIGHTSMITH', '[Template][Advanced][Downtime][Locked: Blightsmith]', 'Sometimes, trolls don’t want a new weapon. They just want a fancy upgrade on their current weapon. When rolling **SOME ASSEMBLY REQUIRED**, instead of making a new weapon you can choose to add a second Abstrata to an already created one on a **GREAT** or higher. On a **GREAT**, you randomly select the Abstrata. On a **MAX**, you get to choose. It costs 2 **LUX** to do this, and these abstrata go away after three encounters as wear and tear eventually destroys your work.\r\nYou can also use this downtime to repair weapons you have made with **SOME ASSEMBLY REQUIRED**. It costs 1 **LUX** to increase the duration by 2 encounters. You can only extend it to 4 encounters, as nothing is forever!'),
('ringmajorGeneral', 'RINGMAJOR GENERAL', 'PURPLE', 'ADULT', '[Purple][Locked: Adult]', 'As it so happens, this IS your circus and these ARE your clowns! You may have led a personal troupe, conducted many services at your local clurch, or were the Don of an entire Mafia back on Alternia. Perhaps you were just friends with a lot of trolls, siblings and non-clowns alike. Regardless, because of your blessed blood and leadership qualities, you\'ve been given the role of Ringmajor General and an entire station or ship to control and order around as you please. Every circus needs a Ringmajor and by the Messiahs, the show must go on. You gain access to the following items which you can give to your allies as an action. They still take up your **VP**, but your allies can use them as they please. You can spend an action to order an ally to use a given item, with additional effect.\r\n\r\n> **GUFFAWING GAS (4 VP)**: OHHH THAT SLAPS YOU ON THE KNEE! Activating this canister of purple chemical causes both user and target of the user to start **[Laughing]** while also inflicting **[Confused]**, both lasting 3 rounds. If ordered to use this, the user is not **[Godawful]** or **[Inept]** at any rolls via **[Laughing]**.\r\n\r\n> **HOKUS POKER (3 VP)**: Hokus pokus joker POKE! This golden pointing stick is painted purple and topped with a pointing clown glove. Using this against a target renders them **[Blind]** and **[Clumsy]** for 2 rounds as you BOP their eyes. If ordered to use this, the user gains 1 **[WHAM]** against that target.\r\n\r\n> **FIREWORKS!!! (3 VP)**: HAPPY WRIGGLING DAY BITCH! Activating these causes the user and target to be set **[Ablaze]**! If ordered to use it, the user is **[Quickened]**.'),
('rip', 'RIP', 'OTHER', 'PRINCE', '[Class][Basic][Unblockable][One-off][Locked: Prince]', 'When a prince wants to destroy something, it\'s going to be destroyed. Once per encounter, you hit them, and there\'s nothing they can do about it. A single **[Strife]** of your choice gains the **[Unblockable]** tag for that round. This intent must be stated before the **[Strife]**’s roll is made.\n\n'),
('ripAndTear', 'RIP AND TEAR', 'OTHER', 'BEAST_BRAWLER', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Craft][Locked: Beast Brawler]\r\n', 'Carnage! Smash! Blam! KILLING BLOW! GLORY KIIIIIILL! STAND ATOP A MOUNTAIN OF THE CORPSES OF MONSTERS AND ROAR! You absolutely MANGLE monstrous foes as they come at you in relentless hordes. You are prepared. You are, you have been told, the only thing they fear. Whenever you hunt down a creature, you gain a material of some sort! Like a loot drop! The type of material you gain changes depending on the creature you’ve hunted. These are consumable resources that you can enhance items with as a **[Downtime]** activity. You can only enhance any one item with one material, though, or it loses its efficacy. There’s only so many cholerbear claws you can grind into your health smoothie before it just becomes gross. \r\n\r\n\r\n> **MONSTER MATERIAL (gained from Lusii)**: Aha! Essence of crockageckor or perhaps fairybull wings. You can enhance your **[Consumable]** items with this material to basically turn them into an insane protein drink. When you use this item, you gain **1 [Somatic]** **[Resistance]** for **2 turns** as your skin toughens into armor. \r\n\r\n\r\n> **STRANGE MATERIAL (gained from Entities)**: This is some freaky shit -you bottled up the cursed essence of an entity monster! The dark magicks fuming from your Peer eyeball goop or whatnot allow you to manipulate the darkest magick of all- capitalism. You can enhance any ACTIVE item with this material, refunding half the **VP**, rounded up, from what you spent on it. However, the item is.. changed. Whenever you use this item you become **[Scared]**, even if you normally wouldn’t as your item is now quite literally alive and haunted. \r\n\r\n\r\n> **FLORAL MATERIAL (gained from Plant Monsters)**: Congrats, a horticullturist somewhere is crying! You tore apart a young plant monster and can now wear its remains to pretend to be a bush. You can enhance your **[Fashion]** items with this material, becoming **[Hidden]** at the start of every encounter to all lusii monsters. This disguise doesn’t work on trolls except for transformed Moonbarks for some reason.\r\n\r\n'),
('ripslagRim', 'RIPSLAG RIM', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Pilot]', 'Hey, boss! You said there was an apocalypse coming, right? Well, change of plans: it\'s CANCELLED. Says who? Uh, ME. Duh. You are the single most badass bitch on Alternia. Just… the image of you wading out from the sea in your cool mecha. Fuck, dude. You gain access to HERO MODE through your HARDCORE HUBRIS, and gain a second use of HERO MODE automatically after **two turns** when you gain the first. On top of that, you are the only thing in this world remotely capable of taking on the monsters at our door. You do **+1 damage** on all **[Strife]** rolls against Level 3+ monsters. You also gain **1 [Resistance]** to their damage if they are at least Level 4 monsters, and ignore any **[Unblockable]** damage they do. If you deem monsters of level 3+ are too dangerous to go easy on, you may spend a **[Free]** action to shift into **NUCLEAR ANALOG**. You increase your mecha\'s **HP** by 5, do an extra 2 damage on all your **[Strife]** rolls against the fuckers, and **[Tier Up]** your **[Strife]** rolls against them. Go big, or go extinct, baby. When your Mecha is destroyed, you do 10 damage to the monster and yourself, risking a **Heroic Death**. Watch out! These effects can apply to **NPC** monsters as well, as long as they are flavored to have a giant robot or creature for you to fight. Where\'s the thrill in picking on meaningless ants?'),
('risktakingBehaviour', 'RISK-TAKING BEHAVIOUR', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'You don\'t know why, but you constantly do things that could seriously hurt you in exchange for immediate gratification. Maybe you seek to punish yourself, but are too proud to admit you\'ve done anything wrong. Maybe you\'re just stupid. Either way, you gain the following **GOOD** SWASHBUCKLE effects.\r\n\r\n> **SCUTTLESURF**: You stand up inside a vehicle, like a total dickshit! Are you driving it with your feet as you stand in the seat?! You can roll moves other than SWASHBUCKLE or LET’S STRIFE while inside a VEHICLE for 2 turns.\r\n\r\n> **RIDICULOUS RISK**: Whelp, what’s the worst that could happen? Roll 1d8 instead of the normal dice for your next move; on an Odd result, your roll **[Tiers Down]** twice. On an even, your roll **[Tiers Up]** twice.\r\n\r\n> **SELF-DESTRUCTIVE SHOWOFF**: NO, ENPECE, DON’T DO A QUADRUPLE BACKFLIP IN THE MIDDLE OF A FREEWAY! You do something really flashy and really, really stupid. Your next move is **[Tiered Down]**; if you still get a **GOOD**+, you become **[Smug]** and all enemies take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> **“NOBLE” SACRIFICE**: This is it… you’re giving up everything for this! You DEFINITELY aren’t seeking martyrdom for pity and awe. This is an alternate version of FINISHING BLOW and as such is a **GREAT** result. When you deal damage with the **[WHAM]** from this move, you take the damage right back. If you survive, you can still make **[Strife]** moves afterwards, but you are **[Bloodied]**. In a TEAM STRIFE, rather than doing damage to yourself (and therefore your team!), you become **[Unconscious]** for 2 turns. In exchange, all allies gain 3 **[Boost]**.'),
('roaaaar', 'ROAAAAR!', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Open][One-Off][Manipulate]\r\n', 'You’ve got a beast inside of you, and you’re not afraid to let it come out and play sometimes! You’re tired of always hiding it, and you won’t play pussycat any more! When you wanna let out a primal roar, roll **+GRT**.\r\n\r\nMIN: roar. What was that! Fuck!! You sound completely powerless! You berate yourself loudly and get **[Humiliated]**. GG.\r\n\r\nBAD: Agh, pleh pleh… your throat! It hurts! And now everyone’s laughing at you… you’re **[Embarrassed]**.\r\n\r\nOK: RAW- ahem, ROOOAAAR! Reroll this move for **[Free]**.\r\n\r\nGOOD: ROAR! You let out some primal frustration, freaking people out and letting off some steam. All opponents are **[Scared]** for **2 turns**, and you gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\nGREAT: Whoa! That’s actually mad impressive! You REALLY roared, huh? You **[Scare]** all opponents for **3 turns**, and you gain **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\nMAX: ROOOOOAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAR! AAAAAAAAAA! SCARY! You’re a beast, a monster! You **[Terrify]** all opponents for **2 turns**, and keep them **[Scared]** for another 3, and you gain **3 [Boost]**.\r\n'),
('rollFudging', 'ROLL FUDGING', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][Passive][Magic][Psionic][Locked: Metagamer]', 'Your psionics start to manifest in the world beyond the Fourth Wall, eroding even the metaknowledge that players share with one another. You can choose to make all your rolls in private, out of sight of others. Additionally, you can choose to fucking lie about your results. Every time you lie about your results, choose the result yourself, and mark down that you lied. Your opponents are allowed to, as a **[Free]** action at the end of any roll you make, call bullshit and demand to know if your result was legit. If it wasn\'t, your opponent gets a number of **[WHAM]** equal to the amount of times you\'ve lied since the encounter started, or your last lie if you\'ve done this more than once. If it was, they take **2 [Drag]**. Use this bluffing game to your advantage! MAKE SURE OTHER PLAYERS ARE AWARE OF THIS MOVE IT YOU INTEND ON USING IT.'),
('rollUpRollUp', 'ROLL UP, ROLL UP!', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Passive][Unlock: Circusfolk]\r\n', 'Come one, come all, and see the Greatest Show on all of Alternia! SEE the Big Top as it stands proudly in the center of the city, deep within the carnival district of clowns! HEAR the calliope music swell as the everlasting performance swishes in the 52nd act of the evening! WATCH the performers do the unthinkable, the impossible, the incredible! You are one of them, and you\'re on stage next! But pray tell— what\'s your act? Choose a trick from the list below, and gain the associated **[Talent]** and effects!\r\n\r\n> **COMEDIAN (+RAS)**: Jokes!! Personally, you love them. Your distracting tomfoolery can turn the tides on others; when someone gains an **[Emotion]**, you can interpose and instead give them **[Giggling]** (or **[Laughing]** if it\'s a **[Heightened]** emotion) as a **[Reaction]**.\r\n\r\n> **ANIMAL TAMER (+PLC)**: You have tamed the savage beast, and now you\'re besties! You gain access to the Bronze Summoner XENODRUID move, except it does not have the **[Psionic]** tag, uses **+PLC** and can only summon your TAMED LUSUS, a single specific monster (Bird, Bug, etc) that you choose and name at creation. On a GREAT, you get **2 [Boost]**, and on a MAX you get **4 [Boost]**. You can replace your TAMED LUSUS with a day of DOWNTIME.\r\n\r\n> **ACROBAT (+GRA)**: Trapezes, tightropes, trollic pyramids… your nimbleness is second to none! Honestly it\'s… kind of frightening how flexible you are..! You can enter NIMBLE MODE as an action as you flash step, dodge or contort yourself out of harm\'s way. In NIMBLE MODE, all **[Physical]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**, but so are all of your **[Physical]** rolls aside from LET\'S STRIFE. You take **1 [Drag]** every turn. You can end NIMBLE MODE as an action.\r\n\r\n> **CARNY (+APP)**: Come chance your luck! You run games, stands and scams that drain people\'s wallets real good! You may ask someone to compete on a **+APP** roll with you to play your game; whoever rolls higher wins **Treasure II**, and the loser drops a Wealth Level. You have a **+2 [Buff]** to this roll. Ssssh!\r\n\r\n> **STRONGMAN (+GRT)**: OHHH, YEAH!! You are MIGHTY! You are STRONG! You can bend iron bars into PRETZELS! On a **GREAT [Strife]** roll, you can do **1 damage** and knock the target **[Floorbound]** instead of the regular move effects.\r\n\r\n> **DAREDEVIL (+HUB)**: Whether it\'s vehicular stunts, fire-eating or some other death-defying skill, you awe the crowd with your brushes with death! Every time you take **2 or more damage** at a time, you gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **RINGLEADER (+PSP)**: AND OUR NEXT ACT TAKES THE STAGE! You are a manager of lesser clowns, knowing how to command the battlefield with ease. You may use **+PSP** to roll an ally\'s move for them as you announce and narrate their actions, making them do so; for example, rolling a Nyanarchist\'s VENATICS with **+PSP** has them use it with your roll result. This does not cost them an action, only you. You still can\'t use multiple moves with the same tag, like **[Strife]** or **[Chicanery]** on your turn. Doing this costs **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **MAGICIAN (+IMG)**: You are a master of misdirection, of illusion, of smoke and mirrors. That image they just saw of you fucking up? IT WAS AN ILLUSION! YOU\'RE IN FACT OVER HERE, FOOL! On **[Recharge: 3]**, you can use an action to retroactively **[Tier Up]** your last roll, revealing a series of elaborate tricks that deceived those who witnessed it!\r\n'),
('rootLegends', 'ROOT LEGENDS', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Folklorist]', 'What are UFO tales if not encounters with the fey for the modern era? What religion isn\'t impacted by the stories of its layfolk? Did ghosts invent Christmas (EVIDENCE: A CHRISTMAS CAROL)? In your studies, you\'ve linked together other areas of folklore that enhance the credibility of your original field. Choose an additional area of expertise from YARNCHASER and link it to your first option; for example, you might take Foodways & Cuisine to heighten your study of  The True Meaning of the Holidays by studying seasonal meals, or you might take Proverbs & Language to translate ancient tales of Faeries & Magic. You only get the effects from YARNCHASER, nowhere else.'),
('roughRoundTheEdges', 'ROUGH ROUND THE EDGES', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Passive][Locked: Gutterblood]', 'You\'ve got a kind of shabby appearance and a personality that certain, more established trolls might find… unusual! All opponents **[Manipulate]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**, cuz… how do you even deal with a troll like you..?'),
('routine', 'ROUTINE', 'DERSE', 'DERSE', '[Sway][Passive][Locked: Derse]', 'You like having a pre-decided routine for how you spend your wipes. You jot ‘em into a planner and choose the time, the place, the outfit you’ll wear, the people you’ll see, the joke you’ll make at EXACTLY this time… okay, maybe not THAT in detail, but yes, you like to have a routine planned out. At the start of the week, you can plan this week out; choose at least **3 days**. On each day, assign a **[Downtime]** activity that you will do on that day. So long as you stick to your routine and don’t miss a day or do something else instead, all rolls you make on those **[Downtime]** activities **[Tier Up]**. Abandoning your routine **[Tiers Down]** these moves instead.'),
('rovingTroublemaker', 'ROVING TROUBLEMAKER', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Passive][Locked: Vagabond]', 'You\'re infamous for your ways throughout the lands you walk. Don\'t talk to that guy— he\'s bad news! You have to admit, this reputation is pretty awesome to have. The roll you need to make to get a **MAX** with your **+RAS** rolls is 18+, not 20+. Whenever you get a **MAX** **+RAS** roll, you also gain **1 [WHAM]** on top of normal effects.'),
('rrrrrrival', 'RRRRRRIVAL', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Passive]', 'You\'ve done it all. You\'ve wrestled with sea monsters. You\'ve bought and blown up mountains. But now… everything feels so… boring. EXCEPT… that one special someone. They might be your kismesis, they might be your actual foe, it doesn\'t matter. The fact is that you have uncovered a true blue RIVAL, someone worth besting and overcoming. Select another troll, and declare them your rival. If they accept, they gain this move for free. While in an encounter with your rival, you get **1 RIVALRY POINT**, or RP, every time you roll higher on average than them in a turn. You can use RIVALRY POINTS in the following ways as an action…\r\n\r\n**SNICKER (1 RP)**: Pffft. Your Rival gets **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**SMUG SMILE (2 RP)**: Keh! Did you see that? You get a **+2 [Buff]** to your last roll this turn retroactively.\r\n\r\n**HURRY (2 RP)**: C\'mon, you don\'t have all day. You\'ve got a bitch to show up! Reduce the active **[Recharge]** or **[Buildup]** of a move by 2.\r\n\r\n**KEEP FIGHTING (3 RP)**: Ngh… like you\'d go down so easy? You roll GUTSUCKERY, even if you\'ve already rolled it. \r\n\r\n**MOCK (3 RP)**: Ohohoho! How PATHETIC. Your rival\'s last move is retroactively **[Tiered Down]**.\r\n\r\n**MAKE IT COUNT (4 RP)**: It\'s all been leading up to this! Your next roll is **[Tiered Up]**, even to a **MAX**.'),
('rude', 'RUDE!', 'BLOOD', 'BLOOD', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Blood]', 'Hey, shit-idiot, shut the fuck up! Are you gonna do what you’re meant to do, or are you gonna keep standing there like a quivering barfgulcher and shit your pants some more, huh?! You’re kind of a jerk when it comes to your words, sometimes. You can use WORDPLAY to **[Strife]** even after a punch is thrown. If you already had a move that let you do this, you receive a **+2 [Buff]** to all WORDPLAY rolls.'),
('ruffiannihilator', 'RUFFIANNIHILATOR', 'BRONZE', 'ADULT', '[Bronze][Locked: Adult]\r\n', 'Though typically a lower position in a squad, many rough and tumble trolls willingly join the Ruffiannihilator Corps. As a Ruffiannihilator, your job is simple: CRUSH EVERYTHING WITH YOUR DAMN BARE HANDS. You and your fellow Ruffians charge forth in a wave of fury, stopping only when there\'s nothing left to trample. As an action with a **[Recharge: 5]**, you can get **ROUGH N\' TUMBLE**. When you do this, you are **[Talented]** to all **+GRT** or **+HUB** rolls for 3 rounds. If you have a **[Talent]** in one stat but not the other, you must choose the other stat. Whenever you take damage, you gain **[Boost]** equal to the amount of damage taken. However, for these 3 rounds, you also have 1 **[Weakness]** to all **[Somatic]** damage, which overrides any **[Resistance]** you have. During this time you also render a target **[Scared]** whenever you roll a **MAX** on a **[Strife]** roll. If they would be immune, they are **[Scared]** for only a single round before they gather themself.\r\n'),
('runTheCalculations', 'RUN THE CALCULATIONS', 'MIND', 'MIND', '[Aspect][Basic][Locked: Mind]', 'You sometimes take a while to figure out the best path forward. Some might chalk it up to indecisiveness, but really, you just need to be totally sure this is the smartest choice for you to make. You can spend a whole turn doing nothing, trying to rule out all choices in a decision you’re about to make; on your next turn, all moves you make are **[Tiered Up]**. This stacks with other **[Tier Up]** effects, and can push **GREAT** rolls into **MAX**.'),
('sacredDuty', 'SACRED DUTY', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Passive][Locked: Cloistered]', 'The Cloistered Caverndorms of the Undercaverns present an unusual microcosm of Jade Society. Due to the limited number of Cloistered Trolls present, everyone has a job… whether they accept it or not! You may take one of the other Jade Trees as a **[Template]**, gaining the **[Entry]** now. You do not gain the **[Talent]** listed in the **[Entry]**, unless you choose to shirk your Cloister duties entirely- you may gain the **[Talent]** in return for losing all **[Cloistered]** moves except this one and the **[Entry]**, along with your **+IMG** talent. The flavour of the trees could be altered as follows…\r\n\r\n> **Auxillatrice**: Priestess in training, reading profane vampire novels to others, and leading prayer circles. \r\n\r\n> **Tunnelwarden**: Protectors of the Cloister from foul monsters deep within the Deepestcaverns.\r\n\r\n> **Slayer**: Expert on the supernatural, aiding Tunnelwardens in their protection by watching out for threats beyond the fauna of the Deepestcaverns. You know, like sexy vampires.\r\n\r\n> **Subcultist**: FUCK THESE CAVES'),
('safetyFirst', 'SAFETY FIRST!', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][Passive]', 'Hey… if you\'re going to a weird planet full of strange aliens… you\'re gonna need to be sure that you don\'t get into trouble! Remember all the lessons taught to you in school, and you\'ll probably be fine. You get the following PROBLEM SLEUTHING effects.\r\n\r\n> **IS THAT SAFE?**: After you roll this move, you can roll another move on your next action. If that roll isn\'t what you want, you can instead roll a different move, **[Tiered Up]**, ignoring the effects of the first move as if it didn\'t happen. Because it didn\'t. You didn\'t go through with it.\r\n\r\n> **WHAT WOULD HAPPEN?**: You take a narrative action, like saying something to someone or touching something. You then see the consequences that it would immediately have (how does the person you say take it, what happens if you touch it). You can choose to then say \"GOOD THING I DIDN\'T DO THAT\" and retcon it to have been you thinking about doing it. If you stick with the consequences, you gain **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **HERE\'S HOW TO FIX IT**: You screwed up! But that\'s okay, you catch yourself and fix what you did. You retroactively **[Tier Up]** the last move you rolled on your turn, so long as it was an **OK** or **BAD**.\r\n\r\n> **TROLLSLEUTH**: You look around and figure out if any of the trolls around you would freak out if you were a human. If any of them are, your next ABSCOND roll is **[Talented]**. If not, you lose a negative **[Emotion]**.\r\n\r\n> **WHAT\'S UP WITH THEM**: You figure out why a troll is experiencing an emotion the way they are… and exactly how to change that. You remove one **[Emotion]** from the target.\r\n\r\n> **PUZZLESOLVERY**: You immediately solve a puzzle or riddle. Fuck you, Clouder! You take **3 [Drag]** as you rush through this obstacle.'),
('saveHives', 'SAFE HIVES', 'OTHER', 'ROGUE', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Rogue]', 'URK! Okay, that heist didn’t go as planned. You’re tuckered out…and might’ve broken a bone or two. But that’s alright, because you have your network of safe hives! You’ve let so many people stay over at your place, they’re more than welcome to let you stay at theirs! The effects of **MI CASA ES SU CASA** now work in reverse. In addition, any **[Downtime]** rolls you make with their hive upgrades are **[Talented]** as you don’t feel a deep moral panic at the idea of using their bathroom. You obviously need **MI CASA ES SU CASA** to take this move.'),
('saveTheDay', 'SAVE THE DAY', 'OTHER', 'KNIGHT', '[Class][Basic][Healthy!][Recharge: 3][Locked: Knight] ', 'Don’t worry guys, you’re here to help. It’s time for you to save the day! And you know just how to do it too… by taking the metaphorical bullet. In an encounter in which you are fighting alongside an ally, such as another troll or your lusus, you may paint a target on your back, forcing all opponents to roll hostile effects such as **[Chicanery]** or **[Strife]** solely against you. This lasts for two rounds or until you are removed from the strife. If you’re facing more than one enemy, you gain 1 **[Resistance]** as you brace for impact. If another knight aligned with your side decides to steal the show by activating this move after you already activated yours, theirs takes priority and they will become the new target, while yours deactivates.'),
('scampermaster', 'SCAMPERMASTER', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Passive][Unlock: Goofball]', 'You’re a rascal; a rapscallion. A scallywag, one might say, though you’re not always conscious of it. Sure, you may come from a long line of jokers, but maybe you’re just a bumbling doofus rambling through life, or someone exceptionally good at causing a little mayhem when they need to. All in all, you\'re just a natural comedian, and that\'s pretty sweet! You are **[Talented]** at **+RAS**, and you gain the following SHENANIGANS options.\r\n\r\n> **ACCIDENTED**: Oh no! A disaster! You \"accidentally\" destroy an item worth **2 VP** or less as you bumble around.\r\n\r\n> **CONFOUNDED**: Hahaha! You disable the disabling abilities of a target with sheer tomfoolery! Any **[Passive]** abilities an opponent has that **[Nerfs]**, **[Tiers Down]** or makes certain effects **[Inept]** are disabled for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **BUCKETED**: You don\'t know why, but trolls really freak out about the whole \"bucket of green slime balanced on a door frame\" trick, so you always keep one handy! Or maybe you do know, and you\'re just twisted. The target can\'t use any items for **2 turns**! If the target is a troll, they\'re also **[Embarrassed]** for the duration.\r\n\r\n> **CAKE-FACED**: SPLAT! Haha, classic! Your target gets the effect of **[Bloodied]**, but you don\'t reveal their blood; instead, you just force them to clean the cake from their face.\r\n\r\n> **GOOD NATURED GOOFERY\'D**: You pull a prank that the target can\'t help but **[Giggle]** at for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **THIS IS STUPID\'D**: You say or do so incredibly stupid, it\'s fucking unreal. Your target is **[Stunned]** as they mumble \"This is stupid\".'),
('scaramoucheScaramouche', 'SCARAMOUCHE! SCARAMOUCHE!', 'OTHER', 'PAGE', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Page]', 'You\'re always a little bit iffy on things, even though you\'re really, really trying not to show it! You\'re basically, like, always feeling a little weird about stuff! You don\'t know what\'s going on ever! You\'re immune to being **[Embarrassed]** and **[Humiliated]** because that\'s just your constant state of being! Any time you would become **[Embarrassed]** or **[Humiliated]**, you instead become **[Smug]** because you think it\'s really great that you managed to thwart your enemy just by existing the way you do.\r\n'),
('scholareaper', 'SCHOLAREAPER', 'INDIGO', 'ADULT', '[Indigo][Locked: Adult]', 'An Empire\\\'s reach involves more than just an iron fist; it also involves inspired ideas and minds. Assimilation can only be achieved when these two concepts work hand in hand, and you are one of the many bridges between that. Scholareapers are the academics of troll society, the ones who ensure that within the ever arching reach of the Empress\\\' nation, trolls themselves have a culture to live up to. Being a literary scholar who argues about the significance of the blue curtains in Saling Ehrres works, your niche interests are what make and break culture and society. Yours and, of course, the other Indigo peers you have with no outside caste influence. Upon taking this move, you gain **PRIVATE SCHOOL PRODIGY** if you did not already have it. If you already had this move, you may choose a secondary academy like a good little scholar. This only gives you benefits from the option, not the **[Talent]**. You also gain the benefits from **PRIVATE SCHOOL PRODIGY**, not any other moves from the STUDENT tree. Additionally, you’ve learned how to apply all that knowledge to real world situations! You may roll any **UNIVERSAL MOVE** with your caste **[Talent]** if you can justify it to the other players in the encounter.'),
('scholarOfSecrets', 'SCHOLAR OF SECRETS', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Magic][Passive][Unlock: Esotericist]', 'What lies beyond religion and science? How do you explain the unexplainable? What makes the world work? These are questions you seek answers to. Between your collections of relics and your perusings of ancient texts, your knowledge of the unknowable is truly— what? No, you\'re not— you\'re not a wizard. It\'s not YOU that does the magic; it\'s your sweet collection of haunted items! You are **[Talented]** at **+PSP**. You also have a burgeoning museum of freaky artifacts, all of which are definitely cursed as fuck. These relics cost **1 LUX**, and you can only bring one to an encounter at a time. You gain 1 for free now.\r\n\r\n> **AUGURY**: The tools in your museum are ones that give you psychic links to the future, like ghost boards, terrort cards or mummified animal guts. As a **[One-Off]**, you may peer into the near future, removing the need to roll for your next **2 turns** and simply automatically get **GOOD** results.\r\n\r\n> **HEALTH**: A long-empty goblet, healing gemstones and mummy powder are YOUR go to to keeping you alive. You become immune to the **[Bloodied]** condition and have **+1 HP**.\r\n\r\n> **LUCK**: Hopalong feet, hoofbeast shoes, wishskulls… you don\'t leave your chance up to chance. Once per encounter, you may choose to reroll a single roll you just made, **[Tiered Up]** even to a **MAX**.\r\n\r\n> **MESMERISM**: Your will is MINE! You employ stuff like pendulums, magic flutes or a mask with changing expressions to hypnotise your targets. You gain access to the FREAKY EYE Mastermind Cerulean **[Entry]** while using this object, except it\'s **[Magic]**, not **[Psionic]**.\r\n\r\n> **WARDING**: You carry relics like amulets, ancient armour or crystallized herbs. The first time in an encounter someone would use **[WHAM]** on you, you ignore it, and any time someone uses **[WHAM]** on you, you gain **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **VANQUISHMENT**: You are here to use messed up evil relics like runecarved handwraps, magic wrings and talking swords to kick ass. You ignore effects that would **[Nerf]**, **[Tier Down]** or make your **[Strife]** rolls **[Inept]**.'),
('schoolfeedingStereotypes', 'SCHOOLFEEDING STEREOTYPES', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Passive]', 'Even if you aren\'t presently attending a Studyheart Academy, practically all Indigos have done at least some Remedial Schoolfeeding. Makes sense, considering how most of your caste\'s social interactions with one another happens there. Within these groups, different cliques form, and chances are, you were part of one. Question is… what type are you?\r\n\r\n> **GEEK**: It takes a special kind of someone to be a geek; on top of being smart, you need to have pretty poor social skills! Your **[Analyze]** rolls cannot be made **[Inept]**, **[Nerfed]** or **[Tiered Down]**.\r\n\r\n> **MEANBLOOD**: The bullies, the plastics, the asshole athletes… you\'re a real terror, you know that? Your **[Strife]** and **[Chicanery]** rolls have a **+1 [Buff]** against trolls with a lower **+GRT** or a lower **+PLC** stat than you, your choice when you take the move. \r\n\r\n> **MISFIT**: You\'re a loner, maybe a quiet kid, perhaps even a goth or an emo. Point is, you don\'t fit in anywhere, especially not among your rich peers. Whenever you gain a **[Negative]** emotion, you can choose to become **[Numb]** instead.\r\n\r\n> **PREP**: You dress well, you\'re a little posh, and you do SO many extracurriculars. Whenever you buy a Fashion item, you get a second one for free. \r\n\r\n> **CLOWN**: Oh my god, shut UUUUP. You are CONSTANTLY joking, causing trouble, and making it impossible to learn. Please, Christ, chill out. You get a **MAX** on **[Chicanery]** rolls on a 19+.\r\n\r\n> **SOME OTHER CLIQUE**: Man! Who knows! There\'s a tonne of different highschool items! Select one of the above mechanics. You may swap out any stats listed if it makes more sense to the clique, like Thespians using the Clown vase to get **MAX** on **[Manipulate]** rolls on a 19+.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('schoolyardMayhem', 'SCHOOLYARD MAYHEM', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Passive]', 'People think that all Indigos are stuffy, stiff-lipped stick-in-the-muds. A lot are, sure… but even the primmest prince of pulchritude must master the art of the practical joke to survive in the war zone that is a schoolfeeding dormitory. By now, you have learned to relax and be a little shit as much as anyone else instead of focusing so hard on always being perfect. You gain access to the following GOOD SHENANIGANS effects.\r\n\r\n> **SPITGLOB**: You chew up a piece of paper, and then blast it like a missile out of a straw at someone. The target is SHOCKED by this, invariably. Their negative **[Emotions]** on a timer do not tick down this turn. \r\n\r\n> **TRIP-EM-UP**: You stick out a leg, making the target struggle and flail. Haha! You make a **[Quickened]** target **[Slowed]** and **[Clumsy]** for **2 turns**. That’ll teach ‘em!\r\n\r\n> **BOMBS? CHU-CHU-CHU-CHERRY BOMB!** You throw down a bomb, and it explodes! It **[Blinds]** and **[Deafens]** the target for **1 turn**. Eurgh!\r\n\r\n> **HEADLOCK**: GOTCHA! You grab the target, holding them in place. Their **[Physical]** rolls next turn are **[Inept]**, and **[Strife]** rolls against them until the start of your next turn have a **+1 [Buff]**.'),
('scientificProwess', 'SCIENTIFIC PROWESS', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Recharge: 3][Locked: Inventor]', 'Robots aren\'t the only thing you create! You have some sick inventions you can use when you need them! You can produce the following items as a single action, building and crafting them first before equipping them. \r\n\r\n> **POWER GLOVES**: Mangrit? Who needs that when you\'ve got BRAINS! These heavy, metal gloves fight for you, leaving a heavy punch. You use **+PSP** for GRIEF.\r\n\r\n> **LUSUS DESTABILISER**: Bringing your mommy to a robot fight? Not so fast! This droning object has **2 HP**, and turns lusii in the area hostile to everyone around them, including former masters.\r\n\r\n> **DEFENSE MATRIX**: Ha! Your pathetic punches won\'t hurt me! This shield button has **2 HP**, and goes on your chest. While wearing it, you have **4 [Resistance]** to **[Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n> **PSIONIC DISRUPTER**: Not so fast, Magic Man! This\'ll put a stop to your tricks! This glowing crystal in a tube has 2 HP and is placed on the ground. All **[Psionic]** rolls in the area are **[Godawful]**.\r\n\r\n> **JET BOOTS**: WHEEEEE! I mean, FOR SCIENCE! These boots have flames exploding from the heel and have **2 HP**. You can **[Fly]**.\r\n\r\n> **SHORT CIRCUITER**: If I can\'t use my robot… nobody can! This electrical widget has **2 HP**, and disables all nearby **[Tech]** effects and makes the moves of mechanical creatures **[Inept]** in the area. Take that!'),
('scourge', 'SCOURGE', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Physical][Strife]', 'Ceruleans are, by and large, a caste riddled with a reputation of extreme sadism and bloodlust. While it\'s not true for every individual troll... You were likely raised to believe that killing was expected of you, and the agony of others a welcome thing. So, when you want to BR8K HEADS, roll the stat you gained **[Talent]** in from your **[Entry]**. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: Ow, FUCK! You accidentally hit yourself as you swing and miss wildly! You take **2 [Somatic]** damage and become **[Bloodied]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Nope. Nice try. You miss, and your momentum carries you into harm’s way. You take **1 [Somatic]** damage!\r\n\r\n**OK**: You didn’t hit them, but you’re definitely outpacing them. You get an extra action this turn. \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: BAM! You do **1 [Somatic]** damage to your opponent.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You hit them in JUST the right spot. And by the looks of it, that’s gonna leave a mark. You do **2 [Somatic]** damage, or **1 [Somatic]** damage and render the target **[Bloodied]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Now THAT’S a critical hit! Whether it’s a nasty artery slash or a wholeass severed limb, you seriously wound the target. You do **3 [Somatic]** damage, or **2 [Somatic]** damage and **[Bloody]** the target.'),
('scrapyardSupergenius', 'SCRAPYARD SUPERGENIUS', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Junker]', 'BEHOLD! YOU ARE THE ULTIMATE GENIUS! You\'ve surpassed all those stuffy nerds in their nice, clinical labs by doing something they could never hope to do: PRACTICAL WORK. You get your hands dirty, you wrestle with problems instead of thinking about them, and you hit stuff with a wrench till it WORKS! You are a GODDAMN GENIUS! HAHAHA! You gain access to HERO MODE through your HARDCORE HUBRIS. You have **12 VP** rather than 8 thanks to the heavier loads of junk you bring everywhere with you. By now, you\'ve automated nearly every aspect of your life with cogs, pipes, and boilers… so it stands to reason that you\'d take a shot at fixing up yourself! You can REBUILD yourself as a **[Downtime]** action as you build yourself mechanical tools and gear that you wear around your limbs, neck, back, etc. You can give yourself a second **[Talent]** to **+HUB**; you gain the following effects depending on the REBUILD you choose. \r\n\r\n> **ROBOTIC RASCALITY**: You\'ve kitted yourself out with an automated defense system that fucks with opponents at every step. Steam valves hiss in their face, oil leaks, etcetera! The **[Recharge]** of all moves opponents use on you are increased by 1.\r\n\r\n> **POWERED-UP PULCHRITUDE**: Your bloodpusher is literally hooked up to an engine to make you more charismatic. It works, weirdly enough. Your **[Manipulate]** rolls are never **[Inept]**, **[Nerfed]** or **[Tiered Down]**.\r\n\r\n> **GUNSLINGING GRACE**: You\'ve got extra robotic arms… that WIELD GUNS! PEW PEW! All of your weapons always have RANGEDKIND attached. This stacks with PIPE GUN PIONEER.\r\n\r\n> **AUTOMATIC APPETITE**: You\'ve got storage all over you— glove compartments, giant bags, cool hats… your **VP** increases to 16. Goddamn.\r\n\r\n> **MECHANICAL MANGRIT**: MECHAAAAA MUSCLE! You\'ve got mechanical braces you wear on your fists that have rockets built into ‘em to help you punch faster. You cannot lose **[WHAM]** until you spend it.\r\n\r\n> **PYROPHORIC PERSPICACITY**: You\'ve got goggles that let you see through EVERYTHING. Trolls can never be **[Hidden]** from you, and you can use PRECICE PERSPICACITY HERO MODE as well as HARDCORE HUBRIS.\r\n\r\n> **IRONCLAD IMAGINATION**: You WILL not be fucked with by wizards thanks to your antimagic alloy armour. **[Magic]** rolls are **[Inept]** against you.'),
('scriptGrubbie', 'SCRIPT GRUBBIE', 'OTHER', 'HACKERMAN', '[Template][Recharge: 2][Tech][Unlock: Hackerman]', 'To put it simply for the viewers at home, you’re an expert in manipulating computers. Be it their code, actual hardware, or something else, you’ve done it all! Believe it or not, everything in there can be used against the user, or to benefit them. Luckily, you know how to make it do just that! As long as you’re in the same trollcial media or at the very least in the same building as someone, you may remotely infect their computer with... Something. You can choose to become **[Talented]** at **+PSP** when you take this move, instead of your Caste **[Entry]** **[Talent]**. When you want to zip-bomb somebody, roll **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Aw shit, aw fuck, aw beans! You’re deep in it now, fucko! You’ve managed to poke around… but you know. ORG territory. By mistake. Better start high tailing it dude. You shoot up to 5 WATCHLIST POINTS on the CIS WATCHLIST (check their **[Template]** **[Entry]** for details) which immediate summons a DRONE STRIKE **[Hazard]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: If you’re going to say quippy hacker one-liners, you should actually do something. Now you look like a dipshit! You fail to make progress.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Okay, this is but a minor setback. That’s all, it’s fine, just… a little annoying. Don’t give up yet. You get **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD: SOMETHING SOMETHING YOU’RE IN OVERUSED HACKER QUOTE! Listen, you’re not good enough yet to have a catchphrase. But you ARE good enough to start digging around where you shouldn’t! Choose an effect of your choices from one of the various branches of hacking below**:\r\n\r\n> **INFOSNATCHING - Doxx**: Lol. Lmao. Lol. Lmao. Get fucked, random indigo! You posted their IP address! So cool. The target must roll 1d8. In that many turns, an ANGRY MOB **[Hazard]** spawns. Further rolls decrease the timer by 1.\r\n\r\n> **DISMANTLERUPTING - Notification Scramble**: Good GOD all these notification sounds are terrible. Actually maybe you shouldn’t have done this in like. The mall? Ugh. Trolls can\'t roll **[Manipulate]** rolls for **2 turns** as loud beeping annoys everyone.\r\n\r\n> **VIRUSCORCHERS - Malware That Creates A Pop Up And Then Upon Clicking Spawns Two More Every Time You Do So Until Your Screen Is Full And You Wail Like A Little Grub**: Also known as a ‘Hydra’. Man. Those fucking suck. You **[Stress]** the target for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **TOOLBAGS - Cool Effects**: Behold! The son of you, the maker! Nobody else could make such a beautiful program. It makes a bunch of cool animations pop up on screen like you’re doing something. You’re so fucking cool. All enemies and allies are **[Stunned]** as they look at your cool effects and nod appreciatively.\r\n\r\n> **SCAMLORD**: ALL YOUR CAEGARS ARE BELONG TO US. You leak their caegarscore into yours. Serves them right for having money in this economy! They drop a Wealth Level, and you gain **Treasure I**.\r\n\r\n> **APIANARCHIST**: Cool hardware, bro. It\'d be a shame if it GREW A LOAD OF LEGS AND STARTED PUKING AND SCREAMING AND CRYING. You destroy an item with the **[Tech]** tag worth **2 VP** or less. The target is **[Disgusted]** for a turn.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: YEAH! HACK HACK HACK. You get a **GOOD**, but the move only has **[Recharge 1]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Oh you completely and utterly fucking demolish them. Whether it be some sort of worm .~ATH or a zip bomb, you expose them to something EXTREME. You get a **GOOD**, but the target is exposed to the DOUBLE MOBIUS REACHAROUND VIRUS **[Affliction]**.'),
('seabedLandmark', 'SEABED LANDMARK', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Royal]', 'Your FIEFDOM has grown to such sizes now that you have even cultivated your own culture! Incredible! Look at you, you\'re like a little ecosystem in a jar, except you have like, nukes maybe. You gain the following exclusive LANDMARK Hivecrafting Upgrade depending on your -CRACY Tree from DIVINE RIGHT OF FISH. This upgrade is free; your FIEFDOM has been constructing it for some time now, and it\'s finally complete! Make sure to name your building. If you have trolls you have given an ALLEGIANCEBLOCK, they may take the **[Entry]** of said tree and the effects of this move. Trolls can only ever take this benefit from one Fiefdom, even if they have ALLEGIANCEBLOCKS in multiple - no aesthetic double-dipping!\r\n\r\n> **ARISTOCRACY**: You build a REGAL CASTLE, to complete your traditional noble aesthetic. You have an overwhelmingly regal presence; as an action, you can make any opponent **[Scared]** or **[Charmed]** as you flaunt your tiptop position on the Hemospectrum to get what you want. \r\n\r\n> **PLUTOCRACY**: You build a SEASCRAPER, an immensely tall tower/hotel/gambling hall. You become ULTRAULTARICH, putting you a level of Wealth above all other trolls. Additionally, all items bought with **LUX** cost **1 LUX** less; it\'s just that easy to buy stuff.\r\n\r\n> **STRATOCRACY**: You build a GRAND IMPERIAL HALL, made with columns of marble, statues of mermaids, and MANY hemoladder affirming pieces of art. You WILL crush all land-dwellers. Maybe. That could be a ruse to get other seadwellers off of your case. You have an additional **2 HP**; additionally, all **[Strife]** rolls against you have a **-1 [Nerf]** as you wear thick and majestic armour that can really save your skin!\r\n\r\n> **TECHNOCRACY**: You build an OMNIFORGETORIUM! This massive, sci-fi-esque structure is like something out of a Cyberpunk movie, and helps to produce countless gadgets and gizmos every day! You increase your total **VP** by 4; additionally, you can create any mechanical item on the fly, effectively purchasing it mid-encounter. However, you can only create any one item once in an encounter.\r\n\r\n> **MAGOCRACY**: You build an OMINOUS MAGE TOWER! A looming building atop a peak that oversees the rest of your FIEFDOM. Whenever someone mentions your name anywhere on Alternia, you become aware of it and the general location of that character when they said it. You can also view other people remotely through a crystal ball, but the character becomes aware that you are doing so. You can communicate with them via magic from a distance, if you so choose, allowing you to roll **[Mental]** or **[Manipulate]** rolls (the latter only on your viewed target) without being present in an encounter.\r\n\r\n> **WHIMSICRACY**: You build a STRANGE MANOR, a building with infinite rooms where reality seems to abandon its usual properties for… a sea fey aesthetic?? It has to be an illusion… right? You also become **[Talented]** at all **+IMG** moves, not just ones from your Magician moves.'),
('seadwellingScion', 'SEADWELLING SCION', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Passive][Ultra][Locked: Royal]', 'You are no mere royal. You are a deity, anointed by your blood and the planet you live on. Today, you rule the seas; tomorrow, planets, and the day after, GALAXIES! All will one day bow to you, as is your birthright! You love being rich as fuck!!! You gain access to HERO MODE through your AWESOME APPETITE. Additionally, you immediately gain **15 LUX** as soon as you gain this move, representing an Imperial Grant given to you in recognition of your services. Your unmatchable perfection means you can NEVER afford to fail at ANYTHING. EVER. You become immune to all moves and effects that would make you **[Inept]** or **[Tiered Down]** at certain moves, unless you would give them to yourself. Any time you would be affected by one of these moves, you instead gain **1 [Boost]** as your defiance for those who would tell you— YOU!— how to live your life blinds all opponents.'),
('seaMonsterRider', 'SEA MONSTER RIDER', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'ORPHANER', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Orphaner]', 'GIDDYUP! You are well used to patrolling the waves on the back of a sea monster. You gain the CUSTODIAN COMPANION Perfectly Generic move, except that your Custodian has 6 Features, not 4, and you can ride on its back as if it were a 2 HORSEPOWER Tiny Vehicle. Your VEHICULATE and ATRIACLIZE rolls both use the stat you are **[Talented]** in from your Caste **[Entry]**.\n\n'),
('seaTreasureGlamour', 'SEA TREASURE GLAMOUR', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'You are so sparkly. Whether it\'s from your flawless complexion, the jewelry you\'re covered in, bioluminescent tattoos, or 100 caegar per ounce sparkling rainbow drinker serum highlighter, you are coated from head to toe in the most gorgeous finery known to troll kind. Jealous? They ought to be! Only seadwellers get to live the life of luxury you get to. You can spend **+1 LUX** on a fashion item to make it a GLAMOURIZED version. GLAMOURIZED versions of items give an extra **+1 [Buff]** to one stat, and a **-1 [Nerf]** to another. When you add GLAMOURIZED versions of Fashion items to a Collection, the Collection adds these additional ±1\'s on top of the Collection\'s regular stats. As always, you can\'t go above the stat cap with Fashion items. You can purchase WARDROBIFIERS without making a BIG BUY.'),
('secondAspect', 'SECOND ASPECT', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][Passive]', 'You are… Well, you are, and that\'s somewhat troubling, isn\'t it? You exist, and with existence comes infinite possibilities of the self that can\'t be condensed into a single concept. What are the urges of Time when the struggles of Heart are just as dire? Oh, is that a vaguely mysterious and mystic statement? Sorry about that. You take on a second Aspect as a Template, gaining the **[Entry]** now. You can take no more than **3 moves** in this alternate aspect.'),
('secretFiles', 'SECRET FILES', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'CIS', '[Template][Basic][Recharge: 2][Analyze][Tech][Locked: CIS]', 'Hoohoohoo… being a secret agent means you’re also privy to planetary secrets— like all your friends’ passwords, or their deepest, darkest secrets! In fact, you might have read about this particular troll in front of you… hmmm!~ Let’s just check your palmhusk! When you want to dig up someone’s secrets, roll **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: IT’S THE WRONG FILE! You get the person in front of you confused with someone else— you gain 3 pieces of false information that you wholeheartedly believe. When it becomes clear you’re wrong, you are **[Humiliated]**, you stupid prick.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Uhhhhhhhh… UHHHHH… no, you don’t know this person.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You gain… something. Their favourite colour? Their height? Not exactly helpful, but… your next SECRET FILES roll is **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Ohohoho! Says here, that… hmm! You gain access to some piece of information you wouldn’t be able to tell with a glance. Where were they last night? Who are their friends? Have they had contact with a particular person? Anything that might be a matter of public record, you can perceive. The target feels **[Dread]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: What the fuck? How… HOW did you know that? You find files on the person that detail some really private stuff— their true caste, their darkest secret, even what they have in their pocket. Anything that wouldn’t be in the public record, you can get. The target feels **[Despair]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You’ve got them cornered now. You gain the target’s in-depth life story, including any public or private record questions you might want to access (max 3). The target feels **[Despair]** for the encounter.\r\n\r\n'),
('secureContainPurge', 'SECURE, CONTAIN, PURGE', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'TIT', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: TIT]', 'The TIT have a wide variety of anomalous threats they must respond to in order to preserve the Empire\'s normalcy and, at times, secondary to the Empire\'s wishes, the stability of the multiverse itself when some absolute fuckshit happens that threatens existence itself. The latter happens more often than you think. Three informal branches exist that take up the majority of the TIT\'s trollpower to deal with. As you have survived your first few nights, you\'re expected to pick a branch to work on! Usually, the TIT prefers to capture over cull due to the rarity of their targets. Especially for aliens and limebloods! Better to catch and risk an escape than learn nothing at all! Additionally, you may choose to make your **[Somatic]** or **[Psychic]** Damage also be **[Non-Lethal]** in order to capture your targets! If a target has twice as much **[Drag]** as **HP** and is **[Eerie]**, an Alien or a Limeblood, you deal +1 **[Non-Lethal]** Damage.\r\n\r\n**EXTRANARRATIVE INCURSIONS**: Limebloods were once a normal caste, but have since become something truly warped and unnatural. Their ability to rewrite reality without even realizing it is a threat to all of existence! And more importantly, to how Condy has designed her Empire! You must contain and research these ‘metapowers’ so that they may be used for the Empire\'s design. You can recognize any **[Lime]** moves for what they are immediately, and **[Lime]** moves against you have a -2 [Nerf]. You\'re trained to watch for this! Your Amnesticizor rolls may instead act as a **+PSP GRIEF [Strife]** roll against Limes thanks to anti-anomaly modifications to the serum; which additionally reveals their caste should you target a disguised Lime and prevents them from ABSCONDING or TELEPORTING for 1 Round.\r\n\r\n**FALSE MAGIC**: **[Eeries]** are real. As much as your agency denies much of their origins, you know they originate from someplace truly evil. It\'s best nobody knows the Truth, lest the Truth make itself known. You are immune to **[Scared]** and **[Terrified]**, and gain 1 **[Boost]** when an **[Eerie]** troll is revealed. Your Amnesticizor rolls may instead act as a **+PSP GRIEF [Strife]** roll against **[Eeries]** thanks to anti-magical modifications to the serum; which additionally prevents them from using **[Magic]** for 1 Round.\r\n\r\n**ALIEN INVADERS**: Alternia is an incredibly important world. If aliens ever found where Gl\'bgolyb was hidden then they could end it all in a single attack... And worse than that, having aliens on Alternia makes the Empire look weak! You hunt down the infiltrator, you dissect them, you study them, you deny they ever existed. You also correct conspiracy theories on the origins of ancient ruins. No Enpece, aliens did not create those ancient cities. As a **[Lengthy] [Tech]** action you can use experimental TIT technology to disable all **[SBURB]** tech in the Encounter for 3 Rounds! Grab that alien before it escapes! Your Amnesticizor rolls may instead act as a **+PSP GRIEF [Strife]** roll against Aliens thanks to a fuckton of poisonous stuff that\'s harmless to trolls added to the serum. Unfortunately, spraying poison in an alien\'s face doesn\'t actually do much else except give them 2 **[Drag]**.'),
('seeingDouble', 'SEEING DOUBLE', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Passive][Psionic]', 'Gold trolls have unusual eyes, usually lacking pupils in favour of two shiny colourful eyes! These eyes impart within you minor **[Psionic]** powers that give you some minor hijinks you can choose from. You can roll a specialized version of SHENANIGANS called PSITRICK, which loses the **[Physical]** tag for the **[Psionic]** one, and uses **+IMG** (or **+PSP** if you are a Network Gold). Select two of the following options, or select the one option twice; if you do, your PSITRICK is **[Tiered Up]**. PSITRICK shares its **[Recharge]** with SHENANIGANS. \r\n\r\n> **JUST REGULAR FUCKING EYES**: What the fuck! Your eyes are normal! The fuck! You don’t get any other eye colours or PSITRICK, but your vision is markedly better than other Golds; your SPOT PROBLEM SLEUTHING rolls are **[Tiered Up]**. You can’t take this if you’re a Battery or Network troll.\r\n\r\n> **RED**: Your eye is a deep scarlet, a pale carmine, a sweet pink… or something. You can charge up a slight LIGHTNING EYE to zap at people, like a less awesome LASER EYE. It does **1 [Electric]** **[Psychic]** damage; this effect has the **[Strife]** tag. On a **GREAT**, this is **2 damage**, and a 3 on a **MAX**, rather than normal effects.\r\n\r\n> **ORANGE**: Oh, how nice! Your eye is like, maybe a shiny apricot, a cool coral, or even an electric orange. You have powerful telekinesis; you can LEVITATE the target to make them **[Fly]** for a turn.\r\n\r\n> **YELLOW**: A calm honey, a hot amber, or maybe an iconic gold colors YOUR eye. You NERVESCRAMBLE people with your powers, shooting electricity through their veins; the target is **[Overwhelmed]** for **2 turns**. This also counts as **[Electric]** damage to monsters affected by it.\r\n\r\n> **GREEN**: You’ve got a nice olive, emerald, or neon lime hue to your peepers. Your eyes can see people’s inner energy. When you POWERGAZE at people like this, they can’t negatively affect **[Psionic]** rolls for **2 turns** .\r\n\r\n> **BLUE**: Faaaaancy! Your eye is turquoise, aquamarine, or (gasp) ULTRAmarine, perhaps? Your psionics can short out those of others with a PSISHORT, giving them **1 [Electric][Somatic]** damage if they attempt a **[Psionic]** roll on their next turn.\r\n\r\n> **PURPLE**: Aw, sweet, look at those lavender/periwinkle/amethyst glimmers! You can halt people’s brainwaves for a moment, frying their thoughts. If you BRAINFRY the target, all of their **[Recharge]** on moves currently recharging don’t tick down at the end of their turn.\r\n\r\n> **GREY**: Silver, soot, metallic… that’s you! Your psionics are fast and sharp, and actually serve to help people! You can zap someone with a ADRENALINATE to reduce their **[Recharge]** for one move to 0.'),
('seenItAll', 'SEEN IT ALL', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Are you supposed to be impressed? Because you’re not. From rampaging juggalos mad that they can’t get their way to drama about Snazzard doping to the horrors brought on by the dystopian capitalist world you live in, you’re kinda… numb to emotions at this point. Whenever you would gain a negative **[Emotion]**, you can choose to instead become **[Stressed]**. This can heighten to **[Agitated]** if you block another incoming **[Emotion]**, and further times to accumulate **[Drag]** as per **[Stressed]**’s normal heightening rules.'),
('seethingSmile', 'SEETHING SMILE', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Open][Free]', 'Hmmmm. Oh, yes, you\'re sure. So true. When someone is really getting on your nerves, but you know you can\'t just lose your cool (it would damage your image!), you just… give a passive aggressive forced grin that just oozes with \"dude, fuck you\". Whenever you become **[Enraged]** or **[Out of Control]**, you maintain the benefits of being in such a state without the downsides, because you\'re still in control. You can choose to become **[Enraged]** when someone rolls a **BAD** or lower result on any **[Manipulate]** roll.\r\n'),
('seeThroughTheirLies', 'SEE THROUGH THEIR LIES', 'RAGE', 'RAGE', '[Aspect][Advanced][One-Off][Locked: Rage]', 'You’ve developed an almost unnatural way of telling when people are lying to you, almost like psionic telepathy, but not quite. You do not need to roll PROBLEM SLEUTHING to know when someone is lying to you; you can simply spend an action and know if their statement is true or not. If you have a move with similar effects from another source, you gain the **GOOD** result of PROBLEM SLEUTHING as well as you suss out the truth immediately, which does not trigger the **[Recharge]**. Your first **[Strife]** roll after a target lied to you is **[Tiered Up]** and does **+1 damage**. However, this move cannot be used in tandem with **[WHAM]**.'),
('selfActualization', 'SELF ACTUALIZATION', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'The moment that a Jade realizes their worth as an individual is the moment that you stop binding yourself to the caves. While you might still love them or hate them, remembering to put yourself first is an important step to take! Your newfound confidence gains you the following GOOD SWASHBUCKLE effects.\r\n\r\n> **GATHER YOUR WORDS**: Oh, prepare to get yelled at, bitch. You **[Tier Up]** your next WORDPLAY roll, even to a **MAX**, and add a free **GOOD** effect so long as you get at least a **GOOD** on your WORDPLAY roll. This has the **[Mental]** tag, not the **[Physical]** one.\r\n\r\n> **BITCHSLAP**: GET A HOLD OF YOURSELF. You slap someone (an ally, an enemy, or even yourself) and slap some sense into them, removing an **[Emotion]** in exchange for **2 [Drag]** (no **[Drag]** if it was positive).\r\n\r\n> **FOCUS**: Think of all the good things that have ever happened to you… your friends, your loved ones… and keep it up, just for them! You **[Heighten]** one **[Emotion]**. This has the **[Mental]** tag, not the **[Physical]** one.\r\n\r\n> **CHARGE!**: You push past your limits and ATTACK! Yeah, cut that seadweller in half, fuck it! You get **1 [WHAM]**.'),
('selfassured', 'SELF-ASSURED', 'HEART', 'HEART', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Heart]', 'You know that shoving your identity in the face of others can drag them down, so you don’t do it too much— but that isn’t to say that you’ve forgotten your crystal clear view of yourself and how much it matters to you. You gain **1 [Resistance]** against **[Verbal]** damage, and you don’t gain any negative effects from **[Base]** Emotions. You still have the emotion, though, and it counts towards heightening it if you gain it from another source.'),
('selfEsteem', 'SELF ESTEEM', 'PROSPIT', 'PROSPIT', '[Sway][Recharge: 3][Locked: Prospit]', 'Hey, who said you could have this? Self esteem? In this economy? You bet! If the world won’t give you a boost, that’s okay! You can give a little **[Boost]** to yourself! Your **+HUB** stat becomes like a little bank of **[Boost]** just for you, and you can pull from it using an action! If you have **+4 HUB**, you can take out up to **+4 [Boost]**! It takes an action to gain **1 [Boost]** like this.'),
('selfinflection', 'SELF-INFLECTION', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Passive]', 'You know your true self and potential a little better than many other trolls know theirs. You must have the Entry move for your Aspect in order to take this move. You gain one **[Basic]** move of your own Zodiac, and the level gate for that particular type— be it your aspect or your sway— drops to Level 1, and **[Advanced]** moves to Level 6, allowing you access now rather than later.'),
('selfMadeSymbol', 'SELF-MADE SYMBOL', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Advanced][Free][One-Off]', 'While others out there choose to use their government-assigned symbol at birth, hemoanonymous folks have chosen a different methodology. While it is illegal to be without a signifier on you, nobody said it had to be what you were given. Lime symbols, hearts, circles, crosses... the world is your bivalve ocean creature and like pronouns you decide what represents you! Choose a custom symbol, whether it be a lime symbol made gray (this counts for Limes who represent as Anon too!) or another shape or design. Choose a permanent **[Emotion]** you assign to this symbol; once per encounter, you may activate this emotion as a **[Free][One-Off]**:\r\n> [Hopeful]\r\n> [Smug]\r\n> [Brave]\r\n> [Happy]\r\n> [Enraged]\r\n> [Proud]\r\n'),
('selfPortrait', 'SELF PORTRAIT', 'OTHER', 'ABOMINARTIST', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Abominartist]', 'I like it. Picaso. Your work has paid off pretty well, and now people are… Aware of your work. Your art. Your glorious, pretty art, that you tried so hard to push and pull out there into this cruel, harsh world. That or you just made a meme piece that happened to explode in popularity while the rest of your actual good work goes unseen. That’s the hardships of being an artist, after all! It never gets easier. Point is, you’re known, even if it’s in small circles. You get a **+2 [Buff]** to **+PLC** rolls for the first 2 rounds of combat. Your opponents are **[Charmed]** by you at the beginning of fights. Is that… the Bongo Cat guy? DA VINKY?!'),
('sendInTheClowns', 'SEND IN THE CLOWNS', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][One-Off]', 'Isn\'t it rich? Are we a pair? Me here at last on the ground… You in mid-air! Whether you like the church or not, you\'ve formed some TIGHT clown sibs who you can call on to watch your back when you\'re in a rough spot. Whether the Church is as good as you originally imagined or not, the fact remains that its laypeople are people like you— people you can care about. You can spend an action to call up to 3 Juggalo to your aid. These use a random selection of Purpleblood NPCs from Chapter 17a: FRIENDS & FOES. They usually arrive within **2 turns**. These clowns can be asked to do the following…\r\n\r\n> **STRIFE!**: The Juggalo join you in a TEAM STRIFE. They won\'t do this if you outnumber the enemy team with their inclusion; clown\'s honour! They can also stand by and beatbox for you, making all trolls **[Talented]** at WORDPLAY and FRAYMOTIF if needed.\r\n\r\n> **DISTRACT**: Hey, heenhonk, over here! They distract guards, drones, or other creatures that need a distraction. You and your allies become **[Hidden]**, and SPOT rolls against you become **[Godawful]**.\r\n\r\n> **DO CRIMES**: The clowns make a BASH-N-RUN **[Downtime]** roll mid-encounter. Whoops! \r\n\r\n> **GETAWAY VEHICLE**: SEEYA! The clowns pull up in a comically small **[Vehicle]** with capacity for 8 passengers. This **[Vehicle]** has 3 HORSEPOWER but no other upgrades, unless you pay them **LUX** when you summon them. You get half your **LUX** back afterwards.'),
('seriouslyScrewCelandine', 'SERIOUSLY, SCREW CELANDINE', 'OTHER', 'BEAST_BRAWLER', '[Template][Basic][Lengthy][Craft][Mental][Locked: Beast Brawler]', 'How are you out of celandine again, for fuck’s sake? Elfroot, you’re out of elfroot, and you could have sworn you still had some blisterwort laying around but NOPE, APPARENTLY NOT, you’re going to have to backtrack to Gulchscourge and hit up the Horticullturist again. Ugh. You gain access to a new type of THE FUNJUNK: Healing Decoctions which take up **2 VP** and you may only ever carry 2 at a time . These are a CONSUMABLE item that instantly restore HP when you use it. As a **[Downtime]** action, or as a **[Lengthy]** action during an encounter, you may **[Craft]** a Healing Decoction, or a concoction from the THE FUN JUNK item list. Roll **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Well, you burnt it, put the wrong ingredient in, and then used up all of the components you needed in the process. A+ work. You become **[Confused]** for a round, and may not roll this move again for the rest of the encounter. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: This is not a potion. This is a bottle of aquafina with a mushroom in it. Good try though buddy, you gotta fill out that codex somehow. \r\n\r\n**OK**: Shit, okay, you got half the potion made but you still have some work to do before this is fit for troll consumption. Your next attempt **[Tiers Up]** and, if performed during an encounter, only costs **1 action**. \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: This right here is a POTION folks, step right up and get a taste. You craft one Tiny Healing Decoction which heals **1 HP** when used or a LOW QUALITY FUNJUNK concoction of your choice, but it cannot be the actual Potions precaptchalogue. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: This ain’t your first day at the alembic, folks. You craft one Healing Decoction which heals **2 HP** when used or a FUNJUNK concoction of your choice, but it cannot be the actual Potions precaptchalogue. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: YEAH buddy, we are stocking up for that Marborassquale raid! You craft one Huge Healing Decoction which heals **3 HP** when used or a HIGH QUALITY FUNJUNK concoction of your choice, including Potions if you so choose.'),
('serviceProvider', 'SERVICE PROVIDER', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Passive][Psionic][Locked: Network]', 'As a Network Gold, your brain upholds the internet! But some Golds do better on certain corners of the planet-wide hivemind, and have their psyches changed by sweeps of exposure to it. Freaks who frequent image boards, sweethearts who comb wikis, etcetera etcetera. So… what corner of the internet are you hooked up to?\r\n\r\n> **E-COMMERCE**: Websites that involve ordering shit online, like Scamazon or Greedbay! You have **12 VP** rather than 8, since you know ALL the best deals.\r\n\r\n> **SOCIAL MEDIA**: Chittr, Prongle, you name it— you know exactly how people act online. It\'s, uh, it\'s a lot. You automatically know trolls you meet, and are aware of their attitudes in private. Choose if they count as nice or not.\r\n\r\n> **NICE**: Okay, they\'re chill. When they gain **[Boost]**, you gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n> **NOT**: You\'ve seen their posts, this is a bulgehead. When they gain **[Drag]**, you gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **EDUCATION**: You spend your time on Wickedpedia or niche sites about like, birds and shit. You know a lot! You can roll PROBLEM SLEUTHING twice in the same turn.\r\n\r\n> **ENTERTAINMENT**: Spewtube, Stitch, MMOs… you can never get bored with THIS amount of entertainment on your hands! Whenever you gain a negative **[Emotion]**, you also gain a random **[Positive]** one as you remind yourself about the FUN that exists online!\r\n\r\n> **OLDNET**: Y\'know, stuff like webcomics, defunct sites using outdated code, Crash games… stuff that\'s a little out of date, but needs to be archived! You just keep these old sites chugging along inside your mind. You little Wayback machine, you.  The **[Recharge]** of all your moves is always 1 lower.\r\n\r\n> **OTHER**: Ugh. What\'s your site, then? I dunno, there are like, a billion different websites, I\'m not writing mechanics for all of them. Just take the mechanical effect of another platform.'),
('shadesOfTeal', 'SHADES OF TEAL', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Passive]', 'Being a Teal is a world of paradoxes. You\'re not quite blue, and not quite green. Where does that even leave you? The answer varies from troll to troll. Some of you act all smug and tell others to suck a bulge, some of you just kinda shrug and go with it, and some of you are giant walking panic attacks. So which are you?\r\n\r\n> **SMUG SAXE**: Oh yeah, you\'re a real piece of shit, and you love it. You can become **[Smug]** as an action.\r\n\r\n> **AVERAGE AQUAMARINE**: You\'d think this was a shade of deep blue, right? But uh, nah, it\'s a teal kinda. Whenever you\'re made to use **[Drag]**, you gain **1 [Boost]** afterwards. \r\n\r\n> **TREMBLING TURQUOISE**: Jesus Christ, man, get some medication! Good lord! Whenever you get **[Scared]**, **[Stressed]** or feel **[Dread]**, you get **1 [Boost]** every turn because \"ah… what a familiar sensation…\". You can\'t increase this **[Boost]** through other means.'),
('shadowyStalker', 'SHADOWY STALKER', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][One-Off][Locked: Subjugglator]', 'The hunt is part of the game. When an encounter starts, you can choose to automatically go **[Hidden]** for **[Free]** as you dip into the shadows. This works even if the target has already seen you. The target cannot interact with you at all except to use PROBLEM SLEUTHING, and you can’t do anything but watch them with this move. For every round that the target cannot find you with PROBLEM SLEUTHING, you gain **1 [Hold]**. You can spend these **[Holds]** in the following ways. You can come out of hiding and jumpscare them for an additional **[Hold]**. You may only select one effect.\r\n\r\n> **1 Hold: JUMP OUT!**: The target takes **1 [Drag]** and  you leap out. You can use this effect multiple times when the target finds you as a **[Reaction]**.\r\n\r\n> **2 Hold: ATMOSPHERIC FEAR**: An ominous feeling is overcoming them… the target is **[Scared]**!\r\n\r\n> **2 Hold: OFF-SCREEN KILL**: The target finds a corpse!!! Oh, ye gods! Who did this? (You.) The target cannot roll PROBLEM SLEUTHING this turn.\r\n\r\n> **3 Hold: QUIET QUIET BANG**: You **[Tier Up]** a move, and launch out of the shadows! You may combine this with JUMP OUT!\r\n\r\n> **4 Hold: TRUE FEAR**: The target is starting to panic; they are **[Terrified]**. This costs only **2 [Hold]** if they were already **[Scared]**.'),
('sharedPride', 'SHARED PRIDE', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Open][Free]', 'Hey, c\'mon! What\'s good enough for you is good enough for anyone! When you use moves to buff yourself up, you can instead give the effect to an ally. Just got **[Boost]**? Enpece, you take it! Are you **[Hopeful]**? Here, someone else needs it more. You\'re part of a team, after all!'),
('sharingIsCaring', 'SHARING IS CARING', 'OTHER', 'SYLPH', '[Class][Basic][Recharge: 2][Locked: Sylph]', 'Oh, come now, that\'s just immature. Share with your hatchmate! For goodness sake, how do you expect prosperity when you\'re going to hoard all of that to yourself? And how do you expect to make it through the darkest hour or whatever’s happening now when you’re being selfish and hoarding all the healing potions over there- I can see you, you know! When an ally would gain a bonus or **[Buff]**, you can spend a **[Reaction]** to chide them into sharing it with your other allies. If one would gain a **[Positive] [Emotion]** like **[Hopeful]**, or **[Boost]**, it applies to up to 3 allies aside from yourself. This does not apply to **[Holds]**, and cannot be used with Finishing Move.'),
('shenanigans', 'SHENANIGANS', 'OTHER', 'UNIVERSAL', '[Chicanery][Physical]', 'In a world of strife and grief like Alternia, slapstick comedy is the only universal language. Each individual SHENANIGANS option is **[Recharge: 3]**, so be sure to plan your gags accordingly! When you want to use your prankster’s wit to help you out, roll **+RAS**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You set up an elaborate prank, only for the other person to suckerpunch you in the face. They may make a **[Free]** **[Strife]** roll.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: MEDIOCRE. Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Could be worse. They get **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD: Your foolsmastery works, and you pull a fast one on your opponent! Choose one of the following effects**:\r\n\r\n> **BOTHERED**: You are SOOOO good at being stupidly annoying, it\'s great. The target is **[Distracted]** for 2 turns. If they get a **BAD** or lower **[Mental]**, **[Manipulate]** or **[Psionic]** roll in this time, the target takes **2 extra [Drag]**. This effect is a **[Manipulate]** one.\r\n\r\n> **TICKLED**: Whether you actually tickle them, or tickle their funnybone, you make the target guffaw. The target starts **[Giggling]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **GRABBED**: GOTCHA!! You hold on tight, not letting go! You and your target are both **[Trapped]**, and the target is **[Stressed]**. If they were **[Flying]**, so are you!\r\n\r\n> **JUKED**: You dodge left- SIKE, IT WAS RIGHT! HAAAAHAHA! The opponent takes **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> **PRANKED**: HAHA! DUMMY! You do something embarrassing that makes a fool out of them. It\'s hilarious! The target is **[Embarrassed]** for **1 turn**. \r\n\r\n> **SOAKED**: SPLOOSH! You kick a hydrant over, you knock them into a puddle or otherwise coat them in water. The target is **[Soggy]** for **3 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **OFF-KILTER\'D**: WHOA, WAH, I\'M TRIPPING HERE, DAMN! The target is **[Clumsy]** for **2 turns**. If they get a **BAD** or lower **[Physical]** move in this time, they become **[Floorbound]** til they get up. \r\n\r\n> **YOINKED**: **MIN**E! You make grabby hands at an opponent\'s Sylladex, stealing from them! You remove an item from their Dex and add it to yours. If this increases your own Sylladex over **8 VP**, you eject an appropriate amount of items onto the floor until you\'re back at 8.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Your goofery is on point! You get a **GOOD**, but you give the target **1 extra [Drag]** as you mess ‘em up OR the Emotion you give them is Heightened.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: SOMEONE, CALL THE POLICE!! THERE\'S A PRANKING MANIAC ON THE LOOSE! You get a **GOOD**, but you give the target **2 extra [Drag]**, and don’t trigger **[Recharge]**.'),
('shenyanigans', 'SHENYANIGANS', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Open][Chicanery]\r\n', 'You\'ve gotta find fun where you\'re able to, y\'know? And sometimes that means… just getting up to a lil bit of mischief, you know? A little bit of harmless fun to distract you from the dullness of life! Meow! You gain access to the following **GOOD** SHENANIGANS effects:\r\n\r\n> **TOXOPLASMOSIS**: You scratch, bite, or otherwise unsanitarily attack them. They are **[Inept]** at **[Heal]** moves for **2 turns**, and take **1 less [Heal]** in this time.  \r\n\r\n> **I CAN HAS CHEEZBURGER**: Nom nom nom! If they use any food or **[Heal]** item in the next **3 turns**, you swipe and consume yourself.\r\n\r\n> **YOU KICK MIETTE??**: Oh my god. How could you do this? Your opponent takes **3 [Drag]** and is put in jail for A THOUSAND YEARS as you yowl and wail. ^;-;^\r\n\r\n> **BAP**: >:3c While maintaining eye contact and not giving a single shit what a mess you\'re making, you bap their weapon out of their hand and off the metaphorical table. They can\'t use ABSTRATA UPGRADES until they pick it up.\r\n\r\n> **NO TOUCH ONLY PET**: You crowd right up in your opponent\'s space, maybe turn around a few times. If they **[Flourish]** in the next **2 turns**, you make an immediate **[Free] [Reaction]** and **[Strife]** them.\r\n'),
('shineBright', 'SHINE BRIGHT', 'LIGHT', 'LIGHT', '[Aspect][Passive][Recharge: 2][Unlock: Light]', 'You’re very good at stuff that matters. Some might say it’s because you’re a pretty bright person with a firm grasp on science, history and academia; others might just call you lucky, untouchable by fate. You like to boil it down to a combination of the two, and call it destiny— and you’re destined for BIG things. You start every encounter with **2 [Boost]**; every time you get a **GREAT** roll, you gain an additional **[Boost]**- though there is a **[Recharge]** to how often you gain **[Boost]** this way.'),
('shippingChart', 'SHIPPING CHART', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Nyastrologist]', 'Shipping Charts are a common tool among Olives, but yours are more powerful than any other. Why? Because it\'s backed by SCIENCE. You\'ve gotten so good at figuring out who\'s compatible with you that you can now tell who would make good pairings out of your allies! Maybe make the chart before the encounter begins, cuz this will get messy. You give the following benefits to allies in combat, including yourself:\r\n\r\n> **COMPATIBLE**: Help each other through the power of cooperation! Any **[Boost]** one person gets is given to both.\r\n\r\n> **INCOMPATIBLE**: Great work, jerk! This is YOUR fault! Any **[Drag]** one person gets is halved, and given to both.'),
('shortLittleFucker', 'SHORT LITTLE FUCKER', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive]', 'Why are you so small? Huh? Why are you so little? You\'re not very big at all! You can fit into spots that you normally couldn\'t, such as a **[Vehicle]** with no more space left. **[Flying]** creatures can easily carry you. You\'re just… compact. You cannot have this move and EXCEPTIONALLY LARGE.'),
('shoulderToCryOn', 'SHOULDER TO CRY ON', 'LIFE', 'LIFE', '[Aspect][Basic][Mental][Locked: Life]\r\n', 'You’re very good at letting people vent out their problems to you; in fact, you’re so good at it that people seem to naturally gravitate to you to do it. Does this cause you stress? A little, sometimes. But if it helps your friends out..! As an action, you can remove an **[Emotion]** from an ally as you invite them to talk about it. This works even if you’re not their moirail; however, if you do it for someone who isn’t your moirail, you take **2 [Drag]**, because listening to other people’s problems can drain you a little. If you’re working with your moirail, calming them down is a **[Free]** action. \r\n'),
('shovelier', 'SHOVELIER', 'RUST', 'ADULT', '[Rust][Locked: Adult]\r\n', 'Did you know? Shovelier is actually an outdated term from a time when ships were powered by massive combustion drives, which Shoveliers were tasked to endlessly shovel coal into. Technical advancements have made this obsolete, and Shoveliers are now focused on energy maintenance, especially in crisis events. Because of this, you are well versed in noticing problems in machines and other delicate structures. Your **[Analyze]** rolls **[Tier Up]** against Robot enemies. Additionally, you can knock allies **[Floorbound]** as an action as you scoop them up and shovel them behind yourself with the shovels you receive as a mark of station. When they are rendered **[Floorbound]** this way, **[Strife]** rolls against them are **[Godawful]**. When allies are knocked **[Floorbound]** this way, they can get up as a **[Free]** action. You can only do this once per ally. \r\n'),
('showOfKindness', 'SHOW OF KINDNESS', 'LIFE', 'LIFE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Downtime][Locked: Life]\r\n', 'You’ve learned that the best way to get someone to work with you is to genuinely listen, rather than order them around. As a **[Downtime]** activity, you can invite someone to talk about their problems to you. If they accept, you learn more about them and what they\'re going through, which functions as the knowledge part of a GREAT RUMORHUNGER roll; on the other hand, your target feels refreshed, starting their next encounter with **2 [Boost]** and feeling **[Peaceful]**. Wow, it was nice to get that off their chest!\r\n');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('showtrialDrama', 'SHOWTRIAL DRAMA', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Passive][Unlock: Splattorney]', 'All trolls are guilty until proven innocent. Everyone loves a good true crime; and YOU are the entertainment star that presents criminals to the court, explains their crimes to a judge and has them punished. All in the name of reality TV! Of course, some boring trolls care about \"truth\" and \"integrity\", instead trying to defend the accused. Yawn. Either way, you are **[Talented]** at **+PLC**. You may, as an action, call together a SHOWTRIAL. All trolls present vote on whether they\'d like to enter the SHOWTRIAL or not. If at least 50% of all trolls present are in favour, a trial begins! All trolls are assigned a role in a SHOWTRIAL; select from the list below.\r\n\r\n> **LAWYERS**: There\'s usually just one, who has the goal of proving the DEFENDANT guilty. However, a second LAWYER may defend the DEFENDANT (cringe) and take their place and duties. LAWYERS may only roll WORDPLAY, **[Manipulate]** and **[Mental]** rolls. They can always roll to JAB. The goal is to reduce the DEFENDANT or the other LAWYER to **0 HP**; if you do, they are either executed, or pay a massive fine— see the JUDGE.\r\n\r\n> **DEFENDANT**: The dude on trial. They can only roll WORDPLAY, **[Manipulate]** and **[Mental]** rolls. If a Defense LAWYER is present, they sit there and whimper. They can only roll BANTER in this case, or use an action to give the LAWYER on their side access to any WORDPLAY effects they may have.\r\n\r\n> **JUDGE**: The Judge (usually the highestblood present or His Honourable Tyranny) watches both sides scrap it out, and decides who\'s being more entertaining each round. Once both sides\' turns have ended, the JUDGE picks a favourite from that round, giving them **1 [Boost]**. Once a side has been knocked to **0 HP**, the JUDGE decides a punishment; the PUNISHMENT TIME Affliction is VERY popular, but also fines, seizure of property or even removal from an ORG or tree if the situation might demand it. Fucked up! The JUDGE may also decide who in the trial did the best,and gives that person a reward— **Treasure III**!! This doesn\'t need to be a LAWYER.\r\n\r\n> **JURY: The audience, the people watching. After the judge makes a decision every round, they vote on whether to cheer or jeer. If they cheer, they increase the **[Boost]** the Judge gave by 1. If they jeer, they give the other side one **[Boost]**. LAWYERS may call upon individuals in the JURY to take the place of one of the LAWYERS on either side for **2 rounds**; the witness has the same HP as the LAWYER just did, but otherwise can use WORDPLAY and **[Mental]** rolls as normal. This effect has **[Recharge: 2]**, and takes an action.'),
('sicknastyMarksman', 'SICKNASTY MARKSMAN', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Flourish][Physical][Locked: Vagabond]', 'You didn’t make it this far by being the biggest or most powerful troll in a fight, but through cunning, not having qualms about what’s “fair” or “sporting”, and this totally rad trickshot you’ve been practicing. When you want to pull off a sick combat maneuver, roll **+RAS**. Each maneuver has the **[Recharge: 3]** tag.\n\n**MIN**: Ugh! You humiliated yourself, and you\'re really undermining anyone\'s ability to take you seriously! Your **[Flourish]** rolls are all **[Inept]** for the rest of the encounter.\n\n**BAD**: Mmgh… disappointment isn\'t the word. You take **2 [Drag]**.\n\n**OK**: You don\'t do what you intended, but your spirit shines through. This move does not gain **[Recharge: 3]** this turn. \n\n**GOOD**: Check this out! You\'ll give something to your fellow lowbloods to be proud about! Select one of the options below:\n\n> **DIVE**: Get down! You duck behind cover, allowing you to become **[Hidden]** for **2 rounds**. Rolling a **[Strife]** move after going **[Hidden]** this way does not remove the **[Hidden]** status early.\n\n> **DEADEYE**: You hold your breath, time slows down, and a chill wind rolls by. Your next **[Strife]** roll is **[Tiered Up]**, even to a **MAX**. \n\n> **DANGEROUS STUNT**: Boom! How do you like THAT, jerkwad? You muster up some courage and do something crazy, completely removing yourself from a **[Hazard]**! This doesn\'t work on weird magic stuff, obviously, but you CAN jump out a burning window!\n\n> **BRAG**: UWAHAHAHA! Nothing like a badass speech to get the engine revving. You become **[Proud]**.\n\n> **HECKLE**: Hey! Bulgebreath! Over here! You taunt the opponent to draw attention to yourself. The target’s next **[Strife]** roll **[Tiers Up]** against you, but **[Tiers Down]** against anyone else, even to a **MIN**.\n\n> **ELEVENTH HOUR**: No way are you going down here! You gain **1 [Hold]**; you can use this **[Hold]** as a **[Reaction]** when you\'re knocked **[Unconscious]** to stay at 1 HP instead. This is a **[One-Off]** and **[Buildup: 4]** effect. This is a **[Last Stand]** effect.\n\n**GREAT**: You do it, and you feel strong because of it. You get **1 [WHAM]** and a **GOOD** effect.\n\n**MAX**: The thrill of showing off your strength thoroughly empowers you. You get a **GREAT**, and all your **[Recharges]** reset to 0.'),
('sidesOfGrumblr', 'SIDES OF GRUMBLR', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Passive][Locked: Fanyatic]', 'Fandom is only part of what you do with your time. After all, it\'s all thanks to the world wide web that fandom can exist, and you spend ALL your time on your blog! Gotta rake up those notes, right? Select your favourite thing to do online, and gain the associated benefit!\r\n\r\n> **ART**: You make art, ranging from grungey photoshoots to fancomics based on obscure video game ships to pencil drawings of your lusus. When someone on the field gains an **[Emotion]**, you may spend a **[Reaction]** to pull out some art. Roll 1d8; on an Odd you swap the emotion for its opposite; on an Even, their emotion is **[Heightened]** and you gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **CODING**: You are CONSTANTLY making blog themes and making shit look nice and pretty. That somehow made the jump into actual hacking. All **[Tech]** moves use **+RAS** for you, and you may take a PERFECTLY GENERIC MOVE with the **[Tech]** tag now.\r\n\r\n> **MISINFORMATION**: Did you know? You love giving out fun trivia to everyone! Learning is great! Thanks, science side of Grumblr! When someone rolls an **[Analyze]** roll around you, they must roll 1d8. On a 1 or an 8, you can choose to get the effects of their move instead and give them wildly inaccurate intel.\r\n\r\n> **MEMES**: Oh boy, you sure crave minerals! Yee! Take a closer look at that snout! ENPECE, YOUR STICKS! You can roll **[Chicanery]** twice in the same turn.\r\n\r\n> **REBLOOPING**: That\'s a pretty nice post. Be a shame if somebody… reblogged it with an unnecessary caption like \"THIS\" or \"SPREAD THIS LIKE WILDFIRE\". On a **[Recharge: 3]**, you may use a **[Reaction]** to make the exact same roll with the exact same effects and exact same target as someone else. \r\n\r\n> **SHIPPING**: You don\'t exactly get all the astrology stuff, but you like knowing which characters should kiss! You gain the ZODIAC CAT Nyastrologist move, but no other moves from that tree.'),
('signatureLaugh', 'SIGNATURE LAUGH', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Reaction][Manipulate][Locked: Bully]', 'YOU CALL THAT A PUNCH? WAHAHAHA! Choose a signature laugh; when someone fails a roll against you, you let that laugh out, and the opponent gets a specific effect. You gotta use the laugh, or it doesn\'t count!\r\n\r\n> **MYAHAHA!** A dainty villain\'s laugh! What a little man your opponent is, compared to you! Your target loses all **[Boost]**, or they take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> **CHAWHAWHAW!** A bellowing chortle, like an ogre mocking its lunch. You gain **1 [Resistance]** to all damage from them for **two turns**.\r\n\r\n> **YAHAHAH!** Your laugh is like a cry of victory! You lose all **[Drag]**, or gain **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **Pfft.** Your laugh is pretty low-key, making the target feel like they can\'t even fail right! The target is **[Overwhelmed]** with a feeling of failure for **two turns**.\r\n\r\n> **HARHARHAR!** Your laugh is raw and LOADED with a mocking energy. You stupid moron! Your target can\'t gain any **[Boost]** or positive **[Emotions]** for **3 turns**!\r\n\r\n> **SOMETHING ELSE**: A WAHAHA? A NYOHOHO, maybe! Perhaps even a KEKEKEKE? Your laugh isn\'t any of the above, but you still need to pick one out! Your target is **[Stunned]** as you point and laugh at them!'),
('silverTongue', 'SILVER TONGUE', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive]', 'Not everyone has a tongue that can weave a tale as good as you. Not everyone lives long enough to learn enough TO weave those tales. The exact kind of verbal tutelage you\'ve received from life experience that\'s given you the illustrious title of having a silver tongue changes caste to caste, but one thing is shared: you\'re a little more suave than most people! You gain the following **GOOD** WORDPLAY effect based on your caste.\r\n\r\n> **RUST**: You\'ve perfected the art of the butlerspeak. You can give a target the **[Smug]** Emotion for **1 turn** as having someone kiss ass goes to their head.\r\n\r\n> **BRONZE**: Darn tootin, seems somebody needs some stereotypical farmhand talk. You can give a target a **+1 [Buff]** to **[Craft]** rolls for a turn- maybe with advice, or maybe just because what you said SOUNDS like advice. \r\n\r\n> **GOLD**: >PWNED >OWNED >LOL. You greentext irl, sadly. You can give a target some pretty bad advice from 4chan, and a **-1 [Nerf]** to **+PLC** rolls for a turn.\r\n\r\n> **LIME**: Being a myth has advantages sometimes. You can give a target insight of what they could never understand, letting them get a **[Free]** PROBLEM SLEUTHING question.\r\n\r\n> **OLIVE**: Rawr! Grr! You\'ve spent a lot of time in the wild and getting sick, or at least watching documentaries. You can give a target some guidance on avoiding a **[Rapid]** **[Affliction]**\'s worst bits, giving them a **+1 [Buff]** to their next check.\r\n\r\n> **JADE**: Ask your father, darling. Mother\'s busy. As a **[Reaction]**, you may redirect a **[Manipulate]** attempt onto someone else in the encounter.\r\n\r\n> **TEAL**: Hey, pay this fine. That bike isn\'t registered. You can give a target a fine and repossess one of their items in their Sylladex valued no higher than **3 VP**. The maximum value increases to 4 **VP** for a **GREAT** and 6 **VP** on a **MAX**. You gain the item for the Encounter.\r\n\r\n> **CERULEAN**: HEY. HEY. PAY ATTENTION. HEY. YOU\'RE COOL. You can force a target to focus entirely on you for **1 turn**, not allowing them to roll anything that doesn\'t target you.\r\n\r\n> **INDIGO**: You believe it\'s time for a debate, good sir. You can force a target to roll a **[Free]** competing **+PSP** check against you for a quick debate on a topic, dealing **1 [Verbal]** damage and **2 [Drag]** to the loser as a **[Strife]** action. On a tie, reroll.\r\n\r\n> **PURPLE**: Hey homie. Have you heard the word? You can give a target the good message of the Church, which translates into either a **+1 [Buff]** for a turn to **[Purple]** moves if they are a clown or a **-1 [Nerf]** for a turn to **+RAS** to anyone else, as they realize that clowning around is a clown\'s turf.\r\n\r\n> **VIOLET**: Hey, out of the way! Monarch coming through. You can remind a target of exactly who you are, giving the target a **[Hold]** they can use as a **[Reaction]** to improve one of your rolls by +2 later. Bootlicker.'),
('simpleDeduction', 'SIMPLE DEDUCTION', 'MIND', 'MIND', '[Aspect][Unlock: Mind]', 'The world around you can easily be broken down into simple pieces, like a jigsaw puzzle; with some careful thought, you’re able to put these pieces together. Any time you make a **GREAT** **[Analyze]** roll, you can gain one of the following effects of your choosing:\r\n\r\n> **1 [WHAM]** as you act fast to shut the problem down.\r\n> **[Tier Up]** your next PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll.\r\n> **2 [Drag]** and 1 extra action as you panic and act fast.'),
('slapstickyMischief', 'SLAPSTICKY MISCHIEF', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Open][Chicanery]', 'You\'re the biggest! Or the smallest? You\'re the baddest! Or perhaps the funniest? You\'re basically motherfuckin\' here to have a good time. :o) And your good time is reliant on everyone else having a worse time, amen brother. You love bullying people with your freaky clown powers and making everyone a little on edge! You gain access to the following **GOOD** SHENANIGANS effects: \r\n\r\n> **SCRUFF**: You pick \'em up by the scruff like a naughty cat and give \'em a little wiggle. Haha, tiny lowerblood go brr. They take a **-3 [Nerf]** to **+RAS** rolls for **2 rounds**. If you use this on a violet, they get a **-4 [Nerf]** instead as the sheer indignity short circuits their snobby fish brains. \r\n\r\n> **PIE TO THE FACE**: Smush! HAH! They look so funny all stickied up and **[Tired]** from all the sopor you just smashed all up in their orifices. It takes **2 turns** for this effect to fade away.\r\n\r\n> **SURPRISE BAPTISM**: Welcome to the fold, sibling! You pull out the water, faygo, public fountain, or nearby bucket of paint and give them a good old fashioned impromptu baptism, leaving them EXCEPTIONALLY sticky. For **2 turns**, they must roll 1d8 whenever making a move; on a 1 or 2, the move becomes **[Lengthy]** if it\'s their first roll on the turn or **[Stunning]** them on their next turn if it\'s their second roll. It\'s so sticky! Bweh!\r\n\r\n> **WHEEEEEEE!** They slip on a banana peel! They get launched out of a cannon! Something! Either way, the target is **[Flying]** for a turn. Seeya!'),
('slapThat', 'SLAP THAT', 'OTHER', 'QUADRANT', '[Quadrant][Passive]\r\n', 'Welcome to kismesissitude, where the bickering is constant and you\'ll (hopefully) never quite find a way to cull them no matter how stupid you find their face. The longer your rivalry goes on, the more creative you\'re forced to get to keep fighting them - and the more you fight them, the more you know how they work. \r\n\r\n**NEW QUADS (1-4 IRL WEEKS)**: Your attacks against them are at a **-1 [Nerf]**. When you fight someone else alongside them, you gain **1 [Boost]** every **3 rounds** as you work together. \r\n\r\n**ESTABLISHED RELATIONSHIP (1-11 IRL MONTHS)**: Your attacks against them are at a **-2 [Nerf]**. When you fight someone else alongside them, you gain **1 [Boost]** every **2 rounds** as you work together in sync. \r\n\r\n**ROCK SOLID (1 YEAR+)**: Your attacks against them **[Tier Down]** as they learn everything about how you fight. When you fight someone else alongside them, you gain **1 [Boost]** every round as you work together in sync. \r\n\r\n**QUAD BONDED**: They have **1 [Resistance]** to all damage inflicted by you, but when you fight together, you gain **1 [WHAM]** every **2 rounds** as you move in perfect sync without having to think about it.\r\n'),
('slashionista', 'SLASHIONISTA', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Passive][Ultra][Locked: Subcultist]', 'You are known far and wide for your innovative style, your fuck-you attitude, and your tremendous feats in service of your subculture. Some whisper that you slew a cholerbear who dissed your taste in music. Others can recognize you merely by your iconic silhouette. You\'re kind of a big deal in your subculture, even if it\'s… underground. Eh? Eh? Anyway, you gain access to HERO MODE through the stat you are **[Talented]** in; this changes if you are wearing an ASS-KICKING OUTFIT. Most importantly, however, is your own contributions to the scene. You are a pioneer of your own personal style, merging in the looks of another subculture into your own. Maybe you\'re mixing Punk and Goth to make the new Gonk movement, or Metalheads and Decora to truly stan Wrigglermetal. You gain the item of a second Subculture, but not the **[Talent]**. This gives you access to that Subcultures FASHION STATEMENTS, ASS-KICKING OUTFITS, and SYSTEM SMASHER benefits, giving you even greater flexibility in your presentation. You are truly ready for ANYTHING.'),
('slayersTricks', 'SLAYER\'S TRICKS', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Recharge: 1][Flourish][Physical][Locked: Slayer]', 'Hook shot! Okay, they\'re stunned. Now wave dash, wave dash, I\'m wide open, you\'re dogwater, GRUB CRUCIFIX TO THE FACE, THAT\'S A K.O. BABY! You have trained in the classic creature hunting techniques from anime and video games. It\'s surprisingly accurate and well-researched, and most veteran Slayers recommend studying RAINBOW HUNTER X4: SHADOW OF LUST as your first step into hunting. When you want to slaaaaay, roll **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Now YOU are dogwater. The opponent may make a **[Free]** **[Strife]** roll against you. It\'s **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Still dogwater. The opponent may make a **[Free]** **[Strife]** roll against you.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Maybe just regular water? Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: \"GOOD\" isn\'t good enough. Will it be \"good\" if you don\'t act at your peak when being chased by seven vampyres? You may reroll this move with a **+2 [Buff]** for **[Free]** once; if you get another **GOOD**, it becomes an **OK**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: HOLY WATER! Choose an effect from below.\r\n\r\n> **WHIPCRACK**: Even if it\'s not your Strife Specibus, you always carry a whip to crack at opponents to keep them back. BACK, YOU SAY! **[Strife]** rolls against you are at a **-2 [Nerf]** next turn.\r\n\r\n> **FEND OFF**: You prepare to catch the opponent with a counterattack, grabbing them by the jaws as they bite you and fighting back. If someone does successfully hit you next turn, they take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> **WALLRUN**: Goddamn. You Naruto Run all over these walls, jumping and clamouring all over the place. You are **[Quickened]** and **[Flying]** for a turn, either this turn or next.\r\n\r\n> **EXPLODE INTO A CLOUD OF BATS AT THE LAST SECOND LEAVING THE TARGET LO**OK**ING AROUND ALL CONFUSED AS YOUR LAUGH ECHOES**: It was actually that you tossed a sweet runestone with a magic illusion etched into it at their feet. You get **1 [Hold]**; this **[Hold]** lets you **[Tier Down]** an opponent\'s **[Strife]** roll. You immediately become **[Hidden]** when you use this **[Hold]**. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: Great heavens!! You blend techniques! Select two options, and use them both!'),
('sleekWeaponry', 'SLEEK WEAPONRY', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Nyanjutsu]', 'Schwing… your weapons are ESPECIALLY dangerous. After all… they\'re intended to bring quick and efficient DEATH to those you battle! GO, BLAZING-GASH-STAR SHURIKEN! You can add up to 3 ABSTRATA UPGRADES to one weapon. You gain one for free now.'),
('sleepMode', 'SLEEP MODE', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Passive][Psionic]', 'Your psionic powers mean you can keep going, even after you fall asleep! When you become **[Tired]** or **[Exhausted]**, you can choose to enter SLEEP MODE. While on SLEEP MODE, you levitate a foot off the floor, and all your **[Mental]** moves are **[Godawful]**. If you\'re **[Exhausted]**, you can\'t roll them at all! However, any **[Physical]** moves become **[Psionic]**, and automatically get a **GOOD** result as your dreaming state knocks shit around. If you are awoken by a loud noise or a **MAX** **[Physical]** roll, you can\'t enter SLEEP MODE again. You are immune to **[Manipulate]** moves in this state.'),
('sleightOfHand', 'SLEIGHT OF HAND', 'OTHER', 'ROGUE', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Rogue]', 'You\'ve got just the thing, and you can get it where it needs to be and to who it needs to be with- fast. Old timey misdirection and fast talking, daring midnight sprints over rooftops, just throwing a Medicalizer at someone\'s head; you know all the tricks. Using anything from your sylladex is a **[Free]** action for you, or one action for a **[Lengthy]**, as is handing it to anyone who might need it. One Medicalizer coming up!'),
('slowAndSteady', 'SLOW AND STEADY', 'SPACE', 'SPACE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Space]', 'You’ve found that you produce your best works when you work reliably rather than quickly. There really is no rush— so why torture yourself about it? Do it well, and do it right. Whenever you are **[Slowed]**, all your rolls **[Tier Up]**, even to a **MAX**. If you use INDECISIVE DECISION while **[Slowed]**, your results are **GREAT**.'),
('slpathwatapThat', 'SLPATHWATAP THAT', 'OTHER', 'QUADRANT', '[Quadrant][Passive]\r\n', 'You\'re vacillating. Please gog just sit down and have a conversation. Get an ashen. I\'m begging you. Your friends are begging you. You can\'t keep having knock down drag out fights in the city center and then papping in the fountain after, PLEASE-\r\n\r\n**NEW UNQUADS (1-4 IRL WEEKS)**: Awww. It\'s a little rocky right now, but you\'ll sort this out. You have the **[Hopeful]** condition in any encounter with your soon-to-be-settled quadrant :)\r\n\r\n**ESTABLISHED LACK OF RELATIONSHIP (1-11 IRL MONTHS)**: Any encounter you share with your ???????mate, you have the **[Confused]** Emotion. \r\n\r\n**ROCK SOLID????? (1 YEAR+)**: Your ashmates begin each of their threads with **-1 HP** from the permanent **[Psychic]** damage you\'re doing to them. Look at them. Look at the consequences of your actions. Any encounter you share with your ???????mate, you have the **[Dumbfounded]** Emotion. \r\n\r\n**QUAD BONDED**: Why did you quad bond when you\'re vacillating. Your PSP drops to 0, and if it was already 0, it drops to -1. Why are you like this?'),
('slumblood', 'SLUMBLOOD', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Passive][Unlock: Gutterblood]', 'Whelp! There\'s literally nowhere lower for you, is there? You are the absolute lowest on the hemospectrum, the gum on the shoe of Alternia. You\'re a lowblood with little to no psionics, no stable job to make highbloods consider not killing you, and no real prospects either. Basically, you\'re living garbage. If you got blown up, nobody would care. And in a weird way… that\'s kind of okay by you. You\'ve grown used to living among garbage, and can\'t imagine living like those stuffy highbloods. You are **[Talented]** at **+APP** because you just won\'t give up and die, no matter what. Your Wealth level is **Destitute**, not **Poor**. Not that it matters. You make do with what you\'ve got! You have access to any item up to the **Well-Off** Wealth threshold, with the exception that it\'s literally garbage you pulled from the trash. Every time you activate an item, there\'s a chance it falls apart. Roll 1d8; on a 1 or a 2, the item breaks after usage. Oops! You can\'t help but chuckle when this happens though, giving you **1 [Boost]**. **[Big Buys]** do not reduce your Wealth Level, though they do look noticeably shoddy; they break on a 1, 2 or 3. You can still garner **LUX** to craft together garbage Vehicles or Hivecrafting Upgrades. What can you say? Who needs treasure when there\'s all this trash lying around?\r\n\r\n'),
('smashYourToys', 'SMASH YOUR TOYS', 'RAGE', 'RAGE', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Rage]', 'You don’t really give that much of a shit about the collateral when you go on your rage sprees; in fact, it’s honestly pretty gratifying to destroy. You get a kick out of breaking stuff, to the point that it’s borderline cruel at times. Any time you destroy an item, you gain **2 [Boost]**.'),
('smellEmotions', 'SMELL EMOTIONS', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Passive]', 'Sniff sniff… hmmm… is that joy? Hatred? Fear, perhaps? Oh, yes all those ambitions and dreams and phobias, you can smell them from miles away. You have the peculiar, probably magic ability to literally smell the emotions of others. Usually fear. Especially fear. Something something SMELL THE FEAR OF YOUR ENEMIES something something TRACK THEM TO THE ENDS OF ALTERNIA. Maybe you just like how people\'s tears smell, though. Or their laughs! Who knows. Point is, your **[Analyze]** rolls against targets with an Emotion condition are **[Tiered Up]**, and their ABSCOND rolls are **[Tiered Down]**.'),
('smite', 'SMITE', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Physical][Strife][Locked: Paladin]', 'Evildoers beware! You wield a mighty weapon, and you know how to use it! You punish the wicked with your STRONG sense of justice, making sure nobody ever crosses you again! When you want to smite some bitches, roll **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: SELF-SMITE! You dishonourable fiend! You give the opponent **3 [Hold]** they can immediately use right back at you. You also take **2 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You look stupid in that ridiculous outfit. You know that, right? You take **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**OK**: A valiant effort! You take 1 **[Hold]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Cleft in twain! Your sword cuts through the opponent, and also their very heart! Metaphorically! You do **1 [Somatic]** damage and gain **1 [Hold]**. You can spend **[Holds]** on the following as a **[Free]** action as part of this attack. \r\n\r\n> **EGO**: You cleave their vanity! **1 [Hold]** becomes **1 [Drag]** you give to your opponent. You can stack this up to 5 times.\r\n\r\n> **VIGOUR**: You slice their stamina to pieces! **2 [Holds]** spent means the target cannot **[Heal]** for **2 turns**. \r\n\r\n> **ADVANTAGE**: You cut right through the edge in the fight they\'ve got! **3 [Hold]** removes an enemy **[Emotion]**. This only reduces **[Heightened]** **[Emotions]** by a Stage.\r\n\r\n> **MAGIC**: You scramble their chakras with a well timed blow. **4 [Holds]** disables all **[Psionic]** and **[Magic]** effects for **3 turns**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: SUFFER, FIEND! You do **2 [Somatic]** damage, and gain **1 [Hold]**; 2 if it\'s an enemy outlined by the oath you chose in OATHKEEPER.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: BISECTION IN THE NAME OF ALTERNIA, MOTHERFUCKER! HRRRAAAAH! You do **3 [Somatic]** damage (4 if it\'s an enemy outlined in the oath you chose in OATHKEEPER) and gain **2 [Hold]** (3 if it\'s an enemy outlined in… you know the rest)'),
('smuglugger', 'SMUGLUGGER', 'OTHER', 'ADULT', '[Cullbait][Locked: Adult]', 'Youth on Alternia only very rarely get the opportunity to see adults in-person. Most commonly, they\\\'ll see Imperial figureheads; however, the very rare anti-Imperial spaceship will make it down to the planet to smuggle lusii off-planet and transport cullbait kids to somewhere where they won\\\'t be, like, culled. YOU are the troll inspiring fear, awe and even hope in the eyes of young Alternians. If you had 10 or less **VP** without this move, you gain 2 **VP** from sylladex upgrades, and you also gain access to the following unique VP items:\n\n> **? VP - A LITERAL PERSON**: You can captchalogue non-Imperial NPCs of your choice for 2 **VP** per level- no better place than your literal sylladex to keep them away from prying eyes! As an action, you can deploy any NPC - they use any one move they have access to of your choice, triggering **[Recharges]** as per the usual if you also have the move, and then **ABSCOND** automatically. These are just civilians you\\\'re transporting to safety, after all! You can also captchalogue willing allies in combat as an action if you have 2 extra **VP**; while captchalogued, they cannot take any actions, but also cannot be damaged in any way. Take shelter under my wing as I guide you to a brighter future!\n\n> **4 VP - BACKUP HOTLINE**: Smugluggers need connections to survive, and you\\\'ve got your share. When you\\\'re in a pinch, you may call this hotline as a **[One-Off]** action - at the start of your next turn, a rebel-aligned **ANGRY MOB** appears. You and your allies\\\' rolls to **ABSCOND [Tier Up]** while the mob\\\'s active, as the other rebels help you rush away to safety.'),
('snazzardRider', 'SNAZZARD RIDER', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Passive][Unlock: Draquestrian]', 'In ancient times, the Teal caste were the keepers of Snazzards, draconic titans that breathe justice upon enemies of the Empire as their finest cavalry. Naturally, this stopped being a widespread practice when Snazzards were replaced by the much more efficient drone armada. The practice still exists, however… in the form of dragon jockeys. You are a Draquestrian, a Teal fortunate enough to have made a soul bond with their Snazzardic Lusus. Whether the Snazzard is an armless Snyvern, a bestial Sndrake or a mighty Crested Snagon is up to you. You and your Snazzard are **[Talented]** at **+HUB**. Your Snazzard usually counts as a Small Vehicle with 4 HORSEPOWER. You may choose larger sizes for the vehicle stats here, but remember it\'ll drop your HORSEPOWER, and a SMALL Vehicle isn\'t a SMALL Lusus! You get **2 LUX** worth of upgrades to your Snazzard, but cannot upgrade it beyond that. It automatically has the FLYING or AQUATIC upgrades for free. Additionally, your Snazzard gets its own Statblock as if it were a separate troll, and tracks **[One-Off]**, **[Recharge]**, etc. separately to you. While it tracks all conditions and effects separately to you, it can only use Universal moves or ones it gains in this tree. On your turn, you can choose whether to roll your own move or your Snazzards, or even both— but you still only get 2 actions total, as normal, and you can still only roll moves with tags like **[Strife]** or **[Chicanery]** once per turn. You both use the same HP, using the rider\'s HP rather than the Snazzard\'s.'),
('snazzviator', 'SNAZZVIATOR', 'TEAL', 'ADULT', '[Teal][Locked: Adult]', 'Anyone showing high aptitude in operating vehicles may be granted ownership of one of The Empire’s esteemed Snazzcrafts. You are a Snazzviator, and using your power orb charged spacecraft you rise to the task of dominating the skies of Troll colonies. You and your ship are there to lead yourself, and those at lower ranks, to eliminate any unwanted fauna that may prove devastating to global conquest. Including people. How\\\'s that for an invasive species? Upon taking this move, you gain a special Tiny SPACESHIP now for free. Instead of having 4 **HP** it has 10 **HP** and all your rolls while flying it are **[Talented]**. Finally, this ship has the following exclusive DRIVE pre-installed into it:\n\n> **POWER ORB DRIVE**: Your ship is fueled by a super charged power orb. This is a method that only works because of how small your ship is. Snazzcrafts can also be powered by the eggs of mighty snazzards! But it’s not wildly done because... Well, you try taking an egg from a mother snazzard, buddy. All your **STARSTEER** rolls **[Tier Up]** even to a **MAX**.'),
('snitchblood', 'SNITCHBLOOD', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Tech]', 'You\'ve long been raised to see the laws of Alternia as totally just. This means that you’re a spineless whelp, and you have no shame. Fuck you, bulgelicker. Bootsucker. Stinky. You can call the drones to an encounter and have them wreak havoc on the people you’re ratting out, you pathetic little weasel. You pull out your phone and call down a DRONE STRIKE **[Hazard]**, you fucking nookworm. You are more likely than not caught in the crossfire.'),
('socialChameleon', 'SOCIAL CHAMELEON', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Passive]', 'Being a Cerulean is… difficult. You try SO HARD to always act like you’re the best, but you’re filled with this overwhelming inadequacy all the same. As such, many Ceruleans try to prove their awesomeness… by taking other caste roles and being better than them. NICE STREAM, GOLDY! WANNA SEE MINE?! Hey, you a scientist? I’M A BETTER SCIENTIST! Of course, despite everything, you never can seem to outdo the others… you can take any tree accessible through the ALTERNATE PATH Perfectly Generic Move (see Chapter 5: PERFECTLY GENERIC MOVES) as a **[Template]**. However, you can only take the **[Entry]** and **2 [Basic]** moves, and you do not gain the **[Talent]** from the **[Entry]** in this way. If you want to really double down, you can use your second **[Template]** slot to also gain access to 2 **[Advanced]** moves and even the **[Ultra]**, but doing so makes you more susceptible to breakdowns; whenever you become **[Stressed]**, you immediately become **[Agitated]** instead as your inferiority complex kicks into overdrive. Moves you take through this **[Template]** cost 2 levels, not 1. You gain the **[Entry]** now. You can\'t take both this move and ALTERNATE PATH.'),
('socialMalnourishment', 'SOCIAL MALNOURISHMENT', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Your private schoolfeeding has left your social skills… stunted. Or at least, it’s made it so that talking to people outside those you were schooled alongside you a little difficult. But at least you know how to conjugate verbs, haha! **[Manipulate]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**, because you struggle to pick up on the exact connotations of certain forms of speaking not common to your caste. Mostly insults.'),
('soldShort', 'SOLD SHORT', 'BREATH', 'BREATH', '[Aspect][Basic][Free][Recharge: 3][Locked: Breath]', 'You? Oh, no, you could never accomplish something like that. You’re too… you to do it. And that doesn’t bother you much! You have a habit of underestimating your own potential, seeing yourself as a totally ordinary person. Every once in a while, you can depreciate yourself and second guess your skills for **[Free]**, only for your next roll to **[Tier Up]**. You react in mild surprise, and then sum it up as a huge fluke instead of giving yourself any credit.'),
('solidarityOfTheDamned', 'SOLIDARITY OF THE DAMNED', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Passive]', 'By now, you may have met your fair share of monsters, and… you\'ve probably learned that they aren\'t all as bad as the caves have long painted them. They\'re victims in their own right, you know? Whether you\'ve studied them as a hunter of the night, learned their aesthetics for your fashion, or just have a few mortally challenged friends… you know now that you shouldn\'t judge a beast by the legends told about them. Your **[Analyze]** rolls against **[Eerie]** trolls are **[Tiered Up]**, and whenever you would become **[Scared]** because of an **[Eerie]** troll, you feel **[Hopeful]** instead; maybe there\'s a way you can help them.'),
('solsticialize', 'SOLSTICIALIZE', 'OTHER', 'WYLDERDRUID', '[Template][Basic][Magic][Strife][Locked: Wylderdruid]', 'If you want nature to cooperate with you, you cannot attempt to change the way life flows within time. Like the trees and weather around you, your magic changes with the seasons. When you want to wreck shit with the elemental power of Alternia’s seasons, roll **+IMG** and select the result corresponding to the real-life season you’re currently in.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Aw, nutballs! Nature was doing just fine without you and you’ve seriously overextended your welcome. A personal rain cloud appears over your head, exposing you and you alone to the **[Rainstorm] HAZARD** for 3 rounds.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You just bored yourself half to death thinking really hard about the fucking weather. You become **[Tired]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Maybe a leaf or two flutters when you try to move it… or maybe that was just the wind. Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: A flurry of elemental phenomena whips around your hands. Take the relevant result depending on your season:\r\n\r\n> **SUMMER**: Your harness a flicker of the sun’s overbearing light. Deal 1 **[Blaze] [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n> **FALL**: The stinging force of Alternian acid rain pelts your opponent. Deal 1 **[Acid] [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n> **WINTER**: Jacque Fraust is nipping at your enemy’s nose. You deal 1 **[Frost] [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n> **SPRING**: Invisible seeds germinate and your opponent coughs up flower petals.  You deal 1 **[Holy] [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: This is more than just a flicker of elemental power, now - you’re the center of your own mini storm. Take the relevant result depending on your season:\r\n\r\n> **SUMMER**: You radiate a harsh, dry heat that could bleach bones. You deal 2 **[Blaze] [Somatic]** damage, or 1 and your target is set **[Ablaze]**.\r\n\r\n> **FALL**: Your opponent… falls! This is a funny pun. Deal 2 **[Acid] [Somatic]** damage, or 1 and you **[Floorbound]** your target.\r\n\r\n> **WINTER**: Magic snowball fight! Deal 2 **[Frost] [Somatic]** damage, or 1 and you **[Slow]** your target for a turn.\r\n\r\n> **SPRING**: Plants grow to bloom in a matter of seconds, entangling your enemy’s legs. Deal 2 **[Holy] [Somatic]** damage, or 1 and you **[Trap]** your target.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You’ve harnessed a maelstrom. Take a **GREAT** result, except your damage is increased by 1.\r\n'),
('someAssemblyRequired', 'SOME ASSEMBLY REQUIRED', 'OTHER', 'BLIGHTSMITH', '[Template][Basic][Downtime][Unlock: Blightsmith]', 'So you’ve got time to kill, but not too much time? Whether or not you’re working towards a big project or aiming to go out and get in a fight, you’ll probably need some weapons before making the real deal. When you want to make an unhardened weapon, roll **+GRT**. Though be advised, any weapons made will break after 3 encounters, and once they break- they’re gone for good!\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Oh man, you completely, royally fucked this one up. You actually embarrassed yourself to a level thought completely unattainable before, as a professional. Your next roll of this move is **[Inept]**. This sucks.\r\n\r\n> **BAD**: Fuck! You spill metal all over the floor. You lose 2 **LUX** in the process.\r\n\r\n> **OK**: You don’t manage to make anything this time, but you organize your forge. It’s better than before! The next time you roll this downtime, it **[Tiers Up]**.\r\n\r\n> **GOOD**: Aha, now we’re getting somewhere. You make a weapon with a random abstrata. Go to Section 26: Abstrata Upgrades, roll 3d8 and subtract 2 from the total. Count down the list of Abstrata until you reach the number from the roll result- that’s the Abstrata you choose. This costs 2 **LUX** to make. If you don’t have enough **LUX**, it does nothing.\r\n\r\n> **GREAT**: Behold, a proper weapon! You make a weapon with two Abstrata. The first is randomly chosen, and the second is your choice. This costs 4 **LUX** to make, because you’re effectively getting double the product in this bad boy.\r\n\r\n> **MAX**: Holy fuck!! You’re literally the best Blightsmith this side of Gulchscourge, or wherever you live. You make a weapon with 2 Abstrata, but both are your choice! The combinations are endless. This costs 4 **LUX** to make.\r\n'),
('soporState', 'SOPOR STATE', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Ah… Sopor. Bedding. Numbing agent. And comfort food. This congealed lime slime is particularly sought after by the Juggalo religion, as consuming it can bring you closer to all those sweet miracles out there in the world. It\'s probably not good for you, but your church says it\'s important, and you just kinda go with it. When you consume HIGH QUALITY FUNJUNK (SOPOR) Precaptchalogues, you don\'t need to roll; you can choose to automatically fail against the INEBRIATION **[Affliction]**. Additionally, as well as making you **[Peaceful]** and **[Serene]**, it opens you to a whole new world of MIRACLES. On STAGE 2 of the INEBRIATION **[Affliction]**, **[Magic]** or **[Psionic]** rolls against you are **[Inept]** and **[Tiered Down]**, even if they normally couldn\'t be. Your brain becomes **[Confused]** as you become dizzy. Consume Sopor responsibly!'),
('soSoSoSoSoSoSoGreatSoCoolSoGreat', 'SO SO SO SO SO SO SO GREAT SO COOL SO GREAT', 'OTHER', 'TRICKSTER', '[Template][Advanced][One-Off][Eerie][Locked: Trickster]', 'YOU’RE FEELING SO AMAZING RIGHT NOW!! In fact, that\'s pretty much all you feel anymore- and you feel your happiest when things are HAPPENING ALL THE TIME ALWAYS CONSTANTLY. Your desire for more and more serotonin-inducing chaos causes reality to make this round more interesting. Roll a 1d8, if you roll an ODD number, all rolls this round are **MIN**. If you roll an EVEN number, all rolls this round are **MAX**, and you may call upon the Confectionerrors to rain down a HAZARD of your choice. \n\n'),
('spaceCase', 'SPACE CASE', 'SPACE', 'SPACE', '[Aspect][Unlock: Space]', 'You’re an astronaut! And you spend all your time exploring the deep, vast expanses of the endless space that lies… in your mind. To call you detached from reality would be unfair; you’re just more of a dreamer, enjoying life without any real direction in mind. Why not just float here for a while…? What’s the rush? When someone manages to successfully **[Manipulate]** you, you can choose to misinterpret their meaning as something more literal or something more abstract; you are compelled to do this, rather than what they might have specifically meant. Oh, you wanted me to get out of your way? Must be because you’re trying to get somewhere fast… here, I’ll stick by you, and clear other obstacles from your path, being careful to stay hidden so I’m not in your way either.'),
('speakToMe', 'SPEAK TO ME', 'OTHER', 'DECOMPOSITIONIST', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Decompositonist]', 'In your line of work you\'ve encountered many a restless soul searching for peace. While you aren\'t always able to lay them to rest right then, the ones whose suffering you\'re able to ease until they are finally ready to pass on into the silence of the Great Oblivion may return to you and whisper secrets, allies in your struggle for a better final days. Ghosts inherently don\'t attempt to attack you, unless you otherwise provoke them; if a player-controlled Ghost attempts to harm you before you\'ve harmed them, their rolls are **[Godawful]**. NPC Ghosts never attack you first. Your rolls to stave off the PARANORMAL ACTIVITY **[Hazard]** are **+PLC** as you try to talk them down.\n\n'),
('spidergang', 'SPIDERGANG', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Delinquent]', 'Delinquency loves company! You\'ve earned enough street cred by now to start your own gang, a place where rough and tough bastards can come hang out, and maybe team up if they wanna stab someone a lot. Anyone can join your gang, but YOU are the boss, so they need YOUR permission to join. Be sure to give your gang a hardcore name and vibe! As the gang leader, you boss around all the others; your **[Manipulate]** rolls are **[Tiered Up]**. Additionally, you have a sweet GANG HIDEOUT, an abandoned hive you\'ve taken as your own. All HIVECRAFTING and VEHICLE purchases in the GANG HIDEOUT are at a 50% discount, and anyone can benefit from these items. Finally, your gang gets access to the following TEAM STRIFE moves, which you can use as long as there\'s at least one other gang member present.\r\n\r\n> **GANG UP**: YEAH, YEAH, FUCK YOU! This variation of FINISHING BLOW SWASHBUCKLE allows all trolls to **[Strife]** the opponent STRUGGLER, even though you normally can\'t. Afterwards, nobody on the team can make a **[Strife]** roll for 3 rounds.\r\n\r\n> **HECKLE**: You mock someone with your friends, making the target feel worse for longer. This WORDPLAY roll stops a target\'s temporary **[Emotion]** timer from ticking down this turn.\r\n\r\n> **AVENGE!**: THEY HURT YOUR BOY! GET \'EM! When you become the STRUGGLER after the last STRUGGLER ABDICATED, you get a **+1 [Buff]** to your first **[Strife]** roll as the new STRUGGLER. This becomes a **+2 [Buff]** if the opponent team has attempted to ANNEX the STRUGGLER! This is a **[Free]** move.\r\n\r\n**STEAL**: NICE WALLET DIPSHIT! At the end of a TEAM STRIFE, you gain **1 extra LUX** if you win.'),
('spiralOut', 'SPIRAL OUT', 'OTHER', 'BARD', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Bard]', 'Keep! Going! The aspects you embody and ghost have enough strings hooked into your brain already. You have learned to lattice and knot up these strings tight enough so that you are a puppet only to that which you choose. Any that even TRY to take the reigns will be sent SPIRALING OUT of your head and soul! For the first round of an encounter, you are completely immune to **[Control]** moves. From that point on, **[Control]** moves against you have a -2 **[Nerf]** and are **[Inept]**. If they succeed despite that, they immediately take 1 **[Freaky] [Psychic]** damage immediately, and take the damage every other round that they keep the **[Control]** effect active on you as their strings get caught up and twisted in the downward spiral of your psyche. They may control the strings, but THIS puppet bites the hand that plays!\r\n'),
('splinters', 'SPLINTERS', 'HEART', 'HEART', '[Aspect][Basic][Locked: Heart]\r\n', 'You sometimes can’t help but spread your sense of self into the world around you. You might write novels with characters eerily similar to you, or play FLARP as a character that mirrors you in an uncanny way, or even create robotic versions of yourself that eventually overwhelm you with your own flaws. In a way, it’s hard for even you to escape yourself. Your splinters stick into your friends; you can allow another troll you are close to to gain a move you have when they level up (to a limit of TWICE overall & ONCE per troll). This move must be an **[Open]** move. If you don’t have any **[Open]** moves they can take, they may choose one of the stats you have **[Talent]** in. This gives them a permanent **+1 [Buff]** to rolls using that stat. Either way, your splinter sticks into them, and they gain a few of your mannerisms. Depending on your own image of yourself, this might set you at unease.  If your target has the BRAIN GHOST Hope move, the image of you in their mind is startlingly real; you can appear in any encounter they’re in, only interacting with them.'),
('sponsoredSegment', 'SPONSORED SEGMENT', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Mental][Tech][Locked: Streamer] ', 'Today\'s video is sponsored by NOOK WARS XIV, one of the biggest mobile role-playing games of 9032 and it\'s totally free! Look, you aren\'t proud of it, but sometimes you need money to live, and that means shoving product placement into your streams. The trick is doing it without your viewers deciding to blitzkrieg your numbers! You may roll this move multiple times in an encounter, but you receive a **-2 [Nerf]** each consecutive time. When you want to sneakily mention brands, roll **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Oh, ye gods! In the middle of you promoting your product, you experienced a spontaneously ruptured organ! You take **3 [Somatic]** damage and **3 [Drag]**. Ruptured organs are terrible for a brand\'s image, and you lose your sponsorship; you feel **[Agitated]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Chat vehemently dislikes being advertised to! You feel **[Agitated]** as they shake their heads and scowl at the other side of the screen. You make no money from this.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Chat murmurs that they found that cringe, and your sponsors don\'t pay well. You feel **[Stressed]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: A few people in chat seem genuinely interested in your product! Maybe they WILL use the discount code G0LD at the checkout! You receive **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Whoa, chat really liked that! Holy shit! You receive **4 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: HOLY POGCHAMPS, STREAMER! You do such an excellent job promoting your product that you get a flood of donations! You immediately make **Treasure II**, and receive **6 [Boost]**!'),
('squidillionaire', 'SQUIDILLIONAIRE', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Passive]', 'Money… is literally not an object to you. It\'s like, nothing. You could melt a million caegars into a frisbee and hurl it into the sea, and it wouldn\'t matter, cuz you can make that back in a few minutes. Yep… you\'re VERY wealthy. And throwing that wealth around can get you basically anything you want. You can roll WORDPLAY using **+APP**; when you do so, the roll is **[Tiered Up]**, but you give the target 2 of your **LUX**, **Treasure I**, or some other form of payment. On a **MIN**, you lose the money offered. You can also access the following WORDPLAY effects, but only while using this move.\r\n\r\n> **SCREW THE RULES**: I have money. You request that something be changed; deactivate that HIVECRAFTING UPGRADE, resolve this encounter in a Vehicle Race, don\'t use **[Drag]** on me for the next **3 turns**, etcetera. This modified REQUEST allows you to activate or deactivate rules as you choose, so long as you pay someone who could control this situation agrees. They only take the money if you agree. \r\n\r\n> **MAKE IT RAIN**: Take that, look at this not me, lol. You throw coins on the floor. All enemies become **[Distracted]** for **1 turn**, and you become **[Hidden]**.\r\n\r\n> **HUSH MONEY**: You didn\'t see that. This modified REQUEST roll makes the target forget something entirely; they repress the memory SUPER hard for you. If they blab anyway, they are wracked with guilt, and feel **[Dread]** until the situation resolves, potentially over multiple encounters. This heightens to **[Despair]** if they meet you again. \r\n\r\n> **MINE NOW**: You just. Buy something from someone else. It\'s like a request, but you get an item forever from it.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('squireErrant', 'SQUIRE ERRANT', 'OTHER', 'PAGE', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Page]\r\n', 'This is it, you\'ve arrived! You made it. Huh? You aren\'t satisfied? You\'re confused by how come you haven\'t gotten any cool class magic? Why you aren\'t an invincible powerhouse? Why, despite it all, you\'re still you? Well, because… you ARE you. You don\'t need to be this hyperpowerful \"I\'M SUDDENLY THE BEST\" like everyone expected you to be… even yourself. Instead, You finally understand yourself and your limits better and you know how to push yourself to keep growing. Ultimately, you know that being yourself is pretty great. With your old MISPLACED POTENTIAL Entry move, the stat you were once **[Inept]** in becomes **[Talented]**. Instead of gaining **[Boost]** from your inconceivable successes, you\'ve learned that you must grow from your failures, and any time you gain a **MIN** or **BAD** roll with that new **[Talent]**, you gain **5 or 2 [Boost]** respectively. Also... you can do new things with those **PP** now! You can spend **PP** as an action to **[Heal]** yourself 1 **HP** per point. You can choose how many you spend, but can only spend up to a max of 3 per action.'),
('stalwartShield', 'STALWART SHIELD', 'OTHER', 'KNIGHT', '[Class][Passive][Unlock: Knight] \r\n', 'You’d literally rather die than let someone hurt your friends. As such, you’ve learned to take a beating; a real, real bad beating. You immediately gain a permanent **+2 HP** in addition to your **+GRT**.\r\n\r\n'),
('stampedecaller', 'STAMPEDE-CALLER', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Psionic][Locked: Summoner]', 'What\'s one lusus when you can summon a whole heap of them? When you roll XENODRUID, you can choose to instead summon a STAMPEDE Hazard, which actively avoids harming you or your allies. On a **GOOD**, Round 1 starts next turn. On a **GREAT**, the Hazard acts as normal. On a **MAX**, OH SNAP the Stampede happens so fast. Rounds 1 and 2 happen simultaneously. If you spot a **[Hidden]** troll taking cover from the stampede with an **[Analyze]** check, they instantly take the damage from the stampede again, and are subject to its wrath!'),
('standTall', 'STAND TALL', 'HOPE', 'HOPE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Free][Reaction][Recharge: 2][Locked: Hope]\r\n', 'You don’t give into fear easily! Once upon a time, people might have tried to drag you down by preying on what your morals held dear to you, but that time is long gone. Any time you would gain the **[Dread]**, **[Scared]**, or **[Sad]** Emotions from someone else, you refuse to give into your anxiety; you can choose to gain **2 [Boost]** instead as you stand defiant of those who would drag you down.'),
('starchosenDestiny', 'STARCHOSEN DESTINY', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Paladin]', 'You are a believer in predestination, as are all noble Crusaculturists. And to have gotten to your level, why… you must surely have done some good now. Reading the esoteric texts of ancient scribes and performing strange magic, you have been subjected to the SAGGATARIC RITUAL OF THE BLADESHIELDER, reading out your destiny and blessing you with a divine role. You must swear to use this new divine role to protect not just the people who live here today, but all trolls, past and present. Select a role, based on your class.\r\n\r\n> **Witch/Heir**: You are a BATTLEARCANIST, trained in magic and spells to aid those around you. All **[Magic]** rolls for you use **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n> **Knight/Page**: Ah, you… you are a BLADESHIELDER, the footmen of the Indigo Order of Crusaculturists. A sword in one hand and a shield in the other! You can spend a **[Reaction]** to reduce an incoming piece of damage by 1 (min. 1) as you block off attacks with your shield.\r\n\r\n> **Maid/Sylph**: You are a THUNDERCLERIC, a healer of the sick and guardian of the poor. Whenever you **[Heal]** a target, the target first loses a physical condition such as **[Bloodied]** or **[Poisoned]** as you treat them expertly.\r\n\r\n> **Mage/Seer**: You are a STARPROPHET, an astrologian who gazes into the night sky to divine messages from them. Your PROBLEM SLEUTHING rolls use **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n> **Thief/Rogue**: You are a BLITZQUISITOR, expertly seeking out those who would defy your calling and sentencing them to an ass-whooping. Select an option from OATHKEEPER, if you do not already have one; you can roll PROBLEM SLEUTHING to ask if the target sympathises with those who would defy your oath (such as Nyanarchists who like lusii if you\'re a BEASTSLAYER or Inventors if you have the OATH OF STABILITY). If they do side with it, you have a **+1 [Buff]** to **[Strife]** rolls against them, permanently.\r\n\r\n> **Prince/Bard**: You are a RAGNAROKCHAMP, a warlord, a one man army, a dark knight, a dragoon… you get the picture. When you are outnumbered in an encounter, or facing a target higher level than you, you can choose to become **[Out of Control]** as an action. While **[Out of Control]**, you can\'t gain **[Heightened]** Negative **[Emotions]**.'),
('starOfTheShow', 'STAR OF THE SHOW', 'OTHER', 'THIEF', '[Class][Basic][Free][Locked: Thief]', 'Not only do you know that the spotlight should be on you- the spotlight BELONGS to you! If you roll a **MAX** on any roll, you can impose a **-2 [Nerf]** to your opponent\'s next move. They\'ll suck and make your cool move look even better than it already was!\r\n\r\n'),
('starryNight', 'STARRY NIGHT', 'OTHER', 'ABOMINARTIST', '[Template][Advanced][One-Off][Locked: Abominartist]', 'You’ve worked… pretty hard. Yeah, you’re willing to admit that to yourself. Anytime you get a **MAX** **+IMG** roll, you can become **[Peaceful]** for **[Free]** as you revel in your talent- you’re confident enough to do that now! Imposter syndrome can fuck right off! Additionally, as an action, you can swap your **[Talents]** around to different stats- turns out the **+IMG** it takes to make jewelry can be used just as well in **+PLC** with charming people! All that glitters, or something like that. This lasts for two rounds.'),
('starstuddedSensate', 'STAR-STUDDED SENSATE', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Passive][Ultra][Locked: Celebrity]', 'You? You\'re a BIG FUCKING DEAL. Think of the biggest thing imaginable. Are you thinking? Yeah. You\'re BIGGER. With the infinite wealth you pour into everything, your fame was always a certain outcome. And now? You\'re not just some B-List celeb. You\'re not even A-List. You\'re S+++-List, and EVERYBODY who\'s ANYBODY knows you! You gain access to HERO MODE through your PERFECT PULCHRITUDE. Your popularity is eternal; you gain **1 POP** every turn, that you can either give to yourself or to an ally as you choose for **[Free]**. Finally, your fame doesn\'t stop where it started; no, no! You, like all celebrities, must certainly branch out into new areas! You may take the CLAIM TO FAME move a second time, now or later for free, with a new CLAIM TO FAME representing your growth as a celebrity!'),
('staunchSecret', 'STAUNCH SECRET', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Basic][Reaction]', 'Your blood is a closely kept secret and you try your hardest to keep everything about it under wraps. But sometimes, try as you might, accidents happen. Not if you have anything to say about it though! Whenever you would be **[Bloodied]** or **[Crying]** in an encounter, you may quickly cover these up as a **[Reaction]** and gain 3 **[Drag]** in place. You can do this a number of times in an encounter equal to your **+APP** modifier.\r\n'),
('staySteady', 'STAY STEADY', 'MIND', 'MIND', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Mind]', 'You’re not so easily swayed by hurtful words or emotional manipulation! You’re confident enough in your stability to stave off the worst people can throw at you. You gain **1 [Resistance]** against **[Verbal]** damage, and you don’t gain any negative effects from basic **[Emotion]** effects. You still have the emotion, though, and it counts towards heightening it if you gain it from another source.'),
('stealthling', 'STEALTHLING', 'OTHER', 'RAINBOW_DRINKER', '[Template][Advanced][Recharge: 2][Eerie][Physical][Locked: Rainbow Drinker]', 'You’ve mastered the art of shutting the damn lights off, and you know how to slip into a crowd and be undetected. You don’t glow unless you choose to, and can slip away totally unnoticed when you need, even in plain sight. When you want to duck away from view, roll **+GRA**.\n\n**MIN**: Ouch! You stub your toe, and— oh, fuck, you just turned the lights on. Everyone around knows what you are, and if you are in a crowded area, an ANGRY MOB **[Hazard]** appears and tries to get you! Run!\n\n**BAD**: Putting a lampshade over your head and standing very still is not good hiding.\n\n**OK**: You dip out of sight… for a moment. You’re **[Hidden]** until the start of your next turn.\n\n**GOOD**: Woosh… you are **[Hidden]**.\n\n**GREAT**: WOOOOOOOOSH… you are VERY **[Hidden]**. Any PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll to find you is **[Inept]**, because you’re so damn hard to pick out right now. \n\n**MAX**: You stealth so well that your target believes you just straight up absconded. They throw their hat on the floor in disgust, and move on with their night… while you stalk them quietly. Your moves against this troll are **[Tiered Up]** until you reveal yourself. The other troll cannot look for you; what rainbow drinker?'),
('sticksAndStones', 'STICKS AND STONES', 'OTHER', 'MAID', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Maid]', 'You know what? You’re tired of listening to other people. You can depend on yourself! You don’t need Empece in your ear telling you that you’ve done something wrong. Because actually? It worked fine, and you know what you’re doing. You’ve built up 1 **[Resistance]** to **[Verbal]** damage, as these things just... don\'t bother you so much anymore. If you already had a **[Verbal] [Resistance]**, **[Manipulate]** and **[Control]** rolls against you are **[Inept]** against you.'),
('stickyInventory', 'STICKY INVENTORY', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Passive][Locked: Beekeeper]', 'Most of what you make is… y\'know, kinda made with honey. So it\'s not exactly easy to snag stuff from you! Any time someone tries to steal an item from you, hits you with a **MAX** **[Physical]** roll, or damages one of your items, they become **[Trapped]** as they get gooped by your tech\'s more sticky properties.'),
('stonkExchange', 'STONK EXCHANGE', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Downtime][Locked: Penpusher]', 'Hey, hey, hey! You and your co-workers have this little game you like to play! It\'s called \"let\'s bet fake money on an imaginary line generated on your phone that we pretend reflects our productivity\"! Sometimes the line goes up, and that\'s great! Sometimes, it goes down, and that\'s BAD. What? You don\'t think playing with these cryptic currencies sounds very fun? What\'s the matter, don\'t you wanna be a big shot? When you take this move, you start with 60 STNKS. Once a week, you may roll 1d8 to see how the line is doing.\r\n\r\n> **1**: Lose half your STNKS.\r\n> **2**: Lose 120 STNKS.\r\n> **3**: Lose 60 STNKS.\r\n> **4**: Gain 60 STNKS.\r\n> **5**: Gain 80 STNKS.\r\n> **6**: Gain 120 STNKS.\r\n> **7**: Double your  STNKS.\r\n> **8**: Quadruple your STNKS.\r\n\r\nYou can spend STNKS on the following effects in an encounter.\r\n\r\n> **WAKE-UP CALL (60)**: Lose an **[Emotion]**.\r\n> **PICK-ME-UP (60)**: You gain 2 **[Boost]**.\r\n> **ASSISTANT (60)**: A Teal NPC spawns. They won\'t **[Strife]** unless threatened, but they otherwise follow orders.\r\n> **WORK INCENTIVE (80)**: You reduce you or an ally\'s **[Buildup]** or **[Recharge]** by 1.\r\n> **HEALTH PACKAGE (80)**: **[Heal]** **2 HP**.\r\n> **MYSTERY SUBSTANCES (80)**: You receive 3 instances of HIGH QUALITY FUNJUNK precaptchalogues that don\'t need Sylladex Slots.\r\n> **ALTERNIAN FREAKAZOID KIT (100)**: Gain a temporary Abstrata Upgrade which can be used alongside any pre-existing Abstrata on your Specibus as well as a **+1 [Buff]** to **[Strife]** rolls for **2 turns**.\r\n> **POWER-UP (200)**: **[Tier Up]** your next move. \r\n> **SNUCCI WARDROBE (250)**: Gain a Collection of Fashion Items from Chapter X.\r\n> **COMPANY CAR (400)**: A 3 HORSEPOWER Medium Scuttlebuggy deploys from the sky. You are **[Talented]** at your VEHICULATE rolls in it.\r\n> **PRIVATE JET (800)**: A 5 HORSEPOWER Flying Vehicle deploys from the sky. You are **[Talented]** at your VEHICULATE rolls in it.\r\n> **ORBITAL STRIKE (2,000)**: You\'re probably gonna get demoted for this, but it\'s fine. You call down a deadly laser (company property) to smite your enemies (competitors). Also you and your allies. Everyone present takes 15 **[Unblockable]** damage.'),
('stopRightThere', 'STOP RIGHT THERE', 'OTHER', 'SYLPH', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Sylph]', 'You know what\'s better than treating a stab wound? Stopping the stab wound from happening in the first place! While you\'re not going to stop helping your friends, you want to lessen the load of the healing that needs done- both so they\'re not suffering... and for the sake of your sanity. Instead of meddling in your allies’ affairs, you take a brief moment to meddle in those of your enemies. All rolls on non-**[Strife]** moves that intend to apply a debilitating effect to you or an ally are at a -2 **[Nerf]**. This **[Nerf]** does not apply to UNIVERSAL MOVES.\r\n'),
('strategySchemist', 'STRATEGY SCHEMIST', 'OTHER', 'SEER', '[Class][Basic][Recharge: 3][Mental][Locked: Seer]', 'Shoot first, ask questions later? What kind of maniac came up with that!? You ALWAYS ask questions first. Always ask “Is this plan stupid? Will this kill me?”. If you didn’t, what would happen if the answers to them were YES? You’d be dead. Dead as hell. That’s why before acting you always ask questions and plan it through! You may choose 2 different moves to roll for 1 action, rolling both and then choosing which result you would like to use as your action.'),
('streetmonarch', 'STREETMONARCH', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Passive][Ultra][Locked: Delinquent]', 'These streets? They\'re YOURS. YOU own the streets. Every other miserable whelp here, from the rusts in the gutters to the clowns in the alleys, they\'re your peons. What you say goes out here, and anyone who disagrees with you on that? They can find out the hard way that you didn\'t get to this level of infamy without being a master of bitchcuttery. You gain access to HERO MODE through your MYTHIC MANGRIT. When you fight, it\'s like a hurricane; you can roll multiple **[Strife]** rolls in a turn, though the second is **[Inept]**, and any further ones **[Godawful]**. You take **2 additional [Drag]** on an **OK** or lower **[Strife]** roll on these subsequent attacks. This does not combine with the ORAORAORA MYTHIC MANGRIT effect. Finally, you are immune to the ANGRY MOB Hazard; the streets know better than to fuck with you.'),
('streetSmarts', 'STREET SMARTS', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'The fact that you\'re even alive means you\'re doing something right, right? You know your way around the mean streets of Alternia, and won\'t let yourself get got by them! You gain the following SWASHBUCKLE effects.\r\n\r\n> **USE SURROUNDINGS**: You climb a wall, jump over a wire fence or otherwise put an obstacle between you and an opponent! Your opponent can\'t roll **[Physical]** moves against you until they deal **3 damage** to the obstacle, **[Fly]** over it or use PROBLEM SLEUTHING to INVESTIGATE… or some other way to get at ya. \r\n\r\n> **VEHICLE SURFING**: You grab onto the back of a vehicle, and hold on tight! You count as a passenger, even if there\'s not enough space. The car needs to be within grabbing distance to do it. Obviously.\r\n\r\n> **SEEYA**: Convenient sewer grate OPEN! You leave the scene and jump into the sewers. You can choose to either become **[Hidden]** or ABSCOND; if your opponents roll CAN\'T ABSCOND BRO or SPOT, they need to follow you into the sewers. Large creatures and spectators don\'t follow, though Hazards might depending on the situation. You must be in an urban environment for this to work. \r\n\r\n> **EXTRA ELBOW GREASE**: You work HARD! You get two SWASHBUCKLE rolls, but you become **[Tired]**.'),
('strongConvictions', 'STRONG CONVICTIONS', 'HOPE', 'HOPE', '[Aspect][Passive][Unlock: Hope]', 'When you believe in something, you believe in it hard. Whether it\'s your friends, your morals, or the existence of wizards, you are a hard troll to change the mind of. **[Manipulate]** rolls that are meant to change your mind or lie to you all **[Tier Down]**. This stacks with other moves that would also **[Tier Down]** these effects.'),
('strongerStuff', 'STRONGER STUFF', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Gutterblood]', 'Folks like you are far from frail. You may bleed Rust, but you only get rust from metal and standing strong over time while weathering the odds. You use your **+APP** as well as your **+GRT** for HP, thanks to your unbelievable resilience. All **[Afflictions]** rolls use your **+APP**, as you power through any inconvenience. No stopping YOU from surviving!'),
('strongSenseOfCommunity', 'STRONG SENSE OF COMMUNITY', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'Community is extremely important to you. Having support systems has honestly gotten you through some real tough times. When you take this move, you pledge yourself to a community. It can be as small as a close friend group or as big as an entire town. Whenever you are in an encounter with trolls in this community, you gain the exclusive AT HOME condition.\r\n\r\n> **AT HOME**: A condition where even if things look tough… you won\'t give up! You get a **[Drag]** buffer, a pool within which **[Drag]** can\'t be used in. The size of this buffer depends on how many trolls triggering the AT HOME condition are present; for example, if three trolls were making you feel AT HOME, you\'d have a buffer of **3 [Drag]**. If an opponent then stacked **5 [Drag]** on you, they\'d only be able to use 2, since your AT HOME buffer swallowed up 3! For the purpose of enemy moves, the **[Drag]** in this buffer does not exist.'),
('stubbornAsHell', 'STUBBORN AS HELL', 'BLOOD', 'BLOOD', '[Aspect][Basic][Free][Last Stand][One-Off][Locked: Blood]', 'Even when it’s clear you should probably give up, you have difficulty throwing in the towel. You KNOW you can persevere! Just… keep pushing through! When you would be knocked down to 0 HP, you instead stay standing, fighting on; however, for every round you stay up, you also take **1 [Drag]** per damage you take— or **2 [Drag]** per round if you don\'t take any/less than 2 damage. The first time you get an **OK** or lower on a roll after hitting 0 HP, you go down hard and drop **[Unconscious]**. You cannot benefit from **[Tier Up]** moves or gain **[Boost]** while this move is active, and must use at least one rolled move per turn.'),
('stumbleForward', 'STUMBLE FORWARD', 'OTHER', 'MAID', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Maid]', 'Geez, things really don\'t want to go your way sometimes! You don\'t get why, you\'ve done everything just right... well, no matter. You know this\'s the right way, so you\'ve just gotta keep following it! When your roll with a **[Buff]** would be affected by debuffs, such as **[Tier Downs]** or **[Inepts]**, you can permanently decrease your **[Buff]** by 1 in order to ignore all debuffs on that roll.'),
('stuntDoublitioner', 'STUNT DOUBLITIONER', 'BRONZE', 'ADULT', '[Bronze][Locked: Adult]\r\n', 'If you\'re a Stunt Doublitioner, you fall into one of two categories. First, a troll who is used to test everything from experimental new weapons to new medicalizer formulas might have a small chance of turning the user\'s blood into actual magma. Second, a troll who acts as a body double standing in for important figures and high ranking officials that don\'t want to risk having their head suddenly blown off in a surprise enemy attack. When you are assigned this job, choose one of the options below. You cannot change this choice unless a superior of efficient rank and authority demands it.\r\n\r\n> **Category One**: Choose one **[Negative]** Emotion and one debilitating Status Effect. You cannot be affected by these choices until 2 rounds have passed since it was applied. Until then, you still have the status effect and/or Emotion, and they can be removed through normal means. You just don’t suffer any of the effects, because this is kind of the usual for you.\r\n\r\n> **Category Two**: Choose a caste of jade or above that you\'ve been assigned to impersonate. While disguised as this caste, you are **[Talented]** in all **[Manipulate]** checks and make all **[Analyze]** checks against you **[Godawful]** as they try to figure out the plans of who you\'re disguised as, not yourself. If a target rolls a **MAX PROBLEM SLEUTH**, they can forgo taking the normal effects and immediately discover that you are merely pretending and dispelling any bonuses you get from being disguised against them. However, they also become **[Embarrassed]** as they realize they\'ve been JAPED TO THE MAX.\r\n'),
('sturdyAsSteel', 'STURDY AS STEEL', 'OTHER', 'KNIGHT', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Knight]', 'You’ve learned how to take a hit, and how to make that hit do as little damage as possible. You care about your friends deeply and don’t want to see them hurt. Nothing will hurt them more than you keeling over dead because you were trying to protect them from that single point of damage, though. Look after yourself, buddy! No single attack may ever deal more than 1/3 your current max **HP** rounded down total (to a minimum of 1), regardless of **WHAM** or other bonuses. If you have 12 **HP**, the most damage you may take from a single hit is 4 damage, etc. The only moves that circumvent this are those with the **UNBLOCKABLE** tag.\r\n\r\n\r\n'),
('subcaste', 'SUBCASTE', 'OTHER', 'MUTANT', '[Mutant][Cullbait][Passive]', 'Whether your blood is just a shade off or something completely different than the twelve castes cultivated by the Alternian empire, it’s clear that you don’t fit into the cage of what the Empire finds the most important in its society. Your blood might be a shade of bright red, ice blue, black, or.. striped? Rainbow? I don’t control you. The point is, it’s not a color that could force you into a caste role easily. There are two types:\n\n**TYPE ONE**: Choose three caste bases, excluding limes and violets. Any moves from these castes are available to take while leveling up except for psionic moves. Choose one caste’s tree to be your primary tree. For the other two castes, you’ll have to rely on **[Open]** moves.\n\n**TYPE TWO**: Choose two caste bases instead of three, such as above, in exchange for the ability to take **[Basic]** **[Psionic]** moves from an additional tree other than your primary tree. You still cannot take a **[Psionic]** tree as your primary tree.\n\nEither way, you’ve gotta hide your blood color, lest you be culled for demonstrating that the Empire’s narrow boxes for castes aren’t as concrete as they seem. You feel **[Dread]** if you begin **[Crying]** or become **[Bloodied]** and someone reacts negatively to your blood color.'),
('subconsciousIntuition', 'SUBCONSCIOUS INTUITION', 'OTHER', 'MAGE', '[Class][Passive][Unlock: Mage]', 'Why are we here...? Is it just to suffer? To gain knowledge and perhaps one day use it, but to have it always and live with this? It’s hard knowing your aspect this deeply. It’s hard and no one understands. Lived experience guides the truth in a way others just can’t comprehend, and once you begin to grasp it, you may still get an inkling from your target as to an answer- a small hint or glimpse, perhaps, from the back of your mind. Your next **[Analyze]** roll against an opponent who has just rolled a **[Strife]** or **[Chicanery]** roll against you is **[Tiered Up]**, even on a **MIN**.'),
('subphoticVariant', 'SUBPHOTIC VARIANT', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Passive][Too Good To Be Cullbait][Unlock: Deep-Sea]', 'You are… different. A rare breed of Violets that are at their most comfortable deep underwater with fathomless pressure crushing you. You might still try to follow your duties as a Violet, or the crushing distance between you and anyone else as you lurk at the seafloor of underwater ravines may have killed any motivation to interact with the world above at all. You are **[Talented]** at **+GRT**. Your appearance is obviously unnatural; your body has evolved since grubhood to produce some flashy bioluminescence, and you have one of the following… alterations.\n\n> **LIGHTLESS EYES**: Your eyes have adapted to a life with basically no light; they might be pale and glossy, or they might be large and extremely light-sensitive. Whether you have vision or not, you are **[Permablind]**. ABSCOND attempts around you are **[Inept]** thanks to your strange senses.\n\n> **LURE**: Whether it’s a literal lure sticking out of your head, your eyes lighting up, or just particular mastery over your regular luminescence, you gain strange abilities. Your WORDPLAY rolls use **+GRT** and are **[Control]** moves, not **[Manipulate]**.\n\n> **NEEDLE TEETH**: Your fangs are the stuff of nightmares, and you’ve developed the ability to unhinge your jaw like a particularly terrifying beast. You may make two **[Strife]** rolls in a turn, though the second time is always **[Tiered Down]**.\n\n> **EXTRA FINS**: Every violet has ear fins, but you’ve got them all over the place! Pectoral fins, dorsal fins, pelvic fins- whether you have one set or five, you are **[Quickened]** anytime you swim.\n\n> **CAMOUFLAGE**: You know how some species can actually change their skin color to blend in with the environment? Yeah. Rolls to become **[Hidden]** use **+GRT** and are considered **[Psionic]**, not **[Physical]**. You can become **[Hidden]** even when you have already been observed.\n\n> **VENOMOUS**: You have evolved to be highly venomous! On a **GREAT** **[Strife]** roll, you may choose to do no damage in exchange for making your opponent **[Slowed]** for two turns and **[Poisoned]** until they **[Heal]**.\n\n> **INKLING**: You\'re a kid you\'re a squid you\'re both a kid and a squid at once actually! And you can make ink, of course! Whether it\'s colorful or just plain black, you can create an **INKBAG** as a **[Downtime]** action, or instantly create and use one as a **GOOD SHENANIGANS** effect; **INKBAGS** have the effects of a **BLOODBAG** of your choice, and while they aren\'t blood and would make a rainbow drinker start **CHOKING**, they **[Blind]** whoever you dump them on for two turns in addition to whichever Emotion they inflict!\n\n> **SHARKSKIN**: You\'re just built different. Literally. Your skin is rough, tough, and bacterially resistant for good measure. Maybe you just straight-up have a carapace. Whenever you would take 3 or more **[Somatic]** damage at once, you take 1 less, and you can make rolls to resist **[Afflictions]** with **+GRT** instead of their usual stat.'),
('subplotter', 'SUBPLOTTER', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][Build-Up: 3][Recharge: 3][Magic][Locked: Narrator]', 'A good story should have subplots! You can\'t just go from getting your laser sword to IMMEDIATELY blowing up the alien space base. You need downtime! You need obstacles! You need SUBPLOTS! In a combat encounter, you can add the following complications. These effects can affect all participants, allies and enemies alike. If you use this move during QUESTGIVER, increase the Treasure Reward to **Treasure III**.\r\n\r\n**MONSTROUS GUARDIAN**: Oez noez! The encounter happens to be near a wild lusus, who has taken issue with you guys! Will our heroes team up with their opponents, proving they aren\'t so different after all? Or will it become a case of survival of the fittest? A level 3 or lower lusus spawns. All combatants gain **1 [WHAM]**.\r\n\r\n**ROMANTIC RINGMARANG**: Feelings bubble up below the tension. Perhaps… An enemies to lovers arc is coming..? All characters who feasibly could experience romantic attraction to another participant are exposed to SIMPTOMS, which becomes a **[Rapid]** Affliction here.\r\n\r\n**TRAITOR!**: An argument bursts up among the combating parties… and a random participant who narratively could be convinced to switch sides does just that!! The drama of it all! All combatants gain **1 [WHAM]**.\r\n\r\n**A NEW CHALLENGER APPROACHES!**: Another troll appears, and joins the encounter! All participants take **2 [Boost]**.'),
('subtleFlex', 'SUBTLE FLEX', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Open][Recharge: 3][Manipulate]', 'Wowwwww. You’re like, just so naturally good at this. It’s crazy, right? You\'ve dumped an insane amount of money into getting good at what you do— money that no other caste could even dream of approaching. Naturally, you can\'t help but show this off, you know? This can often make others feel insecure. When you want to make a show of your talents, roll with a stat that you are **[Talented]** in.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Whoa! Even rich people can be unbelievably shit at things, too?! That’s so inspiring! Your target’s rolls using that stat **[Tier Up]** for **3 rounds**. When that wears off, they keep a **+1 [Buff]** for the rest of the encounter. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: Hey, that makes me feel a little better about myself. Thank you, rich dude! Your target’s rolls using that stat receive a **+1 [Buff]** for the encounter.\r\n\r\n**OK**: It doesn’t register with your opponent that you’re flexing on them. Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Ah, jeez. This makes me feel inept! Your opponent receives a **-1 [Nerf]** on rolls with that stat for **3 turns**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Incredible! Now I’m completely miserable. Your opponent’s rolls on that move receive a **-2 [Nerf]** for **3 turns**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Well fuck. The opponent is so blown away by how good you are, that they consider just giving up and never trying again. Extreme disillusionment, baby! Your opponent’s rolls on that move **[Tier Down]** for **3 rounds**. When that wears off, they keep a **-1 [Nerf]** for the rest of the encounter.'),
('suckerpunch', 'SUCKERPUNCH', 'OTHER', 'TRICKSTER', '[Template][Basic][Eerie][Physical][Strife][Buildup: 1][Recharge 1][Locked: Trickster]', 'BLLLLLLLLLAMMO!!!!! After winding up your arm a little bit, you pull your punch wayyy way back like some kind of freakish loony toon. And then you really let ‘em have it! When you want to punch people in ways only cartoon logic could allow, roll **+RAS**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: SHHHHWAK!!! You somehow land a full-force punch right into your gut. And face??? At the same time??? How’d you manage that? You take **2 [Somatic]** Damage and are knocked **[Floorbound]** from the comical force of the spin you’ve exerted upon yourself.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: TWANG!! Your limb freakishly stretches to strike your opponent, but they step out of the way last second- it rubber-bands back to you, and smacks you instead! You take **1 [Somatic]** damage, and are **[Distracted]** for a turn as you get your head back in the Positive Totally Healthy Mindset.\r\n\r\n**OK**: WHIFF! Okay, you missed, but that looked like it would’ve REALLY hurt if it connected. You might’ve even left some cracks in whatever you hit instead of your target… Whoopsie!! Your opponent is **[Scared]**, and you gain **2 [Boost]** from their silly reaction. \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: BIFF!! A solid punch! Right to the kissa!!! Right on the smoocher!!!! Your opponent takes **1 [Somatic]** damage and is **[Confused]** on their next turn. Aw, it’s almost like they have little stars around their head!!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: BANG!! Your punch stops just short of your foe, where your fist then EXPLODES!! They take **2 [Somatic]** damage, and are **[Blinded]** for **2 turns**, because the blast covered them in soot. It’s like a volcanic snowtroll. :) \r\n\r\n**MAX**: BAM!! POW!!! BOOM!!! Your weapon of choice grows to freakish proportions, and you use it to terrifying effect. Your opponent is sent right onto the floor- they are now **[Floorbound]**, and **[Clumsy]** for a turn. The weight of the impact hits ‘em with a solid **3 [Somatic]** damage. \r\n\r\n'),
('sufferingIsAChoice', 'SUFFERING IS A CHOICE', 'OTHER', 'PRINCE', '[Class][Advanced][Free][One-Off][Magic][Locked: Prince]', 'Listen guy, you’d love to stick around but you’re a busy prince! Turns out that’s a byproduct of increasing your reign from just you to all these numbnuts you’ve taken pity over. You can’t smack them upside the head for making dumb decisions if you’re on fire… or whatever the fuck it is that you’re trying to inflict here. You can activate this move using a **[Free]** action, causing debilitating **[Bodily]** conditions such as **[Ablaze], [Poisoned]**, and **[Slowed]** to have no effect on you for 3 rounds. Yeah, you’ve figured out how to use your destructive power to just delete them for the moment. At the end of these rounds, you take all the effects you held back all at once. \r\n'),
('sufferingSacrifice', 'SUFFERING SACRIFICE', 'BLOOD', 'BLOOD', '[Aspect][Advanced][Magic][Heal][Locked: Blood]', 'Your friends mean the world to you, and if you can take the pain for them, you will. When your allies are hurt, you can spend an action to siphon your own HP into them, losing **1 HP** for each HP you heal them, or taking their **[Drag]** away and giving it to you. When you do this, it’s an almost supernatural effect as you hold your target close, embracing them as you slowly swap wounds.'),
('sufficientlyAdvancedHobbies', 'SUFFICIENTLY ADVANCED HOBBIES', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'You\'re not ashamed of your interests anymore! If you think something is cool, then it is! And it\'s okay to divert time and energy into it, you know? Any moves you gain from a **[Template]** are **[Talented]**. You can thematically link them into your hobby from NERD HOBBIES; for example, you\'re not a real Astrosorcerer, this is your Flarp Gear! You don\'t ACTUALLY turn into a Moonbark… it\'s a fursuit. You can modify one tag per move, for example removing **[Cullbait]** or turning **[Magic]** to **[Tech]**, but only if you explain why it\'s just a mundane thing, not an actual magic one. You can only benefit from one **[Template]** like this.'),
('sugarCrash', 'SUGAR CRASH', 'OTHER', 'TRICKSTER', '[Template][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Trickster]\r\n', 'This is not happiness. This is wrong. Ignorance is bliss, but it is impossible to ignore the teeth rotting out of your mouth and the fact you feel so, so sick.\r\n\r\nIt\'s time to get up and face the music.\r\n\r\nSome Tricksters eventually come down from their sugar high and experience the inevitable Sugar Crash, where they finally realize just how many problems don\'t go away after beating them with candy corn hammers and licorice spears. This can happen after some serious intervention, like therapy session after therapy session after therapy session, unconditional, unrelenting, unending love from friends, or even witnessing the fact that your sugar-coated \'help\' is only hurting your loved ones via a dramatic moment in a heated strife or a screaming match with sobbing Quadrants. Sometimes, it can even happen after being beaten down in an especially shocking or depressing way, literally knocking some sense into you.\r\n\r\nRegardless, you\'re done running from the truth and smothering your sorrows in sugar. You hurt, but you\'re better now. You promise. Upon taking this move, you lose all prior moves from this template and retain only this one, gaining back the levels you spent. This does not count as a second Ultra, allowing you a third, and no longer locks you out of other templates. You\'ve taken off the cherry-tinted glasses.\r\nCavities don\'t go away that easily, though, and relapse is always a possibility. Your efforts to repress the sugar rush give you the following benefits: you can choose to be **[Serious]** as an action, and you get **[Serious]** for **[Free]** when someone enters a MOED MOST TRICKSEY. If you were **[Serious]** before this, you become **[Dead Serious]**. These ignore the limitations set by CONFECTIONARY TERROR. Additionally, when someone enters a MOED MOST TRICKSEY, you gain **[Boost]** equal to the amount of **[Negative]** Emotions lost, and your **[Positive]** Emotions only **[Heighten]** if you choose to. Finally, you are immune to the effects of the Trickster timer from A SPOONFUL OF SUGAR and CONFECTIONARY TERROR and instead become **[Brave]**. You are DONE with this sugary stupidity. However, if you are hit with a MAX **[Strife]** from someone in a MOED MOST TRICKSEY, you immediately start **[Laughing]** and **[Crying]** as you recall times that are...well, bittersweet.\r\n'),
('sugarLusus', 'SUGAR LUSUS', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive]', 'Fancy richpants here wants to spoil their friends and quadrants with free stuff? Isn\'t that sweet! Whether it\'s because you\'re covering up some kind of guilt, just an absolute simp or don\'t know what else to do with all this cash, you can let someone else take a spin with your credit card. When you take this move, select the recipient of your generosity. They gain access to any items you are capable of purchasing for **VP**, and may purchase up to 2 of them using your **VP**. You may take this move multiple times for multiple people, but only until you run out of **VP** to give away. They additionally gain access to any HIVECRAFTING items you possess. You start with **1 [Boost]** for every troll you\'re giving cash away to in the Encounter.'),
('sullenSulk', 'SULLEN SULK', 'BLOOD', 'BLOOD', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Blood]', 'When you fuck up, you get moody. It didn’t work, because… because something else got in the way! (Why didn’t it work? Goddammit… C’mon, you’re starting to look like a real chump here…) Whenever you fail a roll (meaning a roll where the result is either nothing or a penalty to yourself), your next roll is **[Tiered Up]**.'),
('summonerSupreme', 'SUMMONER SUPREME', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Ultra][Passive][Psionic][Locked: Summoner]', 'You\'ve studied books on lusus taxonomy from cover to back. You\'ve linked minds with the mightiest Snazzard. Your gym partner is an ape. You KNOW lusii, much like someone might know themselves. And your mastery over lusii is truly incredible. You gain access to HERO MODE through your INCREDIBLE IMAGINATION. Your summoned lusus has +4 stats to distribute through its stat array. Finally, lusii you summon tend to be much stronger; you gain the following effects.\r\n\r\n> **BEAST**: Aw hell naw. Your opponents are **[Terrified]** when this motherfucker ends up on the field.\r\n\r\n> **BLOB**: This thing’s wounds just keep healing up… it **[Heals] 1 HP** every **3 turns**. This bolsters your mind, **[Healing]** you too.\r\n\r\n> **BUG**: This thing has wicked pincers! Its attacks are **[Unblockable]**, and it rolls GRIEF with **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n> **BIRD**: CAW! Fast as fuck, boy! This thing can make a **[Free]** SWASHBUCKLE roll every turn.\r\n\r\n> **BFISH**: This thing\'s size is absolutely insane. Big Fish. It has an extra 5 HP, which affects you too.\r\n\r\n> **BEING**: Eeebedyy deebedy beep beep… this thing can see into your very mind. It can roll your moves too, and can use the Rust Psychic TELEPOWERS move OR the Cerulean Mastermind FREAKY EYE move.'),
('sunstrider', 'SUNSTRIDER', 'OTHER', 'MUTANT', '[Mutant][Cullbait][Passive]\r\n', 'For the most part, only the undead and a small proportion of jades can bear the harsh rays of the sun. You are different. Despite being a perfectly living, breathing troll, you were born with an innate resistance to the deadly light. You are immune to the negative effects of the DAYTIME hazard, as well as the **[Ablaze]** condition. However, your affinity for the day also means your circadian rhythm is fucked. As a naturally diurnal troll, you are always **[Tired]** during the night. Eeby deepy.\r\n\r\nThis is an invisible mutation, so some trolls can go their whole subadult lives without knowing they even have this trait! However, the Empire doesn\'t like its regular law-abiding citizens waltzing around when they can\'t send agents after you, so it still qualifies you as **[Cullbait]** if you\'re seen walking around during the day or chilling while being on fire. Jades, and trolls with the SHADOWDROPPER or RAINBOWDRINKER template, cannot take this mutation. You can already walk around in the daylight, silly!\r\n'),
('sunTouched', 'SUN TOUCHED', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Passive]', 'Strangely enough, your caste is resilient to the sun\'s light;  maybe it\'s something left from bygone days. Maybe it\'s latent Rainbow in your lineage. Either way, you can actually stand in the sun for a while, sometimes! You are immune to the **[Ablaze]** condition, and when you would be set **[Ablaze]**, you are instead **[Quickened]** for **1 round**, which is absolutely fucking terrifying. The DAYTIME **[Hazard]** takes **3 extra turns** to activate against you.'),
('supercharged', 'SUPERCHARGED', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Psionic][Strife][Unlock: Battery]', 'Many Golds have sick, multicoloured LASER EYES unlike any other caste; trolls with these multicoloured eyes are often beekeepers or social media gurus too, but they don’t know how to control their power. You? You fucking RULE at psionics. You might shoot huge ass lasers from your eyes, or manifest your brimming psionic energy in some other totally kickass way. The important thing is that you have a ton of psionic energy at your disposal, and you know how to throw it around. You’re **[Talented]** at **+IMG** and get access to a resource called CHARGE. You get **3 CHARGE** at the start of an encounter, and can spend an action on your turn to gain **2 CHARGE** as you power up, RAAARRRRGH. Be careful building up too much though, if you hit 10 or more CHARGE, you immediately gain the PSIBURN AFFLICTION, and automatically fail any checks to remove it until your CHARGE is down to 0. When you want to e = mc2 the opponent’s face, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: AH, FUCK! Energy backlashes into you, and it hurts like hell. You take **2 [Somatic]** and experience **[Sensory Overload]** as KZZZZLKLTTTTRRRT!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Smoke sizzles out from your ears. That hurt a little! You take **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**OK**: HNNNNNNNNNG- aw. Energy arcs through you, but instead of blasting into the opponent, it continues to build up. When this gasket blows, it’s probably going to hurt a LOT. You gain **1 CHARGE**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD: Pthew! Kachow! Lightsaber noise! You do **1 [Laser] [Somatic]** damage to your target, and can spend 2 CHARGE for one of the following effects. Each effect has a **[Recharge: 2]:\r\n\r\n> **LOCK**: You weren’t actually aiming for the opponent, but that pile of stuff behind them!  The target is **[Trapped]** as objects fall around them.\r\n\r\n> **SHOCK**: You give the opponent a fun lil zap that causes their muscles to momentarily lock up. Their next **[Physical]** roll is **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n> **BARREL**: Screw their shield! To hell with their armor! You’ll just use more power! BRUTE FORCE IS THE BEST FORCE. Your roll cannot be made **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]** or **[Nerfed]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: How do you like that, Obama?! You get the effects of a **GOOD**, but deal **2 [Laser] [Somatic]** damage instead, or **1 [Laser] [Somatic]** damage and gain **1 CHARGE**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Oh, gosh. That’s… that’s a lot? Even for you? You’re hittin \'em with everything you’ve got. Your target takes **3 [Laser] [Somatic]** damage and you gain **1 CHARGE**, or you can take the effects of a **GREAT** and the use of an effect for free.\r\n\r\n'),
('superego', 'SUPEREGO', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Open][Passive][Recharge: 2]', 'You\'re better than everyone. You\'re smarter, you\'re stronger, you\'re cooler, and most of all, you don’t let your inhibitions hold you back. You do what you WANT, and that means you always WIN!!!!!!!! Whenever you can have a move **[Tiered Up]**, you can choose to make your **GREAT** roll into a **MAX** roll.'),
('supergenius', 'SUPERGENIUS', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][One-Off][Tech][Unlock: Inventor]', 'You are an inventor, and robotics is your passion! Building automated ways to do the impossible on the fly, and making the mundane overly complicated through the power of mechanics. You are **[Talented]** at **+PSP**. You may spend an action to build a robotic NPC. You can give up one, both, or all of your actions to give to your robot to fight with. The robot can use any move on its sheet. Due to the robot being hooked up to your brainwaves, you and your robot share all resources and conditions, from HP to Status Conditions to **[Boost]** or **[Recharge]**. You don\'t increase your HP to match your robot, you decrease it to match yours. When you want to build a bot, roll **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: No… NO! I CREATED YOOOOOU! Your robot rises up against you, spawning a SOULLESSBOT monster that will attack you exclusively.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: It\'s rampaging, but at least it\'s not coming after you exclusively! You create a SOULLESSBOT that attacks a random target every turn. \r\n\r\n**OK**: This is taking… longer than you\'d have liked! You get a **GOOD**, but it\'s a **[Lengthy]** action to create the robot. If this was the last action on your turn, you instead only get **1 action** next turn.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: BEEP BEEP BOOP! BEHOLD! A MECHANICAL TROLL! You build a robot, using the Statblock of a Level 1 NPC. It has **[Weakness]** to **[Electric]** damage, and disassembles at the end of the encounter. The robot cannot speak or think for itself; it may not use **[Mental]** or **[Manipulate]** rolls. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: ADVAAAAAANCED MACHINERY! You build a robot with the Statblock of Level 2 NPC instead. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: BRRRRP CHUNK CHUNK BOOM. That\'s the sound of your DRONE deploying. ADIOS, BITCHLORDS! Oh, uh, I guess you could take a Level 3 NPC if you wanted, but c\'mon, you made your own drone.'),
('superiorStrats', 'SUPERIOR STRATS', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Lesson one of all Studyhearts; you\'re the best and greatest. That\'s not really true or anything, but certainly, a lot of the schools Indigos attend are ones that reinforce the narrative of the hemospectrum while also denouncing clowns and fish as unworthy leaders. This has left you both terminally anxious and overconfident at the same time. Yay! You gain access to the following **GOOD** SWASHBUCKLE effects.\r\n\r\n**GOAD**: Are you AFRAID to fight me? Come on, HIT ME! You gain **2 [Boost]**, and **1 [Weakness]** for a turn. If you are hit during that turn, you gain **2 [Boost]** again.\r\n\r\n**STRONGJUMP**: SEEYA! You start **[Flying]** as you leap around with your STRONG legs. You can choose to end your flight as an action, gaining **1 [WHAM]** as you soar directly towards a target. Uh oh!\r\n\r\n**IMPOSING PRESENCE**: MENACING… your looming figure shatters the target\'s confidence, making their **[Flourish]** rolls **[Inept]** next turn.\r\n\r\n**BLOCK OFF**: Where do you think YOU\'RE going? You plant your feet firmly in the ground as you get up close and personal with the target. The target\'s LET\'S STRIFE rolls are **[Godawful]** for **2 turns**.'),
('superiorUpgrades', 'SUPERIOR UPGRADES', 'OTHER', 'ROBOT', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Robot]', 'You’ve had your new limbs and/or body for a while now and, you gotta say… Surprising lack of extra arms on this bad boy. If you’re getting a mechanical pump biscuit, why stop there? Why not just make your blood into oil instead. Fuck it. Knife toes. You may pick a modified MUTATION move from the list below. These do not count as **[Cullbait]** for you, and instead all gain the **[Mechanical]** tag. Likewise, you do not get the original downsides for the moves. Choose one from the following:\r\n\r\n> **NATURAL WEAPONS**: You’ve gone beyond the use of basic abstrata. Maybe you have a giant hammer for an arm now. Maybe your hair is now made of wires! Whatever it is, you gain the NATURAL WEAPONS move from the MUTANTS list. However, each time you make use of your installed weapon, you take **1 [Drag]** as your body isn’t used to such intense abilities.\r\n\r\n> **BUG WINGS**: Far be it from anyone to tell you to just get a normal jetpack like the rest of us. You’ve decided to fly the old fashion way, with wings made out of what is probably shitty plastic wrap and coat hangers. You gain the BUG WINGS move from the MUTANTS list. Your wings aren’t as good as the real thing, unfortunately, and can only keep you **[Flying]** for **3 rounds**, before you are forced to return to the ground.\r\n\r\n> **ADDITIONAL EXTREMITIES**: You have an extra set of arms! Or legs? Or maybe you gave yourself a tail. Either way, you gain the EXTRA LIMB bonus from ORGANIC VARIANT. The weight of having fully functional arms bears down on you, though, giving you a permanent **-1 [Nerf]** to ACT FAST. This weight is physical of course. Psychologically, you’re freaking ecstatic to have four legs or whatever.\r\n\r\n> **UNNATURAL INNARDS**: For some reason, you decided to just go wild on your organs. That’s cool, man. Do your thing. You gain the ORGANIC VARIANT move from the mutants list, but you can’t use this option to take extra limbs as well. While your pusher may not be in your left hip, it’s definitely still more fragile, what with being tinkered with. Any time you are the subject of being hacked or **[Stunned]** you take **+1 [Somatic]** damage as your body reboots.\r\n\r\n');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('supersFortress', 'SUPER’S FORTRESS', 'OTHER', 'SUPERSCOUNDREL', '[Template][Basic][Locked: Superscoundrel]', 'Every super being needs their own inner sanctum. Troll Superman has his Fortress of Solitude, Troll Batman has his Batcave, the Troll Avengers have their tower, and so on. You are no exception. You gain access to a custom hiveblock and Downtime as listed below:\r\n\r\n**SUPER HIDEAWAY**\r\nThis is SICK! A cavern filled to the brim with super cool tech, vehicles, various weaponry, and big-ass TV to watch over the stemcluster! Here, you can plan out your next act of great heroism or villainy, and keep an eye on the changing tides to stay ahead of the curve. You can’t let your nemesis get ahead of you, after all!\r\n\r\n**DREAMING AND SCHEMING**\r\n**[Downtime]**\r\n\r\nAh yes, time to plot! You’ve got your blueprints to your left, freshly sharpened pencils to your right, and a 40oz cup of piping-hot coffee. Let’s do this thing! Roll **+PSP**. Note that the effects of this Downtime cannot stack.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You’re a gog damn GENIUS before your time! … Well, you would be, if you could actually read what the fuck you just wrote down. You start your next encounter **[Dumbfounded]**. Seriously, what is this, Troll Latin?\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Oh! This is! Hm! Nope. Absolute garbage. Into the incinerator. You start your next encounter **[Confused]** by how people actually make a plan.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Well… it’s something? Certainly not the best plan you’ve ever had. You\'ll figure it out next time.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Alright, we\'re getting somewhere! The basis of a plan lays itself out before you, and you\'re feeling good about it! You start your next encounter with **+1 [Boost]**!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Hell yeah! Look at this! Every entrance and exit marked, every step explained in detail, and you\'ve even got little diagrams about the chance of success of each option! You start your next encounter with **+2 [Boost]** and feeling **[Insightful]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Holy shit. You\'ve done it. This is the plan of all plans. Absolutely NOTHING could go wrong! Even a wriggler could be a mastermind with this! Not that you’d let your plans fall into the claws of a wriggler, because they’re idiots, and you are the greatest mind on this planet. You start your next encounter with **+2 [Boost]** and feeling **[Enlightened]**!\r\n\r\n'),
('superstitiousFeeling', 'SUPERSTITIOUS FEELING', 'OTHER', 'RAPSCALLINEER', '[Template][Advanced][One-off][locked: Rapscallineer]', 'You’ve been out on the sea for a long time. You’ve seen a LOT of things that most trolls would consider out of the ordinary, even for Alternia. You’re not new to superstitions, and neither are your crew! Over time, you’ve developed a range of sailorly superstitions that may range from silly to deeply serious. As a crew, select three things on the below list, and assign emotions to them respectively: One makes you **[Brave]**, one makes you **[Serious]** and one makes you **[Out-of-Control]**. When you’re faced with these things in an encounter, you begin feeling the associated emotion for two rounds. This effect cannot be triggered more than once per encounter per emotion.\r\n\r\n> Purrbeast lusii\r\n> Spilled Jade blood\r\n> Referring to the Condescence or Heiress by name\r\n> Non-golds with more or less than two horns\r\n> Rhymes\r\n> Soulbots\r\n> Violets living on land\r\n> McMiracle’s\r\n> Horn piercings\r\n> Mentioning a hemoanon’s true blood color\r\n> Ligma, henway and updog\r\n> Nicknames that don’t follow the 6 letter format\r\n> Doom FRAYMOTIFs\r\n> Zas (Derse/Mind players)\r\n> Anyone wearing a **[Head]** **[Fashion]** item\r\n> Voidrot\r\n> Mention or presence of the SIMPTOMS **[Affliction]**\r\n> The numbers 413, 612, 1025 and 1111\r\n\r\n'),
('supremeJustydion', 'SUPREME JUSTYDION\r\n', 'TEAL', 'ADULT', '[Teal][Locked: Adult]', 'You are judge, jury, and executioner. Your mission is ordained by someone very important and very powerful - maybe even the Empress herself. Only teals with a celebrated and lauded career are allowed to be assigned as Justydions, and you are the first and last they send in to hunt down the most wanted and highly dangerous of enemies. The crime is their foul existence, THE SENTENCE IS DEATH. You are given a JUSTYDION GAVEL which has the **STURDYKIND** Abstrata Upgrade already added, with room for one more upgrade. If you did not have it already, you gain the teal move **DEAD OR ALIVE**, and when HUNTING a target your **MAX** threshold is always 18+. You can **[Strife]** opponents who aren\'t your target only if they are actively helping your target. If your target is of a higher level than you, has both **[Ultra]** slots filled, or is a Level 4 Monster, you may take an action to lock both of you in a **TRIAL BY COMBAT**. In this TRIAL, you and your target have all emotions cleared and replaced with **[Dead Serious]** and **[Numb]**. Nobody may target either you or your target, whether friend or foe.\r\n'),
('surmount', 'SURMOUNT', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Physical][Strife][Locked: Admiral]', 'HAVE AT THEE! You are exceptionally well trained in hand-to-hand combat with the intent of quashing foes at the head of your armies. You\'re kind of awesome like that! When you want to conquer a foe, roll **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: YOU\'VE BEEN ANNEXED! OH NO! You stumble backward in horror and take **2 [Somatic]** damage. Your next **[Strife]** roll is **[Inept]**, even if it couldn\'t normally be.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Fuck! That smarts! You take **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You aren\'t hitting them, but you\'re on the offensive! You gain **1 [WHAM]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: A well-placed blow! Typical of your skill level. You do **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Keep the pressure up! You do **2 [Somatic]** damage, or **1 [Somatic]** damage and make their next **[Strife]** roll **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: IS THIS A WAR CRIME? You do **3 [Somatic]** damage, or 2 and make their next **[Strife]** roll **[Godawful]**.'),
('surprisingCompassion', 'SURPRISING COMPASSION', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Open][Recharge: 3][Manipulate]', 'Hey, look, are you okay? Yeah, that looks like it sucked. C\'mon, chin up— I\'m here to help, alright? You\'re not like, a wimp or something, but there\'s something genuinely tender about the compassion you show for others when you need to. When you want to check in on someone, roll **+PLC**. \r\n\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Did you say something wrong?! Shit, shit, shit! FUCK! YOU\'RE SUCH A FUCKUUUUP! GRAH! The target starts **[Crying]**, and you become **[Stressed]**. \r\n\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Yeah, you just made them feel worse. The target becomes **[Sad]**.\r\n\r\n\r\n**OK**: It\'s… a surprise that you care? Not a bad one, either. The target takes **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Huh… you do care. You give the target **2 [Boost]**, or give them **1 [Boost]** and remove a negative **[Emotion]**. You can\'t remove **[Heightened]** emotions. \r\n\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You know just what to say, somehow! You get a **GOOD**, but the target is **[Hopeful]** for **3 turns**.\r\n\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Wow! You\'re probably the best friend ever! You get a **GREAT**, but the target is **[Inspired]** instead.'),
('suspiciousStats', 'SUSPICIOUS STATS', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Passive][Magic][Psionic][Locked: Metagamer]', 'Hey. Weren\'t you really bad at that roll earlier? Why is your modifier a +6 now? How did that happen? Strange. Peculiar, even. One might even call it suspicious. Every time you roll poorly, you very subtly change your modifier. Just to ensure you don\'t screw up again. When you get a **BAD** roll, you raise the stat the roll used by 1. On a **MIN**, raise it by 2. These work in reverse however; rolling a **GREAT** takes away 1 and a **MAX** takes away 2 (but only from what you’ve built up, never your original stat!) These increases are cumulative, and reset at the end of the encounter.'),
('suspiciousStranger', 'SUSPICIOUS STRANGER', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Lengthy][One-Off][Sus][Unlock: Espiacrooner]', 'You are a trainee Espiacrooner, a master of disguise and dashing spy. Whether you intend to work as an Imperial Agent rooting out traitors as a secret police member or a private spy working among Violet Celebrities or within Esotericist Magic Circles, your saving grace is your quick wit, your excellent acting abilities, and your ability to take on any role. You are **[Talented]** at +RAS. You are so good at disguising yourself that you may as well be a dozen different trolls… which is exactly what you want people to believe! When you’re IN DISGUISE, you can play the long con and use a fake character sheet without other players even realising. Upon taking this move, you can create up to four different disguises of any caste except for hemoanons, limebloods, Cloistered Jadebloods, purplebloods, fuchsiabloods, and kids. You create these like you would with a normal character sheet, using the typical stat spread. Instead of using your normal levels for your disguises, you gain **FOUR ESPIACROONER LEVELS** when you take this move. Of course, having such an important job means there’s important rules to follow, such as…\r\n\r\n- You cannot create disguises of your own caste.\r\n- Your disguise\'s caste tree must follow the rules of the **ALTERNATE PATH** move, excluding the 5 **[Advanced]** move limit and caste locks- a cerulean ESPIACROONER can have a bronzeblooded FOLKLORIST disguise, even though they themselves could not use ALTERNATE PATH to take the FOLKLORIST tree.\r\n- You cannot take any **[Psionic]** or **[Magic]** caste moves while IN DISGUISE. Additionally, for moves other than your **[Unlock]** and its subsequent **[Locked]** moves, you must rely on **[Open]** moves.\r\n- Moves that give you an item automatically (ex. **INVENTOR [Unlock]**) do not actually give you the item, merely a cheap, narrative imitation.\r\n- Disguises must be submitted at level 1 before use, though they don’t count towards your weekly limit- just be sure to specify they’re a disguise sheet, not a normal troll’s!\r\n- You cannot access caste-exclusive-chats of your disguises (ex. a jade disguise cannot access Cavernspace), nor can you join ORG chats (unless you yourself are an ORG member).\r\n- Your disguises cannot be **[Eerie]** or have a **MUTATION** that you don’t have on your original sheet, though you can give them ones you already have without spending **ESPIACROONER LEVELS**.\r\n- When **IN DISGUISE**, you retain nothing from your original sheet except **ESPIACROONER** moves, **[Eerie] TEMPLATE** moves, **[Mutant]** moves, **VOIDROT** moves, **ROBOT/CYBORG TEMPLATE** moves, your **LUX/VP** inventory, and your own **HP**. How you narratively disguise these things is up to you, but the mechanical effects stay!\r\n- Things that change your appearance (ex. **[Bloodied]** or **[Crying]**, going **A MODE MOSTE GRIM** or **A MODE MOSTE TRICKSY**, entering a **MOONFRENZY** or a **BLOODHYSTERIA**) will reveal you as a spy. \r\n'),
('swarmware', 'SWARMWARE', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Chicanery][Psionic][Tech][Recharge: 1][Locked: Beekeeper]', 'YOU\'RE IN. Your exceptional experience with biotech combined with the tools you carry everywhere means that you can perform some stunts that are pretty dang impressive! Maybe you use them to do your job and help out with infrastructural engineering. Maybe you\'re a notorious hacker. Either way, when you wanna alter some tech, roll **+RAS**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Aw, fuck! You attracted some bad attention, or clicked the wrong link, or whatever! Either way, you spawn a DRONE STRIKE Hazard. Take cover!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Nothing happens. Ugh!\r\n\r\n**OK**: Getting there, just a second… your next BUZZWARE roll is **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: HACKED! Select one of the following effects.\r\n\r\n> **LIGHTS OUT**: You cut the lights! GASP! All trolls become **[Hidden]** for **2 turns**.\r\n> **VEHICLE JAM**: You mess with the biotech inside a vehicle to make it unresponsive. The targeted vehicle\'s VEHICULATE rolls are **[Godawful]** for a turn. \r\n> **DATABUZZ**: You extract information from the powerlarvae of nearby devices to learn more about the device and its wielder. You get the effects of a PSYCHOANALYZE PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll.\r\n> **PHEROBRICK**: You send a special pheremonecode into a target item that causes its biotech to spontaneously explode. It takes 3 damage. This doesn\'t affect items that are organic, like apples or playing cards.\r\n> **GUNKSPLODE**: Oh no! You make their Sylladex\' honey react with itself to explode! Their pockets become all gunky, and their next attempt to use any item becomes **[Lengthy]**.\r\n> **EEEEEEEE**: You cause the biotech inside a piece of tech to start to scream! This is abjectly horrifying. The target is **[Deafened]** and **[Scared]** for a round.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Nice! You sure hacked them! You get two **GOOD** options.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: MOTHER OF ALL HACKS! You hit them with three **GOOD** options.'),
('swashbuckle', 'SWASHBUCKLE', 'OTHER', 'UNIVERSAL', '[Flourish][Physical]', 'You’re not like the other trolls. You’ve got aspirations, and power, and your bulge is huge. You’ve never failed at anything, ever. So why not go the extra mile… and push yourself to the limit? Each individual SWASHBUCKLE option has the **[Recharge: 3]** tag; spice it up and try new stuff! When you want to do something in an extremely risky and stupid way, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You trip over and land on your face, you dumb fuck. You take **1 [Somatic]** damage and gain the **[Floorbound]** condition.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You try to look really cool and do what you set out to do, but you can’t quite do it. You waste this action trying, and gain **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You almost had it, but just about failed! At least you’re able to balance yourself and prevent any negative consequences.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Aha! You pulled it off! You can do one of the following:\r\n\r\n> **ACROBATIC FUCKING PIRHOUETTE**: You jump high in the air while somersaulting. You look really cool doing this, and you receive **1 [WHAM]**.\r\n\r\n> **ONE-LINER**: You say something incredibly cool, and honestly, it really hypes you up. Yeah, you ARE that bitch! You reduce the **[Recharge]** and increase your **[Buildup]** for all moves by 1. \r\n\r\n> **PCHOOOOO**: You propel yourself into the air with a powerful leap, wall jump, or otherwise projectile yourself skyward! You can hit **[Flying]** targets as if they weren’t flying until the end of your turn.\r\n\r\n> **POSE STRIKE**: HAH! Strike a pose to show the opponent how cool you are mid-strife. Only COOL people pose in combat, after all! You start feeling **[Proud]**.\r\n\r\n> **SWEET TRICKS**: You do some sweet flourishing with your weapon and you\'re so dang proud of yourself for looking so fucking cool that you gain **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **YOUTH ROLL**: Duck for cover! You become **[Hidden]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Oh snap! Choose one of the following:\r\n\r\n> **FINISHING MOVE**: You prepare to do some massive harm. You get **3 [WHAM]**, but cannot use any **[Strife]** roll for **3 turns** after spending this **[WHAM]**. After landing the hit, you become **[Exhausted]**.\r\n\r\n> **GODDAMN**: You do what you set out to do, and you do it so well that you stay in motion while you do! You get **1 [Boost]**, as well as one **GOOD** effect. This effect has no **[Recharge]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: With a flourish of style, you push yourself past your limits… and BEYOND! You either choose one **GOOD** roll and get **3 [Boost]**, or one **GREAT** effect and **2 [Boost]**.'),
('sweepHouse', 'SWEEP HOUSE', 'OTHER', 'MAID', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Maid]', 'You have a very specific set of skills, and you use them in pretty limited ways! It\'d be plain irresponsible to use them however you wanted, after all - better to stick to form and discipline. You\'re great at form and discipline, anyways! At the start of each encounter, choose one of your highest stats - no sense in branching out when you know what you\'re good at. The first time each round you roll a **GREAT** or higher with that stat, you gain a +1 **[Buff]** to it for 2 rounds. This **[Buff]** stacks with itself, therefore refreshing its duration each time you gain it, and ignores the usual +5 **[Buff]** cap. No stopping you once you\'ve hit your stride!\r\n'),
('sweetLooks', 'SWEET LOOKS', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][One-Off][Passive][Locked: Delinquent]', 'Hey, you aren\'t a slob. That\'s what separates you from the other scumbags on the streets. You\'ve got STYLE. You gain access to the DELINQUENT\'S DO Head Fashion Item (+1 GRT, -1 PSP) as you comb your hair to make it look just-so. You can combine your DELINQUENT\'S DO with other fashion items to create the following collections. You aren\'t tied to any one collection; mix it up for different occasions!\r\n\r\n**HEARTBREAKER**: (DELINQUENT\'S DO, BASIC BUTTON-UP (but opened just a little too much), SICKASS SHADES, SPEEDY SNEAKERS) **[+2 GRT, +2 PLC, -2 PSP, -2 IMG]** Yeah, baby! You\'re dressed to impress, with your hair all greased up. Trolls who might be attracted to you must roll 1d8 at the end of every encounter; on an 8, they are exposed to the SIMPTOMS Affliction.\r\n\r\n**MUSICAL FREAK**: (DELINQUENT\'S DO, SICKASS SHADES, GRAPHICALLY VIOLENT TEE, JJEANS) **[+2 GRT, +2 IMG, -2 RAS, -2 PSP]** Out here repping your music genre of choice, I see! Your hair is styled to represent your favoured subculture, and you look sick as fuck. You are **[Talented]** at FRAYMOTIF rolls, and it is **[Buildup: 3]**.\r\n\r\n**BIKER BITCH**: (DELINQUENT\'S DO, LUSUSLEATHER COAT, FINGERLESS STRANGLERS, JJEANS) **[+2 GRT, +2 HUB, -2 APP, -2 PSP]** With your hair tied up, sleeveless jackets on and your trusty bike roaring, you\'re ready to DRIVE tonight. While riding a SMALL VEHICLE, you may still roll **[Physical]** moves. You are **[Talented]** at VEHICULATE rolls. \r\n\r\n**ANARCHYFIT**: (DELINQUENT\'S DO, FACEMASK, LIL BEANIE, FINGERLESS STRANGLERS) **[+2 GRT, +2 RAS, -2 GRA, -2 IMG]** Violence on the streets, yeah! Everyone\'s here, and ready to throw hands! And of course… your hair looks immaculate as it curls out from your hat. You gain **1 [Boost]** every time an ally gets a **GREAT** or a **MAX** roll. For this collection alone, DELINQUENT\'S DO can be worn with the LIL BEANIE.'),
('swindlery', 'SWINDLERY', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Recharge: 2][Manipulate][Locked: Gamblignant]', 'C\'mon, they can trust you. Why wouldn\'t they? Alright, you get it, you\'re kind of a con troll. But what a loveable scamp of a con troll, right? Riiiiight. When you want to disarm people, roll **+APP**.\r\n\r\nMIN: You had all the subtlety of a freightscuttler crashing into a powertower! That is to say: none at all! You become **[Humiliated]** for the encounter.\r\n\r\nBAD: You flash a winning smile. It is met with cold stares. You are **[Embarrassed]** for the encounter.\r\n\r\nOK: You… well, you make them raise an eyebrow. That\'s something! They take **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\nGOOD: SWUNDLED! Take one of the following effects…\r\n\r\n> SLEAZED: Come on, give me a smiiiile. The target is **[Charmed]**. You can\'t use this move during combat.\r\n> ROULETTE: Test your luck! Roll 1d8. You roll some dice and see how fortune favours the opponent. On an odd number, the opponent takes **4 [Drag]**. On an even, the target takes **4 [Boost]**.\r\n> WOOOOW!: That\'s lucky, friend, that\'s very very lucky! You stoke the target\'s ego, making them feel **[Icarian]** for **2 rounds**.\r\n> GREED-BOOST: You could have it ALL, son! You convince someone that wealth is all they need, and for a moment, their vision clouds. They become **[Talented]** at **+APP** and lose all other **[Talents]** for **a turn**.\r\n\r\nGREAT: Oh yeah, you\'re on a winning streak! You get a **GOOD**, and **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\nMAX: Wow, who needs luck?! You get a GREAT, but SLEAZE **[Fascinates]** the target, ROULETTE always gets an Odd result, WOOOOW! lasts for the encounter and GREED-BOOST lasts for the encounter.\r\n'),
('switcharoo', 'SWITCHAROO', 'OTHER', 'ROGUE', '[Class][Basic][Physical][Buildup: 3][Recharge: 3][Locked: Rogue]', 'POV, I\'m chasing you. I\'ve got an axe in my hand, and I look mad as hell. You glance over your shoulder and realize I\'m gaining on you. You smile, and decide it\'s time to put on some of your roguish razzle dazzle. Suddenly, you jump, and slide on the floor. My momentum carries me forward, and I\'m forced to stumble over you. I glance over my shoulder, and realize I\'ve dropped my axe. You jump to your feet, pick up my axe, and start chasing me. MFW I\'ve been Rogued. When you want to switch it up a little, roll **+RAS, +APP** or **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You have in fact fucked up a little bit! Whoops! You transfer all your opponent’s negative statuses onto.. yourself. They feel great! So great! You super do not! \r\n\r\n**BAD**: All of your opponent\'s **[Drag]** goes to you. You maybe screwed up. Maybe.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Nothing happens! Yay! \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Eat concussion, bulgewad. You transfer half your **[Drag]** onto your opponent, as well as any negative status effects they\'ve inflicted on you. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Yeah, how do you like it!!! You transfer all your **[Drag]** and all negative status conditions onto your opponent.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You floss over their prone form, free as a bird while they cry under the weight of their own hubris. Your opponent takes all of your **[Drag]**, all of your **[Negative] [Emotions]**, and all of your negative status effects.\r\n\r\n'),
('systemDischarge', 'SYSTEM DISCHARGE', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Recharge: 2][Psionic][Locked: Battery]', 'Listen you’re a potent psionic, and that means holding back your raw awesome power a lot of the time so that you don’t hurt yourself and others.  Blah blah blah, world of cardboard speech. Whether or not you’re actually good at keeping a handle on your psionics, there’s a time and a place to cut loose.  That time is right now, and that place right is directly at this asshole you’re about to eviscerate. As an action, you can convert your built-up CHARGE into **[Wham]** at a rate of **2 CHARGE** to **1 [Wham]** for a maximum of **3 [Wham]** at a time. Using **[Wham]** gained from this move gives you **1 [Weakness]** for a round and **1 [Drag]** for each **[Wham]** used. Don’t burn yourself out!'),
('systemicSpite', 'SYSTEMIC SPITE', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Passive]', 'Blood. Ichor. Life-force. Aqua vitae. The stuff that runs through your veins, keeps you alive and determines where you stand in society… whether you like it or not. Well, what if you DON’T like it? Huh?! Ever thought about that?! Fuck you and fuck your pecking order, you scream to the powers that be, we may not all bleed the same, but at the end of the night, when the sun comes up to burn us all, we all bleed regardless! This is the rallying call behind many hemoanons, and even for those who don’t subscribe to such ideals, the system still is their enemy for the simple crime of not conforming to their order. Whether you want to smash the system, reform it, or simply survive it, you are hemoanon. You bleed for no caste. When you take this move, select your Position and Reason; these will determine the benefits of your anonymity and the moves you can take from going grey.\r\n\r\nHEMOANONIMITY CATEGORIES\r\nPOSITION:\r\nFull-time: You are fully anonymous - you have left behind all ties to your caste to take up the anon lifestyle. You do not take a caste tree; instead, the Full-time version of this move can be taken at entry instead. In exchange for not having a caste tree, you have full access to all moves on the Hemoanon page, including those that say [Locked: Full-Time]. You also gain a [Talent] in a stat of your choosing.\r\nPart-time: You take anonymity seriously, but still retain some aspects from your birth caste. Perhaps you are an anon who still uses your caste-relevant psionics to fight, or utilizes your legislacerator training! With this option, you can take Hemoanon as a template without having to give up your caste tree. However, your Wealth Level does drop to Poor if it wasn’t there already. You may take the Entry move, as well as two [Basic] and [Advanced] moves not under [Locked: Full-Time]- you’re not *that* committed to the bit.\r\nAnalogue: You are not so much divorced from as you are... distant from your caste. You’re in grey, yes, but it doesn’t really matter to you if your true caste is revealed. Perhaps you’re a highblood trying to be more approachable to your rebel-aligned friends, or you just connect with the anon community more than your own without fully leaning into it. Instead of taking this entry move you take the HEMOANALOGUE Perfectly Generic Move now, and do not gain access to the rest of the template.\r\n	\r\nREASON:\r\nHiding from the Past: You have a potentially volatile past, or perhaps you did something that wasn’t good, or maybe someone’s trying to track you down, and you’ve had to go underground! Regardless of circumstances, you’re hiding something (besides the obvious) dark, dangerous or any of the above. Any [Analyze] moves made against you are at a -2 [Nerf].\r\nPersecution: Some people outside the anon community berate those who choose to go hemoanonymous. You never HAD a choice. Likely, there’s something wrong with you in the Empire’s eyes. Maybe you’re a mutant with mutations that make it impossible to blend in with your birth caste, or maybe your blood color doesn’t align with the hemospectrum at all. Because of all this, you’ve gotten pretty good at telling if someone is.. Well.. with you. You can judge if someone would kick your ass or not, and if they would, you gain 1 [WHAM], which cannot be dispelled unless you take 3 [Somatic] damage.\r\nIdealism: You believe in an Alternia where trolls of all Castes are equal, and most people higher up (alongside the Empire, too), don’t agree! Unfortunately, if they were to know your caste or any personal details, you would probably have several Drones, or even federal agents, knocking at your door! Because of your more ideal tendencies, you’re terrific at making convincing arguments! Your rolls for [Verbal] attacks are at a +2 [Buff].\r\nSocietal Roles: Societal roles suck. You’ve found this out firsthand- whether you’re a former indigo being pushed into high society, a jade confined to the caverns or anything else along these lines, being lumped in with your caste, its stereotypes and the post-Alternian future that comes along with it gives you significant distress. You gain the Entry of your formerly associated caste tree now, but do not gain the [Talent] it gives. You may take 1 Basic and 1 Advanced move from this tree as well. Even if you don\'t want to be like this, it\'s hard to leave behind what you\'ve learned.\r\nOther: It’s... complicated! You’re complicated and have a very deep backstory! Choose the effect of one Reason and flavor it to your liking. Maybe your Idealism is based on defending yourself against those who would crush those dreams, or you fight against Persecution with your caste-typical abilities. It doesn’t matter if you’re complicated to others, you have your own damn reasons!\r\n'),
('tacticalManeuvering', 'TACTICAL MANEUVERING', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Analyze][Mental][Locked: Boss]', 'As a commanding figure, you know that trolls are not the only pieces on the chessboard you need to worry about; the battlefield is just another tool you can use to get victory. Hmm, yes, that rock over there could be a hazard… noting that down for later… When you want to use your perception to reveal potential battlefield advantages, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You hum and haw loudly, and your opponent sees an opening. They can make a **[Free]** **[Strife]** or **[Chicanery]** roll which isn’t affected by any nerfs you may have applied.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You furrow your brow as you try to spot something useful, but alas, there’s nothing.\r\n\r\n**OK**: While you don’t quite find anything, you don’t waste time either. You don’t spend an action.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Ah, an advantage, over there! Perhaps a dangling curtain, or a weak floorboard… you receive **2 [Hold]**, which you can spend on a **GOOD** **[Chicanery]** result. **[Hold]** takes one action to spend, but doesn\'t require rolling.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Ohoho! Your opponent is in for quite the nasty surprise! You gain **2 [Hold]**, but you can spend these **[Hold]** on **GREAT** rolls too.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: OHOHOHOHO! PERHAPS IF YOU’D COME PREPARED, YOU WOULDN’T BE IN THIS SPOT! You can immediately use a **GREAT** **[Chicanery]** roll, and you get **3 GREAT** **[Hold]**.'),
('takeAChillPill', 'TAKE A CHILL PILL', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Recharge: 3]', 'AAAAAAAARGH, YOU STUPID NOOKGOBBLING WRIGGLERFOOD PIECE OF-\r\n\r\nInhale.\r\n\r\nExhale.\r\n\r\nSorry. Let’s try that again! You’ve learned how to take a breath to stop… you know, going on a fucking rampage and gutting everyone around you. These coping techniques have made life… easier for you, sometimes! Who’d have thought? You can spend an action to swallow your anger; whenever you gain **[WHAM]**, you can convert it into **[Heal]** as an action, stopping you from lashing the fuck out at everyone around you. This can’t be **[WHAM]** gained from NOBLE SACRIFICE, but can be for FINISHING MOVE. You can also use an action to end the **[Enraged]** or **[Out of Control]** emotions on yourself, gaining **2 or 3 [Boost]** respectively as you swallow your fury. You can’t become **[Enraged]** again for **3 turns** if you do that.'),
('takeMattersIntoYourOwnHands', 'TAKE MATTERS INTO YOUR OWN HANDS', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'CIS', '[Template][Advanced][Locked: CIS]', 'You\'re tired of relying on the HET to do everything for you! Those losers have no idea what they\'re doing! In fact… you\'re going to take a special mission to do it yourself. Ha! That\'ll show them! You can take any one HET move, and give it the CIS tag instead. That\'ll teach those posers!\n\n'),
('takeThePiss', 'TAKE THE PISS', 'OTHER', 'BARD', '[Class][Basic][Reaction][Recharge: 2][Locked: Bard]', 'C\'mon, you were just messing around! What the hell\'s the big idea??? Gosh, SOME people just can\'t take a JOKE nowadays. Sigh, truly comedy is illegal. Whenever someone uses a move to circumvent, remove, or otherwise ignore an effect you put on them from a **[Class], [Aspect]**, or **[Chicanery]** move, you can use a **[Reaction]** to give them 2 **[Drag]** as you rail against them for not being able to take a JOKE, LOSER.'),
('talesOfExploits', 'TALES OF EXPLOITS', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][One-Off][Manipulate][Locked: Dungeoneer]', 'Your journeys through the dungeons below make for inspiring stories! And hey, your stories can sometimes give people trying to kill you pause..? Hey, this reminds you of the time you found a skeletal troll the size of a building underground! When you want to tell (partially embellished) stories, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: SHUT UP BRO! You make your ally start **[Dissociating]** or your enemy becomes **[Enraged]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Sounds… fake. Your target isn\'t affected by this at all.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Uh-huh… pretty cool..! Your target half-listens, and gains either **1 [Boost]** or **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Hm. That\'s actually pretty interesting. Your ally feels **[Peaceful]**, or your enemy feels… Well, they pause. Just for a moment. They are **[Charmed]** for **2 rounds**, before they shake it off.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Whoa— your story is actually really interesting! Your ally feels **[Serene]**, or your enemy is totally hooked. Hey, wait, no, tell the story! They are **[Charmed]** for the encounter.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Call yourself Troll Schezeharade, cuz your stories could keep people entertained for 1,001 nights! Your ally feels **[Serene]** and totally immune to **[Drag]**, and your enemy becomes totally **[Fascinated]** by you.'),
('talkItOver', 'TALK IT OVER', 'BLOOD', 'BLOOD', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Blood]', 'Not all fights need to end with someone about to get completely ass-wiped. It’s okay to call it sometimes; it’s better to live to fight another day, after all. When you want to ask someone to stop fighting, whether it’s to surrender or to show mercy, you can spend an action to offer them a way out. They can either choose to give in, and you both heal all negative status effects, or to keep going, upon which you become **[Quickened]** for **2 rounds** and gain **1 [WHAM]** as you tense and try to survive the final showdown!'),
('talkOfTheTown', 'TALK OF THE TOWN', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Passive]', 'By now, no matter where you go, people know you and are willing to talk to you. Your RUMORHUNGER **[Downtime]** rolls are **[Tiered Up]** so long as you are in the community you selected from COUNTRY VS. CITY. If you are an ITINERANT, you get a +2 to ALL your RUMORHUNGER **[Downtime]** rolls instead. You don\'t need to have the move to take this, but the community you pick here must be the same there if you take it later.'),
('tapThat', 'TAP THAT', 'OTHER', 'QUADRANT', '[Quadrant][Passive]\r\n', 'Ah, young love. Whether you rushed into this in a single night of shortsighted life choices or you\'ve been suffering in slowburn for the last half-sweep, you\'ve got a shiny new matesprit with whom to build a life. \r\n\r\n**NEW QUADS (1-4 IRL WEEKS)**: You always have the **[Charmed]** condition when your matesprit is in the encounter with you. \r\n\r\n**ESTABLISHED RELATIONSHIP (1-11 IRL MONTHS)**: You gain **2 [Boost]** when your matesprit enters the encounter with you. Additionally, you may give them a kiss to heal them **1 HP** as a **[One-Off]** action.\r\n\r\n**ROCK SOLID (1 YEAR+)**: You become immune to the **[Charmed]** condition, and gain **2 [Boost]** when your matesprit appears in an encounter with you. Additionally, you may give them a kiss to heal them **1 HP** as a **[One-Off]** action.\r\n\r\n**QUAD BONDED**: You become immune to the **[Charmed]** AND **[Fascinated]** conditions, and gain **3 [Boost]** when your matesprit appears in an encounter with you. Additionally, you may give them a kiss to heal them **1 HP** as a **[One-Off]** action.\r\n'),
('targetLocked', 'TARGET LOCKED', 'OTHER', 'ROBOT', '[Template][Basic][Reaction][Recharge: 2][Analyze][Tech][Locked: Robot]', 'Whether you have motion sensors installed in your eyes, or your blaster arm just moves on its own, you know how to keep your target from getting away from you. When someone tries to go **[Hidden]** around you, or attempts to ABSCOND from you, roll **+PSP** as a **[Reaction]**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Not only do they escape your sights, but you also might’ve really fried your circuitry? You take a -2 **[Nerf]** to **[Physical]** moves for the duration of the encounter. You can not use this move again for the duration of the encounter.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Yep. You sure are just staring at them real hard. It’s no wonder they still get away. Did you even activate your infrared? Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Your cool targeting system does the thing where it attempts really hard to track your opponent, but they manage to get away at the last second! You gain **1 [Boost]** as you ready to seek them out manually.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Hah! Gotcha. You aren’t going anywhere, pal. You manage to keep track of your target, causing whatever move they tried to use to fail! Nice!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: ZOOM! ENHANCE! Not only do you lock on, but you lock on real well. You even get those terrible blurry mugshots of them in your eye or something. Your opponent’s move fails, and you get a **+1 [Buff]** to your next **[Physical]** move against them.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: They said it couldn’t be done. But here you are. Doing it. You lock on so hard, you’re able to practically see your opponent’s next move. It’s really, probably just some intense internal calculations, but it\'s cool to think you can just see the future for a second. You get a **GREAT**, and your opponent’s next move is **[Tiered Down]**.\r\n\r\n'),
('teacherTeacher', 'TEACHER, TEACHER!', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Unlock: Auxiliatrice]', 'SCHOOLFEEDING. Oh, those dreaded words! Learning… studying… tests… you, as an Auxillatrice, are in charge of all that. Normally, that means you educate wrigglers and help hatch grubs brought up from the Undercaverns. Some Auxiliatrices, however, mentor other trolls your age at Private Schoolfeeding classes or even act as one on one tutors. Your lessons range from teaching how society works, to how to cook delicious meals to how to not get eaten by hellbarks. They guarantee the survival of the next generation of grubs and the continuation of your current generation. And you, by necessity, have to be very good at your job. You are **[Talented]** at **+PLC**. Your stern gaze ensures that people always behave; when someone in an encounter gets an **[Emotion]**, you can choose to flip it and get the **[Emotion]**\'s opposite. **[Enraged]** troll, would you please be **[Focused]**? This takes an action.\r\n'),
('tealsTalk', 'TEALS TALK', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][One-Off][Analyze][Manipulate][Mental]', 'Water cooler gossip. Canteen rumours. Peeking over the cubicles at the Officeblock Supreme with an \"Oh, haven\'t you heard?\" Teals are voracious consumers of knowledge, especially the scandalous kind. Oh, yes- if something happens with a Teal, the first to know are other Teals. You are always **[Talented]** at RUMORHUNGER rolls. You also seek out gossip like there\'s no tomorrow in order to gain an edge over your companions; when you want to use this edge, roll **+RAS**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You accidentally reveal your OWN secret. How could you do this, you dumb weaselblood?! You gain the **[Scared]** condition and lose all your **[Boost]**. This overrides ALL OUT OF VACATION DAYS.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You try to unveil this huge dark secret to them, but you just reveal a dark secret of a random stranger. This is very interesting to the target, and they take **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You know their Caegerscore, but that\'s not exactly useful.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Hmmm. Yes, I know all about you. I\'m sure your dubiously legal trading card collection is going well, right..? Your thinly veiled blackmail **[Stresses]** the target. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Oh, you thought nobody would find out? That\'s adorable. You have the receipts all here… oh, god, this is real! The target is **[Agitated]**!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: And you\'re pretty sure… everyone else you know knows too! This is the talk of the Officeblock, friend! Your in-detail knowledge of their dark secrets not only **[Agitates]** them, but they can\'t even gain **[Boost]** for **three turns** either! Any **[Boost]** they had is reset to 0! Yikes!'),
('teamPlayingPsion', 'TEAM PLAYING PSION', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Passive][Psionic]', 'FFFFFFINE. Good game. Well played. You\'ve been making strides in learning not to be a huge fucking bulgehead to everyone at all times. You even play well on teams, sometimes? You get the following STANDBY moves you can use in a TEAM STRIFE.\r\n\r\n> **POWER SHARE**: KYAAAAA! You use SWASHBUCKLE, except that it has the **[Psionic]** tag. You transfer the effect of your SWASHBUCKLE into your STRUGGLING troll! This still uses **+HUB**; it takes a cool guy to give their power away.\r\n\r\n> **HUYAAAAAHHH…**: You focus hard, and give everyone a boost to their strength. You take a **[Lengthy]** action to give everyone on your team **1 [Boost]**.'),
('teamworker', 'TEAMWORKER', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'Whether it’s training Snazzards or training other Bureaucrats, you’ve gotten very good at working with others, delegating tasks, etcetera. After all, teamwork makes the dream work, right? In a TEAM STRIFE with you, allied trolls on STANDBY have access to the following TEAM STRIFE moves…\r\n\r\n> **COMMUNICATE**: This is what’s going wrong on my side! What’s going on over there? This WORDPLAY roll lets you and an ally split your **[Boost]** between you both evenly as you help one another out. On a **GREAT**, you both also gain **1 extra [Boost]**, and on a **MAX**, make that **2 [Boost]** to both of you.\r\n\r\n> **SHARE RESPONSIBILITY**: Come on, you got this! When an ally makes a **[Lengthy]** move, you can spend a **[Reaction]** to aid them, making it only take **1 action**.\r\n\r\n> **BACKUP PLAN**: You didn’t succeed, and that’s okay! We’ve got someone else who can do it, too! If an ally failed an **[Open]** move roll within the last turn, you may attempt to roll it yourself.\r\n\r\n> ALL-OUT ATTACK! TOGETHER, TEAM! Everyone can roll FINISHING MOVE at once, and trolls on STANDBY can use their next action to make a single **[Strife]** roll against the enemy team each. The moves aren’t **[Talented]** and if the enemy team isn’t defeated by this attack, your team becomes **[Agitated]** as well as **[Exhausted]**.'),
('teamworkMakesTheDreamWork', 'TEAMWORK MAKES THE DREAM WORK', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Mental][Locked: Jock]', 'There\'s no point in just claiming glory for yourself! What about your friends? Give them a HUWAAAAH, why don\'t you? That\'ll push them to compete as hard as you do! You may spend an action to shout out to your allies and cheer them on. When you do so, add up all your allies **[Boost]** and your own, and divide it up equally. Lets GOOO, team!'),
('technicianeer', 'TECHNICIANEER', 'BRONZE', 'ADULT', '[Bronze][Locked: Adult]', 'Like a modern Shovelier, you have a decent amount of knowhow on the topic of ships and the innerworkings of different mechanical things, like robots and various work drones. However, your efforts are more focused on breaking down and scrapping the space junk that accumulates from ships going haywire and brutal skirmishes between heretics and aliens. You can fix up a drone and patch burning holes in ships just fine, but you\\\'re typically just being shipped around to wrecked ships and abandoned stations to cut away all the useful stuff so it can be repurposed. As an action, you can mark a Robot Monster as Scrap. You deal +1 damage to Scrap and also inflict 1 **[Drag]** extra when you give **[Drag]** or a negative Status Effect to Scrap. You may also take an action to roll **+PSP** to **[Heal]** an allied Robot, restoring 1 **HP** on a **GOOD**, 2 **HP** on a **GREAT**, and 3 **HP** on a **MAX**. You achieve nothing on an **OK** or lower. Finally, you still work well against active enemy craft. When you roll to **[Strife]** against a VEHICLE, you may replace the effects of a **GREAT** with the ability to immediately HIJACK it as you cut away an entrance into the cockpit.'),
('telefauna', 'TELEFAUNA', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Passive][Psionic][Locked: Summoner]', 'You know a lusus\' body language well, and can also kinda read their minds. This makes it especially easy for you to tango with monsters! All rolls made by Lusii against you are **[Inept]** as you know what they\'re gonna do before they do.'),
('telemaster', 'TELEMASTER', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Psychic]', 'Your telekinesis is all-powerful; with enough practice, you could probably throw a planet at someone! For now, though, you’ll have to be content with floating around and smashing people through walls. You gain access to HERO MODE through your INCREDIBLE IMAGINATION. Whenever you start a turn at or below **half your max HP**, you gain **1 ESP** as your psionics flare up in your defense, grabbing at anything and everything around you to protect yourself or strike back with. Even acting on instinct, your psionics are a force to be reckoned with now. And when you use them intentionally... the battlefield itself reshapes to suit your will. As a **[One-Off]** action, you may spend **3 ESP** to usher in a PSIPOCALYPSE of your own creation. The special **[Hazards]** created by this action affect only targets of your choosing, as your immense telekinetics safeguard you and your allies from harm... and should any try to escape from it, as a **[Reaction]** you may spend another **ESP** to reach out with your powers and automatically nullify their ABSCOND. Choose one disaster to unleash upon your unfortunate foes:\r\n\r\n> **ROCKS FALL**: And everyone dies. You lift a whole building, or a chunk of the earth the size of a proper meteor, and prepare to slam it down onto whoever might stand in your way. In the SECOND ROUND of this **[Hazard]**, the building rolls CAN’T ABSCOND BRO with your **+IMG** as precisely controlled debris hems your chosen targets in.\r\n\r\n> **FIRE**: At your command, the world itself ignites. You start a psionic flash fire that engulfs the battlefield, smoke swirling to block your enemies’ vision as they fall victim to the flames. The **[Ablaze]** inflicted by this **[Hazard]** ignores immunities - even those well-protected against normal fire can fall victim to this psionic conflagration.\r\n\r\n> **FLOOD**: A torrent bursts into the area, rushing over your foes as you free it from some enclosure or simply bend part of the ocean itself to your will. During the SECOND ROUND and beyond, you choose the trolls knocked **[Floorbound]** by the **[Hazard]** rather than selecting them at random, as the currents and even the debris adrift in them toss your enemies about to suit your every whim.\r\n\r\n> **RAINSTORM**: The sky splits open and pours rain down on you all. All trolls caught in this Hazard must roll 1d8 every turn; on a 1, they are struck by lightning and take **3 [Electric][Psychic]** damage!'),
('telepowers', 'TELEPOWERS', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Psionic][Strife][Unlock: Psychic]', 'Rusts are a caste with somewhat muted psychic powers. They can bend spoons maybe, or have some connection to the dead. You? You go the full fucking mile. Lifting objects with your mind, reading thoughts, seeing the future… if you can think of it, you can do it. You are **[Talented]** at **+IMG**. Using this move gives you EXTRASENSORY POINTS, or ESP, a type of **[Hold]**; as an action, you can spend one or more ESP to launch a TELESTRIKE, dealing **1 [Somatic] damage** per ESP spent as you barrage them with a volley of projectiles. When you spend 3 or more ESP as a single action this way, the attack also inflicts **1 [Somatic] [Weakness]** for **3 turns**, battering your foes with exceptionally large items. When you want to lift heavy loads with your mind and slam some shit around, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: NnnnnnnNNNNNNRGH… oh, whoops, there goes all that stuff you were holding. Your grip on your psionics wavers and you lose all your **ESP** - no meteors in the forecast tonight. If you didn’t have any ESP yet, you’re just **[Inept]** at all rolls for a turn as you recover from the strain.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Well, at least you didn’t pop a blood vessel.\r\n\r\n**OK**:  You channel energy for your next attack, gaining **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You lift up something heavy and prepare to hurl it at the opponent. You gain **1 ESP**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You levitate a whole cluster of objects to barrage the opponent with, doing **1 [Somatic]** damage and gaining **1 ESP**, or just gaining **2 ESP** as you prepare for a truly earth-shaking assault!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: YOU ARE THE APOCALYPSE ARISEN. YOU ARE THE PSION TO END ALL PSIONS. You tear open the earth or crush a building and make some actual, honest-to-HIC meteors to hurl your opponent’s way. You do **2 [Somatic]** damage and gain **2 ESP**, and your next TELEKINETIC STRIKE inflicts **[Ablaze]** as your projectiles - and enemies - catch fire from the sheer psionic force!'),
('temporaryRedistribution', 'TEMPORARY REDISTRIBUTION', 'OTHER', 'ROGUE', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Rogue]', 'Sometimes, things need to be in the right place exactly. And, ultimately, sometimes the right place is with you. And… sometimes, the wrong place is… with a friend. You\'re sorry!!! It\'s for the greater good, you\'ll give it right back when you\'re done! You may take items from your allies’ sylladexes as though they were your own, and insert items into their sylladexes right back. You\'ll give them back at the end of the encounter!\r\n\r\n\r\n'),
('temporarySetback', 'TEMPORARY SETBACK', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Passive][Locked: Mary Sue]', 'NOOOO! IT’S A MAJOR SETBACK!\r\n\r\nAnyway,\r\n\r\nLook, inconvenient problems aren’t really your thing. You don’t mind problems, so long as they emphasise how cool and great you are! When you are above **half HP**, you automatically lose any penalties after **two turns**; **[Recharge]**, conditions, **[Negative]** emotions, you name it. On fire? It’ll go out. Bleeding? Nah. Drag? Pfft! You’re unstoppable! After you’re knocked below half HP, you still have the ability to recover quickly, but in a more grounded way. GUTSUCKERY becomes **[Recharge: 2]**, rather than **[One-Off]** as you cling to what you’ve got left.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('tendrils', 'TENDRILS', 'OTHER', 'GRIMDARK', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Eerie][Locked: Grimdark]', 'Your shadow grows, writhes, expands, flickers across your enemies vision. While in A MODE MOSTE GRIM, you gain a new strife specibus, which you may choose to roll with **+IMG**: TENDRILKIND. It lashes at not your enemy, but their shadow, peeling away pieces of themself and flinging them into nothingness. This deals only **[Freaky] [Psychic]** damage, and inflicts **1 [Psychic]** **[Weakness]** to a max of 2 on your enemies. On a **GREAT**, you may do one less damage to inflict **[Terrified]** on them. On a **MAX**, this effect is **[Free]**, OR you may choose to **[Blind]** them for three turns. \r\n\r\nIf you have taken all moves from this template, your tendrils become stronger. More **[Physical]**. They peel from the shadows in a swirling mass, dealing **[Freaky] [Somatic]** damage if you choose, and inflicting **[Bloodied]** on a **MAX**.'),
('terriblyLonely', 'TERRIBLY LONELY', 'VOID', 'VOID', '[Aspect][Passive][Unlock: Void]', 'Even though you might have a perfectly fine life, you’re constantly filled with a sense of irrelevancy— like nothing you do matters in the long run. It’s like homesickness even while you’re perfectly at home. As a result, it’s hard to get you much more slowed down than you already are; after all, you’re a little numb to things that do matter. You can choose to become **[Numb]** as an action, and even start **[Dissociating]** if you so choose.'),
('terrorformer', 'TERRORFORMER', 'RUST', 'ADULT', '[Rust][Locked: Adult]\r\n', 'After the fires of conquest are put out and all that\'s left are the ruins of a civilization, someone\'s gotta flatten the place and let the farms grow. That\'s you! Get to work! If you can swallow down the horror that comes with wiping a planet clean to make it safe for Imperial habitation, it\'s not so bad. Better than Redshirtmunition. When using a **MASSIVEKIND** Abstrata, you don\'t have to use **[Lengthy]** actions to **[Strife]**, but doing this 3 times renders you **[Tired]**. This emotion is **[Unblockable]**. When **[Tired]**, swinging around a **MASSIVEKIND** weapon without a **[Lengthy]** action two times renders you **[Exhausted]**, after which you\'ll be knocked **[Unconscious]** if you attack without a **[Lengthy]** action again. Additionally, you deal +1 damage to items as you Terrorform a bastard\'s equipment into DUST.\r\n'),
('thatsIncorrect', 'THAT’S INCORRECT', 'VOID', 'VOID', '[Aspect][Basic][Free][Locked: Void]', 'Wrong. Wrong. Wroooong. You can’t help yourself— when people make an incorrect guess or statement, you jump in and let them know they’re not correct. While this might be done with good intentions… it sometimes makes people feel like you’re dragging them into the void with you. Any time someone fails a PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll, you can make one for **[Free]**; if you succeed on your roll and let the other person know, you gain **1 [Boost]**, and they gain **1 [Drag]**.'),
('thatsNotMe', 'THAT\'S NOT ME', 'OTHER', 'HEIR', '[Class][Basic][Free][One-Off][Reaction][Locked: Heir]\r\n', 'You’re right at home in your aspect. So whenever someone else shows off their aspect, you politely look away. Especially when they try using it on you! Hey hey, you’re not about to be affected by that one. When someone tries to affect you with an **[Aspect]** move that isn’t the same **[Aspect]** as yours, you can turn away and say no thanks, as the move has no effect on you.'),
('thaumaturgeTantrum', 'THAUMATURGE TANTRUM', 'OTHER', 'WITCH', '[Class][Basic][Free][Reaction][One-Off][Locked: Witch]', 'Oops! Looks like you screwed up your roll there, haha! That’s okay, you’re sure this next one will be- Oh. That one wasn’t good either, b-bit of a rough patch huh? S-surely things… No. NO. STOP, STOP, STOP! Why are you LOSING!? That’s not how this works! Everything is supposed to go YOUR way! GRAHHHHHHHHHH! When you’re such a controlling try hard, you don’t take too well to failure. If you roll three **BAD** results or one **MIN** in an encounter, you may become your choice of **[Enraged]** or **[Focused]** as you go on the warpath to correcting these wrongs against you.'),
('theAncestors', 'THE ANCESTORS', 'OTHER', 'DECOMPOSITIONIST', '[Template][Advanced][Lengthy][One-Off][Magic][Locked: Decompositonist]', 'After death, the Great Oblivion claims you for the final rest, but even those who finally rest their heads might find that they need to raise it once more, just one more time. Now is that time. You may call upon your ancestral lineage from the earliest nights of your bloodline to your ancestor themselves for help, and they will listen. As a **[Lengthy]** action you may let the spirits of those before you take control, untold tens of thousands of sweeps of experience guiding your hands to survive this ordeal. This will always take every action on your turn, but on your next turn you will be **[Talented]** at all rolls, in addition to the following effects you must take when choosing this move. Choose two, depending on the history your bloodline has had.\r\n\r\n> **OLD WARRIORS**: Your ancestral lineage is known for their warriors, brave and fierce! You can feel the heat of a hundred battles in your body, and you know there must be hundreds more. You gain an additional level of **[Talented]** at **[Strife]**, pushing to a 4d8 if possible!\r\n\r\n> **BOOKLEARNERS**: Ancient knowledge spills into your mind, flashes of Jades and Seadwellers, of Rebellion and industry. You can\'t make it out, but you understand that your lineage has more to learn. You gain a **[Free]** **GREAT** PROBLEM SLEUTHING result.\r\n\r\n> **SORCERERS AND WIZARDS**: Magic is inseparable from you, your ancestors and your eventual descendants. It is part of your whole, and from the comforting chill of astrosorcery to something darker far older, it flows through. You may use the spell from the ASTROSORCERY Entry Move for **[Free]**!\r\n\r\n> **LOYALTY UNENDING**: It might be shameful, but your lineage has rarely strayed from the path the Empire has guided them to. Survival maybe, or cowardice. Perhaps even true agreement. Regardless, your ancestors still understand that you are of their blood, and share with you their knowledge. You gain a **+2 [Buff]** on rolls against any Organization or Empire Loyal trolls, and a free **GOOD** PROBLEM SLEUTHING question for how to avoid their ire.\r\n\r\n> **HELLRAISERS**: Rebellion flows through you, like the sting of a trident through a great leader\'s chest. Your ancestors have done it all. They have spilled blood for a better world, and have died for it. They will ensure you will not join them so soon in such a way. You become **[Quickened]** as centuries of running, hiding and fighting course through your legs.\r\n\r\n> **PAINLENDERS**: You can feel centuries of pain in your hands, but it\'s not yours. It\'s that which your lineage has taken for others, to let them rest and recover. It\'s a good sort of pain. All your allies heal **1 HP**. If you have no allies, you heal **2 HP** instead.\r\n\r\n> **CURSED**: Something has gone wrong. Something is so terribly wrong. You can hear your ancestors, but it\'s ever so slightly off. But nevertheless, they are here. And they are helping. All opponents become **[Scared]** as the presence of something... wrong, but loving courses through you. \r\n\r\n> **JUST YOU**: And them. Your ancestral lineage isn\'t special. You have no great heroes, no deceitful villains. No warriors that inspired hundreds, or rebels that liberated cities. They are simply them, and you are simply you. The masses of whom the world forgets about. Just as they will now. You become **[Hidden]**, and will not stop being **[Hidden]** if you **[Strife]** this turn.'),
('theBand', 'THE BAND', 'OTHER', 'MUSICREANT', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Musicreant]', 'What is a musician without a band? Your band is what gets you and your party roaring to make some sound - and make sound you will, when you\'re all together! You can add a number of allies to be permanently in a band together. You must have this move to join the band. You can only ever be in one band; if you join one, you leave the other. Changing bands requires a DOWNTIME action. You get a number of effects depending on how many band members are in an encounter together.\n\n> **1**: Just you on your lonesome. Your FRAYMOTIF is **[Buildup: 3]**.\n\n> **2**: Some backup to bring out the best in you! Your FRAYMOTIF is **[Buildup: 2]** .\n\n> **3**: Hey, now we\'re making some music! Your FRAYMOTIF is **[Buildup: 1]** .\n\n> **4+**: Let\'s change the world! FRAYMOTIF loses the **[Buildup]** and **[One-off]** tags.'),
('theBestAround', 'THE BEST AROUND', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'CULLSCOUT', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Cullscout]', 'Nothing\'s ever gonna keep ya down! You REFUSE to lose, plain and simple. You can use **[Boost]** to escape a **MIN**, but you become **[Tired]** once you do so.\n\n'),
('theBestPirateEverSeen', 'THE BEST PIRATE EVER SEEN', 'OTHER', 'RAPSCALLINEER', '[Template][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Rapscallineer]', 'You have vast amounts of experience sailing the seas, you’ve gone far and wide and acquired quite the reputation for yourself and your crew. After a while, though, some of the attention has acquired quite a few contacts; as such you can choose to modify your ship in such a way with the association of a group, or choose to go it alone. Or be a ghost, whatever your thing is, man. The CAP’N must be the one to take this ultra- upon their CAP’N taking it, all crew members gain the benefits unlocked by the move, although only the CAP’N gains the additional talent selected by the ship upgrade. Choose from the following options to upgrade your ship with:\r\n\r\n> **SCOURGE OF THE SEAS AND SKIES +HUB**: What more is there to say? You are a legendary pirate on a legendary crew, infamous among the lands as a scoundrel in the ranks of the likes of Edwyrd Teeach and Calico Jahcke. People recognize your flag and are scared shitless of it. You are famous enough that ordinary people will recognize your ship’s flag and Captain’s name, which usually affords lowerbloods on the crew a level of respect only afforded to midbloods and above, because you are not someone to fuck with. You and your crew gain access to one of the following locked moves of your choice, although you still have to use a level to take it**: AFFRIGHT from the Purple Subjugglator tree, EN GARDE! from the Cerulean Marquis tree or FUSILLADE from the Bronze Vagabond tree.\r\n\r\n> **GHOOOOOOOOST SHIP +IMG**: Your ship and crew have been touched by something unnatural- your ship can appear and disappear in a cloud of mist at will, and doesn’t quite seem to obey the laws of reality. While you and your crew are indistinguishable from the average Alternian on land, when you board your ship you become something else- perhaps ghostly apparitions, walking corpses or a literal skeleton crew. You and your crew are identifiable as **[Eerie]** only aboard the ship, and this does not restrict you from taking an **[Eerie]** template as your second template. You and your crew gain access to one of the following locked moves of your choice, although you still have to use a level to take it**: CAN’T KILL WHAT YOU CAN’T SEE AND IS ALSO ALREADY DEAD from the Ghost template, or MASTICATE or TIS BUT A SCRATCH from the Shadowdropper template.\r\n\r\n> **PRIVATEER +APP**: You’ve done did it, Cap, you did the exact thing you swore never to do upon becoming a pirate. You sold out. The empire makes tentative arrangements with skilled enough crews to take on bounties and fight their wars for them in exchange for them to turn a blind eye to some of your crew’s, ahem.. less than Imperially-approved sensibilities. You and your crew lose any **[Cullbait]** tags, although only while on your ship, and not on trollcial media- if you’re talking about your giant mutant wings on Chittr and expect to get special treatment because you’re some airship’s boatswain, well, good luck, bucko. You and your crew gain access to one of the following locked moves of your choice, although you still have to use a level to take it**: SECRET FILES from the Jr. CIS template, IMPERIAL DICTATION from the Jr. HET template or CALL FOR BACKUP from the Jr. TIT template.\r\n\r\n'),
('theBigBadWolf', 'THE BIG BAD WOLF', 'OTHER', 'MOONBARK', '[Template][Ultra][Chicanery][Eerie][Locked: Moonbark]', 'Who\'s afraid of you? Basically everyone, I\'ll be honest. You\'re a terrifying legend, so vicious and powerful that the Bustin\' Division doubts you\'re even paranormal. Probably a really big dog, horse, shark, whatever. Not our problem! Let the Orphaners handle it. Aw, it\'s still our job? Okay… you are always fully in control when you enter MOONFRENZY, even if you are **[Out-of-Control]**, and can flee as you need. Moves that negatively affect **[Eerie]** trolls now do not affect you in MOONFRENZY, though moves that affect lusii do. Finally, you gain the following SHENANIGANS effects, only accessible while transformed (all of which are **[Talented]**):\r\n\r\n**GOOD**:\r\n\r\n> **HOWL**: AROOOOOO! Terrifying! You let out a loud terrifying noise, scaring the shit out of your target. You **[Scare]** them!\r\n\r\n> **HUFF AND PUFF**: You inhale a huge whoosh of air (or water if you\'re aquatic?) and blast your opponent. They drop an item in their grip! \r\n\r\n> **GOBBLE GOBBLE GOBBLE SNARF MUNCH CHEW BURP**: Jegus, your appetite is horrifying! What the hell?! You eat an opponent\'s item that you\'ve successfully dislodged from their person. The item takes **3 damage**; if it\'s destroyed, you eat it, and **[Heal] 1 HP**.\r\n\r\n> **IT WAS ENPECE ALL ALONG**: You shift out of your bestial mode with ease, confusing those who didn\'t realize it was a monster. The target becomes **[Dumbfounded]**, and you reveal your identity.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**:\r\n\r\n> **ASSERT DOMINANCE**: You know the easiest way to get an animal to respect you, from experience, is punching them in the snoot. A Lusus you use this move on becomes **[Fascinated]** by you.\r\n\r\n> **CHEW TOY**: RUGGARUGGARUGGARUGGA! You grasp the target in your mouth and ragdoll them around all fucking scary like. The target is **[Inept]** at their next roll as they stumble around in confusion.\r\n\r\n> **DARK AND STORMY NIGHT**: You howl into the stars, and there\'s a flash of lightning! How cinematic! A RAINSTORM **[Hazard]** begins. You can\'t use this effect if you already caused a **[Hazard]** this encounter.\r\n\r\n**MAX**:\r\n\r\n> **CALL OF THE MOONBARK**: You put out a monstrous call, and summon forward your bestial kin. You cause either an ANGRY MOB or a STAMPEDE **[Hazard]**, your choice. You can\'t use this effect if you already caused a **[Hazard]** this encounter.'),
('theBigNumber', 'THE BIG NUMBER', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][One-Off][Locked: Circusfolk]', 'Building hype is the most important part of your job. Gotta get people excited, gotta get them wired, gotta keep them on the edge of their seats before BAM, THE BIG NUMBER! The same is true for your bloody brawls, too. Every time you get a **GREAT** roll, you gain **1 HYPE**, and 2 on a **MAX**. Once you have accumulated at least **5 HYPE**, you may spend it to throw an opponent into the PUNISHMENT TIME Affliction, except it is themed around your circus performance as you deploy lights, props and machinery you have decaptchalogued. You may also choose to inflict PUNISHMENT TIME on an opponent with **1 HP** exactly left; they are **[Healed]** to full HP before the Affliction starts. This doesn\'t work on lusii and monsters. Obviously.'),
('theChampionship', 'THE CHAMPIONSHIP', 'OTHER', 'MUSCLEMANIAC', '[Template][Advanced][Locked: Musclemaniac]', 'You’re an accomplished fighter, and you need a way to SHOW your accomplishments. Preferably with something absurdly shiny and extra. Upon taking this move you gain a CHAMPIONSHIP BELT with a dramatic name of your choice, an **[Accessories][Fashion]** item that offers you one of the effects listed below while wearing it. This item cannot be YOINKED or otherwise stolen from you via any regular means. Watch out, though- if somebody challenges you to a fight and wins, they receive ownership of the belt and become the CHAMPION, and the only way to get it back is to win it back! You can define certain terms for how and who can get your championship (for example, that no weapons besides UNARMEDKIND can be used in championship fights, or your championship can only be won by members of your caste) but the terms must apply equally to you and your opponent. Select an effect from the list below for your belt:\r\n\r\n> **GAUDY [ +1 HUB, -1 PSP ]**: Holy fuck this thing is shiny! Your opponent is **[Blinded]** for the **first round** of combat as the shiny metal reflects light into their eyes.\r\n\r\n> **RESPECTABLE [ +1 GRA, -1 RAS ]**: People take you seriously when you walk around with this thing. You’ve gotta work extra hard to protect it, and as such are **[Quickened]** for the first round of combat.\r\n\r\n> **SILLY [ +1 RAS, -1 HUB ]**: Not all championships have to be serious! Maybe your belt can only be won if your opponent battles you in oven mitts, or maybe there’s just a cute little cat face on it. The first time you use SHENANIGANS in a fight, you receive a free **GOOD** effect in addition to whatever else you roll.\r\n\r\n> **SPONSORED [ +1 APP, -1 GRA ]**: Sellout! You’ve got your sponsor’s logo front and center on this belt! When you win a strife while wearing this belt, you gain **2 LUX**.\r\n\r\n> **HOLY [ +1 IMG, -1 APP ]**: You have been endorsed by the greatest sponsor of all... God. A decomp, cloistered jade, or a clown kissed this belt once probably, if you’re not one yourself. The first **[Magic]** roll you roll in an encounter can’t be lower than a **GOOD**.'),
('theChosenOne', 'THE CHOSEN ONE', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Passive][Cullbait][Magic][Unlock: Protagonist]', 'There\'s something about you that just feels right. Whether you\'re a Snazzard slayer with a party of like-minded trolls, a charming cult leader with a burgeoning church of narratively sensitive trolls or a crabby 6 sweep old who just wants their friends to get along, you inherently make others feel like they belong when they\'re around you. You are a Limeblood representing the characters that fill the narrative, with yourself being the hero of the story; the one everyone can relate to, the one everyone wants to be. This is your story, and the story of every person you\'ll ever meet. You are **[Talented]** in **+GRA** thanks to how perfectly you seem to hold yourself. Trolls feel inclined to address you before any other opponents in an encounter; when your opponents attempt to use an effect that would target a single one of your allies or one of their allies, roll 1d8. On a 7 or 8, the move affects you instead as the narrative shudders to make them willingly choose to do so instead. They must roleplay out why they are doing this, often by seeing you as the most dangerous threat here or offering you an edge to make the encounter more interesting. This effect applies even if they couldn\'t normally roll against you, like in a TEAM STRIFE.'),
('theCloudmind', 'THE CLOUDMIND', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Passive][Psionic][Unlock: Network]', 'Biotech is the foundation of trollic tech. It should come as no surprise, then, that the most advanced technology of trollkind requires the most advanced biohosts: Trolls. Network Golds are born with an especially powerful telepathy that allows them to link minds with one another. It\'s this psychic hivemind that allows them to store the entirety of the internet in their collective brains. Networks are easily distinguished by their strange dark eyes with scrolling data and text in bright colors. You are **[Talented]** at **+PSP**. Moves with the **[Tech]** tag instead gain the **[Psionic]** tag for you. You gain the following PROBLEM SLEUTHING effects, and the move becomes **[Psionic]** instead of **[Mental]** thanks to the power of the internet.\r\n\r\n> **DOWNLOAD**: BZZZT… DOWNLOADING… INTERNET… You figure out the best way to approach a situation thanks to online resources. You gain 2 PROBLEM SLEUTHING rolls at once; however, this cramming makes you **[Tired]**.\r\n\r\n> **BLACKOUT**: Heheheh. You figure out what sites the target frequents, and cut their connection. HEHEHEH. Your target can\'t use moves involving the internet for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **TEXTIFICATE**: BEEP BEEP. You send a text of no more than 25 words to an ally\'s phone privately, and allow them to reply quickly. Your opponents do not know what you communicated with one another.\r\n\r\n> **PRIVACY BREACH**: Nice Trollian Messages, dipshit. You learn a fact about the opponent, even if it\'s secret, and recite it to their face. They feel **[Dread]** for **2 turns**. Ngh-!\r\n\r\n> **SOOTHE**: You scan through the target\'s history to figure out the exact right thing to calm them down. You remove one **[Emotion]** from the target.\r\n\r\n> **SOLUTIONGEN**: Fuck this puzzle. You run through infinite possibilities and solutions in your head before solving a puzzle or obstacle easily. You take **3 [Drag]** as you rush through this obstacle.'),
('theComeofage', 'THE COMEOFAGE', 'OTHER', 'ADULT', '[Passive][Unlock: Adult]  ', 'Somehow… you did it. You survived Alternia, the Trials, and made it to the one escape you always dreamed of. \r\nSPACE.\r\nOf course, it\'s not really a true escape. For some trolls, the fate that\'s in store for you is arguably worse than what you had back home, a thousand times over. Melding into spaceships, planets of nuns and nobody else, etc. Honestly, it\'s not really an upgrade… more of a sidegrade. Did I mention you absolutely can\'t go back to Alternia? From this day on, you live a life powering the infernal machine that is the Trollic Empire (and certainly never rebelling!). You have earned a TITLE, a moniker most other trolls will know you by. This is either a 7-9 letter long word, or occasionally a set of four four letter nouns put into two names. Examples include The Archduke or Starmage Zincgasp. You also gain a JOB. This job is generally not one you pick yourself; rather, it is one you were assigned during The Trials you took before ascending. You gain the move associated with your job for free now. You can only take jobs available to your caste, though if the lore makes sense for the setting and your character you can gain permission from your Clouder (or from moderators on Serverstuck) and take a job you normally would not be able to access. Shortly after hitting 10 sweeps, you\'re likely to experience your first molt. You shed your skin inside a gross cocoon and come out a little taller and a little scarier. What \"a little\" means varies. Sometimes, it means you grow an inch; sometimes, it means you grow three feet, a dark chitinous hide, blood coloured eyes, and serious bloodlust. Everyone\'s journey to adulthood takes different paces, and that\'s okay! You\'ll have many molts over the years— you might reach your final adult form immediately, or you might remain grey and adolescent-ish (which most trolls do) for sweeps.\r\nEither way, any roll made against you by a NON-ADULT has their tier of success requirements raised by 2 [I.E, a **GOOD** becoming a 13 rather than 11], and your rolls against them lowered by 2 in turn [I.E a **GOOD** becoming a 9 rather than 11]. '),
('theContent', 'THE CONTENT', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Passive][Locked: Streamer]', 'Bro, it\'s all about the CONTENT. That\'s what brings people to your streams! If you stop making the CONTENT, people will stop watching you, and well, if that happened, euthanasia is the only option you can think of. Choose one of the following types of content you predominantly produce. Obviously, you can dabble in many things, but the thing you choose here is the one you\'re most famous for.\n\n> **VIDEOS GAME**: You\'re a gamer, the most oppressed group of all. As an action, you can choose to become **[Enraged]** as you gnash your fangs at a moment\'s notice. The gamer rage is real!\n\n> **E-GOLD**: People come to your streams because you\'re very attractive. That\'s the truth of the matter. You can take an action to check the thirst comments on your stream, and feel **[Proud]**.\n\n> **VIBES**: You make streams where you chill, the viewers chill, there\'s moisturewave and you\'re almost certainly more stoned than an early Christian martyr. Maybe you do some ASMR. I dunno. You can take an action to feel **[Peaceful]**.\n\n> **PODCAST**: Your stream is themed around a topic you discuss in detail, or a hobby you do for fun. Maybe you read horror stories, maybe you discuss movies— whatever it is, you talk about stuff, and people listen. You can become **[Enthusiastic]** as an action.\n\n> **TRUMAN STREAM**: A popular niche of streaming on Alternia— you give up your privacy to willingly broadcast every moment of your entire life to the world. You can take an action to feel **[Smug]** over how interesting you are to be doing this.\n\n> **NICHE**: You do something even more obscure than all the above! Choose one **[Emotion]** when you take this move; you may feel that **[Emotion]** as an action.'),
('theDarkCarnivalBeckons', 'THE DARK CARNIVAL BECKONS', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Passive][Locked: Honkpostle]', 'When you eventually die, the Big Top on the other side awaits you. The holy realm of the Dark Carnival, the afterlife that awaits all true believers is a place of duality. It is paradise and it is hell, it is eternal and it is instant, it is a place well documented by the scriptures and yet a place where logic and reason dissolve into slime and an eternal circus performance of agony is the reward that all await with bated breath. As injuries pile up, you can sense the oncoming show, and you can’t help but feel **[Enthusiastic]** at the prospect whenever you drop to **4 HP** or below. Enemy trolls who are at this threshold feel this innate sense of **[Dread]** as your gaze settles on them, and they hear… no, that can’t be… is that calliope music playing faintly..?'),
('theDevilWearsTrollPrada', 'THE DEVIL WEARS TROLL PRADA', 'OTHER', 'HAUTE_CLAWTURE', '[Template][Basic][Recharge: 2][Mental][Manipulate][Locked: Haute Clawture]\r\n', 'When someone tries to pick a fight, the Haute Clawturist goes after the most vulnerable part: the opponent’s sense of style. WHAT are you wearing? Goodness, you look like Grewis Voutton used a couch as a bucket, CHAWHAWHAWHAW! When you want to break someone’s self esteem, roll **+PSP**:\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Have you looked in a mirror lately? As you prepare a devastating blow, you look down and realize… you’re wearing everything inside-out! You break down on the spot and feel **[Humiliated]** over your insult to fashion everywhere.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: WELL YOUR OUTFIT IS… uh… y-your mom?? You can’t think of anything bad to say about their fit. You take **1 [Drag]** for that lukewarm insult.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You point out their fashion faux pas, they point out yours. You’re stuck in a stylish stalemate where nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You give a scathing remark about the state of their accessories. Honestly, that bracelet with that hat? Ridiculous. The target gains **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: This guy’s a total fashion DON’T! Who even wears tweed anymore? It’s almost silly how totally out of touch they are. The target gains **2 [Drag]** and becomes **[Disgusted]** by their own outfit.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You rip and tear into their outfit like you’re playing Gloom Eternal. That Zucci jacket? Obvious knock-off. That blouse? Ill-fitting. Those shoes? Horrendous. Hotel? Trivago. The target gains **3 [Drag]** and becomes **[Revolted]** as they realize their fashion sense is a crime against trollmanity.'),
('theDocterrorIsIn', 'THE DOCTERROR IS IN', 'OTHER', 'DOCTERROR', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Docterror]', 'Ah, the Docterror: a fine job that, unlike many other roles, can be caste agnostic. From the lowliest slavesurgeon rust to the mighteous grand mediculler violet, anyone can be a Docterror if they put in enough training. You’re training to become one yourself! You haven’t actually… learned much yet, but you’re getting there, setting out an early framework. With a little practice, you’ll have a proper license in no time! Using A BANDAGE, HEALING JUNK, a MEDICALIZER or an ULTRAMEDICALIZER is a **[Free]** action the first time you do so in an Encounter; you gain one your Wealth level gives you access to now for **0 VP**.'),
('theEmpressAnnnnesRevenge', 'THE EMPRESS ANNNNE’S REVENGE', 'OTHER', 'RAPSCALLINEER', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Locked: Rapscallineer]', 'A pirate crew without a ship is just a polycule with extra steps, really. You have an EPIC ship with billowing sails and a custom flag, probably with a name that’s either genuinely intimidating or dangerously silly. While you *can* sail the high seas with it like a regular pirate, it’s also equipped to be able to fly- go raid inland cities like Loamtrench to your heart’s content! I believe in you.\n\nMechanically, your ship counts as a hive owned by all members of the crew, although crew members are still welcome to build hives separate from the ship. Any crew member can use **LUX** to buy any HIVECRAFTING upgrades they are able to for the ship and can benefit from those upgrades, although they can only mechanically use these upgrades if they have this move. \n\n**Pirate ships additionally have access to these exclusive HIVECRAFTING upgrades**:\n\n> **BIG FUCKING SAILS [6 LUX]**: Did you think this thing was stationary? Your pirate ship can now mechanically be used as a vehicle, even if that was narratively obvious. It functions as a 3 HORSEPOWER vehicle with **20 HP**, with the WATER and AIR upgrades. You must have a NAVIGATOR or ENGINEER on your crew to buy this upgrade.\n\n> **CANNONS [5 LUX]**: Yeeeeeah these things aren’t the most accurate, but they do cause a shit ton of havoc. Once per encounter if the ship is present, you can cause some epic explosions and cause the ROCKS FALL **[Hazard]**. You must have a POWDER MONKEY or SAILOR on your crew to buy this upgrade.\n\n> **GALLEY [4 LUX]**: Did you think this was the same thing as a regular mealblock? WRONG. Your food has TETANUS and SCURVY baked into its very crust. Once per day as a **[Downtime]** roll, you can make some hardtack or something equally inedible that you can give to whoever you want. Eating this gives you a random **[Affliction]** because of course it does. You must have a STEWARD or QUARTERMASTER on your crew to buy this upgrade.'),
('theEverythingHunter', 'THE EVERYTHING HUNTER', 'OTHER', 'BEAST_BRAWLER', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Beast Brawler]', 'Scanning… scanning… weak point found. Switching to tearblast arrows. You’ve fought every monster under the moons, and maybe even a couple under the sun. You know how to take them down nice and neat-like, no muss no fuss- or at least, only as much muss and fuss as keeps it fun for you. Your successful **[Strife]** rolls against non-Plant Monsters deal a passive **+1 damage**. If you inflict a **MAX** **[Strife]** roll to a non-Plant Monster, you open up a **[Weakness]** on it for **3 rounds**, allowing others to follow your lead. Weakness that you inflict on monsters doesn’t disperse after the damage is dealt.'),
('theFamily', 'THE FAMILY', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Passive][Unlock: Mafioso]', 'The church binds all clowns together, for sure. But, listen… nothin\' binds people closer than being Clutchmates. And see, clowns need somethin\' to do outside of praising the Messiahs. So you and your clutchmates… you come together, and you make life a little easier for those who need it. You get people things they need, you keep lowbloods safe from highbloods, you turn a healthy profit… and you do it with the help of the Clutch. Oh, sure, others might call you bullies, extortionists and murderers… but unlike most clowns, the Clutch has principles. And you stick to \'em. You all do. You are **[Talented]** at **+APP**. When you take this move, you must bind yourself to a Clutch (not related through biology, but certainly through blood) to pledge yourself to. Select a leader, and give them a kiss on the hand, or set up a new Clutch. All members of a Clutch adopt the Caste Name of the Boss who founded it. You must honour and respect other Clutch members; betraying the Clutch will have you instantly expelled, and Clutch members all get +1 damage against you. When you take this move, you either get the ASSOCIATE role, the DON role (if you\'re leading your own group) or another role selected by your Clutch\'s DON. You can never change your role unless you leave and set up your own clutch, step down as DON or convince your DON to change your role. You\'ll be the UNDERBOSS one day… once that current one is out of the picture.\n\n**ASSOCIATE**: You are this by default! You\'ve yet to impress a boss yet, so you\'re just… gonna keep bein\' annoyin\', yeah! You get 1 **[Boost]** every 2 turns if your DON is present.\n\n**DON**: Yeah, that\'s you. You\'s the boss, boss. Everyone\'s gotta do what you say. When you\'re around, you count as two trolls for the purpose of THE FAMILY, meaning you start at 1 instead of 0 allies present. You\'s just that scary! Your Wealth increases to ULTRARICH. Any other members of your Clutch need to be approved by you first. By speaking to you, you can grant another troll a new role, like UNDERBOSS, or demote them if they displease you. This changes the effect that troll gets from this move. There can only be one DON. Finally, you can use all effects from this tree aside from UNDERBOSS and CONSILIERGE so long as you have someone with that ability appointed to your clutch.\n\n**UNDERBOSS**: That man may be the boss, but you\'s the second boss! You get any one **[Basic]** move from the Boss\' sheet. While present in an encounter with the DON, the DON gains +2 HP. If the DON dies, you become DON. There can only be one UNDERBOSS. \n\n**CONSILIERGE**: You\'s the Don\'s confidant. You tell him the good advice, see. You get a +2 on all **[Analyze]** and **[Manipulation]** checks on the DON, but other troll’s **[Manipulate]** rolls against the DON are **[Inept]** while you’re present. There can only be one CONSILIERGE.\n\n**CAPO**: You do what the Don and Underboss say, sure, but you tell other folks what to do too! Your **[Manipulate]** rolls against any trolls except Violets or higher ranking MAFIOSE trolls have a +2 **[Buff]**, or **[Tiered Up]** if they\'re lower ranking MAFIOSE trolls. There can be three CAPO per clutch. When an UNDERBOSS dies, a CAPO is usually promoted next.\n\n**ROUGHROUSER**: At the bottom of the ladder with CLEANER and EXTORTIONIST (but at least you\'re not an ASSOCIATE), you take care of bodyguarding, physical intimidation or, y\'know. Killing. You get access to the VIDEONASTYQUIN Subjugglator move, but not the rest of the tree.\n\n**CLEANER**: You clean up the messes other clutchmates leave behind. Paper trails, blood trails, all that stuff. It doesn\'t matter as much when you\'re fucking over lowbloods, but it\'s essential when messing with other highbloods. You can spend a **[Lengthy]** action removing evidence from a scene; nobody, not even ORG trolls, will know that something happened here. **[Analyze]** rolls against you are **[Tiered Down]**.\n\n**EXTORTIONIST**: Gotta get blackmail somehow, and you\'re an expert on finding dirty laundry. You have access to the SECRET FILES CIS **[Template]** Move.'),
('theFeministsAreTakingOver', 'THE FEMINISTS ARE TAKING OVER', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'BUSTIN', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Bustin’]', '4 Juggalo Ghostbusters?! You’re real good at working as a team now, and you’re REALLY scary when you’re around specters! When in a TEAM STRIFE, and there’s an **[Eerie]** troll on the other team, your team immediately becomes the CHAMPS. You gain an extra CHAMP ability for every Bustin’ Troll or **[Eerie]** troll in the encounter. '),
('theFriendlyGhost', 'THE FRIENDLY GHOST', 'OTHER', 'GHOST', '[Template][Passive][Eerie][Unlock: Ghost]', 'You have died. Damn. However, while your body may no longer be with us, your spirit sure as hell still is. You look similar to a regular troll, except perhaps more withered and scruffy with blank, white eyes. You also tend to float instead of walk, able to start **[Flying]** for **[Free]**, and you are ever so slightly see-through - which does make it a little hard to hold a physical weapon. You can no longer roll GRIEF or other **[Physical]** **[Strife]** moves ordinarily, thanks to lacking, again, a body. The whole no body thing does have its perks though! You gain the following immunities: \n\n> **[Affliction]**s\n> The **[Physical]** effects of **[Hazard]**s\n> All **[Somatic]** damage, even **[Unblockable]**\n> Status Conditions that need, y\'know, a body? Like **[Poisoned]** or **[Floorbound]**.\n\nOn the flip side, you have **2 [Weakness]** against **[Holy]** or **[Freaky]** damage, which rips at your very existence. **[Psychic]** damage also **[Overwhelms]** you. You\'re nothing but psychic stuff now! If you didn’t already have it, you gain the POLTERIFICATE rust move for free, regardless of your actual caste. However, you roll this with **+IMG** instead of **+RAS**.'),
('theGoldenRule', 'THE GOLDEN RULE', 'OTHER', 'DECOMPOSITIONIST', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Decompositonist]', 'And ye, though the mighty may spit at us and trample our bones to a dust, we must hold in our pushers the golden rule: we all turn to rot, and thou shalt rot with us! You drag at the strong, fighting most furiously when the cards are stacked against you. Whenever you have a negative status condition, drop below half your max HP or roll a **MIN**, you become **[Talented]** at **[Strife]** rolls. If you were already **[Talented]**, you instead become **[Inspired]**. Only through this mantra can you demand an eye for an eye!'),
('theHorde', 'THE HORDE', 'OTHER', 'SHADOWDROPPER', '[Template][Advanced][One-Off][Chicanery][Eerie][Magic][Mental][Locked: Shadowdropper]', 'Not all Shadowdroppers can think like you do. Most of your peers are mindless monsters, but you’ve come to be able to control them like a posse. Did you know that you\'re never more than 20 feet from a corpse on Alternia? Interesting. When you want to summon up the undead from the earth to aid you, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: AH, FUCK, THAT\'S NOT **GOOD**. You summon an ANGRY MOB **[Hazard]**, but they\'re all Shadowdroppers intent on dragging you to hell. Fuck.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You are evidently more than 20 feet from a corpse. \r\n\r\n**OK**: You get the effects of a **GOOD**, but… the emptiness you feel from them is distressing. You take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You call upon the Horde, and they crawl from the ground to aid you! Choose one effect for them to help you with. Regardless of your choice, they stick around, shambling and preventing escape. The opponent’s next Abscond roll immediately fails.\r\n\r\n> **RISE, MY MINIONS!**: Your shadowdroppers crawl out and look terrifying. The target becomes **[Scared]**. \r\n> **BACKUP DANCERS**: FOR NO MERE MORTAL CAN RESIST THE EVIL OF THE HUSSNASTY BREAKDANCE! Your next FRAYMOTIF roll is **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n> **GNASH GNASH**: Yeah they\'re just fucking biting. The target takes **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n> **SPARE PARTS**: Nyahah! You either **[Heal]** yourself by 1 or add a second head you can use for MASTICATE, though this head does not return after being detached or missing. You can\'t have two heads on the target at once. Heads are fucking territorial as hell, dude.\r\n\r\n> **STUNT DOUBLES**: And that\'s how much it WOULD have hurt! You gain **1 [Hold]**; you can use this **[Hold]** as a **[Free]** **[Reaction]** to cancel out the **MIN** of any one move rolled. Boy, you\'re glad you demonstrated that first!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You summon a small army of the dead. It rules! Select two effects.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: H… holy shit..? That\'s… how many people died here? There\'s so insanely many. You select three effects, and the target is **[Trapped]** by hundreds of grasping hands until they free themselves.\r\n\r\n'),
('theLimebloodParable', 'THE LIMEBLOOD PARABLE', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Recharge: 2][Control][Cullbait][Magic][Psionic][Unlock: Narrator]\r\n', '\"The Limeblood Parable\", the player read. Their eyes drifted down to the blurb of the move, their interest piqued. The blurb wasn\'t written like others so far— it was narrating the actions of the player. They supposed that this must be for Limes whose metamagic stem from a subtle control over the narrative they dwell in. Fascinating! Narrator Limes are **[Talented]** in **+PSP** thanks to their tendency to change the storyline to their whim. Remember— use your powers for good, and get consent from other players! When you wish to do just that, roll **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You screw up the story\'s direction! A random HAZARD occurs, and you feel **[Despair]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You overexert yourself to no avail. You feel **[Dread]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You make a minor adjustment, like changing what a target is idly thinking of. \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You can call out a string of text no more than 5 words long, prompting something to happen. This has no mechanical effect, but affects the narrative, potentially influencing how the encounter progresses because of that. The effects cannot be impossible or unlikely; you could write The Juggalo Feels Crushing Guilt, but not The Juggalo Surrenders And Leaves. The target must keep this narrative in mind in future responses; don\'t be an ass and just ignore it!\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Your grip is steely! You can use 10 words, and choose an action they make on their next turn.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Hoh boy, you just chokeslammed the narrative and put it in a headlock. You get to completely change anything around you as much as you like. Change the place, the stuff around you, whatever! You get to choose the target\'s next action and its result, like a **MIN** or a **GREAT**.'),
('themboificMinxery', 'THEMBOIFIC MINXERY', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][One-Off][Manipulate][Locked: Goofball]', 'Look, let’s be real… there’s just something likable about you. Maybe you put off this cool, sexy energy. Maybe you’re a rebel, and people like that about you. Maybe you’re just a silly guy, and people like to laugh. Either way, your actions are charming, not just your words. When you want to make an impression on someone, roll **+RAS**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Hmmm. No, never mind, you suck. The opponent gains **2 [WHAM]**. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: Your opponent has more refined tastes than the likes of you, you saucy sausage. Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You don’t CHARM them, necessarily, but you do pique their interest. You take **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: This foolish little human is quite sweet, actually! You **[Charm]** the opponent for the encounter.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Call that a lasting impression! The opponent is **[Charmed]**, and they remain **[Charmed]** unless you do something that would irk them into combat normally. This effect spans multiple encounters. You’re pretty good at making friends! \r\n\r\n**MAX**: Wow! You are REALLY good at making friends, actually! Like, LIFE-LONG bonds! You get the results of a **GREAT**, except the opponent is **[Fascinated]** by your goofy ways.'),
('theMortifyingOrdeal', 'THE MORTIFYING ORDEAL', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Basic][Passive]', 'The concept of being known is LOATHSOME to you. Fuck other people thinking they can just KNOW stuff about you. Fuck off! The less the world thinks about you the better, to be frank. Any **[Analyze]** rolls against you are **[Tiered Down]**, which can make rolls a **MIN** unlike normal **[Tiered Down]** effects. This does not affect **[Analyze]** rolls not aimed at finding information out about yourself; a roll to **[Analyze]** the area to find you and undo the **[Hidden]** condition is, for example, not affected.\r\n'),
('thenobodyassociationtodestroysociety', 'THE NOBODY ASSOCIATION TO DESTROY SOCIETY\r\n', 'OTHER', 'NADS', '[Template][Cullbait][Movement to suck my NADS][Unlock: NADS]\r\n', 'Congratulations! You’ve passed the NADS’ extensive vetting process and have been allowed access into the most successful rebel group since the Renegade so many sweeps ago. As part of your initiation, you’ve acquired a shiny new mask, a cool rebel title name (Like The Firebrand or The Renegade, though they must be 7-9 letters in length), and the brownie points of being able to say ‘I actually tried to do something about our shithole Empire’. \r\nThis doesn’t come without danger, however- you have, after all, joined an explicitly rebel-aligned group, and the Empire is PISSED about its existence. If anyone finds out you’re part of this group, you\'re a goner. That’s where the mask comes in! The group’s iconic mask hides your identity, leaving you a true nobody. The mask cannot be removed from your person unless you are **[Unconscious]**, and comes with the following neat benefits:\r\n\r\n> NADS Mask\r\n> **[Accessory]**\r\n> [+1 RAS or HUB / -1 APP or IMG]\r\n> You are nobody, and that means everything to you. This **[Fashion]** item is more than just a Trollkyo Rainbowdrinker-style identity-concealing mask, though- it’s a veritable computer that connects you to a massive network of rebels. While wearing the mask, you become **[Cullbait]**. However, you are totally anonymous, and your actions cannot be linked back to you unless you otherwise expose your identity. You can speak into the mask to contact other trolls in the movement and can put out a distress call to summon at most 3 other trolls to your location in a single round to gain allies in a GROUP STRIFE. While wearing this mask, you have access to the NADSUCKERZ secret rebel chatroom, and can use your voice to upload anonymous messages under your title. **[Soggy]** does not affect your NADS Mask, as it has been waterproofed after the first few water-related arrests.\r\n'),
('thePowerOfFriendship', 'THE POWER OF FRIENDSHIP', 'HEART', 'HEART', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Heart]', 'You’ve learned that you aren’t the most important person in the world, or the most interesting, or the most talented. It’s not that you’re not any of those things (you rule!); it’s that everyone around you is just as great too. Where would you be without your friends, after all? You are able to gain a similar effect to the SPLINTERS move, except it affects you rather than them, meaning you can take moves from your friends. You can take this move up to 2 times, but you only need to take it once for Completion of your aspect. You can only gain one move per person; you can’t go back for more as you’d be taking another person’s whole personality.  If they have no **[Open]** moves available to take, you may take a **+1 [Buff]** to a stat they have **[Talent]** in instead. You must have the SPLINTERS move to take this move, and this follows the same restrictions as that move.'),
('theRightMoment', 'THE RIGHT MOMENT', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'By now, you\'ve had a fair share of scraps you\'ve found yourself in. You know to pick the right moment to throw a punch… though how you define the right moment really depends on who you are as a person! You gain the following LET\'S STRIFE options.\r\n\r\n**WAIT YOUR TURN**: Steady… STEADY… now! You wait until the right moment to strike, and then kick ass! This acts as ORDER UP, except you always go last. You gain **1 [WHAM]** at the start of your first turn with this option.\r\n\r\n**RUSH IN**: FUCK THAT NOISE CHAAAAARGE! You go first in order as if you\'d rolled ORDER UP and gain **1 [WHAM]**, but you gain **3 [Drag]** because of your immediate rush.'),
('theSapphirePimpernel', 'THE SAPPHIRE PIMPERNEL', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Marquis]', 'You are a rogue. A legend. A dashing villain or a daring hero. You are shrouded in mystery and coolness that clouds others\' perception of you. You wear a cool cape that goes fwshshwsh even when there isn\'t any wind around. You probably killed a Snazzard once. Yep… it\'s pretty great to be you. You gain access to HERO MODE through your HARDCORE HUBRIS, and your wealth increases to **Ultrarich**, thanks to your increased success in gaining vast troves of wealth with your armada or conquest of pitiful lowblood peasants (robbing their stores). You gain one LUCK POINT. You can use this LUCK POINT to reroll any one roll of your choosing, yours or the opponent\'s. You regain your LUCK POINT whenever you roll a **MAX** result. Upon regaining your LUCK POINT, you are **[Quickened]** for a turn as you feel adrenaline course through you. You\'re scary, bitch!!!!!!!!');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('theStoryContinues', 'THE STORY CONTINUES', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][Recharge: 2][Heal][Magic][Locked: Narrator]', 'You can\'t lose now! The story has just started! You nudge the narrative slightly, hoping to give you or your companions enough plot relevance to power through this obstacle. When you want to heal someone, roll **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Oh no, this actually might be the end... You funnel visions of the Bad End into your target. They enter **[Despair]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Those weren’t plot relevant bits at all! That was a bad future! They gain **[Dread]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Alright, you don’t heal the target, but you reassure them a little. The target gains **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You weave the story in a more appropriate direction, soothing and healing. You either heal **1 damage** or remove an Emotion effect.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Wounds numb and minds calm. The worst comes before the story\'s climax and ultimate victory, after all. You **[Heal] 2 damage** or you **[Heal] 1 damage** and remove an Emotion effect.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: It\'s true! You\'re destined to win! That\'s where THIS story will take you! You heal **3 damage** and remove all **[Negative]** Emotion effects!'),
('theStrongMustProtectTheSweet', 'THE STRONG MUST PROTECT THE SWEET', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'You\'ve made friends outside of the church by now. Chances are, that includes a couple of lowbloods. The propagandic grip of the Clown Church has lessened, and you realize that for all that talk of Church and Empire being different, they sure do basically the exact same thing. Well, fuck that— your friends are worth protecting. You can gain the following CHAMP or CHALLENGER effects to use in a TEAM STRIFE, so long as the majority of the team is of the Jade caste or lower, and the other team has a majority of Teal and up. You can waive this second requirement in TEAM STRIFES against monsters.\r\n\r\n> **CHAMP— UPRISING**: How now, highbloods, honk honk? We got ourselves a lil revolution on our hands— what are we to do? ;o) Every time an allied lowblood gets a **GREAT** roll against an enemy highblood, they get **1 [Boost]**. If they get a **MAX**, everyone gains **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **CHALLENGER— PROTECT THE INNOCENT**: Not so fast, you motherfuckers! Wanna hurt these lil’ guys? Get through ME first! You interpose, becoming the STRUGGLER. You cannot be removed from this position. All allies have **[Legendary]** LET\'S STRIFE rolls to ABSCOND, and they don\'t deduct HP from the group if they flee. For every ally that flees, you gain **2 [WHAM]**.'),
('theTrueSelf', 'THE TRUE SELF', 'HEART', 'HEART', '[Aspect][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Heart]', 'Behind the Persona, the mask you show the world, is the Shadow, the mask you hide from everyone else. But the Shadow is in itself a mask; it hides the Self. The Self is YOU, in all your perfect flaws and flawed perfections; good, bad, beloved, hated. And now that you’ve gotten in touch with yourself, you’re able to show the world what you’re made of! One of your **[Talents]** becomes **[Legendary]** as you focus on what really matters to you. You lose another stat point when you take this move.'),
('theVoice', 'THE VOICE', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Recharge: 3][Control][Magic][Locked: Cloistered]', 'Dude, it\'s like Dune. Have you ever read Dune? All my Dune fans out there get this reference. The point is, Cloistered Jades can\'t rely on the goodwill of others when protecting the Mother Grub. In order to serve her will, you must override the will of others, allowing The Voice of the Mother Grub to pass through your lips in discordant moans and wails that somehow carry a command. When you want to go worm mode, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You remember that maggots are generally not sapient, so none of these are actually commands of the Mother Grub, they\'re yours. She can\'t command anything. You feel **[Despair]** and take **2 [Psychic]** damage as you have a crisis of faith.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: No no no. It\'s the worm\'s commands. You\'re sure. Mostly. Fuck. You feel **[Dread]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You go like, \"mweep\", and everyone\'s like \"what\" and you get embarrassed. Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: FOLLOW THE WILL OF THE WORM. You give the target a one-word command like \"RUN\", \"STOP\" or \"DANCE\". The target must follow this command narratively. You may select two stats you want the target to roll with on their next turn; if they make any rolls, they must involve these stats.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: OBEY THE WORM. OBEY ME. Your command is up to three words, like \"RUN INTO THE ROOM\" or \"LO**OK** THE OTHER WAY\". The target must narratively follow your command, and you may select the actions they take on their turn.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: YOU ARE THE VOICE OF THE MOTHER GRUB. YOU ARE HER SAPIENCE. ALL SHALL BOW. You can give up to a ten-word command, and you decide the targets of the moves you pick out.'),
('theWindyThing', 'THE WINDY THING', 'BREATH', 'BREATH', '[Aspect][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Breath]', 'Life might be more convenient if you ignore all the issues around you and stay carefree and inactive, lost in your own little world— but convenient doesn’t always mean better! Eventually, you need to put your foot down and stand up for what’s right, or else you won’t have the option of being carefree ever again! Any move you have with the **[One-Off]** tag gains the **[Recharge: 3]** tag instead, as the winds seem to blow another opportunity your way. You’re always **[Quickened]**. Finally, you gain **1 [Boost]** at the start of every other round as you build up a heroic, final act to save the world with!'),
('theySeeYou', 'THEY SEE YOU', 'OTHER', 'CTHONOMANCER', '[Template][Basic][Magic][One-Off][Locked: Cthonomancer]', 'From beyond Their eyes peer into this reality, reporting back on the affairs of normalcy. Or… you think so at least? Surely, they’re paying attention. All this would be for naught otherwise! And you can catch their attention! As an action you can summon a Peer from the Subgrubs And Snazzards Monsters section of the book which will join the battle as your ally, appearing glitchy nearby. It can choose to treat you as an Entity under BLOODSHOT’s rules, forwarding the results of its Problem Sleuthing to you. Additionally, the Peer is a powerful focus of Dark Magicks. While a Peer is present and serving you, you may roll DEMON DEAREST and in lieu of the usual effects, raise a fallen troll as a Ghost, Rainbowdrinker or Shadowdropper within the usual caste restrictions on a **GREAT** or **MAX**. Upon gaining FAVORED FIEND, you will summon two Peers rather than one when using this move.'),
('thickerThanWater', 'THICKER THAN WATER', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Passive]', 'Turns out that your caste isn\'t all you have. Far from it; your friends matter to you so much, and not because you\'re meant to protect them; they make you smile, they make you feel safe, they challenge you to look beyond the caverns. You are always **[Talented]** at QUALITY TIME **[Downtime]** rolls. When you get a **GOOD**, rather than the normal result, you can get the following options instead. On a **GREAT** and **MAX**, you get the normal **GOOD** and **GREAT** effects respectively too.\r\n\r\n**STRESS RELIEVER**: Haaah… better. Thanks, guys. All trolls start their next encounter together **[Peaceful]**. \r\n\r\n**SO MUCH FUN**: You guys… that was the best day ever! All trolls start their next encounter together **[Hopeful]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOFIN\' OFF**: Okay, that was pretty funny, you got me. All trolls start their next encounter together **[Smug]**.\r\n\r\n**SHOPPING!!**: Whoa! You bought some sweet stuff together! You buy an item each for **1 VP** or **1 LUX** less than normal.\r\n\r\n'),
('thiefsFlair', 'THIEF’S FLAIR', 'OTHER', 'THIEF', '[Class][Advanced][Physical][Magic][Recharge: 4][Locked: Thief]', 'All eyes on you! You’re a Thief, and you’re proud of it. What you steal isn’t just the abilities of others- you steal the spotlight every time! Some might call you egocentric- you just call yourself confident. It’s your confidence that fuels you to these daring heights, not your inherent anxiety that you aren’t everything that you make yourself out to be! When you want to do what you do best and steal from others, roll **+RAS, +HUB**, or **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Ugh! You fuck up, and as you do, your insecurities overwhelm you! You give the opponent your **GOOD** move benefit instead of yourself, and you suffer the downsides in their place!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: GREAT! Nothing happens! Just wonderful! Ugh!\r\n\r\n**OK**: You don’t manage to steal from them exactly, but you do snag their lead away from them- or, maybe you just bury them beneath you even more! They take **2 [Drag]**, and you gain **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD: It works! You pilfer some of their own inherent power. Choose an effect based on your aspect**:\r\n\r\n> **TIME**: You snag people’s momentum from right under their feet. They are **[Slowed]** for 1 round, and you are **[Quickened]** for 1 round. This effect starts on your enemy\'s next turn. You gotta steal their momentum first before you can use it! \r\n\r\n> **SPACE**: Nice tricks, dipshit! Let’s see how a real master does it! You steal the opponent’s **+RAS** modifier and add it on top of your own, reducing theirs to at most 0. This lasts **3 turns** and can push you up to one past the cap to a +6.\r\n\r\n> **LIFE**: HP DRAIN! You deal 1 **[Somatic]** damage, and you **[Heal]** 2 **HP**.\r\n\r\n> **DOOM**: All your rules are belong to us! Your target loses **1 [Passive]** move for 3 rounds of your choice, and you gain it instead. This does not work on Level 3 Monsters. Know your limits.\r\n\r\n> **HOPE**: Ha! Your aspirations pale compared to mine! You steal ALL your target’s positive conditions and **[Boost]** and gain them yourself for 3 rounds. You also gain another 3 **[Boost]**. After these three rounds, everything gained from this move dissipates.\r\n\r\n> **RAGE**: How’s THIS for angry?! Your opponents do 1 less damage for 3 turns. Nothing can compare to your fury.  \r\n\r\n> **BLOOD**: Cool society, brother! Yoink! You can select any **[Basic]** or **[Advanced] [Caste]** move the opponent has; they lose it for 3 rounds, and you gain it. Stealing a **[Psionic]** move replaces the tag with **[Magic]**.\r\n\r\n> **BREATH**: You’re too slow! The target immediately falls **[Floorbound]**; you, meanwhile, lose any 2 status conditions that were affecting you. \r\n\r\n> **LIGHT**: ALL THE LUCK! ALL OF IT! You gain all the target’s **[Talent]** in addition to yours for **2 rounds**, and they lose their **[Talent]** until then. If you were already **[Talented]**, you get a +1 [Buff]** to rolls with this stat.\r\n\r\n> **VOID**: Everyone, check out THIS guy! All attention turns to your target; lusii, drones or foes all attack them, ignoring you completely, for 3 rounds. If you want to make someone the target of their own allies, this must be a **MAX**.\r\n\r\n> **HEART**: Say goodbye to your self-introspection, meathead! You give the target two new random **[Ineptitudes]** for **2 rounds**, rolling 1d8 twice to choose. This can stack to make them **[Godawful]**.\r\n\r\n> **MIND**: Cool thoughts! MINE! You ask the target to state their next 3 rolls; they can only use the rolls they stated, while you can plan around them as such.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: The perfect crime is not a subtle one; it is a flamboyant one! Your target is **[Confused]** on top of all other effects.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: They’ve never seen anything like it! You leave your target in shock and awe as you rob them blind. Increase all numbers from the **GOOD** results by 1, and the target is **[Dumbfounded]**. For Space, instead last **4 turns** and let your stat be pushed up to +7.\r\n\r\n'),
('thievesTools', 'THIEVES’ TOOLS', 'OTHER', 'ROGUE', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Rogue]', 'You\'ve accumulated an interesting collection indeed! Usually from picking up strange objects and items you found that piqued your interest… but these are no ordinary items! Your sticky fingers have a knack for hunting down the, shall we say, unique. Like these COOL GEMS you nicked off some highblood in weird cosplay robes! For you, **ABSTRATA UPGRADES** can be stored as physical, tangible item. You can hold up to three of them in a single sylladex slot, under the name **BAG OF RUNES**. You can apply these runes to weapons mid combat, both your allies’ and your own, swapping them out as an action. You can apply a **RUNE** to weapons that already have **ABSTRATA UPGRADES**. If you try to add another **RUNE** to a weapon that you already added one, it simply replaces the old **RUNE**. **SLEIGHT OF HAND** does not reduce this action cost. All runes automatically return to you at the end of an encounter. \r\n\r\n\r\n'),
('thinkFast', 'THINK FAST', 'MIND', 'MIND', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Mind]', 'Not everything has to be planned to perfection; a margin for error is absolutely fine in cases where you don’t have time to waste— like when you’re about to get pummeled! When you are below ¼ health (rounded down), your uses of RUN THE CALCULATIONS only take **1 action** rather than 2; this action must be the last on your turn. However, rather than **[Tiering Up]** all moves on your next turn, they are instead **[Talented]**. Still a chance you’ll mess up— but that’s worth the risk right now! You must have RUN THE CALCULATIONS to take this move.'),
('thinkOfTomorrow', 'THINK OF TOMORROW', 'BREATH', 'BREATH', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Breath]', 'Tomorrow always comes; that’s something you can be certain of. So why should you let your problems stick with you? Eventually, there’ll be a tomorrow where you don’t have the problem you’re facing! That little bit of hope you have keeps you going no matter what. All negative conditions you have end after **3 turns**. If you have a move that states you are not affected by a status condition until a certain time this timer only starts until after they begin to actually affect you.'),
('thinkPanPowerhouse', 'THINK PAN POWERHOUSE', 'OTHER', 'MAGE', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Buildup: 3][Locked: Mage]', 'You don’t get so bitter solely because people don’t listen - although that does suck major bulge. There’s also the decision paralysis that comes with the weight of knowledge. It’s horrifying! But… You’ve gotten chances to offload your suffering to others. You’ve learned how to cope with the experience of your aspect without feeling like you’re fucking dying. Deep breath in… Deep breath out. Okay! You have a lot more mental space. Enough standing around, it’s time to ACT! You gain the ability to roll another **UNIVERSAL MOVE** in combination with **PROBLEM SLEUTHING**. This uses the stat modifier of PROBLEM SLEUTHING and only requires one roll, meaning if you roll **PROBLEM SLEUTHING** + **SWASHBUCKLE** and get a **GOOD**, you receive the effects of a **GOOD PROBLEM SLEUTHING** roll and a **GOOD SWASHBUCKLE** roll at the same time. This counts as a **[Lengthy]** action. This uses PROBLEM SLEUTHING as the base roll, meaning you retain the **[Tier Ups], [Tier Downs], [Nerfs]** and **[Buffs]** you would normally have for **PROBLEM SLEUTHING**, while sacrificing the effects you would normally apply to the other move. \r\n'),
('thoroughInvestigation', 'THOROUGH INVESTIGATION', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Passive][Locked: Legislacerator]', 'Being good at fighting is one thing. But you need to be intelligent if you want to track down your perps. You may HUNT DOWN your target as a **[Downtime]** effect. You may **[Strife]** others when HUNTING your target in this way, so long as your target isn\'t present. Every encounter which involves you speaking to someone else about your target while HUNTING them, you get **1 INVESTIGATION POINT**, a type of **[Hold]** used to determine how much you know about the target. You can use these INVESTIGATION POINTS to gain the following effects. If your target is informed by someone that you were asking about them, you lose half your IP and can\'t gain any more. Be subtle! Every **1 LUX** or **Treasure I** you are paid by an employer to take this douchebag out counts as **one IP**.\r\n\r\n> 1. Reduce the lower Roll Threshold for a specific move\'s **MAX** from 20 to 18.\r\n> 2. Increase the enemy\'s upper Roll Threshold for a specific move\'s **MIN** from rolling two 1\'s to rolling a 1 and a 2.\r\n> 3. Increase the enemy\'s upper Roll Threshold for a specific move\'s **MIN** further, from a 1 and a 2 to two 2\'s.\r\n> 4. Reduce the lower Roll Threshold for a specific move\'s **GREAT** from a 14 to a 12.\r\n> 5. Reduce the lower Roll Threshold for a specific move\'s **GOOD** from an 11 to a 9.\r\n> 6. Increase the enemy\'s upper Roll Threshold for a specific move\'s **BAD** from a 7 to a 9.\r\n> 7. Gain a **[WHAM]** at the start of the encounter.'),
('thoughtgleaner', 'THOUGHTGLEANER', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Advanced][Analyze][Psionic][Locked: Psychic]', 'FOOLS! You aren\'t even safe within the confines of your own mind! OBSERVE: HRNNNNHHRRRHHNNNN. You can read people\'s thoughts as easily as anyone can read a book. This gives you exceptionally good insight into what\'s coming next with flashes of insight and secret lore. When you want to read someone\'s mind, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN: You do a different cool trick instead**: projecting your own thoughts into the opponent\'s mind. Yuh oh! The opponent receives the effects of a **GREAT**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You just kinda guess what they\'re thinking. It\'s not very impressive.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Mmmmm… you get… a glimpse..? But not much more. Your next **[Analyze]** roll has a **+2 [Buff]** to it.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Aha! There– their secrets reach through the fog! Select one of the following to glean.\r\n\r\n> **TACTICS**: Your target tells you the next two moves they will roll. They must roll those moves on their turn, even if it would be a mistake to do so.\r\n> **SECRETS**: You learn a secret they\'re hiding. If you let them know, they take **2 [Drag]**.\r\n> **SURFACE THOUGHTS**: hey… salami..! give me back my hamster..! You find out EXACTLY what they\'re presently thinking, even if it\'s kinda dumb. You gain **2[Boost]**.\r\n> **SOMETHING INSIDE YOU**: You\'re not alone in there… there\'s some great evil… you learn of an **[Eerie]** **[Affliction]** inside them, or if they\'re **[Eerie]** themselves. Take **2 ESP** if they are. If they are affected by an **[Eerie]** **[Affliction]**, you give them a **+1 [Buff]** to their next roll for it. This is a **[One-Off]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Whoa! Your mind probe makes their brain all… fizzy! You get a **GOOD**, and the target is **[Overwhelmed]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Holy shit, that\'s REALLY fizzy! You can practically feel the static coming off of them! You get a **GREAT**, but they experience **[Sensory Overload]** for **2 turns** and are **[Overwhelmed]** after that.'),
('threeActStructure', 'THREE ACT STRUCTURE', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Passive][Magic][Locked: Narrator]', 'You\'ve likely heard it a thousand times; every story has a beginning, middle and end. The exacts of how those beginnings, middle and ends work are subtly defined by a very strict ruleset. Seriously, think of any story you know, and ask yourself if it doesn\'t, to some degree, follow these rules! The rules are metamagically tightened when you\'re around, your presence enforcing this structure on a reality-bending level. You can choose whether or not to activate this move or not at the start of the encounter, but you can\'t turn it off midway through.\r\n\r\n> **ACT ONE**: The ordinary world is introduced, and then soon after the story is plunged into action! On the first turn of a combat encounter, you and your allies all get a +2 to your rolls.\r\n\r\n> **ACT TWO**: The main body of our adventure! Subplots begin and end, heroes go through trials and tribulations, and our characters learn more about themselves on the way. Every two turns between Act One and Three (starting on your second turn), you gain **1 [Boost]** as you act awesome and gear up for the finale. \r\n\r\n> **ACT THREE**: The grand finale, the climax, the final battle. Loved ones die after giving you meaningful messages, people doubt the heroes, but ultimately the quest is complete and the story resolves. The first time anyone on the field hits **4 HP** or below, all other participants take **2 [Psychic]** damage in a metareal effort to even the playing fields. You and your allies gain **1 [Resistance]** to all damage after this.'),
('threshecutioner', 'THRESHECUTIONER', 'OLIVE', 'ADULT', '[Olive][Locked: Adult]', 'Charge! Cut! Cull! Chop! For the Empress, \\\'till we drop! Charge! Cut! Cull! Chop! \\\'Till they\\\'re dead, \\\'till they stop! The Threshecutioner is probably one of the most recognizable of the front-line fighters in the glorious army of the Empire. You and your flaysquad create carnage with your threshing sickles, partaking in marching songs and chants as you wade through the enemies. This bolsters morale, keeps track of each other, and scares the shit out of your foes. As a Threshecutioner, you are issued a standard issue THRESHING SICKLE, which comes with two Abstrata of your choice pre-installed. Neither Abstrata can be **MERCYKIND**. Additionally, when in an encounter, you can take an action to begin chanting, which makes you **[Proud]** as well as giving you 1 **[WHAM]** every 3 rounds. If you\\\'re with other Threshecutioners, they can join in as a **[Free] [Reaction]**, making you all **[Icarian]**. Being **[Stunned]**, sent **[Floorbound]**, or knocked **[Unconscious]** stops the singing immediately, and if any allies had joined in, they immediately take 2 **[Drag]** as the beat is interrupted abruptly.'),
('throughGritTeeth', 'THROUGH GRIT TEETH', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Passive][Locked: Labourer]', 'Ugh, fuck. You messed up. You\'re hard at work, but you really need to say the right thing to an ally, to analyze the situation, to do something OTHER than work. But if your focus lapses, your rhythm falls apart, and the work you\'ve trained yourself to never stop doing stops being done. You can\'t waste your breath. But… maybe, through grit teeth, you can pause your work for just long enough to make it count. As a **[One-Off]** while you\'re GETTING TO WORK, you can choose not to make any **[Physical]** rolls this turn and instead make **[Mental]** ones. These don\'t use **+APP**. If you use this effect, you replace all **[Emotions]** you have with the exclusive **[Determined]** emotion, described below. This doesn\'t affect **[Tired]** or **[Exhausted]**.\n\n**Determined**: An emotion where you won\'t give up, no matter what. All **[Drag]** you gain so long as you have this emotion is reduced by 1 (min. 1), and you only trigger **[Drag]** from **[Tired]** or **[Exhausted]** on an **OK** or **GOOD** respectively.'),
('thunderdomeThunderbulge', 'THUNDERDOME THUNDERBULGE', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Jock]', 'LLLLLLET’S GET RRRRRREADY TO RRRRRRRRUMBLE! TIGHTEN YOUR ABS! FLEX YOUR CALVES! PUMP! THOSE! BICEPS! IN THE YEAR 4130 BC A CAVETROLL PICKED UP A ROCK AND DROP KICKED IT INTO A PLAGUEMOOSE, THUS INVENTING SPORTS. AND THAT TROLL? WAS TROLL ALBERT EINSTEIN. YOU ARE HIS CHILD. AND YOU ARE READY TO TEST THE LIMITS OF THE TROLLIC RACE. BECAUSE YOU ARE THE LIMIT! LET’S! F%CKING! GOOOOOOOO! You gain access to HERO MODE through your MYTHIC MANGRIT. You may take action to convert **[Boost]** to **[WHAM]** at a conversion rate of 3 to 1. Additionally, you are built like a brick shithouse; you have **1 [Resistance]** against **[Somatic]** damage thanks to your AWESOME build. Finally, when you\'re on your last legs, it\'s all muscle, all hustle. When you have **3 HP** or lower, all rolls use **+GRT**. All of them.'),
('thwapThat', 'THWAP THAT', 'OTHER', 'QUADRANT', '[Quadrant][Passive]\r\n', 'Oh geez, what idiot is over there trying to pick up someone six castes higher with cheesy pick-up lines. That\'s so cringe. \r\n. . . . . .\r\nOh fuck, that\'s YOUR IDIOT!!!\r\n\r\n**NEW QUADS (1-4 IRL WEEKS)**: Your **[Manipulate]** rolls against your ashmate get a **+1 [Buff]**. You take **1 [Psychic]** damage every time they fail a **[Manipulate]** roll in front of you from secondhand cringe.\r\n\r\n**ESTABLISHED RELATIONSHIP (1-11 IRL MONTHS)**: Your **[Manipulate]** rolls against your ashmate get a **+2 [Buff]**. You take **1 [Psychic]** damage every time they fail a **[Manipulate]** roll in front of you because jegus fuck are you STILL doing this??? \r\n\r\n**ROCK SOLID (1 YEAR+)**: Your **[Manipulate]** rolls against your ashmate get a **+2 [Buff]**, and on a successful WORDPLAY roll against them, you may apply one **[Base]** Emotion to them. \r\n\r\n**QUAD BONDED**: Your **[Manipulate]** rolls against your ashmate **[Tier Up]**, and on a successful WORDPLAY roll against them, you may apply one Base **[Emotion]** to them. You gain **2 [Boost]** every time they successfully **[Manipulate]** in front of you from sheer pride at how far they\'ve come.\r\n'),
('timehopper', 'TIMEHOPPER', 'TIME', 'TIME', '[Aspect][Ultra][Recharge: 3][Locked: Time]', 'For a long time you’ve considered life a direct, single line from start to end, and when you die, you die. But you’ve learned things aren’t that simple! Time splits into a trillion tributaries, each telling incrementally different stories, each of them different and beautiful. You are **[Talented]** at all **[Strife]** rolls, as you’ve learned to stay in pace with the eternal battle against time. Forget staying in pace, even - you\'re a step or three ahead! You can use the following two **[Free] [Reactions]**, each of which has its own **[Recharge: 3]**: \r\n\r\n> **BACKSTEP**: Record scratch. Reset. Let\'s try that again. At the end of any turn, you can BACKSTEP, pinning the clock back to the start of the turn to give it a second go. Your opponents\' rolls during rewound turns are **[Inept]** as they stumble, and yours are **[Talented]** as you rise to the challenge, which can push **[Strife]** rolls up to **[Legendary]** - if the tables turn, you\'ll be the one turning them.\r\n\r\n> **TIMESKIP**: Double time, on the double! At the start of any turn, you can TIMESKIP, instantly moving the encounter a round forward as you kick up the tempo. This makes all time-based effects advance, from **[Hazards]** to **[Recharges]** to timed conditions - no pause button on this track, just a fast-forward!\r\n'),
('timeOff', 'TIME OFF', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'You’ve forced yourself to stop worrying about working all the time, and… huh! Turns out, taking time to focus on yourself has really helped you become a more rounded person. Who knew not burning yourself out like a candle in the wind was a viable choice? Whenever you don’t roll MONEYMAKERY for a whole week, when you finally roll another MONEYMAKERY move, you get +1 **LUX** on your result so long as you get a **GOOD**+.'),
('tinfoilImplants', 'TINFOIL IMPLANTS', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'TIT', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Locked: TIT]', 'You have tangoed with the freaky and unnatural too many times to leave shit up to chance. You CANNOT let yourself be screwed over by trolls who happen to break reality. You\'ve taken on some extra tech (read: plates in your skull or something) to ensure that they don\'t give you any trouble. As such, **[Magic]** and **[Control]** moves against you are **[Inept]**, and when you get a **GREAT** **[Analyze]** troll on a **[Cullbait]** troll (including Lime Troll with the WALKING COGNITOHAZARD move), you see right through them, even if they\'re disguised. OVER HERE! CULLBAIT!\n\n'),
('tipOfYourTongue', 'TIP OF YOUR TONGUE', 'OTHER', 'MAGE', '[Class][Basic][Passive][One-off][Locked: Mage]', 'Hey… hey wait a minute. Oh! Oh! Ooooh, oh, you know this one, you know this one! It’s the thing… the thing that is tied to like, your sense of self. An aspect if you will. Yeah! Yeah you know that one! Of course you know that one! When you or someone else in the encounter uses a non-**[Passive] [Aspect]** move of your **[Aspect]** for the first time, you become **[Enthusiastic]**.\r\n'),
('tippingTheScales', 'TIPPING THE SCALES', 'OTHER', 'HEIR', '[Class][Basic][Free][One-Off][Magic][Locked: Heir]', 'You don’t really make the things you want happen. They just kind of… well, HAPPEN! Stuff just turns out to be the best for you and your friends! Or horribly horribly wrong. But hey! Stand close enough to bad guys and maybe that can be a positive! As a **[Free]** action at the start of an encounter, choose one group of moves from the list below. Then decide if everyone in the encounter, including you, will gain a +1 **[Buff]** or a -1 **[Nerf]** when they roll a move with that tag. It’s not cheating if you’re inadvertently messing with fate just a teensy bit. right? \r\n\r\nMOVES:\r\n- **[Mental]**\r\n- **[Psionic]**, but not **[Strife]**\r\n- **[Physical]**, but not **[Strife]**\r\n- **[Manipulation]**\r\n- **[Reaction]**\r\n'),
('tisButAScratch', 'TIS BUT A SCRATCH', 'OTHER', 'SHADOWDROPPER', '[Template][Basic][Recharge: 2][Eerie][Heal][Physical][Locked: Shadowdropper]', 'Look, buddy, it\'s kinda stupid to try to kill you. You\'re licherally (get it) undead. You\'ve been through this before! Look, you\'ll prove it! (CLACK CLACK CLACK) Easy! You can always push your body back together and pretend it’s as good as new! You can\'t do this while you\'re under 0 HP. When you want to fix yourself up, roll **+APP**. \r\n\r\n**MIN**: aAAAAAUUURGGHUUUHHHHH… you fall to pieces and immediately disassemble. Wwwwwhelp. That\'s cool, you guess. Suuuuure. You cannot use any **[Physical]** moves at all until you spend a **[Lengthy]** action putting yourself back together. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: Ah, fuck, you flung your body part away! Stupid! You take **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Aaaaaalright… took some finessing, but see, no problem! You get a **GOOD**, but this becomes a **[Lengthy]** action. If you have no more actions on your turn, you instead become **[Slowed]** next turn.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Tada!!! All good! You\'re very good at this. You heal **1 HP**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Aaand… yeah, nice, okay! **2 HP** healed! You\'re doing great, buddy.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: It really is good as new! Wow, this whole being dead thing is easy! You heal **3 HP**, simple!\r\n\r\n'),
('titantussler', 'TITANTUSSLER', 'VIOLET', 'ADULT', '[Violet][Locked: Adult]', 'ALIENS. They’re out there. They’re big, scary, and totally want to rock your shit… But not if you rock THEIR shit first! You are a Titantussler. You help prepare alien planets for colonization and protect existing colonies from outside evils by clearing out the local wildlife, whether you’re operating a mech or using plain ol’ violet fisticuffs. Additionally, you excavate holes to be filled with water for new violet cities. More oceans, MORE! You accomplish all this with your standard issue HEAVEN-PIERCING GIGA DRILL! Your training for facing such threats lets you act accordingly. When you face a foe that is lower leveled than you or a monster below level 3, you begin the encounter **[Enthusiastic]** to kick some ass! If the enemy is higher leveled than you or a monster at or above level 3, you become **[Brave]** as you prepare to fearlessly face down giants. This effect is based on the highest level foe in the encounter. Additionally, you gain access to the very exclusive **DRILLKIND** Abstrata now for free. You may use it in tandem with any other abstrata you have.\n\n> **DRILLKIND**: VRRRRRRM! Your weapon is a sharp, high speed spinning drill. You can practically tear into almost anything with this bad boy! On a **MAX [Strife]** roll, you can entirely ignore a target’s **[Somatic] [Resistance]**.'),
('toAGoodCause', 'TO A GOOD CAUSE', 'OTHER', 'ROGUE', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Magic][Locked: Rogue]', 'You are a rogue. You steal things! It\'s what you do. Your tipsy friend\'s scuttlebuggy keys, fresh veg out of your neighbor\'s garden for your lusus, spicy diary entries from your ashmate\'s crush… Seeing things go to waste feels so wrong, and if there\'s nobody else around to help… why not help yourself? Every other **GREAT [Strife]** roll you hit someone with, one point of the damage dealt is stolen and goes to you as **HP**. Don\'t worry, it\'s going to a good cause! Additionally, when you, an ally, or an enemy uses a move that requires all **[Boost]** to be spent, one point of that **[Boost]** is reserved and goes to you. Waste not!\r\n\r\n\r\n'),
('toilAndTrouble', 'TOIL AND TROUBLE', 'OTHER', 'WITCH', '[Class][Passive][Unlock: Witch]', 'You don\'t accept consequences. You just don\'t! Why should you, when your ambition burns as brightly as it does? Double double toil and trouble, fire burn and cauldron- oops. Knocked the cauldron over. That’s fine! You can work with this! When your actions backfire on you, you work around it. Any time you roll a **MIN** on a **[Chicanery]** roll, it tiers up to a **BAD** and you suffer zero consequences!\n\n'),
('toolsOfTheTrade', 'TOOLS OF THE TRADE', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Legislacerator]', 'No good Legislacerator leaves the hive unprepared. You gain access to the following **[Consumable]** items, each worth **1 VP**. You have **10 VP**, not 8.\r\n\r\n> **GRAPPLING HOOK**: Deploy to start **[Flying]** for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **FLASHBANGS**: **[Stun]** and **[Blind]** all enemies and allies except for your HUNTED target, who is **[Quickened]** for a turn. This is **[One-Off]**. \r\n\r\n> **BOLAS**: When you **[Trap]** an opponent, you also knock them **[Floorbound]** if you were wielding this item.\r\n\r\n> **WANTED POSTERS**: Wave this in someone\'s face; if it\'s of them or someone they know, they become **[Scared]**, and you notice.\r\n\r\n> **TRACKING DEVICE**: Discreetly apply this to someone (which may require a **GOOD** SHENANIGANS roll) or their vehicle to see where they go. They can\'t be **[Hidden]** from you until they find it with a PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll.\r\n\r\n> **SMOKE BOMB**: Become **[Hidden]** without rolling.\r\n\r\n> **NERVE AGENT**: On a **MAX** **[Strife]** roll, do no damage as you make the target **[Godawful]** at **[Physical]** rolls for **3 turns**.\r\n\r\n> **RESTRAINTS**: Bag em and tag em. With these ropes, chains and shackles, you can move an unconscious troll anywhere you like, taking them back to your hive, your vehicle or your employer. They can\'t roll any moves until released.'),
('tooMuchTooFast', 'TOO MUCH TOO FAST', 'HEART', 'HEART', '[Aspect][Basic][Lengthy][Locked: Heart]', 'You have very intense interests and an equally intense personality. Sometimes, you are prone to kinda go off, infodumping about your interests hard. This can leave other trolls a little overwhelmed since you have difficulty remembering their limits are different to yours. You can drop a high brow lecture on personality, rant about anime, or give a heroic monologue as a single action. This makes the target **[Confused]**. You can turn this into a **[Lengthy]** action to additionally deal **1 [Verbal]** damage, which doesn’t stack with **[WHAM]**.'),
('topStudent', 'TOP STUDENT', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Bookworm]', 'You\'re the smartest! Smarter than anyone else! It\'s a point of pride for you to never fail. Ever! So, uh, if someone else is acting smart… you can\'t lose! When someone else makes a **+PSP** roll around you, your **+PSP** rolls can\'t be lower than theirs for a round. If you roll lower than them, you gain a number of **[Drag]** equal to half the difference between your actual roll and theirs, and then get the same roll result as them. If you get higher, you gain a number of **[Boost]** equal to a quarter of the difference between your roll and theirs.'),
('toTheVictor', 'TO THE VICTOR', 'FUCHSIA', 'FUCHSIA', '[Fuchsia][Ultra][Passive]', 'You can\'t be beaten. Like, the only one who could ever come close isn\'t on this planet. You cannot die unless by the hand of another Fuchsia, either JUSTLY or HEROICALLY; you simply go **[Unconscious]**. Your max HP doubles again, making you an unstoppable bullet sponge. You may choose to inflict a JUST or HEROIC death on your enemies upon your inevitable victory. You are **[Legendary]** at all rolls, and you have access to ALL HERO MODES. Yup!'),
('touchy', 'TOUCHY', 'TIME', 'TIME', '[Aspect][Basic][Free][Reaction][Locked: Time]', 'You’re a little fast to guess that people are assuming the worst of you. It’s not that you’re defensive- defensive? Who said that? You’re NOT defensive. What the hell is that supposed to mean? Are you trying to start something, buddy?! Go to hell! Whenever someone rolls to **[Manipulate]** or deal **[Verbal]** damage against you, you can go on the defensive; your **[Strife]** rolls get a **+1 [Buff]** and their **[Manipulate]** rolls **[Tier Down]**. This effect lasts until they apologize and rescind, which gives you **3 [Boost]** instead.'),
('tractoExCulo', 'TRACTO EX CULO', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Mary Sue]', 'NOW… YOU KNOW MY TRUE SECRET… I’M ACTUALLY A MUTANT!\r\n\r\nYou aren’t.\r\n\r\nWhat? Where the hell did this come from? You’re not a mutant. What? Oh! Right, see, the thing is, your life was starting to feel a little stale, so… hey, you added a sudden sweet twist! Cool, right? And well-researched too, I’ll bet. Your supposed permanent change disappears when you are **below half HP**. Select one of the following options. You can change it with a day of **[Downtime]**.\r\n\r\n> 1. You gain any one mutation from the MUTANTS chapter. \r\n> 2. You gain access to an **[Eerie]** Template, even if you would not normally be able to, such as Rainbow Drinker or Grimdark, and gain the **[Entry]** now.'),
('traditionalMedicine', 'TRADITIONAL MEDICINE', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Recharge: 2][Heal][Physical][Locked: Folklorist]', 'Herbal remedies, granny cures, mellified moles… medicine in Alternia is generally frowned upon aside from state-controlled medicalizers, because you know. The Wounded Shall Be Culled and all that. In theory, that should mean many lowbloods should die due to a lack of access to healing products. In practice, that means that these castes have made their own alternatives. Some work, some don\'t, but it\'s better than nothing. When you want to believe in the power of old-fashioned curatives and aid yourself or someone else, roll **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Oh no! You didn\'t believe shit, and now you are exposed to a great illness! Roll 2d8 on the **BAD** table.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You **[Heal] 1 HP**… and are afflicted with an effect! Roll 1d8.\r\n\r\n> 1. Exposed to the Dancing Fever affliction (Uh-oh).\r\n> 2. **[Poisoned]**.\r\n> 3. Exposed to the Psiburn affliction.\r\n> 4. **[Overwhelmed]**.\r\n> 5. Exposed to the Fury Fever affliction.\r\n> 6. **[Tired]**.\r\n> 7. Exposed to the Sniffles affliction \r\n> 8. **[Sad]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Believe harder next time. Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Okay! You **[Heal] 1 HP**, or use this roll against an **[Affliction]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Getting there, getting there… you **[Heal] 2 HP**, or use this roll against an **[Affliction]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: What a panacea! You **[Heal] 3 HP**, or use this roll against an **[Affliction]**!'),
('tragicomicMask', 'TRAGICOMIC MASK', 'OTHER', 'BARD', '[Class][Passive][Unlock: Bard]', 'Teehee! You spend your life playing a part that you don\'t entirely understand. This means that you\'re somewhat... lacking in your aspect a little bit. You lean naturally towards your opposite, in fact! So much so, that you gain access to the **[Unlock]** move of your opposite **[Aspect]** upon taking this move. You can gain the other moves, too! But... at a cost. Every time you take one of the 12 moves from your aspect, you lock yourself from taking more from your natural **[Aspect]**. (i.e if you take 8 from your opposite you may only ever take 4 moves from your true **[Aspect]**) Additionally, you can’t unlock the opposite **[Aspect] [Ultra]** like this and **[Aspect]** moves of your opposite **[Aspect]** do not count towards your completion for your true **[Aspect] [Ultra]**, you silly billy. \r\n'),
('trainedInstincts', 'TRAINED INSTINCTS', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Passive]', 'Ultra aware! You may be easily distractible, but when you focus your senses, you become impossible to stop! From assassins chasing down a target to shopkeepers chasing a thief, you’re good at hunting prey, no matter what! Your PROBLEM SLEUTHING rolls to SPOT targets are **[Tiered Up]**.'),
('treasureHoarder', 'TREASURE HOARDER', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'MYAHAHAHA! YOU LOVE BEING RICH! You prove your self worth to yourself with material wealth, and boy, that’s a lot of it. Even higher castes aren’t as flashy as you with your treasure hordes leaking out of the corners of your rooms, like some blue-tongued snazzard. You are always **[Talented]** at MONEYMAKERY **[Downtime]** rolls. You gain access to the following Hivecrafting Upgrades. \r\n\r\n**OBNOXIOUS PAINTINGS (3 LUX)**: They\'re all of you! Opponents are a little shocked by how insanely egotistical you appear to be, and start any combat encounter in your hive with **2 [Drag]**. However, they can figure out a lot about you here; their first **[Analyze]** roll against you in your hive is **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n\r\n**LUSUS DEATH PIT (3 LUX)**: GOOD LORD! Some Ceruleans have trap doors that lead to a fight chamber with their custodian. Knocking a troll **[Floorbound]** in your hive may knock them into a room where they must fight your Custodian (usually using stats for a monster that would be fair for the character or group to fight at their level), and if they win, you immediately lose the will to fight yourself.\r\n\r\n**PILES OF TREASURE (5 LUX)**: Ayo… talk about subtle flexing, right? Piles of treasure litter the halls of your home. People definitely think you\'re obnoxious, but you feel RICH. Opponent **+APP** rolls in your hive are **[Inept]**. However, if the opponent wins here, they gain **Treasure II** as they pocket some stuff.\r\n\r\n**EXPENSIVE COLLECTION (5 LUX)**: You\'ve got all SORTS of stuff here, huh?! Any troll in an encounter in your hive can buy **Rich** items on the fly as they pick up your stuff. Enemies can\'t leave with them unless they sneak it out, or beat you in combat.'),
('treeLimbs', 'TREE LIMBS', 'OTHER', 'WYLDERDRUID', '[Template][Basic][Downtime][Magic][Locked: Wylderdruid]', 'When people think of Alternian prosthetics, they usually think of cybernetics. Fuck that! You’re incorporating nature itself into your body, making prosthetic limbs out of living vines, swirling vortices of leaves or seawater, or maybe you’re just growing a whole-ass slitherbeast out of your shoulder blade. You can take this even if you don’t have missing limbs - Spidermoms didn’t stop at two limbs, after all. As a **[Downtime]** action, you can construct an artificial arm or leg from the **PROSTHETICS** chapter at the **ULTRARICH** level for no LUX. You can only have one of these additional prosthetic limbs, but you can switch up the traits it has as a **[Downtime]** action; it also doesn’t have the **[Mechanical]** tag or count towards the **CYBORG [Template]** because it’s not, well, mechanical. In addition, you can select from the following traits for your wacky nature prosthetic, in addition to the traits listed in the **PROSTHETICS** chapter:\r\n\r\n> **BITER**: Your limb has fangs, or maybe particularly grapply thorns. On a **GREAT** or higher **[Strife]** roll, your limb can detach from your body, munching on your opponent and causing 1 **[Somatic]** damage per round until they take an action to remove it. Until they do this you can\'t roll **[Strife]** moves.\r\n\r\n> **OVERGROWN**: Your limb is a tangled mess of vines, flowers, or mushrooms. It grows so fast! When you take 2 or more damage in one attack, roll a 1d6; on a 6, you take 1 less damage.\r\n\r\n> **MOIST**: ...Spongy! Your limb might be sparkling with the morning dew, slimy like a snail or maybe is just a vaguely leg-shaped churning mass of water. Your rolls to SOAK your opponents with a **SHENANIGANS** roll are **[Legendary]**.\r\n\r\n> **SELF-PRESERVING**: Ah, yes, your loyal leg. What? You\'re a druid. Your limb may be a condensed swarm of insects or an emboldened limb from an ancient tree- whatever it is, it likely has some basic thoughts and is concerned with its, and therefore your, survival. If you ever go **[Unconscious]** and **CLOCK\'S TICKING** activates, your limb will attempt to drag you out of danger. It rolls **ABSCOND** with your **+GRA** stat, although the roll is **[Inept]** because only one (1) of your limbs is operational.'),
('trendsetter', 'TRENDSETTER', 'OTHER', 'HAUTE_CLAWTURE', '[Template][Advanced][Buildup: 2][Free][Locked: Haute Clawture]', 'Every good designer is prepared to change up their looks at a moment\'s notice. If you\'re not trendy, then what are you? Stuck in one style, like those trolls who pretend the scene stage never left? Pffff. You\'re not a neanderthal. At the beginning of your turn, decide who among you is FASHION FORWARD or FASHION BACKWARD. Then, roll 1d8:\r\n\r\n> **1-2**: TO THE FUTURE! The trends change in favor of the FASHION FORWARD. All who are FASHION FORWARD feel **[Proud]**, and FASHION BACKWARD trolls feel **[Dread]**.\r\n\r\n> **3-5**: TREND LONGEVITY! Whichever trend was chosen last time around becomes the new normal, resetting all buffs and debuffs.\r\n\r\n> **6-8**: RETRO INSPIRATION! The trends change in favor of the FASHION BACKWARD. All who are FASHION BACKWARD get **[Hopeful]**, and all FASHION FORWARD trolls feel **[Enraged]**.'),
('tricksOfTheTrade', 'TRICKS OF THE TRADE', 'OTHER', 'THIEF', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Thief]', 'Like all skills, the more you steal, the better you get at it. By now, you’ve stolen a lot. Enough that you’ve learned some new tricks of the trade. Whenever you **YOINK** something successfully, you gain 1 **[Boost]**. Also, your **VP** expands by 6 so you can hold even more. It’s not like you’re going to let it fall on the floor, are you?'),
('trolled', 'TROLLED!', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Basic][One-Off][Reaction][Mental]', 'Oooogh! You’ve had it! You’ve had it with these trolls! They did it, they got your goat! They fully deserve the ability to say “Trololo” in your face now, like the funny internet video everyone knows and loves forever! You feel like a real Rick Astley’s “Rickroll’d” victim right now! When you are pushed too hard, you snap, losing your temper and going off on your opponent! Living on Alteria is VERY frustrating, you know! When someone uses a **MAX** **[Chicanery]** effect on you, you may choose to become **[Enraged]** for **[Free]**, but can only use **[Verbal]** **[Strife]** rolls such as WORDPLAY\'s JAB, even if you were in a physical fight prior to this. The opponent also cannot use **[Physical]** or **[Psionic]** moves against you in this state, a little ashamed to have pushed you this far- though they can retaliate with their own **[Verbal]** **[Strife]** rolls. They can end this effect by apologizing to you as a **[Lengthy]** action, giving you **3 [Boost]**.'),
('trollInTheChair', 'TROLL IN THE CHAIR', 'OTHER', 'HACKERMAN', '[Template][Basic][Locked: Hackerman]', 'You\'re Mission Control, the Troll Ned Leeds rather than the action hero. Although your involvement with people typically needs you to get in the field and help out, you\'re used to being the troll at the computer with three monitors and a headset telling the protagonist what to do. You can be present in a scene without physically being present, observing the scene through cameras, drone feeds, etcetera. You may make **[Mental]** rolls and **[Tech]** rolls, but nothing else. You can designate another troll as your BOOTS ON THE GROUND. This troll can roll any move on your sheet that is physically possible and reasonable for them to achieve, if you spend an action instructing them on how to. However, you can only use moves that affect allies on your BOOTS ON THE GROUND.'),
('trollSeeTrollDo', 'TROLL SEE TROLL DO', 'OTHER', 'PERFECTLY_GENERIC', '[Passive]', 'Huh… you REALLY want this move for your character, but unfortunately, you’re not in that caste! Whatever shall you do? You’ll take TROLL SEE TROLL DO, baby! You gain an **[Open]** **[Basic]** move from any caste. This move costs two levels, and can only be taken once.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('trollsInTeal', 'TROLLS IN TEAL', 'ORGANIZATIONS', 'TIT', '[Template][Passive][One-Off][Unlock: TIT]', 'Prerequisite: You are Teal.\r\n\r\nYou are a member of the Trolls in Teal; the abnormality censorship and Eerie phenomena research division of the Imperial Color Guard. The Researcherasor, the Scienstiff, the Thoughtcop. With the great honor of serving your Heiress and Empress, you additionally carry their voice through your own if you can justify your orders as Org related. You have a conditional authority over all non-Org trolls, and Drones will not target you while in your ORG Uniform, which you gain now for free, as well as a flair on all social media marking you as a member of the JR. TIT. Your duties to Alternia are to maintain stability and order from behind the scenes, rather than the flashy and upfront art of violent repression the CIS and HET engage in. Discover something new? Erased. Discover some political art? Censored. Make a scientific breakthrough that could change the world? Well, that\'s for YOU to know... As such, you\'ve gotten pretty good at quickly wiping memories. You have an Amnesticizor, a special item that takes no Sylladex Slot. It has **2 HP**, and can be replaced for free at the end of an encounter. When you want to wipe someone\'s memories, roll **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: It wasn\'t amnestics you sprayed! It was BEE PHEROMONES! How clumsy of you! You summon a BEE SWARM **[Hazard]** that is hostile to everyone in the area.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: They don\'t forget shit. And you used it all up. Oh, you\'re such a ditz.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You spray some the wrong way... Thankfully, you have another dose! You can try again next turn.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Whew! You make the target forget about some stuff. You reset the target\'s stats (except for HP) back to any point in the last three turns. They also forget anything said, revealed or understood at this time. You may use it on yourself.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: PSSSSHT! How\'s THAT for knowledge retention, dickbits? You get the effects of a **GOOD**, but you have **[Recharge: 3]**, not **[One-Off]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: A dose so powerful, you can rewrite the mind. You get the effects of a **GREAT**, and the troll instantly becomes friendly towards you. You may implant up to three false memories (each of which can only be four word sentences), and erase up to a week\'s worth of information from their minds. Whether or not they believe the false memories is on them, but they won\'t know you put them there.'),
('trollsWorldTour', 'TROLLS WORLD TOUR', 'OTHER', 'MUSICREANT', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Musicreant]', 'You count yourself among those who would use music to change the world… but how you go about this is an altogether different ordeal! Choose your genre and gain a bonus from it:\r\n\r\n**ROCK**: Keraaang! Electricity and percussion drives your song! You gain **1 [Boost]** whenever you take **[Electrical]** damage, because you\'re pretty used to self electrocution by now, and can apply VOLTKIND on a **GREAT** instead of a **MAX**.\r\n\r\n**METAL**: I\'m sorry, I can\'t hear you, I\'m making everyone MOSH. Once per encounter, as a **GOOD** WORDPLAY roll with **[Buildup: 3]**, you can make all your allies **[Enraged]**.\r\n\r\n**SLAM POETRY**: Your words flow in a constant beat, a constant flow, dropping the sickest rap you\'ve ever known! You can use WORDPLAY twice in the same turn.\r\n\r\n**JAZZ**: Your music, reportedly, has no boundaries. You track **[Boost]** and **[Drag]** separately; gaining one does not affect the other.\r\n\r\n**ORCHESTRAL**: You play COOL instruments. You\'ve got style and taste. You have a +1 on all **[Manipulate]** rolls on trolls of jade and up.\r\n\r\n**ADULT CONTEMPORARY**: Wrong answer. Choose again. \r\n\r\n**COUNTRY**:  No, not the modern stuff about scuttletrucks and lemon juice. The old stuff, where you talked about shooting teals (IN A HEMOSPECTRUM ABIDING WAY) and forming unions (TO BETTER SERVE HIGHBLOODS), you know? Unless, uh, scuttletrucks really are your thing. You gain **1 [Boost]** at the start of any encounter with an ally, and every **three turns** thereafter.\r\n\r\n**VOCAL**: You focus on using your voice like an instrument. You get **3 [Hold]** at the start of every encounter; you can spend this **[Hold]** to get a **GOOD** WORDPLAY roll.\r\n\r\n**POP**: In a saccharinely cute dress with saccharinely cute music, you\'re… annoyingly cute. You can reduce one of your other stats to boost your **+PLC** by 1, even to +5. You still can\'t roll higher than a +5 on a single roll.\r\n\r\n**EDM**: BWEEEP BWAPBWAP SCREE! You somehow make random metal scraping noises sound **GOOD**! Good for you! While you are present, you and your allies cannot roll lower than an **OK** at a FRAYMOTIF roll.\r\n\r\n**SOME OTHER BULLSHIT**: Look man, you make the music, not me. I\'m just a TTRPG designer. Pick one of the above effects that best reflects your genre of music.'),
('truckFreak', 'TRUCK FREAK', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Passive][Locked: Junker]', 'Out of your friends, which are you? Well, that one’s easy: you\'re the one that LOVES scuttlebuggies! You’d be surprised how many usable pieces of scuttlebuggies get left out in junkyards or on the plains, and they’re pretty easy to salvage! VEHICLES and VEHICLE UPGRADES cost **2 LUX** less than normal for you; when you take this move, you gain **4 LUX** to spend on a VEHICLE and UPGRADES immediately. Additionally, you have access to the following exclusive VEHICLE UPGRADES.\r\n\r\n> **CRASH GEAR (1 LUX)**: Yeah, you hooked up your truck to run people over. It\'s pretty great. You don\'t need to STEER in order to RAM, but you do 1 less damage if you don\'t.\r\n\r\n> **OPEN BUILD (1 LUX)**: You\'ve got lots of places you can hang from on your vehicle, like open doors or roofs. You can make **[Physical]** rolls as normal inside your VEHICLE, but HIJACK rolls against you are **[Tiered Up]**.\r\n\r\n> **EXTRA SEATING (2 LUX)**: You can always get more people! Your VEHICLE gains an additional seat you can put a passenger in. These passengers get their own controls, allowing them to roll VEHICULATE as well.\r\n\r\n> **HAZARDOUS SPIKES (2 LUX)**: Witness you! This thing is covered in spikes and shit; your ride does **1 [Somatic]** damage to anyone who does **[Somatic]** damage to it first.\r\n\r\n> **MILLIPEDE LEGS (3 LUX)**: Many legs are better than six! Your stable build and sleek design mean the penalty to VEHICULATE you take from high HORSEPOWER reduces to -1 rather than -2.\r\n\r\n> **JET ENGINE (3 LUX)**: EXPERIMENTAL TURBO CORE LET\'S GOOOOOO! As an action, you can double your current HORSEPOWER. This is completely suicidal of you, but hey, have fun!'),
('trueBeliever', 'TRUE BELIEVER', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Ultra][Buildup: 3][Passive][Magic][Locked: Honkpostle]', 'You are among the most respected and feared preachers of the Church, having proven yourself a mighty inheritor of the Mirthful Messiahs\' maddening troupe. With your devotion, you\'ve learned to unlock something in yourself that turns you into a miraculous manifestation of their twin power. You gain access to HERO MODE through your INCREDIBLE IMAGINATION. You may take your aspect and class\'s opposite\'s moves; for example, if you are a Knight of Rage, you\'d be able to take the moves of a Page of Hope. After **[Buildup: 3]** in combat, you split your soul in two and become divine manifestations of the gods. You automatically gain the benefits of the SPLIT ACTIONS LET\'S STRIFE roll, except that it lasts for the encounter. While in this form, you become dazzling and idealized twin versions of yourself and your opposite, a silhouette of your aspect\'s colors with flitting nebulas shining through, and perfectly white face paint. One half of you retains your aspect but not class, while the other your class and not aspect. For example, if you are a Knight of Rage, you would split into a purple Page of Rage, and a golden Knight of Hope. These two manifestations split your current HP, **[Boost]** and **[Drag]** in half (rounded up) and share it equally between them. If you had conditions affecting you beforehand, they are split randomly between you. Each half can only use the appropriate **[Zodiac]** moves that would be accessible to that half. If you have an **[Aspect]** or **[Class]** **[Ultra]**, you temporarily gain the other for halves (Such as, here, gaining the Hope ultra if you have the Rage ultra). Your halves may not use the same moves twice in one turn; otherwise, for all intents and purposes, you are two trolls who have seperate **[Recharge]**, **[Boost]** and conditions. If one of you is downed, the other may fight on, though they are **[Tired]**. Any opponents who see you in this form are **[Overwhelmed]**. Honk honk!'),
('trueGamer', 'TRUE GAMER', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Passive]', 'You\'ve played enough video games by now to know that to win any game, you need to focus on the objective rather than fun! And what is life except for the world\'s greatest MMO? Or something. You get the following CHAMPION and CHALLENGER effects in a TEAM STRIFE.\r\n\r\n> **CHAMPION— MATCHING OUTFITS**: Oh god. You really came here with an ESports jersey for everyone, huh? Good lord. The entire team gets the effects of a Fashion Collection of your choice without spending **LUX**. You all have the same colour, usually ones associated with your eyes. Let\'s go, team!\r\n\r\n> **CHALLENGER— BOSS BATTLERS**: WATCH OUT! This level looks really hard… but we can DO IT! Your STRUGGLER\'s **[Strife]** rolls can\'t be made **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]** or **[Nerfed]**.'),
('truncate', 'TRUNCATE', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Advanced][Physical][Strife][Locked: Cyberpunk]', 'You didn\'t do all these sweet upgrades so that you could stand around and get your ass kicked, did you? No, no. You\'re a living weapon! You\'ve got neon chainsaws in your arms! You have a gun in your throat! Bzzt blam blam blam! When you want to truncate someone\'s life expectancy, roll with the stat you got from NEONLIBERAL.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You explode. Take **10 [Somatic]** damage you overmodded fuck.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You miss, and your cybernetics hiss! You take **1 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Ssssss… steam hisses from your joints. You take **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: There\'s the payoff! You do **1 [Somatic]** damage. It triggers the **[Weakness]** of anything weak to VOLTKIND weapons.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: HAHA! YOUR SUPERIOR TECHNOLOGY WILL SHOW THEM! You either do **2 [Somatic]** damage, or do **1 [Somatic]** damage and one of the following effects based on your stat choice from NEONLIBERAL.\r\n\r\n> +RAS: Your arms stretch out on big silly springs! You **[Trap]** the opponent in your tangled limbs.\r\n> +PLC: Your hologram lets out a piercing scream, **[Deafening]** the opponent for **2 turns**.\r\n> +GRA: Your attack is so fast they can barely process it. You can make a second **[Strife]** roll, though it\'s at a **-3 [Nerf]**. If you\'re lucky, you can chain this multiple times for **[Free]** if the second roll is also **GREAT**, but the **[Nerf]** is cumulative.\r\n> +APP: Your attack leaves them dripping with acid! The target is **[Poisoned]** for **three turns**.\r\n> +HUB: Electricity storms out of you! YEAAAAH BABY! You either do 1 **[Electric]** damage to everyone present, or do **2 [Drag]** to your target.\r\n> +GRT: Your massive strength stuns the opponent! All of their **[Mental]** rolls are **[Inept]** for a turn.\r\n> +PSP: SIKE! This isn\'t a physical attack! It\'s **[Psychic]**! You still do **2 [Somatic]** damage.\r\n> +IMG: REALITY IS AN ILLUSION THE UNIVERSE IS A HOLOGRAM BUY GOLD! Your opponent\'s active **[Recharge]** is all increased by 1 as you overwhelm their senses. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: HOOOOOLY shit! Now that\'s intense! You get a **GREAT**, but do **2 damage** rather than 1.'),
('trustMe', 'TRUST ME', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][One-Off][Control][Magic]', 'Put out a hand. Offer it to someone. Ask them to trust you. Save their life. Sometimes, you need to ask people to put their faith in you to be able to help them… and that\'s not an easy thing to do. When you want to get a stranger to cooperate, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: WHAT THE FUCK ARE YOU DOOOIIIING? Your self preservation instincts make you freeze up. You feel **[Agitated]** as you struggle to find the will to help them.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Ngh… you can try, but… the look on their face makes you really wonder if it\'s worth it… you gain the **[Stressed]** condition.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You\'re not sure they heard you. You can roll again.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: They nod a little, cautiously. That\'s better than nothing. They probably comply, trusting you. If you blow your cover in their presence, and they choose to react poorly or tell someone, they feel **[Dread]** with all the guilt they\'ve got in them. You also take **2 [Boost]** as you prepare to do whatever it takes.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: The serious tone in your voice convinces the target to listen to you, no matter the revelation. The opponent physically cannot tell anyone about your secret, and you gain **3 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: The revelation rocks their world. Not only does the opponent find themselves unable to tell anyone, but their views on **[Cullbait]** trolls are seriously challenged. They are **[Charmed]** by you. You gain **5 [Boost]**.'),
('trustYouTrustMe', 'TRUST YOU TRUST ME', 'OTHER', 'HEMOANON', '[Hemoanon][Basic][Recharge: 3]', 'Trust, as a Hemoanon, is a hard commodity to come by nowanights. And while the age old adage \'stupid Anons are dead Anons\' holds true, it\'s a bit tough for you to tell what stupid exactly looks like. It could look like you, for all you know! Thankfully there are Anons who have come before you to help guide you, just as you will guide another sometime. Once per encounter, choose another Hemoanon to be your Guide. This Guide can be part of the current encounter. They may use a **[Reaction]** to guide you through a move on either your sheet or theirs that is reasonable for you to do, which you now roll with a **[Tier Up]**. Said roll uses your stat block, not theirs.\r\n'),
('tryIt', 'TRY IT!', 'HEART', 'HEART', '[Aspect][Basic][One-Off][Locked: Heart]', 'You’re pretty good at haranguing people to join in with your interests. Hey, hey, come do this mural with me, c’mon, c’mon! Your overboard insistence that they come along and do what you like instead of what they like gets to be kinda overwhelming, sometimes… you have a tendency to pester the target into doing something you like (take over the world with me! Talk about your issues with me! Write a novel with me!) even if they don\'t reeeeaallyyyy look like they\'re that interested. This habit extends to the middle of a fight too, when your latest brilliant plan to use a trampoline to take out that flying drone starts coming out of your mouth. You can take an action to bug your target into your latest scheme; If they refuse, they receive **2 [Drag]** as you continue to pester them about it. If they agree and do what you ask, you get **1 [Boost]** as you excitedly get to work; they receive one of the following benefits (their choice):\r\n\r\n> **ASSISTANCE**: Take **1 [Hold]** you can use to **[Tier Up]** rolls having to do with the Heartbound’s interest.\r\n> **MERRIMENT**: **[Heal] 2 HP** as you relax and play along.\r\n> **EXCITEMENT**: Take **3 [Boost]** as you psych yourself up to deal with the Heartbound’s request.\r\n> **GRATITUDE**: Take **1 [Hold]** you can use to later bribe the Heartbound with for an automatic **GREAT** **[Manipulate]** roll.'),
('tryItADifferentWay', 'TRY IT A DIFFERENT WAY', 'OTHER', 'MAID', '[Class][Advanced][Recharge: 1][Locked: Maid]', 'You never know - doing something different might mean new possibilities! Whenever you roll a **GREAT** or **MAX** on a move you have access to that offers you multiple effects from a list, you can substitute in an effect from another move, too; for example, rolling a **GREAT SWASHBUCKLE** and substituting in one effect of the same tier of success from **SHENANIGANS**, or one **GOOD SHENANIGANS** and one **GOOD SWASHBUCKLE**, etc. This does not include **[Strife]** options, such as with **WORDPLAY**. You get 1 **[Boost]** every time you do this as you feel energized by your ingenuity. '),
('trySomethingNew', 'TRY SOMETHING NEW', 'LIFE', 'LIFE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Life]', 'You’ve spent so long cooping yourself up and refusing to take a risk. Wouldn’t it be nice to try something new? At the beginning of an encounter, choose any move you have, including caste moves or other moves you chose through leveling up, that you are not **[Talented]** in. You get a **+2 [Buff]** to all rolls involving that move; if you were **[Inept]**, you instead lose the **[Inept]** condition. Once you have chosen a move to benefit, you cannot use the effects of TRY SOMETHING NEW on it until you have done so with 3 other moves.'),
('tryThisAgain', 'TRY THIS AGAIN', 'DOOM', 'DOOM', '[Aspect][Advanced][One-Off][Lengthy][Locked: Doom]', 'You know that when you tunnel vision on your goals, you can get a little heated, and so can your opponents. When things are looking rough, you can just… reset things and do it over with a fresh outlook. Once per encounter, you can spend both your actions to invite a fog to pass over you and your targets, resetting every troll in the encounter back to before the first round of your fight; no conditions, no **[Buffs]**, no **[Nerfs]**, no **[WHAM]**... you get the picture. **HP**, however, does not change. Both sides\' **[Strife]** rolls are **[Tiered Down]** for a round. Maybe this will be a good time to try holding out an olive branch?'),
('tunneltaunt', 'TUNNELTAUNT', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][One-Off][Manipulate]', 'What are they gonna do about it? Hm? Hit you? You\'re a Jade, Fishboy. There are only so many of you, and culling you is a bulge move. After all, if we get culled, the Troll Life Cycle grinds to a halt! Come on, cry about it!~ Your newfound confidence has helped you learn to weaponize your caste to say shit people really wouldn\'t usually take. When you wanna lay it down, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: OH GOD. OH GOD THEY\'RE KILLING YOU. OH GOD. The target gets **2 [WHAM]** that they can\'t lose for **a turn**, and you can\'t roll **[Manipulate]** moves for the encounter.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Oooookay, you pissed them off really badly. You can\'t roll **[Manipulate]** moves for the next **3 turns**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: The target squints, but isn\'t that affected. They\'re still gonna whoop your ass.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: BWEEEEEH! You seriously piss the target off… but they can\'t do shit about it! You say something you can\'t be held accountable for, and the target is **[Stressed]** for **3 turns**. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Dang, your words cut real deep, huh? Scary stuff. Your target becomes **[Stressed]** for the encounter. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: DUDE! You\'re BULLYING this dipshit highblood!! The target becomes **[Agitated]** for the encounter.'),
('turnABlindEye', 'TURN A BLIND EYE', 'HOPE', 'HOPE', '[Aspect][Basic][Locked: Hope]', 'Hold people accountable? Why, you could never! Your friends are perfect beings, after all. There’s no reason to believe they’d ever willingly do wrong. When your allies are doing something you don’t necessarily agree with (like breaking a window to get in somewhere, stealing something, or talking shit about wizards), you can announce that you are turning a blind eye and make a show of how you totally aren’t seeing this happen. Oh, your shoelaces, they’re untied! You can voluntarily give a target up to **5 [Boost]** with a single action as you don’t actively aid them, but don’t stop them either; you take this amount back in **[Drag]**. This **[Drag]** cannot be reduced by other moves.'),
('turnOrderShuffle', 'TURN ORDER SHUFFLE', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][One-Off][Magic][Psionic][Locked: Metagamer] ', 'In the heat of battle, everyone acts at once. Except… not really! You can perceive that in reality, everyone gets to do precisely two things in turns, a pattern nobody else can notice. But with your tightening grasp of the real world, you can alter this process quite a lot. At the start of the encounter, you decide what order people go in, ignoring the initiative order set up by LET\'S STRIFE! Maybe you want all your allies to perform a complex strategy that only works if you all act at the right time— maybe you just want your enemy to go last. Up to you, pal! This can only be done once per encounter, even if there are multiple Metagamers present, and **[Magic]** effects (such as Zodiac magic) that alter turn order ignore this move.'),
('tutelation', 'TUTELATION', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Recharge: 2][Chicanery][Manipulate][Mental][Locked: Auxiliatrice]', 'As a teacher, it\'s your job to teach. And teach you do! Whether it\'s through pleasantly instructing how to perform good behaviour or sternly smacking some knuckles with a ruler to discourage bad behaviour, you take your instructerror job very seriously! When you want to teach someone a lesson, roll **+PLC**.\n\n**MIN**: SHUT UP! Nobody cares about your stinking lessons! The ingratitude of your pupils brings a tear to your eyes; you start **[Crying]**.\n\n**BAD**: You don\'t think they learned at all… that makes you **[Sad]**.\n\n**OK**: Your lesson goes unobserved. Curses.\n\n**GOOD**: There! That\'ll pass the test! Your target gains one of the following effects…\n\n> **Doting Encouragement**: Oh, aren\'t you such a dear! Yes, you are! You compliment the target, distracting them from what they were doing. Swap any one Emotion they have with **[Proud]**.\n> **Positive Reinforcement**: You reduce the **[Recharge]** of an ally\'s move by 1 as you explain the benefits of what they did.\n> **Scathing Punishment**: Bad student! Idiot! The target\'s **[Recharge]** for all moves actively **[Recharging]** is increased by 1.\n> **Guided Analysis**: So… what do YOU think the curtains mean? The target\'s next **[Analyze]** roll is **[Talented]**.\n> **Career Guidance**: I think you should get into STEM. The target\'s **[Buildup]** for all moves either increases or decreases by 1.\n> **DETENTION**: NOOOOOOO! Your target gains the **[Crying]**, **[Dread]**, and **[Out-Of-Control]** emotions for one turn. It isn\'t fair!!!\n\n**GREAT**: A+, baby! You get a **GOOD** and don\'t activate the move\'s **[Recharge]** this turn. Onto the next lesson!\n\n**MAX**: Goddamn, you pack a LOT into this lesson! You take 2 effects instead of 1, and don\'t activate your **[Recharge]**.'),
('twinbulginess', 'TWIN-BULGINESS', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Is… is that true? Probably not… right? It sounds fake as hell. But that being said, you ACT twice as ballsy as other trolls, so… who knows if you really do have…? You get the following SWASHBUCKLE effects.\r\n\r\n> **RUDE CAJOLING**: KEHEHEHEH! FUCKERSSSSS! You cackle with glee, waving the middle finger around and hyping up your own genius(?) at someone else\'s expense, giving half of your **[Drag]** to them. Sucks to suck!\r\n\r\n> **DO SOMETHING DANGEROUS**: Fuck it, what could go wrong? (You are immediately electrocuted). You **[Tier Up]** your next roll twice, even into a **MAX**, but take **3 [Somatic]** damage in the process, somehow. \r\n\r\n> **UNDESERVED BRAG**: AFTER ALL, I, ENPECE, AM THE COOLEST GOLD AROUND! You overhype yourself completely. You become **[Proud]**.\r\n\r\n> **CAUSE A RUCKUS**: You knock shit over and make a scene! Roll 1d8; on an 8, a random Hazard occurs(?!)'),
('tyrannicalTutor', 'TYRANNICAL TUTOR', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Passive][Ultra][Locked: Auxiliatrice]', 'Your teaching skill has passed merely teaching wrigglers the basics now. You\'re so adept in the education scene that your expertise is requested by any trolls who may take remedial schoolfeeding, be they Indigos and their studies of culture or Teals needing to test themselves in the exam hall. As such, politely explaining won\'t cut it anymore— you need to KNOW your stuff. As such, your **+PLC** and **+PSP** merge together into one stat: PULCHRIPACITY, or +PLP. You add together your stats for **+PLC** and **+PSP** to get your +PLP. The resulting number cannot be higher than +5; any excess to +5 is redistributed to other stats (for example, if you had +4 PLC and +3 PSP, you\'d have +5 PLP and a +2 to put into any other two stats). You gain access to HERO MODE through your PERFECT PULCHRITUDE and PRECISE PERSPICACITY. You can roll +PLP for any moves that would use **+PLC** or **+PSP**. Whenever you succeed at a +PLP roll, you can\'t help but feel a little smug; you gain **1 [Boost]** any time you get a **GOOD** or higher +PLP roll. You can allow allies to use your **[Boost]** on their turns as they take your guiding words to heart.'),
('tyrannize', 'TYRANNIZE', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Physical][Strife][Locked: Mafioso]', 'Some people think they can outsmart you. Maybe. Maybe. You have yet to meet someone who can outsmart a crowbar to the chin. Crime is a dirty business, and in order to keep your Clutch running, you need to get your hands filthy. When you want to make a motherfucker pay, roll **+APP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: THEY OUTSMART YOUR CROWBAR TO THE CHIN! You take **2 [Somatic]** damage as you accidentally leave yourself open to attack, and fall **[Floorbound]** in the process.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Ngh- agh! You weren’t careful enough, and accidentally hurt yourself in the attack. You take **1 [Somatic]** damage. \r\n\r\n**OK**: No direct hits, but enough to distress them. The target takes **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Gotcha, asshole! You do **1 [Somatic]** damage. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: CLANK! That’ll teach them a lesson they won’t soon forget! You do **2 [Somatic]** damage, or you do **1 [Somatic]** damage and make their next **[Physical]** roll **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Holy shit, did you break a bone or something? Damn, they… really will need to learn from this, huh? You do **3 [Somatic]** damage, or **2 [Somatic]** damage and make their next **[Physical]** roll **[Godawful]**.'),
('ultimateInstinct', 'ULTIMATE INSTINCT', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Ultra][One-Off][Locked: Nyanjutsu]\r\n', 'You used to just be some troll who LARPed as a martial artist, swinging your limbs wildly and shouting out attack names before you did them. While the moves may have been fake, your dedication and desire to improve was real. Now you know to not tuck your thumb in while throwing a punch. You’re basically a martial arts master. You even meditated once!  You’re cool, you’re dangerous, and everyone better watch out, Rawr >:3c. You gain access to HERO MODE through your GLORIOUS GRACE. Your reflexes are the best they’ve ever been; the **[Recharge]** for all your moves is reduced by 1. When you fall below **½ HP** you enter a HYPERINSTINCTUAL STATE. You become **[Hyperfocused]** as a **[Free]** action as your senses heighten. When you become **[Hyperfocused]** this way, thoughts become action as if by reflex, and all **+GRA** moves lose their **[Physical]** tag and instead gain the **[Mental]** one as your mind and body move as one. While in this state, you gain the following NINJA CAT abilities:\r\n\r\n> **POWER BLAST**: You conjure up your soul energy and blast it into a target! You immediately roll a **[Free]** NYASSASSINATE roll, except it becomes **[Magic]** and deals all **[Energy]** damages together in terms of triggering monster vulnerabilities. This gives you **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> **BREATH CONTROL**: Realign yourself with some breathing techniques… ohmmm… EXHALE. You reset your **[Drag]** to 0. In a GROUP STRIFE, you reduce it by a fraction (for example, in a group of 3, you reduce it by 1/3).\r\n\r\n> **KI REDISTRIBUTION**: JAB JAB JAB JAB! You add up everyone on the field\'s **[Boost]** and **[Drag]** before redistributing it to everyone equally.\r\n\r\n> **ABSOLUTE SPEED**: ZOOOOOOM! You move so fast, it\'s like teleportation! You are **[Quickened]** for **2 turns**, but can\'t roll **[Strife]** until the last action of these **2 turns**! This can stack with LET\'S STRIFE rolls to RUSH.\r\n\r\n> **TOTAL DISCIPLINE**: Your body and mind are seperate right now; if you can keep it up, you can ignore mental anguish to continue being at your strongest. You lose a **[Mental]** condition affecting you, and gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **DELAYED INJURY**: Your mind doesn\'t register that your shoulder was blown off! Pretty cool! You **[Heal]** up to **3 HP**, but you take all that damage, plus 1, in **2 turns**. You can use this as a **[Reaction]** as a **[Last Stand]**; in this case, the effect is a **[One-Off]**.'),
('ultramegasuperstar', 'ULTRAMEGASUPERSTAR', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Passive][Unlock: Celebrity]', 'YOU ARE THE STAR. THE STAR IS YOU. Alternia has a churning sea of infinite content, and you are its Poseidon. Whether through posting vlogs on Spewtube, acting and directing your own feature films with YOU as the lead, or otherwise showing surface dwellers a life they can only DREAM of having (they simply aren\'t as infinitely wealthy as you), you\'re kind of a big deal.  You are **[Talented]** at **+PLC**. You chase the one true measurement of fame and fortune: POPULARITY, or POPS. POPS represent how popular you are right now. As a **[Free]** **[Tech]** action, your current encounter is broadcast to the world on TV, Spewtube, or wherever you are most popular, and anyone can watch and see how it\'s going, and people can start gaining POPS. Every time you or an opponent get a **GOOD** or **OK** roll, you gain **±1 POPS**. If you get a **GREAT** or **BAD** roll, that\'s **±2 POPS**. If you get a **MAX** or **MIN** roll, you gain **±3 POPS**. If an enemy hits you with a move that gains POPS, you lose an equal amount, and if an ally does the same to you, you gain it! You gain the following effects depending on how high your RATINGS are…\r\n\r\n**-10 POPS**: You\'ve been CANCELLED! NOOOO! Everyone thinks your ass is lame! You are **[Inept]** at all rolls until you figure something out!\r\n\r\n**-5 POPS**: You\'re really not too popular right now, according to your palmhusk! You have a **-2 [Nerf]** to all rolls!\r\n\r\n**-2 POPS**: Not trending the way you waaaant, but hey, you can fix it. You have a **-1 [Nerf]** to all rolls.\r\n\r\n**0 POPS**: Who are you again?\r\n\r\n**+2 POPS**: People like you! Niiiice! You get a **+1 [Buff]** to all rolls.\r\n\r\n**+5 POPS**: Fame and fortune are on their way! People are like, making fancams of you! That\'s crazy! You have a **+2 [Buff]** to all rolls!\r\n\r\n**+10 POPS**: That\'s it, you\'re famous. You are **[Talented]** at all rolls, and if you end the encounter with **10 POPS** or more, you gain Treasure equal to the amount over 9 POPS you had (for example, **Treasure I** for **10 POPS**, **Treasure IV** for **13 POPS**, etc).'),
('uMad', 'U MAD?', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'You put the troll in trolling!! Your shit-eating grin is overwhelming; whenever a target is **[Enraged]**, you can become **[Smug]**. Are you mad? Huh? Huh?'),
('uncrackableConfidence', 'UNCRACKABLE CONFIDENCE', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Advanced][Passive]', 'You know what? Doesn\'t matter if deep down you\'re terrified. Fake it til you make it! If you act like you know EXACTLY what you\'re doing, people will think it, and you will too. So you know what? You know EXACTLY what you\'re doing! Your rolls against **[Hazards]** always use your **[Talent]** from your **[Entry]** move.'),
('undercoverActivity', 'UNDERCOVER ACTIVITY', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Recharge: 2][Flourish][Locked: Espiacrooner]', 'Playing dress-up is all well and good, but when you\'re looking for information, you need to be able to pull a few tricks from your sleeve. You may do this roll in private if others are not aware that you\'re an Espiacrooner out of character. When you want to be sneaky, roll **+RAS**.\n\n**MIN**: AGH— FUCK. YIKES. WOOF. You immediately reveal yourself for who you truly are, and all of your ABSCOND rolls **[Tier Down]**. Shit!\n\n**BAD**: Not good… your opponents receive a **[Free] GOOD Problem Sleuthing** roll against you as you become, well… suspicious. You don\'t automatically reveal yourself, but… better be careful.\n\n**OK**: Just a cough. You don\'t reveal yourself. \n\n**GOOD**: Okay… sneaky, sneaky… you take one of the following effects.\n\n> **SUBTLE MOVE**: Nobody will know! You can make your next roll a move from your own sheet without immediately blowing your cover, or activate a **[Passive]** move from your own sheet for one round. Using this reveals you as an Espiacrooner, though it doesn\'t necessarily reveal your true identity, in or out of character- just the fact that you\'re a spy!\n\n> **INNOCENT QUESTION**: Hum hum hum, nothing strange here! You gain the effects of the **QUESTION** Wordplay roll and the **SCOUT** Problem Sleuthing roll. This triggers all associated move **[Recharges]**.\n\n> **PICK UP ITEM, ADMIRE IT, AND SWAP IT OUT FOR A FAKE**: Exactly what it sounds like. Nobody around you noticed as you pocket the item, so long as it wasn\'t in someone\'s Sylladex. You must have enough **VP** in your inventory for it.\n\n> **FADE AWAY**: Huh? Where\'d they go?! You become **[Hidden]**, even in plain sight. If you are still **[Hidden]** on your next turn, you can **ABSCOND** without rolling or triggering **CAN\'T ABSCOND BRO**.\n\n**GREAT**: You\'re doing an EXCELLENT job of not being suspicious. Keep it up! You get a **GOOD**, and 1 **[Boost]**.\n\n> **MAX**: COMPLETELY UNDETECTABLE. You get two **GOOD** effects and one **[Boost]**, or one **GOOD** effect and two **[Boost]**.'),
('undermostdog', 'UNDERMOSTDOG', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][Passive]', 'Even the lowest of the lowbloods should have a better life than you… and yet you thrive anyway. No matter what, you\'re an unlikely winner in any battle, and people root for you… even if they don\'t want to. When you are in a TEAM STRIFE, you can automatically elect for your team to be the CHALLENGERS rather than the CHAMPIONS. When you become a CHALLENGER in this case, you can select two CHALLENGER options, not just one; one that activates when your team drops past 50% and one when they drop past 75%. You decide what order they activate in.'),
('underMySpell', 'UNDER MY SPELL', 'OTHER', 'WITCH', '[Class][Advanced][Reaction][Recharge: 5][Magic][Locked: Witch]', 'They won’t know that they fell… Now that they’re under your spell! You don’t need to rely on mere petty tricks anymore to bring the enemy down. The universe marches to YOUR beat and these bozos should’ve gotten with the program a whole five microsweeps ago! You can use a **[Reaction]** to force an opponent to roll their move with whatever stat you tell them to, as you bend the rules to whatever you see fit.'),
('unendingWill', 'UNENDING WILL', 'OTHER', 'THIEF', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Thief]', 'Despite being the coolest thief around, you\'re not the best at everything. That\'s right, you have a couple flaws of your own! While that\'s a hard pill to swallow, you\'ve managed to do it. Maybe you suck at some things, but you\'re going to do your best despite it. Whenever you get a **BAD** on a roll, you get a +1 **[Buff]** the next time you roll it. Whenever you get a **MIN**, you get a +2 **[Buff]**. If you keep failing, the buffs stack. Get a **BAD** and then a **MIN** on the same roll? Next time you roll, it\'s with a +3 **[Buff]**. You can do better than this if you try! \r\n'),
('unfocusedAmbition', 'UNFOCUSED AMBITION', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Open][One-Off][Mental]', 'Hmm? Oh, sorry! You were off daydreaming again. About what? Well… you aren\'t really sure. There\'s a part of you that feels like there\'s something bigger out there than just mediocrity… something **GREAT**, and AMAZING… but that\'s just a silly day dream. When you want to think about what could be, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Aw fuck! Your future looks AWFUL! Your life serves ZERO purpose! Roll on the **BAD** table twice! If you get the same emotion twice, it\'s **[Heightened]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Hmmm. Yeah, you don\'t think you\'re that good. Everyone\'s right about you sucking. You SUCK. Roll 1d8. \r\n\r\n> **1-2**: **[Dread]**\r\n> **3-4**: **[Stressed]**\r\n> **5-6**: **[Sad]**\r\n> **7-8**: **[Embarrassed]**\r\n\r\n**OK**: You muse and ponder… a lot. You are **[Stunned]**, either this turn or next, but you get a **GOOD**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Hmm… maybe someday… you could even… hmm! Roll 1d8!\r\n\r\n> **1-2**: **[Happy]**\r\n> **3-4**: **[Hopeful]**\r\n> **5-6**: **[Enthusiastic]**\r\n> **7-8**: **[Peaceful]**\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Wow, you feel really great after that introspection! Roll on the **GOOD** table twice. If you get the same emotion twice, it\'s **[Heightened]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: That\'s right! You\'re AWESOME! You know exactly what you want from life and yourself! And you\'ve GOT THIS! You roll on the **GOOD** table three times.'),
('unfortunateEvents', 'UNFORTUNATE EVENTS', 'DOOM', 'DOOM', '[Aspect][Basic][Recharge: 3][Unblockable][Locked: Doom]', 'Bad things happen to good people. And bad people. And people just hanging out on the sidelines. The point is bad things happen— and you know perfectly well that most of the time there’s nothing you can do about it except watch. Maybe pick up the pieces after. As an action, you can forgo rolling SHENANIGANS, instead just watching on as it happens. The odds of your opponent just slipping on a banana peel and tripping at this exact moment were so low, and yet… Anyway, this comes at a cost: you know your own luck is running out, too. It costs **3 [Drag]** for a **GOOD** SHENANIGANS roll, and **5 [Drag]** for a **GREAT** one.'),
('unhingedAttitude', 'UNHINGED ATTITUDE', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'HAHAHAHAH, yeaaaaah, you’re all kinds of fucked up, y’know? But hey, don’t worry, you wouldn’t hurt your friends. Unless they hurt you first. HAHAAHAH! You’re… definitely troubled. Now, whether you even try to hide it depends, but your caste has been conditioned into lashing out frequently, so even if you don’t, people are going to just assume that. And hey, that just perpetuates your bloodthirsty vibes even more, you know? Trolls who have moves that make them immune to certain emotions, or allow themselves to swap out one emotion for another, find their moves disabled against you, because… deep down, they’re kinda scared of you.\n\n'),
('unhingedGenius', 'UNHINGED GENIUS', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Scienceling]', 'You are a GOD! A GOD LIVING AMONG MORTALS! The laws of the universe BEND to your will, and you will NEVER know consequences to your actions! YAAAAAHAHAHAHA! You gain access to HERO MODE through your PRECISE PERSPICACITY. Additionally, you can use your EUREKAs for the following new effects.\r\n\r\n> **DEFINITELY INVINCIBLE**: Yup! You\'re pretty fucking unstoppable! Can\'t see anything get in YOUR way! You become **[Talented]** at **+HUB** instead of **+PSP** for a turn, and gain HARDCORE HUBRIS instead of PRECISE PERSPICACITY. This costs 1 EUREKA. This can\'t be stacked with JEKYLIFICATION.\r\n\r\n> **CREATE UNLIFE**: THEY SAID IT COULDN\'T BE DONE! BUT IT COULD! IT WAS EASY! Oh, they said \"shouldn\'t\"? Oooooh. Well. This is awkward. You bring a dead troll (or unconscious troll) back to life, giving them the SHADOWDROPPER Template. They are healed to full HP. This takes an action, and costs **2 EUREKAs**.\r\n\r\n> **JEKYLIFICATION**: You unleash the fiend inside of you, your base instincts turned into a monster. And that monster is going to bust a fucking move. You lose your **+PSP** **[Talent]** and lose your PRECISE PERSPICACITY. Instead, you become **[Talented]** in **+GRT**, gain **4 HP**, gain access to MYTHIC MANGRIT, and any moves that use **+PSP** from this tree (including OMNIDISCIPLINARY SCIENTIST) use **+GRT**. You don\'t have a new mind or anything; it\'s still you, just you without inhibition. You are **[Out-Of-Control]**, but MAD CACKLE is unaffected. This costs **3 EUREKAs**.'),
('unrealSteal', 'UNREAL STEAL', 'OTHER', 'THIEF', '[Class][Advanced][Reaction][Recharge: 3][Magic][Locked: Thief]', 'With a slight tingle to your claws… even the ethereal is yours for the taking. Whenever a move would give someone else a positive status effect from any roll like **[Boost]**, HP, or Positive **[Emotion]**s, you may spend a **[Reaction]** and roll **+RAS, +HUB**, or +IMG to try and take it for yourself.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: AUGHHH, you tried reaching for it and they saw you coming. They get a **[Free]** **[Strife]** roll against you to smack your hands away!!!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You accidentally gave them **2 [Boost]** by mistake. Fuck. Shit.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Nothing happens! \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You manage to steal whatever their status effect is for yourself! \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Not only do you manage to steal it, but you also gain **1 [Boost]** from the smug satisfaction.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You manage to steal their condition AND you can either steal one extra positive condition from them OR choose to double the one you stole already!\r\n\r\n'),
('untoTheBreach', 'UNTO THE BREACH', 'OTHER', 'PAGE', '[Class][Advanced][Recharge: 3][Manipulation][Mental][Locked: Page]', 'You’ve rushed into danger a shit load of times and had to be bailed out just as much too. It’s been a bit embarrassing but those experiences have made you better in a fight! Since you’re the one usually in trouble, you also know better than anyone else what trouble looks like. You’ve seen what monsters are the scariest and which bullies the meanest. With this you can direct your allies to which foe they should REALLY be pummeling. When you want to give a rousing anime protagonist speech, roll **+RAS**, **+PLC** or **+HUB**. \n\n**MIN**: Against all odds, you make it worse for yourself. In some tragic calamity, you cause a **[Hazard]**, and it affects everyone present. Good job, fella.\n\n**BAD**: You just cry and plead and shit your pants or something. Nobody is all that moved except to grimace at you. This just makes you feel bad. You take 2 **[Drag]**.\n\n**OK**: Uhm… blah blah blahh… your mumbling and crying kinda motivates your ally, I guess. You take **1 [Drag]**, and your ally takes **1 [Boost]**.\n\n**GOOD**: Okay, someone should seriously take that guy out. You take **1 [Drag]**, and your ally\'s next **[Strife]** or **[Chicanery]** roll they make against whatever is causing so much distress is **[Tiered Up]**.\n\n**GREAT**: We can’t just wait with lives at stake! This storm is growing deadly! You get a **GOOD**, but their **[Tiered Up]** move can be any move, so long as it either targets your opponent or you. You can choose to give them the **[Hopeful]** condition in exchange for really playing up your distress, making you feel **[Sad]**.\n\n**MAX**: We’ll be the ones to touch the sun… THE TRIUMPH SHALL BE OURS! You get a **GREAT**, but you can choose to make the target **[Inspired]** in exchange for making yourself start **[Crying]**.'),
('upgradesPeople', 'UPGRADES, PEOPLE!', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Inventor]', 'C\'mon, you can make something better than just a standard machine, you know! You\'re here to build something ADVANCED! When you create a robot through SUPERGENIUS, you may apply one of the following upgrades on a GOOD or higher.\r\n\r\n> **BROBOT**: This robot can RAP! It\'ll fight your verbal duels for you, blaring nonsensical lyrics at your opponent as you turn your back and huff. It has **+2 in +PLC** and is **[Talented] at WORDPLAY**. Though its primary function is to Jab, it can also use other WORDPLAY rolls when you ask it to.\r\n\r\n> **UPGRADED CHASIS**: The robot loses its **[Weakness]**.\r\n\r\n> **INTEGRATED WEAPONS**: You give the robot a Strifekind Abstrata. \r\n\r\n> **PLATED**: Your robot gains **+2 extra HP**. \r\n\r\n> **MEDIBOT**: Your robot will treat extra conditions, such as picking you up, brushing you off, or numbing emotions with anesthetics. It can deal **1 damage** to remove any one status effect or Emotion from you. \r\n\r\n> **PERSONALITY CORE**: This robot has a semblance of awareness, which makes it better at what it does! It gets a +1 to all stats, speak in up to ten word sentences, can roll **[Mental]** rolls, and is **[Talented]** at a stat of your choosing.\r\n\r\n> **SELF DESTRUCT BUTTON**: Killing the robot makes it explode, dealing **3 [Somatic]** damage to everyone who isn\'t **[Hidden]** or **[Flying]** the moment it is destroyed. GG.\r\n'),
('uprooterrogator', 'UPROOTERROGATOR', 'TEAL', 'ADULT', '[Teal][Locked: Adult]', 'You either love the Empire and hate seeing people using their blood-given privilege to HELP the lesser bloods (ugh), or you realize that getting rid of your rival would be much easier if you just… accused them. You have been given a special mission to weed out and cull heretics that hide behind their highblood and bring them to JUSTICE using the art of Uprooterrogation. If you have reason to believe a troll of blue or higher is committing treasonous activity and convince someone of sufficient authority via evidence or lies, you may launch an **UPROOTERROGATION** against them if you are currently in an encounter with the accused troll. Accused blues and indigos become **[Stressed]**, which makes you **[Smug]**, while purples and violets become **[Agitated]**, which makes you **[Supercilious]**. GOG you love conditional authority. While in an **UPROOTERROGATION**, your **WORDPLAY** rolls **[Tier Up]** and you may roll **WORDPLAY** to **JAB** and deal **[Verbal]** damage even if a physical fight has broken out. If you take any damage from the accused, you gain 1 **[WHAM]** which you can only use on **[Verbal]** damage and can only be dispelled with **[Verbal]** damage if they have a move which allows them to use **JAB** after a fight has broken out. You can dismiss an **UPROOTERROGATION** as a **[Free]** action at any time. '),
('urbanLegend', 'URBAN LEGEND', 'OTHER', 'GHOST', '[Template][Ultra][Chicanery][Eerie][Locked: Ghost]', 'Your supernatural power is unmatched. Despite all odds, you have clung to your spirit following death rather than drifting into anonymity like the rest of your spooky, spooky brethren. You aren\'t just a ghost; you\'re a rumour. A story Jades tell Wrigglers to make them behave. Choose a persona, like THE RIPPER OF REDRUN ALLEY or MISS BLOODFIEND. Whenever someone rolls to **[Analyze]** you, unless it has the **[Magic]** tag, they only learn about your persona, not you. Trolls are automatically **[Scared]** around you. You may use Abstrata while in ECTOPLASMIC FORM (GHOST WITH A SWORD YEAHHHH). Finally, your mastery over all things paranormal gives you the following SHENANIGANS rolls…\r\n\r\n> **BEATIFIC APPEARANCE**: You make yourself look like a dead person your opponent recognizes and misses. Haha! SENTIMENTALITY! The opponent becomes **[Charmed]** until you reveal your true nature.\r\n\r\n> **PHASE WITH ME**: You drag a target into another room, possibly separating them from their allies. Whooohhh!\r\n\r\n> **COLD SPOT**: Breath becomes visible, heat turns out… yeah, something is here. Any **[Stunned]** opponents are instead **[Slowed]** for **two turns**, and **[Ablaze]** trolls go out. Trolls who are **[Floorbound]** must make a **[Free]** SWASHBUCKLE roll to get up or they slip on ice and become **[Floorbound]** again! \r\n\r\n> **HIVEHAUNT**: Ohoho! Let\'s slam the mealheater\'s door a few times, maybe lock and unlock doors! If you are inside a Hive and use your CAN\'T KILL WHAT YOU CAN\'T SEE AND IS ALSO DEAD to hide inside the walls, it becomes yours to control. You do one of the following effects, and may continue to do so once per turn until an opponent finds you.\r\n\r\n> **YOU CAN RUN BUT YOU CAN\'T HIDE**: Find a **[Hidden]** troll and prevent them from **[Hiding]** for the encounter. There you are, hiding in my closet!\r\n\r\n> **MY MISTAKE YOU CAN\'T RUN EITHER**: Lock the doors. CAN\'T ABSCOND, BRO!\r\n\r\n> **SPOOKY SMACK**: Attack from any corner! You make a **[Strife]** roll and remain **[Hidden]**.\r\n\r\n> **BREAKTIME**: Help yourself to whatever’s around. You may make any **[Downtime]** rolls from HIVECRAFTING in the middle of an encounter. Mmmm, what\'s in the fridge?'),
('vagueWords', 'VAGUE WORDS', 'SPACE', 'SPACE', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Space]', 'You can sometimes be… a little hard to pin down. It’s not that you mean to be or anything— you just happen to be a little… mmm… it’s not that you can’t pinpoint a decision at times, you’re just… ahhh… could you be called mysterious? It might not be that simple… your inner dialogue often overcomes your outer dialogue. It’s very hard to actually figure out what your intentions are since most of your conversations take place inside your head. Plus… making decisions is hard! PROBLEM SLEUTHING rolls against you are **[Inept]**.'),
('valedictatorian', 'VALEDICTATORIAN', 'FUCHSIA', 'FUCHSIA', '[Fuchsia][Passive]', 'Welcome to the real world, sunshine! Guess what- it’s exactly like the movies! You’re the top dog, the baddest bitch on the block, and you know it. Your HP doubles, because you’re quite literally the toughest person on the planet. You are **[Talented]** at all stats. You can take **[Open]** moves from any caste because you have the time and ability to become more than capable of using them; the exception is that you can take any and all violet moves, because you INVENTED that shit. All your damage against life forms that aren’t other fuchsias is doubled. You know full well what you’re capable of, and you’re going to make sure everyone else knows it, too.');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('valetkyrie', 'VALETKYRIE', 'RUST', 'ADULT', '[Rust][Locked: Adult]\r\n', 'Highbloods can wax poetic about their perfectly loyal Underhosts all they like, but your dedication to the craft would make their head spin. You are no mere helper - you are a Valetkyrie, one of the most envied and cushy jobs among rusts. For your service, you will always be remembered as… a slightly better Servicesquire. When in an encounter with an allied troll higher than your caste, you may designate them as a Patron. You may roll any stat using a Patron\'s stat instead of yours (and vice versa) as you do their job for them. Additionally, you gain access to items from your Patron’s Wealth level without the need for a **[Big Buy]**. You may carry up to 5 **VP** worth of these items in your SYLLADEX at a time as you serve your Patron’s items out on silver platters. \r\n'),
('valueChaser', 'VALUE CHASER', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'C\'mon, c\'mon, don\'t break on you! It was hard enough to grab a medicalizer in the first place, man… whenever you use a **[Consumable]** item, roll 1d8. On a 7 or an 8— miracle of miracles! The item doesn\'t break! Hell yeah!'),
('vanHellsinger', 'VAN HELLSINGER', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Slayer]', 'All the devils in the world fear you, and for good reason; you are a planet-renowned slayer of the monstrous. Emissaries of the Undercavern\'s Cloisters have blessed you, the most powerful of Dark Magicians have damned you, and you have learned everything there is to know of your prey. You gain access to HERO MODE through your GLORIOUS GRACE. Additionally, you gain access to the appropriate template for the Monster you hunt, mimicking all of their abilities with the aid of magic runestones without actually becoming the monster. For example, a LYCANTHROPE Hunter would gain supernatural strength and bestial traits (fangs, claws) but would not become a furry weremonster, or a SPECTRE Hunter would be able to phase through objects without actually being dead. You gain the **[Entry]** when you take this move. You are not **[Cullbait]**, you never lose control (you stay in control of your actions and can end fights by fleeing during MOONFRENZY MODE as a Moonbark, you don\'t start the countdown timer in A MODE MOSTE GRIM as a Grimdark, etc), and you may suppress any effects as an action (ending your ghostly abilities as a Ghost, for example, to interact with the real world). This does not count as the one **[Eerie]** Template you may have, but it must still be physically possible to combine; so even a robotic Jade can take Grimdark as an example, but not a Ghost Shadowdropper!'),
('veganOption', 'VEGAN OPTION', 'OTHER', 'RAINBOW_DRINKER', '[Template][Advanced][Passive][Eerie][Locked: Rainbow Drinker]', 'You don’t need to drink blood. You’re a nice vampire, and all you do is drink p— wait, you what. You drink paint? That’s… I mean, okay?? I guess? You, uh, you’re a nice vampire, and, all you do, is drink, paint. You do not enter BLOODHYSTERIA mode unless you choose to; any time you would be **[Enraged]**, you can choose to instead gain **1 [WHAM]** as you stave off your violent instincts. Your diet has left you particularly hungry, and your sense of smell keenly seeks out the blood of the living that you abstain from; you can find **[Hidden]** opponents by spending an action, without rolling.'),
('vehiculate', 'VEHICULATE', 'OTHER', 'CERULEAN', '[Physical][Chicanery][Flourish][Beep Beep Meow]\r\n', 'Vroom vroom! Piloting any vehicle is a piece of cake, be it a simple scuttlebuggy or an aeronautical warship. You\'re pretty sure, at least. Probably. Oh well! Only one way to find out! Since speed usually isn\'t a concern with Subgrubs & Snazzards, here it\'s measured in the abstract of **VROOMS**, which represents the current distance between you and another vehicle. If either you or the opponent\'s current **VROOM**s ever surpass the other by 5, that vehicle is too far away to chase! While in a vehicle, VEHICULATE is normally the only **[Physical]** move you can make aside from SWASHBUCKLE. When you want to pilot a vehicle, roll **+HUB**.\n\n> **MIN**: AAAAAAAARGH! BRICK WALL! FUCK! OH, OH GOD NO, EVERYTHING\'S ON FIRE! YOU\'RE GOING OFF THE BRIDGE… AND RIGHT INTO AN ORPHANAGE! FULL OF CHOLERBEARS! ARGH! You did a bad job driving. All passengers and bystanders in the way take **10 damage** and the vehicle is destroyed.\n\n> **BAD**: Oop! You super didn\'t react fast enough! You take **2 [Drag]** as your slow reflexes haunt you.\n\n> **OK**: Dangit! Missed your turn. Oh well.\n \n> **GOOD**: Sweet! You pull off one of the following maneuvers. \n\n> **RAM**: BONK! You do **1 [Somatic] damage** to an opponent vehicle, or 2 to an opponent outside of a vehicle that you have STEERED towards. You must have the same **VROOM** as the target to use this effect if they have a vehicle. This option has the **[Strife]** tag.\n\n> **STEER**: You lock onto a target, lining up the perfect shot. You aim your vehicle at an opponent outside of a vehicle. So long as they don\'t become **[Hidden]** or start **[Flying]** before your next RAM roll, you should be able to hit them!\n\n> **DRIVE**: You move a number of **VROOMS**, up to your vehicle\'s HORSEPOWER. This counts as ABSCONDING if the opponent isn\'t in a vehicle, and forces your opponent to DRIVE after you if they are in a vehicle too and want to catch up to you. Remember: if you get at least 5 **VROOMS** higher than your opponent at any stage, you get the hell out of there! You can choose to reduce your VROOMS rather than increase them with this option. \n\n**STEP ON IT**: You drive recklessly. Uh oh! Your next VEHICULATE roll is **[Tiered Up]** to a **GREAT** if you roll a **GOOD** and **[Tiered Down]** to a **BAD** if **OK**.\n\n> **REALLY STEP ON IT**: Okay this is maybe seriously dangerous. Your next VEHICULATE roll is **[Tiered Up]** to a **MAX** if **GREAT**, and **[Tiered Down]** to a **MIN** if **GOOD** or lower.\n\n> **HIJACK**: You launch yourself into the driver\'s seat of a target with the same number of **VROOM**s as you. You\'re the pilot now, and can attempt regular rolls against the opponent pilot or try to VEHICULATE with their vehicle.\n\n> **BAIL**: Seeya! You leap out of your vehicle, letting it continue on. If nobody in the vehicle takes over driving by your next turn, the vehicle automatically gets a **MIN** VEHICULATE roll at the start of your next turn.\n\n> **GREAT**: Oh you are SUCH a great driver. You get a **GOOD**, but you either do an extra **1 Damage** to RAM, STEER for **[Free]**, DRIVE an extra **VROOM** or gain **2 [Boost]**.\n\n> **MAX**: YOU ARE THE HOTTEST SHIT ON ALTERNIA. SERIOUSLY, LOOK AT YOU. HOLY FUUUUUCK. YOU JUST DROVE THROUGH AN EXPLOSION, DUDE! You gain **3 [Boost]**, and get a **GOOD** but either do an extra **2 Damage** to RAM, STEER for **[Free]** and gain **1 [Resistance]**, DRIVE 2 extra **VROOM**s or gain an extra **3 [Boost]**. My god.'),
('venatics', 'VENATICS', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Basic][Physical][Strife][Locked: Nyanarchist]', 'Hunting lusii is what you do. Trolls and robots aren\'t really of much concern to you when there\'s hot single Megatoads or Grublord Supremes in your area. Thank fuck you know how to hold your own against even the most dangerous of monsters! When you want to hunt prey, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: AW JEEZ! YOU\'RE THE PREY! You gain **2 [Weakness]** to all attacks for a turn.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You let your guard down, and now the heat is on. You gain **1 [Weakness]** to all attacks for a turn.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Great hunting, dipshit. You missed.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Now we\'re on the attack! You do **1 [Somatic]** damage, or 2 against a lusus.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: SLASH SLASH CHEW CHEW! You hunt the fuck outta that guy! You do **2 [Somatic]** damage, or 3 against a lusus.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: HAHAHA! THIS IS WHY YOU\'RE TOP OF THE FOOD CHAIN! You do **3 [Somatic]** damage, or 4 against a lusus.'),
('verbalExecution', 'VERBAL EXECUTION', 'OTHER', 'PRINCE', '[Class][Basic][Buildup: 3][One-off][Locked: Prince]', 'Why just kill the people that piss you off when you can humiliate them in front of gog and the nutbeasts and everyone instead? When you want to throw someone off their game with your words or a well placed trip and embarrass them like they deserve, roll **+GRT, +HUB** or **+PSP**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Uh. Whoops. You miss, and throw a little loser bitch tantrum about it, **[Humiliate]**ing yourself for two turns in the process. You become **[Godawful]** at the move you were trying to make them awful at for the rest of the encounter. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: You trip over your own feet or insult yourself on accident instead, and are **[Godawful]** at **+HUB** rolls for 2 turns. \r\n\r\n**OK**: They just... shrug it off??? Excuse you???? Oh they\'ll pay for that. You get **+1 [Buff]** to your **+HUB** rolls on your next turn as you swear to make them pay for their good mental health. \r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Hah! With a well placed word or a well timed bit of shenanigans, you throw them off their game. They become **[Inept]** at a stat of your choice for 2 turns.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: AHAHHAHAHAHAH, LOSER! They become **[Godawful]** at a stat of your choice for 2 turns.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: THAT\'S RIGHT. YOU\'RE A LOSER. EVERYONE LOOK AT THIS LOSER BEING BAD! SEE! SEE! YOU\'RE SO MUCH BETTER THAN THEM! AHAHAHAHHAHAHAH! They’re **[Godawful]** at a stat of your choice for the rest of the encounter, and you become **[Smug]**.\r\n\r\n'),
('verified', '#VERIFIED', 'GOLD', 'GOLD', '[Gold][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Streamer]', 'You\'ve done it. You\'ve been #verified. You\'re front-page material on any platform you might use, and you have countless fans around the planet. Of course, this virtual fame isn\'t nearly as profitable as that one might find with highblood influencers, who may view your streams as trashy and forgettable, but that doesn\'t matter. All that matters is that you\'re doing what you wanna do, instead of what you\'re told to— a luxury rare among lowbloods. You have access to HERO MODE through your PERFECT PULCHRITUDE. Your fame has led you to push your limits much more often than others might; whenever you gain **[Boost]**, you gain 1 extra. This bonus **[Boost]** is NOT shared with others in AND WE\'RE LIVE, instead of being stored in a private pool— but you do gain it anytime someone else contributes to AND WE\'RE LIVE\'s shared **[Boost]** pool. Not everyone is quite as lucky as you, after all! You can use **[Boost]** in the following extra ways:\r\n\r\n> **HYPE**: Come on chat, let\'s GOOOO! You spend **3 [Boost]** and gain 1 extra action. You are **[Tired]** afterward. This can stack to make you **[Exhausted]** if you do it multiple times!\r\n\r\n> **HEARTFELT SPEECH**: You spend **3 [Boost]** telling your chat how much everything they do means to you. It\'s very sweet. You **[Heal] 2 HP**. This takes an action.\r\n\r\n> **SHOUTOUT**: You either HYPE or HEARTFELT SPEECH an ally for **1 [Boost]** more than normal. Gotta share the love!\r\n\r\n> **CASH OUT**: Kaching! Each **2 [Boost]** you spend turns to **1 LUX**. Wouldn\'t want your **[Boost]** going to waste at the end of an encounter, right?'),
('versusTheMachine', 'VERSUS THE MACHINE', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Labourer]', 'You don\'t trust a machine to do a troll\'s work. After all, you can do the labour of ten scuttletractors in a fraction of the time! That and drones are kind of an existential pain in the ass for lowbloods, and you\'ve gotten used to hammering metal into shape, and… you get what I\'m saying. Your rolls against mechanical foes can never be **[Inept]**, **[Tiered Down]**, or **[Nerfed]**, and you do **+1** damage to items and VEHICLES.'),
('versusTheMob', 'VERSUS THE MOB', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Basic][Passive][Locked: Mafioso]', 'Look… you don’t wanna get on this gang of clown’s bad side, hey? So why don’t you just… consider running away, and we’ll forget about all this? No? Ah, well, you made an offer. You and your companions are vicious little fuckers, and in a TEAM STRIFE, you’re just all the more terrifying. You gain access to the following TEAM STRIFE moves. If the majority of your team belongs to your Clutch, the opposing team is **[Scared]**. If the entire team belongs to the clutch, they are **[Terrified]**.\r\n\r\n> **BRIBE**: You, as a STANDBY troll, slink up to an enemy STANDBY target and offer them some money to not say anything about what they saw here, to run away, or to join your side. This REQUEST roll uses your **+APP**, and you can offer them Treasure from your own collection as an incentive. They don’t get the Treasure unless they agree. Unlike other TEAM STRIFE moves, you can use this outside of a TEAM STRIFE if you need.\r\n\r\n> **GANG UP**: You know that one scene in Trotro’s Strange Adventures when the three Mafioso Clowns start kicking the shit out of a guy on the floor? Yeah. As a **[One-Off]**, all STANDBY trolls can gang up on a **[Floorbound]** enemy STRUGGLER, and make a single **[Lengthy]** **[Strife]** roll against them. They all then become **[Exhausted]**, and your team’s STRUGGLER’s **[Strife]** rolls are **[Inept]** for **3 turns**. \r\n\r\n> **REWARD MONEY**: You gain double the usual reward **LUX** from a TEAM STRIFE.\r\n\r\n> **VANDALIZE**: You can roll BASH-N-RUN **[Downtime]** rolls while in a TEAM STRIFE, so long as you are present in the Hive.'),
('veryMuchAlive', 'VERY MUCH ALIVE', 'OTHER', 'VOIDROT', '[Template][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Voidrot]', 'And you intend to stay that way. You have managed to finally learn to cope with your voidrot. You may have no eyes, but you\'ve adapted. You either found a support network of psionic friends willing to let you bum lifeforce off them while you got back on your feet or you took it for yourself from some other poor saps. You\'ve started taking showers, breaking from the cultural legacy of your caste. You may have voidrot, but it hasn\'t killed you! You can now take and store energy relatively long term instead of consuming it immediately to survive, granting you much more flexibility in your everyday life. The HP loss from DYING BATTERY is now every **2 turns**, and when you spend your **[Reserve]** on ANIME POWERSPIKE, **1 [Reserve]** goes to making your next **[Physical]** move **[Talented]**, too- you’ve gotten good at putting the energy you’ve stored up to use! So good, in fact, that you can now push all the energy you\'ve stored into one massive attack. You may, as the goldologist experts call it, \"Spirit Bomb\" your opponents, a **[Lengthy]** **[Psionic]** **[Strife]** that deals **1 [Somatic/Psychic]** Damage for every **2 [Reserve]** you possess against all opponents on the field. This is a **[One-Off]** which renders you **[Tired]** as well as burning up all your **[Reserve]**. Your Battery Buddy allies may spend a **[Reaction]** to give you their energy, although doing so does take an action.\r\n\r\n'),
('vestalVampyr', 'VESTAL VAMPYR', 'OTHER', 'RAINBOW_DRINKER', '[Template][Eerie][Unlock: Rainbow Drinker]', 'You have died once in the past, and it unlocked your darkest (brightest?) secret: you are a vampire. Your skin glows painfully bright, and you have a pair of long, sharp fangs. When you get a **GREAT** **[Strife]** roll using your fangs, you may plunge your teeth into your opponent and, in exchange for doing **1 less damage**, heal **1 HP**. Additionally, your skin always glows a bright white. Legends say this was a way of dazzling foes who would prey on grubs, or maybe it was just to daze them in order to get that sweet sweet rainbow juice inside them. As a **[One-Off]** action, you may let out a burst of light and blind everyone else in the encounter, giving them the **[Blinded]** effect for **2 rounds**. Your condition is not without downsides; any time you see blood in a fight, whether it’s from a friend or a foe, you fly into a shrieking hysteria as you try to drink it up. You enter BLOODHYSTERIA mode, which counts as a combination of **[Out-Of-Control]** and **[Quickened]** and only ends when you’ve had your fill, having healed at least **6 HP**. (The blood of shadowdroppers and other rainbowdrinkers does not activate BLOODHYSTERIA- only the blood of the living can satiate the dead.) All trolls who see you enter BLOODHYSTERIA know what you are, and freak the fuck out as you glow and hiss like a fucking lunatic. You are immune to the DAYTIME **[Hazard]**. This move does not replace your jade tree **[Unlock]** move. Revealing yourself to a Cloistered Jade can, rather than making them **[Scared]**, render them **[Hopeful]** or **[Charmed]** depending on their view of you.'),
('veteranVip', 'VETERAN VIP', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Advanced][Locked: Celebrity]', 'Look, let\'s be real. These other guys? They aren\'t used to the spotlight! But you? Yeah, you know how to handle the good, the bad, the whatever. You get the following options you alone may choose from when you hit certain POP Thresholds.\r\n\r\n**-10 POPS**: Heighten the **[Emotion]** from the -5 Threshold.\r\n\r\n**-5 POPS**: Choose between **[Stressed]**, **[Sad]**, **[Dread]** or **[Embarrassed]**.\r\n\r\n**-2 POPS**: Gain **2 [Drag]** now, and again every **2 turns** you remain at -2 POPS.\r\n\r\n**+2 POPS**: Gain **2 [Boost]** now, and again every **2 turns** you remain at +2 POPS.\r\n\r\n**+5 POPS**: Choose between **[Hopeful]**, **[Smug]**, **[Confident]** or **[Proud]**, and gain 1 **[Boost]** every 2 turns you remain at +5 POPS. This **[Boost]** can\'t be increased through other means.\r\n\r\n**+10 POPS**: Heighten the **[Emotion]** you gained from the +5 Threshold, and gain **1 [Boost]** every **2 turns** you remain at +5 POPS. If you end the encounter with 10 POPS or more, you gain Treasure equal to the amount over 9 POPS you had.'),
('viciousVindication', 'VICIOUS VINDICATION', 'RAGE', 'RAGE', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Rage]', 'BLAMMO! You love nothing more than a sweet, sweet punch to the gut. After all, you crave destruction, whether you realize it or not. Any time you gain **[WHAM]**, you gain an extra **1 [WHAM]** (once per round). This move can be used in conjunction with the SWASHBUCKLING effect Finishing Move for a total of **4 [WHAM]**, but only in this case.'),
('videonastyquin', 'VIDEONASTYQUIN', 'PURPLE', 'PURPLE', '[Purple][Free][Unlock: Subjugglator]', 'HONK. honk. HONK. honk. HONK. honk. Violence on the streets, terror in the bloodpushers of the weak, a brutal and bloody reminder to all that fear rules all, and you are the MOTHERFUCKING SCARIEST OF ALL, BITCHES. You are a Subjugglator, a terrifying slasher clown tasked with scaring the populace into submission. And how do you SCARE people so bad they’ll never forget it? You break. Their motherfucking. KNEES. You are **[Talented]** at **+GRT**. Whenever you roll a **GREAT** or above **[Physical]** **[Strife]** move, you can choose one of the following effects, do **1 less damage**, and ignore the regular **GREAT** effects of the move. \r\n\r\n> **BRUTALIZED**: Ain’tcha gonna run away, brother? Aww, out of breath? I knocked the wind outta you real hard, huh? Your target’s LET’S STRIFE rolls are **[Inept]** for **3 turns** as they gasp in pain at your brutal assault. Targets can’t be **[Quickened]** during this. On a **MAX**, the target is instead **[Slowed]** for the duration.\r\n\r\n> **BEATEN**: Come on. Let’s see some COLOR. You wanna show some COLOR, don’t you? Rainbow, rainbow, rainbow… the target becomes **[Bloodied]**.\r\n\r\n> **KNOCKED AROUND**: Hey, hey, hey, anything in there? Bonk bonk bonk! You smack at their head a little, fucking up their focus. The target is **[Confused]** for **1 turn**. If you give them this effect three times in a single encounter, the target becomes **[Dumbfounded]** for the encounter as they suffer a concussion of some sort. On a **MAX**, skip right to **[Dumbfounded]**.\r\n\r\n> **SHITBROKEN**: SMASH YOUR SALVATION! You do **3 damage to an item**, or 4 on a **MAX**.'),
('violentBreakthrough', 'VIOLENT BREAKTHROUGH', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Scienceling]', 'BEHOLD: YOUR LATEST CREATION! A FUCKING GUN! You have applied your scientific knowledge to weaponry, and have made instruments that would be illegal on most civilised planets. You select one of these Abstrata Upgrades now; you may take more in the future, even choosing to sell them if you choose, but it costs you **1 LUX** to make!\r\n\r\n> **CHEMISTRY**: Wow! Enzymes that eat metal! Your sword is dripping in the stuff! You gain access to the CHEMICALKIND ABSTRATA UPGRADE, which does **+2 damage** to Items and Vehicles.\r\n\r\n> **BIOLOGY**: Ah, a gun that\'s got various infections in the laser. Very cool! You gain the BIOWEAPONKIND ABSTRATA UPGRADE. On a **GREAT** **[Strife]** roll, you may do **1 less damage** to make the opponent become **[Bloodied]**. On a **MAX**, this item exposes the target to THE HEMOCOUGH Affliction.\r\n\r\n> **PHYSICS**: Weaponizing the F=MA formula! Nice!! You gain access to the GRAVKIND ABSTRATA UPGRADE, which sets your opponent **[Flying]** on a **GREAT** for **1 turn**. Careful, though-! They take **1 [Somatic]** damage when they land.\r\n\r\n> **ATOMICS**: Tired of opponents resisting your attacks? Some low grade plutonium will put a stop to that! You gain access to the RADIATIONKIND ABSTRATA UPGRADE, which does **[Unblockable]** **[Glitchy]** damage. On a **MAX**, this item exposes the target to the RADIATION POISONING Affliction.'),
('violentFlailing', 'VIOLENT FLAILING', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Free][Physical]', 'AAAAAH! YOU DON\'T WANNA BE GRABBED! LET GO! AEEEIII! You HATE being manhandled, and will trash and flail in a panic whenever someone tries to do so. You aren\'t gonna get got! No way! Whenever someone tries to GRAB you with SHENANIGANS, APPREHEND you during a GROUP STRIFE, or otherwise physically grabs or **[Traps]** you, you can roll **+GRT** to thrash.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Your survival instincts fail you. You go limp, and are functionally **[Unconscious]**. You give up. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: You just **[Tire]** yourself out! No joy.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You cuss and shriek and flail and cry and bite and wiggle! Nothing happens.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: GWAAAAH! Whatever it is that\'s got you takes **1 [Drag]** if it\'s an enemy, and 1 damage if it\'s an object. You can choose to end the **[Trapped]** condition if you are affected by it, but you won\'t be able to use this move again if you\'re not still **[Trapped]**.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: LEMME OOOOOUT! You get a **GOOD**, but you do **1 additional [Somatic]** damage with each option!\r\n\r\n**MAX**: H— dude, holy fuck, what? You\'re like a little storm! You get a **GREAT**, but all numbers are doubled?!'),
('visionTwofold', 'VISION TWOFOLD', 'DOOM', 'DOOM', '[Aspect][Advanced][Recharge: 3][Locked: Doom]\r\n', 'The one nice thing about seeing the worst possible outcomes everywhere is knowing exactly what the best possible outcome is too. You’ve been training yourself to look on the bright side every once in a while instead of letting your preoccupation with the worst overwhelm you. You can declare you’re going to peer into the future and see how your actions and their consequences might shake out. Roll any one move, and see what the short-term consequences are. You can continue on this path, gaining **1 [Boost]**; or you can rewind, and state that roll was merely a vision your troll had, and roll a completely different move, branching the paths and trying something else. Doing this gives you **1 [Drag]**, since it hurts to think about bad situations like that.\r\n'),
('viveLaRevolution', 'VIVE LA REVOLUTION!', 'RAGE', 'RAGE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Rage]', 'To you, hope and anger are identical; both are a form of commitment to a goal you stick to no matter what. When you would become either **[Hopeful]** or **[Enraged]**, you may choose to gain the other **[Emotion]** instead; the same applies to **[Inspired]** and **[Out of Control]**.\r\n'),
('voidIncarnate', 'VOID INCARNATE', 'OTHER', 'GRIMDARK', '[Template][Basic][Passive][Eerie][Locked: Grimdark]', 'Your flesh is no longer quite... flesh. Gray and sinuous, it knits itself back together like something living and not altogether yourself, despite its unsettling fragility. While in A MODE MOSTE GRIM, you regenerate **+2 HP** at the beginning of each of your turns as it writhes and squirms back into a facsimile of your body, but these tendrils part like a river around your enemies weapons. Normal **[Healing]** effects no longer work on you, meant for more terrestrial flesh. You have **1 [Weakness]** to all damage. Your regeneration is not a **[Heal]** effect, and is not affected or nerfed if you are **[Bloodied]**. In return, all of your rolls are at a **-1 [Nerf]** when you are **[Bloodied]**, as your body is quite literally being torn apart.\r\n\r\nIf you have taken all moves from this template, your healing becomes ever stranger as you give yourself further to the void. Roll 1d3 at the beginning of any turn you are not at full HP. \r\n\r\n> **1**: Your flesh knits together... wrong. There is an eye where an eye should not be. Opponents can no longer be **[Hidden]** from you. \r\n\r\n> **2**: Where there was once flesh and wound, there is now a hole into the darkness beyond reality. You begin to **[Gush]** ichor and the absence of stars into the air around you. Opponents take **1 [Drag]** per turn for each instance of this effect.  \r\n\r\n> **3**: The void’s teeth close over your wound, and open to devour more. Opponents that roll **[Physical]** moves against you and fail take **1 damage** as something bites back in your defense.'),
('walkingWall', 'WALKING WALL', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Buildup: 3][One-Off][Locked: Paladin]', 'The best offense is a wildly good defense. You deploy a huge, spacemetal infused shield that essentially acts like a forcefield wall coming from your forearm. While the shield is active, opponents **[Strife]** moves against you are **[Inept]**, but you are **[Slowed]**, because it\'s a heavy fucking shield, okay? Hard light doesn\'t weigh nothing. Fuck. Your Shield lasts until you drop the shield (after which point it can\'t be reactivated in this encounter), or until someone does 4 damage to the shield specifically. **[Verbal]** damage doesn’t count towards the shield’s damage counter- no, you can’t yell at something until it breaks, no matter how loud you are.'),
('walkTalkWalk', 'WALK TALK WALK', 'KID', 'KOB', '[Template][Basic][Locked: Kids on Bikes]', 'Ah, the walkie talkie. The single most useful communication device in history. With this, you can talk to friends... From a DISTANCE! Also, it can\'t be tracked by alien government agents, which is helpful. As an action, you can contact additional Kids on Bikes agents to appear in a thread, even if there are none around as a single action. No need to go through loops sending a text— just clicking a button and saying \"REQUESTING SUPPORT OVER\" should be enough to get another kid with a bicycle down from the moon in no time.\n\n'),
('warpstorm', 'WARPSTORM', 'OTHER', 'CTHONOMANCER', '[Template][Advanced][Recharge: 1][Magic][Strife][Locked: Cthonomancer]', 'Sometimes an interloper walks in on a sacrifice, sometimes your kismesis won’t stop teasing you about being edgier than a flavordisc cutter. Both are equally valid reasons to tear a hole in reality and expose the peons of this lowly plane of existence to the direct gaze of The Dark Shapes In The Corners Of Our Eyes With Increasingly Longer Names. When you want to tear the fifth wall down, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You tore down the third wall, not the fifth wall! Oh, what the Hell is that? Whatever you just saw is freaky even by your standards! You become **[Overwhelmed]** and take **2 [Freaky] [Psychic]** Damage.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: The veil is more resilient than expected, but the vibes are ruined regardless. Everyone takes **1 [Drag]**, you take **1 [Freaky] [Psychic]** Damage as well. Your next **[Negative]** Emotion will be **[Heightened]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Just for a moment, it was there. Gli’vir the All Consuming’s legendary eye. You’re not sure if it was looking though. Everyone takes **1 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Aeh’lil the Last Planeskaped Wrath, tear down this wall! The veil parts long enough for you to direct the gaze of Those Beyond. Everyone takes **1 [Drag]**, and your target takes **2 [Drag]** and **1 [Freaky] [Psychic]** Damage.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Look! Look! It’s trying to reach into our plane of existence! Or.. it just rolled over. But it definitely got a good look at them! Everyone takes **1 [Drag]**, and your target takes either **2 [Drag]** and **2 [Freaky] [Psychic]** Damage, or **1 [Freaky] [Psychic]** Damage and the next **[Negative]** Emotion they receive is **[Heightened]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: For just a moment, something greater paid attention. For just a moment, this world was perceived by something that Shouldn’t. Everyone takes **2 [Drag]**, and your target receives **2 [Drag]** and **2 [Freaky] [Psychic]** Damage, as well as a **[Negative]** emotion of your choice.\r\n\r\n'),
('warriorClan', 'WARRIOR CLAN', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Passive]', 'You and your friends need to stick together, no matter what, no matter how! Whether you\'re a gang of street toughs, an online friend clique, a business association or a commune of hunter-gatherers, you and your friends work together no matter what. When you take this move, select at least 3 other trolls who pledge to take the move with you; they must take it with you. They don\'t need to be **[Advanced]** to take the move yet, so long as you are. Appoint a CLAN LEADER, who gets an extra benefit from the move. If you\'re the only troll with the ability to take **[Advanced]** or **[Olive]** moves, it\'s gotta be you. If the CLAN LEADER is doing a shit job as a leader, another CLANMATE can challenge your position on a 1v1 strife, the loser loses the move, and is ejected from the clan. Your clan can add more members, if all current members agree. CLANMATES gain the following effect depending on their tree, and CLAN LEADERS gain the leader effect as well!\r\n\r\n> **CLAN LEADER**: You\'re the boss! YOU\'RE in charge! On your turn, you can use an action to make an ally use a move. \r\n\r\n> **NYINJITSU**: Your friends count on you to do the fighting! If you are the STRUGGLER in a TEAM STRIFE with at least two other allies, moves to swap you out of the STRUGGLER role are **[Inept]**.\r\n\r\n> **MEOWCHANT**: You\'ve got all the goods to support your CLANMATES! Items you sell them cost **2 VP** less than normal (min. 1) rather than 1.\r\n\r\n> **NYASTROLOGIST**: Yup! Stars say whatever! You can choose whether CLANMATES are COMPATIBLE or INCOMPATIBLE even if they aren\'t; if they already were, you can make them ULTRACOMPATIBLE or ULTRAINCOMPATIBLE.\r\n\r\n> **NYANARCHIST**: Your allies WILL survive in the wild! When in an encounter with at least 2 CLANMATES, all of your groups **[Magic]** rolls become **[Talented]**.\r\n\r\n> **FANYATIC**: Wow! Your friends all get access to some primo internet content! They can take the SIDES OF GRUMBLR move.\r\n\r\n> **AN OUTSIDER**: You\'re not a kitty! Eh… we\'ll keep you, anyway. You can take an Olive tree as a Template, only taking the **[Entry]** (which you gain now), 1 **[Basic]** move and 1 **[Advanced]**, but no extra **[Talents]**. There can never be more Outsiders than Olives in your clan.'),
('wateryWarlord', 'WATERY WARLORD', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Ultra][Passive][Locked: Admiral]', 'MWAHAHAHA! YOU ARE INVINCIBLE! A Tidal Tyrant! A Beach Barbarian! You RULE the seas, and if anyone EVER tries to fuck with you, you\'ll RULE THEIR SHIT! You now run one of the strongest militaries on the planet, and god help anyone who tries to fuck with you. You gain access to HERO MODE through your GLORIOUS GRACE. Your knowledge of combat knows no bounds! You can take the **GREAT** **[Strife]** effects of any **[Physical]** **[Strife]** move (even locked ones!) when you level up, and slot them into your choice of effects from NAUTICAL NIGHTMARE. You gain 3 when you take this move. Additionally, you can add up to 5 ABSTRATA UPGRADES to your weapons, not 3. You gain 1 now. Enjoy being the scariest motherfucker in the sea!'),
('weirdBuilds', 'WEIRD BUILDS', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Inventor]', 'Sometimes, you build a robot that’s just… really, really weird! Some kind of animal robot dog, maybe? When you get a **GOOD** SUPERGENIUS roll, you may create a robot with the statblock of a Level 1 Lusus, on a **GREAT** a Level 2 Lusus, and on a **MAX** a Level 3 Lusus! These lusii are robotic, and have a **[Weakness]** to **[Electric]** damage. This otherwise follows SUPERGENIUS’ rules.'),
('weirdFlex', 'WEIRD FLEX', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Open][Recharge: 3][Physical]', 'Literally. It’s… a weird time to flex. You know that ultimately, physical fitness is one thing you KNOW you’ve got going for you, no matter what. At least, that’s what’s been drilled into you for sweeps. So a lot of your confidence lies there. And when you make a fool of yourself, you sometimes just… flex? And hope that makes you feel better. When you want to bulge your muscles to avoid feeling shitty, roll **+GRT**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: CRAAAAAMP! AAARGH! You become **[Agitated]** on top of everything else!\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Why is this happening to you? Your flexing isn’t working! You become **[Stressed]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Hnnrrrgh… you flex for a long, long time. You get a **GOOD**, but you’re also **[Stunned]** as you just keep going.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Hnnrgh… okay. All good. You remove an **[Emotion]** that you didn’t want. You got this.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Whoa! You’re really putting your all into it, huh? You remove an **[Emotion]** that you didn’t want, and gain **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: HOLY COW! That’s a HELL of a flex! Are those veins?! You remove all **[Emotions]** that you didn’t want, and gain **4 [Boost]**!'),
('wellknownReputation', 'WELL-KNOWN REPUTATION', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'People know you! Thanks to your work in your respective field, it\'s kinda hard not to. Whether you\'re that storyteller that comes round sometimes, the troll who can reap an entire field in a day, or that motherfucker with the guns, you enjoy a reputation of some sort. Pick whether it\'s good or bad!\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You\'re a helpful sorta person! All allies are **[Hopeful]** for **2 turns** at the start of a combat encounter with you.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: NOT THIS BITCH! All enemies feel **[Stressed]** for **2 turns** at the start of a combat encounter with you.\r\n\r\n**MYSTERIOUS**: Oh jeez… you\'re one of those morally grey wanderer types, aren\'t you… all other trolls are **[Numb]** for the first **2 turns** of combat with you as they try to suss you out.'),
('wellLaidPlans', 'WELL-LAID PLANS', 'OTHER', 'SYLPH', '[Class][Advanced][Locked: Sylph]', 'Proper planning prevents piss-poor performance. You’ve told your friends all you know about what you’re getting into. If they take your advice, it’s up to them, but you KNOW it’ll save their hides. At the start of the encounter, you and your allies each start with one **[Hold]**. You can declare you are spending this **[Hold]** for **[Free]** before rolling a move allows you to make sure that the result cannot be below a **GOOD**. If the roll result would be below a **GOOD**, it’s automatically boosted up to a **GOOD** and you both receive 2 **[Boost]**! See? You told ‘em!\r\n'),
('whatever', 'WHATEVER…', 'VOID', 'VOID', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Void]', 'You hope this doesn’t come off as rude or anything, but… you have a really hard time caring, sometimes. Why should you, when it feels like nobody else really cares about you? **[Manipulate]** rolls against you are **[Inept]**.'),
('whateverItTakes', 'WHATEVER IT TAKES', 'LIGHT', 'LIGHT', '[Aspect][Basic][Locked: Light]', 'When you want something, you get it. It doesn’t matter what the cost is, even if it’s yourself! You can boost yourself up big-time on a single roll, giving yourself as much **[Boost]** as you like at once. However, this comes at a big cost to yourself— you take **1 [Non-Lethal]** damage for every **2 [Boost]** you artificially gave yourself rounded down. You cannot give yourself less than **2 [Boost]** per use of this move.'),
('whatsLeftBehind', 'WHAT\'S LEFT BEHIND', 'OTHER', 'SEER', '[Class][Advanced][Magic][One-Off][Locked: Seer]', 'The world is full of things nobody really questions. Sylladices, for example. The ability to store and fetch items in what amounts to personal hammerspace is a fact of life - and so are many other phenomena. As you progress in your quest for knowledge, you’ve become aware of strange powers - powers you can, with enough focus, nudge. As an action, you can choose to do one of these things: \r\n\r\n> Reset one of your other **[One-Off]** moves, allowing you to use it twice.\r\n> Reset two of your current **[Recharge]** moves/effects to be able to use them again.\r\n> Reset two of your enemy\'s **[Recharge]** moves/effects to full, starting their cooldown over.\r\n\r\n'),
('whatsYoursIsMine', 'WHAT’S YOURS IS MINE', 'OTHER', 'THIEF', '[Class][Basic][Locked: Thief]', 'You\'re not here to make friends, you\'re here to be effective. Just because you\'re fighting with allies doesn’t mean anything! Sh-shut up! What it does mean is that, as an action, you can **YOINK** your ally\'s positive status effects (Emotions, **[Boost]**, etc.), taking it from them and giving it to yourself! It\'s not like you want to steal their hearts, too… b-baka...'),
('whatVoidbound', 'WHAT VOIDBOUND', 'VOID', 'VOID', '[Aspect][Advanced][Free][Recharge: 2][Locked: Void]', 'The notion that there was ever a Voidbound troll here is frankly ridiculous. You understand that you don’t need to hide all the time, but at the same time, it has its benefits! You shouldn’t avoid hiding when you need to— it’s part of your nature all the same. Any move that would make you **[Hidden]** is a **[Free]** action. Poof!\r\n'),
('whatWentWrong', 'WHAT WENT WRONG', 'MIND', 'MIND', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Mind]', 'Alright, that didn’t work. Let’s identify your mistakes and avoid them in the future! You’re particularly good at correcting yourself based on findings from past errors; any time you get an **OK** or lower result on a roll, your next roll for that move is **[Tiered Up]**.'),
('whimsOfFate', 'WHIMS OF FATE', 'OTHER', 'HEIR', '[Class][Basic][Passive][Locked: Heir]', 'Oh, that was lucky! Your aspect\'s always there for you, whether you realize it or not - cushioning your falls and pushing you on towards your successes. At the end of each turn, you get a Fate Point, or **FP**, a kind of **[Hold]**! Based on the number of **FP** you have, you gain one of the following effects:\r\n\r\n> **0 FP**: All out of plot armor, for now at least!\r\n> **1 FP**: Whoops, that was a close one! If you roll a MIN, lose 1 **FP** and it **[Tiers Up]** to **BAD**.\r\n> **2 FP**: Just a little push, helping you on your way. If you roll an OK, lose 2 **FP** and it **[Tiers Up]** to **GOOD**.\r\n> **3+ FP**: Wow, didn\'t know you had it in you! If you roll a 17+, lose 3 **FP** and it **[Tiers Up]** to **MAX**.'),
('whiskersWarning', 'WHISKER’S WARNING', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Advanced][Passive]', 'Hmmm? What was THAT? You’ve got an uncanny knack to know when a fight is about to begin, like a shiver that runs down your spine. This sixth sense lets you know when danger is afoot, and you become **[Legendary]** at LET’S STRIFE rolls to ORDER UP, as well as the first roll you make during a **[Hazard]**.'),
('whoaNelly', 'WHOA NELLY', 'HOPE', 'HOPE', '[Aspect][Advanced][Locked: Hope]', 'You never let anger get the better of you. It is better to create and repair than it is to destroy, and you never let your own personal convictions get the better of that. Whenever you would become **[Enraged]**, you can choose to instead become **[Hopeful]**. Similarly, if you would become **[Out of Control]**, you can become **[Inspired]**.'),
('whodunnitry', 'WHODUNNITRY', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Advanced][One-Off][Manipulate][Locked: Splattorney]', 'You\'ve gotten to a point in your career where you realize; the crowd loves a plot twist! So… turn an encounter on its head and BLINDLY ACCUSE SOMEONE OF A CRIME! When you want to derail the plot, roll **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Shut the fuck up. Stupid. Idiot. You become **[Humiliated]** as everyone around you looks decidedly fed up with you. \r\n\r\n**BAD**: Mmm… kinda cringe of you to try that. You become **[Embarrassed]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Everyone looks a little surprised, but your attempt is quickly overruled. One person present takes **1 [Drag]** as it kinda surprises them.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: It was… YOU! You point a finger, accusing someone of a terrible crime. You make the target **[Stressed]**. If you do this during SHOWTRIAL DRAMA, the move has **[Buildup: 4]** and the target becomes the new DEFENDANT, getting yours off scott-free. Well, so long as the JURY and JUDGE buy your explanation as to why, and votes in your favour. Otherwise, your roll becomes a **BAD**. If the defending LAWYER switches out their DEFENDANT, they must prove this new DEFENDANT guilty, and the previously attacking LAWYER must now defend them. Both sides add up their HP, and split it equally between them.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Wow, that was a pretty good accusation. Are they… actually hiding something..? You get a **GOOD**, but the target is **[Agitated]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Okay, wow, this dude\'s guilty as fuck. The target is **[Agitated]** and **[Overwhelmed]**, and the JURY and JUDGE don\'t get to vote, because uh, holy shit.'),
('wildCat', 'WILD CAT', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Passive][Unlock: Nyanarchist]', 'Go back! I want to be kitte cat! Life in the city was too much for you, so you did the only sane thing and moved to the wilderness to live among the lusii. Now, whether you’re a cave dwelling anarcho-primalist hunting lusii and wearing their pelts, a farmer in a remote mushroom hive growing fungus, or a cottagecore pussycat that fishes for a living, one thing is for sure: to fit into nature, you gotta be one with nature. The survival tricks you\'ve learned make you **[Talented]** at **+HUB**. Choose an option from below and gain an exclusive ABSTRATA UPGRADE you can add to your starting weapon for free. You can purchase others with **LUX** later, and you can add 1 additional ABSTRATA UPGRADE to your weapons with these tags.\r\n\r\n> **TRAPKIND**: You carry around a big ol’ lusus trap on a chain, or maybe even wear them like makeshift gloves! When you roll a **GREAT** or higher on a **[Strife]** roll, the opponent becomes **[Trapped]** in exchange for **1 damage** less. As long as they are **[Trapped]**, you can spend an action to automatically do **1 [Somatic]** damage as you yank them around. An opponent’s ACT FAST roll to ABSCOND breaks the trap; you can’t use this effect again, though you may counter with a CAN’T ABSCOND BRO.\r\n\r\n> **CLAWKIND**: You carry the mark of the beast! Or— you leave the mark of beasts, on your foes, cuz, you mark them, and are a beast. Your claws hook into already weak spots; you have a **+2 [Buff]** to **[Strife]** rolls against foes with a **[Weakness]** to **[Somatic]** damage, or who are **[Bloodied]**.\r\n\r\n> **SPEARKIND**: You normally use this for fishing or hunting, but you’re not against using this on someone encroaching on your territory! You give the **[Stressed]** condition to Lusii or sufficiently animalistic trolls, such as Moonbarks or Trolls in Fursuits.\r\n\r\n> **CHOMPKIND**: CRUNCH! You love biting and gnashing! Hell yeah! You can use your teeth to **[Strife]**, doing **2 [Drag]** in exchange for one less damage on a **GREAT**. \r\n\r\n> **GARDENKIND**: You don’t even like strifing that much; you just wanna tend to your plants, for god’s sake! You can roll **[Strife]** rolls on yourself, **[Heal]**ing yourself when you’d harm or harming yourself when you’d heal by digging juicy vegetables out of the earth and munching them, or whipping out some prior produce when needed! This move still has the **[Strife]** tag, so you can’t wild out attacking and healing nonstop.\r\n\r\n> **VINEKIND**: Troll of the Jungle, watch out for that tree! Whether a literal vine, a rope or a lasso, you swing from vine to vine, and can vine up your enemies if you need! You may begin **[Flying]** on a **GREAT** **[Strife]** roll, dealing 1 less damage, as you start swinging around! If you fail to deal damage with a **[Strife]** roll afterwards, you stop **[Flying]** as your momentum falls apart.\r\n\r\n> **FISHKIND**: Tom Sawyer lookin\' ass. Your fishing rod catches trolls as they try to run; opponents CAN’T ABSCOND BRO if you hit them with a **[Strife]** roll last turn.'),
('wildWits', 'WILD WITS', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Look, whatever your position in Bronze society, you know that it’s best to play defensively. Blah blah, acting out could get the whole caste crushed by propaganda. But that doesn’t mean “fairly” or “with honour”. Hell, it’s actually really fun to let people think they’re getting the upper hand, and then point-blank a trick down their throat!  You get access to the following SHENANIGANS effects:\r\n\r\n> **BRAINBUST**: You pick up the opponent and BAM! Give them a headbutt that could shatter steel. The opponent loses one positive **[Emotion]**.\r\n\r\n> **BUCKAROO**: If you\'re a city slicker, this is extremely embarrassing. If you\'re a country folk, this comes naturally. When you roll this move, you get **1 [Hold]**. If your opponent summons their CUSTODIAN in the middle of a fight, you can use a **[Free]** **[Reaction]** to jump on their back and cling on for dear life. YEEHAW! The CUSTODIAN can\'t use its effects until you get off, and counts as a 2 HORSEPOWER VEHICLE. You can also roll this on wild lusii, but they\'ll still try to kill you.\r\n\r\n> **CHARGE!**: You grab someone and crash through a wall. You both become **[Bloodied]** and **[Floorbound]**.\r\n\r\n> **SUCKERPUNCH**: Yeah, come on, you\'re wide open! Sucker… If your opponent uses a **[Strife]** move against you on their next turn, you deck ‘em right the fuck back, getting **1 [WHAM]** after they hit you. In a TEAM STRIFE, this becomes **3 [Boost]** instead because people in a STRUGGLE can\'t not do it!'),
('windmillSlayer', 'WINDMILL SLAYER', 'OTHER', 'PAGE', '[Class][Advanced][Free][Recharge: 2][Locked: Page]', 'Okay... you\'ve had more time to practice things a bit, find out what really works for you and what doesn\'t. You\'ve had a handful of minor accomplishments, even! You pushed a bully once, yeah! You\'ve gotten to a point where you\'re able to succeed at things far more often than you would possibly, uh, fail at them! When rolling QUIXOTIC BOAST, you still roll a 1d8, but your chances are switched up. On a 1-2, your roll **[Tiers Down]**, possibly to a **MIN** still. On a 3-8, however, your next roll **[Tiers Up]**, which could go up to a **MAX**.\n\n'),
('windupPunch', 'WIND-UP PUNCH', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Buildup: 4][Lengthy][One-Off][Locked: Bully]', 'You swing your arm in a circle before attacking, aaaaand… POW! SEND EM FLYING! You get ready for a really heavy attack, and launch a **[Strife]** roll as a **[Lengthy]** action. If it hits, you double the base damage of the move, before applying **[WHAM]**, **[Weakness]** or **[Resistance]**.\r\n');
INSERT INTO `move` (`key`, `title`, `color`, `doc`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('witchsRebellion', 'WITCH’S REBELLION', 'OTHER', 'WITCH', '[Class][Advanced][Mental][Recharge: 5][Magic][Locked: Witch]', 'You’re a Witch, and that means two things: you’re a confident, knowing person, and you like to challenge things. Why should the sky be purple? Why should the grass be a different shade of purple? Why are things the way they are? You question the fundamentals, and reshape things to be the way you think they should be- because as it stands, the fundamentals are a little bit suffocating, and you really wish they weren’t! When you want to rebel against your aspect, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\nYou’re a Witch, and that means two things: you’re a confident, knowing person, and you like to challenge things. Why should the sky be purple? Why should the grass be a different shade of purple? Why are things the way they are? You question the fundamentals, and reshape things to be the way you think they should be - because as it stands, the fundamentals are a little bit suffocating, and you really wish they weren’t! When you want to rebel against your aspect, roll **+RAS, +HUB**, or **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Nnngh - your aspect’s oppressive grip grows only tighter. It’s getting hard to breathe… you’re **[Slowed]** for 2 rounds, and take 2 **[Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Your aspect stoically refuses to give a shit about your problems. When does it ever?\r\n\r\n**OK**: Your aspect bends to your will briefly- but not for long enough! You get the results of a **GOOD**, but only for 1 round.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You cast a spell on your aspect, and it’s forced to listen! Choose an effect based on your aspect…\r\n\r\n> **TIME**: You overwhelm effects that control your pacing; you rearrange the initiative/turn order to your liking. If another Witch of Time happens to be trying to do this too, call a coin flip.\r\n\r\n> **SPACE**: Turn it around! You swap an effect someone has with its opposite - for example, a **[Flying]** target becomes **[Floorbound]**, an **[Ablaze]** troll is put out and **[Healed]** an equal amount of damage, a **[Tiered Up]** effect becomes **[Tiered Down]**, etc.\r\n\r\n> **LIFE**: Challenge your limits! All effects are doubled to a cap of 3 for 3 rounds; all **[Boost]** gained, damage dealt, **HP [Healed]**, etc, both for you and your opponent. \r\n\r\n> **DOOM**: Suffering is eternal, and if it isn\'t, yes it is. For the next 3 rounds, you may choose 1 status effect inflicted (i.e. [Floorbound]) and prolong the time that your opponent has it, making them have to keep it for at least one full round.\r\n\r\n> **HOPE**: Does good have to truly be good, or evil truly evil? You swap your **[Boost]** and **[Drag]**, or swap your opponent’s **[Boost]** and **[Drag]**, or both.\r\n\r\n> **RAGE**: Misery loves company. Come! Be miserable with me, then! For the next 3 rounds, when someone gives you **[Drag]**, **[Negative]** Emotions, or status effects, they receive it right back!\r\n\r\n> **BREATH**: No, but really, if you do it like this then maybe it\'d work better, just hang on... on your next turn you may freely choose what stats to use to roll.\r\n\r\n> **BLOOD**: Let’s share! If the opponent has a Custodian or NPC on their side, you can use an action to control it yourself. If they don’t, you can use an action to make your opponent use moves against themselves costing you each an action, **[Tiered Down]**! You may not perform the same move you made them do. This effect lasts 2 turns.\r\n\r\n> **LIGHT**: Knowing things only drags people down! The target is **[Blinded]**, and their **PROBLEM SLEUTHING** rolls are **[Inept]** for 3 turns.\r\n\r\n> **VOID**: You’re tired of being forgotten! All trolls pay attention to you alone and cannot use moves that affect themselves or others for 3 turns.\r\n\r\n> **HEART**: Your power over souls is borderline terrifying! You may change a single **[Emotion]** inflicted on you or anyone else into another **[Emotion]**. The new and old must both be **[Positive]** or both be **[Negative]**, because contrary to what you might think, you\'re not God.\r\n\r\n> **MIND**: Enough thinking, more action. With the exception of yourself, nobody can use **[Mental]** rolls for 3 turns.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Whoo! You rebel so hard, you can feel your aspect’s grasp cracking; you gain a **GOOD** effect and 2 **[Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Ha! YOU’RE in charge, not your aspect! You get a **GOOD** result, 4 **[Boost]**, and your next usage of this move becomes **[Recharge: 3]**.'),
('withGreatPower', 'WITH GREAT POWER…', 'OTHER', 'SUPERSCOUNDREL', '[Template][Passive][Unlock: Superscoundrel]', 'You are, undoubtedly, exceptional. All exceptional beings have some sort of moral code, whether it’s steadfast or as loose as a limp noodle. This code inevitably falls on the path of good, evil, or somewhere in between. Choose your path from the options below:\r\n\r\n> **HERO**: … Comes great responsibility! You are trollmanity\'s last line of defense against the forces of evil. When the world is plunged into darkness, you are the bringer of light! When faced with an opponent who has aligned with VILLAINY, all rolls **[Tier Up]**. Additionally, any time you enter a **[STRIFE]**, all allies feel **[Hopeful]**. If an ally was already **[Hopeful]**, they gain **+1 [Boost]** instead. This emotion becomes **[Heightened]** in the presence of more than one hero.\r\n\r\n> **ANTIHERO**: … Comes great chaos! You’re neither on the side of good nor evil. You play by your own rules and opportunities, and everyone’s fair game for your acts of unknowable morality. When faced with an opponent who has aligned with ANTIHERO, all rolls **[Tier Up]**. Additionally, any time you enter a **[STRIFE]**, all members of the **[STRIFE]** feel **[Scared]**. If someone was already feeling **[Scared]**, they roll a 1d2. On a 1, they get **+1 [Drag]**. On a 2, they get +1 **[Boost]**. Should they get **[Drag]**, it doesn\'t increase to +2 automatically due to being **[Scared]**. This emotion becomes **[Heightened]** in the presence of more than one antihero.\r\n\r\n> **VILLAIN**: … Comes great opportunity! You have chosen to follow the shadows to become something greater. Whether beckoned by power, freedom, or cookies, the dark side welcomes you. When faced with an opponent who has aligned with HEROISM, all rolls **[Tier Up]**. Additionally, any time you enter a **[STRIFE]**, all opponents feel **[Dread]**. If an opponent was already feeling **[Dread]**, they gain **+1 [Drag]** instead. This emotion becomes **[Heightened]** in the presence of more than one villain.\r\n\r\n'),
('withGreatSuffering', 'WITH GREAT SUFFERING…', 'DOOM', 'DOOM', '[Aspect][Advanced][Yup!][Locked: Doom]', '...comes great empathy. C’mere, bud. You need a hug? It’s gonna be okay. You’ve had the highs and the lows, you get it. You can be the shoulder to cry on and the steady rock amidst all the despair because of it. Anything your target is going through… the chances are, you’ve gone through it too. You can offer the target respite— if they accept, up to three of their emotion tags are cleared and they heal **3 HP**, and they give you **1 [Hold]** which acts as a GREAT WORDPLAY roll to **[Manipulate]**. This **[Hold]** lasts forever, and only goes away once it\'s spent. The healing is a **[One-Off]** effect for the thread it\'s used in, and you can only ever have **1 [Hold]** per person until you use it.\r\n'),
('withTheSteelChair', 'WITH THE STEEL CHAIR!', 'OTHER', 'MUSCLEMANIAC', '[Template][Basic][Free][Buildup: 4][Recharge: 4][Locked: Musclemaniac]', 'Gogdamn ENPECE IS READYING THEIR BLUDGEONING STICK, THEY’RE CHARGING THEIR PSIONICS, THEY’RE ABOUT TO DO THE JACKHAMMER…! Regardless of what kind of move you might be about to pull off, the most dramatic shit to do is to be your own announcer and call out exactly what you’re about to do like an anime protagonist. Declare what move you’re going to roll next and declare how well you will roll that roll (whether you’ll get a **GOOD**, **BAD**, etc.), and come up with a name for your signature move. This roll cannot be affected by **[Tier Ups]** or **[Tier Downs]**. If you achieve the result on the roll that you predicted (i.e a **GOOD** SHENANIGANS roll), you get a **MAX**. If you achieve anything other than what you predicted, you get a **MIN**.'),
('withThisKnowledgeIWill', 'WITH THIS KNOWLEDGE, I WILL...', 'OTHER', 'SEER', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Seer]\r\n', 'Contrary to popular belief, you don\'t just wildly consume knowledge for the sake of it. You learn, and you plan. There’s almost a feeling in the back of your mind, sometimes, like you need  this information. That you’re planning for something you can’t quite see in your future yet… but that’s ridiculous. You may be extremely enlightened and well reasoned compared to… well, basically everyone you know. Let’s cast aside false modesty, shall we? But you can be rational on top of that! Anyway: now every time you learn something, you immediately try to apply it to your situation. You gain the following **GOOD PROBLEM SLEUTHING** options:\r\n\r\n> **ABJURE:** Take **-1 damage** from their next attack as you see their plan of action. \r\n> **ATTACK:** Deal a passive **+1 damage** on your next attack as you see their weak points. \r\n> **ASSESS:** Take a **+1 [Buff]** to your next **[Strife]** against them as you pinpoint an opening in their defense.'),
('witsAboutYou', 'WITS ABOUT YOU', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Passive]', 'Look… you need to be careful, okay? The world is an AWFUL place for people like you, if you aren\'t careful. As such, you need to… be careful! You gain the following PROBLEM SLEUTHING options.\r\n\r\n> **HEMOPONDER**: Does this guy look like they\'d kill you for being Lime? If the target has negative opinions of Lime trolls, you gain **1 [WHAM]** as you gulp and prepare yourself. If the target is cool with Limes, you become **[Peaceful]**. Phew…\r\n\r\n> **LOCATIONIZE**: What\'s gonna happen? If you are in a situation where a Hazard could randomly strike, such as when you\'re SEEKING ADVENTURE, you can select the Hazard most likely to trigger. Lo and behold, if a Hazard strikes, it\'s that one.\r\n\r\n> **CONSEQUENCERY**: You pause, thinking about what you\'re about to do. Roll any move; if you\'re not happy with the immediate response, roll something entirely different on your next move and say GOOD THING I DIDN\'T DO THAT.\r\n\r\n> **STUDY WOUNDS**: Oof… looks like that HURT! You look at a wound someone has, figuring out who caused it and one thing about them. The person who caused the wound has a **-2 [Nerf]** on their next **[Strife]** roll against you.'),
('wontGiveIn', 'WON\'T GIVE IN', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Basic][Passive]', 'A long standing record of subjugation marks the clouded history of your caste… and you aren\'t going to let it ever happen again. **[Control]** moves are **[Godawful]** against you as you fight back with every ounce of your might against them.'),
('woosh', 'WOOSH', 'BREATH', 'BREATH', '[Aspect][Basic][Passive][Locked: Breath]', 'You’re a little oblivious sometimes, bless your heart. The rude things people say to you just kinda float through one ear and out the other. It makes it a little hard for you to pick up on when someone is trying to be rude to you, so sometimes you’ll just stay in bad situations because you haven’t realized there’s even a problem yet. You gain **1 [Resistance]** against all **[Verbal]** damage.'),
('wordplay', 'WORDPLAY', 'OTHER', 'UNIVERSAL', '[Mental][Manipulate]', 'Many trolls prefer to fight with their fists, sure— but sometimes, it’s better to let the wits do the talking. Between verbal jousting, commands or instilling emotions, knowing how to deliver a line is particularly important on a planet that wants you dead. Each WORDPLAY result is on a **[Recharge: 2]**. When you want to use your words, roll **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Oh, you said the WORST possible thing! What the hell is wrong with you? You\'re **[Humiliated]** until the end of your turn, and you take **1 [Psychic]** damage as you kick yourself.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You, ah, you- the thing, uh- okay. You take **1 [Drag]** while you stumble over your words and sound like an idiot.\r\n\r\n**OK**: They didn\'t hear you! Speak up!\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You play your funky words, and your target hears ‘em loud and clear! Choose one of the effects below:\r\n\r\n> **BANTER**: You make a witty comment, making your target chuckle and feel a little better. Give them **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **DECEIVE**: UHHHHH… you DIDN\'T just roll this! You give a falsitude or act in a misleading way, **[Tiering Down]** the next or last **[Analyze]** or REQUEST asking information\'s roll against you by 1 stage.\r\n\r\n> **DEFLECT**: Aha, so, aaaanyways…  If you roll a higher numerical WORDPLAY result than your  target, you undo the mechanical effect of a WORDPLAY roll they succeeded at against you.\r\n\r\n> **FLIRT**: Eyyyy ];) Whether you\'re implying someone would be a great friend, partner, enemy, or needs therapy, you have a sparkle about you that can\'t be ignored! The target becomes **[Charmed]** by you for one turn.\r\n\r\n> **JAB**: Ah, a keenly crafted dig! Up yours! You do **1 [Verbal]** damage. You cannot use this once a **[Strife]** move other than JAB has been rolled. It ignores the **[Nerf]** to **[Strife]** moves from **[Hidden]**, as you don\'t need to see someone to call them a blugewad loser. This option has the **[Strife]** tag, and no **[Recharge]**.\r\n\r\n> **REQUEST**: Do this for me, please! You ask your target to do something. They either do it, or they don\'t; if they don\'t, they take **1 [Drag]**. If you roll WORDPLAY again to keep asking them, the **[Drag]** taken increases by 1 every time they refuse. If you REQUEST someone to do something they obviously can\'t do, such as ask an olive to use psionics or a high ranking ORG agent to become a rebel, your roll automatically fails and nothing happens.\r\n\r\n> **RILE**: You pour verbal gasoline very close to the social fire. They gain **1 [Boost]**. The next time you take damage from your opponent, you gain **1 [Boost]** and **1 [WHAM]** in vindication.\r\n\r\n> **SCHMOOZE**: Ass kicking? You\'re here for the ass KISSING! You compliment your allies or perhaps concede your enemies have some good qualities to them! Your next non-**[Strife]** +PLC roll gets a +2 **[Buff]**, as people are more willing to hear you out.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: A true wordsmith! You gain the effects of a **GOOD**, except the bonus is increased by 1 on all numerical results. On a DEFLECT, the target takes **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: YOU ARE INFINITE MONKEYS AT A TYPEWRITER. You say the exact perfect thing, and it works perfectly. The bonus on all numerical results is increased by 2, for FLIRT targets become **[Fascinated]** for 2 turns and you can reduce the damage of JAB by 1 to give the target **[Sad]** as that taunt really hurts their feelings.'),
('workaholic', 'WORKAHOLIC', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Doing your job is 90% of what you do. Seriously, you never stop. Work work work work… even your hobbies are sometimes related to work. It’s because you need to prove yourself an exceptional worker if you want to get picked for a good role post-Ascension, and all the OTHER Tealbloods do it, so if you don’t, then… boom, you’ll be given an Officewarren to rot in til you expire. Not really great. Your MONEYMAKERY rolls are always **[Talented]**.'),
('workingRelationship', 'WORKING RELATIONSHIP', 'OTHER', 'MAID', '[Class][Basic][Recharge: 2][Locked: Maid]', 'Help! You need leadership! Be it from a prince or a pauper, you don\'t care, as long as that person can help you figure out what to do. At the beginning of an encounter, you can designate one ally to be your leader! This gives them the ability to give you orders for **[Free]**, allowing them to tell you what moves to use on your next turn. Doing so leaves them **[Distracted]** on the turns that they help you, though, because it\'s hard to focus on two people at the same time! Once you get to your turn, all moves you roll **[Tier Up]**. If you roll a **GREAT** on the moves they told you to roll, then you both gain 2 **[Boost]** per GREAT result from the satisfaction of a job well done. On a **MAX**, you both gain the 2 **[Boost]** and **[Heal]** 1 **HP**. You both take 2 **[Drag]** if you roll a **MIN**, though.\r\n'),
('workplaceWhiz', 'WORKPLACE WHIZ', 'TEAL', 'TEAL', '[Teal][Passive][Unlock: Penpusher]', 'Teals are the Trollic Empire\'s chosen bureaucrats, the sniveling midbloods who keep the empire running. You may take offense to this stereotype, but thanks to your extensive training… you\'re pretty good at it. You do work experience in a fake office, because everyone else does and you don\'t want to be left in the dust. Choose a department, and gain the associated benefits.\r\n\r\n> **ACCOUNTING (+RAS)**: Money makes the world go round, and you get some sick pleasure in stopping people\'s worlds through TAXATION. Any time someone gets a **GREAT** or higher roll around you, you may tax them their **[Boost]**, taking 2 away as a **[Reaction]** and giving it to yourself. \r\n\r\n> **TROLL RESOURCES (+PLC)**: Alright, look, it\'s not an easy job being what is essentially a corporate auspice, but you do it well. Trolls cannot have **[Emotions]** around you unless they take **2 [Drag]** when they gain it, or you allow it. Come on, let\'s show some restraint and be professional.\r\n\r\n> **ASSISTANT (+GRA)**: You stand there and look pretty while the others argue, and then do the hard work yourself. Yeesh. You can spend an action to **[Tier Up]** an ally\'s roll. This has **[Recharge: 3]**.\r\n\r\n> **ACQUISITIONS (+APP)**: What do you mean, the orders are backlogged? We need 32 Medicalizers in by Gruelsday, or we\'ll be behind schedule! You take part in ordering supplies for the office to sell elsewhere, or use as supplies. You have **10 VP** instead of 8, and all items cost **1 VP** less (min. 1).\r\n\r\n> **INSURANCE AGENT (+GRT)**: There\'s no way around this, you\'re basically an armed brute. Like, you collect \"insurance\" from local businesses, and maybe even have links with a Juggalo Crime Clutch? And hey, if someone can\'t pay insurance… you COLLECT. You gain **Treasure I** and reduce the opponent’s Wealth a level if you beat them in a fight.\r\n\r\n> **SALES: (+HUB)**: Oh, yeah, beautiful. I get you. Look, this stuff? You\'re gonna want in on this, you know? You\'re in the marketing department, and your larger than life personality makes you MARKET, you feel me? You can use your **+HUB** to roll WORDPLAY, but any **BAD** roll you make like this **[Tiers Down]** to a **MIN**. \r\n\r\n> **ADMINISTRATION (+PSP)**: You are the nerve center of the office. Emails, scheduling, spying on colleagues, providing endless blackmail… oh yeah. You can read other trolls\' private messages, and may spend a **[Lengthy]** **[Tech]** action to make a **[Tiered Up]** PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll by checking your emails for clues.\r\n\r\n> **OFFICE WARLOCK (+IMG)**: This is an extremely important job. Who\'s going to put protective runes on the office hardware to stop them catching viruses? Who\'s going to stave off ghouls who would eat the printing cartridges? You. You may make GRIEF rolls with your **+IMG**; this is a **[Magic]** effect, not a **[Physical]** one.'),
('worldcrushingEgo', 'WORLDCRUSHING EGO', 'VIOLET', 'VIOLET', '[Violet][Basic][Passive]', 'Let\'s face it! You\'re, uh, the best. That\'s what everyone says. That\'s what you know to be true. There\'s really no way to look at it any other way; you\'re better at everything than everyone, you\'re faster, you\'re richer… yeah, dude. You\'re pretty fucking great. You gain the following **GOOD** SWASHBUCKLE effects.\r\n\r\n**INSANE COOLAGE**: Seriously, you hold yourself with such confidence that it is actually patently nuts. Docterrors everywhere recommend invasive medicull treatment for how sicknasty you are. All opponents and allies become **[Charmed]** by you for a turn, and you get a **MAX** on an 18+ this turn.\r\n\r\n**LAUGHTALE**: HE LAUGHED. What, something like this isn\'t going to keep you down. You can replace any negative **[Emotion]** with the **[Laughing]** one, which then ends after **1 turn**, taking the emotion with it.\r\n\r\n**SWIFT SWIM**: Not so FUCKING fast. While underwater, you can swim very, very, VERY fast. You keep pace with boats, ships, whatever! This move acts as a **GOOD**, **GREAT**, or **MAX** VEHICULATE roll underwater, except that you\'re the Vehicle. You have 2 HORSEPOWER underwater.\r\n\r\n**OVERCOME LIMITS**: ONE MORE PUSH! You get a **GOOD**/**GREAT**/**MAX** on another two moves, and then become **[Exhausted]**.'),
('wormChurch', 'WORM CHURCH', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Passive][Unlock: Cloistered]', 'Congratulations! You were selected upon hatching to tend directly to the Holy Mother Grub, birther of the trollic race. Your reward? ETERNAL SERVITUDE TO YOUR GODDESS. Whether you take to this with open arms or not depends on who you are, but your duties are still duties. You must wear a Troll Catholic School Uniform, you must revere the Grandmother Grub as the virgin goddess of trollkind, and you MUST stay in the deep reaches of the Undercaverns no matter what. It’s a lonely life, only ever interacting occasionally with other trolls, but such is the price of purity. And you love being pure and holy, don’t you? You gain the **[Cullbait]** tag when leaving the Undercaverns. You are **[Talented]** at **+IMG**. You can take the following options when you use FRAYMOTIF, using your **[Class]** rather than **[Aspect]**; you\'ve long been educated to just follow your role, and that affects your destiny dance.\r\n\r\n**WITCH/HEIR**: You twirl and spiral in countless pirouettes. You change the path of tomorrow, and everyone follows you. You invert your troll\'s **[Aspect]**; for example, getting a Heart FRAYMOTIF from a Mind troll.\r\n\r\n**KNIGHT/PAGE**: Your dance is visible, it\'s proud, it\'s present. Only you and your allies can use **[Boost]** so long as you keep dancing.  \r\n\r\n**MAID/SYLPH**: Your swaying dance will make everyone feel calmer. You and your allies are **[Talented]** at GUTSUCKERY, which has a **[Recharge: 3]**.\r\n\r\n**MAGE/SEER**: A slow, pondering dance. You understand what nobody else could possibly understand. PROBLEM SLEUTHING rolls become **[Free]** for you and your allies.\r\n\r\n**THIEF/ROGUE**: Such sleek movement! Your dance collectivizes the belongings of others. All trolls add up their **VP** together, and share items with one another. Any opponent can use your items, and vice versa.\r\n\r\n**PRINCE/BARD**: Fast-paced, energetic, distracting! All will fall apart, all will collapse! Opponent trolls get **1 [Drag]** each turn.'),
('wrigglersitter', 'WRIGGLERSITTER', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Basic][Open][Recharge: 3][Flourish]', 'You must ALWAYS keep your friends safe, no matter what. Sometimes, you act as a second custodian for your friends, even if you don\'t really want to be. You can\'t help it— it\'s what you were raised to do. When you\'re on STANDBY in a TEAM STRIFE and want to make sure your STRUGGLER doesn\'t get into too much trouble, roll **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: NO! Your meddling made the situation WORSE! **[Strife]** rolls against your STRUGGLER are now **[Tiered Up]** for **2 turns**, and they can\'t ABDICATE during this time. NOOOO! \r\n\r\n**BAD**: You\'re just making them feel a little pressured, dude, back up. The STRUGGLER can\'t ABDICATE for **2 turns**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You don\'t really… do much! But it\'s the thought that counts.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Aha! You\'re taking care of them now! Choose one of the following tags to make **[Inept]** against the target for **2 turns**: \r\n\r\n> 1. **[Chicanery]**\r\n> 2. **[Manipulate]**\r\n> 3. **[Control]**\r\n> 4. **[Strife]**, but only for 1 turn\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Whoa! You\'re doing a **GREAT** job taking care of them! You get a **GOOD**, but increase the duration by 1 turn. On the second turn, **[Strife]** protection only gives the opponent a **-2 [Nerf]** to their roll.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: See? Now, this is why everyone needs you around. You get a **GOOD**, but increase the duration by **2 turns. On the second turn, **[Strife]** protection only gives the opponent a **-3 [Nerf]** to their roll, and on the third a -2.'),
('wylderdruid', 'WYLDERDRUID', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Ultra][Magic][Locked: Nyanarchist]', 'There\'s magic in the land beyond trolls. Can you hear it? It sighs, and whispers new life to those who sigh back. You have become well acquainted with all that lives and breathes… and you have touched the magic beneath it all. You gain access to HERO MODE through your HARDCORE HUBRIS. Lusii and plants never attack you, unless you attack first; you have an understanding with the forces of nature. You may also roll **+HUB** to use **[Manipulate]** moves on these creatures; this is a **[Magic]** effect, as you speak the tongues of the bark and the beast. You may use your magic to literally change shape and become a lusus yourself. Choose any lusus or plant from the FRIENDS AND FOES chapter of 3rd level or lower; you can become the lusus, adopting its stats. You lose your normal moves, but keep your stat array (gaining the modifications the lusus has atop your own). You also keep your HP at the current level. You can only use moves the lusus has and Universal Moves in this form. Any **[Psionic]** or **[Magic]** rolls the lusus has, or any other option you may gain them from, use **+HUB**. Becoming a sufficiently inconspicuous lusus may hide you from those who are chasing you, if the scene allows for it.'),
('xenodruid', 'XENODRUID', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][One-Off][Psionic][Unlock: Summoner]', 'Bronze psionics are notably rare; you, however, are lucky enough to have the ability to COMMUNE, controlling the minds of lusii to fight for you! Your power comes from a mix of innate psychic might and a deep understanding of how lusii work. You are **[Talented]** at **+IMG**. You may spend an action to summon a lusus. You can give up one, both, or all of your actions to give to your lusus to fight with. The lusus can only use Universal moves. Due to the nature of your empathetic link, you and your summoned lusus share all resources and conditions, from HP to Status Conditions to **[Boost]** or **[Recharge]**. When you want to COMMUNE, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: AAAAAAHHH! YOU ANGERED A BEAR! THIS IS THE WORST OUTCOME! A Cholerbear appears, and it is hostile to you.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Hnnnhhh… headache… you get **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n**OK**: You thought you felt some psychic stuff coming, but it was just a sneeze. Achoo! You waste this action, but you can try again next turn.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: LUSUS: SUMMONED! Choose one of the stat arrays below; it uses these stats and **[Talents]** instead of your own when it rolls. It also gains the listed effect.\r\n\r\n> **BEAST**: +1 RAS, +1 GRA, +0 APP, +3 GRT, +2 HUB, +0 IMG **+GRT** All opponents become **[Scared]** when it\'s on the field.\r\n\r\n> **BLOB**: +0 RAS, +0 GRA, +3 APP, +1 GRT, +0 HUB, +2 IMG **+APP** Has 1 **[Resistance]** to **[Somatic]** damage, and intercepts **[Strife]** moves that would deal **[Somatic]** damage to you, taking the damage instead.\r\n\r\n> **BUG**: +1 RAS, +3 GRA, +0 APP, +0 GRT, +1 HUB, +2 IMG **+GRA** **[Deafens]** all opponents on the field with its loud noises.\r\n\r\n> **BIRD**: +1 RAS, +2 GRA, +0 APP, +1 GRT, +3 HUB, +0 IMG **+HUB** Can **[Fly]**, and can spend an action to pick you up and **[Fly]** too.\r\n\r\n> **BFISH**: +3 RAS, +1 GRA, +0 APP, +2 GRT, +1 HUB, +0 IMG **+RAS** Can breathe underwater, and if it keeps you in its mouth, you can be down there too.\r\n\r\n> **BEING**: +2 RAS, +1 GRA, +0 APP, +0 GRT, +1 HUB, +3 IMG **+IMG** Can roll GRIEF with **+IMG**, does **[Psychic]** damage.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Wow! You summoned a really weird lusus! Though it has the array of only one lusus, it gains the effects listed under two of the above, like Bird and Beast. \r\n\r\n**MAX**: Holy freak show! This thing is BIZARRE! You get a **GREAT**, but you gain three effects.'),
('yarnchaser', 'YARNCHASER', 'BRONZE', 'BRONZE', '[Bronze][Passive][Unlock: Folklorist]', 'What do you believe in? Bronze trolls have a strong oral tradition, and folktales spread like wildfire through their communities. Whether you\'re an illustrator for wigglertomes writing about fairy tales or a librarian of handmade books, nobody knows folklore like you! You are **[Talented]** in **+PLC**. Select an area of expertise from the list below, and gain the associated effect.\r\n\r\n**Faeries & Magic**: Some people like to say that magic is fake as shit, but you disagree! You know how to ward off bad vibes; do three spins and clap your hands, and hey presto, **[Magic]** rolls are **[Inept]** against you!\r\n\r\n**Beasts & Creatures**: Ah, that! That\'s a four-legged gollygosher. In certain tales, they\'re good omens! Or were they bad… you study bestiaries and know all about monsters. When you first encounter a monster, you can mark them as a **GOOD OMEN** or a **BAD OMEN** for **[Free]**. If Good, when fighting it, all combatants are **[Hopeful]**. If Bad, all combatants are **[Scared]** but do **+1 damage**. \r\n\r\n**Beliefs & Religions**: From dark carnivals to astrosorcery, everyone has something they believe in. You study the origins of such beliefs closely, including ones long since gone. You may add **[Holy]** energy to any damage you do as you pray forgotten prayers from a bygone era.\r\n\r\n**The True Meaning Of Holidays In General**: GOD YOU FUCKING LOVE HOLIDAYS. When you encounter someone during a festival or holiday, you can take one of the following effects:\r\n\r\n> **Holiday Cheer**: They like the holidays! You become **[Hopeful]**.\r\n> **Holiday Smear**: THEY DON\'T LIKE THE HOLIDAYS. You become **[Enraged]**.\r\n> **Foodways & Cuisine**: Food is a language in itself, telling stories about how people eat and what their cultures think of food. You can fill up your inventory with TAPAS, **1 VP** foods with the following choice of effects when you eat them.  \r\n\r\n> 1. **2 [Boost]**\r\n> 2. Lower **[Recharge]** of a move by 1.\r\n> 3. Increase **[Build-Up]** of a move by 1.\r\n> 4. Heighten an **[Emotion]**.\r\n\r\n> **Proverbs & Language**: Ho-hum, a bag in the bush is a friend of the morrow. You study language, slang, dialects, even ones long since dead. You get a **MAX** WORDPLAY roll on a 17+.\r\n\r\n> **Music & Dance**: Folk songs, a people\'s earliest storytelling, and dancing its earliest theatre! Your FRAYMOTIF rolls use **+PLC** as you contribute your own music to the scene!\r\n\r\n> **Art & Literature**: You can tell a lot about a society just from the beauty they create. You can inspire a willing target to swap out their old **[Talent]** to temporarily become **[Talented]** at **+PLC**.'),
('yellAtCustodians', 'YELL AT CUSTODIANS', 'JADE', 'JADE', '[Jade][Advanced][Open][Passive]', 'At this point, you\'ve dealt with enough raging lusii to not be scared of them. Maybe once you might have considered something like screaming at one improper, but… HEY! BICLOPS! WHAT ARE YOU DOING, LETTING YOUR CHARGE RUN WILD LIKE THAT, HUH?! Hostile ALTRICIALIZE rolls (See Chapter 11: CUSTODIANS) in your presence are **[Inept]**, and your **[Manipulate]** rolls can affect Lusii.'),
('yesSir', 'YES SIR', 'RUST', 'RUST', '[Rust][Basic][Passive][Locked: Worker]', 'Sometimes it\'s just easier to do what you\'re told, and deal with the consequences later. Whenever someone attempts a **[Manipulate]** or **[Control]** move against you, you can just automatically give them a **GOOD**. If you do so, you immediately gain **3 [Boost]**. You\'re gonna need it! This effect does not apply to allies, since you\'re probably actually okay with doing what your friends need as opposed to dipshit highbloods trying to buy a Scuttlebuggy at an Oblong Meat Product Saloon.'),
('youArePerceiving', 'YOU ARE PERCEIVING', 'OTHER', 'MAGE', '[Class][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Mage]', 'Learning is not a one way street. When you close yourself off from taking in new input, your advice is only based on past experience. Therefore, you’ve started observing others to catch onto what works for them. Who knows? It could be useful one day! When you roll **PROBLEM SLEUTHING**, you may gain a +1 **[Buff]*** to your choice of one **UNIVERSAL MOVE** aside from **PROBLEM SLEUTHING** itself for the next 3 rounds. This effect stacks.'),
('youCantGiveUpNow', 'YOU CAN’T GIVE UP NOW!', 'BREATH', 'BREATH', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Locked: Breath]', 'The going is tough, but that’s not an excuse to give up! You know you can do this! You know you can push through, and win despite the odds! You’ve spent so long running, but this… this is the time you stand and fight! When you first drop below a quarter of your HP (rounded down), you immediately gain **5 [Boost]** as you get ready for the final push. If you land at **1 HP** exactly, you immediately become **[Quickened]** until you’re either  knocked out or heal as the winds almost seem to blow in your favour no matter where you move.'),
('youDidNotSuccumb', 'YOU DID NOT SUCCUMB', 'DOOM', 'DOOM', '[Aspect][Advanced][Passive][Last Stand][Locked: Doom]\r\n', 'Sometimes you need to see things through to the very end, even if you don’t want to. Giving up early gets you nowhere; if you have to fight for any scrap of goodness and justice in this universe, then you\'re damned well going to fight. You stay up and conscious all the way until -5 HP. You may still fight as normal, all the way to -5, but for each hitpoint below 0 you receive a **-1 [Nerf]** to all rolls. **-3 HP** and rolling something with a **+2 [Buff]**? You roll 2d8-1, etc.\r\n'),
('youFool', 'YOU FOOL!', 'CERULEAN', 'CERULEAN', '[Cerulean][Basic][Passive][One-Off][Locked: Espiacrooner]', 'What\'s a spy without a little backstabbing? That\'s what they get for having such a delicious, juicy back. Your **RUMORHUNGER [Downtime]** rolls always **[Tier Up]** - you know everything there is to know about anyone who\'s in the know. This cannot stack with other **[Tier Up]**s. When you attack a character who hasn\'t figured out you\'re a spy yet, or if you attack while starting a strife **[Hidden]**- such as from a **RUMORHUNGER** success- you can shout YOU FOOL!! and make a **[Free] [Tiered Up] [Strife]** roll before rolling **LET\'S STRIFE**. It doesn\'t work if you don\'t shout YOU FOOL, and therefore reveal you are a spy to all present.'),
('youGotIt', 'YOU GOT IT', 'PROSPIT', 'PROSPIT', '[Sway][Passive][Locked: Prospit]', 'The world is scary, and you’d love to see changes to it, sure… but you’re also content with living a normal life. Instead of struggling with authority, you often find ways to co-exist with it. If an authority figure like a higherblood, an ORG **[Template]** troll, or a narrative superior uses a **[Manipulate]** roll against you, you may roll a counter **[Manipulate]** roll as a **[Reaction]**. If you succeed with a better roll than they do, you can choose to appear to comply, even if you’re only saying what they want to hear with no intention of doing it. Doing this lets the other person believe they succeeded, and won’t prompt further aggression. You gain **2 [Boost]** for tricking them.'),
('youMeanIt', 'YOU MEAN IT?', 'BREATH', 'BREATH', '[Aspect][Basic][Locked: Breath]', 'It totally says gullible up on the ceiling! Your friend told you, so it must be true! When someone tells you a lie, you can choose to take it at face value, spending an action to ask them if they’re serious. If they affirm that yes, they’re definitely serious, they take **4 [Drag]** for lying to you, and if you ever find out they were lying to you, you can choose to become **[Enraged]**— because, like, hey! That really isn’t cool, they shouldn’t take advantage of people like that! It’s dishonest! If they tell you they were lying, they must tell you the truth, the whole truth and nothing but the truth, or give you another chance to use this move.'),
('yourBootsSir', 'YOUR BOOTS, SIR', 'OTHER', 'SERVICESQUIRE', '[Template][Passive][Recharge: 3][Locked: Servicesquire]', 'Kissing higher castes ass is the easiest and safest way to get through life. Not that you necessarily agree that this is right; you just know it’s true. You can buy items on the fly in an encounter if someone requested them, eager to please. Yes, you just had these on hand! You must have the VP available in order to use this move without relying on your Boss’ VP to do this. You also cannot buy the same item more than once.\r\n'),
('youreAPirate', 'YOU’RE A PIRATE', 'OTHER', 'RAPSCALLINEER', '[Template][Basic][Buildup: 6][One-off][Locked: Rapscallineer]', 'You honestly thought pirates were all about being gay anarchocommunist sailors, huh? Well… so did I, honestly, until I remembered literally everything about pirates. You STEAL shit. You’re a MENACE to merchants and HOLD PEOPLE AT GUNPOINT, leaving them with nothing left but their pantaloons. When you want to rock someone’s shit by stealing stuff they didn’t even know they had, roll **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: Okay, so you know how you wanted to steal something from this guy? Well you’ve done the exact opposite, tripping all over yourself you’ve managed to deal **1 [Psychic]** damage to yourself, disarm yourself and somehow, someway, drop one **LUX** to your target, and if you don’t have any **LUX**, you become **[Confused]** and **[Floorbound]**, because you tried to drop yourself at them instead.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: The move does not enter cooldown, go straight to jail, do not collect 200 dollars. You deal **1 [Psychic]** damage to yourself, not the worst, but at least it wasn’t a **MIN**!\r\n\r\n**OK**: Ah!!! You’re the one getting **[Confused]**, and it sucks!! You can attempt this move on a **[Cooldown: 6]** until you manage to actually nab something!\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: You stole a single tiny potted plant from your quarry. You have accomplished nothing except team building.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: You did it! You stole a thing! You steal one **LUX** from your target. You get this **LUX** even if they didn’t mechanically have any, although if they didn’t have any beforehand, they become **[Confused]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Waow! With a swish of your sword, some agile footstepping and other pirate fuckery you’ve really raided this motherfucker. You gain two **LUX** and become **[Proud]**; if your target didn’t have any **LUX** beforehand, they become **[Dumbfounded]**.'),
('yourShitIsWrecked', 'YOUR SHIT IS WRECKED', 'OTHER', 'PRINCE', '[Class][Passive][Unlock: Prince]', 'You are a prince, and as such, you are deserving of all of the nicest and best things, and all the peasants around you are NOT. Look at those plebeians, with their simple minds and power from a single aspect. YOU ARE ABOVE THEM! Due to such ruthless destruction of your own aspect, you often ghost its opposite. You gain the **[Unlock]** move of your opposite **[Aspect]** upon taking this move. If you so wish, you may take your opposite **[Aspect]** as a **[Template]** and take moves from it alongside your own. A mighty ruler needs an arsenal to match, no? You may not gain your opposite **[Aspect]**’s **[Ultra]** with this, nor do moves from your opposite **[Aspect]** count towards completion.\r\n\r\n\r\n'),
('youthsInSuits', 'YOUTHS IN SUITS', 'INDIGO', 'INDIGO', '[Indigo][Basic][Open][Passive]', 'Indigos gotta dress smart! Dress well! Dress NICE! Dress like you don’t really want people’s approval but have no idea how to communicate well with people outside of your caste! You can wear up to two Fashion items per clothing slot at a time, merging the fashions together into something new. You generally only benefit from one of these items’ stat alteration effects at a time. However, you can have two complete collections equipped at a time; one for the stat alteration, and one for the collection effect. You can swap between these two as a **[Lengthy]** action by twirling on the spot and striking a pose. KYA!'),
('zap', 'ZAP', 'LIME', 'LIME', '[Lime][Advanced][Recharge: 3][Cullbait][Flourish][Magic]', 'Sometimes, you would rather not be here. Actually, you know what? Fuck this! You poof out of where you are, scrambling through the narrative to somewhere else, whether it’s miles away or a few inches to the right. It’s kinda hard to choose, actually; you’re not that good at teleporting. When you want to disappear and reappear elsewhere, roll **+IMG**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: You teleport… 15 feet in the air directly over where you were standing. Oof! You take **2 [Somatic]** damage and become **[Floorbound]** when you land. If there was a dangerous spot nearby, you can choose to teleport into it instead and receive a condition- for example, zapping into a furnace and becoming **[Ablaze]**.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You scrunch up your face real hard, and… nothing. \r\n\r\n**OK**: You teleport slightly, but not far enough. You don’t waste time, though- you get another action this turn. \r\n\r\n**GOOD: Hey, not bad! You teleport like you wanted to! You teleport, and gain the following effects**:\r\n\r\n> **ABSCOND**: Fuck this! Adios! You ABSCOND, and the opponent can\'t roll CAN\'T ABSCOND BRO. LET\'S SKEDDADLE applies to this effect.\r\n> **GROCERY STORE TRIP**: ZIP… ZAP! You return with stuff from the store, buying an item on the fly.\r\n> **SIDESTEP**: No! Your opponent’s next **[Physical][Strife]** roll is **[Inept]**. You leave yourself open, though, and they do **+1 damage** on their next successful attack against you. This is cumulative.\r\n> **HIDE!!!**: You don’t want them to see you! You become **[Hidden]**.  \r\n> **TIMEZAP**: Oops? You accidentally travel through time! You vanish for **3 turns** and then come back in the exact state you left, or you vanish and immediately reappear with all your **[Recharge]** moves picked up. \r\n> **GROUP ZAP**: Let\'s go! The battle scene changes places, potentially into a Hazard. Roll 1d8; on an odd number, you don\'t end up somewhere safe. But who doesn\'t like some spice?\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: ZOOMP! Feels great! You get a **GOOD**, and **2 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: Whoa! You teleport- and then you just can’t stop teleporting either? You don’t have to move anymore, you just teleport like crazy! You are **[Quickened]** for **3 rounds**.'),
('zodiacCat', 'ZODIAC CAT', 'OLIVE', 'OLIVE', '[Olive][Passive][Unlock: Nyastrologist]', 'You know, like a Leo? The point is, there\'s a million, billion, trillion stars in the sky, and they each have an effect on the trolls that are spawned beneath them. And you are a scholar of the stuff! You\'ve trawled the arcane blogs, you\'ve consulted charts, you\'ve cross referenced shipping wikis… suffice to say, you know your stuff! Your studies into the mundane side of the Zodiac (not necessarily that Astrosorcery stuff, that\'s a whole other bag of worms) has made you **[Talented]** at **+PLC**. You get the following effect when you meet a troll, based on their sign and your own.\n\n> **COMPATIBLE**: This troll and you have an innate chemistry in the positive aspects of life! Your non-**[Strife]** **+PLC** rolls against them have a **+2 [Buff]**. If you\'re ULTRACOMPATIBLE (with 3 matching groups) this rises to +3.\n\n> **INCOMPATIBLE**: Stars say this troll is a little bitch. Perfect negative aspect material. Your JAB WORDPLAY rolls against them can continue even after an encounter starts. If you\'re ULTRAINCOMPATIBLE (with NO matching groups), you have a +2 on these rolls.\n\nDespite the name, INCOMPATIBLE is no less compatible than COMPATIBLE; in this case, positive and negative just refers to affecting your life the way a matesprit or kismesis might affect your love life. To be compatible, the other troll must have at least two of the following groups shared with you. \n\n**CASTE**: \n\n> **Earth**: [Taurus, Virgo, Capricorn]\n> **Water**: [Pisces, Scorpio, Cancer]\n> **Fire**: [Sagittarius, Leo, Aries]\n> **Air**: [Libra, Aquarius, Gemini]\n\n**SWAY**: \n\n> Derse or Prospit\n\n**ASPECT**:\n\n> **Body**: [Blood, Life, Rage, Heart, Time, Void]\n> **Soul**: [Breath, Doom, Hope, Mind, Space, Light]'),
('zodiactouched', 'ZODIAC-TOUCHED', 'KID', 'KID', '[Kid][Advanced][Passive]', 'Having grown up in a society that does not try to kill you from the moment you are born (literally, at least) has given you time to think, and your presence on Alternia has made you reflective on this. It’s made you reflective on a lot of stuff, honestly. You gain one **[Advanced]** move of your own Aspect, and the level gate drops to Level 6, allowing you access now rather than later. You must have the appropriate **[Entry]** move to take this move first. Once you hit Level 12, you can gain the Aspect Entry Move of your Aspect’s pair (for example, a Light Player gaining the Void Entry, or a Rage Player gaining the Hope Entry), though you cannot get any other moves from that tree.');
INSERT INTO `prosthetic` (`key`, `title`, `text`) VALUES
('multiarm', 'MULTIARM', 'Why have an arm that can do just one thing like your old, boring flesh arm could do, when you can have an arm that does all kinds of things? MultiArms are built to be swiss ARMy knives, full of useful goodies for any situation.\r\n \r\n**DESTITUTE, POOR, DECENT, AVERAGE: 1 LUX;** Your arm has the **[Mechanical]** tag! Choose two of the following: \r\n\r\n> **TOOL:** Your hand slides back to make way for a screwdriver or a laser or a welder or some other useful item. You gain infinite uses of 1 Item of your choice from the following choices on a **[Recharge: 3]**; MAKESHIFT CALTROPS, WARDROBIFIER, ESSENTIAL OILS or POKING STICK. This does not cost VP. Your LET’S STRIFE rolls **[Tier Down]** on an **OK**. \r\n\r\n> **CYBERNETIC MUSCLE**: Your arm moves and functions mostly like a real arm, but way stronger. You gain **+1 GRT**. On a **MIN** of any **+GRT** roll, your arm short circuits as you overuse the prosthetic, rendering you **[Stunned]**. \r\n\r\n> **SICK LOOKING**: Bro you got a badass robot arm! It looks cool as shit. When you make someone **[Charmed]**, you gain **1 [Boost]**.\r\n\r\n> **EXTENDING**: The arm shoots out, allowing you to hit **[Flying]** targets as though you had the RANGEDKIND abstrata.\r\n\r\n> **WELL OFF, RICH, ULTRARICH: 2 LUX**; Your arm is the finest engineering money can buy. It’s definitely **[Mechanical]**, and probably has unnecessary bits and bobs to look cool as well. Choose 3 of the following:\r\n\r\n> **TOOL**: Your hand slides back to make way for a screwdriver or a laser or a welder or some other TOOL. You gain infinite uses of 3 TOOL types. Your LET’S STRIFE rolls are normal.\r\n\r\n> **CYBERNETIC MUSCLE**: Your arm moves and functions as seamlessly and fluidly as a real arm, but with inbuilt indigo strength. You gain **+1 GRT**.\r\n\r\n> **INTIMIDATING**: Your arm is wild as hell. What is this made of? It’s big as a tree trunk, oh god please don’t punch me- your arm has a built in MASSIVEKIND Abstrata, which you can use in a Strife.\r\n\r\n> **EXTENDING**: The arm shoots out, allowing you to hit **[Flying]** targets as though you had the RANGEDKIND abstrata.\r\n\r\n> **CURSED**: Your arm is etched in subtle, glowing runes that hum with mysterious power. The arm acts as a MYSTICAL FOCUS Item, costs an extra **1 LUX**, and cannot be acquired unless you would normally be able to acquire **[Rare]** items. \r\n'),
('realisticProstheticArm', 'REALISTIC PROSTHETIC ARM', 'Hey, listen. Your old arm was pretty good, actually. It had a shoulder, an elbow, a wrist, and probably something in the vicinity of five fingers. Tried and true, aesthetically pleasing, a massive pain to draw, everything an arm and hand should be. Maybe you just want to have a regular old arm back! Maybe you’re just a pussy and afraid of cool robot arms. In that case, these arms are for you.  \r\n\r\n**DESTITUTE, POOR, DECENT, AVERAGE: 1 LUX**; A perfectly good, slick looking prosthetic arm. It can do something cool, like glow different colors or act like a mood ring. As a **[One-Off]**, you may avoid becoming **[Bloodied]** as your prosthetic soaks up the worst of the hit instead. Additionally, it grants you a **+1** to your choice of **+GRT** or **+GRA**.\r\n\r\n**WELL OFF, RICH, ULTRARICH: 2 LUX**; This is some seadweller level tech, right here. As a **[One-Off]**, you may avoid becoming **[Bloodied]** as you use your prosthetic to block. Additionally, it grants you a **+1** to your choice of **+GRT** or **+GRA**, and once per encounter you may push a **GREAT [Physical]** roll up to a **MAX**.'),
('realisticProstheticLeg', 'REALISTIC PROSTHETIC LEG', 'This is a leg! It looks like a leg (but metal), walks like a leg (but metal) and generally does everything a leg would do, but faster and better (and metaller). Bet your old leg didn’t come in twelve different customizable colors. Pure upgrade, baby! \r\n\r\n**DESTITUTE, POOR, DECENT, AVERAGE: 1 LUX**; This, this is a leg. This is some high tech cool leg going on. You gain a new SWASHBUCKLE effect: ZOOM, which grants you **[Quickened]** for **1 round**. \r\n\r\n**WELL OFF, RICH, ULTRARICH: 2 LUX**; This leg? This is quite possibly the sexiest leg. Your boring old flesh leg could never have given you this. You gain access to the ZOOM SWASHBUCKLE effect, and additionally lets you get up from **[Floorbound]** for **[Free]** twice per Encounter.\r\n'),
('combatLeg', 'COMBAT LEG', 'Imagine: It’s past exile. You’re on some derelict moon on the ass-end of the galaxy, you and your squadron pinned down, out of ammunition, your helmsman dead and your ship grounded, and the enemy aliens are bearing down on you. So what do you do? You whip out your Combat Leggy and you kick them in their faces so hard it turns their heads into disgusting alien-blood colored mist! POW!!!! Ain’t you glad you lost your leg now? \r\n\r\n**DESTITUTE, POOR, DECENT, AVERAGE: 1 LUX**; This is a certified ultra cool Combat Leggy©. Choose 2 upgrades from the list below. \r\n\r\n**WELL OFF, RICH, ULTRARICH: 2 LUX**; Your leg may actually be worth more than the rest of your body, depending on your caste and how into expensive tattoos you are. Choose 3 upgrades from the list below:\r\n\r\n> **STURDY**: Your leg is built solidly. You gain a +1 to GUTSUCKERY, and a -1 to LET’S STRIFE.\r\n\r\n> **SPRING-LOADED**: You know that space age tech the shoe commercials promise your tennis shoes have in them that make you jump like Troll Lebron? That. You gain a **+3 [Buff]** to all SWASHBUCKLE rolls to PCHOOOOO, even past the stat cap. \r\n\r\n> **HYDRAULICS**: Now YOU can stomp on bars of soap and non-newtonian fluids and squish them really satisfyingly. You get a **+1 [Buff]** to rolls to break weapons and items. \r\n\r\n> **SEXY**: Check out these GAMS. You gain a **+1 [Buff]** to **[Manipulate]** rolls, but you gotta stick your leggy out and run your hand along it like a razor commercial first. \r\n\r\n> **NIMBLE**: Lusus, lusus, look how fast I can run! You can really zoom in these things! On a **GREAT** or higher LET’S STRIFE or SWASHBUCKLE roll, you passively gain **+1 [Boost]**.'),
('weirdLeg', 'WEIRD LEG', 'This is not a troll leg. Any prosthetic leg can be modified with the optional WEIRD leg add on for **2 LUX**. Legs that are just bones, sword feet like a spy-maid, literal pogo springs, maybe you gave yourself a segmented metal naga tail and none of the other options cut it: this is where you get your weird cool leg fix. Choose a narratively sensible +1 to a stat of your choice, and apply a -2 penalty to SWASHBUCKLE, WORDPLAY, or LET’S STRIFE.'),
('biomechanicalEye', 'BIOMECHANICAL EYE', '**DESTITUTE, POOR, DECENT, AVERAGE: 1 LUX**; Yessir, that is an eye! Seems like it all checks out to me. It has the **[Mechanical]** tag. Choose 2 abilities from the list below.\r\n\r\n**WELL OFF, RICH, ULTRARICH: 2 LUX**; The highest in high tech [Mechanical] prosthetic eyewear, this is almost as much a fashion accessory and critical tool for daily life as it is a replacement for your fifth sense. Choose 3 abilities from the list below:\r\n\r\n> **INFRARED**: Inbuilt infrared vision! These probably look red and creepy, but hey, your rolls to spot **[Hidden]** trolls **[Tier Up]**.\r\n\r\n> **DARKVISION**: You are immune to the **[Blinded]** status unless your eyes are disabled. \r\n\r\n> **COLOR CHANGING**: The blood vessels are tiny and the iris changes color subtly at will, allowing you to hide your blood color more easily. Rolls to discover your blood color **[Tier Down]** unless you are **[Bloodied]**. \r\n\r\n> **NATURAL**: These are designed specially to look like the average eye of your caste. Attempts to **[Analyze]** you have a **-1 [Nerf]** due to your effortless ability to look natural and innocent. You cannot have this with UNSETTLING.\r\n\r\n> **UNSETTLING: These are designed specifically NOT to look natural. Your **+PLC** rolls have a **-2 [Nerf]**, but when you would apply **[Dread]** or **[Scared]** for the first time in an encounter, the Emotion is automatically **[Heightened]**. You cannot have this with NATURAL. \r\n\r\n> **SCANNER**: An inbuilt environmental scanner. It grants a **+1 [Buff]** to **[Analyze]** rolls.\r\n\r\n> **INFORMATION READOUT**: This gives you a readout right over your vision that identifies a person for you, and gives helpful tips for identifying unsavories. You get a +1 to identifying **[Eerie]** and **[Cullbait]** trolls, plus criminals, known rebels, anyone who has been on a watchlist, masked marauders, and anyone with a salacious Chittr history.\r\n\r\n> **TARGETING READOUT**: You get a new GOOD PROBLEM SLEUTHING option: TARGET LOCKED, which grants a **+2 [Buff]** to your next **[Strife]** against a single target.\r\n'),
('bloodpusher', 'BLOODPUSHER', '**ALL: 1 LUX** \r\nThe standard mechanical pumpbiscuit. If you are **[Unconscious]**, being the target of an attack that would deal **[Electric] [Energy]** Damage will bring you back to **1 HP** instead. CLEAR!!!!\r\n'),
('digestionBladder', 'DIGESTION BLADDER', '**ALL: 1 LUX**\r\nHere you go buddy, now you can eat all the grass and antifreeze you want. Go join that hotdog eating contest. Become a champion, you disgusting wastrel. A mechanical stomach is extra efficient! You gain **+1 HP** from eating **[Healing]** foods like the Prizeberry or Homecooked Meals.'),
('hemofiltrationSack', 'HEMOFILTRATION SACK', '**ALL: 1 LUX** \r\nNever have another hangover. **[Poison]** is automatically cleared from your system at a **[Recharge: 2]**.\r\n'),
('tongue', 'TONGUE', '**ALL: 1 LUX**\r\nOh, you silver tongued devil you. You get a **+1 [Buff]** to **[Manipulate]**. Don’t think about it too hard.'),
('windbags', 'WINDBAGS', '**ALL: 1 LUX**\r\nBe the blowhard you were always meant to be. You gain an extra round of safety from fire, smoke, and various other inhalation-based **[Hazards]** like DROWNING.'),
('hearingAids', 'HEARING AIDS', '**ALL: 1 LUX**\r\nFuck dude, you hear so good now. You have a **+1** to finding **[Hidden]** trolls by sound alone.\r\n'),
('posturePole', 'POSTURE POLE', '**ALL: 1 LUX**\r\nYou’ve already committed, so why not toss a literal spine of steel in there? You gain an unremovable **+1 [Physical] [Resistance]** at the cost of a **-1 [Nerf]** to GRA and taking **+1 damage** from attacks with **[Electric]** and **[Laser] [Energy]** types.'),
('reinforcedBones', 'REINFORCED BONES', '**ALL: 1 LUX**\r\nA light titanium rod is laid along your major support bones. Just like… the big ones, you know? You’re not Wolverine. You gain **1 [Boost]** from using a **[Reaction]**.');
INSERT INTO `spaceship` (`key`, `title`, `cost`, `text`) VALUES
('behemoth', 'BEHEMOTH', 52, '14 HP\r\nCarries as many people as you damn well please, 44 **SUPPLIES** and 12 **UPGRADE SLOTS**.'),
('camouflageSystem', 'CAMOUFLAGE SYSTEM', 8, '\r\nSurprisingly, you don’t really wanna get robbed by space pirates. Or maybe you’re a space pirate and want to jump people like a bastard. No matter which camp you slot into, this state of the art camouflage system has just what you’re looking for! When you engage in ship combat, your ship automatically starts **[Hidden]**. Your **NAVIGATE** rolls to go **[Hidden]** or **ABSCOND** are **[Tiered Up]**, even to a **MAX**.'),
('caravan', 'CARAVAN CLASS', 0, 'Talent: **MAINTAIN**\r\nYou are, without a doubt, the most robust class of ship; you can shrug off a huge amount of damage, either to your own detriment or the poor helmsman. Your hull plating is denser, toughened by psionics, or perhaps you just know something about quickly plugging up a hole in the wall.'),
('crew', 'CREW', 0, 'If you don’t have enough pals to go around talent-wise, you can expend **SUPPLIES** or cash to obtain an additional NPC crewmember. The base cost for hiring an NPC is 4 **SUPPLIES** / 8 **LUX** / **Treasure IV** for Level 1 NPCs. Level 2 NPCs cost double the price and Level 3 NPCs cost triple, as hired help gets more pricey with how snooty they are.\r\n\r\nWhen these NPCs are part of your crew, you can benefit from their **[Talents]** and stats during spaceflight, and even summon them to fight alongside you in a face-to-face battle. If you roll a **MIN** on **STARSTEER** or your ship health hits 0, you lose half your hired NPCS rounded up. When they die, they’re gone for good, and you’ll have to hire new ones. That sucks!'),
('crewQuarters', 'CREW QUARTERS', 8, '\r\nWith a few exceptions, spaceships are meant to be your hive away from hive! Space can get lonely… So why not make sure you can bring as many crewmates as possible! You may carry +3 people on your ship per **CREW QUARTERS** and have up to 3 **CREW QUARTERS** on your ship.'),
('destroyer', 'DESTROYER CLASS', 0, 'Talent: **AGGRIEVE**\r\nKlaxons! Red lights flashing! Any ship worth its salt knows the silhouette of this type alone. A menacing Destroyer class is nothing but a force to be reckoned with.'),
('exploration', 'EXPLORATION CLASS', 0, 'Talent: **NAVIGATE**\r\nThe final frontier. You often find yourself marking off the second star to the left and going on till morning. Even without the power of a helmsman or other powerful stardrive, you find yourself outmaneuvering anyone you encounter.'),
('extraShields', 'EXTRA SHIELDS', 0, 'If you haven’t noticed, space is like, super fucking deadly. Keep your ship safer with the best environmental hazard protection systems money can buy! When you buy this upgrade, choose a damage type. Your ship then gains 1 **[Resistance]** to that form of damage. This **[Resistance]** only applies to the ship itself and not the shields. Be warned - once these shields are depleted in an encounter, they won’t be able to reactivate for the rest of that encounter. \r\n\r\n> **BASIC SHIELD; 8 LUX, 2 HP:** Yep, that’s your standard shield! Nothing too special about it. Once depleted, it requires 1 **SUPPLIES** to fix.\r\n> **ADVANCED SHIELD; 24 LUX, 4 HP**: A bit fancier than normal, and with even sturdier hard-light reflection. Once depleted, it requires 3 **SUPPLIES** to fix.\r\n> **ULTRA SHIELD; 48 LUX, 6 HP:** Hot damn! This baby comes with high-quality damage absorbing, top-of-the-line radiation refraction, and looks cool as hell to boot! Once depleted, it requires 5 **SUPPLIES** to fix.'),
('gateway', 'GATEWAY DRIVE', 6, '**[Crew Requirement: None]**\r\nAw, what’s wrong? You don’t have your own FTL technology? That’s okay! Public transport exists in space, too! Your ship may only use FTL travel in locations with Gates in place. Gates are not bi-directional or remarkably accurate in where they fling you, but hey, they’re there! When you roll **STARSTEER** your **OK** rolls **[Tier Up]** to a **GOOD** one, as the gates are reliable at ensuring you\'re always moving forward. However, it\'s unreliable in ensuring you get there in one piece. Your **BAD** rolls [Tier Down] into a **MIN**, as you get rocketed to Gog knows where.'),
('guidanceSystem', 'GUIDANCE SYSTEM', 8, 'Listen, you don’t got all day here! …Or night…? You can’t really tell what time it is in space. Doesn’t matter. The point is you’re BUSY and don’t have time to spend your **SPACETIME** flying a ship! So you let your ship move on its own! Your ship may roll **STARSTEER** in your stead so you don’t use up your **[Downtime]** roll. This is however a flat 2d8 roll before any other bonuses you may get from your ship.'),
('helmingRoom', 'HELMING ROOM', 8, 'This is the place where Helmsman goldbloods get hooked up so they can have the very life sucked out of them… Whenever the ship takes damage, a Helmsman can overclock themselves, pouring out twice the psionic energy to keep the ship going. They can take the incoming damage from **STARSTEER** or **AGGRIEVE** onto themselves, reducing the ship’s damage to a minimum of 1. If a Helmsman is brought to 0 **HP** in this way, they are burnt out. They either die or, if they are lucky, simply expend their psionic capacity and gain the **VOIDROT [Template]**.'),
('helmskeep', 'HELMSKEEP', 6, '**[Crew Requirement: Battery Gold]**\r\nYou have a helmsman! That\'s so poggers! This is arguably the best drive you can get within a ship. All it really costs is the infinite suffering of one goldblood, for all of eternity! (You may even name them, to be nice, if you want.) A Helmsman crew member may roll **STARSTEER** with **+IMG** instead of **+HUB** as being hooked up to the ship also allows them to steer it. Due to being powered by the immense energy of a goldblood, all your **STARSTEER** rolls **[Tier Up]** even to a **MAX**. '),
('large', 'LARGE', 40, '12 HP\r\nCarries 9 people, 32 **SUPPLIES** and 8 **UPGRADE SLOTS**.'),
('limelight', 'LIMELIGHT DRIVE', 6, '**[Crew Requirement: Lime]**\r\nIf you\'re a lime and your metapowers are strong enough, you can just will an entire ship to blink someplace else! It also turns out that this isn’t very easy or healthy to do at all! Who knew? You get a **GREAT** result for **STARSTEER** without the need to roll for anything. After you use this drive, any Lime crewmembers on board must spend 1d4 days of **SPACETIME** doing nothing but recovering before the drive can be used again.'),
('mechanicRoom', 'MECHANIC ROOM', 8, 'Hot engines, welding tools, and an ungogly amount of oil. Welcome to the **MECHANIC ROOM** my friend! This is where Shoveliers and Technicaneers work their magic to keep the ship running! When you use **SUPPLIES** to heal your ship, your craft heals an additional +1 HP.'),
('medium', 'MEDIUM', 32, '10 HP\r\nCarries 5 people, 24 **SUPPLIES** and 4 **UPGRADE SLOTS**.'),
('quasar', 'QUASAR DRIVE', 6, '**[Crew Requirement: Astrosorceror]**\r\nFly a ship… with your HANDS? Tch! What kind of Plutonian flies a vessel like that!? No, you’re a student of the stars and master of all things astral. Watch in awe as you steer this hunk of metal with MAGIC! HUZZAH! An Astrosorcerer crew member may roll **STARSTEER** with **+IMG** instead of **+HUB**, as they let the magic of those not-so-distant stars guide the way.'),
('research', 'RESEARCH CLASS', 0, 'Talent: **OUTSMART**\r\nYour sensors are second-to-none- you’re a science vessel through and through, searching for strange new worlds to settle upon or perhaps charting the endless reaches of the galaxy.'),
('skimwraith', 'SKIMWRAITH DRIVE', 6, '**[Crew Requirement: Cthonomancer]**\r\nYour ship takes a roundabout route to different places in the galaxy - namely, it rips a hole to the Furthest Ring, then from the Furthest Ring to wherever you wanna go. You get a **GREAT** result for **STARSTEER** without the need to roll for anything. On top of giving this ship the **[Eerie]** tag, every time you travel with this ship, roll 1d8. On a 1-4, you are VISITED BY ENTITIES, who are not too happy about you driving your ship through their turf! Your ship takes 3 damage as punishment.'),
('small', 'SMALL', 8, '8 HP\r\nCarries 3 people, 12 **SUPPLIES** and 2 **UPGRADE SLOTS**.'),
('spaceBender', 'SPACE-BENDER DRIVE', 6, '**[Crew Requirement: None]**\r\nHuh. As it turns out, with the right exotic materials, you can compress space in front of your ship and expand it behind you, so it’s compelled to propel you forward while only slightly breaking the laws of physics. But remember, there\'s no such thing as a free lunch. While this is still underpowered compared to a regular Helmsman, you can travel to any destination without rolling **STARSTEER** at the cost of taking 4 **[Unblockable]** damage.'),
('superDriveFromHell', 'SUPER DRIVE FROM HELL', 6, '**[Crew Requirement: ~~DERANGED MANIAC~~ None]**\r\n[Crew Requirement: DERANGED MANIAC None]\r\nWhy is this thing glowing a bright green…? Why does it sound more like a chainsaw than anything that should be allowed on a ship…? Why does it feel like your skin is MELTING when you stand near it…? WHO CARES! YEEHAW! Roll a 1d2. If you roll a 2, you immediately blast off to your destination. No several days of travel needed! On a 1, you don’t even lift off. Your ship blows up, either losing a UPGRADE or taking 10 **[Unblockable]** damage. Oops...'),
('supplyRoom', 'SUPPLY ROOM', 8, 'It’s totally different from a **STORAGEPIT**. Look, you want your greasy toolkits right next to your limited edition event-exclusive Hey There Purrbeast emotion-restoring plushie? Of course you don’t. That’s what this room is for! You can store up to 12 **SUPPLIES** in each **SUPPLY ROOM**, and have up to 3 **SUPPLY ROOMS** on your ship.'),
('tiny', 'TINY', 6, '4 HP\r\nCarries 1 person, 6 **SUPPLIES** and 1 **UPGRADE SLOT**.'),
('transportation', 'TRANSPORTATION CLASS', 0, 'Talent: **STARSTEER**\r\nAh, a traditionalist. Your ship is exceptionally talented in simply making things go, and no matter how far away you are, you will be getting from Point A to Point B- through sheer willpower alone if need be.'),
('weaponSystems', 'WEAPON SYSTEMS', 8, 'Standard ships have built-in blasters that do the job just fine in a pinch. However, some trolls have bigger dreams for what their ships can do - like having flamethrowers, shooting raw JPEGs, or having even bigger guns! You can add up to three Abstrata which deal **[Energy]** damage to this system; each is on [Recharge: 2]** in a combat encounter. Adding multiple of the same kind reduces the **[Recharge]** by 1 to a minimum of 0 (ex. If you buy **BLAZEKIND** three times, you can use it every round).');
INSERT INTO `strife` (`ID`, `name`, `narrative_thread_ID`, `rolls_thread_ID`, `clouder`, `players`) VALUES
('3c610c80', 'Strife #`3c610c80`', 1252066933004566578, 1252066830852296734, 315220045141770241, '308760900016537610 214817932331450368'),
('3c612786', 'Strife #`3c612786`', NULL, NULL, 315220045141770241, ' 308760900016537610'),
('3c61346e', 'Strife #`3c61346e`', NULL, NULL, 315220045141770241, ' 308760900016537610'),
('3c614129', 'Strife #`3c614129`', NULL, NULL, 315220045141770241, ' 308760900016537610'),
('3c614f01', 'Strife #`3c614f01`', NULL, NULL, 315220045141770241, ' 308760900016537610'),
('47695d73', 'Beep Cheep', NULL, 1257055570964250726, 315220045141770241, '308760900016537610'),
('6a5402d6', 'testStrife', NULL, NULL, 315220045141770241, ' 308760900016537610'),
('6a547d85', 'testStrife', NULL, NULL, 315220045141770241, ' 308760900016537610'),
('deadbeef', 'Bot-Owned Strife', NULL, 1252125808038776955, 815669451658887209, ' 308760900016537610'),
('e147e21d', 'testStrife', NULL, NULL, 315220045141770241, NULL);
INSERT INTO `sylladex` (`key`, `title`, `wealth`, `tags`, `text`) VALUES
('aBandage', 'A BANDAGE', 'DESTITUTE', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 2**\r\nJust one! That’s all you need, or more likely, all you found while rummaging through an abandoned hive.  Slap this on someone to **[Heal] 1 HP**.'),
('ahSorrow', 'AH, SORROW', 'UNUSUAL AND RARE', '[Active Item][Consumable][Rare]\r\n', '**VP 3**\r\nThis thick, mucous gravy looks more like oil than food… probably due to the fact that it\'s made of Ambient Grimdarks! When you coat your weapon with AH, SORROW, you can choose to do **1 less damage** to an opponent to give them the **[Dread]** condition. Or if you trick someone into eating it, it does the same. Ah… sorrow. '),
('ancestralRelic', 'ANCESTRAL RELIC', 'UNUSUAL AND RARE', '[Active Item][Rare][Equipment]\r\n', '**VP 3**\r\nHuh? No way, is this… this item belonged to your Ancestor! Maybe it\'s some ancient necklace, or a signet ring, or even a missing hand or something. How\'d it get down here on Alternia, you must wonder… if you have access to **[Advanced] [Class]** moves, you gain access to a Class Move from another Class than your own that uses your own **[Aspect]**. Your Ancestor was very similar to you… but they probably had a lot of differences too. '),
('arms', 'ARMS', 'AVERAGE', '[Passive Item]\r\n', '**VP 1**\r\nYou already GOT arms, shit for brains! Ah, but the importance of a fake pair of arms cannot be overstated. Who knows what kind of situation you might need arms for! Whenever someone tries to use the YOINK Shennanigans option, they automatically retrieve arms instead. '),
('batterybug', 'BATTERYBUG', 'DECENT', '[Active Item]\r\n', '**VP 2**\r\nThis green, cuboid-looking caterpillar thing looks a lot like a certain lightning-grub type Fiduspawn. It is highly sought after by psions, who can use it to clear their mind of residual rot. Holding it to your head as a **[Psionic]** troll gives a pleasing numbness, making them **[Numb]** for **2 turns**. It does, however, leave you a little dazzled. Trolls gain **2 [Drag]** every time they use a **[Psionic]** move for the first encounter they have after using a Batterybug.'),
('bubbleHelmet', 'BUBBLE HELMET', 'AVERAGE', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 1**\r\nAdventure calls! You’re not really the seadwelling type, but hey, if you need to go underwater, you need one of these to avoid the DROWNING **[Affliction]**. Hope you know how to swim!\r\n'),
('cleverDisguise', 'CLEVER DISGUISE', 'WELL OFF', '[Active Item]\r\n', '**VP 2**\r\nSometimes, you need to inconspicuously pretend to be someone you’re not. Thankfully, you have this EXCELLENT fucking disguise kit. A sweet Beaglepuss, a Pipe and a Bowler hat- hoho! Nobody shall know it’s you! Use it to prank your friends, or get away in a sticky situation! When you want to trick someone about your appearance, roll **+PLC**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: YO THAT’S THE FUCKING GUY! Your target knows it’s you, and you’re so shocked that they saw right through you that you’re **[Stunned]** for a moment.\r\n\r\n**BAD**: Yeah, this isn’t fooling anyone. At all. The target sees through your disguise.\r\n\r\n**OK**: HmmmMMMmmm. The target strokes their chin and squints at you. Reroll this move, and see if your costume holds up to further inspection.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: It works! Your target notices you, but doesn’t recognize you. \r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Your target is particularly fooled by your sweet disguise; they don’t even notice you! You are **[Hidden]**.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: THE ULTIMATE DISGUISE! You get away scott free! Even if you attack, your target doesn’t realize who you are, and you can return to being **[Hidden]** as an action. You can do this until they spot you with an **[Analyze]** roll.'),
('crackedBubbleHelmet', 'CRACKED BUBBLE HELMET', 'DECENT', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 1**\r\nAw jeez… is this safe to wear..? You don’t really know. All you know is you need to be underwater for some reason, and this is the only way to avoid the DROWNING **[Affliction]**, so… bottoms up..?!'),
('cullbaitBGone', 'CULLBAIT-B-GONE', 'DECENT', '[Passive Item][Equipment]\r\n', '**3 VP**\r\nUnlike the similarly named brand of murder weapons, this brand of item is produced in the troll underground. Whether it\'s binders to keep your wings flat and out of sight, bloodbags hidden in select areas of your clothes where you might be stabbed or simply painting over your weirdly discolored horns, with this VASTLY overpriced equipment you can hide your hideous mutations much better than usual. You are able to pass as a normal, everyday troll while this item is equipped thanks to a handy selection of numerous illegal as fuck items. Blood cartridges to trick the bloodtesters, fake papers that confirm you were and always have been a bronze troll, contact lenses, body heat masking clothes, an emergency pair of shears for your wings. Bribe money. If you play it cool, you\'ll be fiiine and have a **-1 [Nerf]** to any attempts to discern something is... illegal about you. When you fail to act cool and are outed as a **[Cullbait]** troll while equipped with this item, you have two rounds to solve the situation before your secret comes out and whatever outed you applies in full; whether its your wings sprouting forth, an investigative troll putting the PROBLEM SLEUTHING pieces together or your pink blood seeping through the faux-rust. This is a **[One-Off]** effect, and deals **1 [Psychic] Damage** to the item every time it happens. This does not apply when you reveal yourself.\r\n'),
('cursedAmulet', 'CURSED AMULET', 'UNUSUAL AND RARE', '[Active Item][Rare][Equipment][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 3**\r\nSomething truly wicked lives inside this amulet… so watch out! The first time you would be exposed to an **[Affliction]** while wearing this **[Amulet]**, if you succeed on your roll against Stage 0 of the **[Affliction]**, you absorb it into the amulet. When you’re next hit by a **MAX** roll that physically touches you, the **[Amulet]** hisses, and releases the **[Affliction]** into the air, which then seeks out the person who hurt you. Their rolls against the **[Affliction]** are **[Inept]**. '),
('doomsdayDevice', 'DOOMSDAY DEVICE', 'ULTRARICH', '[Active Item]\r\n', '**VP 4**\r\nMuahahaha… after all this time… finally. The perfect weapon. You have purchased the most devastating weapon known to Alternia: a Doomsday Device. This box-shaped device has two tesla coils zapping energy into one another, a few meters and wires, and a big, red button that leads to a giant bomb (at least it\'s not a nuke!). Detonation immediately does **20 [Unblockable] [Laser] [Somatic]** damage to everyone present, topples buildings, ruins held items, destroys scuttlebuggies— you name it. The only problem is you have to hold it to activate it, and there’s no countdown or anything, so it just kinda… goes off with you in the radius (about 200 ft). Also, if it’s destroyed or hit with a **MAX [Strife]** roll, it automatically detonates... or you could detonate it yourself? Please don\'t detonate it yourself. A minor oversight in the design process, perhaps— but it still acts as an EXCELLENT bargaining chip. When you threaten to blow everyone to kingdom come if they don’t do what you say, roll **+HUB**.\r\n\r\n**MIN**: YOU ACCIDENTALLY PRESS THE BUTTON\r\n\r\n**BAD**: You try to intentionally press the button, but it doesn’t work. Fucking— shit! Your threat is flat, and you can’t try to bluff (or try to blow everyone up) again for the rest of the thread.\r\n\r\n**OK**: Negotiations are at a stalemate. You consider activating the weapon.\r\n\r\n**GOOD**: Your opponent realizes you mean business, and anxiously complies with one request. Further requests require further convincing.\r\n\r\n**GREAT**: Oh, oh god, please don’t blow me and everyone up! You can make up to 3 requests that they need to comply with before you need to try again.\r\n\r\n**MAX**: You convince the opponent to do EXACTLY what you say. As long as you have your bomb on you and they\'re in the blast radius, they have to listen to you.\r\n'),
('eastAlternianAnimationHeadband', 'EAST ALTERNIAN ANIMATION HEADBAND', 'DECENT', '[Passive Item][Equipment][Weeb]\r\n', '**VP 2**\r\nA strip of fabric with a metal plate on it, etched with the symbol of mighty ninja power. When you put this on you become **[Inspired]** for **2 turns**, and get a +3 Buff to LET’S STRIFE rolls, but you automatically fail all **[Manipulation]** rolls against anyone who isn’t also wearing one of these ultra cool babies. If you get a **BAD** or **MIN** while wearing this item, you become **[Embarrassed]** or [Humiliated]. You can’t take it off without becoming **[Embarrassed]**, either.'),
('essentialOil', 'ESSENTIAL OIL', 'WELL OFF', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**3 VP** (Garbage Snake Oil) or **6 VP** (Swanky Ultra Purified Troll Tibetan Distillation)\r\nYay, alternative Alternian medicine! Spraying these in the air won\'t heal you, and consuming them will in fact **[Poison]** you, but the power of the placebo effect will make you feel **[Hopeful]** for **3 rounds** if you use them. Using these in the presence of a lusus immediately ends the ALTRICIALIZE, or deals **2 [Somatic] Damage** if it is a wild monster. There is no difference in effect between the snake oil and the whole foods brand, and both have **3 HP**. You are spending more on a scam.'),
('everlitCandle', 'EVERLIT CANDLE', 'UNUSUAL AND RARE', 'EVERLIT CANDLE\r\n', '**VP 2 **\r\nThese candles are left by the followers of the Decompositionism at their resting places, to aid spirits and the unliving to move on. The flame has always been a sign of quiet rebellion, not least because it never refused to cease burning all four colors of the lowborn, even as the Empire attempted to erase the fourth. All **[Eerie]** trolls gain **+3 [Boost]** when this ever burning candle is lit. As a **[Reaction]** they may make an **[Unblockable] [Strife]** roll against the Everlit Candle to immediately extinguish it and take **3 [Holy] [Psychic]** Damage. Otherwise, any combat encounter presently going on ends. You cannot receive this item except through moves which mention it. Cthonomancers are unaffected by the Everlit Candle. They’re too edgy for religion.'),
('faultyWiring', 'FAULTY WIRING', 'POOR', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**Poor: VP 3**\r\nWow! That— this is EXTREMELY dangerous? You just have a load of wires in your pocket? What the fuck, are some of these live wires? How? They\'re not even plugged in! YOU ATTACHED A BATTERYGRUB TO THEM? WHY! This exceptionally hazardous mix of items are waiting to burst with electricity. When you throw it at an opponent with a vulnerability to **[Energy]** damage, that **[Energy]** weakness turns to **[Electric]** for **2 turns**. But watch out! While in your Dex, you **[Tier Up] [Electric]** attacks aimed at you, even to a **MAX**!\r\n'),
('faygo', 'FAYGO', 'RICH', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 3**\r\nWHOOP WHOOP. It\'s the Clurch\'s advertisement for the LATEST NEW FLAVOR OF FAYGO POP FROM FAYGO BEVERAGES HEADQUARTERED PLANETSIDE IN TROLL DETROIT MALICIOUSGAN. Over fifty flavors, and that\'s just the ones available to normies that don\'t wear face paint, sib. There\'s a few thousand more in the clown vaults under every clown church. Drinking faygo is an important tenet of the Mirthful faith, and... it\'s pretty okay for everyone else. It\'s like. Not bad. It\'s just soda. The Empire prefers you buy the Empress\'s TAB so you don\'t fund the Clurch, but eh. You can drink this overly sugary soda to remove **[Tired]** and gain **1 [Boost]**. If you\'re a practicing clown however, you instead gain **3 [Boost]** and a **+3 [Buff]** to your next **[Purple]** move\'s roll.'),
('flashlight', 'FLASHLIGHT', 'EARTH', '[Active Item]\r\n', '**VP 2**\r\nTrolls can see in the dark… but you can’t! Thankfully, your trusty flashlight will help you see the way… and dazzle the nocturnal creatures of Alternia too! Whenever you have this item equipped, trolls or monsters that are **[Blinded]** are **[Blinded]** for an extra turn. Flash flash flash flash!'),
('flipPhone', 'FLIP PHONE', 'EARTH', '[Active Item]\r\n', '**VP 2**\r\nThese things are ALL the rage. You don’t know why trolls insist on using their weird computer “phones”. After all, these phones… FLIP open! Lemme just… lemme quickly text… (sound of mashing the 1 button three times to get the letter C). On your Flip Phone, moves that affect **[Tech]** don’t affect you (it barely counts as tech), and the CIS can’t monitor your private conversations. Also, you can sit down and play SNAKE as a **[Lengthy]** action to become **[Serene]**. Ah… old mobile phone games… '),
('funjunk', 'FUNJUNK', 'AVERAGE', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 2**\r\nTeen drinking is very very bad! I\'m serious! You\'ll go to hell! This isn\'t a mechanic, but if I were your Clouder and you consumed this, I\'d say any death you have would be JUST. Anyway, Funjunk is a blanket term for loads of different sci-fi intoxicants, like 200% sugar deserts or weird beverages or stuff. Consuming this gives you the INEBRIATED [Affliction]. You can willingly choose to make yourself [Inept] against rolls for this [Affliction].\r\n\r\n> **CATNIP**: A mysterious plant that is particularly popular among Olive trolls and… Trans Trolls? Am I reading this right? Oh, high doses are used in HRT, to make people catgirls or catboys, got it. Anyway, when you take a puff of this plant, it makes you extremely cuddly and cutesy. STAGE 1 and 2 of INEBRIATION happen after **2 rounds** each; it makes you **[Numb]** and then **[Dissociating]** because heheheheh, u//m//u brain kitty heheheh. On STAGE 3, you start **[Giggling]** too, but you lose all **[Inepts]**. On STAGE 4, watch out, kitty effects can be permanent, making you more feline when you sober up. If you are not Olive, roll 1d8; on an 8, you retain feline personality quirks. Doing this again with feline quirks (or if you were already Olive) successfully and totally transitions you to a different gender. You go, catgirl.\r\n\r\n> **CEREBROBUBBLES**: This shit is so fucking good at helping you with your unmedicated mental shit, and also, letting you levitate slightly. STAGE 1 and 2 of INEBRIATION happen after **2 rounds** each; this makes you **[Focused]** and then **[Hyperfocused]**. On STAGE 2, your head glows a little and you speak in a monotone and float a foot off the floor; you gain the **[Cullbait]** tag because frankly, that\'s horrifying, and very distressing to see. \r\n\r\n> **OCTAHEDRONIC GATEU**: This insanely good cake is illegal in most civilized solar systems for its unbelievably high sugar count and worryingly high nitrous oxide levels. Consuming multiple cakes forces you to the next stage of INEBRIATION. It makes you **[Hopeful]** and then **[Inspired]**. On STAGE 2, you also start **[Laughing]** uncontrollably! Good gracious! \r\n'),
('greatBook', 'GREAT BOOK', 'EARTH', '[Active Item]\r\n', '**VP 2**\r\nLet’s see here… ah yes! When you read through this book to prepare yourself, you can make a PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll as a **[Lengthy]** action. This roll is then **[Tiered Up]**, even to a **MAX** roll. '),
('hauntedPalmhusk', 'HAUNTED PALMHUSK', 'UNUSUAL AND RARE', '[Active Item][Rare]\r\n', '**VP 1**\r\nIs it haunted by The Phantom Of Twelfth Perigee’s Eve Yet To Come?! Probably not, it seems to be haunted by an actual poltergeist. Either way, when you go online with this thing, your private text conversations can’t be monitored… though you are exposed to the HAUNTING **[Affliction]** after you use it. If you succeed on your roll against the item, everything’s all good. If you fail, the object becomes useless, and also a ghost is haunting you.'),
('hazardGear', 'HAZARD GEAR', 'WELL OFF', '[Passive Item][Equipment]\r\n', 'Whether it’s an umbrella, a perilous amount of sunscreen, or a scuba kit, you’re ready for the worst! Choose one **[Hazard]** from the list below; you are immune to this **[Hazard]**.\r\n> DAYTIME\r\n> FIRE!\r\n> RAINSTORM\r\n> BEE SWARM\r\n> ROCKS FALL\r\n> SNOWSTORM\r\n'),
('healingStuff', 'HEALING STUFF', 'POOR', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 2**\r\nYup… yup… just wrap the wounds up, don’t even worry about it… cover up that broken leg with a nice, homemade bandaid… look at you! Good as new. When you use this item, you **[Heal] 1 HP**. Not everyone can afford a nice, fancy medicalizer, after all… '),
('highbloodbag', 'HIGHBLOODBAG', 'RICH', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', 'Poor: **VP 1**\r\nYou never know when you might need some blood! Maybe it’s to disguise a crime scene. Maybe it’s to paint a beautiful picture. Maybe it’s to slurp up and satisfy the Bloodhysteria of a Rainbow Drinker. You can also use it to make someone\'s **[Analyze]** rolls **[Inept]** towards a crime scene you’ve interfered in. This bag is… oh fuck me, it’s all sorts of purples and blues. Fuck fuck fuck, you’re so dead, fuck. It’s DEFINITELY going to look bad for you if you get splattered with this, in the eyes of the law! Splooging someone with it makes them feel **[Dread]** for **2 turns**.'),
('highQualityFunjunk', 'HIGH QUALITY FUNJUNK', 'RICH', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', 'VP 2\r\nTeen drinking is very very bad! I\'m serious! You\'ll go to hell! This isn\'t a mechanic, but if I were your Clouder and you consumed this, I\'d say any death you have would be JUST. Anyway, Funjunk is a blanket term for loads of different sci-fi intoxicants, like 200% sugar deserts or weird beverages or stuff. Consuming this gives you the INEBRIATED **[Affliction]**. You can willingly choose to make yourself **[Inept]** against rolls for this **[Affliction]**.\r\n\r\n> **CATNIP**: A mysterious plant that is particularly popular among Olive trolls and… Trans Trolls? Am I reading this right? Oh, high doses are used in HRT, to make people catgirls or catboys, got it. Anyway, when you take a puff of this plant, it makes you extremely cuddly and cutesy. STAGE 1 and 2 of INEBRIATION happen after **2 rounds** each; it makes you [Numb] and then **[Dissociating]** because heheheheh, u//m//u brain kitty heheheh. On STAGE 3, you start **[Giggling]** too, but you lose all **[Inepts]**. On STAGE 4, watch out, kitty effects can be permanent, making you more feline when you sober up. If you are not Olive, roll 1d8; on an 8, you retain feline personality quirks. Doing this again with feline quirks (or if you were already Olive) successfully and totally transitions you to a different gender. You go, catgirl.\r\n\r\n> **SOPOR**: Miracles… this stuff is usually used for bedding and recupracoons, but some people (particularly Clowns) use it to eat. STAGE 1 and 2 of INEBRIATION happen after **2 rounds each**; it makes you **[Peaceful]** and then **[Serene]**. On STAGE 3, you become **[Godawful]** at **[Mental]** rolls, but your **[Serenity]** cannot be dispelled.\r\n\r\n> **POTIONS**: Can you really handle these strong potions? These items give you mystical powers. Consuming multiple potions forces you to the next stage of INEBRIATION. It makes you **[Talented]** at **[Magic]** rolls and then **[Tiered Up]** at **[Magic]** rolls. On STAGE 2, you become **[Dumbfounded]** as your brain is overwhelmed by MAGIC.\r\n'),
('imperialTiara', 'IMPERIAL TIARA', 'ULTRARICH', '[Passive Item][Equipment]\r\n', '**VP 3**\r\nHey, you like. You know the Heiress? You like, yeah. She lent you this. The tiara? Yeah. You\'re one of *those* people. Flex. Not just on the poors, but on the lesser richies that don\'t have an audience with the Heiress. Tiaras are a motif of Alternian royalty, and those who wear them are typically those either working for or on behalf of the throne. Or are wealthy enough to just buy the privilege! Corruption works! Drones will not target you while you are wearing the Imperial Tiara unless you do something truly stupid in front of them; including DRONE STRIKE **[Hazards]**! Additionally, the display of authority you have is more than enough to silence questions. As a **[One-Off]**, the first time an ally is exposed as **[Eerie]** or **[Cullbait]** you can shove that back under the cupe; preventing any legal consequences as you direct the drones to... Look away! This is Empire business, those wings.'),
('literalGarbage', 'LITERAL GARBAGE', 'DESTITUTE', '[Active Item]\r\n', 'VP 1\r\nWhat it says on the tin. Why do you even have this? When someone tries to YOINK an item from your Sylladex, they must roll 1d8. On an odd number, they pull out… a handful of garbage. They become **[Revolted]** for **2 turns**. Yuck!'),
('lostBackpack', 'LOST BACKPACK', 'UNUSUAL AND RARE', '[Passive Item][Rare]\r\n', '**VP 4**\r\nWhoa… this is some loot left behind by an adventurer from aeons ago. That’s crazy! Who knows what’s inside. It could be something great! It could be something shit. Whatever it is, it’s gonna take up 4 VP, so… hopefully it’s good! When you open this ancient satchel, roll 2d8. On the first dice, a 1 gives you a Destitute Item, a 2 gives you a Poor one, a 3 gives you a Decent item, a 4 gives you an Average item, a 5 gives you a Well-Off item, a 6 gives you a Rich item, a 7 gives you an Ultrarich item, and an 8 makes you reroll twice. On the second dice, reroll on a 7 or an 8, but otherwise use the dice roll to pick the item listed alphabetically (for example, rolling a 3 picks the third item of that wealth level alphabetically).'),
('lowbloodbag', 'LOWBLOODBAG', 'POOR', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**Poor: VP 1**\r\nYou never know when you might need some blood! Maybe it’s to disguise a crime scene. Maybe it’s to paint a beautiful picture. Maybe it’s to slurp up and satisfy the Bloodhysteria of a Rainbow Drinker. You can also use it to make someone\'s **[Analyze]** rolls **[Inept]** towards a crime scene you’ve interfered in. This particular bag is full of nice, warm colours like rusts or golds. This blood is not treated very well by whoever gathered it, which makes it kinda rank. Why not fucking, squirt them at someone to make them **[Disgusted]** for **two rounds**! It’ll gross ‘em out, guaranteed!'),
('lowQualityFunjunk', 'LOW QUALITY FUNJUNK', 'POOR', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 2**\r\nTeen drinking is very very bad! I\'m serious! You\'ll go to hell! This isn\'t a mechanic, but if I were your Clouder and you consumed this, I\'d say any death you have would be JUST. Anyway, Funjunk is a blanket term for loads of different sci-fi intoxicants, like 200% sugar deserts or weird beverages or stuff. Consuming this gives you the INEBRIATED [Affliction]. You can willingly choose to make yourself [Inept] against rolls for this [Affliction].\r\n\r\n> CATNIP: A mysterious plant that is particularly popular among Olive trolls and… Trans Trolls? Am I reading this right? Oh, high doses are used in HRT, to make people catgirls or catboys, got it. Anyway, when you take a puff of this plant, it makes you extremely cuddly and cutesy. STAGE 1 and 2 of INEBRIATION happen after **2 rounds** each; it makes you **[Numb]** and then **[Dissociating]** because heheheheh, u//m//u brain kitty heheheh. On STAGE 3, you start **[Giggling]** too, but you lose all **[Inepts]**. On STAGE 4, watch out, kitty effects can be permanent, making you more feline when you sober up. If you are not Olive, roll 1d8; on an 8, you retain feline personality quirks. Doing this again with feline quirks (or if you were already Olive) successfully and totally transitions you to a different gender. You go, catgirl.\r\n\r\n> **DRUGS BRAND ENERGY DRINK**: A genius marketing ploy indeed, this energy drink is INSANELY full of sugar. Consuming multiple cans forces you to the next stage of INEBRIATION. It makes you **[Enthusiastic]** and then **[Passionate]**. On STAGE 2, you start trembling, and **[Manipulation]** rolls against you **[Tier Up]** as you find yourself easily suggested. \r\n\r\n> **MIND HONEY**: This elusive ichor made from specialized bees has an interesting and unusual effect on Gold Bloods. For most trolls, this makes you **[Enraged]** at STAGE 1 after a round and **[Out-Of-Control]** plus gives you **1 [Weakness]** to **[Psychic]** damage at STAGE 2 a round later. However, Gold trolls instead experience the PSIBURN affliction. Uh oh!\r\n'),
('lunchbox', 'LUNCHBOX', 'EARTH', '[Active Item]\r\n', '**VP 2**\r\nIt’s for storing delicious sweet treats inside of! When you’re tuckered out, use this to munch munch munch your way to feeling better. Eating stuff from this item **[Heals]** you **1 HP**. If a troll eats any of this food, they go BLEH and are **[Disgusted]** for **3 turns**.'),
('magicStaff', 'MAGIC STAFF', 'UNUSUAL AND RARE', '[Active Item][Rare][Equipment]\r\n', '**VP 3**\r\nYOOOO! THIS STAFF HAS MAGIC POWERS, DUDE! PCHEW, PCHEW! While wielding this staff in your hand, you can turn any **[Somatic] damage** dealing **[Strife]** roll you make into a **[Psychic]** damage dealing one. This gives your **[Strife]** roll the **[Magic]** tag instead of the **[Physical]** or **[Psionic]** tag. You can upgrade this MAGIC STAFF with ABSTRATA UPGRADES, if you so choose. '),
('makeshiftCaltrops', 'MAKESHIFT CALTROPS', 'POOR', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 1**\r\nThat’ll show them! You can throw this item down on the floor. If a **[Vehicle]** is within range, their next VEHICULATE roll is **[Inept]** and **[Tiered Down]**. Watch out!'),
('makeshiftJunkbuggy', 'MAKESHIFT JUNKBUGGY', 'DESTITUTE', '[Active Item]\r\n', '**VP 4**\r\nIt\'s like in Little Rascals (1994)! This buggy doesn\'t have an engine, but is frankly a miracle of teenage ingenuity; made of scrap, junk and otherwise scavenged together, it\'s like a gokart with caterpillar treads and sharp rusty edges. This acts as a 2 HORSEPOWER **[Vehicle]**; all VEHICULATE rolls inside it have a **-2 [Nerf]**. However, if you\'re in the same VROOM as someone with an actual vehicle, they also take this **-2 [Nerf]** as they stare in awe at your dumb little car. '),
('marbles', 'MARBLES', 'EARTH', '[Active Item]\r\n', '**VP 1**\r\nTruly the epitome of Earthy human recreational stuff! Flick em around, it’s great! When you throw these bad boys on the floor, all rolls that would knock people **[Floorbound]** are **[Tiered Up]**, and to get up from being **[Floorbound]**, people need to make a GOOD LET’S STRIFE roll. This does include you, unfortunately.'),
('medicalizer', 'MEDICALIZER', 'AVERAGE', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 2**\r\nNice! Just slot your wound into this advanced regeneration device, and you’ll heal your wound, good as new! And then when you get home… boom, charge it up and it’s ready to go again! Technology is incredible. When you activate this item, you **[Heal] 1 HP**.\r\n'),
('midbloodbag', 'MIDBLOODBAG', 'AVERAGE', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 1**\r\nYou never know when you might need some blood! Maybe it’s to disguise a crime scene. Maybe it’s to paint a beautiful picture. Maybe it’s to slurp up and satisfy the Bloodhysteria of a Rainbow Drinker. You can also use it to make someone\'s **[Analyze]** rolls **[Inept]** towards a crime scene you’ve interfered in. You’ve got a nice, green mix of blood in this one. Great for a scare! You can gunk someone with this blood to make them **[Stressed]** for **2 turns**.\r\n'),
('mysticalFocus', 'MYSTICAL FOCUS', 'UNUSUAL AND RARE', '[Active Item][Magic][Rare]\r\n', '**VP 5**\r\nA conduit for powers beyond! The exact nature of this item varies by its origins? Is it a holy artifact of your faith? A fragment of a fallen star for your signbound powers? A... bitchy horrorterror baby? Uh... probably not that one. Create your MYSTICAL FOCUS by choosing one from each of the below categories. A MYSTICAL FOCUS has a **[Recharge: 3]** per activation.\r\n\r\nORIGIN:\r\n> **Religious Icon**: It\'s an artifact of a religion or another! Its effects are always **[Holy]**. Cloistered Jades, Decompositionists, Paladin Indigos and Practicing Clowns additionally lose **2 [Drag]** the first time they summon this item in an Encounter, going into negative **[Drag]** if they have none.\r\n\r\n> **Astral Creation**: It\'s from the stars, void or some other ethereal body! Using this item gives you **+1 [Boost]** when you\'re below open sky; and **2 [Boost]** during the DAYTIME **[Hazard]** or **1 [Drag]** during the DIMMING STARS **[Hazard]**.\r\n\r\n> **Unnatural Entity**: It\'s...! Wrong! This thing was created in some kind of dark ritual or by something better left unspoken of. **[Eerie]** trolls have their **[Drag]** reduced by 1 every **2 Turns** while wielding this item.\r\n\r\n> **Artificially Made**: Magic is merely science we do not understand yet, and whoever created this got close to understanding it! This item counts as a **[Tech]** item and is unaffected by any anti-**[Magic]** defenses that would normally interfere with it. It\'s still **[Magic]** though.\r\n\r\nPOWER:\r\n> **Destruction**: This focus was meant to destroy! Choose two targets to receive **1 [Somatic]** and **1 [Psychic] Damage**. You must choose two targets, or else the spell fizzles out.\r\n\r\n> **Healing**: A focus for a cleric. **3 HP** is dispensed into the Encounter. At the start of each turn, everyone rolls a 1d8. On an even number, they **[Heal] 1 HP**. This repeats until all **3 HP** have been used. You roll now.\r\n\r\n> **Chaos**: Chaos! You can do anything! Change three of your stats around, then choose a target to allow to change theirs as well. Using this focus again changes all stats to normal.\r\n\r\n> **Support**: You\'re here to help! Choose two targets in the Encounter. They gain **-2 [Drag]**, going into negative **[Drag]** if they have none. You gain **2 [Drag]**.\r\n\r\n> **Prayer**: It\'s...! A tool for prayer? Cool! Only Religious Icon and Unnatural Entity Origins may take this Power. You become **[Numb]** for **1 turn** as you allow a being from beyond to assuage your fears; or just.. eat them or something, if they\'re Unnatural. You then become **[Focused]**.\r\n\r\n> **Apocalypse**: You\'re uh. Not gonna get the seven pieces of the complete artifact to bring about the end of existence. That\'s been done like four times and it keeps failing. You\'re not gonna be lucky number five. But hey! You can cause localized problems! Summon a **[Hazard]** that is not a DRONE STRIKE or DIMMING STARS. If you use this effect multiple times in an Encounter, new **[Hazards]** dispel any active from previous activations.\r\n\r\nUSAGE:\r\n> **Offering**: You offer something up and it activates the power within. Destroy an item in your possession to activate the MYSTICAL FOCUS. For every **3 VP** it cost, add 1 to any numerical value in the Power section; or gain **1 [Boost]** if it has none. There is no **[Recharge]**, but you cannot sacrifice multiple of the same item.\r\n\r\n> **Belief**: The power of! You simply roll **+IMG** as a **[Magic]** roll to use it! On a **GOOD** you activate it, on a **GREAT** you reduce the **[Recharge]** by 1, and on a **MAX** there is no **[Recharge]**. On an **OK** you waste the action, and on a **BAD** or **MIN** you activate the **[Recharge]** anyways.\r\n\r\n> **Energy**: It has a magic battery! The **[Recharge]** drops to 1 and you may spend an action to simply use it, but it costs 1 stat point of IMG as it uses your energy up! You cannot reduce your **+IMG** below 0 this way. You get the stats back at the end of the Encounter.\r\n\r\n> **Break It**: It\'s **[Consumable]**, my brother. You crack it apart, pull it open or splash what\'s within at your target. Whatever it is; you can\'t use it again this Encounter. Choose a second Power; you gain it now. You can spend an action to use the MYSTICAL FOCUS.'),
('oblongMeatProduct', 'OBLONG MEAT PRODUCT', 'DESTITUTE', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 1**\r\nOh boy, a delicious treat! When’s the last time you had a delicious treat? You better savour it… while holding this item, every time you gain **[Boost]**, you gain 1 extra. But beware! If someone else successfully YOINKS it from you, they can spend an action to eat it and **[Heal] 1 HP**, sending you into **[Despair]**.'),
('olGum', 'OL\' GUM ', 'DESTITUTE', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 1**\r\nYou found it on the street! Great for pelting people with, right? You can throw this at an opponent to give them **1 [Drag]**. If the opponent is **[Flying]**, they need to roll 1d8. On a 1 or 2, they fall **[Floorbound]** as you get \'em good! Get gummed on!'),
('orgUniform', 'ORG UNIFORM', 'UNUSUAL AND RARE', '[Passive Item][Equipment][Rare]', '**VP 1**\r\nSuits. Ties. Jumpsuits. Big dick capes. The ORG Uniform is worn by trolls in the Junior Branches of various imperial organizations. While wearing it, you ignore moves that nerf **[Manipulate]** rolls, and will never be attacked by individual DRONES unless you provoke them, though you may get caught in the crossfire of DRONE STRIKE Hazards. Higher castes get a **+2 [Buff]** to **[Manipulate]** you as you must do what you\'re told. Wearing this while not in an organization gives you the **[Cullbait]** tag if someone successfully **[Analyses]** you. You cannot receive this item except through moves which mention it.\r\n'),
('petAnimal', 'PET ANIMAL', 'EARTH', '[Active Item][Equipment]\r\n', '**VP 2**\r\nIt’s a kitty! Or a puppy, perhaps! Whatever it is, it’s an animal, and it’s your BEST FRIEND. This item gives you the functions of the CUSTODIAN COMPANION move, but only gives you 2 options. Your pet can’t be killed by trolls; it’s too fast and clever for that.'),
('pokingStick', 'POKING STICK', 'DESTITUTE', '[Active Item]\r\n', '**VP 1**\r\nNOTHING beats a poking stick. Poke dead things, poke weird objects, poke scary bombs… man, it doesn\'t get better than this. When you poke a living thing with a stick, you find out if it\'s alive or dead. If it\'s dead, it\'s probably because you killed it. You can make a **[Tiered Up]** PROBLEM SLEUTHING roll about them, to figure out more. If they\'re alive, you know how long they have before they wake up, and can safely bind them and stop them from escaping. You can also interact with nearby objects without getting into the open with this stick, like pressing a door button while **[Hidden]** behind a dumpster.'),
('ridiculouslyLuxuriousFlexItem', 'RIDICULOUSLY LUXURIOUS FLEX ITEM', 'ULTRARICH', '[Passive Item][Equipment]\r\n', '**VP 6**\r\nWhy do you even… need this? What are these, glasses made of obsidian? You\'re not even shortsighted! Rings made of a planet\'s rings? How does that even WORK! You pay a lot of money for shit that frankly doesn\'t matter. You can change the stat needed to roll one move to another.\r\n'),
('ritualMaterials', 'RITUAL MATERIALS', 'UNUSUAL AND RARE', '[Active Item][Consumable][Eerie][Rare]\r\n', '**VP 8**\r\nOh... what.. what are you doing with this? You.. oh, that\'s what you\'re doing? That\'s.. are you sure? These dark materials are said to have originated from the Lich King of the Undead himself; or at least the knowledge to use them. The specifics vary by the intent; but the end result is clear. Using these materials turns you into an **[Eerie]** troll one way or another. Choose one of the following. You must be able to take the Template ordinarily to use them; otherwise they do nothing. \r\n\r\n> **THE VIRUS**: An ancient pathogen that puts you to a fretful sleep; and should nobody awaken you in time, jolts you back to existence as an undead SHADOWDROPPER. While you sleep your body will move on its own until it defeats another in a Strife; awakening as it expels the body\'s original spirit.  You may choose to become a GHOST instead; should you desire.\r\n\r\n> **MOONSILVER**: Combining the pink iron and the green copper of the twin moons creates something truly strange. Defying all metallurgy; it creates silver! And the cut of it bears the curse of Moonbarkism within! You are perpetually and unstoppably **[Out of Control]** until you first are reduced to **0 HP**, upon which you become a MOONBARK unless you had been made **[Peaceful]**; which instead cures the ailment. \r\n\r\n> **ANCIENT LIPSTICK**: This is either a divine artifact or extremely gaudy depending on who you are. Some say that ancient Cloistered Jades would don this lipstick in times of emergency to protect their classmates at the ultimate price, and others say that monsters of great power would wear it to prey on the weak. Either way; applying this lipstick to a dead Jade revives them as a RAINBOWDRINKER immediately. A Jade who dies while wearing this lipstick is likewise immediately revived.\r\n\r\n> **FINAL CONTRACT**: No pen needed. This one is remarkably simple, even if the text seems to go on for eternity. You sacrifice your pain to those Beyond, and they will make it stop. Sign here; all you have to do is want it for even a moment! You become a GRIMDARK; and unless a Teal can nullify the contract by informing the Horrorterrors that the Empire already owns your soul with a **GREAT [Manipulate]** roll and thus you cannot sell it before you first utilize **[Numbness]** in an Encounter; it will be permanent!\r\n\r\n> **PSI-FRUIT**: A series of fruits, berries and mystical juices meant to supercharge psionics. Enough of them in the right combinations can allow your spirit and psionic energy to simply... slip out of your body. Unless a **[Psionic]** or **[Magic]** troll can shove you back into your body by making you **[Tired]** and reducing you to half HP before you make someone **[Scared]**, you will permanently become a GHOST! You can instead become a SHADOWDROPPER; should you desire.\r\n'),
('scalemates', 'SCALEMATES', 'WELL OFF', '[Active Item]\r\n', '**VP 3**\r\nYour best friends in the world, now available in plushy form! Scalemates are dragon dolls that you can tell all your secrets to, and they’ll never make fun of you for it! They have delightful names such as Pucefoot, Berrybreath, or Pumpkinsniffle, and are totally capable of committing terrible crimes that you must hang them for. You can toss a Scalemate onto the field to take incoming attacks; something about those corrupt, lecherous scumbags just makes your opponents want to attack them before they attack you. Scalemates have immunity to **[Non-Lethal]** damage; after they lose all their HP, they’re slain. Scalemates can’t take any actions as they are, in fact, dragon teddies. Your opponents MUST destroy the Scalemate before they attack you— but watch out, because losing a Scalemate is actually pretty upsetting, and you become **[Sad]** if you let one of them get destroyed on your watch. This is also a **[One-Off]** effect for you and your allies - after the first time, all the novelty slash outrage wears off and your opponent just kind of... stares at you funny, as you continue scattering plushies about the battlefield.\r\n'),
('sensibleHat', 'SENSIBLE HAT', 'RICH', '[Active Item][Equipment][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 3**\r\nA sensible, mature looking fedora, particularly popular among detectives and indigos. When you get a BAD or MIN result on any roll while wearing your Sensible Hat, you can choose to toss your hat to the floor in disgust and gain **10 [Boost]**. It’s VERY cathartic to get this shit off your head.'),
('shellphone', 'SHELLPHONE', 'ULTRARICH', '[Active Item]\r\n', '**VP 1**\r\nThe GREATEST FLEX OF ALL. This extremely luxurious and powerful palmhusk resembles a sea shell… but it\'s actually one of the most powerful computers on the planet. User friendly, intelligent and sleek… it also reads your body temperature and refuses to function if you aren\'t a seadweller. While using this item, your **[Tech]** rolls can\'t be **[Inept], [Tiered Down]** or **[Nerfed]**, and you can turn any **[Analyze]** roll into a **[Tech]** roll by dialling up questions onto the exclusive seadweller side of the internet. Nobody can read private conversations you have on this phone, fuck you CIS!'),
('specialStardust', 'SPECIAL STARDUST', 'UNUSUAL AND RARE', '[Active Item][Consumable][Rare]\r\n', '**VP 1**\r\nWow! This is how you KNOW you’ve got some magical shit about to go down! You can sprinkle this stardust in your face, and after a few moments of coughing and spluttering, it’ll make you exceptionally good at magic and shit; any **+IMG** rolls you make are **[Talented]** (if you were not already **[Talented]** in **+IMG**) for the next **4 turns**. You can also, like, spray it in someone’s face using a GOOD SHENANIGANS to **[Blind]** them for **3 turns**, if you’re a fucking asshole. A bag of Special Stardust contains 4 doses; when all the doses are used up, it’s gone.'),
('spiralSucker', 'SPIRAL SUCKER', 'UNUSUAL AND RARE', '[Active Item][Eerie][Rare]\r\n', '**VP 7**\r\nRitual materials? What are you talking about, silly?? This is just a goofy lollipop! A goofy silly funny lollipop for goofy silly funny people. Don’t you want to be a goofy silly funny person? I bet you do! You want to so much, in fact, that while it’s on your person you need a **GREAT +PSP** roll at the end of every encounter not to pull it out and take a lick! Or at the end of every turn, if you take it out of your Sylladex. You should do that! Or maybe give it to someone else with a YOINK effect instead of taking anything, so they can be goofy funny silly! Whatever you do, you’d never get rid of your precious, super-special lollipop - you’d need a **MAX +PSP** roll while resisting the urge to do that, but why in the world would you want to? Just take a lick already, and become a TRICKSTER! It’ll be fun!!\r\n'),
('squiddles', 'SQUIDDLES!!!', 'WELL OFF', '[Passive Item][Squiddles!]\r\n', '**VP 2**\r\nSQUIDDLES!!! Do you have any memory of even purchasing these silly squid plushies? While you’re holding these adorable, nonthreatening delights, rolls to **[Charm]** someone have a **+2 [Buff]**.'),
('sunbeamInAJar', 'SUNBEAM IN A JAR', 'UNUSUAL AND RARE', '[Active Item][Consumable][Magic][Rare]\r\n', '**VP 4**\r\nYou know when sunlight breaks through the canopy and makes those godrays, that’re really pretty and cinematic? Yeah, well, you caught one. Or it was previously caught, and you just found the jar. Either way, this item somehow has literal solar energy inside of it, which as you all know is deadly to trolls. As a single action, you may open the jar, dealing **2 [Blazing] [Psychic]** damage to everyone, and instantly **[Blinding]** everyone, including you, for the duration of the encounter, and can choose to become PERMABLIND after the encounter. Jades take **1 less damage**, but are still **[Blind]**.'),
('treachorousRosaceae', 'TREACHOROUS ROSACEAE ', 'DECENT', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP: 2**\r\nThis vile fruit is the bane of medical professionals everywhere. Pulling it out gives any troll with the DOCTERROR **[Template]** in the area the **[Disgusted]** condition for **3 rounds**. You can also eat it to remove **2 [Drag]**. You sick fuck.'),
('trollLego', 'TROLL LEGO', 'DECENT', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 3**\r\nIt\'s a box of Troll Lego. The floor is lava now, bitch! You can spend an action to throw these across the playing field. Anyone who uses a **[Physical]** move afterwards gains **1 [Drag]**, including yourself. **[Flying]** trolls are immune to this. Becoming **[Floorbound]** gives you **2 [Somatic] damage** because EEEAAAAUUUGHHHHHH.'),
('ultimateQualityStuff', 'ULTIMATE QUALITY STUFF', 'ULTRARICH', '[Active Item]\r\n', '**VP 5**\r\nOh yes. OH YES. You\'re living in the lap of luxury, and you know what that means? You can buy ANYTHING. Of course, stuff comes with inflated price tags up at the top, but you can afford it! When you select this item, choose any other item on the PRECAPTCHALOGUE list except unusual/rare items. You receive it as this item; for example, buying a set of ARMS would make them ULTIMATE QUALITY ARMS, costing **5 VP**. It costs caegars to have this much stuff, baby! If an item costs more than **5 VP**, this item raises to match that price.'),
('ultramedicalizer', 'MEDICALIZER', 'RICH', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 2**\r\nWEE-WOO WEE-WOO! Did someone get a boo-boo? BOO-BOO NO MORE! This ADVANCED and SPECIAL Medicalizer… does basically the same as any other. BUT LOOK AT THE STYLE! LOOK AT THE GRACE! IT LOOKS AMAZING! It has flashing lights, and it’s got suuuch a sleek design. Now you too can flex on the haters by using a sexy, sexy medicalizer that looks way better than anyone else’s. When you activate this item, you **[Heal] 1 HP**. '),
('utterlyEverydayAlternianSurvivalKit', 'UTTERLY EVERYDAY ALTERNIAN SURVIVAL KIT', 'AVERAGE', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 8**\r\nWhen you\'re average on Alternia, that means you have to deal with... everything. Angry psionic golds that wear red or yellow? Furious walking tanks with face paint? Haughty fish that can lift up malls? An angry teenage teacher talking about your grades? Yeah. You have to deal with it all at some point. The UTTERLY EVERYDAY ALTERNIAN SURVIVAL KIT lets you do just that. This overly expensive emergency pack lets you deploy it and summon any item from the POOR or RICH wealth categories. Luckily you had this on hand, just in case... It only works once though, whatever you pull out. And then you gain **2 [Drag]** as you use up your supplies. \r\n'),
('wardrobifier', 'WARDROBIFIER', 'WELL OFF', '[Active Item]\r\n', '**VP 3**\r\nThis sweet tech lets you swap out outfits with a moment’s notice! Nowadays, this bad boy is conveniently stored in some lipstick, for nostalgically anachronistic reasons. Activating this item allows you to swap between **[Fashion]** Items on the fly, totally redoing your look.'),
('yourVeryOwnServicesquire', 'YOUR VERY OWN SERVICESQUIRE', 'ULTRARICH', '[Passive Item(..?)]\r\n', '**VP 3**\r\nVery good, sir. You have a SERVICESQUIRE, a henchman and right hand troll, and mostly a butler. This acts as a SERVICESQUIRE NPC from Chapter 19b. They\'ll do anything you ask, any time, even breaking into hives or driving **[Vehicles]** for you, if you so choose. If they die, that sucks. '),
('zeroNutritionChisps', 'ZERO NUTRITION CHISPS', 'POOR', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**Poor: VP 2**\r\nCrunch… crunch… crunch. The latest craze in low blood communities, these hybrid crisps and chips have zero, that\'s right, ZERO nutritional value! When you eat these chisps, you increase the timer on negative **[Emotions]** for all opponents by 1. CRNCH… CRNCH… '),
('zucciBubbleHelmet', 'ZUCCI BUBBLE HELMET', 'RICH', '[Active Item][Consumable]\r\n', '**VP 1**\r\nGotta rub elbows with the seadwellers! How are you gonna attend that fancy ball underwater? With this DESIGNER Bubble Helmet, that’s how! You wouldn’t be caught dead underwater without it! Because you’d be exposed to the DROWNING **[Affliction]** if you were.');
INSERT INTO `tag` (`key`, `title`, `text`) VALUES
('activeItem', 'ACTIVE ITEM', 'A type of item which you have to spend an action to use, rather than its effects always being activated.\r\n'),
('affliction', 'AFFLICTION', 'As one of the many dangers found on Alternia, an Affliction affects your physical wellbeing, whether that means foaming at the mouth or falling helplessly in love. Afflictions usually come from an outside source, such as a bite or a move.\r\n'),
('analyse', 'ANALYSE', 'A type of move that gives you insight and information into a specific target.\r\n'),
('base', 'BASE', 'The first stage of an Emotion. If that Emotion is applied again by a different move or effect, it becomes **[Heightened]**. \r\n'),
('boost', 'BOOST', 'A numerical bonus you add to your rolls alongside your stat modifier. Once you gain Boost, you can hold onto it indefinitely, and it stacks. Once you use it to raise any one of your rolls, it’s gone. You need to use ALL your Boost at once; you can’t hold onto some of it. Boost gained from one move can be used anywhere else, and stacks with Boost gained from any other move. You can either add Boost to a roll before or after the dice are rolled. You can’t use Boost to undo a **MIN** Roll. **[Drag]** cancels out **[Boost]**, 1 point at a time, before taking effect only after you have 0 Boost left.\r\n'),
('buildup', 'BUILDUP', 'It takes a little bit to get to build up momentum to the point where you can begin using this move. Buildup always has a value; you must succeed (i.e. getting a **GREAT** roll or up) on that many rolls during combat specifically before you can use this move. Moves used before combat do not count towards your Buildup efforts, and neither do moves that offer you an automatic **GREAT** result or something similar.'),
('buff', 'BUFF', 'A bonus boosting your troll for an entire encounter. You get a +X to certain rolls with it, which can be neutralized by a **[Nerf]** of the same type.\r\n'),
('brainmelt', 'BRAINMELT', 'Brainmelt is a permanent counter that can affect gold psionics. You cannot get rid of Brainmelt under ordinary circumstances; upon accumulating 12 points of Brainmelt, you lose your **[Psionic]** moves permanently, and gain the DYING BATTERY move, giving you access to the Voidrot template. Levels you spent investing into **[Psionic]** moves can be reinvested elsewhere. \r\n'),
('chicanery', 'CHICANERY', 'A type of move that gives the opponent a special debuff from a list of choices.\r\n'),
('control', 'CONTROL', 'A type of move that\'s like **[Manipulate]**, but 100% worse. Control moves use some kind of psionic effect that alters your state of mind against your will. Terrible!\r\n'),
('consumable', 'CONSUMABLE', 'A type of item that can only be used once, after which you no longer have the item for the rest of the encounter. Once the encounter ends you get the item back.'),
('craft', 'CRAFT', 'A type of move where you build or create an item, typically mid-encounter.\r\n'),
('cullbait', 'CULLBAIT', 'Kill on sight! If you gain a move with this tag, you cannot openly express what you are, whether that’s a lime, a mutant, or some other monstrosity. You become a Cullbait troll. Drones are automatically hostile to you, and will single you out. Hemoist or Pro-Imperial trolls may try to cull you if you reveal yourself, and if they win the fight have full ability to inflict a JUST or HEROIC death on you, regardless of your intent! Revealing yourself is taken as automatic consent for potential character death. Hide your truth as best as you can, be careful who you trust and remember that running is always an option. (Note: Scenarios in which this comes into play are best talked about OOC with your partner prior to happening!)\r\n'),
('downtime', 'DOWNTIME', 'Downtime is the kind of activities your trolls go on between adventures. Moves that are labeled as Downtime can only be rolled outside of an encounter, unless agreed upon out of character. See ACT 3, Chapter 16: Downtime for details.\r\n'),
('drag', 'DRAG', 'A penalty to your rolls you hold onto for your opponent to spend later. When your opponent calls for you to expend your Drag, you add all your Drag to a penalty on your roll after it’s been rolled. Drag stacks; you keep building Drag indefinitely, but once you use it, it’s gone. You use ALL your Drag at once, when your opponent chooses for you to do so. Drag gained from one move can be used anywhere else, and stacks with Drag gained from any other move. Drag cancels out **[Boost]**, 1 point at a time, before taking effect only after you have **0 [Boost]** left.\r\n'),
('eerie', 'EERIE', 'WhoooOOOOoooh! A move with this tag means you\'re kinda supernatural. You become an Eerie Troll. People are **[Scared]** when you reveal yourself, but some trolls are dedicated to culling you; you gain the **[Cullbait]** tag too.\r\n'),
('encounter', 'ENCOUNTER', 'A situation your troll finds themselves in, be it social or combat. Lasts until parties split ways.\r\n'),
('equipment', 'EQUIPMENT', 'A type of item that can be worn, and does not take up a sylladex slot. You have 2 Equipment allocations at a time; once both are in use, any other Equipment must go in a sylladex slot or STORAGEPIT.\r\n'),
('flourish', 'FLOURISH', 'A type of move that gives you a special buff from a list of choices.\r\n'),
('free', 'FREE', 'A type of action you can take immediately upon certain triggers, and which doesn’t count as using any of your actions.\r\n'),
('godawful', 'GODAWFUL', 'A more extreme version of **[Inept]**; rather than 3d8, you roll 4d8, and choose the lowest two. If a trigger would render you **[Talented]** on a Godawful roll, you become **[Inept]**. If a trigger would render you **[Inept]** on a Godawful roll, you instead gain **3 [Drag]**.\r\n'),
('hazard', 'HAZARD', 'A natural disaster or challenge that trolls might have to overcome or suffer from, such as sunlight or acid rain; see the Hazard section of the ALTERNIA chapter for more details.\r\n'),
('heal', 'HEAL', 'A type of move that allows you to regain **HP**. You can only use one Heal move per turn.\r\n'),
('heightened', 'HEIGHTENED', 'The second, more volatile stage of an emotion.\r\n'),
('hold', 'HOLD', 'A token that you can spend for a given result. Moves that give **[Hold]** will explain in their description what kind of effect the **[Hold]** can be spent for and will explain how to use that **[Hold]** when it is spent.\r\n'),
('indestructable', 'INDESTRUCTABLE', 'A type of item that cannot be damaged or destroyed.\r\n'),
('inept', 'INEPT', 'A condition that leaves you piss poor at certain rolls. When you roll something you are Inept in, you roll 3d8 rather than 2d8, and use the two lowest numbers you receive. This can be temporary (as a result of a move) or permanent (as a result of a caste choice). If a trigger would render you Inept at a certain roll you were already Inept at, it becomes **[Godawful]**. If a trigger would render you **[Talented]** in an Inept roll, your Ineptitude is cancelled out.\r\n'),
('lastStand', 'LAST STAND', 'A move that would allow you to carry on fighting despite reaching a condition that would normally render you **[Unconscious]**, usually by reaching 0 HP or below. Only one Last Stand move may ever be used in an encounter unless otherwise stated.\r\n'),
('lengthy', 'LENGTHY', 'This move takes a little while to use. It takes **2 actions** to accomplish this, rather than one.\r\n'),
('legendary', 'LEGENDARY', 'A more extreme version of [Talented]; rather than 3d8, you roll 4d8, and choose the highest two. If a trigger would render you **[Inept]** in a Legendary roll, you become **[Talented]**. If a trigger would render you **[Talented]** in a Legendary roll, you instead gain **3 [Boost]**.\r\n'),
('locked', 'LOCKED', 'You cannot take this move unless you have taken the corresponding **[Unlock]** move. \r\n'),
('magic', 'MAGIC', 'It\'s magic, man, I don\'t need to explain shit. Whether it\'s from practiced spellcasting or metauniversal glitch exploits, moves with this tag are flashy, unexplainable, and nobody* cares if you do it. Think Scott Pilgrim style and don\'t ask questions.\r\n*Nobody except some Dib kinnie teals, probably.\r\n'),
('manipulate', 'MANIPULATE', 'A move that allows you to change the attitudes of another troll. You can only use one Manipulate move per turn.\r\n'),
('mechanical', 'MECHANICAL', 'A type of item or entity that makes use of Alternia’s superior technology. Mechanical items and entities are vulnerable to hacking, and take **1 [Somatic]** damage whenever they take **[Electric]** damage.\r\n'),
('mental', 'MENTAL', 'A type of move that requires you to be able to think. Mental moves are separate and mutually exclusive from **[Psionic]** moves, though they can have similar effects.\r\n'),
('move', 'MOVE', 'What you do! These are the actions you take in combat. When your turn comes, you can choose any move you know and use it. You get two moves per **[Turn]**; choose wisely!\r\n'),
('negative', 'NEGATIVE', 'A type of Emotion that hurts you. Sucks to be you! Whenever you\'re inflicted by Negative Emotions, they give some kind of debuff.\r\n'),
('nerf', 'NERF', 'A setback afflicting your troll for an entire encounter. You get a -X to certain rolls with it, which can be neutralized by a **[Buff]** of the same type. \r\n'),
('neutral', 'NEUTRAL', 'These Emotions are what you make of them. Are you comfortably numb? Going into a blind rage and murdering the last members of your species? Are you a functional gay or a disaster gay?\r\n'),
('nonLethal', 'NON-LETHAL', 'A type of damage that will never kill the opponent; merely make them lose the ability to fight. You don’t track lethal and non-lethal damage seperately; the only one that matters is the finishing blow that knocks the opponent below **0 HP**.\r\n'),
('oneOff', 'ONE-OFF', 'A move with this tag can only be done once per encounter.\r\n'),
('open', 'OPEN', 'Open moves are a type of move that can be \'stolen\'; for example, certain moves will say that you can take **[Open]** moves you would not otherwise have access to. Please note that other people cannot \'steal\' a \'stolen\' move from you.\r\n'),
('passive', 'PASSIVE', 'A type of move that doesn’t require an action to use; it is an upgrade to an existing move or rule that buffs your troll.\r\n'),
('passiveItem', 'PASSIVE ITEM', 'A type of item whose effects are constantly activated.\r\n'),
('physical', 'PHYSICAL', 'This type of thing requires physical movement or effort! If it is a move, it requires you to be able to move. \r\n'),
('positive', 'POSITIVE', 'A type of Emotion that helps you! Whether it\'s pleasant or not to be feeling them, Positive Emotions give you some kind of helpful buff.\r\n'),
('psionic', 'PSIONIC', 'A type of move that requires magical(?) powers. These are often hidden behind a **[Lock]** trait!\r\n'),
('psychic', 'PSYCHIC', 'A type of damage that affects the mind. Typically from [Psionic] moves.\r\n'),
('rapid', 'RAPID', 'A type of **[Affliction]** that advances quickly; you must roll at the end of your turn, every turn, to see if it progresses.\r\n'),
('rare', 'RARE', 'A type of item you cannot usually find in shops; you can only discover it from adventures or very specific stores.\r\n'),
('reaction', 'REACTION', 'A type of move you use outside of your turn, such as during an opponent’s; when you use a Reaction, you give up one of your moves from your turn.\r\n'),
('recharge', 'RECHARGE', 'You can’t manage to repeat this move too often before it wears you down. Recharge always has a value; after using a move with Recharge, you must wait that many turns before rerolling this move. Recharge counters decrease at the end of your turn, starting on the turn after you use a move - a move with Recharge: 1 can be used every other turn normally, a move with Recharge: 2 every third turn, et cetera.\r\n'),
('resistance', 'RESISTANCE', 'Resistance allows you to take X amount less damage from certain damage types. This cannot reduce the damage you take to 0; the minimum is always 1. This effect stacks from multiple sources.\r\n'),
('slowburn', 'SLOWBURN', 'A type of **[Affliction]** that advances slowly; you must roll at the end of every encounter to see if it progresses.\r\n'),
('somatic', 'SOMATIC', 'A type of damage that affects your physical body with potentially lethal consequences.\r\n'),
('soulstuck', 'SOULSTUCK', 'A type of item which cannot be removed from your person, whether it’s physically attached to you or simply yours by law of the universe.\r\n'),
('strife', 'STRIFE', 'A type of move which is primarily meant to do damage. You can only use one Strife move per turn.\r\n'),
('talented', 'TALENTED ', 'A trait that makes you pretty damn good at certain rolls. When you roll something you are Talented at, you roll 3d8 rather than 2d8, and use the two highest numbers you receive. This can be temporary (as a result of a move) or permanent (as a result of a caste choice.) If a trigger would render you Talented at a certain roll you were already Talented at, you receive a **+2 [Buff]** to that roll, unless a move says otherwise. If a trigger would render you **[Inept]** in a Talented roll, your Talent is cancelled out.\r\n'),
('tech', 'TECH', 'A type of move which uses a palmhusk, husktop or other form of Alternian biotechnology.\r\n'),
('tierDown', 'TIER DOWN', 'A trait where certain moves’ roll results will be one tier lower than normal; for example, an **OK** becomes a **BAD** or a **GREAT** becomes a **GOOD**. This cannot make **BAD** rolls **MIN**.\r\n'),
('tierUp', 'TIER UP', 'A trait where certain moves roll results will be one tier higher than normal; for example, a **BAD** roll becomes an **OK**, while a **GOOD** roll becomes a **GREAT**. This cannot make **GREAT** rolls **MAX**.\r\n'),
('turn', 'TURN', 'Your time to shine in combat! During a Turn, you get two moves. Use them wisely! When everyone has used their Turn, a new **[Round]** begins.\r\n'),
('unblockable', 'UNBLOCKABLE', 'A type of move which simply cannot be countered. You can\'t punch someone to stop the universe from deciding you can\'t break the rules, silly! \r\n'),
('unlock', 'UNLOCK', 'A type of move that allows you to use other moves which require this one as a prerequisite. Unlock moves open up an entire **[Tree]** of moves- they’re your gateway to exclusive moves!\r\n'),
('verbal', 'VERBAL', 'A type of damage you do with your words and insults. Verbal damage is always **[Non-Lethal]**, and cannot kill you; knocking someone below 0 HP with Verbal attacks simply drops them to the floor as their emotions take over and they can’t fight, just blubber about your insults.\r\n'),
('wham', 'WHAM', 'WHAM! A type of boost to your damage. WHAM stacks in the same way as **[Boost]**, except using it increases your damage, not your roll. You use your WHAM whenever you choose to, all at once, but be careful; it dissipates any time you take damage. Some moves give your opponent WHAM, but in this case, that WHAM does not take effect (and so can\'t be made to dissipate) until the end of your turn. You can only have a MAX of **3 WHAM** at any given time.\r\n');
INSERT INTO `vehicle` (`key`, `title`, `cost`, `text`) VALUES
('tiny', 'TINY', 1, '**1 HP**\r\nThis is a unicycle. Maybe a skateboard? The point is, calling this a vehicle is generous. The only passenger that can be on this vehicle is you. You get **-2 HORSEPOWER**, but you gain a new SHENANIGANS effect while riding it:\r\n \r\nCOMICALLY FALL OFF OF VEHICLE AND GO SPLAT: You do that. All of your enemies begin **[Laughing]**. This counts as exiting your vehicle.'),
('small', 'SMALL', 2, '**4 HP**\r\nA motorscuttle, hoverbike, etc. Your smaller frame means that you can zip around a little faster; you get **+1 HORSEPOWER**. You can carry one other passenger.\r\n'),
('medium', 'MEDIUM', 3, '**8 HP**\r\nYes sir, that is your standard, no-frills scuttlebuggy. No change to your HORSEPOWER. You can carry up to four other passengers.\r\n'),
('large', 'LARGE', 5, '**12 HP**\r\nA van, a boat, etc. The size of this vehicle makes it ever so slightly slower; you get **-1 HORSEPOWER**. You can carry up to seven other passengers.\r\n'),
('xxl', 'XXL', 8, '**20 HP**\r\nAn airship, a ship, a walking castle, etc. One of these big boys generally isn\'t used for chases so much as it is as mobile fortresses. You have **-2 HORSEPOWER**, but can add HIVECRAFTING modifications to it. You can carry as many passengers as you like.\r\n'),
('armored', 'ARMORED', 3, 'Your vehicle has **1 [Somatic] [Resistance]**, because of all those armored plates.\r\n'),
('trunk', 'TRUNK', 1, 'It has 5 independent VP slots. You cannot access the items in these slots unless you\'re nearby.\r\n'),
('clownCar', 'CLOWN CAR', 1, 'You can fit up to 10 additional passengers in here. The vehicle must be **MEDIUM** or **SMALL** sized, and you must be a Purple Blood.\r\n'),
('weaponized', 'WEAPONIZED', 5, 'ACTIVATE THE MINIGUN ON THE ROOF OF THE VEHICLE! You can make RAM rolls against **[Flying]** targets, or targets within **1 VROOM** of you.\r\n'),
('slowPlow', 'SNOW PLOW', 2, 'For people! You get the following GOOD VEHICULATE result:\r\n\r\nPLOW: On a **[Recharge: 5]**, you can spend a **[Lengthy]** action to knock up to 4 targets not presently in vehicles **[Floorbound]**. '),
('trailer', 'TRAILER', 2, 'Instead of keeping your STORAGE PIT in your hive, you bring it with you! You gain access to your STORAGE PIT, if you have one, in any encounter where you have access to your vehicle. If the vehicle is destroyed, so is the STORAGE PIT and all non **[Indestructible]** items inside. \r\n'),
('explodable', 'EXPLODABLE', 2, 'COME OUT YE BLACK AND TANS COME OUT AND FIGHT ME LIKE A MAN SHOW YOUR WIFE HOW YOU WON MEDALS DOWN IN FLAAAANDERS. This vehicle is also a bomb. As an action, or when the vehicle hits **0 HP**, the vehicle explodes, dealing **10 [Unblockable] [Somatic]** damage to everything in the area, yourself included.\r\n'),
('soundSystem', 'SOUND SYSTEM', 2, 'BWOOMM BWOOMM BWOOMM! Your neighbors hate you! The entire street hates you! And everyone knows how small your bulge is! FRAYMOTIFS for you and your allies in the presence of the vehicle **[Tier Up]**.\r\n'),
('afterburner', 'AFTERBURNER', 5, 'You gain the following GOOD VEHICULATE effect.\r\n\r\nFWOOSH: On a **[Buildup 4]**, you can floor it to make your tailpipe spit flame. It sets up to 3 random players outside of vehicles **[Ablaze]**.'),
('water', 'WATER', 5, 'Only other Water vehicles can follow you into water. Water vehicles cannot be smaller than **MEDIUM** size. When it falls below **4 HP**, it begins sinking. After 3 turns of sinking, it capsizes and sinks completely. The clouder has the choice of applying the DROWNING **[Affliction]** to everyone on board. \r\n'),
('air', 'AIR', 5, 'It flies! In fact, it is always **[Flying]**, and can gain a second VROOM pool to dictate its altitude. This cannot be smaller than **SMALL** size. When it falls below **3 HP** rounded down, it begins falling. You automatically take the BAIL VEHICULATE roll, and it crashes at the start of your next turn.\r\n'),
('hovering', 'HOVERING', 3, 'The latest in space age hover technology. You get **+1 HORSEPOWER**.\r\n'),
('selfDriving', 'SELF DRIVING', 3, 'This vehicle doesn’t need someone at the wheel! It makes 1 VEHICULATE roll with a +3 modifier each turn while you’re in the vehicle, and you can treat it as if you were a passenger. You can own multiple Self Driving vehicles, but be careful! Scuttlebuggies are incredibly territorial, and if they\'re self aware enough to drive themselves, they\'re self aware enough to try and destroy any other self driving vehicles belonging to their owner to claim territory instead of driving if you bring them out together. Self Driving scuttlebuggies of the same owner will always attempt to RAM one another to death if deployed without drivers.\r\n');
